27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','suraj-jagan'),(127,0,22,22,'Sippy Gill','Sippy Gill, an upcoming raising star that hails from the soils of Punjab not only is he a sensational singer but he is also an astounding lyricist. Sippy Gill is truly Indian by heart and tries to target the young youth of today with his style of singing. Few words from Sippy himself are \'Music is my passion and I had always wanted to convert this passion into a professional career He has been taught his musical skills from Guru Surinder Dhir Ji of Moga, Punjab since 1999. Along with music, Sippy has many other pass times he enjoys such as his favourite sport soccer or just being at home and spending time with his family.','<span class=\"skype_pnh_print_container_1342002799\">+919872400677</span><span class=\"skype_pnh_container\" dir=\"ltr\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"skype_pnh_mark\"> begin_of_the_skype_highlighting</span><s','http://www.facebook.com/sippygillfanpage/info','http://www.sippygillonline.com','','','0','12042',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sippy-gill'),(128,0,2,2,'Demonstealer','Demonstealer is the vocalist/guitarist for the bands Demonic Resurrection and Workshop. He also runs India\'s only label for extreme metal music called Demonstealer Records. www.twitter.com/thedemonstealer','','http://www.facebook.com/DemonstealerOfficial/info?ref=ts','','http://soundcloud.com/demonstealer','','0','11935',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','demonstealer'),(129,2,1,1,'Phobia','Phobia is :\r\n\r\nVocals : Vikas Sorenn,\r\nVocals/Guitars : Jimmy Jacob, \r\nGuitars : Aaquib Wani, \r\nBass : Robin John\r\nDrums : Udit Mahar\r\n\r\n\r\nBrutal riffs weft on a melodic soundscape. Accentuated by intense breakdowns and superlayered with an equally intense vocal lines which tantamount to an eargasmic progressive experi-metal cascade. Phobia thereby declares itself. Touted to be \"one of the upcoming bands to watch out for\" by the Rock Street Journal Magazine, this band is on a brazen rampage and has been making waves in the Indian metal Circuit in their short one year reinvented span of life. So here are 5 delhiites who think heavy and progressive; And believe is what it should take to incite the epiphysis for a virtuous transcendence and hence inspire to conquer one\'s Phobia.','+91-981-84-84-711','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Phobia/110275162376403','http://www.PhobiaTheBand.com/','http://soundcloud.com/phobiaind/sets/phobia/','','110275162376403','856',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 13:31:25',208,'[\"\"]','[\"+91-981-84-84-711\"]','phobia'),(130,0,2,2,'Lost Stories','Life for  Prayag Mehta and  Rishab Joshi [Lost Stories] has been on the constant upswing ever since their first phenomenal record, False Promises was picked up by one of the world\'s leading independent Record Label, Black Hole Recordings, owned by none other than DJ Tiesto. They are the first Indians to have this coveted title on their mantles and these studio-at-home geniuses from Mumbai have been belting out remixes and releases in the last six months that have monstrous written all over them.\r\n\r\nIt was mid-2008 when the Lost Stories as they call themselves were formed, and after a few individual releases on Indias popular Record Label Brutal by Birth, it was finally time for the big stage. False Promises hit the trance scene and seismic waves were felt everywhere. India had arrived after Armin van Buuren decided to play False Promises within 3 days of its release on A State of Trance as Tune of The Week.\r\n\r\nAnd if thats enough evidence that these two are of top trance-pedigree, and Armins not the only top-bracket-man whos swooning over these two. Tiesto, Markus Schulz, Ferry Corsten, Above and Beyond, Andy Moor, The Thrillseekers, Mr Sam, M.I.K.E and many more have supported these two and their tunes have been played on radio shows and clubs all around by them.\r\n\r\nAfter spending a week in top five and a day on the number one spot on the Black Hole charts along with appearances on the Beatport and Audiojelly Top 20sLost Stories are rapidly turning into every progressive trancers remix-wish list.\r\n\r\nTheir soundscape is every bit the fresh, the dark and the eclectic. With immense melodies and groovy basslines reflecting in their brand new releases, their demand is surging and the duo is pulsing with confidence, pushing the limits of their musical abilities into infinity.\r\n\r\nThe future of Indian trance lays in the safe hands. The futures bright. The futures Lost.  ','press@loststories.in','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Lost-Stories/45235867421?sk=info','http://www.loststories.in','http://soundcloud.com/loststories','','0','11763',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 17:52:14',335,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','lost-stories'),(132,0,29,29,'Rupam Islam','','','http://www.facebook.com/rupamislam74/info','','','','0','11727',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rupam-islam'),(133,0,2,52,'JOSHISH','JOSHISH is a Progressive/Experimental Rock Band based in Mumbai, originated from Bhopal, India .It has been more than five years of several concerts across India. The band has been dominating the Central Indian Rock scene from its very onset. Their concert has myriad hues of interactive sessions, zippy stage act and surreal feel to their music and lyrics, a complete Audio-Visual bliss. Currently the band is busy in the studios recording the originals for their upcoming album, due to be released by the end of this year.\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Nikhil Asnani','http://www.facebook.com/joshishindia/info','http://www.joshish.com','http://soundcloud.com/joshishindia','','0','11685',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','joshish'),(134,0,53,53,'DJ Harsh Lalka','DJing and Music Production','Times of India,The Hindu,The Deccan Chronicles','http://www.facebook.com/Djharshlalka/info?ref=ts','','http://soundcloud.com/dj-harsh-lalka','','0','11683',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-harsh-lalka'),(136,0,54,54,'Gevolt','GEVOLT was founded in 2001.\r\nIn 2006 released a debut CD called Sidur (ritual metal for practical use). Later the band changes the concept and start singing in traditional European Jewish language Yiddish, covering some classic Yiddish songs. As a result we get a 2-song containing EP \"Yiddish Metal\" which was self released by the band as promo package in 2007. During 2009-2010 GEVOLT makes some lineup changes and a second full-length album AlefBase was released in February-March of 2011.','','http://www.facebook.com/Gevolt/info','http://www.gevolt.com','http://soundcloud.com/gevolt','http://www.reverbnation.com/gevolt','0','11667',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','gevolt'),(137,0,55,55,'MC KASH   (OFFICIAL)','Labelled as the first emcee to come out of Kashmir, MC Kash, a Srinagar born and bred rapper has been defined as a rebel and a revolutionary, home and abroad. At 21, MCK / Kash stands firm in his beliefs and merciless in his poetry, \"who\'s words cut deeper than the barbed wire that are everywhere\".\r\n\r\nKash shot into the public eye with his song I Protest (Remembrance) in September 2010, and since then has went on to get featured on BBC, PressTV, Washington Post, Dawn, Times of India, Tehelka, Rising Kashmir, VOA (Voice of America), Al Jazeera, and many other media outlets.\r\n\r\nAs \"I Protest\" went on to find its place in every other mobile phone in Kashmir, the Indian Police raided the studio where MCK had recorded the song. This eventually, rendered him without a studio to record in. \r\nWith only a handful of recording studios available in Kashmir, all of whom by now knew of the raid and the artist associated with it, Kash wasn\'t able to record for months.\r\n\r\nBut, the very fact that MC Kash has continued to produce more and more songs since the \'The Raid\' in 2010, is a testament to his undying love for his Nation and the belief in the Cause that he upholds.\r\nWorking with whatever little resources he can find, K has carried on with his journey. Still, Speaking his Mind.\r\n\r\nMC Kash, even produced the first Hip Hop video to come out of Kashmir for his song \"Beneath This Sky\", which was directed by Elayne McCabe and which has, till date, crossed more than 27K views on YouTube. \r\nKash, then went to perform at the One Young Kashmir summit in 2011, where \"he received a standing ovation from the crowd\". Even making headlines on some local and Indian newspapers.\r\n\r\nAnd with still miles to go, the journey for this independent artist from Kashmir has just begun. Knowing, that if he could reach out to even one person out there, his music and his hard work won\'t go waste.','(contact_mck@ymail.com) (shayannabi@yahoo.co.uk)','http://www.facebook.com/MCKashKashmir/info','','','http://www.reverbnation.com/#/mckashkashmir','0','11560',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','mc-kash-official'),(138,0,1,1,'Nds & Blue Fans Club','About the Duos Nds and Blue\r\n\r\nThe dashing duo of DJs-cum-Producers NDS & BLUE (Real names Siddharth Sharma and Gaurav Sharma, respectively) come from the small yet modest towns of Agra and Rewari, respectively. The two were pursuing their higher studies together in Gurgaon when the music bug bit them. \r\n\r\nWhile there, they got in touch with the local clubs situated there and they further explored their love for music to the fullest. This is when the expected story of stardom happened. When the young chaps started their monthly Podcast and their own nights, called Aftermidnight, they received an overwhelming response not only locally or nationally, but internationally as well. This was aired on some of the finest radios of the world, including Radio 1190 Colarado. \r\n\r\nIn 2010, they started doing some Local Acts at Residencies and Clubs and started their own Production house. \r\n\r\nCurrently based in Delhi, their hard work started taking shape in 2011, when they got support from National and International DJs and their records with some renowned International artists and the well-known DJ Aqeel were released. Theyve also performed opening acts for eminent artists like Bobina,Myon and Shane 54,Tritonal,Alex Morph,Cosmic Gate, Matt Darey.\r\n\r\nWhile all this was remarkable, their future plans seem no less exciting. This year, their new EPS with famous International records will be released while they also plan to tour with a lot of them  namely Cosmic Gate, Bobina amongst many others. Their new track, titled Toska which is scheduled to be released by Colorful Recording is supported by Worlds #2 DJ Armin Van Buren. \r\nThe awesome-twosome have also been opening  for one of the best clubs of India, Blue Frog.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCheck \r\n\r\nwww.soundcloud.com/ndsandblueproductions\r\nwww.soundcloud.com/aftermidnightpodcast\r\n','info@ndsandblue.com','http://www.facebook.com/Ndsandblue/info','','http://soundcloud.com/ndsandblueproductions','','0','11493',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','nds-blue-fans-club'),(139,0,0,0,'Mumbai Science','Science does not know its debt to imagination. ~Ralph Waldo Emerson\r\n\r\nIf there is one thing you cant blame Maarten Elen and Jonas Kiesekoms  alias Mumbai Science  its a lack of imagination. At only 24, the duo already has a decade worth of creative experimenting behind them, from making politically incorrect rock music to writing absurd theatrical plays. However, it was only in 2010 that their musical passion culminated into the indie electro vibes of Mumbai Science, creating a sound that melts contemporary electro-synths with a vintage techno feel.\r\n\r\nBegin 2010, the duo signed with the notorious label Lektroluv Records, releasing four original EPs (Woof EP, Ancova EP, Gold EP and Lotus EP). Club hits like Ancova, Gold and Lotus got picked up rapidly by artists around the globe (2 many djs, Crookers, Erol Alkan, Boys Noize, Tiga and beyond), putting Mumbai Science on the worlds EDM radar. Apart from their original work, Mumbai Science is building an impressive list of remixes. To date, the duo finished remixes for Mixhell (Boysnoize Records), Goose (!K7), Crookers (Southern Fried), Alex Gopher (Go 4 Music), Shameboy (East), Highbloo (Lektroluv) and Jaymo & Andy George (Moda Music). \r\n\r\nSo, whats next for Mumbai Science? The duo plans to release not one, not two, but three (!!!) original EPs in the coming months: With this trilogy, I feel like we experimented with genres like New Beat, Future Techno, Acid and Electro... In a way, I think we tried to contemporize everything we liked from our youth... We just made something we think is quite cool. And theres that!\r\n\r\n\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/Mumbaiscience/info?ref=ts','http://www.mumbaiscience.net','http://soundcloud.com/mumbaiscience','','0','11474',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','mumbai-science'),(141,0,1,1,'Ozyris The Band','MEANING OF OZYRIS:\r\n\r\n\"Osiris\" is the Egyptian God of Afterlife.\r\n\r\nNo one knows what \'afterlife\' is. No one knows what more is after death. \r\nWe say it\'s music and we are a part of it. We say it\'s us, Ozyris.\r\n\r\nOzyris - Giving Music, Giving Life\r\n\r\n\r\n-*-TERMS & CONDITIONS FOR ANY PERFORMANCE OFFER-*-\r\n\r\n1.It would be preferable if prior notice of at least 20 days would be given before the Performance Date.\r\n\r\n2.The Sound System should be as per the requirements of the band.\r\n\r\n3.A Memorandum Of Understanding (MoU) would be signed between both the parties, ie, The Band and the Contacting Party before the performance, which will include the total sum to be paid to Ozyris The Band, in written along with signatures of both the parties.\r\n\r\n4.50% of the entire remuneration should be paid at the time of signing the MoU and the remaining 50% should be paid on the date of the performance before the band gets on stage to perform. These terms would be stated in the MoU.\r\n\r\n5.If the Performance is Cancelled due to any reason by the party engaging the band, then the entire amount taken in advance would be forfeited. If the band cancels the performance, then the advance would be returned.','','http://www.facebook.com/OzyrisTheBand/info','','','http://www.reverbnation.com/OzyrisTheBand','0','11349',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ozyris-the-band'),(142,0,56,1,'Dj Harsh','INTERNATIONAL GIGS\r\n*Switzerland -Miss India Switzerland Final @ Club Indochine (Zurich)19th November 2011 \r\n\r\n* Turkey-kimpinsky Hotel (Bordum)16th april 2011\r\n\r\n* Switzerland -Club Hilti (Zurich) 7th april  2011\r\n\r\n* Bahrain - Club Havana -14th Feb 2011\r\n\r\n* Kenya -Nairobi-Club Iguana- jan 2011\r\n\r\n*Malaysia ,singapore -april 2010\r\n\r\n* Mauritius (curepipe club) (28TH DEC 2007)\r\n\r\n* China (shanghai) Club Attica (22nd MAR 2008)\r\n\r\n* Thailand-hua hin (hotel Hyatt Regency)(18TH APR 2008)\r\n\r\n* China-(Shanghai) Club Attica (6th june 2008)\r\n\r\n* China-(Shanghai) MAO Club ( 14th june 2008)\r\n\r\n* Dubai- keva club (8th Aug 2008)\r\n\r\n* Dubai- keva club ( 29th Aug 2008)\r\n\r\n* China (Shanghai) Club M2 ( 18th oct 2008)\r\n\r\n* China (shanghai) (31st dec 2008)\r\n\r\n* Nepal ( kathmandu & pokhra)-16th-20th april\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nNATIONAL GIGS\r\n\r\n* Bottles & Chimney HYEDRABAD \r\n\r\n* Back To Basic-JAIPUR-RAJASTHAN\r\n\r\n* Udapi Institute of Hotel & Tourism science- MANGLORE\r\n\r\n* Hotel Cida-de Goa, /\r\n* Hotel Radisson white sand resort / GOA\r\n* Taj exotica /\r\n\r\n* EAU BAR(Hotel Le Meridian) NEW DELHI \r\n\r\n* Capitol club (Ashoka hotel) NEW DELHI \r\n\r\n* BLACK THE CLUB (Pacific Mall) GAZHIABAD ,U.P\r\n\r\n* ICE CUBE- NOIDA ,U.P\r\n\r\n* FELIX Club KANPUR-U.P\r\n\r\n* ZERO DEGREE LUCKHNOW-U.P\r\n\r\n* THE BEACH -BANGALORE\r\n\r\n* PIOSON IVY- DELHI\r\n\r\n\r\nAnd many more\r\n\r\n\r\nCheck out his gigs pics @ http://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=703617292&sk=photos\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAreas Of Specialization:\r\n\r\n01. Remixing / Music Production \r\n\r\n02. Range of Genres:\r\n\r\n(Spl. In) Bollywood  Remixes  Pop, House & all Commercial music\r\n\r\n\r\nCHECK OUT SOME OF HIS CREATIVE PRODUCTION @ \r\nwww.myspace.com/djharryno1\r\n\r\nwww.zorpia.com/djharryno1\r\n\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/OFFICIALDJHARSH/info','http://www.djharsh.blogspot.com','http://soundcloud.com/deejayharsha-1','','0','11331',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-harsh'),(143,0,2,2,'BLAKC','This is the story of BLAKC. BLAKC is a band from Mumbai made up of five very unique, talented individuals. They are (in no order of importance) Shawn Pereira, Shishir Thakur, Roop Thomas, Rein Dias and Anish Menon. Before we get to know them better, lets see how BLAKC was first formed. \r\n\r\nIn early 2006, Shawn was a fun-loving college-going kid. His priorities in life were to attend as little college as possible while meeting as many women as possible. He decided the way to go was to be a rockstar. Enter Anish, another fun-loving, college-going kid. He wanted to be a high flying guy in the corporate world. So much so that he actually turned up for one of BLAKCs gigs at a later time in a suit, and then left without playing. But he too wanted to be a rockstar. They made a lot more money and did a lot less to earn it. Anyway, Anish met Shawn and concluded that they might just have something in common. So they got together with Gaurav and Vishwanath (who then formed Red Cube after they left BLAKC) and Sylvester, Shawns guitarist-friend. They jammed for a week, entered into a competition under the supposedly temporary name of BLAKC and came third in a college competition and the name stuck. \r\n\r\nTowards the end of 2006, Gaurav and Nath were replaced by Roop and Shishir and BLAKC started composing its own music. In February 2007, Reinhardt replaced Sylvester and the lineup was complete. BLAKC went on to win a local college competition and thats where it all began. \r\n\r\nIn the past three years that BLAKC has been around with its present lineup, they participated in a lot of local college competitions. After making it to the finals of both IRock and Campus Rock, they graduated to opening and headlining shows in Mumbai as well as other cities. Today BLAKC has played over eighty shows across 14 cities in India. \r\n\r\nBLAKC released their debut album \'Choking On  A Dream\' in December 2008. The album DID NOT sell out like crazy :) but the general consensus (fans and critics alike) is that BLAKC is definitely a band to watch out for. Lucky enough to sell around 700 cds. The band is currently writing new music for their second album and has no plans to allow life as such to disrupt the crazy life they are living. \r\n\r\nBLAKC has always been about two things, the music and the people. We believe that our music is an extension of our personalities and the only way to connect to so many music lovers. Off stage we are weird; on stage we can tear a place apart purely because of the energy we have. BLAKC since its beginning has been unable to fit into genres, we stopped trying and stuck to doing what we loved doing more than any other which is making our own music. We each have such various influences that every song has multiple personalities. We love what we do and we love that you like us enough to have read this. Peace.........and let the BLACKATTAINMENT begin.............\r\n\r\n','9820528062 or 9820107822','http://www.facebook.com/blackattainment/info','http://blakc.bandcamp.com','http://soundcloud.com/blakc','http://www.reverbnation.com/blakc','0','11227',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','blakc'),(144,0,0,0,'Harris Mania','Early life:\r\n\r\nHarris Jayaraj was born to a pious Christian Nadar family. He studied at the Krishnaswamy Matric School, Chennai. His father, S. M. Jayakumar, was a film guitarist who later became a noted musician and Chennai film composer. His father was an assistant to Malayalam music director Shyam and he hoped to make his child Harris a great singer. But his interest was in film music and he once confessed that he could not sing well. Jayaraj was an early admirer of the work of Hans Zimmer','','http://www.facebook.com/isaiminnal/info','http://www.harrismania.com','','','0','11169',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','harris-mania'),(145,0,0,0,'DJ Stash','Profession:-Deejay, Music producer, Times Music Artiste.\r\n \r\nMusic style:-Majorly known for Bollywood, UK Bhangra,Commercial House & Rnb Hip Hop...\r\n\r\nStash started his journey in dj.ing in the year 1996...as music has always been a passion in his life he decided to pursue it as a careerhas specialized in Bollywood, Hip Hop & RnB..He has performed across the world in the best night clubs, commercial gigs n corporate events Burning the dance floor to setting up trendz with his own style of mixing UK Bhangra, Hip hop N majorly Bollywood, In no time STASH proved himself n gained popularity in the party circuit \r\nHe played in one of the top clubs in Dubai named BOMBAY FUNK n CLUB DESI which was covered LIVE by Dubai fm & B4U music channelThen he moved on to Doha (QATAR) where he is known as one of the top urban djs n the first one to introduce the most happening Bollywood nites in Qatar.also one of the djs who plays all genre of music on TURNTABLES.\r\nHaving started his production n recently gained more popularity with his Exclusive selection of work in his album DOUBLE TADKA Bollywood remixes officially released on TIMES MUSIC which are played by most of the djs and is featured on top fm stations worldwide including Dubai, Canada & Doha to name a few .\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/stash4u/info?ref=ts','http://stash4u.com','http://soundcloud.com/user2533663','','0','11150',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-stash'),(146,0,57,57,'Apanhador S','Um punhado de belas canes e uma invejvel capacidade de cativar o pblico de imediato: foram estes ingredientes que garantiram ao Apanhador S prestgio e destaque na frtil cena musical brasileira, desde 2006, quando surgiu com o EP Embrulho Pra Levar.\r\n\r\nCom versos filosficos e msica de esprito aventureiro, o disco do quarteto de Porto Alegre conquistou admiradores fiis em shows pelos principais palcos do Rio Grande do Sul. Com ele, a banda ganhou, em votao popular, concurso da TramaVirtual e foi ao Rio de Janeiro abrir show de Maria Rita.  viagem seguiram-se apresentaes em So Paulo que renderam bons comentrios e garantiram regresso  capital paulista, em 2008.\r\n\r\nO segredo do sucesso do grupo est no talento para compor canes que remetem a uma ancestralidade pop de assimilao imediata, ao mesmo tempo em que desafia ouvintes atentos a desvendar novas camadas sonoras e lricas a cada audio. Foi esse equilbrio entre o popular e o experimental que rendeu ao Apanhador S tanto reconhecimento, antes mesmo de seu primeiro lbum, Apanhador S, ser lanado em 2010 e ir direto para as listas de melhores daquele ano.\r\n\r\nConsagrado pop\r\nCom o lanamento do primeiro disco cheio, choveram elogios nas principais publicaes culturais brasileiras destacando a destreza dos gachos para renovar e lapidar o rock  fundindo referncias do tango ao reggae com o charme da percusso sucateira e poesias bem escritas e bem cantadas. Tudo isso numa embalagem impecvel: cada cano ganhou uma ilustrao do cartunista Fabiano Gummo e caligrafia prprias no encarte do disco  inestimvel presente para os que, em plena revoluo digital, esgotaram a primeira tiragem da bolachinha nos concorridos shows de lanamento.\r\n\r\nO refinamento pop de seu debut colocou, definitivamente, o grupo na linha de frente da nova msica brasileira, com direito a indicao na categoria Aposta MTV do Video Music Brasil (VMB) 2010 e consagrao no Prmio Aorianos de Msica, de onde o Apanhador S saiu laureado por Melhor lbum Pop, Melhor Produtor Musical (Marcelo Fruet) e Melhor Projeto Grfico (Rafael Rocha).\r\n\r\nTambm disponvel gratuitamente em seu site, Apanhador S atingiu a impressionante marca de mais de 50 mil downloads em um ano  nmero que duplicou nos meses seguintes e vem crescendo diariamente. Os nmeros se convertem em coro durante os shows, em especial em Um Rei e o Z  cujo clipe, uma adorvel e divertida partida de taco-bola produzida com esmero pela Sof Verde Filmes,  presena constante na programao da MTV e levou a banda a ser indicada ao VMB 2011, desta vez como Revelao.\r\n\r\nAonde o povo est\r\nO reconhecimento da crtica amparado por um squito fiel de admiradores sustenta apresentaes lotadas tanto em sua Porto Alegre natal quanto no cobiado circuito do SESC So Paulo, em eventos disputados como Virada Cultural Paulista e Feira Msica Brasil, e em festivais, casas de show e teatros das principais cidades brasileiras. A simpatia irresistvel do frontman Alexandre Kumpinski, somada  guitarra esmerilhada de Felipe Zancanaro, ao baixo sedutor de Ferno Agra,  bateria precisa de Martin Estevez e  inefvel bicicleta percussiva  smbolo da banda , arrebata plateias por onde quer que passe.\r\n\r\nAinda colhendo os louros de sua bela estreia, o Apanhador S decidiu, em 2011, reinventar seus recentes clssicos e trouxe a pblico um novo trabalho. Gravado na sala da casa de Kumpinski usando gaiola, sacos plsticos, ralador de queijo, cantil de escoteiro, talheres, pedaos de condute, tecladinhos, walkie-talkie e outras bugigangas, objetos eletrnicos e instrumentos lo-fi, o disco Acstico-Sucateiro evidenciou a capacidade de experimentar e inovar da banda. Alm de disponibilizado para download gratuito, o material  que traz ainda a indita Na Ponta dos Ps  saiu em fita cassete.\r\n\r\nNovamente, com projeto grfico ousado desenvolvido por Felipe Oliveira e ilustrado pelo cartunista Diego Gerlach, o lanamento incentiva o pblico a reciclar ideias e materiais. No encarte, a banda convida os fs a tambm lanarem mo de objetos do dia-a-dia para criar arte e, nas apresentaes, prope que o pblico leve fitas cassetes (novas ou usadas) para serem trocadas por cpias do Acstico-Sucateiro.\r\n\r\nA iniciativa abriu possibilidades para o grupo, que passou a realizar intervenes em lugares pblicos das cidades que visita em turn, como praas, parques, estaes de metr e pequenos teatros histricos, numa eficiente estratgia de ocupao e revalorizao de espaos urbanos, para alm da ampliao de plateias e contato contguo com seu pblico.\r\n\r\nJunto e misturado\r\nDa sntese das duas experincias, nasceu o espetculo Eltrico-Acstico-Sucateiro, que estreou com sucesso em Porto Alegre, com convidados, cenrio, iluminao e projees especiais, e catarse do pblico em noites de sesses duplas  que devem percorrer teatros de outras cidades em breve.\r\n\r\nNo momento, o quarteto trabalha no clipe de Nescaf, considerada uma das melhores msicas de 2010. A cano recentemente foi cantada em show por Vitor Ramil e seu filho Ian (parceiro de Kumpinski nesta composio e tambm em Um Rei e o Z) e est no lbum de estreia do cantor Filipe Catto, lanado pela Universal.\r\n\r\nO Apanhador S promete novo disco para 2012. Algumas msicas j aparecem no set list das apresentaes do grupo  como Torcicolo, Mas No, Ele se Acordou, Salo de Festas, Carto Postal e Paraquedas  e apontam caminhos ensolarados para o futuro do grupo, mantendo o foco em experimentos que testam os limites do pop.','Pamela Leme | 11-7319-8840 | pamela@alavanca.art.br','http://www.facebook.com/apanhadorso/info','http://www.apanhadorso.com','http://soundcloud.com/apanhadorso','','0','11141',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','apanhador-so'),(147,0,0,0,'HOLY OTHER','','(UK) keongwoo [at] familyltd.co.uk (USA) heathcliff.berru [at] gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/holyother/info','','http://soundcloud.com/holyother','','0','11113',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','holy-other'),(148,0,2,2,'GODS ROBOTS','The seamless blend of catchy English lyrics, classical Indian instrumentation and underground rhythms defines the unique Gods Robots sound. It is the sound of an infinitely interconnected world where borders are becoming increasing meaningless. Gods Robots exciting stage show highlights their dynamic blend of cross cultural songwriting, energetic and infectious performance using cutting edge technology and old school musicianship. Elements of drumstep, dubstep, hip hop, dub and even drum n bass shine as singer Taamara effortlessly moves from soulful and bluesy English lyrics to classical Indian vocal melodies. \r\n\r\nBBC Radio 1 Host Nihal described their music as authentic and gave them the best sound review along with the band to watch out for on the show Strand in 2010; following which heavy airplay on BBC fetched them a wide fan base. Championed by Rolling Stone India, Gods Robots is been featured 3 times in articles that discuss their 2010 India tour, their use of technology to create music whilst the two core band members reside on different continents and producer Janaka Selektas critically acclaimed album Pushing Air.\r\n\r\nTheir debut \"Stormy Weather\" especially produced for Bittorrent features virtuoso Sarod player Alam Khan in a rare non-classical Indian music context and Mike Pipes on flute and guitar. Stormy Weather brings in sounds and stories the duo has explored through their two year journey built across continents. \r\n\r\nIt\'s up for free download. Grab your copy now:: http://featuredcontent.utorrent.com/\r\n','yuvraj.bajwa@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/GODSROBOTS/info','http://www.godsrobots.net','http://soundcloud.com/godsrobots','','0','10607',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','gods-robots'),(149,0,58,58,'Eelke Kleijn (official)','Ever since his 2003 landing in the world of electronic music, Eelke Kleijn has been a name synchronous with quality. Fans and enthusiasts worldwide have come to love the sympathetic Dutchman for his affectionate sound, unique productions and dynamic DJ sets, which have taken him from Mexico to Russia, and almost everywhere in between. And it\'s not just the fans that are moved by his work; avid followers include internationally renowned DJs such as Hern?n Catt?neo, Sasha and Dave Seaman, who repeatedly drop his tracks in clubs and festivals around the world.\r\n\r\nEelke\'s real breakthrough came in 2006 when Nick Warren included \'8 Bit Era\' on his \'GU 030: Paris\' compilation. A few months later, Global Underground snapped up his debut artist album \'Naturally Artificial\', which hit the market late 2007 and received critical acclaim from press and reviewers worldwide. The attention from an international best-selling label also sky rocketed his DJ career, playing at massive events such as Moonpark in Buenos Aires, Dance Valley, Extrema Outdoor and Sensation to club gigs at the world famous Warung in Brazil and Privilege Ibiza.\r\n\r\nThroughout the years, Eelke\'s increasing profile has given him the opportunity to remix numerous well known acts and DJs, including Way Out West, Hybrid, Miss Nine and Sander Kleinenberg. His area of work extends well beyond the borders of conventional dance music however, having written music for clients such as NIKE & Joolz and often being credited as a mixing and mastering engineer for various artists and labels.\r\n\r\nBesides his work as a DJ and producer, Eelke also successfully runs the record label \'Outside the Box Music\', launched in 2006. His similarly named radio show and podcast has grown into an internet sensation, reaching tens of thousands of people each month.\r\n\r\nOn November 24th Eelke released his second artist album, \'Untold Stories\', on Manual Music. The philosophy behind his second full-length album is that music should be continuous, an uninterrupted, emotional experience. Having written the album as one single piece instead of a collection of individual tracks, Untold Stories is truly Eelke\'s way of pushing boundaries with music. The album received great reviews and international DJ support by the likes of Hernan Catanneo and Nick Warren.\r\n\r\nWith a second solo album released and an incredible amount of work to look back upon, Eelke Kleijn establishes himself not just as another producer or DJ, but as a modern day electronic composer.','Urban Rebel PR: vass@urbanrebelpr.com','http://www.facebook.com/eelkekleijn/info','http://www.eelkekleijn.nl','http://www.soundcloud.com/eelke-kleijn','','0','10361',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','eelke-kleijn-official'),(150,0,2,2,'Zygnema','*Their Achievements*:\r\n\r\nHeadlined Resonance at Terna College, Nerul on 14th March 2012.\r\nHeadlined Transfusion 2011, Goa - Curcherum on Dec 10th 2011.\r\nCo-headlined alongside with Firezone (Netherlands) and Dead City ruins (Australia) at Metal Asylum Festival-DUBAI,UAE on November 06th 2011.\r\nRolling Stone Metal Awards 2011: Best Band and Song (Popular Choice) \r\nCo-Headlined with Tesseract (U.K) at Springfest 2011, IIT Kharagpur, Calcutta on 24th Jan 2011\r\nPerformed at the Bastard Club, Osnabrck, Germany on 8th Jan 2011\r\nRosenhof, Osnabrk, Germany on 7th Jan 2011\r\nYamaha Asian Beat GLOBAL Finals, Bangkok on 10th November 2010 and Award for the best guitarist \r\nWinner of Yamaha Asian Beat NATIONAL Finals, Award for the Best Bassist and Best Drummer at Hard Rock Cafe, Lower Parel on 2nd September 2010\r\nMumbai Finalists of Yamaha Asian Beat & Award for the Best Guitarist at Bhaidas Hall on 10th July 2010\r\nAlbum Promotional Gig at Musician\'s Mall on 18th June 2010\r\nHammer Fest India III - Zygnema\'s Album Launch - Mumbai (4th June), Bangalore(6th June) and Pune(13th June) 2010\r\nMumbai Finalists of Independence Rock XXIV, Andheri on 3rd Oct 2009\r\n2nd Place at Apocalypse 2009, Bangalore on 29th April 2009\r\nWinners of Zodiac 09 and award for the Best Guitarist Raj