comunicacin especializados (Mondo Sonoro, Go, Rock Deluxe...).\r\n\r\nThe Cathedral ha sido el ltimo trabajo que la banda realiz a finales del 2009 y que ha sido puesto a la venta en formato digital. Consta de 5 versiones personales y casi acsticas de temas de lbumes anteriores.\r\n\r\nOblique se encuentra en pleno proceso de creacin de lo que ser su nuevo trabajo y ya tiene editado el primer single titulado \"Akind of electric current\" con un videoclip realizado por Javi Moreno.\r\nActualmente, acaba de rodar su segundo videoclip realizado por Pep Sanabra con estilismo de diseadores de primer nivel como Manuel Bolao, Luis Manteiga, Jose Zambrano y Alba Prat.\r\n\r\n\r\nPremios recibidos por Oblique:\r\n\r\n-	Premio mejor banda electrnica Premios Pop-Eye.\r\n-	Premio mejor banda electrnica Diario Metro.\r\n-	Premio mejor banda electrnica Heineken Kulture Movement.\r\n-	Premio del pblico mejor video clip My Medicine Festival de Cine de Medina del Campo.\r\n-	Premio del pblico mejor video clip My Medicine Festival Internacional Musiclip.\r\n-	Electronically Yours (UK) elige All We Want como mejor cancin electrnica en su TOP 20 2008.\r\n-	Mejor Apuesta 2010 MTV.\r\n\r\ncontacto:\r\nJuan Gonzlez\r\nbooking@oblique-music.com\r\n\r\n\r\nmas info:\r\nmyspace: www.myspace.com/obliquemusic\r\nblog: http://obliquemusic.wordpress.com/\r\nweb: www.oblique-music.com\r\nyoutube: www.youtube.com/user/Obliquemusic\r\nfacebook: www.facebook.com/pages/Oblique/48725309892?ref=ts','info@oblique-music.com','http://www.facebook.com/ObliqueMusic/info','http://www.oblique-music.com','http://soundcloud.com/oblique','','0','10312',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','oblique'),(152,0,2,2,'Balli Riar','Just When You Thought Youve Heard It All, Along Comes An Artist With The Power And Vitality To Steer Music In A New Direction.\r\n                        Balli Riar  was born and raised in Chandigarh, Punjab . He completed his school and Graduation From Punjab University , Chandigarh and for higher education he went to U.K for MBA. .Coming from a family oriented background, Balli Riars traditional upbringing enabled him to maintain a deep connection with his roots So After completing his MBA from Sunderland, U.K he came back to india .\r\n         During his College days he was famous among his friends and college masses for his singing and acting. He voice & acting appealed to many when he performed at college stage & on fairs held in the university.\r\n      Balli Riar Has been thinking about building his career since he was a little boy He had great passion for sports and music. At first he playe cricket[professionally], he has been part of Punjab cricket team and represented it at national level But singing had always been what he wanted to do...so this passion for music turned into His Debut Album  Never DonE Before in summer 2011. \r\n       The Idea of this album was build up in his mind from a long time and he implemented it with the well known music director Honey singh. Balli riar began his training to be a vocalist under the tuition of Kakri ji ( mohali). Balli riars influences include the greats such as Kuldip Manak, Chamkila, Mohd Sadiq ,Gurdass mann,George Michael and Strings .\r\n\r\nWith his debut release he became a rage with young generation of Punjabi music fans with his laid back style with hip hop tints and up-market video style. His BreakThrough Track  Banda Bunda Marna Tan Das  has become a top hit on the charts all over and has already established him as a Unique and Vibrant Artist. He Focuses his Eye on the youth culture..\r\n         He puts his heart and soul in every song he sings. His Goal is to provide feel good music to the masses in the hope that he can revitalize the Spirit Of The People for the Punjabi Music.\r\n     For him this is just the beginning..the best is yet to come. He is working on various projects : as in collaboration album & his new solo album and he also a part of a movie project.\r\nBalli Rair is thankful to god for showering his blessing upon him and feels blessed to have a a supporting family and encouraging friends.','','http://www.facebook.com/balliriar/info?ref=ts','http://www.balliriar.com','','','0','10255',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','balli-riar'),(153,0,3,3,'Dj Ivan','DJ Ivan is one of Bangalores (India) foremost prime DJ, is unquestionably one of the pioneers of excellent music and entertainment today. Ivans versatility in various music genres has always created an ambience of taste, talent and celebration for all music lovers. It is DJ Ivans passion, originality & individuality that set him apart from the world. It is not only his music that stands in the foreground, but also the integration of strong words and images  always different and mystical, against the current and diverse in terms of Style. DJ Ivans talent isnt confined to the decks, he is well known for his music acumen which has secured him the position of a notable DJ over the years.\r\n\r\nDJ Ivans success burgeoned and was evident at the very early stages of his DJing career, making him immensely popular & favored in the scenes. His extensive knowledge of music & mixing has been the hallmark to set and changed the moods of people, ensuring non-stop fun at all parties.\r\n	\r\nHe utilizes his vast knowledge of the scene and its music to help create parties that focus on diverse quality sounds and a welcoming, energetic vibe. DJ Ivans larger than life character has won him friends all over the world. Today, DJ Ivans outlook is to produce his own music and he wishes that this soon becomes a testament to quality control and a signpost of his long-term wider aims.\r\n\r\nDJ Ivans Journey towards success has been a an eventful one, with an experience in the scene like no other; \r\n\r\n-DJ Ivan kick started his career 15 years ago at a nightclub called Time & Again 1992-94\r\n\r\n-Played at the Midnight Express Pub and later at The Club Bangalore 1995-96\r\n\r\n-Resident DJ  Three Flights up (Mumbai)  1997-98\r\n\r\n-Official Disc Jockey  Channel V India  1998-2001\r\n\r\n-Official DJ Bacardi Martini  1998  2001\r\n\r\n-Runner up at DMC World Championship 1998, India\r\n\r\n-First and only Indian DJ to play at Ministry of Sounds first official tour of India  2001\r\n\r\n-First Indian DJ to host an international dance show on a radio station  Radio City 91 FM  2001-03\r\n\r\n-Official DJ for Smirnoff India  2002 present\r\n\r\n-Played with Paul Van Dyk, Danny Rampling, Sasha, Smoking Joe, Tom Stephen, Lee Buridge, Steve Lawler  some of worlds top DJs\r\n\r\n-First Indian DJ to perform in Dubai  Copas at Four Point Sheraton Hotel\r\n\r\n-Wednesday residency at Spinn  Bangalores biggest and most successful club\r\n\r\n-Currently hosting own radio show  Hotmix on Radio Indigo 91.9Bangalore for the last 5yrs \r\n\r\n-Owns and runs the Ministry of Sound franchise in India for the last 3yrs and is the official MOS India Resident..\r\n\r\n-Played at Ministry of Sound 19th Birthday party at Ministry of Sound London alongside Danny Tenaglia.\r\n\r\n-Created and runs a nite as a resident called STUDIO 54 at the very reputed and swanky SHIRO in Mumbai....\r\n\r\n-Has just started a brand new concept where he mixes and scratches music videos on an led screen to take you into the future of clubbing....\r\n\r\n-Has a wealth of his productions,mash ups and re-edits  that have  already been released and coming out shortly is his already highly acclaimed and appropriately called new single -MUSIC IS MY LIFE...\r\n\r\n\r\nAnd the Journey continues\r\n\r\n-www.djivanindia.in','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Dj-Ivan/10464958622?sk=info','http://www.djivanindia.in','','','0','10112',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-ivan'),(154,0,2,2,'Indus Creed','The story of Indian rock cannot be told without a mention of the countrys most iconic rock band. Uday Benegal (vocals), Mahesh Tinaikar (guitar), Mark Selwyn (bass), Jayesh Gandhi (guitar), Zubin Balaporia (keyboards) and Mark Menezes (drums) first came together in 1985. Then called Rock Machine, the guys had no mission or plan. Just an unflagging desire to play the music they loved. In the face of all reason (there was just one government-run TV channel and radio station, neither of which thought rocknroll to be particularly \"cultural\") the band set out to do just that. It took blood, guts and a steely resolve to cut through the crap. It was just a matter of time before practically every college and concert promoter in the country wanted to book what had become Indias favourite band. The rest is history. They recorded three albums, won a bunch of awards and changed their name to Indus Creed. And in the process they inspired an entire generation to pick up an instrument and rock it out. Heres a quick roundup of some of their multifarious achievements:\r\n Toured the length and breadth of India\r\n Repped the country at the Festival of India in the USSR\r\n Played at Peter Gabriel\'s WOMAD festival in the UK\r\n Performed with Bon Jovi to over 40,000 people in Bombay\r\n Performed on stage with GNR guitar player Slash for MTVs launch in Bangalore\r\n Toured the UK and the Middle East extensively','info@induscreed.net','http://www.facebook.com/IndusCreedNow/info','www.induscreed.net','http://soundcloud.com/induscreed','','0','9960',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','indus-creed'),(155,0,5,5,'Tara','TARA PRIYA is a retro-soul singer/songwriter born and raised in San Francisco, CA. Of Indian-Persian parentage, Tara combines vintage soul, poetic lyrics, and a dash of pop to provide relief from todays Auto-Tune avalanche.\r\n\r\nThe great-niece of the famed Middle Eastern poet, Sohrab Sepehri, art is in Taras blood. Piano and poetry began at 4, drums at 9; opera training commenced at 11, jazz voice added in high school. After winning two prestigious writing scholarships, Tara switched coasts to attend Columbia University, where she quickly settled down in NYCs  performance circuit.\r\n\r\nAnxious to focus solely on music but reluctant to drop out like her Columbia inspirations (Alicia Keys, Lauryn Hill), Tara sped through school and graduated in 2.5 years with her BA in Economics. She returned to California to write and record her November 2010 eponymous EP, which continues to receive praise from bloggers/critics and airplay on both CHR and college radio stations.\r\n\r\nIn February 2012, Tara released her 2nd independent EP in the United States and her 1st full length album in Japan via P-Vine Records. When she is not traveling to perform in San Francisco, New York, Canada, the UK, India, or Japan, Tara can be found eating vegan oatmeal raisin cookies in Los Angeles.\r\n\r\n--Winner of the 18th Annual Billboard Song Contest, 03/2011\r\n--Winner of the Great American Song Contest, 03/2011\r\n--#8, Best Emerging Artists of 2010, The Deli Magazine, 02/2011\r\n--Top 25 finalist, Music City Songwriting Contest , 12/2010\r\n--1 of 3 Pop finalists, John Lennon Songwriting Contest, 09/2010\r\n--CMJ Music Marathon; 2010 Miami Music Festival; 2011 NAMM Show; Canadian Music Fest; San Diego County Fair; Playground Music Festival 2011; 2011 MidPoint Music Festival; 2011 Indie Week Canada; Bacardi NH7 Weekender','USA: Sara Jayne Crow, straypoodle@gmail.com; CANADA: Diane Foy, diane@skylarentertainment.ca; UK, MIDDLE EAST, INDIA: Raj Ghai, raj@mediamoguls.com; JAPAN: P-Vine Records; GERMANY/AUSTRIA/SWITZERLAND:','http://www.facebook.com/tarapriyamusic','http://tarapriya.bandcamp.com','http://soundcloud.com/tarapriya/sets/tara-priya-highlights/','http://www.reverbnation.com/play_now/song_12033908','0','9852',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','tara'),(156,0,1,1,'Jasleen Royal','Looking at the petite Jasleen Royal, in her trademark pyjamas and long loose t-shirts, all of 20 years, no one can imagine of how talented this little girl might be. But as soon as she puts her guitar around her neck, starts strumming those strings and lending her voice, we can be nothing but astounded. Studying at Hindu college Jasleen is like any other collegiate. Random yet certain, humorous and appealing.\r\nHer love for music dates a long time back. Started with learning the keyboard, she used all she gathered to figure out guitar and mouth-organ herself. Now she can play two of these things at the same time. Expertise is her specialty when the context is music. She broke the ice with being one of the semi finalists in India\'s got talent and just one and a half year old in the industry, she already has a lot of accomplishments in her kitty.She has been chosen as the youth Icon by IIT Roorkee and was invited as a Guest of Honor by The Indian Embassy in Nepal.\r\nShe has judged shows like Hindustan Rockstars and Zee Aspire for Zee Business and has performed at the annual fests of a lot of renowned colleges like IIT Delhi, AIIMS etc. At an age of 20 when people don\'t even know where to start from. Jasleen has already made her mark and its just going to get deeper and deeper with time. No stopping the rockstar!\r\n','Subir Malik / Parikrama Inc.','http://www.facebook.com/jasleenroyal/info','http://jasleenroyal.in','','','0','9679',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','jasleen-royal'),(157,0,2,2,'Scribe','Say hello to Scribe - India\'s torchbearer for hardcore.\r\n\r\nWhen their particular brand of irreverent extreme music landed them the Winners title at Independence Rock 2007 in Mumbai; their insatiable hunger for composing, playing and releasing music started taking prominence.\r\n\r\nShortly after their 2006 EP \'Have Hard. Will Core\', Scribe released their first full-length album called \'Confect.\' following it up with an intensive tour making all sorts of squiggly lines upon the Map of India, and in the process, winning fans outside the map as well!\r\n\r\nAfter having planted their flags across the map with tours spanning Delhi, Bangalore, Mumbai, Shillong, Guwahati,Pune and most recently playing at the prestigious INFERNO METAL FESTIVAL in Norway, Oslo, India\'s most adamant DIY band have just launched their second album \"Mark of Teja\" - which won the Best Metal Album at the first ever Rolling Stone Metal Awards alongwith winning the Best Metal Band, Best Metal Song (DemonPra) and Best Metal Vocalist (Vishwesh Krishnamoorthy)\r\n\r\nIn addition to the album, they collaborated with photographer Varun Dutt for their off-beat music video for \"Dum Hai To Aage Aah!\" from the new album - which showcased DIY B-Boying kids from Dharavi. \r\n\r\nWatch the video: \r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=atRQBkTYluo\r\n\r\nIt has also recently been nationally broadcasted on VH1 India. ','','http://www.facebook.com/scribecore.in/info','http://www.scribecore.in','','','0','9643',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','scribe'),(158,2,1,1,'Them Clones','Them Clones were created sometime in 2000.\r\n\r\n\"It came about as we were looking to forge an identity as a left-of-the-middle sort of band. The name reflects the general attitude of the band which was to look at their stage personalities as clones of their selves\".\r\n\r\nInspired by the dramatic world of rock n\' roll and of course themselves, their tryst with songwriting has directed them across the course of the thoughtful to confessional, from the assertive to the provocative; but has been, consistently, accompanied by a tight groove or a silken melody.\r\n\r\nDiscography :\r\n\r\nOct 2009\r\n\'Love.Hate.Heroes.\' in Oct 2009. \r\nreleased under Counter Culture Records and EMI label\r\n\r\nJune 2011\r\n\'Singles\' \r\n#All about a heartbreak \r\n#Jealousy \r\n\r\n                          \r\nFeats :\r\n2010 : BIG IMA Awards in the Rock Category\r\n2009 : JD Rock Awards  in \'Best Song\' \'Best Vocalist\', \'Best Drummer\' category\r\n2007 : \'Best Band\' JD Rock Awards \r\n2006 : \'Best Band\' JD Rock Awards\r\n2005 : \'Best Band\' Channel [V] Launchpad\r\n\r\n\r\nFor more details log onto http://www.themclones.com\r\nWrite to us : clones@themclones.com','Them Clones','http://www.facebook.com/themclones/info','http://www.themclones.com/contacts','http://soundcloud.com/them-clones','','0','9604',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 13:34:25',176,'[\"clones@themclones.com\"]','[\"+91 9811979905\"]','them-clones'),(159,0,34,34,'Severe Dementia','Raising hell from Dhaka, the heart and capital of Bangladesh, Severe Dementia is a death metal band with technical influences and a keen lyrical focus towards ancient and historical events which created a major impact on certain nations and the human race. Since the formation in January 2004, Severe Dementia has been a band that embodies absolute brutality, blistering speed, technical proficiency and the utmost in quality extreme musicianship. In a country such as Bangladesh, where the people were previously unaware of devastating drum blasts, monstrous guttural growls, ravaging screams and pure aggression rendered guitar lines, Severe Dementia have become a major act to change that all over the years. Upon its formation, the band unleashed its own true form of death metal with utter ferocity that knew no bounds. Soon after, landing numerous successful gigs the band received great feedback from the local underground scene and the appreciation from the massive hordes of head bangers. Thus Severe Dementia has become the mightiest force that ever represented extreme metal from Bangladesh. \r\n\r\nIn February 2007, Severe Dementia signed a deal with Demonstealer Records (India) to release an EP in a split album Rise of the Eastern Blood with Demonic Resurrection (India), Dusk (Pakistan) and Helmksey (Singapore). The conceptual EP is entitled as Epitaph of Plassey with 5 continuous songs based on the historical Battle of Plassey between the British East India Company and the Bengal in 1757. Following that, Severe Dementia undertook a tour in India in April 2007 as being the first ever underground band from Bangladesh to play overseas. The opening of the album took place at the last gig of the tour on April 8 2007, at Razzberry Rhinoceros, Mumbai. The band played two gigs at Mumbai and Pune as the headliner unleashing on the unsuspecting crowd a torrent of unbelievably brutal, pulverizing and cataclysmic death metal. The band set the standards high and with the release of Epitaph of Plassey, showed the metal hordes worldwide that metal was well alive and kicking even from a country like Bangladesh. \r\n\r\nAfter a long break and suffering a few minor changes in the line-up, the revamped Severe Dementia resurfaced to take back their rightful dominion in the underground. The band has been working heavily on the writing and composing of new materials as well as the pre-production of its second official release, which would be the bands first full length album since, Epitaph of Plassey (EP, 2007). Although the name of the album had not been titled yet, the band announced that the album concept and lyrical themes would be based upon ancient Sumerian mythology. The approximate release date will be announced once the band completes the pre-production. \r\n','+88 01712 927 429','http://www.facebook.com/severedementia/info','http://www.severedementia.com','','','0','9224',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','severe-dementia'),(160,0,60,60,'ARSAMES','The First Persian Ancient Death Metal \r\nARSAMES\r\nArsames is an Ancient melodic death metal band from Iran, Arsames was formed in 2002 by Ali madarshahi ( frontman and first Drummer) in mashhad one of the largest City of Iran\r\nThe former members started to create their songs and playing them in their rehearsal room at the same time , the result was Songs :\r\n1-Homo sapiens 2-Cyrus The Great 3- Immortal Identity 4-Adipocere 5- Cyclopia (instrumental) 6-Exile , Metal music is banned in Iran so they couldn\'t release their songs\r\nthey decided to make an official web site to promote the band in Internet and follow that the myspace website in 2006 , they recorded all the tracks in a Home studio and put some of them in\r\ntheir myspace and start to promote ... the feed back was great so many fans joined their myspace to see how death metal sounds in Persia, the fans added bunch of comments and good vibes\r\nto their myspace and some magazines around the world ask them for Interview at that time , so they found a good energy for continuing\r\nin 2008 Metalcamp festival invited underground bands to joined a competition and between thousands of bands Arsames won to play in Metalcamp ...\r\nin 2009 an international 3days unirock festival in turkey invited them to play in istanbul turkey along with famous acts like:\r\nAmon Amarth , Arch enemy , Kreator ...and the last day of the fest they opened the stage for Amon Amarth and Arsames had an interview with metalhammer that night and it published in\r\nmetalhammer magazine in 2009 , they also played in Dorock bar in istanbul turkey few days later after they came back to Iran huge number of Turkish fans joined Arsames websites . in 2010 they invited\r\nto be the headliner and played in Metal asylum in Dubai\r\nin 2010 The band Decide to re record the first album with better quality an add some new tracks, now they have 9 studio tracks and It will be released worldwide in Nov 2010\r\nAlso they invited and played as headlining act in a huge metal festival in India Sikkim metal fest in Nov 2010','Alimadarshahe@yahoo.com ','http://www.facebook.com/pages/ARSAMES/111288558020?sk=info','http://www.arsames.net','','','0','9215',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','arsames'),(161,0,62,61,'Thieve','Nothing is original. Take what you want.','Louise Crouse, suukiemusic@gmail.com, 0767051642','http://www.facebook.com/thieve/info','http://www.thieve.co.za','http://soundcloud.com/thieve','','0','9010',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','thieve'),(162,2,1,1,'B.L.O.T. :: Basic Love Of Things','BLOT is an acronym for the Basic Love of Things, \r\n\r\nA multidisciplinary project helmed by Gaurav Malaker and\r\nAvinash Kumar and supported by a network of artists, BLOT focus on creating atypical clubland experiences.\r\n\r\nAvinash Kumar is a designer, visual artist, filmmaker and VJ, and a founding member of design and research firms Quicksand and BOX. Gaurav Malaker is a DJ, producer and a founding member of Qilla Records.\r\n\r\n They blend sound and music, while manipulating their performance spaces to expand the frontiers of electronica performances. Visually BLOT employ traditional filmmaking techniques as well as stop-motion animation and motion graphics, and the duo s diversity is as apparent in their music as it is in their visuals. \r\n\r\nAs India s original and leading audiovisual collective, BLOT curated the experimental stage at Sunburn Festival in Goa (2010) and further afield, have performed at legendary venues like Tresor and Bar25 (Berlin) several times, as well as at Geneva s Electron Festival (2011), Berlin Music Week\r\n(2010), Champagnerama in Berlin (2010), London s South Bank Centre (2010) and at Nuits Sonores in Lyon (2009). \r\n\r\nThey ve been invited to Austin s SXSW festival and will perform at CO-Pop (Cologne) in summer 2011, with tours in Russia, Switzerland, UK and USA to follow later in the year.\r\n\r\nBLOT DVD ALBUM \r\nComing soon.\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n','gaurav@blot.in','http://www.facebook.com/blottin/info','http://www.blottin.blogspot.com','http://soundcloud.com/blot','','0','8968',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 13:20:59',262,'[\"gaurav@blot.in\\r\",\"\\r\",\"India :UnMute Agency - dev@unmute.in \"]','[\"+91-9999369935\"]','blot-basic-love-of-things'),(163,0,2,2,'Workshop','When satan and god had sex, the big bang happened. However since satan was prone to multiple orgasms another bang happened.... and thats how Workshop was formed.\r\n\r\nA poly-rhythmic drummer, an Apollonian Quest that lost its way, a classic rock chromatic scale playing bassist and a fiery demonic monster all combined, with their powers united as one, a musical comedy of sorts is the best way to define the creative power of the Workshop. \r\n\r\nPlaying a vast span of genres ranging from EMO to Garba to Bhangra to Pop but all injected with the venom of demonic metal is what the musical creations of Workshop could be classified under. \r\n\r\nWorkshop has come a long way from being a backing band for Demonstealer\'s ESP Guitar Workshop to a full-fledged band that formed in March 2008, started working on their debut album immediately. The Rajbot was induced in November 2008 and in December 2008 the band started tickling everyone\'s funny bones at their live gigs which received huge praise from fans and even bystanders. \r\n\r\nWorkshop launched their 1st video Cookie Monster on 19th March 2009, exactly a year after transforming into Workshop and starting writing their debut effort.\r\n\r\nMay 2009 saw the release of the Khooni Murga CD + DVD combo, the 1st for any India band and the album is already creating waves across the country.\r\n\r\nAnd while people clutch their tummies from guffawing too much Workshop gears up for a gig near you and a new album next year......\r\n\r\nDiscography:\r\nKhooni Murga - 2009\r\n','Demonstealer Records: demonstealerrecords@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/WorkshopMusic/info','http://www.workshopband.com','http://soundcloud.com/workshop','','0','8810',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','workshop'),(164,0,4,4,'AbraXas','The following are the achievements of AbraXas since October 2008 (Band Competitions) :\r\n\r\n\r\n1\r\n1st Runners Up - Sakaal Times / Idea Rocks\r\nElysium, Pune - October 2008\r\n\r\n\r\n2\r\nWinners - RAIT Unchained\r\nBest Guitarist (Negi) - RAIT Unchained\r\nMumbai - 31 Jan 2009\r\n\r