?sk=info','http://www.starfuckerband.com','','','0','6533',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','starfucker'),(191,0,2,2,'Goddess Gagged','Cast away your tried and tested alt rock flavorings, and find a new home in the atmospheric, prog-laden abyss that is Goddess Gagged, initially a three piece showcase of Bombays youngest rock talent and now a full fledged five-piece behemoth. Breathing in influences from all cross sections of nineties rock/metal following up to present day prog kings like Karnivool and Porcupine Tree, these five fantasists find cohesion within layers of intricate guitar work, crushing rhythms, solid bass lines and moody atmospherics worthy of the darkest nights of solitude.','gaggedgoddess@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/goddessgaggedband/info','www.goddessgagged.com','http://soundcloud.com/goddessgagged','','0','6431',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','goddess-gagged'),(192,2,74,1,'Avi & The Uprising','A word says what a thousand pictures can\'t, and three chords can change the world for Avi and the Uprising. With a canvas ranging from the surreal to the satirical, their songwriting seeks to answer age old existential questions while prompting socio-political action right here, right now. Folksy \'sing along\' melodies are backed by an electric blues driven machinery, atmospheric yet groovy.\r\n\r\nIntimate tales of telepathy, reincarnation and faith find equal footage in their songwriting along with globally relevant socio political themes like political idealism & climate change as well as topical themes from an urban India in tumult like the repressive educational system, rampant corruption and homicide.\r\nMusically, the band is firmly rooted in American folk, blues and 60\'s rock while integrating diverse influences like opera, Bollywood and stadium rock. Their Indianness is an organic reflection of the crazy melting pot of contemporary India while steering clear of the clichd postcard of a sitar, tabla and snake charmer type...\r\n\r\nThe band is all set to release their much awaited debut album \'Eyes on the radio\' by May 2012.','Avi','http://www.facebook.com/AviandtheUprising/info','','http://soundcloud.com/thebluefrog/avi-the-uprising-who','','0','6426',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 13:44:15',101,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','avi-the-uprising'),(193,0,4,4,'Noiseware','O HAI. V R METL BND. PLZ BECUM OWER FAN.','Adhiraj Singh @ +91 9923065584 (adhirajsingh90@gmail.com)','http://www.facebook.com/noiseware/info','http://www.noiseware.in','http://soundcloud.com/noiseware','','0','6384',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','noiseware'),(194,0,0,0,'Shiva Moon','Rudraksh Records // MMD Recs // Air Snare Recs\r\n\r\nsoundcloud.com/djshivamoon \r\n\r\ntwitter.com/djshivamoon\r\n\r\nmixcloud.com/djshivamoon','','http://www.facebook.com/djshivamoon/info','','http://soundcloud.com/djshivamoon','','0','6372',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','shiva-moon'),(195,0,3,3,'Agam','AGAM is a multiple award winning contemporary carnatic rock act from bangalore, india. AGAM derives its name from the ancient tamil word which translates to \'the inner self\'. AGAM\'s music encapsulates the boundless, vibrant emotions of the human psyche. It explores, depicts and contemplates these countless aspirations and sentiments of the inner self. Their music combines the myriad hues of melodic scales and intricate rhythm structures offered by carnatic music with the aesthetic principles and tonal elegance from western world. \r\n\r\nHarish - Vocals & Violin\r\nGanesh - Drums\r\nSuraj - Guitars\r\nShiva - Percussions\r\nVignesh - Bass\r\nPraveen - Guitars\r\nSwamy - Keyboards','Harish','http://www.facebook.com/agamtheband/info?ref=ts','http://www.agamtheband.in/','','','0','6347',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','agam'),(196,0,1,1,'Dj o2 & Dj Srk','','Prakhar Risodkar','http://www.facebook.com/DJo2.DJSrk/info','http://www.downloads4djs.co.in','http://soundcloud.com/o2_and_srk','','0','6273',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-o2-dj-srk'),(197,0,4,4,'HIGHWAY 61','Highway 61 is Sufi Ethnic Rock band based out of Pune. Their music embodies Music, Expression, Freedom - a fusion of classic rock with Urdu/Hindi lyrics. \r\nThe name \'Highway 61\' is a metaphor for finding a road to freedom, with nothing but ones own creativity as the compass. The music resounds with contemporary references and an informed understanding of the two-faced times we live in.\r\n \r\nThe People: \r\n\r\nMohammad Muneem: Lead Vocals/Lyricist has been writing and singing since the age of fourteen. \r\n \r\nRohit Vasudevan: Lead Guitars/Backing Vocals\r\nHe is a classically trained Sitarist. All this apart, he pilots the bands craft during his solos and is a super vocalist in his own right.\r\n\r\nJatin Kale: Lead Guitars \r\nIn Jatin, Highway 61 has a Metal-head. His power-packed high voltage solos lend the energy to the feel.\r\n\r\n\r\nRahul Majumdar: Bass Guitars/Backing Vocals \r\nTrained in Hindustani Classical Music and Tabla since the age of 4, Rahul has been into music for over 20 years. \r\n\r\nHardik Vaghela: Keys/Backing Vocals \r\nHardik lends an air of creativity to the band. His fillers, environment fills and keyboard solos make every song complete. \r\n \r\n\r\nAnant Joshi: Drums \r\nAnant keeps the band tight. A perfect machine on the drums when let loose, his beats give the platform for every song to take off. \r\n','Hardik Vaghela - 9922443357','http://www.facebook.com/Highway61Band/info','http://www.highway61.in','','http://www.reverbnation.com/highway61','0','6271',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','highway-61'),(198,0,3,3,'Tiffin Box',' Formed sometime in the month of May 2010 by a few people interested in bringing in a new genre of metal, \'Tiffin Box\' came into existence. Fusing Hindustani and Carnatic elements with strong growls and screeches, the band succeeded in their endeavour to create what \r\nthey like to call \'Tantric Metal\'. While the hindustani vocals and the sanskrit shlokas give the music a melodic touch, the growls and screeches, along with heavy guitar riffs compliment each other brilliantly, and at the same time, add power and aggression to the entire composition. The addition of frequently used jazz signatures and double bass grooves also influence the sound of the band to a great extent. This, coupled with great live performances, the band assures both, metalheads and non-metalheads brilliant music- stuff that is all set to scorch the metal scene.  ','tiffinboxtheband@gmail.com,','http://www.facebook.com/tiffinbox/info','http://www.reverbnation.com/tiffinboxtheband','http://soundcloud.com/tiffin-box-band','','0','6217',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','tiffin-box'),(199,0,1,1,'Nasha','\'Nasha\' a Delhi based \'Sufi Rock Band\' formed in November 2009... We play soulful music in a \'Modern Contemporary Rock version\'... The kind of music we play is popular among the masses and also includes bollywood hit numbers in our own sufi style... The band includes \'Akhil Sacheva\' on the lead vocals... \'Saurabh jain\' on the \'Acoustics \'n\' vocals\'..\'rohit\' on the guitar\'s... Jivi on \'bass\' \'n\' \'Ankur\' on drums....!!\r\n\r\nThe band has performed all over the nation till date from doing various concerts, private shows, corporate shows to institutional gigs.... Also performed with re-known artists like Ustad Rahat Fateh Ali Khan, Mohit Chauhan, Atif Aslam, Hard kaur etc...\r\n\r\n\'Nasha\' has been awarded as The \'Best Band from North India\' by \'Times Music\'... Have been the winners of \'Mtv Rockothon 2010\' \'n\' have also been the participants of \'Mtv Rock On\'(top 7)... Have shared the same stage to perform with bands like Parikrama, Indian Ocean etc..\r\n\r\nThe band has just performed internationally in europe,turkey \'n\' also for a corporate show with \'Standard Chartered Bank\' in \'Dubai\'....\r\nThe title track \'Nasha\' is about to be released in an upcoming bollywood movie \'n\' our first album \'Nasha\' has been launched by \'sa re ga ma\' ...!!','','http://www.facebook.com/thebandnasha/info','http://www.myspace.com/nashaband','http://soundcloud.com/nasha-the-sufi-band','http://www.reverbnation.com/thebandnasha','0','6202',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','nasha'),(200,0,29,29,'Five Little Indians','Five Little Indians (FLI) was formed in January 2007. The band merges melodic rock and a heavier sound with singer-songwriter sensibilities. The bands use of Hindustani Classical vocals as another voice  and not as a fusion ploy  results in a soundscape that can only be defined as its own.\r\nFLI played its debut show at the Eastwind Festival \'08. Since then, the band has gone on to be featured in Stupidditties 2, a compilation of Indian \"un-metal\" music from ennui.BOMB , supported by Counter Culture Records.\r\nFLI, along with Bertie Da Silva and The Supersonics, organised the first chapter of Elektrik Kool Rock Revue in May 2009, a platform for original music. \r\nThe band headlined the Autumn Festival 2009 at Shillong and then the prestigious Hornbill Festival in Kisama, Kohima, Nagaland. In February 2010, FLI supported pop superstar Richard Marx at Rock\'N\'India, Bangalore, along with Swarathma, Jaycee Lewis and Prime Circle from South Africa. FLI also played the Greenpeace Earth Day Fest in May 2010. \r\nThe band also created the soundtrack and background to director Q\'s underground/extreme film Gandu. \r\nFive Little Indians is currently working on its debut album.  ','fivelittleindians@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Five-Little-Indians/7825836655?ref=ts&sk=info','http://fivelittleindians.com/ ','','','0','6173',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','five-little-indians')