re Rock! \r\nWe kicked off in the college dumpster way back in 2006; and from then it has been a good trip. The first, virgin hit was for ECHO-a charity event hosted by Mallya Aditi school at Guru Nanak Bhavan. At Dayanand Sagar College of engineering was the first win for the band. From then we have gathered quite a lot on our platter.\r\n\r\nThe band bagged the Regional winner\'s title of Campus Rock Idols 07-08 and toured with Kingfisher across the country performing gigs in cities like, Bangalore, Pune, Chennai, Hyderabad, Cochin, Calcutta etc.\r\nThe band has also had 2 consecutive wins at Whiplash \'07 and \'08(BMSCE), Hellraiser \'08 and \'09(IIML), Unmad \'08 and \'09 (IIMB), Spandan \'07 (JIPMER).\r\nThe list goes a little longer, but skipping that to the influences, bands, people, friends and all those things living and non-living that have kept us going in this journey.\r\n\r\nFrom Pink Floyd to Tool this is the spectrum of our influences. Our parents and well wishers have only added more to what we have. Our one aim, make music which even the pan walla can headbang too! Keep it catchy and keep it fresh!\r\n\r\nWe have a few tracks scratch recorded give them a listen here, http://www.myspace.com/illuminatibangalore, but we are aiming for a full release soon, for that info you will have to follow us on facebook, https://www.facebook.com/IlluminatiIndia.\r\n\r\nWith Ravish on guitars, Shubho on bass, Yadhu on Drums, Sid on keys and Venky on vocals, the sound from here is only gonna get heavier.\r\nDescription\r\nWe started out as a college band a few years ago. I think 6 years, I am not sure. We play music that does get you off your seats. Stuff from the 60\'s - present. Rock is our broader genre. We love to listen to all sorts of music, genre no bar. \r\nYou wanna know more about us then you should stick on this page and come for our gig.','','http://www.facebook.com/IlluminatiIndia/info','http://www.illuminati.co.in','','','0','5962',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','illuminati'),(205,0,77,77,'Now, Now','Threads  the second full-length release from Minneapolis based Now, Now  explores the fragile and often\r\ntransitory nature of our existence, our perceived understanding of the world around us and relationships shared\r\nwith others physically and emotionally. Produced by Howard Redekopp (Tegan and Sara, An Horse, New\r\nPornographers), Threads forms a sprawling sonic endeavor that showcases the bands incredible growth as\r\nsongwriters and musicians. Vulnerable vocals give way to oceans of sound retaining definition via deftly layered\r\nguitar parts augmented by lingering synths which alternate between background and center stage.\r\n\r\nThis past June, Now, Now, a trio composed of Cacie Dalager (Vocals, Guitar), Jess Abbot (Vocals, Guitar), and\r\nBrad Hale (Drums, Synth) packed up their van and drove 1800 miles across North America to record with Redekopp\r\nin Vancouver, BC. Beyond the geographical shift, the recording felt miles removed from their full-length debut\r\nCars. Released in 2008 prior to Abbot joining the band, Cars saw the fresh out of High School Dalager and Hale\r\ntraveling the United States non-stop and finding their way onto European arena tours. Through word of mouth and\r\nconstant touring, Now, Now (formerly Now, Now Every Children) began building a support system of fans and\r\nfriends, including Maine native, Abbot. Hale and Dalager quickly became fans of the music Abbot was making\r\nin other bands; It was kind of funny because she and I used to make jokes about how in an alternate universe we\r\nwould probably be in a band together,\" recalls Dalager. We had a practice where she played for us the parts she\r\nhad written for songs off Cars, recalls Hale. It was apparent from those sessions Abbot could bring something to\r\nNow, Now. Her guitar work is amazing, says Dalager, and just adding another creative brain into the mix was\r\nrefreshing for us.\r\n\r\nSoon enough, Abbot relocated to the Twin Cities to become the third member of Now, Now Every Children, sharing\r\nequally in songwriting and vocal contributions. Dropping Every Children from their name, Now, Now began\r\nworking on the Neighbors EP, an experiment in writing and recording for the first time as a three piece. Though\r\nthe original plan was to self-release the EP, it found a home at No Sleep Records, who encouraged the band to tour\r\nthrough the first half of 2011.\r\n\r\nIt was during this time another relationship formed during the years following Cars began to grow. Chris Walla,\r\nguitarist/producer of Death Cab for Cutie, had taken an interest in the bands music. From the very first time we\r\nhad contact with him, explains Hale, he was always excited and positive about things. Support from an artist\r\nthey admired musically and personally proved inspiring to Now, Now. At SXSW 2011 Walla came to each of their\r\nshows, helped them lug gear and even talked a police officer out of giving them a parking ticket. With mutual\r\nadmiration all around, it was natural for Now, Now to sign to Wallas Trans- Records. In working with Chris and\r\nhis label, explains Abbot, weve been given a lot of freedom to make sure were happy with the music. We run at\r\na slower place as a band, and hes not pushed us, but instead given us our time. Its nice to have that from somebody\r\nwho could probably sign any number of bands, and make them do what he wants.\r\n\r\nWith a true sense of purpose and excitement they hadnt felt in years, Now, Now made the trip to meet with\r\nRedekopp to record Threads. What people will specifically notice about the songs on Threads, says Hale, is the\r\nway that they are put together. We spent a lot of time going through the basic song ideas and restructuring them to\r\nmake them their best. Since we haven\'t released a full-length in so long,\" he explains, \"we wanted to make sure we\r\nwere all loving everything about it before we went all the way out there to record. Between recording and tracking\r\nat three studios in Vancouver, the band would hang out with Redekopp at his house or watch him hit the half pipe at\r\na local skate park. He became an extended member of the band; explains Dalager, he got inside our heads and\r\nunderstood everything we were going for. During the recording Now, Now could tell they were hitting their stride\r\nfor the first time. As happy as we are with Neighbors, Abbot says, a lot of things didnt click because we were\r\njust learning how to write together. Dalager notes, We killed ourselves over Threads. That sounds dramatic, but\r\neverything about it was excruciating in a good way. Every little idea was worked to its best. As a result, this is the\r\nfirst release we feel really proud of.\r\n\r\nWith the album complete, Now, Now look to the future with great anticipation. This band feels like an extension\r\nof us as people, explains Dalager. Its something weve been nurturing for a long time and is all we really care\r\nabout;something weve worked really hard for and need to make happen no matter what.','Chris Vinyard at Big Hassle Media','http://www.facebook.com/NowNowMusic/info','http://nownowband.com','http://soundcloud.com/now-now','','0','5944',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','now-now'),(206,0,3,3,'Galeej Gurus','The Galeej Gurus are a band that believes in exploring music and also to have as much fun as possible doing it. \r\n\r\nThey have been on the circuit since 2000 & played over 500 gigs within & outside the country.\r\n\r\nAfter over nine years of touring and performing, the Galeej Gurus are working towards the release of their debut album in 2010. \r\n\r\nThe Galeej Gurus, in 2008, won SHAMAL - Dubais very \r\nown International Battle of the Bands and performed at the Dubai Desert Rock Festival (Asias Largest Music Festival) alongside Velvet Revolver, Muse, Korn, Machinehead, Killswitch Engage, As I Lay Dying & Slapshock. \r\n\r\nIn India, the Galeej Gurus have also opened for legendary rockers such as MR. BIG & Deep Purple.\r\n\r\n\r\nKEY ACHIEVEMENTS  \r\n- In March 2010, the Rolling Stone magazine featured the Galeej Gurus as one of Indias Hottest Bands.\r\n\r\n- The Galeej Gurus opened for the legendary rock band MR. BIG on October 10, 2009 in Bangalore.\r\n\r\n- Galeej Gurus were recently placed amongst the Top 12 bands, out of 100s of bands that competed for Spin Earths Free The Noise Competition 2009, which was an International search for the next big Rock band.\r\n  \r\n- The Galeej Gurus opened for both days of the Dubai Desert Rock Festival (DDRF) held on March 7 &  8, 2008, alongside Velvet Revolver, Muse, Korn, Machinehead, Killswitch Engage, As I Lay Dying & Slapshock.\r\n\r\n- In March 2008, The Galeej Gurus participated & won Shamal   Dubais very own International Battle of the Bands. Amidst stiff competition with bands from Egypt, Syria, Iran, Nigeria, Lebanon, Saudi Arabia to name a few, the Gurus  emerged victorious and earned themselves the  opening slot at the prestigious  DDRF. \r\n\r\n- The Galeej Gurus also performed at the Eastwind Music Festival at Delhi  in February 2008 with the best Indian bands from across the country.\r\n\r\n- In 2006 The Galeej Gurus opened for Classic rock legends - Deep Purple in Bangalore for a crowd of 15,000. \r\n\r\n- The Galeej Gurus were the headlining act for  The Campus Rock Idols, South Zone  in 2006 & 2007, the most popular national talent search competition in India .\r\n\r\n- They also played alongside The Rasmus in 2005.\r\n\r\n- The Galeej Gurus were a part of the warm \r\nup concerts leading up to the Bryan Adams concert in 2004. \r\n\r\n\r\nSTRATEGIC PARTNERS:\r\nGIBSON: Gibson strongly believes in the bands talent and growth & in 2008 signed the Galeej Gurus to an Exclusive Artist deal.  The band will now have access to Gibson instruments for all live shows and performances.\r\n\r\nAKG: In July 2009, AKG (A Harman International Company) also tied up with the Galeej Gurus. The band will now endorse AKG products exclusively, specifically microphones, headphones, in-ear monitor systems and wireless microphone systems.','','http://www.facebook.com/galeejgurus/info','','','','0','5855',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','galeej-gurus'),(208,0,22,22,'Indian Metalheads','This page is officially created to promote Indian Metalheads scene/bands.Show people who we are and what we do.\r\nAll bands are welcome to post information about themselves and update their fans about their upcoming gigs.\r\nLet it be small or Big . All bands are also welcome to post links to their music pages for downloads!\r\n\\m/ Do Help Us in Promoting Indian Metal scene \\m/','','http://www.facebook.com/IndianMetalheads/info','','','http://www.reverbnation.com/indianmetalheads','0','5797',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','indian-metalheads'),(209,0,1,1,'CHRONIC XORN','The saying goes: something has to change for everything to stay as it was - and this is justified in the arena of music as well. Its visible foothold emboldens us to think that a new trend is setting in - something is really getting changed and everything else driven by emotion remains unchanged!\nGreat on stage, they dared to express their emotion in one of its acknowledged forms - Inveterate anger thats where the band derives its name from, and having seen them, it can be said that they are mutually exclusive and collectively explosive. \n\nThere is a dearth of metal bands all around us but the bands which stand out are the bands who are prepared to take that extra effort, and are thus able to go that extra mile.\nCHRONIC XORN is one of those bands who believe in the philosophy of giving in that hard work and making an effort to go for that extra mile!\nWith this belief and desire to become one of the eminences of Metalcore, Chronic Xorn began its journey in 2007 and has traveled a long way with numerous obstacles and is prepared to take on any thing that comes its way! \nThe name of the band characterizes the negative side of the human emotion which is often portrayed by many. The band strongly believes that to tackle any hurdle in life, one has to have that zeal to make it through and has to persist with the same in order to make things work out.\nDuring the journey, the band has learnt that living is not the same thing as making a life and while shaping themselves for the showdown they drew the required inspiration from metalcore and melodic death metal bands like All That Remains, Heaven Shall Burn, The Black Dahlia Murder, As I Lay Dying, Lamb of God, Killswitch Engage, Devil driver and likes. All may not be mentioned but none is nonetheless forgotten!\nChronic Xorn is presently working on its first EP  Death.Destruction.Sermon which is currently at the pre-production stage. It is expected that the EP will hit the market in the first week of May. The band has always strived for true and honest music which comes with originality and through years of dedication. The only thing constant for the band is change itself, from a spark, to a meteor, to an undying fire ball, CHRONIC XORN evolves everyday; the fans keep the zeal burning!!\n','Angshuman Majumder: +91-98300613944','http://www.facebook.com/chronicxorn','','','','319590608637','5751',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','chronic-xorn'),(210,0,10,10,'Ayurveda','Ayurveda means \"the science or knowledge of life\" in sanskrit.  It\'s not only our name, but also at the core of our message.  We are a collection of people from all over the world.  Diwas is from Nepal, Shikhar is first generation Nepali-American from Maine, Dan is from  Massachusetts, Mike is from upstate New York, and I (Tom) am from way out west in Arizona, where wild fires and religious zealotry come from.  We all met in Ithaca, NY where we currently live.  All of us, with the exception of Mike, went to Ithaca College - two of us graduated.\r\n\r\nSo there you go - the basics and shit. \r\n\r\nIf you\'d like to know more about us, just send us a message!  We love (most) people.  And we love to hear feedback - or just a howdy works too.  \r\n\r\nWe do have different content all over the web, if you like what you hear/see.  We\'ve concentrated most of our super powers on a few select sites that are updated the most frequently.  Obviously here on Facebook, but in addition I would recommend checking us out on Myspace, Youtube, and ayurvedamusic.com.\r\n\r\nNamaste, hope you are happy and healthy at the moment of reading this and at every moment there after...\r\n\r\nTom','andy@adelewitz.com','http://www.facebook.com/ayurvedamusic/info?ref=ts','http://ayurvedamusic.com','','','0','5668',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ayurveda'),(211,0,2,29,'Adrija Gupta',' Adrija Gupta, September 4,1994 born, only girl child to a musician father, grew into a musical environment. Passed out from Trinity College Of Music, London, specialized in classical guitar, sings from the age of 4...','','http://www.facebook.com/adrijaguptaofficial/info','','http://soundcloud.com/user760623','http://www.reverbnation.com/adrijagupta','0','5608',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','adrija-gupta'),(212,0,52,52,'Acrimony','For some it may be the music, for many it may be the by-products. But we had inhaled enough war gas to burn our innocent selves & feel wretched enough not to care about all that. You close your eyes & try to breathe some fresh air, & all you can smell is reminiscence of the number of times you choked within the endless yet widening gap between people; the times they shook hands with you, hugged you, kissed you, then scarred your face & bruised your heart; the times you were forsaken without a reason & you could only see question marks as far as you could see; the times your father would look at you, say nothing, but those wink-less eyes would convey how disappointed he was in you; the times your parents would cheat on each other right in front of you & you had to act that you were miniature enough not to be able to put together the puzzle & figure them out; the times you hated being yourself & the times you hated the world; the times you\'d see them bay each other\'s blood in the name of their belief, & you knew how stupid they were being still you could only stand & watch them batter humanity; the times you saw them twinge & twist & play around with the balance in nature & suddenly felt you do actually care, & then calamity struck & paid them back tenfold, & you felt cold as you knew they deserved this! \r\n\r\nNothing lasts forever, and there were purple patches too, but then again, nothing lasts forever.\r\n\r\nSo, we came together because of the one term for all of this, \"Acrimony\".\r\n\r\nFoundation Day ->\r\nMarch 8, 2008 (Founder - Gaurav Khanna & Arjun Singh Jarial)\r\n\r\nBreak through - >\r\nAcrimony released  a couple of promo tracks [\"EP Teaser\" & \"Dark & Blissful\"] followed by the debut EP release on December 21, 2011.\r\nThe EP, named \"False Vacuum\", can be accessed at the following link:\r\nhttp://acrimony.bandcamp.com/album/ep-false-vacuum\r\n\r\nCurrent line-up ->\r\n1. Dhairya Anand - Lead Vocals (February 2011 to present)\r\n2. Abhilab Das - Rhtyhm Guitars (March 2012 to present)\r\n3. Sana Khan - Rhythm Guitars (March 2012 to present)\r\n4. Gaurav Khanna (co-founder) - Drums (March 2008 to present)\r\n5. Yash Vasaniya - Bass (March 2008 to present)\r\n6. Samar Mehdi - Lead Guitars, Vocals & Keys (March 2008 to present)\r\n\r\nEx-members ->\r\n1. Arjun Singh Jarial (co-founder) (March 2008 - Nov 2011) - Lead Vocals, Rhythm Guitars\r\n2. Lakshya Nair (March 2008 - July 2009) - Rhythm Guitars\r\n3. Om Bahadur Thapa (Feb 2010 - May 2010) - Rhythm Guitars\r\n\r\nThe Member Bio (Current Line-up : as in March 2012) ->\r\n>Dhairya Anand - Lead Vocals (