 present)\r\nBirthday: August 29, 1993\r\nAge: 18\r\nHometown: Bhopal\r\nCurrent City: Hyderabad\r\nPreferences: Hard Rock, Classic Rock, Heavy Metal, Alternative Metal, Progressive Rock, Experimental\r\n*Top Attributes: Promising talent, Extremely persevering, Focused, Determined\r\n\r\nMaterial Achievements ->\r\n>Headlining Act at\r\n1. War of Bands, Manthan 2010, PIMR, Indore\r\n2. Aarmabh 2.0 (2011), SATM, Indore\r\n \r\n>Winners at\r\n1. S\'fiesta 2010, Sistec, Bhopal\r\n2. War of Bands, Frisson 2010, Amity Institute, Indore\r\n3. Xplod Battle of Bands 2010, Bhopal\r\n4. Corna-Aurora 2011, IIITM, Gwalior\r\n5. RocKombat 2011, VITS, Indore\r\n6. Battle of Bands, Distortion 2012, IIM Indore\r\n7. War of Strings 2012, IET-DAVV, Indore\r\n\r\n>Runners up at\r\n1. S\'fiesta 2009, Sistec, Bhopal\r\n2. Euphony 2010, MITS, Indore\r\n\r\n>Other valuable gigs played\r\n*Played at HARD ROCK CAFE Pune, as a part of \"Hard Rock Rising 2012\"\r\n*Finalist at Rocktaves 2010, BITS Pilani, Pilani\r\n*Finalist at Chaos Carnivals, Neev 2010, SCMHRD Pune\r\n\r\n>Specials\r\nA) Featured in national level compilations\r\n1. Indicore MixTape India Vol.4 - Track (Demo): Smash \'em Good\r\nhttp://www.indicore.com/downloads/?id=MixTape+INDIA-Volume+4\r\n\r\n2. Unholy Maunder Indian Rock Vol.1 - Track (Demo): Showdown\r\nhttp://1.bp.blogspot.com/-aeDwp-DaZZs/Tk-u2vB_kgI/AAAAAAAAALM/RvIKJhnIheA/s1600/Indian+Bands.jpg\r\n\r\nB) Interviewed by Indian Music Mug\r\nhttp://www.indianmusicmug.com/2011/01/interview-with-progressive-metal-band.html#more\r\n\r\nC) Rated #2 (all India) in WORMEFEST\'11 Round1 Scores that had a total of 92 participant bands from all over India, on the basis of demo tracks (Showdown & We All Deserve to Die).\r\nhttps://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=284091031617307&set=a.284089961617414.85420.222554064437671&type=3&theater\r\n\r\nD) Debut EP \"False Vacuum\" rated #3 in INDIANROCKMP3\'s list of \"Best of 2011 - Top 5 Metal EPs\", despite its release occuring just 9 days from the end of the year\r\nhttp://indianrockmp3.com/2011/12/29/best-of-2011-top-5-metal-eps\r\n\r\nE) Interviewed by INDIANROCKMP3\r\nhttp://indianrockmp3.com/2012/01/07/acrimony-bhopal-interview','Dhairya Anand [91-9713357911] [acrimony.india@gmail.com]','http://www.facebook.com/acrimonyindia/info','http://acrimony.bandcamp.com','http://soundcloud.com/acrimonyindia','','0','5596',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','acrimony'),(213,0,2,2,'BANDISH PROJEKT','Today, Bandish projekt is a solo effort and a new wav from Indian electronic music continent . As chaotic as it is calm. Infused with the right amount of classical. Maddened by the right content of frenzy. An experiment in sound. An evolution in music. A phenomenon that will force you to sit up and take notice. It is about the music of sound.\r\n\r\nBANDISH PROJEKT NEWS +Updates\r\n\r\n1) Bandish Projekt Ep - I am not alone.\r\n\r\n2) Bandish projekt album Correkt Remix. \r\n\r\n3)  Next studio album Connekt \r\n\r\n\r\n','info@bandishprojekt.com','http://www.facebook.com/bandishprojekt/info','http://www.bandishprojekt.com','http://soundcloud.com/bandishprojekt','','0','5589',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','bandish-projekt'),(214,0,78,78,'Pink Noise','::Pink Noise!::\r\nFernanda Martins & Candy Cox on 4 decks\r\n\r\nAny hardtechno lover already heard about Fernanda Martins (www.djfernandamartins.com) and Candy Cox (www.djcandycox.com). \r\n\r\nSeparately, these two Brazilian djanes won the floors around the globe for their unique technique, charisma and excellent music. \r\n\r\nNow they join forces on their new project to provide the public a delightful and powerful musical and visual spectacle: \r\nPiNK NOISE! - The only Female HardTechno Duo in 4 decks!!!!','press@cubbo.net','http://www.facebook.com/pinknoisetechno/info','','','','0','5572',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','pink-noise'),(215,0,1,1,'Trilok Gurtu','\"Trilok Gurtu was born into a highly musical family in Bombay, India where his grandfather was a noted Sitar player and his mother Shobha Gurtu, a classical singing star and constant influence. He began to play practically from infancy at the age of six. Eventually Trilok traveled to Europe, joining up with trumpeter Don Cherry (father of Neneh and Eagle Eye) for two years; touring worldwide with Oregon, the highly respected jazz group and was an important part of the quartet that L. Shankar led with Jan Garbarek and Zakir Hussain.\" -  www.trilokgurtu.net','Mintaka Music Ltd','http://www.facebook.com/trilokgurtu','','','','46012193911','5527',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','trilok-gurtu'),(216,0,22,22,'Albatross','Albatross is a band which combines bone chilling stories with bone crushing metal. The band started out as the solo project of bassist Riju Dasgupta(Workshop, Old Monks), who wanted to marry his love of literature with his other love- metal. Later on, a lineup of like-minded musicians was standardised and hence Albatross was born. The band released the critically acclaimed \'Dinner is You\', a concept EP about cannibalism and the Kuru disease, which was mastered by Grammy nominated Swedish producer Andy LaRocque from King Diamond, in September 2010. The band supported Dubai Nervecell on a 2 city India tour soon after. The current Albatross lineup has already started work on their next album, which promises to bring a new dose of fear into your lives. So be scared...be very scared. We could be in your closests as we speak...with a knife...dripping blood.','rdore2000@gmail.com, ','http://www.facebook.com/albatrossindia/info','','','','0','73381',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','albatross'),(217,4,1,1,'Dualist Inquiry','Dualist Inquiry is the brainchild and solo project of Sahej Bakshi, a producer, guitarist and cerebral agent who graduated from the Thornton Music School at USC in Los Angeles, CA.\r\n\r\nSince returning to Delhi in March 2010, Sahej has been touring India extensively, in addition to being selected to perform at Berlin Music Week in Sept 2010. Additionally, he was ranked #1 nationally in the Burn Sasha Tour remix competition (2010) and was the 2nd Runner Up in the MTV Submerge Ultimate Pro DJ Championship 2010, held at Blue Frog in Mumbai. He was featured in Platform Magazine\'s Music special, in the list of \'6 new acts not to miss\', in addition to being featured in Timeout Delhi, Food & Nightlife, Delhi Times, MTV Noise Factory and HT City, among others. Most recently, Dualist Inquiry performed at The Great Escape Festival in Brighton UK, opening for international sensation Beardyman and hip-hop legend DJ Shadow at the world famous Brighton Dome.','dualistinquiry@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/dualistinquiry/info','http://www.dualistinquiry.com/','http://soundcloud.com/dualistinquiry','','0','5515',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 16:43:01',275,'[\"dualistinquiry@gmail.com\\r\",\"\\r\",\"nihaal@oml.in\"]','[\"BOOKING and MANAGEMENT I Nihaal Poonja +91 9920585595\"]','dualist-inquiry'),(218,2,2,2,'Amogh Symphony/Vishal J. Singh','\"Consisting of Vishal J. Singh (guitars, programming, mixing) and Jim Drumblast Richman (percussion), Amogh Symphony is a progressive metal project formed in 2004. The EP Ashwamedh was released in 2005 in the UK under Kollosal (now defunct) and was distributed in limited copies for reviews. The EP was recognized for influences in its unique progressive metal sound, ranging from eastern music to jazz, and gathered a positive reception from listeners and reviewers. Within 4 years of existence of this project and mayhem in the underground circuit of Asian metal, Vishal inspired a whole new generation of Progressive/Technical metal bands not just in his country India but United States, many European countries and Asian regions like Japan and Indonesia. Reports and evidences clearly indicates that Amogh Symphony is one of the pioneer of Technical Metal movement in India. Some other reputed Indian metal bands who changed their sound to more technical and experimental side are Infernal Wrath and Undying Inc. North-east part of India is growing up giving birth to a bunch progressive and technical metal bands and solo artists in the last 2 years.\r\n\r\n\r\nVishal, born in April 1986, is a multi-instrumentalist, composer and producer based in Bombay, India. Vishal began his career in music as a Drummer-cum-percussionist. He started playing the guitar at the age of 11 and drums at the age of 13. Vishal belongs from a musical family with both his parents are musicians. Born of a Guitarist Father and a Classical singer/dancer mother, Vishal grew up in a family of music where he taught himself how to play and write music. Initially, his elder brother Vikram J.Singh(who is now a software corporate) taught him how to play the guitar. He moved to Mumbai from his hometown Duliajan(Assam) to pursue a carrier as session guitarist and composer. Vishal, now, apart from his project Amogh Symphony, composes music for big brand TV commercials, Radio jingles and also produces International as well as Indian bands and artists. His projects includes some of the most niche and experimental artists and bands across the Globe with an intention to produce a unique record. Some of his main influences were Al Dimeola, Paco De Lucia, Gene Hoglan, Death, Gorguts, Ozric Tentacles, Tony Macalpine, Shawn Lane, Chick Correa, Prodigy, Yngwie Malmsteen, Stevie Ray Vaughan and so on.\r\n\r\n\r\nAbout Drummer Jim Richman. It all started when young Jim got a snare drum kit at age 4 after seeing Elvis Presley\'s drummer on TV. At 14, Jim bought a drumset and the next day started playing in a cover high school band with his twin brother George Richman. \r\n\r\nJim played in Malefice and recorded 7 songs to be found on the Lotus Blossum LP on Lost and Found Records. He also went to VA Tech and studied Jazz with the late Joe Kennedy Jr. Jim also attended Drummers Collective in NYC, hooking up with Pete Zeldman, Frank Katz, Mike Clarke and many others and studied with Jim Chapin, Joe Morello and Gary Chaffee.\r\n\r\nBeing as Jim was very serious in drums, he wanted to study them with the masters. After College, Jim played in many different groups and  recorded an EP with Dizzy Dizzy, featuring members of Government Issue and 76% Uncertain. But soon he decided to quit that band to join a Variety Wedding band and played the Nascar Circuit in many Holiday Inns. He played in various groups, opening for Angela Bofil, Joan Jett, the Meat Puppets. \r\n\r\nThe technical metal/fusion journey started with Modulus. He formed Modulus and played as a two man project, initially. They recorded the Prototype EP, engineered mixed and mastered by Jim Richman himself. Modulus opened for many top extreme metal acts at the legendary Jaxx Nightclub for a few years before the band fell apart. \r\nJim also recorded a couple of tribute tracks with Aurora Borealis released on Dwell Records. He is a fulltime Drum Teacher for almost 15 years. Now, Jim devotes his time to his family, job, Amogh Symphony, Hypnorock, and sub for a variety of gigs as Session Drummer that pay good money. Jim also play keyboards as a composer.\r\n\r\n\r\nAbolishing the Obsolete System, their first full-length album, was released in April 2009. Soon after 5 months of this album\'s release, Jim Richman joined Amogh Symphony as permanent drummer. Their second album, The Quantum Hack Code, was released in 2010, receiving positive attention from critics and non-professional listeners alike. For many critics and reviewers, TQHC is one of the top progressive metal releases of the year 2010 and 2011 as well with it\'s own unique tradmark sound of technical metal.\"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSome reviews from Media about the latest album The Quantum Hack Code : \r\n\r\n\"Todo ello sin que suene forzado, de una manera muy natural y como no, mrito de Vishal, que se erige como un msico realmente despierto y con un talento muy pocas veces visto en este tipo de msica. Todo realizado con mimo y esmero, con mucha elegancia y clase, desde sus guitarras rtmicas, bajo, samplers, baterase incluso la propia produccin del trabajo.\" - Pitchline Zine, Spanish extreme metal webzine\r\n\r\n\"In a time where guitarists/producers seem to be gravitating towards a djenty sound, Vishal avoids chug like the plague, instead opting for virtuosity and picking and choosing genre styles to his liking through experimentation and soloing. After you finish listening to The Quantum Hack Code, youll be thinking, Tosin Abasi, who? \" - Heavy Blog is Heavy\r\n\r\n\"Vishal is a mad scientist and that will be understood after a few listens. I am reviewing the album as a whole epic song because that\'s how concept albums should be treated and rated. With most modern technical bands jumping on the Djent train as their musical direction, Vishal avoids it and formed his own melting pot of various techniques and styles that will no doubt get him the virtuosic recognition he and Amogh Symphony more than deserve. The mastering done on this album needs to be commended. Aditya Naik has succeeded in not making this album sound like a trashcan being shoved into your eardrum with glass shards. While most modern metal albums feature brick wall mastering and usually end up being clipped, this album has a user-friendly sound that lets the user mould it to how he or she likes music.\" - Metal Assault\r\n\r\n\r\n\"At its heart, The Quantum Hack Code is a defiantly adventurous ride, throwing at the listener every manner of complex and varied instrumental music spanning multiple genres, coupled with dextrous and versatile percussion, in a format that might not be immediately digestible. In fact, it\'s almost an understatement to say this album is a challenging listen, demanding complete attention, an ear for detail and a tolerance for a wide spectrum of styles. The instrumental performances on display are faultless, Singh effortlessly switching between frenzied, jagged riffing and silky funk vamps with remarkable ease, accompanied by Richman\'s intricate yet tasteful drum work. The inherent penchant for diversity and eclecticism makes The Quantum Hack Code far and away the most colourful and fresh album I\'ve heard this year. \"  - Sea of Traquility\r\n\r\n\r\n\"It is not an easy album to get into and requires multiple listens to fully digest all aspects of it. \" - Indianrockmp3\r\n\r\n\"Its a very, very dense piece of work, and as such can be a bit overwhelming at first, like all great technical metal albums. Its definitely not the sort of album you can just jump right into, but the real reward here is listening to the album multiple times so as to absorb the various elements at play here.\" - The Number of The Blog/Fucking Metal Reviews\r\n\r\n\"This is one album you need to listen to and when you do, youll realize that Vishal Singh does not need any form of mindless, shameless promotion for his music or infact even reviews such as this for he has now established himself as no less than a genius atleast in the eyes of people who know and understand music.\" - Demrockritic\r\n\r\n\"Rapid tempo and key changes at the drop of a hat, transitions from futuristic metal groove and mind-bending guitar solos to Spanish folk with surgical precision, all leave one thinking about how far weve really come. This is a true melting pot of modern musical genius, equal parts abrasive and melancholy, performed and produced by men who are at the absolute peak of their prowess. \" - Underground.in / Keshav Dhar a.k.a Skyharbor\r\n\r\n\r\n\"This album gives it all  progressive, jazz, funk, blues, flamenco, tech-death, classical, even trance. Vishal Singhs music has evolved to the point where it took me 8 listens to be even vaguely confident about writing a review. But that does not imply it being a blatant display of virtuosity and technical prowess. The slower passages accentuate the dystopian feel that this album tries to get across quite succinctly, and the last track The Collapse of Q-Web And Osiris portrays the revival of humanity exceedingly well.\" - Headbangers India\r\n\r\n\"Geek/Nerd metal for the masses with an open mind.  That is the best way to describe the sophomore effort from the 1 man band Amogh Symphony.  Vishaljit Singh has surely stated his case for being the best solo project in the metal these days based on the superb album Quantum Hack Code.  Quantum Hack Code has extremely impressive sound, PLENTY of different genres, plenty of technicality to the musicianship, multitudes of changes throughout the songs and a concept/theme to the entire album.\" - RYM\r\n\r\n\"Quantum Hack Code CD music None of the songs on the album are similar to another. Everything from fast tempos, groovy rythms, great guitar solos and precise vocals. The music is basically based on guitar riffs, so if that is what you\'re looking for you ...\" - CD Universe\r\n\r\n\r\n\"Sometimes its like Christopher Nolan joined hands with Devin Townsend to make history. Personally, i think it could be the soundtrack of Matrix. This album is a fuel for musical intelligence and creative thoughts for any music loving brain. I highly recommend this album to Engineeringand PhD Students. Solve your problems with this record on, you will be posessed by Einsteins ghost.\" - Groovy Djenty Blog/14all-all41\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\"Future is here. \" - Got-Djent\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSome reviews from Media about the last album Abolishing the obsolete system : \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nA dense mash of genres  theres everything from electronica to jazz to technical death metal here  the sounds on the album weave impossible structures with masterly musicianship. Amogh Symphonys raised the bar for experimental metal in the country to heights that other bands can only hope to aspire towards.  Rolling Stone, India \r\n\r\nAbolishing the obsolete system is an extremely diverse album. It features many aspects of nearly all the genres of music. From hardcore Trance to Technical Death Metal riffs, Vishal J.Singh has it all! The tempo is never constant on this album, meaning it\'s a Progressive Metal album. The album is so unique and unheard before that trying to describe it to you would seem useless. Just give it a try, and embrace the originality behind the songwriting from this multi-faceted Indian 1-man band!   RateYourMusic \r\n\r\nIt is instrumental prog death that alternates between very aggressive and more technical metal to some very nice atmospheric metal.  A few of the tracks certainly have some jazz influence and we also get some very interesting electronica on a couple of tracks and even some \"Indian\" ethnic vocals/sounds added here and there.   RYM\r\n\r\n\"One side - World was tripping on Djent. This side - Metal was never so unique and versatile before. This man is truly a genius.\" - Hazard Noize \r\n\r\nWhat makes the album so different from other acts of this genre is the simple fact that Vishal plays an intricate style of technical Death Metal in the album fusing Jazz elements wonderfully alongside Indian classical music influences as well as techno-synth sounds as heard in tracks like Cyborg Activation and Abolishing The Obsolete System. And its the inclusion of such structures that soon engulfs the listener in a cosmic atmosphere, making him anticipate each track with such a zeal that pretty soon he may find his head banging to the beats of the album.The whole album unquestionably sounds like one great song where every track sounds like a part of a greater track, with every track maintaining it\'s own unique identity. And this is where lies Amogh Symphony\'s beauty. Single masterpieces joining together in greater harmony to form a larger magnum opus. Amogh Symphony pulls off a brilliant masterpiece in his new album without any flaws worth mentioning. The magic Vishal spins with his skills is simply awe-inspiring.  Metalhead Chronicles \r\n\r\nFrom start to finish, this album is just weaving in and out of death metal, techno-ish synth breakdowns, and Indian-styled music infused within one another. Every track fuses within one another, making the whole album feel like one great song, even so with the identical riffage in \"Cyborg Activation\" and \"Swallowing The Infected Sun\" (the only track with vocals on it). Though flowing within one another, the tracks each carry a separate but together identify, making each song different from the last, but carrying identical styles from Vishal that make it feel like one album, not tracks thrown together. Even without the death growling that is a staple for this genre, this whole album carries a death metal vibe, whether weak or strong depending on song, makes this album approachable to anyone who is not familiar (or hates) death metal.   CMK Music Review.\r\n\r\nCambios que te mueven en segundos desde el Death metal ms elaborado y rajao, pasando por interludios acsticos sacados del medio oriente y luego llegando a bases electrnicas acompaadas con guitarra Jazz Lo que hace AMOGH SYMPHONY en su disco debut, se podra catalogar a la rpida como Death Metal Progresivo, pero sera pobre quedarse con eso no ms. La banda te lleva en un viaje csmico lleno de atmsferas logradas gracias al buen uso de bases electrnicas y de ritmos sincopados.  Brutal Zone / Hellcast.  \r\n\r\n??? ???? ?????? ???? ??? ??????? ???????, ???  ??????????? ?? ?????, ?? ? ??????? ???? ???????. ???????? ??????-??????????? ???? - ??????, ??????, ?????? ??? ???? ????????????  ?? ?? ???????? ?? ?????, ????? ??? ???????. ?? ????? ?? ?????? ? ???????? ?? ?????, ????????? Abolishing the Obsolete System. This is \"Abolishing the Obsolete System\" - a product of short glimpses of hidden cameras and bustle of native talent. ???????? ???????? ? ????????? ??????? ?? ???? ??????-??????????? ????, ????? ???? ?? ?????? ?? ????????, ?? ????????? ?????????? ?? ? ?????????? ? ???????????? ?? ????????? ? ???? ???????????? ???????? Amazing detailed and complete picture of a science fiction epic, which makes you think about the past, to appreciate what is happening in the present and also to feel and even foretaste future .- Metal World. \r\n\r\n','amoghsymphony@gmail.com , amogh_311@yahoo.com & drumblast@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/amoghsymphony/info','http://amoghsymphony.bandcamp.com/','http://www.soundcloud.com/amoghsymphony','','0','5438',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 13:18:14',193,'[\"amoghsymphony@gmail.com , amogh_311@yahoo.com & drumblast@gmail.com\"]','[\"\"]','amogh-symphonyvishal-j-singh'),(219,0,1,1,'Guillotine','.. In an age where Indian rock/metal acts have reached a stage no one even dreamt of , very rarely does there stand a band that doesnt thrive on the mainstream success most bands root for. Guillotine is one such band ,low profiled but all about the music .Guillotine\'s one of the very limited progressive acts that India has produced , Progressive melodic death metal, as we call our music is all about combining the different elements of death/extreme metal with melodies ranging from jazz to thrash metal. We started off with the name 1 fret higher ,but with countless line up changes, Guillotine is what we came out with The band has recorded three of their original tracks which are basically a part of a three tier concept of a man\'s realization of the hollowness of religious faith .we only recently recorded our third track Upon My Return which has majorly caught on the Indian metal scene With influences ranging from porcupine tree , tool ,dream theater , opeth, children of bodom etc the band is a definite stand for the varied diversity the Indian metal scene is about. Despite being only a year old the band is one of the talked about band in and around Delhi, with the youngest member being only 15 yrs old Guillotine is definitely here to stay','Karan Nambiar - 9910909822','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Guillotine/17224782605?ref=ts&sk=info','http://www.myspace.com/guillotine0','','','0','5423',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','guillotine'),(220,0,79,79,'DivineConnection','Formed on 31st September 2004. Divine Connection is a multi faceted Band which experiments Rock, Blues, Funk Jazz, Hindi and contemporary Gospel Music.\r\n\r\nDC believes that young people can enjoy life and music without the influence of, Drugs, Sex, Alcohol and Violence. \r\n\r\nDC has earned themselves headlining slots at college fests and major music events and eventually performing alongside international sensations. Divine connection has also performed in Pattaya Thailand. \r\n\r\nWith over hundreds of concerts across the country and even Abroad to their credit and 2 stellar releases, the Self titled EP and a full length Album El-Roi in 2008 both met with stellar reviews from fans and zines across the world, Apart from that Divine Connection as a whole attracting countless laurels: each of the 4 individuals has gradually become a key figure in the music community and won several awards for their outstanding proficiency, Best Guitarist, Bassist and best vocalist awards. A star line-up of experienced musicians with diverse musical interests; this is precisely what gives Divine Connection its soothing shifting flavor. The media have always been kind to Divine Connection: with featured articles in acclaimed Indian Music magazines Rollingstone (Mumbai), RSJ (Rock street journal), and also in countless mainstream newspapers and websites. Theyve been invited for interviews and in-studio performances aired on televisions and Radio.\r\n\r\n\r\nDc has shared stage with bands such as Dub L.F.O (Israel), Too late lucy (U.K) etc... They have also played along with some of the better Indian bands like Parikarma, Raghu Dixit, Pt. Vishwa Mohan Bhatt , Bhayanak Maut, Mother Jane, Mind Snare. DivineConnection has also been privileged to perform with Rahul Ram(Indian Ocean)\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/DivineConnection/338120800190?sk=info','http://www.divineconnectionindia.com','','','0','5398',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','divineconnection'),(221,0,1,1,'Bauchklang','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Bauchklang/113404752003612','','','','113404752003612','5389',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','bauchklang'),(222,0,18,18,'Pangaea','','','http://www.facebook.com/journeytopangaea/info','','http://soundcloud.com/pangaea','','0','5347',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','pangaea'),(223,0,4,4,'Swastik ','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Swastika-The-Band/169425573071911?sk=info','','http://soundcloud.com/swastik-the-band','http://www.reverbnation.com/swastikatheband','0','5339',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','swastik'),(224,0,1,80,'IGNATIUS CAMILO A.K.A IGGYTHEDJ','Creating sound...recognizing sound...predicting sound...comes from your own method... \"Your madness\"\r\n\r\nI learn\'t it with the skill of being flexible and the willingness to be a part of that atmosphere. It started from bagging speakers to a gig and back. \"NOT TO PERFORM BUT TO OBSERVE\" i slowly worked my way through to a place where the observation of the ear has been edited to a singular motion of my fingers...\r\n\r\nI know all of this sounds quite idiotically intense, but the truth is I wrote this in a higher state of consciousness...and u know when u do that it all makes sense. Don\'t get me wrong. I meant the music...\r\n\r\nThis all is very passionate but the truth is thats how I really feel. Just letting my feelings decide Where I play...what I play...how I play... and by this exercise I hope it will all come together resulting into what I make. \r\n\r\nAt this point I need to expand my observation to different parts of the world...playing in the unknown... Having that uncomfortable itch in the ass but always playing with my instinct...\r\n\r\nI\'m one of the very few dj\'s in India pushing the movement of slick underground music and im a treat to a sensitive ear...  See ya ...\r\n\r\n ??? ?\' ?\'\\????\\?=(??)=?/??\'\'\'\'\'\'','iggythedj@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/Iggythedj/info?ref=ts','','http://soundcloud.com/iggythedj','','0','5306',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ignatius-camilo-aka-iggythedj'),(225,0,3,3,'Lounge Piranha','Lounge Piranha is an alternative/post-rock band from Bangalore.','loungepiranha@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/loungepiranha/info','http://www.loungepiranha.in','http://soundcloud.com/loungepiranha','','0','5254',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','lounge-piranha'),(226,2,1,1,'Reggae Rajahs','Reggae Rajahs are India\'s first reggae sound system. The trio composed of Diggy Dang, Mr. Herbalist and DJ MoCity (Iraq\'s first soundboy) are reggae entertainers and promoters based out of New Delhi. They operate in a traditional Jamaican sound system style with one DJ and two MC\'s.\r\n\r\nComing together for their love of reggae music in New Delhi in early 2009, the Rajahs have been introducing the Indian masses to an eclectic mix of roots reggae, dub, lovers rock, ska and dancehall. They frequently perform in New Delhi and have also played in Mumbai, Pune, Bangalore, Chennai, Goa and Manali. International performances in the last 2 years include Peru, Panama and New York City. They were recently nominated for the Best International Group award at the British Reggae Industry Awards (2012) alongside illustrious Jamaican artists such as Toots & the Maytals, Mighty Diamonds and Third World.\r\n\r\nReggae Rajahs have performed with a number of established international artists such as Apache Indian (UK), Mr. Williamz (UK), Brother Culture (UK), Soom T (UK), Mungo\'s HI Fi (UK), Deadly Dragon Sound System (USA), IllBilly Hitec & Longfingah (Germany), Steppa Style (Russia), Blessed Love Sound System (Germany), Graeme Hamilton (ex-UB40), Supa Bassie & Sargento Garcia (Spain), Subatomic Sound (USA) and Heartical Sound (France). \r\n\r\nApart from performing at many of the country\'s top music venues, the Rajahs have also performed at the Holi Cow Festival (Delhi), Escape Festival (Naukuchiatal), Sunburn Festival (Goa) and SulaFest (Nashik). They hosted their own stage at the Bacardi NH7 Weekender 2011 (Pune) called the Pepsi Dubstation which was roaring success and introduced thousands of music lovers to dub based sounds. They are set to tour Europe this summer, having been invited to play at Outlook Festival (Croatia), Europe\'s premier festival celebrating sound system culture and bass heavy music.\r\n\r\nKnown for their energetic live performances, the Rajahs hope to release their first single and music video in 2012. They are dedicated to spreading the positive, conscious message of reggae music across India. The movement is in full effect!\r\n','| Raghav | +9811902478 | reggae.rajahs@gmail.com ','http://www.facebook.com/reggaerajahs/info','http://www.reggaerajahs.com','http://soundcloud.com/reggaerajahs','','0','5246',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 14:56:57',305,'[\"sohail@krunklive.com\\r\",\"\\r\",\"reggae.rajahs@gmail.com\"]','[\"+919820546976\\r\",\"\\r\",\"+9811902478\"]','reggae-rajahs'),(227,0,2,2,'Prayag','It was Independence Day 2002, when two guys who had nothing in common met up in Mumbai.\r\n\r\nPranab had posted an ad about wanting to form a band. Swapnil was there to answer the ad, hoping against hope to find musical resonance.\r\n\r\nThey found a lot in common, eventually. The determination to create rock music that goes beyond imitation. To sing about life as they lived it, not some Westerner on a dark desert highway. To not care about aping the stars, but to express what they felt, in the language they thought in.\r\n\r\nThe first rivers of thought merged  Prayag was formed. With the help of an old friend, Hitesh, a few initial compositions  including the basic structure of the now popular Tejo Mahalaya  were created. A few months later Kiran Roy was invited to record for the band and became the lead guitarist for Prayag along with Pradeep Radhakrishnan on drums. Kiran played a major role in the composition of the song Raaste, which still never fails to rock a live audience.\r\n\r\nPrayag hit the usual bottlenecks. Record companies wanted remixes, not original material. Pradeep vanished into thin air (we still dont know where he is). Differences saw Kiran bid adieu. Swapnil and Pranab were left with an album no one wanted. The inevitable tensions followed. Their determination to do rock music was being tested.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, Viru  who had engineered Prayags initial songs along with Mr Rajesh Ranjan Singh of the erstwhile Throatlatch Records  was invited to try his hand on the drums. And it was clear from the first snare shot that here was a guy with rhythm in his blood.\r\n\r\nA few days later Swapnil came across another online ad, posted by a guitarist wanting to play any kind of music. His name was Sumit. Sounded pretty ordinary. He even looked the sober, workingman type. But all that changed when he strapped his guitar on.\r\n\r\nSwapnil, Pranab and Viru were stunned. Sumit hemmed and hawed at first, but later accepted the invitation to join the band, and suggested taking another guitar player along with him. So in came Pasha, full of life and enthusiasm. The rivers had merged. Prayag was ready to rock. Big time. Right now, the band is recording a few new songs in the studio and winning new fans with every astounding performance.','manager@prayagzone.com','http://www.facebook.com/prayagzone/info','http://www.prayagzone.com','http://soundcloud.com/prayagzone','http://www.reverbnation.com.com/prayag','0','5236',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','prayag'),(228,2,1,1,'Nasya','Nasya is a fusion rock band based in Delhi. Playing a blend of Sufi, Haryanvi and Punjabi Folk and rock influences, they are not your typical fusion band. Their sound is distinctly characteristic, finely balancing traditional hindustani vocals with western elements of jazz, blues and rock music.\r\n\r\nGood music can set the mood right for a good conversation, but great music makes one want to stand up, listen and forget the conversation  and that is exactly what Nasya is best known for.\r\n\r\nThe name Nasya comes from a Hebrew word meaning A miracle of God. And it is indeed quite a miracle that a few talented and skilled individuals from extremely diverse musical backgrounds could come together and in a very short while realize their dream to create and play rousing music while transcending boundaries of influences, genres and stereotypes.\r\n\r\nAfter winning several rock band competitions across Delhi like Jamia Hamdard, PGDAV, Dyal Singh and CVS to name a few, Nasya headlined at colleges like Miranda House and Lady Irwin College in 2009.\r\n\r\nThe hysteria of 2009 paled in comparison with the euphoria of 2010. With corporate shows at Canon and Green Peace and guest performances alongside artistes like Shibani Kashyap and Manak-E. But the best was yet to come in the form of MTV Rock On Season 2 which expanded the bands audience  all over the country.\r\n\r\nAfter their hugely memorable performance at MTV Rock On, Nasya returned home armed with new fans and new members to kick start their 2011 campaign.\r\n\r\nBeing featured twice on SAHARA TVs Cricket World Cup discussion show alongside eminent personalities like Raju Srivastava and Manoj Tiwari was indeed a feather in the cap of Nasya. Combined with great performances alongside the likes of Pakistani group JAL and guest performances at colleges like College of Business Studies, Jamia Milia Islamia, Dyal Singh College, Sri Guru Gobind Singh College of Commerce, NC College of Engineering, ANDC College and many more, 2011 has been a roller coaster ride for the band and their well wishers.\r\n\r\nWith an Album release in 2012, we believe that the best of Nasya is yet to come.\r\n\r\n','(+91-9711415735)','http://www.facebook.com/nasyaband/info','http://www.nasya.co.in','http://soundcloud.com/nasya','','0','5211',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 15:01:29',325,'[\"contact@nasya.co.in\"]','[\"+919717733823; +919971933550\\r\",\"\\r\",\"\"]','nasya'),(229,0,2,2,'Split','Split\'s music is equally about conflict and resolution; a slick construction of wit and drunken wisdom, with rumbling bass and pounding drums that chase edgy guitar riffs and screaming solos right down to a breakdown of nuclear proportions. \r\n\r\nThe themes range from the epic to the mundane; from slimy evangelists to local trains, from revolution to traffic signals, and from existential angst to the eternal favorite  a broken heart. The band is most at home with a steady supply of new ideas, old grouses, and 7-year vatted rum.\r\n\r\n\r\nMilestones  \r\n\r\nSplit has played the pants off festivals like Independence Rock & GIR (Mumbai and Delhi) more than once, not to mention Eastwind &  June Rock Out .They have  also been featured on GIRs Volume X and twice  on India\'s premier Indie Unmetal compilation Stupiditties.\r\nSome of the other notable performances include: \r\n	The Jack Daniel Annual Rock Awards\r\n	IIT - Delhi (Winners) and Bombay (RU). \r\n	Mood Indigo \r\n	Yamaha Roxx\r\n	RSJ Pubrockfest\r\n	Channel V- Launch pad\r\n	Harley Rock Riders (5 city 6 gig tour)\r\n\r\n\r\nSounds like - \r\nRamshackle blues meets rum-soaked rock n roll!  \r\n\r\nLooks like -\r\nA spiritual revival meeting gone wrong.\r\n\r\nFor more on the band, visit \r\nwww.splitsplit.org\r\nwww.myspace.com/splitsplit www.reverbnation.com/splitsplit http://splitspace.blogspot.com\r\n\r\nSplit is managed by SideStand. For bookings please contact Himanshu Vaswani - 9867263038 or mail sidestandmanagement@gmail.com\r\n','Himanshu Vaswani - 9867263038','http://www.facebook.com/splitsplit/info?ref=ts','http://www.splitsplit.org','http://soundcloud.com/splitsplit','','0','5201',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','split'),(230,0,3,3,'Audio Units','If there is one thing you cant blame Ashwin Baburao and Ashrith Baburao  alias Audio Units  its a lack of imagination. At 28 and 21 respectively, the duo already have  years worth of creative experimenting behind them. However, it was only last year that their musical passion culminated into the electronic vibes of Audio Units, creating a sound that melts their influences of house, techno, psy trance with new inspirations that come every ticking minute.\r\n\r\nBegin 2011, the duo signed with their debut release \"Manipulated Axis\" with the mighty Plusquam Recordings under their sub-label Future Lovers. Plusquam Recordings boasts of top artists like Liquid Soul, Sunstryk, Auricular, Ace Ventura and many more to name a few. There next release \"Submerge Supernova\" was picked up by Massive Groove Records.\r\n\r\nSo, whats next for Audio Units? The duo are working hard on designing fresh sounds everyday, that stand unique to their productions. Apart from their work in the studio, DJ Inferno (Ashwin Baburao) has had a reputable DJ career lasting over 8 years having played across the biggest venues & festivals across the country, proving to be versatile DJ  as well. When asking them what 2011 will bring, they answer in an ancient Indian proverb saying: If music be the food of love, play on!  Or was that Shakespeare?\r\n\r\nAudio Units are currently working on a live act to take take things on stage and to the next level, more details on that soon!\r\n\r\nJoin us on this page, we wont spam you with pictures from our studio, mainly because its also our bedroom, but we\'ll open some headroom to sharing tutorials, interacting with other waveforms of producers.\r\n\r\n\r\nDISCOGRAPHY\r\n\r\nJUN 2012 - \"Sample The Example\" EP [3AM RECORDINGS]\r\n\r\nMAY 2012 - \"Fragments of a Feeling\" on VA Open Dialect [QILLA RECORDS]\r\n\r\nFEB 2012 - Portamento EP [PLUSQUAM/VERTIKAL RECORDS]\r\n\r\nFEB 2012 - \"Organik\" on VA Nu:Breeds Vol. 2 [SPRING TUBE/PROTON MUSIC]\r\n\r\nNOV 2011 - Manipulated Axis EP [PLUSQUAM/FUTURE LOVERS]\r\n\r\nJUNE 2011 - Submerge Supernova (Single/Compilation) [MASSIVE GROOVE RECS]\r\n\r\nDEC 2010 - Nadia Ali - Love Story (Audio Units Remix) [Top 5 in Remix Contest]\r\n\r\n\r\nFollow us on Twitter:\r\n\r\nDJ Inferno - www.twitter.com/Inferno_dj\r\nAshrith - www.twitter.com/ashrithmb','audiounitsAU@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/AudioUnits/info','http://www.djnferno.in','http://soundcloud.com/dj-inferno-audio-units','','0','5186',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','audio-units'),(231,0,49,49,'Rudra','The world was introduced to the exotic sounds of Vedic Metal from Singapore in 1998 with the release of the self titled debut album. How ironical that Vedic Metal originated in a tiny island in South East Asia instead of India, the land of Vedic Mysticism and sacrifices. Although the band has been alive since 1992, it was in 1998 that the world finally got a taste of what this legendary outfit had to offer the world of Metal. The debut album was a revolutionary and unprecedented statement in extreme metal at the time. The good production in spite of it being recorded with a shoestring budget and its unique songwriting amazed reviewers around the world. The lyrical theme being the ancient Vedic philosophies made RUDRA really the founders of this genre.\r\n\r\n2001\'s The Aryan Crusade cemented RUDRAs reputation as truly innovative and visionary composers by pushing the boundaries of their previous offering further. Till date many fans around the world consider this album to be definitive Vedic Metal album.  \'The Aryan Crusade\' retained the extreme metal sound along with their exotic sound that had become their trademark and took it to another dimension. \r\n\r\nWith two groundbreaking albums behind them, the band had become a force destined for recognition further outside of the ever evolving metal community. In 2003, they started to put out concept albums and Kurukshetra was released with the theme taken off the famous battle featured in the Indian epic Mahabharata. \'Kurukshetra\' proved that RUDRA can also be fine Death/Black Metal musicians.  \r\n2005 marked another turning point for the band. This time they pushed their craft further by releasing the first of a Trilogy entitled Brahmavidya: Primordial I.  With this album RUDRA was perceived as a band that ever-evolved to become a reality far beyond comprehension. Till date the song The Pathless Path to the Knowable Unknown of this album has become the Anthem of Vedic Metal. \r\n\r\n2009 saw the release of the second chapter of the Brahmavidya trilogy, Brahmavidya: Transcendental I. This was another masterpiece with longer songs and trance inducing interludes. Soon after this release, the band produced an epic video for the song Hymns from the Blazing Chariot which was nominated for an award in the local film industry. \r\n\r\nIn 2010 RUDRA made another breakthrough by incorporating traditional and contemporary dance into their performance. This was staged at the Indian Arts Festival in 2010 with rousing reviews. \r\n\r\nThe phenomenal artistic achievement of a band hidden in the tropical forests of South East Asia has been missed by many but not the musicologists. Several papers have been published about RUDRA and Vedic Metal, making them a band for both metalheads and academics. \r\n\r\n2011 brought the final chapter of the Trilogy entitled Brahmavidya: Immortal I. The band is currently doing a world tour and planning to stage a full length Metal Dance fusion performance.\r\n','imran@apsara-asia.com.sg','http://www.facebook.com/RudraBand/info','http://www.rudraonline.org','','','0','5133',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rudra'),(232,0,81,81,'Lucid Recess','Lucid Recess is an Alternative Metal band from Guwahati, Assam, India formed in April 2004 by brothers Siddharth and Amitabh. Partha Boro joined as their new drummer in 2009. \r\n\r\nTheir music is a blend of Alternative Metal and Rock. Their songs range from both heavy and fast to slow ballads and try to write songs that people can relate to. The elements that can be seen in their songs are catchy choruses, meaningful lyrics, good melodies and memorable hooks. \r\n\r\nLucid Recess released their 7 song EP Carved on 18th December 2007. Lyrics on the EP were about various social issues like Aids (The Maze), Global Warming (End That We Know), Terrorism (The Forever War), Alcohol and Drug abuse (Painstaking Obsession). The song \'If I Could\' from the EP got 3/5 in Rolling Stones India magazine. The video of their song \'Painstaking Obsession\' was released on 26th October 2008.  It was created and directed by Rueban Issac and the cast were postgraduate students in Theatre Studies, The University of Surrey, UK. \r\n\r\nTheir EP \'Carved\', along with a previously unreleased acoustic version of \'Painstaking Obsession\' was distributed with the June 2009 Issue of RSJ magazine. With more than 42,000 copy circulation, the CD with RSJ magazine gave them a huge exposure and a much wider audience. It is now available for free download in their website www.lucidrecess.com.\r\n\r\nSince the release of their EP, they have played in some of the major shows and festivals in India and have played in many places all over India  Delhi, Kolkata, Bangalore, Gurgaon, Gangtok and lots more.\r\n\r\nLucid Recess released their 1st full length album Engraved Invitation under their own label LR Records on 26th April 2010 in India. The album has 12 songs including previously released singles Cant Help Me and Socially Active Warrior. For the first time, the band has also recorded a piano based song Calling for this album.  The album is recorded at Lucid Recess Studios, Guwahati and is produced by Siddharth Barooa. \r\n\r\nOn January 8th 2011, Lucid Recess won the prestigious Toto Awards for Music 2011 held in Bangalore. The Band received a prize amount of Rs. 50,000. Every year since 2005, this award is given to one band in the country.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSome important shows:\r\n\r\n1.	Great Indian Rock 2010 in Delhi with Meshuggah (Sweden) and other Indian Bands. \r\n2.	Great Indian Rock 2008 in Shillong with Sahg (Norway) and other Indian bands.\r\n3.	Headlined in IIT Guwahati Rock O Phoenix 2010 with Eluveitie (Switzerland).\r\n4.	Sikkim Music Fest 2010 with ARSAMES (Iran), X-Mantra (Nepal) etc.\r\n5.	Kingfisher Pub Rock Fest 2010, 2009 and 2008 in Delhi, Gurgaon, Bangalore, Kolkata, Shillong and Guwahati.\r\n6.	Unseen Underground Pub Fest 2010 in Kolkata, Guwahati and Shillong.\r\n7.	Guest Band at Caf Live and Loud, Gangtok (May 2010) where bands like Parikrama, Pentagram, Them Clones, Soul Mate etc have been guest bands before.\r\n8.	Fireball Vol. II 2010 in Guwahati with Bhayanak Maut, East India Company etc.\r\n9.	Fireball Vo. I 2008 in Guwahati with III Sovereign, Alien Gods etc.\r\n10.	Headlined in numerous colleges  and festivals in Assam.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPress Comments \r\n\r\n\"this band has released one of the clearest, cleanest and most sharply produced CD I\'ve ever heard\"   \"the vocals are harmonized well without a trace of any accent. Each track is sung well and superbly crisp\"\r\n-	Rock Society Magazine UK, Aug/Sept 2010 issue (On their album Engraved Invitation):\r\n\r\n\"..this young trio have nailed the glossy thump of 90s alternative rock for the first time out; this sounds huge and confident and full of energy, deftly mirroring the moody post-Nirvana era with surging riffs and lashings of angsty melodrama..\"\r\n-	Classic Rock Magazine UK, Sept 2010 Issue (On their album Engraved Invitation):\r\n\r\n\"..In Engraved Invitation, Lucid Recess have managed to create a well thought out album that seamlessly alternative metal and rock to create something that is melancholically tuneful. Rating - 7/10\r\n-	 Powerplay Magazine UK, Sept 2010 Issue (On their album Engraved Invitation):\r\n\r\n\r\n\"..This band have self-produced the rock album that Radiohead could have made - it comes up trumps on all fronts...\"\r\n-	www.uberrock.co.uk (On their album Engraved Invitation):\r\n\r\n\r\nA successful debut album - 5.5/7 \r\n-	www.hardharderheavy.de (On their album Engraved Invitation):\r\n\r\nInspiring first visit from these young men - 7.5/10\r\n-	www.metalliville.co.uk (On their album Engraved Invitation):\r\n\r\n\r\n..Lucid Recess cuts a well-primed, sharp, surprisingly well produced record, chock full of nifty guitar lines and crisp riffs     ..splendidly produced record..\r\n-	Rolling Stone India Magazine, April 2010 (On their album Engraved Invitation):\r\n\r\n\r\n\"...a colossal nominee for one of the Rock albums of the year\"\r\n-	   Indian Music Revolution Website (On their album Engraved Invitation):\r\n\r\n\r\n\"No. 3 of the Top 10 Indian Albums of 2010\"\r\n-	 RSJ Magazine India (On their album Engraved Invitation):\r\n\r\nIndias answer to modern alternative take the DIY route to success.\r\n-	RSJ Magazine, Jan 2009 Annual Issue \r\n\r\n\r\nThe hard rock climate in India is about to change for the better with the addition of new blood like Lucid Recess.\r\n	RSJ Magazine, June 2009\r\n','Amitabh Barooa <span class=\"skype_pnh_print_container_1342002799\">+91 97060 13278</span><span class=\"skype_pnh_container\" dir=\"ltr\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"skype_pnh_mark\"> begin_of_the_skype_highl','http://www.facebook.com/lucidrecess/info','http://www.lucidrecess.com','http://soundcloud.com/lucidrecess','','0','5105',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','lucid-recess'),(233,0,2,2,'Tough on Tobacco','Tough on Tobacco is singer-songwriter Sidd Couttos talent packed, genre bending, convention defying, wildly funny, brand new live act. The music is a mlange of pop, rock and reggae.\r\n\r\nTough on Tobacco is an anti-tobacco message. Dont start smoking!\r\nIts hard to quit once you start. And its just not worth it. If even one young adult says no to tobacco because they heard us, well be justified in our cause.\r\n\r\nTough on Tobacco is Sidd Couttos first solo album. Sidd has written and produced 5 albums besides performing hundreds of gigs with erstwhile bands Zero and Helgas Fun Castle, composed and produced background scores and songs for bollywood films and television and\r\ndoes a little acting on the side as well. But this endeavor is what he is truly all about, putting his heart and spirit into extremely captivating melodies and lyrics. This is an album of songs with a simple soul, played by a bunch of exceptionally gifted musicians.\r\n\r\nThe band includes Helgas Fun Castles Johan Pais on bass and Jai Row Kavi on drums, Zeros last guitar line-up of Pozy Dhar and Gaurav Gupta,  and is fronted by Sidd Coutto on vocals, guitars, keyboards, percussion, drums and computers.\r\n\r\nThe first album,  titled \'The Happy goat\' was released in 2009 and is up for free download on www.toughontobacco.in ... their second untitled album is currently a work in progress.. should be released by late 2010 ','oml@oml.com','http://www.facebook.com/toughontobacco/info','http://www.toughontobacco.in/','','','0','5038',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','tough-on-tobacco'),(234,0,10,10,'Goldspot','Imagine the West Coast of California, psychedelia-laced George Harrison, and a 1960s Indian film, and youre getting close to the sound of Goldspots  second album And the Elephant is Dancing\".  Available worldwide on iTunes, the album has caught the ear of tastemaker djs Nic Harcourt and Jason Bentley (KCRWs Morning Becomes Eclectic), and has officially been added to several npr and indie stations playlists.  The band was just featured in the Emmy-nominated hit television show How I Met Your Mother, NBC\'s \"Perfect Couples,\" and on the soundtrack for London Film Festival hit \"Today\'s Special.\" \r\n\r\nGoldspot has performed at the prestigious Glastonbury and iTunes festivals, and opened for several major acts including Death Cab for Cutie, Feist, Franz Ferdinand, Travis, and even Bon Jovi.  Their music videos have been featured on VH1 and MTV.\r\n\r\nThis album has lived in the mind of singer/songwriter Siddhartha Khosla since he was a child, growing up in his New Jersey home listening to Bollywood oldies and western rock bands.  Western indie pop/rock sounds together with Bollywood inspired melodies and instrumentation just seems like a natural and wonderful musical partnership to me, he says. Mohd. Rafi, Michael Stipe of REM, Kishore Kumar, and The Beatles all have inspired me ever since I could sing my first note.  Khosla formed the first incarnation of Goldspot eight years ago, and while he enjoys mixing the band up to play with different sounds and ideas, he remains the constant driving force, songwriter, and lead performer.     \r\n\r\nAnd The Elephant is Dancing  is the follow-up to Goldspots critically acclaimed full-length debut \"Tally Of The Yes Men\" (MERCURY UK/UNIVERSAL MUSIC GROUP), an inspired melding of decades of rock and pop influences with the melodic sensibilities of old Indian film music. \"Tally\" was recognized by the Sunday Times (UK) as one of the best albums of the year, with Goldspot being named as one of their best new acts of the year.   Hit single \"Friday\" put the band in the top 20 in the UK radio charts, and at No. 10 in the alternative charts.   Follow-up single, Its Getting Old was awarded an iTunes Single of the Week slot and became the retailers largest free download in its history.  Goldspot\'s music has been featured multiple times on hit US TV shows How I Met your Mother\", The OC\" and several films, including the Simon Pegg hit \"Run Fatboy Run\", Rohan Sippys The President is Coming, and most recently in the soundtrack to Todays Special.  \"Clap Clap\" appeared in Apple\'s video for the ipad.\r\n\r\n    \"One of the best bands to come out of America in years.\" -Sunday Times \r\n    \"Superbly Measured\" - Q \r\n    \"Subtle Sparkling Pop \" - Sunday Express\r\n    \"Sun drenched and beautifully melodic\" - The London Paper \r\n    \"Some of the most memorable vocal melodies heard in a long time.\" Popjournalism\r\n    \"Delirious and delicious\" - Vogue India\r\n\r\n              For more information:  www.goldspot.net, www.mypace.com/goldspot.  ','Juliana Plotkin, Ink Tank PR (juliana@ink-tankpr.com), Raj Ghai, UK Press (raj@mediamoguls.com)  ','http://www.facebook.com/Goldspot.music/info','www.goldspot.net','','','0','5012',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','goldspot'),(235,2,1,1,'Mrigya','This is a story... ruled by fate\r\nThe Players.... with the old cliche..... at the right place, at the right time.\r\n\r\n6th May, 1999; FRIENDS OF MUSIC was one of those shows, \"Drummers Jam\', where the performers decided not to show up. Everyone, except Ashwini from Orange Street and Rajat from Parikrama. They decided the show had to go on and brought in Indraneel, the bassist from Orange Street along with Sharat, Sonam and Gyan from Parikrama.\r\n\r\nThree days of intensive rehearsals - a combination of compositions - resulting in Ganga, Pahari Funk and Caravan - three songs that would give definition to what would become the sound of the band. The prerequisite of course, was a name - every band needs a name. Our local Archimedes, Neel, in a flash of inspiration in the shower (where else!) came up with \'Mrigaya\'. Mr. Kakkar, who incidentally won the spelling bee contest in his childhood (held only at Darya Ganj in the early 70s) mispelt it as \'Mrigya\' in one of the band profiles and the name stuck. \r\n\r\nThe show turned out to be a huge success which got them thinking of carrying on even though every member was a full time member of some band or the other at that particular time.\r\n\r\n18th Sept. 1999, IIT-DELHI, JAZZ NITE - A show - after which they realized a stronger rhythm section was needed. Enter Sachin - having played with the band Warlock in college, was reputed to be a keyboardist par excellence. It was an obvious choice. With that followed Sukriti, a classical singer who added such a different feel to \'Ganga\' that it became impossible to think of the band without her. Sadly, Sonam had to leave due to commitments to Parikrama but has always been there to help them out. Karan has taken his role since and is holding his own.\r\n\r\nOne album old and numerous concerts across towns and cities in India to Europe, Africa, Australia and Russia, they\'ve composed countless tunes while experimenting wildly with different genres and carrying on exploring the endless frontiers of their musicianship.\r\n\r\nMrigya has blossomed into a fascinating contemporary group venturing to stretch the boundaries of music becoming the harbinger of a unique fusion band offering a rich blend of blues, funk, folk, latino, Indian Classical, and jazz. The objective of Mrigya is to expand in all directions and to play music without boundaries. It perhaps best represents the coming together of various strains of music.\r\n\r\nStay tuned for the more news and views','Anand Kanwar','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Mrigya/82191877697?sk=info','http://www.mrigya.com','http://soundcloud.com/mrigya','','0','5008',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 15:01:59',244,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','mrigya'),(236,0,115,115,'Cody','Cody is a Danish seven-piece band playing folk inspired pop melodies with hints of post rock and nordic gloom. Cody has released two EPs (Cody 2009, Under the Pillow, Under the Elms 2011), an album (Songs, 2009) and is currently working on new material.\r\n\r\nThe band was started out by front man Kaspar Kaae in 2004 and several musicians has since then taken part in the band. In the last couple of years the band has had a more steady composition and has evolved into a band of extremely talented and hard working live musicians. \r\n\r\nDuring the years CODY has been invited to support acts like Black Francis (2007), The National (2008), Bonnie \'Prince\' Billy (2008), Tindersticks (2010) and Band Of Horses (2011). They have played G! Festival (FO), Spot Festival (DK) and Roskilde Festival (DK) twice, and their music has featured films such as the German Warner Bros. Film 12 Meter Ohne Kopf and the Danish award -winning film En Familie (DK) / A Family (UK).Cody is a Danish seven-piece band playing folk inspired pop melodies with hints of post rock and nordic gloom. Cody has released two EPs (Cody 2009, Under the Pillow, Under the Elms 2011), an album (Songs, 2009) and is currently working on new material.\r\n\r\nThe band was started out by front man Kaspar Kaae in 2004 and several musicians has since then taken part in the band. In the last couple of years the band has had a more steady composition and has evolved into a band of extremely talented and hard working live musicians. \r\n\r\nDuring the years CODY has been invited to support acts like Black Francis (2007), The National (2008), Bonnie \'Prince\' Billy (2008), Tindersticks (2010) and Band Of Horses (2011). They have played G! Festival (FO), Spot Festival (DK) and Roskilde Festival (DK) twice, and their music has featured films such as the German Warner Bros. Film 12 Meter Ohne Kopf and the Danish award -winning film En Familie (DK) / A Family (UK).','Jon Madsen // Slow Shark records // jon@slowsharkrecords.dk','http://www.facebook.com/comeondieyoung','http://www.sonicbids.com/codydk','http://www.myspace.com/codysongs','http://www.last.fm/music/cody','45436907647','4947',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','cody'),(237,0,15,15,'Hari & Sukhmani','A trained Hindustani classical vocalist from the Rampur Gharana, Sukhmani Malik has a voice dense with character, that doesnt fail to strike you as powerful.\r\nHari Singh, a producer and audio engineer, has electronic skills tuned finely to appease the ear.\r\nThe two combine eclecticism with a curiously contemporary take on traditional folk songs from the land of Punjab. Their sounds are a blend of folk music fused with ambient electronica. Hari and Sukhmanis music resonates with their sincere and cultured touch. \r\nSukhmanis cultured voice coupled with Haris fine production skills makes them one of a kind act in the music scene today.\r\nHari & Sukhmani have been touring Nationally & Internationally since December of 2008.  Among the cities theyve performed at are Delhi, Mumbai, Punjab, Rajasthan, Lucknow, Benaras, Jim Corbett, Manali, etc. along with performances in Australia and New Zealand as well!\r\nHailing from Chandi Town(chandigarh), Hari & Sukhmani are a young and ambitious duo who plan to take Punjabi folk music from the yester years into the future, from New Delhi to New York City. \r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Hari-Sukhmani/103467873106?sk=info','http://www.harisukhmani.com','http://soundcloud.com/harisukhmani','','0','4877',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','hari-sukhmani'),(238,0,1,1,'Infernal Wrath','Infernal Wrath is a Mumbai based extreme metal band formed in early 2005 whose influences also include Indian classical & world music, creating a very unique aural landscape & a live experience that has made a lasting impression on audiences in Mumbai, Pune, Delhi, Goa, Hyderabad & Bangalore and have become the crowds favorite live act.\n\nAlbum Concept\n\nThe band speaks about the path of self realization that is set to a backdrop of the events preceeding the Apocalypse which has been foretold in various scriptures which form the basis of various religions & sects all across the globe.\n\nAs a part of the events that will take place, one of the key figures is that of the messiah.\nThis expected chosen one is given many different names by various religions of the world.\nThrough the journey of the album, one will realize that the messiah is not some third person but we are our own messiah.\n\nIn todays time, the foreign & domestic policies that are being made, the present conflicts that are being pursued in our present geo-political scenario by the politicians & the priestly class to pursue their own selfish agendas, use these scriptures to indoctrinate the masses to demand those Armageddon like situation to take place, claming that the messiah will appear & their salvation is near.\n\nSo, in the light of the present scenario, we, as a band, want to show a completely different perspective using the very same texts so that individuals can understand their true goal, the one of self-realization. \n\n','','http://www.facebook.com/infernalwrath','','http://soundcloud.com/infernalwrathindia','','6745458955','4825',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','infernal-wrath'),(239,0,80,80,'Anish Sood','Anish Sood is part of an emerging new breed of young artists that are sweeping the Indian dance music scene. At just 22, hes been jet setting between playing at the biggest venues in India to leading festivals like the annual Sunburn Festival in Goa.\r\n\r\nAn in-depth understanding of crowds, dance floors and electronic music have made him one of the most sought after warmup DJs in the country having opened for Gareth Emery, Sultan, Funkagenda, Felix Da Housecat, Miss Nine, Norman Doray, Albin Myers and John 00 Fleming amongst others.\r\n\r\nAnishs musical versatility can be easily proven by the fact that he can effortlessly switch between playing deep, melodic warmups to working packed main rooms with pounding progressive house, trance and techno.\r\nHis consistent sets are backed by solid technical prowess in the studio, a fact that was cemented when he churned out a winning remix for Nadia Alis club-hit single Love Story which garnered support from around the world.\r\n\r\nHis debut single Catapult was picked up by Trance legend Marcel Woods label Musical Madness and has subsequently been released on the legendary High Contrast imprint. His much in-demand edits and bootlegs are regularly hammered out by DJs across the world and add a unique element to his sets, that enable crowds to connect with the classics he samples.\r\n\r\nWith a host of forthcoming releases on international labels as well as a string of high profile events, Anish is set to take off in 2012.','press@anishsood.com','http://www.facebook.com/anishsoodmusic/info','http://www.anishsood.com','http://soundcloud.com/anishsood','','0','4791',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-10 16:00:15',352,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','anish-sood'),(240,0,64,64,'TANTRUM','In 2002 three teenagers, tired of the meaningless music being pumped into Sri Lankan veins through the mainstream, got an idea to form a band and realize the potency of the one pure form of music they all loved, Heavy Metal. At the time they barely knew the rudiments of instrumentation, and actually getting a band off the ground seemed like an unrealistic dream for the 16 year old school mates. But as time went on, there was a significant improvement, and at the beginning of 2004 the guys decided to take this more seriously after realizing the possible potential for a Metal Band in the Sri Lankan music industry, and the name \'Tantrum was born.\r\n\r\nThe band\'s style is considered Thrash Metal, with a touch of technical Death Metal with various melodic elements. Classical, Blues, Jazz & Eastern elements are also influential to the band when creating music.\r\n\r\nThe band recorded and released their first single titled The Destroyer which became a Number 1 hit on the local chart show (TNLs SL Hot 10). This earned Tantrum some recognition in the metal scene. Soon afterwards, Tantrum released their 2nd single titled Alone, which proved that the band had great talent and it impressed many of the listeners, and so Tantrum had the fortune of starting off with two smash singles. Tantrum was also one of the few bands to take part in TNL Onstage (a battle of the bands like competition in Sri Lanka) for the 1st time & come out winners of the competition. This was in 2005. Tantrum then released an EP titled \"The Destruction Begins\" in 2006 and soon after the band went through a major line up change. Currently the line up is as follows -\r\n\r\n\r\nJaveen Soysa - Vocals & Bass Guitar\r\nAkila Pieris - Guitars\r\nThishan Wijesinghe - Guitars\r\nTharaka Senevirathne - Drums\r\n\r\n\r\nEver since the change the bands music evolved into genres stated above and the usage of crushing 7 string guitars became a unique and a first ever in Sri Lanka. Tantrum has also managed to appear in countless number of interviews, front covers of magazines and press articles etc, as well as electronic media around Asia and has been labeled as one of the leading Metal bands in Sri Lanka. The band cannot wait to get out there and delight the Metal World by providing them with dynamic music and performances to break their necks moshing to. Tantrum is looking forward to open the floodgates to a whole new level of music, and take Sri Lankan heavy metal to greater heights, and their journey has just begun.....','Tantrum Inc: (94) 777311698','http://www.facebook.com/tantrumental/info','http://www.tantrumental.com','','','0','4741',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','tantrum'),(241,2,1,1,'Middle Finger Theory','Middle Finger Theory is a NuMetal/Experimental act\r\nhailing from New Delhi, India brought into being in July of 2010. Our music is a mlange of Heavy Metal and NuMetal consisting of catchy yet ear ripping riffs, fuzzy and dominating bass lines with some extra crunch, precise drum patterns often played at ridiculous speeds, topped with melodious rap, growls and screeches with some killer work on the Turntables and Synth by DJ Navendu which confers a completely different sound. We are open to experiment and have a wide range of influences from Deftones, Limp Bizkit, Linkin Park, to Tool, Radiohead, Incubus, Sleepytime Gorilla Museum. We have been doing a few gigs across New Delhi lately and have managed a pretty decent fan base too. Soon the energies started to resonate as a result of which the band got short listed for the Unseen Underground Pub fest and the first track got featured on the California State University\'s Global Radio known as KBeach Radio following which the band also got short listed for RSJ Pubrockfest and played alongside Undying Inc and Rabbit is Rich. The lyrics of our songs revolve around quests of the divine human mind, skepticism about reality, Consciousness and social stigmas & evils which haunt our society. The band believes in making music which gets you thinking as soon as your neurons transmit it through your ears to the most divine thing in the whole cosmos, YOUR MIND!\r\n\r\nOur gigs are known and remembered for the Party atmosphere we create, audience interaction which is unique and full of what we call \"Bakchodi\" and how we make each and every one dance and mosh with us. Fans describe us \"crazy as anal fuck\".\r\n\r\nAppearances :\r\nShivaji College Fest\r\nSRCC, Woodstock (Runners Up)\r\nKirori Mal College Fest\r\nDelhi College of Arts and Commerce Annual Fest\r\nNetaji Subhash Institute of Technology, Moksha 2010\r\nGlobal School of Management Sciences Annual Fest\r\nRGIM, Evening Jam Sessions\r\nRSJ Red Romanov Pubrockfest 2010 along with Undying Inc. and Rabbit is Rich\r\nKingfisher Rash Rockrum PubFest 2010 along with October and Jester\r\nAIIMS Pulse 2010 - One of the biggest events in the country\r\nTeri University\'s Green Rock Festival\r\nIIT Roorkie, Wargasm 2010\r\nBITS - Pilani, Rocktaves 2010\r\nIIT Kanpur, Synchronicity 2010\r\nPlayed DEFTONES Tribute Gig at Kyra Theater, Bangalore\r\nRock/Metal Eve, Rajouri Garden Institute of Music\r\nMood Indigo, IIT Bombay Livewire 2010\r\nConverse Original Band Hunt 2010\r\nDelhi Zone Finalists for Mood Indigo, IIT Bombay Livewire 2010\r\nHeadlined Maulana Azad Medical College Fest 2010\r\nIIT Kharagpur Wildfire 2010\r\nSelected in top 6 bands for Channel V Launchpad 2011\r\nUtopia 2011, School of Planning and Architecture (Qualified for the finals and First Runners Up in the finals)\r\nCafe Morrison (2010, 2011)\r\nTurquoise Cottage (2011)\r\nFeatured in Rolling Stone India Magazine, July 2011\r\nThe Gig Week 2011\r\nRolling Stones Ray Ban Never Hide Sounds 2011\r\nPlayed along Social Suicide (Norway)\r\nPlayed alongside Torch (Norway) at TC, Gurgaon\r\nRSJ Pubrockfest 2011\r\nQualified in the Top 2 Bands at Dream Rigs ProActivate 2011 out of 61 Entries from all over India.\r\nPlayed at Casio Edifice G-Shock Official Launch Event, Imperial Hotel, New Delhi.\r\nHeadlined at the War of Bands at Gurgaon Institute of Technology and Management, Gurgaon\r\nHeadlined at the Battle of Bands at Gurgaon College of Engineering, Gurgaon','+91-9250370469, +91-9953880130','http://www.facebook.com/MiddleFingerTheory/info','','http://soundcloud.com/middlefingertheory','','0','4726',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 15:02:26',205,'[\"\"]','[\"+91-7838769526 +91-9811295006\"]','middle-finger-theory'),(242,0,82,82,'Purple Blood','Formed in 2008 by the frontman and guitarist and later on found the other members in college, Purple Blood was not constrained as a college band and in a quick passage of time the band has got the highest credibility of being the second Kerala band after Motherjane to open for an International act when they opened for the Swedish Giants Hammerfall after winning the prestigious Saarang competition at IIT Madras. A five piece metalcore band with high progressive influences,the band concentrates in creating a unique sound of their own and the songs reflect the pent of frustration,the longing desires, the dark corners of the human mind. The band has released their debut single which was widely appreciated and has won so many college titles and headlining acts to their name. The band is currently writing new material and entering studios soon for the recording of their debut EP which will be released by the end of this year.\r\n','+919746073768','http://www.facebook.com/purplebloodindia/info','','http://soundcloud.com/meetprash','http://www.reverbnation.com/purplebloodindia','0','4717',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','purple-blood'),(243,0,83,83,'Two Hours Traffic','','killbeat - ken beattie - kb@killbeatmusic.com','http://www.facebook.com/thtmusic/info?ref=ts','http://www.twohourstraffic.com','','','0','4662',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','two-hours-traffic'),(244,0,11,11,'Blind Image','Blind Image is a Thrash/ Groove Metal band from Chennai, India, formed in early 2006. \r\n\r\nBlind Image has released two albums so far:\r\nThe first one titled \'Psychobabble was released in 2008.\r\nThe second , a concept album titled \'More Than Human was released in 2009.\r\n\r\nThe band has been doing a lot of international tour off-late and recently toured Australia and the middle east headlining festivals . The band has also announced the tour of southeast asia for september. \r\n\r\nThe band is supported by brands such as Gibson, Spector, Vater, Sonor and, Soultone\r\n\r\nContact: blindimage@gmail.com\r\n \r\nWant to know more about the band and check out the music? Visit us at:\r\n\r\nwww.reverbnation.com/blindimage\r\n\r\nwww.myspace.com/blindimageofficial\r\n\r\nwww.youtube.com/blindimagebootlegs\r\n','Krishna - +919884242023, blindimage@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/blindimageofficial/info','','','http://www.reverbnation.com/blindimage','0','4653',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','blind-image'),(245,0,2,2,'Woody [ Jarrod Wood ]','Woody a.k.a Jarrod Wood is a DJ, composer, electronic music producer and flute, saxophone and bansuri artist from New Zealand. For the last 4 years he\'s been living in India training with bansuri maestro Hariprasad Chaurasia.\r\n\r\n