Of The Year at ProDJ Awards in 2010.\r\n\r\nJuicy M is an awesome DJ with a perfect ability to communicate with the audience. She precisely knows what party people want and she always creates the right mood and just blows the party up! ','','http://www.facebook.com/djjuicym/info','http://juicy-m.com/','http://soundcloud.com/dj-juicy-m','','0','4577',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-juicy-m'),(248,0,34,34,'The Joint Family','It\'s a solo project created by Raef aka Rafa, the multi talented musician who plays different instruments for a few other bands such as Aurthohin, KraL, Severe Dementia, Dripping gore.\r\n\r\nAs Raef decided to go solo, he asked Hythum to play guitars with him for few gigs at different lounges. But it wasn\'t enough for them, the duo planned to make it a proper \'band\'. Nabil was already playing bass with them. \r\n\r\nJust when the band was planning on auditioning a drummer, Atanu auditioned, and that\'s when Raef knew what to do!\r\n\r\nSo that\'s it, The Joint Family is now officially ON!','n/a','http://www.facebook.com/thejointfamily/info','','','','0','4529',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-joint-family'),(249,0,116,116,'SPARTAK KURTESHI','Muzikan','','http://www.facebook.com/SpartakKurteshi','','','','246031099225','4521',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','spartak-kurteshi'),(250,0,25,25,'Baiju Dharmajan','Commanding an unparalleled fan base across India, Baiju Dharmajan is one of the best guitar players to have surfaced in the country in the last decade. His unique ability to infuse a mighty distinctiveness while giving life to hard-hitting distorted grooves as well as mellifluous clean tone melodic rhythms is the reason why he has emerged today a most wanted guitar instructor. Voted twice as the best guitarist at the Jack Daniel\'s Awards, There are elements in Baiju\'s guitar playing that satisfies every one among the followers of Metal, Hard Rock, Fusion, Progressive, Blues or highly technical variants of rock music.\r\n\r\nThe effortlessness displayed while making his guitar weep through the soul stirring patterns has enabled him to etch a stature that has resulted him getting more occupied that ever before.\r\n\r\nPost the Motherjane era, Baiju Dharmajan is today more focused on his solo album which is due to release later this year. Baiju is part of multiple musical projects with different musicians as well as concentrating on music production for the upcoming bands. Currently he is part of \'Kashmir\' cofounded with Sanjeev Thomas and other initiatives with prolific players such as John Antony of the jazz fusion experimental band \'Karnatriix\' and \'Bluefire\' a brainchild of classical violinist Harikumar Sivan. With an experience of producing two epic rock albums with Motherjane, Baiju is today lending his expertise in being a music producer with new bands like Kaav. This exponent of a new mode of guitar playing named \'Carnatic Shredding\' is in the threshold of creating more challenging never before tried musical synthesis.\r\n\r\n','http://cochym.com','http://www.facebook.com/BaijuMDharmajan/info','http://baijudharmajan.in','http://soundcloud.com/baiju-dharmajan','','0','4443',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','baiju-dharmajan'),(252,0,84,84,'Blackstratblues','After picking up the guitar at the age of 5, Warren would go on to play rhythm guitar in a few local bands with friends Siddharth Coutto (drums), & Girish \'Bobby\' Talwar (rhythm guitar, bass). Sometime around 1997-98, they would form Zero, with Rajeev Talwar on vocals.\r\n\r\nOver the years, Zero grew to enjoy nationwide popularity in India. With Warren, Zero released 2 albums & an EP - Albummed (1999), Hook EP (2002), & Procrastination (2005).\r\nBesides his work in Zero, Warren recorded & released numerous instrumentals - Christmas In July, Spitleaf, & Evil, to name a few popular songs - which enjoyed some fame on online music forums like Gigpad, & Harmony Central. He was also involved in many online collaborations with musicians - most notably Adam Martin, Ed DeGenaro, & Zorran Mendonsa - which resulted in a few songs. In late 2004, Warren moved to Auckland, New Zealand, thereby quitting Zero.\r\nDuring this period, he was also a highly sought-after recording engineer & session guitarist in Bombay, having worked on various film soundtracks, ad jingles, & other albums.\r\n\r\nAfter moving to Auckland, Warren began work on solo instrumental material. While visiting India, he reunited with Zero for a few gigs, most notably at the Great Indian Rock Festival 2006.','blackstratblues@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/Blackstratblues/info','http://www.blackstratblues.com','','','0','4439',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','blackstratblues'),(253,0,3,3,'Escher\'s Knot','Escher\'s Knot is a Metal outfit from Chennai formed in July 2009. Members of IIIrd Sovereign, Theorized, Ston\'d and Blood&Iron get together in this experimental entity.','Abijith - +91 9886480413','http://www.facebook.com/eschersknot/info','','','http://www.reverbnation.com/eschersknot','0','4398',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','eschers-knot'),(254,0,18,18,'Cypher16','Cypher16 are a young, talented new organic rock band, who fuse electronic and metal influences with hints of industrial to create their own unique musical mix.\r\n \r\nHaving toured in India and America, playing with the likes of Lacuna Coil, Mudvayne, and In This Moment, Symphonic/Dance/Metal band Cypher16 have begun to make international strides in the music world. Cypher16 are currently in the studio with Dan Weller (Sikth/Enter Shikari) and are \r\n\r\nIn 2009 and still just in their teens, the band received an the invitation to play at Locofest in Florida with metal heavy-weights Mudvayne, In This Moment, Head P.E. and Nonpoint, around which they built their first tour of America.\r\n\r\nShortly after returning to the UK, the band filmed their debut music video for the lead track off their 2008 EP \'Symphony To End It All (III)\' in the incredible Gloucester Cathedral (the location for scenes from the Harry Potter films). The video has been received with unanimous praise, and has been described as having \'an epic location for an epic track\'. The video is now being shown on the major music channels in the UK , and to see it on Scuzz then please send your request to requests@scuzz.tv\r\n\r\nIn the autumn of 2009, Cypher16 were signed to WOA Records, and consequently became one of the first British metal bands to tour in India, playing shows in Goa, Bangalore, Mumbai and Pune. The tour was a huge success, and the band gained a great many fans eagerly awaiting their return.\r\n\r\nIn mid-2010, Cypher16 entered Fortress Studios in London with WellerHill Productions (Sikth/Enter Shikari/The Gallows) to begin recording follow-up tracks to The Man Of The Black Abyss, which was re-released with bonus material, including the video for Symphony To End It All.  With short UK tours throughout the year, several shows in Europe and a performance at Herefords Wyeside Festival with legendary punk act The Stranglers, 2010 has been a busy year for the band.\r\n\r\nMore recently, the band have been making an even bigger name for themselves by playing with veteran Gothenburg band Dark Tranquillity at a sold-out show London Underworld show in September. In October they made a much anticipated return to India, this time playing with Italian Gothic band Lacuna Coil at the Great Indian Octoberfest. As well as plans to return to India and America, to discover more of Europe with a longer tour, and recording and preparing their new EP for release in early 2011, Cypher16 are also planning their next music video, which has been promised to have as epic a location as the last.\r\n\r\nIn September 2010, Cypher16 played with the veteran Gothenburg band Dark Tranquility at a sold-out show at the Underworld in London. The most recent international trip took place in October, when the band flew out for their second tour to India, which included headlining the second stage at The Kingfisher Octoberfest festival in Bangalore with Lacuna Coil. Rave reviews and a new management deal with overture India (famous for bringing Lamb of God to India) followed the band\'s performance and they are returning in September 2011 for a full scale headline tour, such is the demand. \'The Metaphorical Apocalypse\' EP has just been released to more rave reviews from the press and fans alike and the band are now preparing to shoot the music video for single, \'Lonely Road\' at the world famousBattersea Power Station in August. This will be followed the the third tour to India, with a UK tour taking place in October.\r\n\r\nIn September Cypher16 played with the veteran Gothenburg band DARK TRANQUILLITY at a sold-out show at the London Underworld. In October 2010 Cypher16 flew out for their second tour to INDIA, this time to headline the second stage of The Kingfisher Great Indian October Festival with LACUNA COIL. Rave reviews followed and the band began working with Overture India (famous for bringing Lamb Of God to the country). \r\n \r\n\'The Metaphorical Apocalypse EP was released in May 2011 to more rave reviews from the press and fans alike, and the band recently shot the music video for Lonely Road at the world famous Battersea Power Station. The video was premiered by SCUZZ TV and shortly afterwards the band went back over to India for their first headline tour of the country. They have recently returned, and immediately followed it with a sold-out show at The Barfly in London. The \'Lonely Road\' video has since been voted the 2nd best video of the year on SCUZZ.','Emma Watson at FifteenThree PR/contact@cypher16.net                ','http://www.facebook.com/Cypher16/info','http://www.cypher16.net','','','0','4371',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','cypher16'),(255,2,1,1,'The Circus','Funky. Groovy. Eclectic. Vicious. Happy. Mellow. Furious. Quirky. Angsty. Bouncy. Think of a musical recipe which has a healthy dollop of all these ingredients and youre thinking The Circus. A band that believes in ferocity of intent and perfection of execution, and an absolutely take-no-prisoners attitude when it comes to their original music. The eldritch, beaming wails of Abhishek Bhatia, the left-field pummeling guitar attack of Arsh Sharma, the ridiculously complex bass work of Abhinav Chaudhary and the tireless groove machine of Anshul Lall put together create some of the most refreshing and original music to emerge out of the Indian subcontinent in years. Live, they are the essence of what rock and roll is all about, and bring the fun and decadence that has all but died out in a scene where bands sound increasingly manufactured in an attempt to be appreciated. The Circus are none of that. This is no-frills rock and roll at its finest, and it has only been two years into their existence. With a debut full-length album scheduled for imminent release, the band is set to go places. You would be wise to show up at the next gig.','','http://www.facebook.com/circusthe/info','http://www.thecircus.in ','http://soundcloud.com/circusthe','','0','4349',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 15:03:36',154,'[\"the.circus@live.in\"]','[\"Arsh Sharma - 9818804297 Ashwin Sharma - 09987666108\"]','the-circus'),(256,0,3,3,'Slain','Melodic Progressive Rock: a sound that retains the glory of Classic Rock, while being driven by the barrier-breaking musicianship exclusive to Progressive Metal; Slain has dedicated itself to exploring this sweet spot in the sonic landscape - and the countless awards suggest we\'re getting fairly good at it.\r\n\r\nSlain\'s FB page features exclusive content like recommendations, videos and blogs that help expand your musical tastes, polish your knowledge, and keep you updated with the latest and greatest in the world of Melodic Rock!\r\n\r\nHeck, you may even become a better person. Join us now!','mail@slainandbeyond.com','http://www.facebook.com/slainindia/info','http://www.slainandbeyond.com','','http://www.reverbnation.com/slain','0','4330',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-10 14:05:54',341,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','slain'),(257,0,2,2,'Dj Chirag','                  As one of Gujarat\'s most respected industry figures, 26 years old DJ Chirag has been spinning tunes for two years. DJ Chirag was born in Surat (Gujarat) on 10th October and he always had a real passion for music. As a teenager he started collecting every kind of music. After finishing secondary school his DJ adventure began when he started spinning at his friends party. DJing has always been a passion for him and he was exposed to musicality from a very young age.\r\n\r\nHe started of his journey from a very low level Dj. worked for local sound providers and understood the working of consoles. At the age of 21 he started playing for private gigs, inspired a passion for electronic music and an ambition to make a career in this fascinating, elusive little world. But that wasnt enough for him. He always wanted to make it big. Chirag entered into professional djing at the age of 21 and since then he has rocked some of the high-quality parties in Surat,Baroda,Ahemdabad and his tunes are considered to be the most energetic and danceable around. He played in so many places & cities\r\n\r\nIt is for his remixing and production work that Chirag is now starting to make it on the electronic music stage. He always had a curiosity for softwares, to make his own tunes. He started learning them by trail and error method, and soon learned to put together small, very simple pieces and produce his own bollywood remixes. Appreciation from some of the well-known figures of this industry made this artist never look back. After enough of club banging mash-up and some remixes from his side, now with all new funky, punchier basslines and kickinn kicks to bang the speakers. His newest releases RAGE-FURY OF MUSICAL JOURNEY,vol:1 2009, and PHIR SE WAHI (CLUB MIX) is getting appreciation from all over.\r\n\r\nDJ Chirag does not only know how to play his tunes, he sure knows how to organise a thumping party as well. He is known for his set of house music, especially when it comes to sub-genre electro house (commercial). He owns a very special set of electro house, comprising some of the very best of the international music scene, enough to make party people raise their eye-brows and go crazy. He always maintains a healthy combination of both bollywood and house music ensuring the feets on the dance floor doesnt sleeps. His friendly, funny nature and sense for quality music are the jewels for any event.\r\n\r\nChirag started his own Music production academy name \r\nRage Productionz \r\n\r\nDj ChiragS Some Bollywood & pop remixes now available on Google & So Many different web pages\r\n\r\nHis Personal exclusive mixes & Various Mix tapes & Nonstop Sets being aired on radio stations across India & Out of India\r\n\r\nNamely: BIG F.M 92.7,\r\n91.9 KLUB NINE (SILIGIRI- INDIA),\r\nLOTUS F.M KLUB KULCHA (SOUTH AFRICA)\r\nRED F.M (CANADA),\r\nCurry Smugglers (U.S)\r\n\r\nReleased Music Albums :\r\nDj Chirag\'s Rage Vol : 1\r\nDj Chirag\'s Rage Vol : 2\r\nDj Chirag\'s Rage Vol : 3\r\nDj Chirag\'s Rage Vol : 4\r\nDj Chirag\'s Rage Vol : 5\r\nDj Chirag\'s Rage Vol : 6\r\n(Biggest Online Music album with 33 Tracks )\r\nDj Chirag\'s Just Bounce 2012\r\n\r\nOfficial Bollywood Remixes \r\n\r\nMovie : Yeh Dooriyaan \r\n>Yeh Dooriyaan ( Remix ) Title Track\r\n>Ya Maula ( Remix )\r\n>Jab se Mujhe Mila -Neend Nadarat ( Planet M Exclusive Remix )\r\n\r\nMovie : Chitkabrey \r\nChinese Khusi (Remix)Title Track\r\n\r\nFor Programming Contact : +91-96871-29729 \r\n                            BB Pin    :         2358C3D4','+91-96871-29729 ','http://www.facebook.com/DjChiragOfficial/info','','http://soundcloud.com/dj-chirag-2','','0','4323',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-chirag'),(258,0,85,85,'Gaurav Pandey','I am an untrained singer-songwriter from the lake-city Nainital,Uttrakhand.I don\'t go out to studios to record my songs, i have a small home setup where i work and create music. I grew up learning music from the Streets and till date have had no professional training classes.(I don\'t need sympathy for that)\r\nA second year student studying Engineering.\r\nI\'m just doing music for ME and alone ME plus add a few people around me reason being I LOVE DOING IT and this is the only thing that makes me feel all the taste and feelings of life, actually IT MAKES ME FEEL ME.\r\nI\'m not here to prove it to anyone and i don\'t give a shit if you don\'t like me.I don\'t need sympathy or anything of that sort for anything...say for being untrained as mentioned.\r\nThe thing is \'\' IF YOU LIKE MY MUSIC YOU LIKE MY MUSIC , IF YOU DON\'T LIKE MY MUSIC YOU DON\'T LIKE MY MUSIC.\'\'\r\nAs for the people associated with me Aakash Sharma(a fellow Engineer),Ankit Saini(a fellow engineer) along with ME together form the roots of the sound that flows out through the wires and into your ears.\r\n\r\nShivil Bhasin a friend and an Electronic music producer/dj as well as an audio engineer handles the mixing/mastering aspect of all the tracks.\r\n\r\nIn the month of July,2009 Gaurav fused with a few musicians under the name NUCLEUS and competed in a band quest,organised by Big 92.3 Fm barelly. They stood Third overall and First in their state, Uttarakhand.\r\nIn the annual fest of Nainital 2010 \"Sardotsav\" He along with the band Vikshipt scored a place for themselves and were even praised by newspapers and the audience.\r\nIn the month of October,2011,Goldi Thapa and Gaurav toured across Nepal playing and promoting music.','gauravpandeymusic@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/GauravPandeyMusic','','','','257063981012255','4298',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','gaurav-pandey'),(259,0,86,86,'Dominique Young Unique','19-year-old Tampa Bay rapper Dominique Young Unique has gone from rapping in the courts her Robles Park projects to playing a world wide stage within a year of releasing her 1st mixtape performing alongside the likes of N.E.R.D, Big Boi, Die Antwoord and Gucci Mane. Teaming up with producer David Alexander, she has a taste for rapid-fire raps and high-speed electro club beats. Youthful, raw and full of bite, this 19 year-old is crashing onto dancefloors with her militaristic mash-up of club and hip-hop. \r\n\r\n\"YES, I\'ve ruddy seen her. YES, I\'ve ducked and dodged her richocheting shrapnel-pinging verses. And YES, I\'m aware of the fact she\'s underground booty-bass\' best stab at a genuine popstar.\" - NME\r\n\r\n\"Her statacco rhymes serve as the track\'s bedrock rhythm while the production moves quickly between percussion-only \"Lip Gloss\" clap to bass-driven 1-3 bop to shimmering new wave. \"I\'m doin\' this right,\" goes one of the many hooks packed into this short little tune. Pretty much, yeah.\" - Pitchfork\r\n\r\n\"With the sexy swagger of Lil Kim, the ghetto credibility of Trina and the spitting skills of Nicki Minaj, its impossible to ignore Tampa electro rap queen, Dominique Young Unique\" - Dazed and Confused\r\n\r\n\"The young female rapper everyone is talking about.\" - RWD','Press USA: Siena Reese / Biz 3 siena@biz3.net .  Press UK: Heather Finlay/ Sainted PR heatherfinlay@saintedpr.com , Digital Publicity UK: Leyla Leonard / Sainted PR leyla@saintedpr.com ','http://www.facebook.com/youngunique/info','http://dominiqueyoungunique.com','','','0','4231',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dominique-young-unique'),(260,0,11,11,'Franks got the funk','Launched in 2009, Franks Got The Funk is a band which treads in various genres, primarily influenced by Electronic and Progressive rock. Bjorn, the bands front man and vocalist, started it off as a 4-piece college band, playing a very few covers and spurning out a couple of new songs. The line up, which at the time kept changing, saw the entry of Vikram (keyboardist) at an early stage. Soon after, Sajith and Shashank (bassist and drummer) stepped in to complete the picture. The latest addition to the band is Mervin Christopher (lead guitarist) who is ready and set to fill in the shoes of his predecessors. The band has yet another member - Frank. An alter-ego of the band, he writes all their songs for them. \r\n\r\nThe band has a simple principle which they stick to when making their music  Its all about fun and love for the music based on situations and incidents which theyve been through . In fact, the sole motivation for the band to record and release their music is to get the music out there to the people. The surging energy and the addictive songs the band churns out are complemented by the capturing stage presence and wacky costumes, which keeps audiences enraptured and jumping.  \r\n\r\nFGTF, as the band is popularly known, have won various competitions such as Deepwoods, Strawberry fields, NXG Rockstar , IIT Saarang and many more. After proving themselves in the inter-collegiate circle, the band progressed to playing professional gigs and live acts, headlining in different colleges.\r\nOnce the band had achieved all that they had aspired to, in the college foray, they decided to take it to the the Next Level. And thats precisely what they did. The bands first album was released in August 2011, aptly named the Next Level, to an overwhelming response from all quarters. An independent album, it was produced in Tobes Garage.\r\n\r\nThe bands vision as far as the near future is concerned is to get their music out across the country and play professional gigs of all sorts. In the long run, they aim to hit the international stage and take it by storm!\r\n\r\nAnd Yes We\'ve  done this so far . \r\n\r\nunderground 09 acoustic winners . with best vocalist and instrumentalist \r\n\r\nplaced 2nd @ iit saarang powerchords 2010 with best drummer and bassy .\r\n\r\nwinners of Chennai live acoustic competition .\r\n\r\nwinners of mcc deep woods 2010 with best drummer , guitarist and Best song - Franks Got The Funk\r\n\r\nDIrect entry to play @ JRO 2010 !\r\n\r\nWinners of techofes 2010 with best vocalist , drummer , bassy and keyboardist titles .\r\n\r\nChristian medical college (CmC) vellore - Pegasus 2010 - winners ! along with best keyboardist .\r\n\r\nunderground 10 winners . best keyboardist and bassist .\r\n\r\nNls strawberry feilds bangalore 2010 . Runners up \r\n+ best keyboardist \r\n\r\nFinalists @ IIT Saarang Decibels 2011 . Winning best Drummer . best keyboardist and best Front man .\r\n\r\nNxg Rockstars 2011 Winnners ! Along with best bassy .\r\n \r\nHeadlining act at PIMS ( Pondicherry ) 2011.  ','','http://www.facebook.com/fgtf.music/info','','http://soundcloud.com/franks-got-the-funk','http://www.reverbnation.com/Fgtf','0','4205',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','franks-got-the-funk'),(261,0,3,3,'Kryptos','','','http://www.facebook.com/KryptosIndia/info','http://www.kryptosindia.com','','','0','4204',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','kryptos'),(262,0,22,22,'The Metal Review','Biography:  Welcome to the metal review, founded in august of 2008 and purely based on Myspace. In July 2011 Nads joined the team and created a facebook fanpage as well as started a website. \r\n\r\nIn this short time our numbers have grown and the word is spreading! Our foremost importance is you, getting the music out there and heard is key. We\'ve worked with bands throughout the United States, France, Greece, Sweden, South Africa, Australia, Italy, Switzerland and many other locations . We\'re based on the principle of true, honest promotion and work hard to do just that. Everything from interviews, reviews, promotions, help with bookings and the list goes on! We work with all genre\'s of metal.You can contact us here to inquire about anything and be assured a fairly quick response. Welcome aboard, join the metal hoardes.','promo packs - info@themetalreview.com - press packs send to news@themetalreview.com','http://www.facebook.com/TheMetalReview/info','http://www.themetalreview.com','','','0','4190',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-metal-review'),(263,0,88,88,'Davide Swarup','A musician :)','','http://www.facebook.com/davideswarup/info','http://www.davideswarup.com','','http://www.reverbnation.com/davideswarup','0','4172',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','davide-swarup'),(264,0,1,1,'MOH','MOHIT \'M.O.H\' THAKUR - (Power House Of Entertainment) - Coming straight from the capital, New Delhi, who loves to entertain people through his passion for music, started out as a Dancer, now is a Music Artist.\r\n\r\nAfter being betrayed by most of the people from his friends to family...he has only one thing left to move forward with...and that is \'his love for music\'. He was never supported for this by anyone except by his elder brother \"Rohit \'Badmash\' Thakur\" but despite of all that hardship...he has become self - dependent & this dream means everything to him now.\r\n\r\nNobody has taught him anything, he\'s a self learnt artist, trying to make it big in a place where the passion for entertainment has been forgotten...and all people care is about \'fame & money\'...\r\n\r\nBut M.O.H\'s music is all about creativity & originality, he won\'t make the obvious songs which people wanna listen. But the opposite...he talks about life and its hardship, love and its consequences, & more importantly he focuses on an individual & his problems & human psychological nature. Basically, he keeps it real & crazy.\r\n\r\nEvery time he does something, its always different. Those who will understand him & his music, they will, no doubt, love his personality & nature. And whatever is on the outside of him, its the same on the inside. He has strict rules that he follows & his pride and honor means everything. And, he wants to create a new style and taste and so far, he\'s been experimenting with his songs in a number of different ways...\r\n\r\nThrough his experience in life, he knows that everyone has suffered with pain and loneliness, and this has made him kind to others but his kindness is taken as a weakness !!! Why is it like that ? he doesn\'t get it ? There is too much selfishness, hatred & jealousy which is growing more & more & that is why, he talks about how to keep going in life, no matter how much hard it gets...So, all he wants is to share his story & his views. He wants to see a peaceful world...where one can understand true feelings of each other !!! But is that even possible ?\r\n\r\nHe is passionate & hardworking and further more, he is ready to cross every obstacle which life throws at him !!!\r\n__________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\nAim - Change the whole view and perspective of Hip Hop in Indian Music Culture & start a new trend.\r\n                \r\n                    \" Music will never be the same.\" - M.O.H\r\n__________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\nM.O.H - stands for My Other Half !!!\r\n[Rapper/ Singer/ Lyricist / Dancer / Story / Writer / Music composer & Beat maker.] \r\n\r\nBackground Story - Hes the one who rules the world of Indian Rapper, hes been also putting himself in all sorts of the genre of hardcore, love, life and other based tracks. Hes famous for his looks, lyrics, attitude and rap style.\r\n\r\nHe has promised to succeed no matter what happens, gonna fulfill his \'\'only\'\' dream of becoming an entertainer a reality. He knows he\'ll be big but for that to happen, unfortunately, it will take some time and patience. \r\n\r\n2012 is his new beginning and from here and out...he\'ll grow bigger and stronger...\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/TheRealMOH/info','','http://soundcloud.com/mohakamctrigga','http://www.reverbnation.com/mohakamctrigga','0','4165',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','moh'),(265,0,2,2,'Chandresh Kudwa','Learning to play the Guitar was quite an accident, I must say.. it changed my whole life. Cant imagine what I would have been If I wasn\'t a musician...! \r\nI am currently touring with my latest project \"Axe-tortion\" which is a collaboration between guitar players from across the country that I have recently started and also in the process of releasing my 2nd Solo Instrumental album titled \"The Conqueror\".','','http://www.facebook.com/kudwachandresh/info','http://www.chandreshkudwa.com','http://soundcloud.com/chandreshkudwa','','0','4159',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','chandresh-kudwa'),(266,0,89,89,'Meghdhanush','With the colors of a Meghdhanush (rainbow) in heart, a passion in soul and a purpose of spreading smiles in the world through a medium none other and better than music, a group of young budding musicians from Ahmedabad- India, came up and above all in late 2009.\r\n\r\nMeghdhanush is a hindi rock band that believes in their passion more than anything else; a band that believes in the power of music to overcome all the negative energy and spread flurry of positivity and peace all over the world. With a vision of a happy, peaceful and smiling humanity, Meghdhanush primarily believes in creativity, originality and freshness in their music. This inspires Meghdhanush to give some original, soothing, peaceful and heart-touching compositions in the genre of Desi Experimental Rock. With an optimum blend of sheer hard work, training of Indian Classical Music and Blessings of almighty, something irresistible is bound to be born.\r\n\r\nSo come, celebrate, get blown away & join for the amazing journey called Life with the seven colors of Meghdhanush: Music-Smile-Scream-Happiness-Love-Passion-Celebration of life...!\r\n\r\nSince their birth in late 2009, on the way to their vision of spreading music for happiness, Meghdhanush have given their performances to rock the music lovers at various occasions.\r\n\r\nAnd the journey has just begun..!!','Paresh Pahuja - +91 992 431 4794, +91 955 888 4343','http://www.facebook.com/TheMeghdhanush/info','http://www.meghdhanush.in','http://soundcloud.com/user3704472','','0','4149',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','meghdhanush'),(267,0,90,90,'Dammit','Dammit is an Alt Rock/Alt Punk/Garage act started recently in 2010. It consists of 6 wishful thinking, idealistic, idiotic, composers who say music is the one thing that keeps them sane.\r\n\r\n  Dammit released their debut EP called \"Confused\" in october 2010. The cover art was silly as hell. The EP got bashed by a few critics and praised by some others including american music blog beatplay.com.\r\n\r\n  This music is dedicated by Dammit to all those who are bored out of their minds with capitalism, communism, tv, internet, radio, their car, their pending loan payments, credit card bills, irritating boyfriends and girlfriends, nagging wives and husbands, idiotic employers, corrupt governments, endless commercials expecting them to buy everything on the planet and basically every aspect of their lives in general. We want you to listen to the music and take whatever meaning you want from it, whatever gives you your own personal high and get lost in the music for a few minutes at least...let the music take you where your heart should be......\r\nThanks for listening and stuff. cheers!\r\n','dammitinfo@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/Dammitrock/info?ref=ts','','','','0','4136',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dammit'),(268,0,91,1,'.fire on dawson','Fire On Dawson is a German rock band from Karlsruhe , Baden-Wrttemberg , which was founded in 2005. Their music was a mix of funk metal and crossover style of the early Red Hot Chili Peppers, which, however, with access of the Indian frontman changed towards alternative rock.\r\n\r\nHistory\r\nThe band was founded in autumn 2005 by Moritz Lietz Mayer (drums), Nicolas Morales Ocampo (guitar) and Martin Sunday (bass). It originated ideas for songs in very open framework, with no limits in style. So step by step to a growing pool of ideas. In spring 2006, then came after numerous auditions Ankur Batra added as a singer. With it, the style of rather funky rock to alternative rock with metal character was amended and composes the first own songs.\r\n\r\nBy the swing in the harder direction soon, the desire grew stronger, to have a second guitarist. That the band was in Manuel Odendahl, but it has been now prescribed his electric projects. In 2007, then began the first recordings for the debut album 7 symptom . But Odendahl and Ocampo due to musical reorientation and change of study location, the left band in mid-2007, the band faced a problem: there was a guitarist.\r\n\r\nThis time they found - no audition - by personal contact in Markus Stricker. By summer 2009, the band played in this lineup.\r\n\r\nThe debut album was completed and released in the same year. It is in the press as \"music with a lot of heart and feeling, which knows quite touching.\" The song End Of May their album in 2007 on the HP Compilation New Stars of Rock and Pop published with a circulation of 40,000 along with 9 others.','mail@fireondawson.com','http://www.facebook.com/fireondawson/info','http://www.fireondawson.com','','','0','4135',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','fire-on-dawson'),(269,0,5,5,'Isolation In Infamy','','Info@ImmortalPathManagement.com','http://www.facebook.com/IIIofficial/info','http://isolationininfamy.com/','','','0','4111',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','isolation-in-infamy'),(270,0,3,3,'Sonic Flare','It is a daunting task to write an introduction of a band like Sonic Flare.  Simply because, over the years, it has had many beginnings.  So may be it makes sense to start at the very beginning.\r\n\r\nLet me take you back to the time in the mid 90s when Neeraj and Jongky were wandering aimlessly around the streets of Tumkur as engineering students.   For the folks who do not know, Tumkur is a little town tucked away in the back of beyond.  Due to a serious lack of social life and also potential eye candy, they decided to engage themselves in something more serious and less frivolous than obtaining an engineering degree.  In time, they became a part of the college band which shot their stud status to dizzying heights  in Tumkur, that is.\r\n\r\nA few years later, a scrawny pimple faced teenager sauntered in to the same college.  The young and impressionable Ajit was captivated with the demigod status of Neeraj and Jongky.  He was determined, he wanted some of the action for himself.  Ajit went on to form a band of his own, and soon another band was thrown in the face of the hapless, unsuspecting engineering students of Tumkur.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately you can only take so many years to complete an engineering degree, however hard you try.  Four years later, they came out of college armed with an engineering degree in one hand and a guitar in the other.  It soon became obvious to them that the degree had more weight and thus music was put on the backburner for a while as they got busy in their respective jobs.\r\n\r\nSoon enough, to the shock and dismay of no one in particular, the monotony of a regular job set in. And what else did they do but turn to music. This was the second beginning.  Martin an old friend from another engineering college in Tumkur (where else) joined the trio as vocalist.  A massive hunt for a drummer was launched via advertisements on the internet.  Elaborate auditions were planned for the anticipated response.Only one person queued up outside the house for the job.  Needless to say, he was selected. And thus,Vinay Raghavan aka Vinay,Vinnie,Rags made his grand entry and Sonic Flare was born.  This was 2002.\r\n\r\nThe band began jamming in Neerajs house regularly when Martin moved out of the city for professional reasons.  And you would think that this long story comes to an end here.  Alas!! No such joy.  Yet another beginning right here.  Vinay roped in Saurabh as the vocalist and in a few years time, the band carved a name and space for itself in Bangalore.  Things were finally falling in place when suddenly Saurabh decided to take a break from the band to pursue an MBA.   This was circa 2009.\r\n\r\nVinay, in the short span of five long years, had assumed the position of problem solver, manager, gig magnet, carpet duster and the like.  With his vast network, he was able to convince the young and effervescent Priyanka to join the band as a guest vocalist till the time that Saurabh got back.  Priyanka apart from hugely shifting the average age of the band to the right side of 30, managed to infuse a new freshness to the sound of the band. Soon enough, the band had a huge fan following and were performing in prime venues in Bangalore.  Rags soon roped in Nikhil as a vocalist to perform with the band.  Apart from further shifting the average age to the right side of 30, Nikhil brought in a new zest to the band.  Needless to say, Sonic Flare as it stands now is getting more and more popular with the crowds and the road ahead surely looks promising.\r\n\r\nYou would think that this long story would end here, right?  Wrong. Sonic Flare has just begun !','','http://www.facebook.com/sonicflare.bangalore/info','http://sonicflare.in','','','0','4071',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sonic-flare'),(271,0,92,92,'Ear split','THE EAR SPLIT is an Indian Thrash Metal band from Shimla, formed in 2008.\r\nP.S. METAL is NOT just noisy music with inhuman screaming, it is our way of fuelling the youth with hope and positivity.\r\nWe prefer our music to be LOUD and right through people\'s ears.\r\nAnd for those who judge us by our looks or the long hair, we\'re just as human as you.. so chill!','+919816002214 +919882205046','http://www.facebook.com/earsplittheband/info?ref=ts','http://theearsplit.com','http://soundcloud.com/theearsplit','','0','4054',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ear-split'),(272,0,63,63,'Pip Of The Fourth Mother','','email@potfmtheband.com','http://www.facebook.com/POTFM/info','http://www.potfmtheband.com','','','0','4027',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','pip-of-the-fourth-mother'),(273,0,2,2,'Gaurav Dagaonkar','Gaurav Dagaonkar is a Music Director from Mumbai, India . He has made his debut in Vikram Bhatt\'s - \'Lanka\'. An ex IIM-A passout, Gaurav is currently doing the music for Rajeev Khandelwal-Prachi Desai starrer \"J for Joker\". Gaurav is also the composer-singer of the popular college anthem \"College Days\".','','http://www.facebook.com/dagaonkargaurav/info','','','','0','4008',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','gaurav-dagaonkar'),(274,0,3,3,'The Bicycle days','The Bicycle Days are a 4 member alternative band.\r\n\r\nListen:\r\n\r\nwww.myspace.com/thebicycledays\r\nwww.reverbnation.com/thebicycledays','thebicycledays@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/thebicycledays/info','','http://soundcloud.com/the-bicycle-days','www.reverbnation.com/thebicycledays','0','3976',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-bicycle-days'),(275,0,2,2,'Chronic Phobia','Metch0ol\r\n\r\nhttp://chronicphobia.bandcamp.com/','','http://www.facebook.com/chronicphobiaindia/info','http://chronicphobia.bandcamp.com/','http://soundcloud.com/chronicphobia','','0','3956',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','chronic-phobia'),(276,2,1,1,'Artillerie','Artillerie is a 5 member metal mayhem squad from New Delhi and have been playing together for almost 4 years.Armed with an extreme edge of brutality and musicianship,The Band has established a reputation for its relentless live performances and intense songwriting and are also considered to be one of the country\'s premier extreme metal acts.\r\n\r\nTheir EP \'New Offensive\' was released by RSJ as a part of the Extreme Metal Madness compilation in 2008.\r\n\r\nBesides doing shows,The Band released its first full length concept album called \'ERADEFILED\',which has been put up as a free download on their official website- www.artillerie.in.\r\n\r\nRecently the band has been nominated by Rolling stones metal awards for almost 6 categories which include Best metal Album,Band,Artwork,Drummer,Vocalist and Guitarist.\r\n\r\nso all said and done, we hope you enjoy our shows!\r\n\r\n\r\n','Noble Luke; Raul Belgard - M +91 9958549637; +91 9999160324','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Artillerie/26163803884?sk=info','http://www.artillerie.in','http://soundcloud.com/artillerie','','0','3903',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 12:55:21',222,'[\"\"]','[\"Noble Luke; Raul Belgard - M +91 9958549637; +91 9999160324\"]','artillerie'),(277,0,11,11,'kARNATRiix','kARNATRiix is the soul-soothing culmination of a band of musicians experiments with different styles and sounds, much like a new colour produced by the skillful combination of various hues and shades.\r\n\r\nIt is contemporary and yet traditional. It is not simple and yet not complicated. It is electronica and also acoustica. You can chill out or just sit in silent contemplation as the music fills up your senses. Misguided and conflicting it might seem, but the music is direct and clear, offering Indian classical creations in a new age package to people all over the world.\r\n\r\nkARNATRiixs music has elements of jazz, blues, rock, trance, funk, and classical sounding in perfect harmony with the Carnatic kritis of Saint Thyagaraja.\r\n\r\nkARNATRiix can be contacted by\r\n\r\ne-mail @ : karnatriix@gmail.com\r\n\r\nkARNATRi