L,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-juice'),(279,0,82,82,'Rex Vijayan','I\'m a guitarist,composer and music producer.\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/RexVijayan/info','http://www.avial.in','http://soundcloud.com/avial','','0','3869',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rex-vijayan'),(280,0,93,93,'Chet Faker','','info@chetfaker.com','http://www.facebook.com/Chetfaker/info','http://www.chetfaker.com','http://soundcloud.com/chet-faker','','0','3850',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','chet-faker'),(281,0,81,81,'SILVER TEARS','Silver Tears have arrived and are poised to be part of the cookie called NWOIHM. In a time when majority of National bands are too self-involved to create music that anyone can relate to, its a welcome change that Silver Tears dont take themselves too seriously and are clearly having fun whilst still developing their\r\nsound.\r\nThese six lads are the sauce to an Indian band sandwich. They pull together the thick sliced foundations of honest, shout-loud songs from bands like Dream Theater and Textures yet still manage to cover the acquired taste of storytelling lyrics- an art highly favored by the present day kings of rock n roll- Porcupine tree. Its impressive that Silver Tears manage to remain influenced by some great International bands yet have weaved enough of their own uplifting, street-smart quality and demeanor into their music, making them incomparable to any singular band in todays scene.','contact@silvertearstheband.com ','http://www.facebook.com/silvertearstheband/info','http://www.silvertearstheband.com','http://soundcloud.com/silvertears','http://www.reverbnation.com/silvertears','0','3833',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','silver-tears'),(282,0,49,49,'Kalodin','Kalodin is a musical outfit consisting of 4 central members, with occasional collaborative ventures featuring several guest artistes, and their creative contributions to various projects.\r\n\r\nThe members of Kalodin hitherto include Davin Shakya on lead guitars, Omeo on rhythm guitar, Bikash Rai on bass guitar, and Gobind on Drums.\r\n\r\nIn our first album, \"The Bestial Ritualism of Harlotry\", QJ was part of our whole production. Sadly, he had to leave due to personal reasons.\r\n\r\n*Kalodin is currently unsigned, self written, recorded and produced; with a full-length album released, entitled \"The Bestial Ritualism of Harlotry\" (2010).\r\n\r\nKalodin\'s music follows closely after, but not restricted to, the audio subcultures of modern rock and roll; namely within the metal genre.\r\n\r\nListeners can expect to enjoy a large incorporation of heavy metal, death metal, black metal and symphonic melodies.\r\n\r\nRegardless if one prefers dark and heavy guitar rhythms over the quaking hell-swept speed of percussion beats, or even the sheer fury of vocal grunts\r\nand screams; Kalodin ensures that there is something for everyone.\r\n\r\nFor in the family of metal, we are one.\r\n\r\n====================================================\r\n\r\n\"Reviews & Interviews\"\r\n-----------------------------\r\n\r\n* \"They take the genre and your imagination further, and with more time under their belts (and a live drummer), they could be a terrifying force with which to contend.\" -- Metaleater, North America. \r\n\r\n( http://www.metaleater.com/albumreviews-kalodin2010.php)\r\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n* \"So the whole album is a real kick in the ass. The band succeed in offering to the listener a great dose of brutality. A grim brutality with catchy melodies. Their black/death metal is a real pleasure to hear and I bet to see on stage.\" -- Yargla, France. \r\n\r\n(http://yargla.over-blog.com/article-kalodin-the-bestial-ritualism-of-harlotry-62122359.html)\r\n---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n* \"KALODIN once again surprises with Interlewd: Into Purity, a keyboard-driven track with a haunting female vocals, and a heavy atmosphere. However, it seems that the music takes a turn from this point onwards, with the band focussing more on the mood of the music instead of the speed from here on. Numbers like Face of War, while not as fast as the first half of the album, are still crushing and chilling.\" -- Heavy Metal Tribune, Singapore\r\n\r\n(http://heavymetaltribune.blogspot.com/2010/10/album-review-bestial-ritualism-of.html)\r\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n* \"I often lean to seek for the it in every other music I listen to, in relation or in comparison to these good bands. Saying these, I think the band in hand currently, Kalodin, after having a few listens have hit me hard enough, informing about the sharp existence of the it. The Bestial Ritualism of Harlotry may be one of the finest releases in symphonic black metal Ive heard recently, and is also likely to go well with the followers of any other metal subgenre than that.\" -- KtmRocks, Nepal. \r\n\r\n(http://ktmrocks.com/site/?p=539)\r\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n* \"Kalodin are a sure winner for Metal Hammer\'s golden gods \'global metal\' award.\" -- Rhys Stevenson, Terrorizer Magazine, UK\r\n\r\n(http://truecultheavymetal.com/blog6.php/2010/09/02/rhys-re-viewz-vol-21-extreme-metal-entities-persefone-non-opus-dei-helmskey-kalodin)\r\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n* \"Interview with Kalodin\" -- HMT, Singapore\r\n\r\n(http://heavymetaltribune.blogspot.com/2010/08/interview-with-kalodin.html)\r\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n* \"Interview with Davin\" -- KtmRocks, Nepal\r\n\r\n(http://ktmrocks.com/site/?page_id=15)\r\n\r\n========================================================\r\n\r\n','Davin Shakya ( davin.shakya@hotmail.com)','http://www.facebook.com/Kalodin/info','','','http://www.reverbnation.com/kalodin','0','3748',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','kalodin'),(283,0,94,94,'VERSES','VerseS debuted in 2008 through various inter-collegiate gigs. Impressed by their consistent successes at various venues, Flying Machine endorsed them for a year (2010-2011). They consolidated their success streak by releasing an EP on May 1st 2011, subsequently signing on to MCube Records Label. Their EP Threshold, the title track of which coalesces the themes of a potential musical revolution with enchanting mystic undertones, sold over a thousand copies within the first five months of its release.\n\nBesides headlining a host of shows in and outside Bangalore, this Bangalore-based band has also opened at the Octoberfest 2010, finished as runners-up in the band-hunt to open for Metallica; supported international acts such as Lacuna Coil, Cypher 16, Fractalline; regularly winning both critical and popular acclaim, even for their individual performances. They are fresh from their Strawberry Fields Victory as well as IITM Live wire and will be representing India at the Global Battle of the Bands to be held in Bucharest, Romania later this year.\n\nAdditional Info\n\nCompetitions won: \n	VIT, Bangalore, 2008\n	Vibes 08 and 09, Sambhram college (twice) \n	MVIT  June 2008\n	MSRIT, 2009\n	Dayanand Sagar Institute of Technology, 2009\n	Reva Institute of Technology, 2009\n	Vistas 11, PES BBM Sept 2010\n	Festember 10 NIT Trichy Sept 2010\n	Autumn Muse, 11. St Johns Bangalore Aug 2010\n	Reliance Time-Out 11 July 2011\n	Riviera 2011, VIT, Vellore Jan 2011\n	Ananya 11, KSIT April 2011\n	Sea rock 11, BITS-PILANI GOA November 2011\n	Strawberry Fields 11, Nov 2011\n\nShows headlined at: \nHeadlined the following shows\n	R. L. Jalappa Institute of Technology \n	VIT, Bangalore \n	PES BBM, Bangalore\n	St Francis College, Bangalore\n	JSSIT, Bangalore\n	DBIT, Bangalore (Co-headliners with Swarathma)\n	UVCE, Bangalore, \n\n\n All the band members are accomplished in so many other ways and pursue their rocking dream that they share in common, even though their individual influences are varied. Fresh from their Strawberry Fields victory, Verses is looking forward to the release of their album and an All India Tour in the near future.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n','verses@live.co.uk','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Verses/149157301792922','http://www.versesuk.com','','','149157301792922','1656',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','verses'),(284,0,3,3,'DISTORTION CULTURE','There is no greater sound than the sound of music. And with that in mind, 5 musicians came together to form a band that would echo the sound of music far and wide.\r\nDistortion culture was formed in the year 2009 as a progressive rock band by individuals who had different musical backgrounds from a guitarist who had a background in classical music to a novice drummer and bassist who had nothing in common at all except for their love for music. The band was thus formed with 5 members whove amalgamated their different styles and sounds into the energy-rich, power packed music that Distortion Culture is identified by. Having played in numerous college\r\nlevel competitions since the bands inception, theyve gathered a lot of appreciation and awe wherever they go. A melodic and progressive rock taste is what they\'ve come to be famous for. Some of the crowning moments in our journey so far has been winning IIM-B 2011, NIT Calicut 2010, finishing first runners-up at Cobalt Skies 2009 Bangalore Medical College, the very first competition the band took part in with the guitarist and bassist receiving a special mention by the judges of the event and the two maiden compositions, Unforeseen Truth and Mahaganapathim blowing the audience away, second runners-up at MCC, Ambedkar medical college, Christ university and being listed in top ten bands in NLS Strawberry fields 2010. There was no looking back from then onward with invitations to play at Palace Grounds, Strawberry Fields(NLS), The Kyra Theater, Yamaha Asia beats, Freedom Jam,\r\nLegends of Rock, My Opus radio , Fete De La Musique, Vh1 Media Nights and various other college events. A well blended feel of classical Indian music with the raw energy of\r\nprogressive metal is what the band is all about, with influences such as Dream Theater, Mr. Big, Liquid Tension Experiment, Animals as leaders, Porcupine Tree, Tool and Indian bands such as Motherjane and Avial, they have come out with a unique sound that identifies them as fresh and original in every sense. Distortion Cultures success so far is a mere reflection of the band\'s outstanding energy and originality in their music. And this is just the beginning.\r\nCheers \\m/','distortion.culture@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/distortionculture/info','http://www.distortionculture.co.nr','','http://www.reverbnation.com/distortionculture','0','3651',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','distortion-culture'),(285,0,95,95,'Khawar Jawad','Khawar Jawad, the singer , The music producer, the \'Bandya HO \' guy, who made a mark on the music world after singing on the \'Khuda Kay Liye; Movie Soundtrack \"bandeya ho \" \"mahi way \" and also composed and did music of \"ALLAH HOO \" \r\n\r\nKhawar Jawad is easily one of the most promising singers on the block and with a 2nd album in the making, it seems Khawar is set to conquer.\r\n\r\nThe last time we heard about Bulleh Shah was when Rabbi Shergill adapted his poetry in the popular fusion Bulla Ki Jaana And now Khawar Jawad adapts another piece of writing of this Sufi Punjabi poet from Pakistan to compose an enticing number Bandya .Ably supported by the vocals of Farah Zala, the Sufi number is infused with lively guitaring and drumming to give it a rock feel. The pure Punjabi lyrics by Bulleh Shah are instilled with some English lines though not in the usual rap format.\r\n\r\nKhawar Jawad has stolen the hearts of millions.With such confidence and Strong Will power,Khawar Jawad will Indeed Acheive All his Goals Soon.\r\n\r\nworked with director Shoaib Mansoor in his film KHUDA KAY LIYE and produced Three songs of that movie including \"BANDEYA HOO\", \"ALLAH HOO\" and 3rd one is \"MAHI WAY\"\r\n\r\n\"Bandya Hoo \" was highly regarded and appreciated in india and all over the world...\r\nand than remix was done by SONY BMG INDIA ....\r\nthan hit another one as MAULA....\r\n\r\nHis new album was launched by Fire Records by the title of \"MAULA \" \r\n\r\nAvailable in Market....\r\n\r\nanother projects with shoiab mansoor were \"ishq supreme anarkali \" and \" ishq nachaya kar thayya thayya \" music by khawar jawad and directed by shoiab mansoor......\r\nrecently khawar jawad has featured Quratulain baloch baloch (QB ) in his song peera ....it was sufi trance....\r\n\r\ngave a tribute to RIP LEGENDARY MICHEAL JACKSON through \"HEAL THE WORLD \" , a small gesture of love to the KING OF POP...','','http://www.facebook.com/khawarjawad/info','','http://soundcloud.com/khawarjawad','','0','3617',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','khawar-jawad'),(287,0,22,5,'Mandeep Sethi','    Representing San Francisco Universal Zulu Nation as well as the global Hip-Hop scene, Mandeep Sethi is a young yet seasoned emcee/DJ from that has shown\r\nand proven his ability to rhyme and freestyle with the best. As a member of Zulu Nation, Mandeep was raised by the 5 elements of\r\nhip-hop: emceeing, djing, breakdancing, graffiti, and KNOWLEDGE. For Sethi, the microphone represents a catalyst of change, rhyming about social consciousness as well as cultural awarenesss while remaining true to the undefinable essence of hip hop\'s versatility.\r\n    Mandeep\'s primary focus is to educate the youth about the circumstances in which we are living in and resonate ancient culture within them, revealing the\r\ngods in all of us. From rhyming to djing, music serves as the language translating beats and words into scripts and hymns. The music speaks for itself.\r\n\r\nMANDEEP HAS PERFORMED WITH/ALONGSIDE:\r\n\r\nAFRIKA BAMBAATAA [ ZULU NATION ]\r\nZIGGY MARLEY\r\nDEAD PREZ\r\nMICHAEL FRANTI & SPEARHEAD\r\nCAMP LO\r\nDIAMOND D\r\nKILLAH PRIEST [WU TANG CLAN, SUNZ OF MAN]\r\nDILATED PEOPLES [RAKAA IRISCIENCE + EVIDENCE + DJ BABU]\r\nRZA [WU TANG CLAN]\r\nAESOP + BICASSO [LIVING LEGENDS]\r\nMURS [LIVING LEGENDS]\r\nNON STOP BHANGRA [SF]\r\nAKIL THE MC [ JURASSIC 5]\r\nBAYONICS\r\nSILA\r\nDENGUE FEVER\r\n\r\nPRODUCER FAMILIA::\r\nPovan Beats\r\nSikh Knowledge\r\nSpanix Graza\r\nMidpoint Beats\r\nDeacon LF\r\nDJ Descry\r\nGnotes\r\nWazulu Da ill Dravidian\r\nDoc Bladez\r\nMr. Rey\r\n\r\nEMCEE FAMILIA::\r\nSahku\r\nSpanix Graza\r\nPovan \r\nBwan\r\n\r\nDJ FAMILIA::\r\nThe Mighty DJ Delrokz\r\nBeats ME\r\nDj Concerned\r\nDJ Canyon Cody\r\nDoc Bladez\r\nDJ Rav-E\r\nDj Jimmy Love\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/mandeepsethiX/info','','http://soundcloud.com/mandeepsethi','','0','3598',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','mandeep-sethi'),(288,0,97,97,'Benea Reach','The Oslo-based metal band Benea Reach is widely considered to become the future leader of Norwegian metal. The band made an early career statement by receiving a Norwegian Grammy nomination for their 2006 debut album, Monument Bineothan. Mixing dark melodies and heavy grooves with hardcore attitude, they soon gathered fans from all corners of hard and heavy music. \r\n	\r\nWith their 2008 release, Alleviat, they returned even stronger. With a heavier yet more accessible sound they stated their position as one of the main nationwide metal acts and received yet another Grammy nomination. Danish studio-wizard Tue Madsen (The Haunted, Mnemic, Sick Of It All) was the man to mix down the monumental masterpiece. The song \"Awakening\" appeared on the big screen in 2009 as one of the main songs on the Dead Snow (Dd Sn) soundtrack. \r\n\r\nAfter several tours in Scandinavia, Europe and a headlining tour in India, they have become an experienced and highly rated live-act. They have shared the stage with bands like Dillinger Escape Plan, Cult Of Luna, Slipknot, Underoath, All That Remains, Bhayanak Maut, Zao, Insense, Enslaved, Dropkick Murphys and The Chariot to name a few. Having co-produced both albums and produced all three of their music videos themselves, with drummer Marco Storm doing direction, digital effects and post production, the band shows talent beyond just songwriting and performing.','','http://www.facebook.com/beneareach/info','http://www.beneareach.com','','','0','3587',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','benea-reach'),(289,0,31,31,'BIDROHA','It is a THRASH/HEAVY metal band formed in early 2010 with the initiation of the front man Saurab(EX KAFAN/ARACHNIDS) & Lead guitarist Zantu(EX KAFAN). Both of them were in search of a drummer which was completed in March 5th, 2010. In the beginning the band was named KAYAKAIRAN (literal meaning: REVOLUTION) which was later changed to BIDROHA (literal meaning: RETALIATION). Bass guitars was being played by Saugat Adhikari (EX KAFAN) but later he left the band due to his studies and all; after that Bsal Manandhar who was a colleague with Zantu in a call center joined the band. Then they began to make music together... So far they have recorded their 3 originals and are planning for an album in late 2011 or if not in early 2012. With their music, they are \'retaliating\' against all the social evils prevailing in the society in the current scenario and lyrics are especially focused towards POLITICAL SARCASM. The band is mostly influenced by the music of SLAYER, SEPULTURA, MEGADETH, EVILE n some other THRASH METAL bands.','bidroha@live.com','http://www.facebook.com/BIDROHA/info','','','','0','3559',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','bidroha'),(290,0,2,2,'Airport','Whats flying? Lets ask the flightmeisters.\r\n\r\nArijit says, When you stop chasing and accept what you have or dont have, things just start to happen.\r\n\r\nArijit Datta had been writing heart-touching melodies for years. On another stage, Vinay Lobo was strumming every genre he could think of from blues, funk, reggae, rock, jazz and R&B. They wondered what would happen if Arijits old world Hindi jazz were to meet Vinays crunchy blues.\r\n\r\nThey dialed a number that rang in a Bandra flat. Amit Ahuja (known to friends only as AmZ) answered and when Arijit asked if hed like to bring his bass along for a trip, the band had found its bassist.\r\n\r\nZohran Miranda was an Oman-based musician with bands like Klarity and Human Touch. When he quit his job to pursue his music dreams in Mumbai, it seemed natural for him to hop on board, with his guitar.\r\n\r\nTogether, they form Airport, making you want to stop and ride with their music as they fly you through a myriad of emotions. Airports songs are primarily in Hindi with the characteristic Arijit flavour of Urdu infusions. They touch you, uplift you, rock you, get you to tap your feet, make you smile and reflect about things that were or may be. \r\n\r\nAirport had a successful launch in December 2009 at Del Italia, Mumbai. They played to a packed house of 250 + people. Since then, the band has played at several youth festivals and hang-outs, corporate events and live music venues across India. Airport recently played in the prestigious NH7 Festival in Pune, December 2010.\r\n\r\nAirport consists of Arijit Datta on vocals and guitar, Vinay Lobo on lead guitar, Amit Ahuja on bass, Zohran Miranda on rhythm guitar and Ashwin Andrews on drums.\r\n\r\n-bio written by the lovely Idea Smith','arijit.datta@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/thebandairport','http://www.myspace.com/thebandairport','http://soundcloud.com/airport-2','','172744261818','3558',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','airport'),(291,0,98,98,'La Abuela Disco','La Abuela Disco es una banda formada por Romny Freitez en la batera, Fuaz Kassen en la guitarra, Fauadz Kassen como vocalista y segunda guitarra, Eduardo Daza en el Teclado y Arnoldo Freitez en el bajo.\r\nInfluenciada por diversas corrientes musicales, como rock alternativo, post-grunge, electrnica e indie, esta banda naci a mediados del 2009 bajo la inquietud de hacer msica alternativa y a su vez original, los integrantes se encargaron de reunir viejos amigos para concretar el proyecto musical logrando as presentarse en diversos festivales y locaciones del pas.\r\nEn la actualidad la banda est en proceso de promocion de su primer album de estudio q lleva por nombre \"POLVO LUNAR\" Y salio a mediados del ao 2011\r\n','Fauadz Kassen','http://www.facebook.com/pages/La-Abuela-Disco/112024625510278?sk=info','http://www.laabueladisco.com','http://soundcloud.com/laabueladisco','http://www.reverbnation.com/laabueladisco','0','3547',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','la-abuela-disco'),(292,0,0,0,'Hard Electric Tour','Hard Electric Tour is an alternative winter music festival tour in India under the rock umbrella genres of pop, punk, hardcore, emo etc etc... \r\n\r\nStarting this winter 2010 and the tour would become an annual event going forward. The tour is a young baby, but she has a dream. This december she wants to travel to three cities with a basket full of rock n roll music.','','http://www.facebook.com/hetour/info','http://hardelectrictour.com','','','0','3543',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','hard-electric-tour'),(293,0,99,99,'The Pretty Blue Guns','The Guns recently finished recording their sophomore album \"SHED YOUR SKIN\", which will be released over the second half of April 2011. The album will be available at all the launch shows nationwide.\r\n\r\nhttp://issuu.com/bitocreative/docs/prettyblueguns_shedyourskin_pk\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n==============================\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Pretty Blue Guns are four best friends who love making a noise. They have been playing shows all over South Africa for the past few years with some of the countrys top acts, ranging from small intimate theatre shows to huge festivals.\r\n\r\n\"...almal wat ek ken wat die Gewere al sien rook het, reken dit is spiekeries.\"  litnet.co.za\r\n\r\nTheir style has been described as gritty blues rock, with influences ranging from early Robert Johnson era blues and Tom Waits to modern rock giants such as The White Stripes or Kings Of Leon.\r\n\r\nWhat the Pretty Blue Guns do well, is introduce this genre of music to an audience that would not normally be familiar with it, back to a time when music was still considered an art. Not only do they introduce it, but they set the standard for others to follow. -morethanmusic.co.za\r\n\r\nThey recently released an album entitled Cutting Heads, the name of which is a reference to blues buskers in the 1920s that would battle for tips from passers-by, playing the same traditional blues songs as other buskers, except finding ways to make the songs more interesting and more entertaining in order to capture the attention and respect of the crowds. The album has been received with critical acclaim:\r\n\r\nn indrukkende debuut en n sterk kandidaat vir die plaaslike rock-album van die jaar toekenning. -Beeld (4/5 stars)\r\n\r\nI can honestly say these guys, with the help of a brilliant producer and sound engineer have made an album thats difficult to switch off once you started listening. -samusicblog.co.za\r\n\r\nif you are a fan of any version of the blues, you will love Cutting Heads. - twindie.net\r\n\r\nits a great album, I can almost describe the album as modern vintage, uniting the old and new into a complete package that is Cutting Heads.  morethanmusic.co.za\r\n\r\nA fine, fine release from a shit-hot band. Highly recommended. - Muse Magazine (4/5 Stars)\r\n\r\nThe Pretty Blue Guns do not follow the expectations of any particular \"scene\", and they have been praised for their heartfelt approach to the creation of music and their identity as a musical force that does not follow trends, but instead stays true to its roots. \r\n\r\nPick up you copy of \'Cutting Heads\' at the following stores:\r\n\r\nALL MUSICAS COUNTRY WIDE\r\nALL LOOK & LISTENS COUNTRY WIDE\r\nALL TOP CD\r\nALL PHASE 2\r\nALL MUSIC MOODS  STORES\r\n\r\nSUPER CD EASTRAND\r\nSUPER CD WESTGATE\r\nSUPER CD NELSPRUIT\r\nSUPER CD GLEN\r\n','lucavincenzo@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/prettyblueguns/info','http://www.prettyblueguns.co.za','http://soundcloud.com/prettyblueguns','','0','3530',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-pretty-blue-guns'),(294,0,3,3,'DJ Inferno','Welcome to DJ Inferno\'s Official Facebook Fan Page, You can find the latest mixsets , remixes, productions and gig updates.\r\n\r\nUpcoming Dates :\r\n\r\nNOV\r\n\r\n19/TBC\r\n04/BlueFrog (MUM)\r\n03/China House (MUM)\r\n\r\nOCT\r\n\r\n30/1Lounge (PUNE)\r\n29/BlueWaves (BLR)\r\n22/Private Party (BLR)\r\n16/Esko (BLR)\r\n14/O Bar (BLR)\r\n09/Esko (BLR)\r\n08/Private Party (BLR)\r\n\r\nSEP\r\n\r\n17/O2 Lounge (INDORE)\r\n4/TBC (GOA)\r\n3/Cafe Mambo (GOA)\r\n2/O Bar (BLR)\r\n\r\nAUG\r\n\r\n27/Private Party w/ Ma Faiza (BLR)\r\n26/O-BAR (BLR)\r\n20/Taj Mangalore + Paradise Isle Manipal\r\n\r\nJULY\r\n\r\n30/AMET Cruise Ship (CHE)\r\n29/BlueFrog (MUM)\r\n23/O2 Lounge (IND)\r\n22/NewsCafe (HYD)\r\n20/Pebble (BLR)\r\n17/Love Of Music Festival (BLR) \r\n15/Coco Bongo (BLR) \r\n13/Pebble (BLR)\r\n8/Coco Bongo (BLR)\r\n6/Pebble (BLR) \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nJUNE\r\n\r\n24/O Bar (Bangalore)\r\n18/Club Zeus (Bangalore)\r\n17/O Bar (Bangalore)\r\n11/Dugout (Bangalore)\r\n10/O Bar (Bangalore)\r\n05/Tech Music Festival @ Chancery (Bangalore)\r\n04/Ibiza (Kolkata)\r\n03/The Basement (Kolkata)\r\n\r\n\r\nMAY\r\n\r\n27/O Bar (BLR)\r\n21/Base Music Festival @ Chancery (BLR)\r\n20/O Bar (BLR)\r\n15/SuperNova Festival(BLR)\r\n13/O Bar (BLR)\r\n06/Coco Bongo (BLR)\r\n\r\nAPR\r\n\r\n10/Fuga(BLR)\r\n16/Fluid(MYSORE)\r\n24/Stone Water Grill(PUNE)\r\n\r\n\r\nMAR\r\n\r\n2/Pebble(BLR)\r\n4/TBA (GOA)\r\n5/Club Ivy (GOA)\r\n10/Ujjan Festival (KOL)\r\n11/Ujjan Festival (KOL)\r\n12/Ujjan Festival (KOL)\r\n\r\nFEB\r\n\r\n5/Club Night Flight (MANGALORE) [DAY]\r\n5/Club Paradise Isle (MANIPAL) [NIGHT]\r\n18/Lava Lounge (GOA)\r\n21/Shiva Palace w/ Karan/Raol/Nitin/Earthling (GOA)\r\n\r\n\r\nJAN \r\n\r\n2/Zanzibar (GOA)\r\n7/Manchester Bar (BLR)\r\n20/Shiva Palace (GOA)\r\n21/Aurus w/ Paul Taylor (MUM)\r\n23/Pebble (BLR)\r\n\r\nDEC \r\n\r\n4/Pebble w/ BT (BLR)\r\n10/Plush (KOL)\r\n11/Pebble w/ UMEK (BLR)\r\n17/Firangi Pani (MUM)\r\n18/Oz Bar (DEL)\r\n24/Manchester United Bar (BLR)\r\n26/9Bar (GOA)\r\n27/Sunburn (GOA)\r\n31/Quorom (INDORE) \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:: BIOGRAPHY ::\r\n\r\n\r\nMusic was never an unfamiliar territory for DJ Inferno, born into a family that loved and appreciated music in 1984; he spent all his juvenile life listening to all forms of music. At an early age of 16 when kids around him were still caught in the boy band and pop revolution, Inferno was firmly making his roots in the music communities world wide with a burning desire to acquire more knowledge about the specific genres. In a quick span of 2 years he had a wealth of music that most people did not even know existed, propelling him further on underground online music sharing communities, he was much respected. This was the inclining step to a DJ Career that just began with residencies in pubs in the City and guest appearances with the citys top DJs.\r\n\r\nAt a time when fresh house music was of the essence, Inferno was armed with some of the most exclusive and unreleased music that only a few could even dream about, unfortunately his immense talent only came into light when he was quickly identified and inducted in the Submerge Clan of DJs (www.submerge.in), an elite dance music promotion agency/community that only a select few are proud to be a part of, with international artists like Carl Cox, Ferry Corsten, Axwell, Copyright, Norman Doray and Indian artist like DJ Nikil Chinapa, Pearl, Nawed, Sanjay Dutta on their roster. Inferno was on the right path. \r\n\r\nRegular appearances at various clubs & venues across the country & outside was a part of Infernos roster, playing along side artists like DJ San (Fektive Recs, NL), Norman Doray & Arno Cost (Serial Recs, France), Copyright (Defected, UK) only pushed his skills beyond the comprehension of his peers. Performing on the same platform as these artists along with the biggest names in the Indian industry such as Jalabee Cartel, DJ Pearl, Nawed Khan, Sanjay Dutta etc Inferno was now standing on a solid foundation of musical knowledge, skill and experience, all this at an age of 23 adding to his belt a host of residencies across the city.\r\n\r\nDJ Inferno co-produces music under the moniker Audio Units\', their music has been getting some lush feedback from the bigwigs in the industry. \r\n\r\nBeing called back to perform at every venue only speaks volumes about the vibe and experience his music provides to audience from all walks and venues of all sizes, be it uplifting progressive trance, to jacking minimal house or pounding techno and of course his signature style of music that you will probably hear months later, you can be sure to have a packed house in awe and appreciation of the music.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:: CLUB APPEARANCES ::\r\n\r\n- International -\r\n\r\n* NEPAL - Club Galaxy (Kathmandu)\r\n\r\n\r\n- National - \r\n\r\n* GOA - Sunburn 2010 / Sunburn 2009 / Sunburn Afterdark 2008 / Loungefly / Zanzibar / Mambos / 9 Bar / Club Ivy / Shiva Palace\r\n\r\n* MUMBAI - Squeeze / Bar 21 / Aurus / Firangi Paani / Tote / BlueFrog\r\n\r\n* COCHIN - Le Meredien\r\n\r\n* TRIVANDRUM - Twist\r\n\r\n* PUNE - Flags / 1Lounge / Gaia / Stone Water Grill\r\n\r\n* DELHI - Oz Bar / Ivyz\r\n\r\n* KOLKATA - Plush / Amoda / Basement\r\n\r\n* INDORE - Quorom / O2 Lounge\r\n\r\n* BANGALORE - Manchester United Bar (Current Resident) / Sutra / F-Bar / Nero / Blue Bar / Fuga / Pebble / Zero-G / Hint / Amnesia  & More\r\n\r\n:: DISCOGRAPHY ::\r\n\r\nhttp://soundcloud.com/dj-inferno/\r\n\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/DJ.Infern0/info','http://www.djinferno.in','','','0','3481',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-inferno'),(295,0,100,100,'Boat Beam','La msica de Boat Beam provoca. Provoca sentimientos y pensamientos, provoca miedo y emocin Las canciones cambian tanto que es posible viajar por todas esas sensaciones al escuchar el disco o asistir a uno de sus conciertos.\r\n\r\nBoat Beam empez hace poco en la vida de la australiana Josephine Ayling. Josephine tuvo un grupo (Terapin) con unos amigos del instituto, en Sydney, su ciudad natal. Incluso llegaron a publicar un EP que tuvo buenas crticas, pero ella tena ganas de viajar y conocer mundo. Y eso es lo que hizo. Josephine viaj, conoci Per, Bolivia, Brasil, India, Tailandia, Taiwn, y lleg a Londres y acab haciendo lo inevitable: componiendo canciones. En Londres pas un tiempo trabajando y viviendo en una casa con otros 12 extranjeros. Y all supo cul sera su siguiente paso. Quera aprender otro idioma y decidi que, como haba aprendido algo de espaol en sus viajes, ira a Espaa.\r\n\r\nJosephine lleg a Madrid en 2006 para aprender castellano y conocer ms a fondo una cultura de la que slo saba los tpicos: toros, flamenco, siesta Estuvo tres meses, pero le llamaron desde Australia para algo importante. Se uni a un grupo llamado Sparkadia y volvi a Londres, esta vez para grabar un disco producido por Ben Hillier (productor del Think Tank, de Blur, entre muchos otros). Durante 2007 estuvo de gira por Australia e Inglaterra, Sparkadia actuaba abriendo para bandas como Elbow y The Thrills y poco a poco se iba asentando. Pero a finales de ao, Josephine suspiraba por volver a Espaa. A comienzos de 2008, se instal en Madrid.\r\n\r\nVino con un disco grabado a medias, entre giras y con varios colaboradores, en un estudio de Sydney. Y en Madrid sigui grabando mientras haca conciertos como solista. Un da conoci Alisha, una americana que haba tocado la viola en grupos de msica clsica, jazz, y rock. Se juntaron para probar las canciones con guitarra y viola y sonaban muy bien! Empezaron a tocar juntas y en uno de esos conciertos conocieron a Aurora, una chelista que haba tocado en varios proyectos en Madrid. Aurora llevaba tiempo con la idea de formar un grupo con gente con la que congeniara tanto en el plano musical como en el personal y por fin la haba encontrado. As naci Boat Beam. Alisha y Aurora aadieron sus instrumentos al disco que tena a medias Josephine y entre todas decidieron incorporar otros elementos como teclados y coros. Finalmente, acabaron la grabacin en septiembre.\r\n\r\nSus influencias musicales son muy variadas, desde Cinematic Orchestra y Jhann Jhannson, hasta Pink Martini, Lhasa, the Dresden Dolls, The Shins, Supergrass, The Pixies, Sonic Youth, y Why? Les encantan Fiona Apple y Juana Molina pero tambin la msica clsica de Satie y Debussy Muchas ideas surgen de libros, de escritores como Herman Hesse, Michael Ende, Patrick Sskind, Ian McEwan, Juan Rulfo, Jonathan Franzen, Virginia Woolf, Sylvia Plath, John Irving, Louis De Bernires y muchos ms. Las tres estn unidas por algo ms que la msica. Les interesa la ecologa y los asuntos que afectan el mundo. Les gusta viajar, leer, vivir. Y todo lo que aprenden y comparten acaba formando parte de las canciones. Esas canciones que provocan sentimientos, pensamientos, miedo, emocin Esas canciones que no te dejarn indiferente.','miguel@arigatocomunicacion.com','http://www.facebook.com/boatbeammusic/info','','','','0','3471',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','boat-beam'),(296,0,31,31,'Vhumi','Vhumi (June 14, 2008)\r\n\r\nTRACK LIST:\r\n1. Mrityu ko Tandab\r\n2. Balatkar\r\n3. Suicide\r\n4. Bhariya\r\n5. Stoned Hunter\r\n6. Shant Mahatma\r\n7. Live to thrill\r\n8. Aatanka','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Vhumi/157461386437?sk=info','','','','0','3471',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','vhumi'),(297,0,31,2,'Ankytrixx','He is a voyager of deep emotive cutting edge sound that has catapulted him to the halls of dance & fame, forever! \r\n\r\nAnkytrixx is an Indian Electronica DJ and producer. Currently ranked No.1 in India for Electronic Music on the VH1 MyFavDj Poll, he is a stalwart in the scene who started DJing 12 years ago. From being a respected voice whom the audience turn to for their musical education, to his own evolution and adaptation as an artist in the scene, Ankytrixx truly represents the sound of Indian EDM.\r\n\r\nFor more than a decade, Ankit has fast forwarded himself into one of the most contemporary and exciting acts in these modern times.A disco goers delight, hes has smiling crowds blissfully lost in speedy, jump-at-you performances with melodic goodness amplified in extravagant, chunky bass lines. His energetic and emotional shows capture the audience, as his energy flows off the console infecting them with euphoric dance floor power. \r\n\r\nCurrently Ankytrixx is enjoying superstar status as the chosen beat freak to play at swanky and sold-out venues in India like The Blue Frog, Pacha, Tantra, F Bar, Aurus and many more! \r\n\r\nHe has taken his brand of foot-stomping music to international clubs in Amsterdam, Berlin, Singapore, Bangkok, and Colombo while also headlining in some of the most prestigious festivals, like A.D.E Amsterdam Dance Event 2011, Sunburn (2010, 2011), Sula Fest 2012, Universal Religion (2009,2010,2011), Global Underground India (2011) and many more. \r\n\r\n2012 promises to be a big year for the dance floor blaster, with appearances at Universal Religion in Nepal and Tree of Life in Turkey, just to start! Catch him scorching the dance floor this European summer, with appearances in Clubs in Istanbul, Asmterdam, Berlin, Brussels and more!! \r\n\r\n In recent times Ankytrixx has shared stage space with legends of music spanning several genres of EDM. From John Digweed and Dave Seaman, to Armin Van Buren, Richie Hawtin, Axwell and Spartaque to Infected Mushroom, Ace Ventura, Liquid Soul, Zen Mechanics and many more! \r\n\r\nThe maestro spins his magic overlapping several EDM genres seamlessly, taking you on musical journeys through house, techno, progressive and psychedelic. Ankytrixx delivers consistently, both in terms of technique and tune, providing an overall performance package like very few DJs do.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n>>LINKS<<\r\n\r\nFacebook -  Ankytrixx\r\n\r\nMySpace - ankytrixx\r\n\r\nTwitter - ankytrixx\r\n\r\nSkype - ankytrixx\r\n\r\nSoundcloud -  ankytrixx\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n>> BOOKINGS & INQUIRIES <<\r\n\r\nAUDIOPHILE NETWORKS\r\n\r\nAliya Rashid\r\n\r\nPh# 9833414794\r\n\r\nbookings.ankytrixx@gmail.com\r\nbookings@ankytrixx\r\n\r\n','Audiophile Network','http://www.facebook.com/Ankytrixx/info','','http://soundcloud.com/ankytrixx','','0','3351',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ankytrixx'),(298,0,3,3,'Eccentric Pendulum',' Eccentric Pendulum is a metal band formed in November 2008 owing to the amalgamation of musical Ideas exchanged by the founding members of the band --? Arun (ex Extinct Reflections), Vibhas( ex Spitfire), Ashish( ex Inner Sanctum, Spit) and Nikhil( ex Asylum). Having played with their previous bands for quite a while, the quartet aimed at composing songs which were inspired by various forms of music with no particular bias towards any genre/sub genre. While maintaining progressive metal as their prime focus, the band composes songs combining elements from jazz, fusion and ambient resulting in an unconventional musical concoction. \r\n\r\n The band gained respect and popularity in the local scene at quiet an early stage for their ability to engage their audiences and appeal to their intellectual side through the bands live performances. In March 2009, the band released their debut EP titled The Sculptor of Negative Emotions\" at Bangalore\'s premier \"All Original Music Fest\"  Rock Ethos. The bands intention to deliver a package of high artistic value lead to stunning cover art by American artist Alex Eckman Lawn. The EP saw buyers across the Indian Subcontinent and some parts of Europe and America. \r\n\r\n In August 2009, the band welcomed Faheem as their lead guitarist to help extend its musical boundaries into unmapped metal territories. Thus adding another dimension to the bands sound. In September 2010, Arjun replaced Ashish on guitars as the latter fled to France for his higher education. \r\n\r\n Highlights of the band include winning and headlining at various college festivals and also sharing the stage with metal heavy weights such as Meshuggah, Textures, Amon Amarth, Tesseract, Enslaved and a host of killer Indian bands.\r\n\r\n In August 2011, the band represented India in the Wacken Metal Battle at W:O:A in Germany and were very well received by their international audience.  \r\nFull video for your viewing pleasure here (http://media.ndr.de/progressive/2011/0811/TV-20110811-1112-3901.hq.mp4)\r\n\r\n Currently, the band has finished writing and recording their full length debut album - \'Winding the Optics\' which is aimed at a September 2011 release. The album contains over 45 min of progressive metal written over a span of 2 years.\r\n\r\n\"If you like your metal equal parts modern and old school, be sure to check out the amazing Eccentric Pendulum - sinister progressions, vicious thrash riffs, carefully calculated prog, sweetly crafted melodies topped off with soaring guitar solos make this a powerful and intricate album you want to sit down with and chew over for a long time. Great stuff.\" - Keshav Dhar (Skyharbor)','Vibhas - 9844222483/Arjun - 9845077794','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Eccentric-Pendulum/198704042390?sk=info','http://eccentricpendulum.bandcamp.com','http://soundcloud.com/eccentric-pendulum','http://www.reverbnation.com/eccentricpendulum','0','3338',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','eccentric-pendulum'),(299,0,1,1,'Joint Family','Formed in December 2004, Joint Family consists of 5 stupid lazy motherfuckers who always wanna chill, have fun not do any work and make music that makes them and other people jump around like crazy. \r\n\r\nThe line was Shardul Mehta and Rahul Sainani (both ex cyanide) on skin bashing and guitar respectively, Rohit Amwan on guitar, Akshay de on vocal manipulation and Clarence Gonsalves (ex incognito, ex level 9, oidua and anoushka shankar) on bass.\r\n\r\nSome of the major gigs that the band has played include, \r\nJune Rock Out 2005 (Chennai), \r\nIndependence Rock (Mumbai), \r\nThe Great Indian Rock Festival 2006 & 2007 (held in Delhi and Mumbai), \r\nWon 4 lac ruppees as winners of The Hornbill Music Festival 2006(Kohima), \r\nwinners at IIT Delhi Blitzkrieg 2005, \r\nCampus Rock Idols (Delhi, Chandigarh and Goa). \r\nThe band has also played numerous gigs at packed pubs and clubs around the city. \r\n\r\nThe band has come a long way since it was formed. With constant support and appreciation from all the fans around the country. We would like to thank all those people who have been with us, held their fists high and moshed like br00tal motherfuckers at our gigs, given us so much love that it actually got us to get off our lazy ass and release an album!, driven their cars like fucking maniacs while listening to our cd on full volume, actually asked us for our autographs! (wtf??)... you made us yuppies feel like total rockishtaars! ;) \r\nThank you!\r\n\r\nFor those who haven\'t heard of the band or any of the band\'s music, do check out our myspace page and we hope you like our shit. If you\'re a major music label executive (or not!) then come check us out at our next gig! :P \r\nWatch this space for future  updates about the band.\r\n\r\nWe launched our Debut album titled \'HotBox\' in July 2007. Produced by Anupam Roy (Narsil), the album consists of 9 tracks. We hope you\'ve got yourself a copy of the album. If not, then please let us know and we\'ll tell you how you can get one!\r\n\r\nCurrently the band has hit the pause button on the music as most of the band members are outta town doin their own shit.\r\nShardul\'s studying in Australia, Akshay\'s studying in Malaysia and Amwan\'s working in Singapore.\r\n\r\nThe band\'s gonna start jamming as soon as everyone comes back in another 8-9 months. Work on a few new tracks is going on slow and steady. Till then, we hope you enjoy listening to \'Hotbox\'. ','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Joint-Family/44031455528?ref=ts&sk=info','','','','0','3327',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','joint-family'),(300,0,101,101,'Sinister Violence','                                          ON THY VERGE OF METAL MUSIC IN THY WOODS OV DARJEELING EVOLVED A BUNCH OF TEENS WHO CALLD THEMSELVES \"SINISTER VIOLENCE\". THE TERM ITSELF MEANS \"DIABOLICAL BLOODSHED\".\r\n                                           HIGHLY INSPIRED BY BANDS LIKE DIMMU BORGIR, DYING FETUS, MARDUK, LAST DAYS OF HUMANITY,  GRAVEWORM, MY DYING BRIDE ETC. WE HAVE BEEN PLAYIN OUT WITH SME BRUTAL RIFFS WITH DARK MELODIES BLEND WITH GUTTRAL, SCREECH,GROWLS AND PIGSQUEELS ON THE VOCALS WITH ENORMOUS BRUTALITY ON THE SKINS. SINISTER VIOLENCE HAS BEEN PLAYING, HEADLINING GIGS AND WINNING COMPETION ALL OVER AND HAS AN UNDISPUTED WINS OF 13 IN MAJOR NATIONAL COMP INCLUDING HIMALAYAN ROCK , NORTHEASTERN ROCKERS, SOLASTICATE, BLOSSOM FEST, LAUNCHPAD ZONAL WINNERS ETC.. . AS PER THEIR MUSIC THEY CAN BE CATEGORISED AMONG N.W.O.I.H.M.(NEW WAVE OF INDIAN HEAVY METAL).  \r\nIN THE BEGINNING WHEN  VIOLENCE WAS FIRST FORMED IN DECEMBER2010 THEY USED TO COVER MELODIC DEATH AND THRASH SONGS LIKE \"DEAD EYES SEE NO FUTURE\",  \"TERRITORY\", \"The PATHLESS PATH TO THE KNOWABLE UNKNOWN\", \"YESTERDAY DONT MEAN A SHIT\".  AND NOW HAVE BEEN WORKIN OUT ON MUCH ORIGINAL MATERIAL AND MUCH MORE DIFFERENT FROM OTHER METAL SCENE.  AS PER OUR SCENE THERE  ARE LOTS OF BAND WHO ENTITLE THERE GENRE AS BLACK METAL WITHOUT ANY AMBIENCY OF THEM. \r\n LYRICALLY THE BAND IS HIGHLY  BASED ON ANTIRELIGION, DEATH, MYSTICAL DEMONS. WHICH CAN CLEARLY REFLECTED BY THY TITLE OF RELEASED SINGLES TRACK LIKE  \r\n\"LORDESS OV DESTRUCTION\", \"SACRIFICIAL GOAT\", SUICIDAL TENDENCY\", \"WEREWOLF\" AND \" KINGDOM OV BLOOD AND FIRE\".\r\n                                                                       \r\n','Gyaltzen Lama','http://www.facebook.com/sinisterviolence666/info','http://www.reverbnation.com/sinisterviolence666','http://soundcloud.com/sinisterviolence666','','0','3323',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sinister-violence'),(301,2,1,1,'Indigo Children','Indigo Children are a Delhi-based duo and have been part of the Indian circuit since 2004.\r\n\r\nThey first found recognition playing pubs and college fests around India. Some of the bigger competitions they won over their first few years include Campus Rock Idols in 2005, the Great Indian Rock festival 2006 and Channel [V] Launch pad.\r\n\r\nThese competitions brought them Nation-wide attention among the underground rock scene and built the foundations for a fan-base. Indigo Children were one of the few bands chosen to represent India in Singapore for Sutasi, a reality television show, featuring talent across Asia. They were also one of the four bands chosen to record with world - renowned producer John Leckie as a part of the British Councils Soundpad. As a part of the Soundpad project the band went on a 2 - week tour of the United Kingdom; playing at festivals and venues such as The Great Escape festival, Brighton and the Barfly. The band has also opened for Bryan Adams, Your Code Name is Milo, Freak Kitchen, Intronaut, Benea Reach and Backstreet Boys in India.\r\n\r\nIndigo Children comprises Sanchal Malhar and Nikhil Rufus Raj, featuring an extended line up for the live act. The band refrains from categorizing their music to a genre but likes to write idiosyncratic vocal pop music. \r\n','+91 9910001202','http://www.facebook.com/indigochildrenmusic/info','','http://soundcloud.com/indigochildrenmusic','','0','3295',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 13:01:11',130,'[\"Ritnika Nayan - ritnika@mgmh.net\"]','[\"\"]','indigo-children'),(302,0,1,1,'Kohra','Kohra is the deep, hypnotic and often grungy mirror image of Madhav Shorey. Raw analog signals and lush soundscapes mixed with percussion sounds and sharp glitches is what can be heard through his mysterious productions. A style that is intelligent enough to mesmerize, yet simple enough to move you.\r\n\r\nConstantly paving the way for a new sub-culture of underground dance music is no task for the timid, which is why he has already become the first Indian to have hit the top 10 charts on global industry standards such as Beatport. As a producer his music has been signed to many well respected international record labels including Sounds Of Earth, Trident Music, Wide Angle Recordings and Echoes Records to name a few.\r\n\r\nHis Live set comprise his own productions performed in a deconstructive format with a constantly evolving component of granular synthesis, vocal sampling, various percussion and effect units. As a Dj, his sets are extremely captivating and reflect a distinct progressive, organic and streamlined approach to techno. He maintains that not only through his high standards of track selection but also with the release schedule of his own quality imprint of Qilla Records. \r\n\r\nKohra has performed at some of the best festivals in India, Dubai, Italy and Australia and is also the official label Dj for Zenon Records. The fact that he has been officially endorsed by leading brands such as Blackberry and Puma is only further authentication of his work. \r\n\r\nKeep your ears open, there is always more with this one...\r\n\r\nDISCOGRAPHY\r\nRELEASES:\r\nKohra - Air Pedro\r\nKohra - Air Pedro (Fog Remix)\r\nKohra - Air Pedro (Elastic Remix)\r\nKohra - Air Pedro (Jalebee Cartel Remix)\r\nKohra - FutureShock\r\nKohra - Inner Space\r\nKohra - Over The Under\r\nKohra - Rubber Ducks\r\nKohra - The Green Escape\r\nKohra - Clear Grounds (Feat. Gravitactional)\r\nKohra - Blue Moves\r\nKohra - Mojza\r\nKohra - Sceneric Sunrise\r\nKohra - Malagudi Daze (Midimal Remix)\r\nKohra - Malgudi Daze\r\nKohra - Malgudi Daze (Antix Remix)\r\nKohra - Malgudi Daze (Blackout Remix)\r\nKohra - Plastic Fantastic\r\nKohra - Big Bazzaar\r\nKohra - Wired\r\nKohra - Tummelplatz \r\nKohra - Paradigm \r\nKohra - Paradigm (BLOT Remix)\r\nKohra - Paradigm (Knobs Remix)\r\nKohra - Shiromonaki\r\nKohra - Shiromonaki (BLOT Remix)\r\nKohra - Shiromonaki (Matador Remix)\r\nKohra - Shiromonaki (Kane Roth Remix)\r\nKohra - Crystalized\r\nKohra - Sidewinder \r\nKohra - Sidewinder (Vazik & Xahno Remix)\r\nKohra - Sidewinder (Nir Shoshani Remix)\r\nKohra - Burnt Cinema\r\nKohra - Burnt Cinema (Vipul Remix)\r\nKohra - Burnt Cinema (Jorge Martins Remix)\r\nKohra - Burnt Cinema (Groovotron Remix)\r\n\r\nREMIXES:\r\nElastic - Animal Slave (Kohra Remix)\r\n\r\nCOMPILATIONS: \r\nV.A. Get Wet Go (Compiled By Dj Nick) \r\nV.A. Chakrunas (Compiled By Dj Gino)\r\nV.A. Sector 9 (Compiled By Fuzz)\r\nV.A. Sonic Waves (Compiled By Kohra)\r\nV.A. Deep Electric India (Compiled By Kohra)\r\nV.A. The Summer Chillout (Blender Magazine)\r\nV.A. Deep Electric Hypnosis (Compiled By Kohra)\r\nV.A. The Hub - Indian Electronica\r\n\r\nCOMING SOON:\r\n\r\nKohra - Secret Shadow EP\r\nKohra - Dream Machine EP\r\nKohra - Miasma (Original Mix)\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/kohra.in/info','www.kohra.in','http://soundcloud.com/kohra','http://www.reverbnation.com/kohra','0','3294',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','kohra'),(303,0,102,0,'Blue Nipple Boy','Everything turned to blue in the early Spring of 2010. First was an idea, then was the searching and in the end, the meeting. It was between two guys, one with the spirit and the other with the voice and more. After tones of discussions and more than 60 names, Blue Nipple Boy was the one and so will remain. We needed a special invitation to see the light and weve got it the summer of 2010. This was the birth of Special Invitation  first single ever. \r\n\r\nFirst audition on a radio was at City FM, a Romanian rock station where Special Invitation smiled in charts for five weeks.\r\n\r\nThe next release was one of the catchiest and is called Womanman, due to its vibe and story, way too spicy and undefined. Womanman conquered few national radio stations, but has found its no.1 position in Radio Guerrillas Chart for weeks. It was the second most rated and voted single of 2011 by Guerrillas listeners.    \r\n\r\nAlong with the third member  the percussionist Balasa Gabriel, we had the stage debut in March 2011 at Control Club, Bucharest. It was a trio based concert with a lot good energy and fun. After few weeks, the bass/contra-bass player, Adi Neacsu, joined the band and so, the next single was released. Bear Comes Naked is a simple, chill and positive combination of acoustics and it was self recorded and released in 2011. The official video for Bear Comes Naked was released at National Television on June 3, 2011. This single was elected to be part of what is called Music Alliance Pact, an international music compilation comprising songs from 36 countries. Bear represented Romania in May 2011 and became no. 1 in charts, as Womanman did it before. \r\n\r\nAfter Alexandru Alexe (drums) and Luis Angel Palomino (sax & flute) joined the band in 2011, we have recorded and released the next single, Salta Montes, a combination of oriental, rock and disco music. \r\n\r\nThe band gained a lot of experience as a group of 6 members and was invited to join the largest festivals and concerts in Romania, like Peninsula Felsziget Festival, BESTFEST, Street Heroes Festival, Street Delivery Festival and many more. At Peninsula Felsziget we have gained our participation at Sziget 2012, which is considered the best major festival in Europe.  \r\n   \r\nThe newest single it is called Hot and is a cover version of INNA  Hot. With a bossa-nova vibe, we believe we have turned the original tune in a different one, so that a new blue song has been released. \r\n\r\nThe debut album is on the road and we hope that in the Spring of 2012 you will be able to listen it in every possible place and mood. Once you will listen it you will discover a very fusion album, mixing pop, rock, bossa, rap, punk, latino, oriental, folklore, disco, 8bit sounds and more. \r\n','PR Aleka Sarah Vladareanu, phone: +40727820314 email: aleka.sarah@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Blue-Nipple-Boy/135484266491040?sk=info','','http://soundcloud.com/bluenippleboy','http://www.reverbnation.com/bluenippleboy','0','3283',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','blue-nipple-boy'),(304,0,1,1,'Kailasa','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Kailasa/109603329058565','','','','109603329058565','3272',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','kailasa'),(305,0,4,4,'Ashwamedh','Redefining the boundaries of Hindi Rock and defining an unprecedented sound for the masses, was the sole aim with which Ashwamedh was formed.\r\n \r\nBringing home a heady mix of Indian Classical, Funk, Hard Rock and Metal, we choose not to restrict ourselves to any particular genre.\r\n\r\nWith groovy yet powerful originals, laden with inspiring lyrics and vocals, crushing riffs, monster leads and drumming work, Ashwamedh has always had the crowd hungry for more in it\'s wake...\r\n\r\nShattered pre-defined notions about Hindi Rock are a collateral, for which we take full responsibility :-P\r\n\r\nThe name \'Ashwamedh\' has been derived from the ancient custom of \'Ashwamedh Yagna\' where the sacred horse runs to the limits to determine the boundaries of the king\'s newly acquired kingdom.\r\nSimilarly, with a rabidly increasing and fiercely loyal fan following, we believe our music is the emperor and we shall serve by defining newer boundaries for it!\r\n\r\nThe first two original \'Qaid\' and \'Aelaan\' are up for listening here:\r\n    www.reverbnation.com/ashwamedh\r\n\r\nNews n Gigs :\r\n   \r\n    *Won the Silver for India in the Best Rock Song category at the the Indiego Music Awards 2011-2012, Asia\'s Biggest Music Awards.\r\n\r\n   * Nominated in the Best Rock Song category at the BiteMyMusic Global Music Awards 2012, world\'s one of the biggest music awards.\r\n\r\n   * Only Asian band to be globally shortlisted for Sweden Rock festival 2012.\r\n  \r\n    * Headlined at Chaos 2012, the annual fest of IIM Ahmedabad.\r\n\r\n    * Headlined at Aurora 2012, the annual fest of IIITM Gwalior.\r\n\r\n    * Headlined at Taksh 2012, the annual festival of IIT Rajasthan.\r\n\r\n    * Headlined at Elan 2012 the annual festival of IIT Hyderabad.\r\n\r\n    * Co-headlined with Indus Creed at EOS 2012, Mumbai.\r\n\r\n    * Headlined at Trascend 2012, the annual festival of Symbiosis Institute of Business Management, Pune.\r\n\r\n    * Headlined MADMA 2012, annual festival of Xavier\'s Institute Communication.\r\n\r\n    * Headlined at Zest 2012 the annual sports festival of College of Engineering Pune.\r\n\r\n    * Co-Headlined with Agnee at Creo 2011, annual fest of F.L.A.M.E School of Management Pune.\r\n\r\n    * Headlined at Vidyut 2011, RV College of Engineering, Bangalore.\r\n\r\n    * Featured by Jaago Mumbai 90.8 FM for their show Desi Trax.\r\n\r\n    * Headlined Blizzard - Rock Festival 2011, Pune.\r\n\r\n    * Headlined at Surge 2011, Annual Festival of NIT Kurukshetra.\r\n\r\n    * Headlined at Fundamental 2011, Annual Festival of Symboisis Institute for Design, Pune.\