7:31',0,'','','ashwamedh'),(306,0,34,34,'Saimum Hasan Nahian','This Page has been created by a Fan.\r\n\r\nSaimum Hasan Nahian (Schizoid Horns)\r\nGuitarist,\r\nSevere Dementia, Powersurge\r\n\r\n\r\nGears:\r\nJACKSON RR customized\r\nMesa/Boogie Dual Rectifier 100W Amp Head\r\nMesa/Boogie 4X12 Rectifier Slant Cabinet 280W\r\nTC Electronic G Major Effects Processor\r\ndbx 266XL Compressor/Gate\r\ndbx 231 dual channel Graphic Equalizer\r\nX2 Digital XDR95 Instrument Wireless\r\nRocktron Hush Super C Noise Reduction Unit\r\nDunlop Crybaby 95Q Wah Pedal\r\nMonster Power Pro 3500 Power Center\r\nDigitech GNX3 Guitar Workstation\r\nZoom Tri-Metal Distortion Pedal\r\nMarshall JackHammer JH-1 Distortion Pedal\r\nPeavey Blazer-158 Transtube Series Amp','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Saimum-Hasan-Nahian/29177069354?sk=info','http://www.severedementia.com','','','0','3241',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','saimum-hasan-nahian'),(307,0,1,1,'Caesars Of The Green','Caesars of the Green is an indie rock band. Formed in the fall of 2011 in New Delhi, the band currently consists of Sidharth Malik (lead vocals, rhythm guitar), Ajit Rajian (bass guitar), Ujjwal Kumar (drums, percussion) and Ritwik De (lead guitar), who joined in the summer 2012, following the departure of Satyum Joshi. The band released their debut EP \'You\'ve Seen As I\'ve Made You\' in February, 2012. Their brand of indie rock draws on influences such as Kings of Leon, Blur, The Libertines, MGMT, Bob Dylan, Sigur Ros, Joy Division and Dylan Thomas, leading to the creation of a unique brit-pop inflicted indie rock sound. The theme of their lyrically driven music revolves around the philosophy of an ideal for living.','Sidharth Malik 9891996070, 9717886860','http://www.facebook.com/caesarsofthegreen/info','	http://caesarsofthegreen.bandcamp.com','http://soundcloud.com/caesarsofthegreen','http://www.reverbnation.com/caesarsofthegreen','0','3239',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','caesars-of-the-green'),(308,0,103,103,'Evergreen','Evergreens roots lie in their individually varied tastes in music. What makes them different is their approach to music as it is targeted both at musicians and the common ear. Their first album* Between and Beyond is a product of their unique intuitive style of songwriting. Between and Beyond speaks about the multi-universes, physical and meta-physical, things we see and yearn to see, and about the many lives and personalities inherent in us all, and about how our lives are connected in our choices and experiences resulting from them.\r\n\r\nIn the early part of the bands 8 year history, they were known for their near perfect covers. Evergreen grew from a commercial/corporate circuit to the rockers they are today.\r\n\r\nThey give special attention in selecting their equipment, emphasizing on creating a sound of their own. Their national experience won them many accolades, making them a formidable opponent in any nation-wide competition and an elemental sounding band waiting to unleash.\r\n\r\nIn the soundscapes and imagery of Evergreen, there is an apparent \"guardian\" theme, be it of nature, innocence or against ignorance. These messages are obvious in their song Run to the Light and contextualized in From Here to Clarity. These songs not only offer the premise but also the irony. Thus they had made a stand against issues like Global Warming and Cruelty Against Animals, not by being preachy but choosing the Post-Modern path.','evergreenrocks@gmail.com      ','http://www.facebook.com/EvergreenIndia/info','http://www.evergreenrocks.com','','http://www.reverbnation.com/evergreen','0','3231',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','evergreen'),(309,0,63,63,'Street Stories','Street Stories are an indie, pop-punk band from Shillong, India. Street Stories have recently been performing at the various competitions besides a couple of high profile pro gigs that have taken place in the region. With a serious desire to make music their form of release the lads have big plans for the future\r\n\r\n\r\n Consisting of Pezo Kronu, Riko Kronu and Matsram Sangma, the band was officially formed on the outset of last years winter that is January, 2010. The band is well known for their spirit of playing full on high energy concerts and they have already made quite an impression at all the gigs they have played at.\r\n\r\nThe band was founded by the two brothers Riko and Pezo. And the two say that they have been breathing and talking music ever since they were toddlers, Initially as we grew up, our minds expanded and we had the desire to get on further with our musical adventure and that was when we finally decided to form a band. Although, at first it was just the two of us and a friend who seasoned as a drummer but eventually left due to personal reasons. Nonetheless, this never blocked our way from building up our musical careers, we moved on forward with what we do best i.e. making music. Finally, a year later we met our current and permanent drummer, at our local church (Shillong Baptist Church) where we first played together, then we came to realize that he had potential and not only that but he also had the same common ideas, concepts as we did too when it comes to playing live. So basically Church singing has brought the band together and thats how it happened.\r\n\r\nThe band does not have any contradicting ideas or music to implement it on the sound of the band because they are all open to all sorts of musical genres and their taste of music is extensively varied. The band believes that tunes are tunes regardless of genres and that any song with catchy tunes and strong melodies are the key ingredients to a good song. The main influence these guys have in common would be the desire and love that they share towards making music and getting it on recordings/tapes for all their listeners and also for themselves and playing them live. \r\n\r\nThe Apple & the Clown is the title of the bands debut EP. The album is a product of five songs spanning for about 20 minutes from start till end. However, the album is still in its shell awaiting to be released. The Apple & the Clown is inspired by the relationship of the lead singer (Pezo) and his girlfriend. The Apple is referred to his girlfriend while he refers to himself as the Clown. Its a rare thing perhaps, when considering of making it a theme for a debut production.\r\n\r\n\r\nthank you for reading :)\r\n\r\n',' springboardbands@gmail.com, <span class=\"skype_pnh_print_container_1342002799\">+919436119961</span><span class=\"skype_pnh_container\" dir=\"ltr\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"skype_pnh_mark\"> begin_of_the','http://www.facebook.com/streetstoriesband/info','','http://soundcloud.com/streetstories','','0','3193',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','street-stories'),(310,0,104,104,'Skrypt','KRYPT is a 5 piece Thrash metal band from Hyderabad. Primarily a Thrash band but with added Groove, Death and Progressive influence.\r\nDescription\r\nSupported Nervecell - Hyderabad 2010 || Supported Cyanide Serenity - Hyderabad 2010 || Co-Headlined BITS Pilani Hyderabad 2012 w/Thurisaz || Headlined Nalsar Law College 2010 || Supported Torch at RSJ Pubrockfest - Hyderabad 2011 ||','pr@darkharvestrecords.com / +91 9963815222','http://www.facebook.com/skrypt/info','','http://soundcloud.com/skrypt','http://www.reverbnation.com/skryptband','0','3189',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','skrypt'),(311,0,105,105,'KURAKA','KURAKA es una banda de rock , que nace de la fusin de varios msicos de la escena local, con el fin de armar un proyecto musical paralelo y diverso respecto a sus bandas originales.\r\n\r\nGiorgio Bertoli (batero de ZEN), Paco Holgun (voz de THE EMERGENCY BLANKET), Miguel Tuesta (bajo de M.A.S.A.C.R.E.) y Gonzalo Farfn (voz y guitarra de INYECTORES) juntaron estilos desde hace un par de aos en sesiones de jamming, y aunque la idea pareciera algo difcil de ensamblar por la diferencia de los aportes que traa cada uno, la amistad que exista entre ellos los hizo sospechar que algo palpitante escupira esta aleacin. \r\nProducto de las sesiones de composicin y preproduccin, lanzaron a travs de la red a finales de junio 2009 el primer single Voltaje, como adelanto a las sesiones definitivas del disco, y dos meses despus una segunda entrega a manera de single promocional, como para ir marcando el terreno sonoro por donde se movera el lbum debut, con el nuevo tema Lugares Extraos, el que desarrolla la pugna entre el bien y el mal, como entes interdependientes desde un inicio, el alejamiento y despedida de uno, la intencin de retencin del otro, la lucha por mantenerse vivos entre ambos. Como si el mal no hubiera sido expulsado del paraso, sino que se hubiera ido por eleccin propia.\r\n\r\nLuego de sembrar el camino por donde se movera la banda con estos singles y algunas presentaciones en vivo entre finales del 2009 y principios del 2010, la banda se intern en los estudios de Mundano Records entre noviembre 2009 y febrero 2010, y plasm 12 estupendos temas en su primera placa, bajo el ttulo de Fuego Negro, lbum debut que resume en perfecta conjuncin las influencias y estilos de sus integrantes en una demoledora mquina que avanza por los caminos del rock alternativo.\r\n\r\nFuego Negro fue lanzado en Agosto 2010 va Mundano Records, y se viene presentando en vivo en varios shows iniciales, en los que se puede encontrar el lbum a precios especiales. \r\n\r\nEscucha muestras del album \"Fuego Negro\" y hazle download a los singles \"Liblula\" y \"Fuego Negro\" en alta calidad, dale click a la flechita al lado derecho de cada tema en el player:\r\nhttp://soundcloud.com/mundanorecords/sets/kuraka-fuego-negro-album-samples\r\n\r\nCONTACTO\r\nmundanorecords@gmail.com\r\n98137*8005\r\n99400*3734\r\n\r\nCD \"FUEGO NEGRO\" DE VENTA EN:\r\nTiendas de la cadena Phantom, Two Music de Larcomar, Va Music de Av. Larco, Moving Sound de Galeras Brasil, Music Prad de Polvos Rosados, Primavera y Galeras Brasil. \r\n\r\n','mundanorecords@gmail.com - 98137*8005','http://www.facebook.com/pages/KURAKA/147562236398?sk=info','','http://soundcloud.com/mundanorecords/sets/kuraka-fuego-negro-album-samples','','0','3169',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','kuraka'),(312,0,29,29,'Yonsample','YONSAMPLE is a metal act from Kolkata, India.\r\n\r\nYon [O.E. geon (adj.)] is the archaic dialect for the word yonder (that) . It indicates something further but within sight (separated in space) or (coming from/going to a distance indicated). \'Sample\' is \"something which confirms a proposition or statement,\" while intended here as representation, instance or illustration.\r\n\r\nArka Das -- Vocals\r\nTuhin Paul -- Drums \r\nAnudhyan Chakrabarti-- Keyboards\r\nAnirban Banerjee -- Bass\r\nSoumik Roy -- Guitars\r\n\r\nAbesh Thakur -- Lyrics\r\nRito -- Production/Recording.\r\n','09874929619 / 09830405745 / 09836224334','http://www.facebook.com/yonsample/info','','http://soundcloud.com/yonsample','','0','3061',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','yonsample'),(314,0,3,3,'Allegro Fudge','Allegro Fudge is a contemporary acoustic band that plays original music which is in the process of being defined as a genre. Our songs have a distinct flavour of their own and draw inspiration from our everyday lives.\r\n\r\nAllegro Fudge draws from the experience and the flavour that each musician brings, ranging from Blues, Country, Classical, Folk, Jazz, Metal to Pop to make very interesting music which doesnt attempt to sound like anyone or be anything, but becomes a musical counterpoint!\r\n\r\nBand Lineup:\r\n\r\nSaahas Patil - Vocals\r\nJason Zachariah - Piano \r\nShalini Mohan - Bass','Jason Zachariah','http://www.facebook.com/allegrofudge/info','','http://soundcloud.com/allegrofudge','http://www.reverbnation.com/#!/allegrofudge','0','3024',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','allegro-fudge'),(315,0,95,95,'Odyssey','The band was formed in February 2008 by Hussam Raza, Waqas Ahmed and Omar Sohail because of a common interest in making progressive music. The name \'Odyssey\' was chosen because it signified a long musical journey that the band felt like it was embarking on. Odyssey is also the name of a very famous poem based on Greek mythology, which are elements that can be found in Odyssey\'s original music as well.\r\n\r\nAfter trying out a couple of vocalists, the band was introduced to Raja Nabeel Banwa who was a big fan of progressive music as well. As it turns out, he could play keyboards too, so after meeting up with him, the band chose him as their vocalist and keyboard player. The band also recruited Fawad Nadir for playing bass for them at live gigs, but after producing their 1st album with the help of a close friend Ahmed Waqar, they invited Ahmed to join as a bass player in the band. Also knowing that Ahmed is an extremely talented guitar player as well, Odyssey were not surprised to see him become a beast on that 6-Stringed Ibanez Bass.\r\n\r\nSadly, after being in the band for around a year, producing Odyssey\'s 2nd album called \"Crossroads to Oblivion\" and more importantly getting an admission in the prestigious Berklee College of Music, Boston, Ahmed Waqar had to leave Odyssey to pursue his own academic and musical career.\r\n\r\nIn the fall of 2011, during their hunt for their next bass guitarist, Odyssey were introduced to Haider Abbas who had been a prominent member of the Lahore Underground Scene since a couple of years. They were really impressed by his playing and hence he was asked to join the band.\r\n\r\nSo far Odyssey has written 2 original albums, played at numerous gigs in Lahore & Islamabad, given interviews for different T.V/Radio shows and documentaries which has developed a strong fanbase for the band in the local scene.\r\n\r\nOdyssey\'s music is inspired by bands like Dream Theater, Symphony X, Metallica, Megadeth, Black Sabbath, Pantera, Savatage, Ark, Opeth and Liquid Tension Experiment amongst others','+923214314321 - You can also email at odysseypakistan@gmail.com, hussam.raza@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/odysseypk/info','','http://soundcloud.com/odysseypk\n','http://www.reverbnation.com/odysseyprog','0','3011',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','odyssey'),(316,0,106,106,'Alobo Naga & the Band','BAND BIO\r\n\r\nGenre: Contemporary Progressive Rock.\r\n\r\nBand members:\r\n\r\nAlobo Naga- Vocals, Guitar, Piano, Bamhum\r\n\r\nAkum Jams- Guitar/Ukulele/vocals\r\n\r\nFung Walling- Bass/vocals\r\n\r\nDJ Sumika Yepthomi- Turntable / Guitar/vocals\r\n\r\n\r\nBAND PROFILE:\r\n\r\n\'Alobo Naga and the band\' is made up of five very ordinary and typical young Naga men.\r\nNagaland has the reputation of being perhaps the most musical state in India. And considering the fact that India itself is a virtual treasure of musical styles and traditions that\'s no mean feat! Dimapur, the town where the band originates, has been at the center of the musical revolution which has been progressively overtaking the state. From Bach and Beethoven to the Black Eyed Peas and Maroon 5\'s \'Moves like Jagger\', Nagaland is no stranger to any genre you can think of. \'Alobo Naga and the band\' by establishing themselves as heavyweights in this environment of musical explosion has earned their stripes. After all the critics here are as unforgiving as they come! Formed in 2010 they have been making more and more noise, of the good kind of course. While their roots are firmly entrenched in the contemporary progressive rock genre, they nevertheless appreciate and are quick to incorporate from any other genre.\r\n\r\nALOBO NAGA\r\n\r\nThe main Vocalist of the group, Alobo Naga holds a grade 8 certificate in Concert performance in Contemporary Vocals, from Rock School under Trinity School of Music, London. Prior to the band\'s formation, Alobo was already an established pop musician, He is at ranked at 6th spot nationwide at Gospel/Christian music on www.Reverbnation.com, besides being a performing artist & a composer, he is also a music teacher at the Furtados School of music, one of the premiere institutes of the country.\r\n\r\nRecently he won the Best Folk Fusion song Award in the Nagaland Music Award 2011 for his song \"Kumsujulo\" from his Solo debut album. It is interesting to note that while Alobo might be considered the main vocalist of the band, the other members themselves are formidable singers and frequently lend their vocals to the songs.\r\n\r\n\r\nAKUM JAMS\r\n\r\nAkum is the lead guitarist of the band. Formerly with the much lauded band \'Melodrama\', Akum was featured by \'TNT\' magazine as one of the gen next guitarists from the north east. The man himself bears a striking resemblance to the bad boys of western music with his tattoos and a very \'Rolling Stone\'ish\' vibe. However, his band mates will tell you that he is far from being the juvenile bad boy.\r\n\r\nFUNG WALLING\r\n\r\nThe Bass maestro of the band Fung is diminutive and soft spoken, yet morphs into a performing machine on stage. Before the band happened he was a member of the successful Christian band \'Blended For Him\'. He works at \'Furtado\'s music Dimapur\'.\r\n\r\nSUMIKA\r\n\r\nDJ Sumika, as he is popularly known, brings the club to the band! A Turntablist with the meanest skills, he most definitely adds chutzpah! to the band\'s music. With his added mix the band\'s music very audibly reaches into the playing fields of international bands like \'Linkin Park\' and \'Incubus\'. He also teaches music at \'Furtado\'s\'.\r\n\r\nNOTABLE ACHIEVEMENTS\r\n\r\nAlobo Naga & The Bands song Painted Dreams was selected as the Theme Song of the prestigious International Short Film Festival 2011 Guwahati. The song \"Painted Dreams\" went up to No.4 at International Top 10 chart at VH1, and was successively pronounced one of the top 50 videos of 2011 by the same channel. \r\n\r\nAt the Nagaland Music awards 2011 the band won honors including, \"Best Rock song\" for \'Painted Dreams\',  \"Best Producer\" and \"Best Mixing\" .\r\n\r\nThe band is ranked at the 9th spot nationwide on www.Reverbnation.com\r\n\r\nThe band has performed tracks for a Bollywood movie \'Beyond\' under Golden Eye production and is also working on other movies.\r\n\r\nPlayed at FREE BIRD festival, W.O.R.M.E fest , KINX, Taj Deccan ...\r\n\r\n\r\nManager  Prithish Chakroborty & Betoka Swu\r\n Find us @ www.Facebook@alobonagaandtheband\r\n website : www.alobonaga.com\r\n For booking @ booking@alobonaga.com\r\n','+91 9615 1025 45','http://www.facebook.com/alobonagaandtheband/info','http://www.alobonaga.com','http://soundcloud.com/alobo-naga','','0','2980',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','alobo-naga-the-band'),(317,0,2,2,'Coshish','Fusing elements of Progressive Rock, with the more easily acceptable mainstream song writing styles of Hindi Rock, seems to come naturally to Mumbai based band Coshish. The band believes that their songs should have mass appeal and yet retain enough musical dexterity to appease technical musicians without compromising on simplicity. Their songs have a spiritual bent delivered beautifully through Hindi lyrics.\r\n','coshishband@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/Coshish/info','','http://soundcloud.com/coshish','','0','2979',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','coshish'),(318,0,2,2,'EXHUMATION (India)','2003, In the small by lanes of the suburb Andheri, in the city of Mumbai, India, 3 musicians that craved to create some extreme music got together and have been doing just that for the last 7 years. In 2004, they released the single \'Among The Dead\' which drew favourable responses and encouragement from all. Towards the end of 2005 they completed the first album \'Among The Dead\' and not having the patience to wait for a record deal, made it available online to all who were willing to hear. The album not only garnered critical acclaim but also cemented status as the death metal elite. In 2006, they made their second record, a ear-shattering mix of brutal death metal and blasting goregrind, \'For Personal Consumption Only\', which was released as a part of Defaced And Split, India\'s first death metal split album, available on Demonstealer Records. has also been featured on follow up to the international documentary \'Metal: A Headbangers Journey\', titled \'global metal\', which was directed by Sam Dunn. 2 years after their last release, has set out to release another album, titled \'Consider This\', at end of the year 2010. has also added another member and will reveal more on this at a later date. So yes, watch this space, for the lull will soon give way to the storm.\r\n\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/exhumationindia/info?ref=ts','','','','0','2977',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','exhumation-india'),(319,0,89,89,'Sweetblame','Nothing much just a punk band consisting of simple,decent,good for nothing,jobless students makin music as they lack s*xual satisfaction in their life  :P\r\n\r\nThe only difference is that we guys give what we feel in our music which is quite noticeable in our live acts.\r\nOur songs speak about us and other random topics we can come up with,from our dead brain cells :D\r\n\r\nWell we actually don\'t like flaunting but yeah we have been tagged as the \"Fastest upcoming band in the history of the Gujrat rock scene\"\r\n(we know its one big tag for a band,but we like it that way :P)\r\n\r\nPast shows n Victories :-\r\n\r\n->We guys won 2nd prize at IIT(Gandhinagar),\r\n\r\n->Performed at Fret O Fire III(One of Gujarat\'s largest private rock show) \r\n\r\n->Came 2nd at Paramarsh 09(MS University,Baroda)\r\n\r\n->Opened for Bombay Rockers (Yes we did it,to hard to believe huh....???? but its true.. :D)\r\n\r\n->Youngest band to make it to the finals of Ahmedabad\'s biggest rock competition,\"ROCK PARVA\",which featured bands from all over the country.\r\nWe guys were in the top 3.\r\n\r\n->Won the \"RED FM\",On Air Band Competition (2009)\r\n\r\n-> Performed at NIRMA culfest\r\n\r\n-> Headlined the show Mirage \'10\r\n\r\n-> Performed at the auditions of IIT Kharagpur at B69, Mumbai We were among the 10 selected bands :)  \r\n\r\n-> Performed at IIM-A Chaos blizzards of rock\r\n\r\n-> Opened for Bhayanak Maut and Undying Inc at Ragnarock 2012, DAIICT\r\n\r\nThe achievements are quite less but still enough to get us noticed :P\r\n\r\nWe\'ll to know more about us,be there at our shows and we\'ll show you why we\'re called the Renegades Of PUNK....!!! :D\r\n\r\nPS-Good looking girls do get in touch with us.Please contact our Band manager for more details*\r\n\r\nPS[2]-SARCASM INTENDED** :D\r\n\r\n*Conditions apply\r\n\r\n**Rules to be strictly followed :P','','http://www.facebook.com/Sweetblame/info?ref=ts','','','http://www.reverbnation.com/sweetblame','0','2975',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sweetblame'),(320,0,36,36,'Agrath','Formed on the 10th of September 2010, \"Leadership\" is what Agrath stands for and strives for.\r\nSet out to create out of the box music mixing a plethora of different sounds, and experimenting with various styles; from deadly guitar riffs to spine chilling vocals and gravity defying drum fills,\r\nWe say - \' BRING IT ON\'\r\n- Team Agrath','Tarun Singha - +91 - 9650100907','http://www.facebook.com/agrathofficial/info','http://www.agraththeband.com','http://soundcloud.com/agrath','','0','2974',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','agrath'),(321,0,1,1,'1833 AD','1833 AD brings forth a fresh approach to Black Metal digressing from the traditional abrasive sound, concocting a mixture of extreme tremolo picking riffs and mellow melodic hooks and solos. The band bring together their individual playing styles to create an atmosphere of sorrow and hatred which do justice to the lyrical themes of the band. \r\n\r\nWith lyrical themes mostly centered on fiction, hatred, destruction and exploitation of the human race, 1833 AD takes a little detour from what people mostly categorize Black Metal lyrics as. Few songs do speak of supremacy of evil in this world but only to imply the ways of men and not by endorsing Satanism, Atheism or even Christianity. ','Nishant - <span class=\"skype_pnh_print_container_1342002799\">+91 96868 58858</span><span class=\"skype_pnh_container\" dir=\"ltr\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"skype_pnh_mark\"> begin_of_the_skype_highlighti','http://www.facebook.com/1833ad/info','http://www.1833ad.com','http://soundcloud.com/1833_ad','http://www.reverbnation.com/1833ad','0','2966',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','1833-ad'),(322,0,18,18,'De Profundis','To date, De Profundis has performed in 22 countries, taking part in three international tours and several major music festivals worldwide.\r\n\r\nThe band\'s unique sound takes influence from not only many of the subgenres of heavy metal, but also from progressive rock and jazz.\r\n\r\nWith two critically-acclaimed full-length albums (\"Beyond Redemption\" - 2007 - (Self-release/Sony Music) and 2010\'s \"A Bleak Reflection\" -2010 - (Kolony Records/Sony Music) under their belt, the third De Profundis album \'The Emptiness Within\' will be released in May 2012.\r\n\r\n\r\n===========================================\r\nFULL BIOGRAPHY\r\n===========================================\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDe Profundis was formed in November 2005 by vocalist Craig Land and guitarist Roman Subbotin. As the bands sound evolved over the course of the next 18 months, Christophe Szpajdel (Emperor, Enthoned) was approached to design a suitable logo reflecting the band\'s music visually. The band underwent several personnel changes until a stable and committed line-up was completed with the recruitment of Aleksej Obradovic (bass) and Shoi Sen (guitar), with David Andrews stepping in to play the drums on the recording. In April 2007, De Profundis recorded its first album, entitled Beyond Redemption, which was mixed by Steve Watkins at Warehouse Studios, Oxford and mastered by Tim Turan at Turan Audio (Dimmu Borgir, Opeth, Emperor). Achilleas Gatsopoulos (Dark Tranquillity, Arcturus) created the artwork for the album. Beyond Redemption self-released in August 2007.\r\n\r\nDelivering unique-sounding progressive extreme metal, De Profundis has many genre-bridging elements to their sound spanning across death, black and doom metal right through to jazz and progressive rock. These draw on a wide range of influences and the diverse nationalities of the band members. Having played their first show in September 2007 with drummer Sterghios Moschos, De Profundis has been delivering high impact live performances to rave reviews and enthusiastic crowds, being voted the 6th Best Unsigned Band in the 2007 Terrorizer Readers\' Poll. \r\n\r\nFollowing further glowing reviews, De Profundis was invited to perform at the MMD Festival in Athens (Greece) in March 2008. Upon returning from Greece, the band supported the French band Misanthrope on both of their exclusive UK shows. In July 2008, Nick Tingle replaced Sterghios Moschos, making his live debut with De Profundis at Bloodstock Open Air 2008 Festival. In December 2008, De Profundis was handpicked by Zero Tolerance magazine to take part in their showcase \"Day of Unrest\" gig. \r\n\r\nIn February 2009, De Profundis supported Iron Maiden at the Rock in India Festival in Bangalore, India in front of 20,000 people. On the back of this performance, Sony BMG gave the band a record deal to release their debut album \"Beyond Redemption\" in India. \r\n\r\nWith De Profundis now putting all their effort on completing their sophomore album, growing musical differences resulted in Aleksej Obradovic departing from the band and being replaced by Arran McSporran in May 2009. \r\n\r\nIn the months of June and July 2009, De Profundis recorded their second album \"A Bleak Reflection\" with producer Fernando Pereira Lopes (Misanthrope, Orakle). The album was once again mastered by none-other-than Tim Turan at Turan Audio. Darryll Jones created the album\'s artwork. \r\n\r\nAugust 2009 saw the band resuming its intensive live schedule with a show in Bucharest (Romania) and an appearance at Portugals Festival Ilha do Ermal 2009. In Autumn 2009, De Profundis performed in Paris (France) and toured across Northern England and Scotland. \r\n\r\nFollowing the European release of album \"A Bleak Reflection\" on Kolony Records in February 2010, De Profundis officially launched the new album with a show at the Underworld, London. The band returned to play at the Underworld several weeks later for the Infernal Damnation VI festival. In May 2010, De Profundis undertook a two-week European tour with Ragnarok (Norway) and Noctem (Spain), performing in Germany, Austria, Poland, Holland and Belgium. \r\n\r\nFollowing the European release of \"A Bleak Reflection\" several months earlier, De Profundis signed with Relapse Records for exclusive distribution in USA and Canada. Following the success of the bands first album, Sony BMG released A Bleak Reflection in India in June 2010. With the support of the British Council, De Profundis returned to India on a headlining tour in October 2010, which included co-headlining Kingfishers Octoberfest 2010 in Bangalore in front of 30,000 alongside Lacuna Coil.\r\n\r\nIn April / May 2011, De Profundis went on a 14-date European tour with Rotting Christ and Omnium Gatherum, performing in 11 countries across Central and Eastern Europe.\r\n\r\nThe third De Profundis album \'The Emptiness Within\' will be released in May 2012.\r\n\r\nRead more: http://www.deprofundistheband.com','wietze@armadaagency.com','http://www.facebook.com/deprofundistheband/info','http://www.deprofundistheband.com','','','0','2963',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','de-profundis'),(323,0,0,0,'Aux Raus','','','http://www.facebook.com/auxraus/info','http://www.auxraus.com','','','0','2962',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','aux-raus'),(324,0,3,3,'Theorized','Theorized is a Thrash Metal outfit from Bangalore, India. Though it was formed in 2005, the band has come a long way from playing happy chords at birthday parties to destroying pubs with their brand of thrash. It was around 2008 when things got a little serious after few changes in the line-up and they started developing their own sound with strong inspirations from Nevermore, Death, Old Monk, Opeth, Exodus, Martyr, Haywards 5000, Meshuggah, Testament and the likes. The band has received an amazing response after the release of the debut E.P False Hope Of Tyranny in January 2009, managing to sell more than 1000 copies all over the country and also abroad in Australia, USA, Canada and Japan without a record label.\r\n                The sound has turned a little progressive ever since the EP release and we have been working on some new material rooting for a full length sometime in 2011. WATCH OUT BEACHES!','Sandeep - +91 988 0606 257','http://www.facebook.com/theorized/info','','http://soundcloud.com/theorized','http://www.reverbnation.com/theorized','0','2927',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','theorized'),(325,0,22,22,'DJ HAMZA','Hailing from New Delhi, Hamza has attained a reputation as a pioneer of the house scene in India and one of the more innovative and exciting up-and-coming producers today. Hamza\'s diverse international sound is influenced from his strong musical background as well as growing up in India and traveling the world, living in Paris, Boston, and New York. Exposure to renowned house DJs such as Terry Francis, Dave Mothersole, DJ Heather, and Danny Teneglia inspired Hamza to create his own electronic dance productions. Soon he found a unique style of house music combining deep, tribal, and funky sounds with strong world music influences.\r\n\r\nAt the age of 27 Hamza has already worked with some of the biggest names in world music. These artists include Punjabi icon Jasbir Jassi and David Hykes, the only western vocalist specializing in sacred Mongolian chants. Besides these artists, Hamza has also worked with Taz from Stereo Nation, the largest selling Indian pop fusion act ever. \r\n\r\nTo further nourish this growing production repertoire, Hamza has set up his own label Wind Horse Records. While in New York, Hamza did his Masters in Music Business at New York University, which gave him a very strong foundation and insight into how to creatively promote his own music. Wind Horse Records, the first Indian house music label, is a major part of that vision. Hamza has recently launched the label with his own Sufi Soul EP, containing three original world music influenced house music jewels. The Sufi Soul EP\'s vibrant, tribal sound earned the notice and accolades of many new fans including Dubfire (Deep Dish), Peter Kruder (Kruder & Dorfmeister), Richie Hawtin, Quentin Harris, and Tom Findlay (Groove Armada).\r\n\r\nHamza is also a top notch DJ, bringing his fresh sound to dancefloors from New York to Portugal, Boston to Hyderabad, Paris to Pune. His sets typically start with his signature deep house sound, heavily influenced by Latin/Afro/World flavors, before developing into powerful tribal and deep, tech-house influenced beats perfect for the peak time. Hamza\'s unmistakable style, combined with many of his own productions, create memorable DJ sets that turn many clubbers into instant fans and followers.\r\n\r\nCurrently Hamza is working on expanding his base in New Delhi to include regular stays in Europe and North America to allow for global partnerships and yearly DJ tours in different parts of the world. His vision is unstoppable, as Hamza has recently formed two different live acts with two different percussionists: Jasu Khan, a famous Rajasthani percussionist, and Manu Idhra, a Portuguese master of dance music percussion. Hamza has already taken this act on the festival circuit with an acclaimed performance at the Elektron Festival in Switzerland with percussionist Latif Khan playing Morchang and Khartal. Future performances will include even more musicians as well as dancers creating a truly unique performance atmosphere.\r\n\r\nAs for Wind Horse Records, a dozen releases have appeared thus far and the labels world-wide audience is growing considerably. An EP recorded with David Hykes has been released, as well as Hamza EPs featuring fantastic world music artists such as Yungchen Lhamo of Real World Records and female Indian classical maestro Sunanda Sharma. Wind Horse will also be including remixes from highly regarded producers from the west like Presslaboys and Amit Shoham. In addition, Hamza has started working with labels outside of Wind Horse, contributing tracks and remixes for the likes of Kompakt, Open Bar, One Thirty, and Clubstar. To help people keep up with all this musical activity Hamza has launched the WHR Podcast Series which will feature a monthly mix from the headquarters of Wind Horse Records.\r\n\r\nHamza has established himself as one to keep a close eye on in the house music scene. With his impressive list of past and upcoming projects as well as fiery worldwide DJ performances Hamza is quickly becoming an important and influential talent in his own right. Through Wind Horse Records and his inventive east-west fusions Hamza is working to bring the world closer to his listeners, one beat at a time.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/DJ-HAMZA/29866618780?sk=info','http://www.djhamza.com','','','0','2927',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-hamza'),(326,0,22,22,'B.R.E.E.D','After the first track released by B.R.E.E.D landed directly in the Top Ten Beatport Dubstep Charts in 2010, the road was thereby soundly paved for this matured identity. B.R.E.E.D\'s colorfully-raw avenues have become the foundations for his evolving production and musical promenade with his upcoming releases featuring heavily-layered bass lines and exquisitely original intonations.  \r\n\r\nShortly after the Top Ten Dubstep success, B.R.E.E.D released an EP on High Chai Recordings called \"Sound Killer,\" of which both tracks appeared in the Beatport dubstep charts yet again!  But this notable activity was induced by layers of exploration and intellectual evolution. Previously, under his initial name, DJ Nasha, this self-manufactured artist claimed the World DMC Championship (India) in 1999 and 2000, of which he appeared for the finals of in New York and London.   He then capitalized on this energetic snowball of creation and consequently changed the musical horizon in his homeland of India. Recently labeled on MistaJam\'s BBC Radio One Program as the \"dubstep ambassador of India,\" B.R.E.E.D has evolved his musical disposition from an exclusively self-trained DJ and producer from Bombay India, to an artist who has now played alongside internationally-recognized personalities like Cold Cut, Freq Nasty, Caspa, and Howie B.  Without the support and infrastructure of professional musical institutes to aid his progress, this DJ and producer has sculpted a powerful magnetism among the world of experimental aficionados with his own determined hands.  \r\n\r\nCurrently B.R.E.E.D\'s latest 2011 releases are sure to wreck havoc for those who crave expressionistic beats and bass. Check out www.breedbass.com for more information! ','tara@breedbass.com','http://www.facebook.com/Breeddub/info','http://www.breedbass.com','http://soundcloud.com/breed','','0','2877',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','breed'),(327,0,2,2,'GRiMMoRTaL','A Deathcore band from Navi Mumbai formed in the summer of 2009 who combine their various individual influences to create the sound you can here in the original compositions.\r\n\r\nIt started when Joy (Guitars), Deep (Vocals) and Prateek (Bass) felt the need to play some Extreme metal. We found a drummer in Saurav who had to leave a year later. The search for a good metal drummer finally led Joy switching onto Drums. Vivek (Guitars) and Rahul (Vocals) who were close friends of the band joined in and the new line-up started playing live around town.\r\n\r\nLyrically, the themes are as diverse as: Motivating ourselves about not laying low and emotionally depressed without necessity (Why So Emo?), to releasing the rage and hatred in a constructive way (Burn In Peace). From somehow digesting the happenings of the corrupt and unfair (Resistance) to speaking about the chaotic and unstable mental state that is the result of years of pain and suffering (Tormented). The latest track talks about the thoughts of complete dehumanization as the phrase goes \'kill or be killed\' (Fatality).\r\n\r\nPERFORMANCES:\r\n===========\r\n\r\nA Quarter Down Gig - Marine Centre, Vashi (May \'09)\r\nRunners Up @ Youth Opia, Central, Raghuleela Mall, Vashi (June \'09)\r\nWilson College Rock Fest, Grant Road (Sept \'09)\r\nMusic Liberation Union 6 - SIES College, Nerul (Sept \'09)\r\nBandwagon, Yuvana - R.N.Podar, Santacruz (Nov \'09)\r\nHeadlined @ PBG Festival - Palm Beach Galleria Mall, Vashi (Dec \'09)\r\nHigh Voltage \'09 - Ruia Collge, Matunga (Dec \'09)\r\nBattle Of The Bands - Thakur College, Kandivali (Dec \'09)\r\nRedemption \'09 - Sathaye College, Vile Parle (Dec \'09)\r\nRunners Up @ Prodigies \'10 - Tilak College, Vashi (Jan \'10)\r\nHeadlined @ Shikhar feat. Infinite Redemption - BVP IMSR, CBD-Belapur (Jan \'10)\r\nHeadlined @ Badlapur Gig (Jan \'10)\r\n\r\nHeadlined @ Marine Noize Fest - Marine Centre, Vashi (Dec \'10)\r\n2nd Place @ Incendiary, Frisson feat. Devoid - ITM College, Kharghar (Dec \'10)\r\nRunners Up @ High Voltage \'10 feat. Zygnema - Ruia College, Matunga (Dec \'10)\r\nRock2Nite - Thane (Dec \'10)\r\n2nd Place @ SIESons, SIES College, Nerul (Jan \'11)\r\n\r\nMetal Bajaao III along with Exhumation, Atmosfear & Providence - B69, Andheri (Aug \'11)\r\nGuitar.Inc Rock Show III feat. Demonic Resurrection - United 21, Thane (Aug \'11)\r\nHeadlined @ Lokmanya Tilak COE - Koperkhairne (Sept \'11)\r\nWINNERS @ Rocktaves, Oasis \'11, BITS-Pilani, Rajasthan (Oct \'11)\r\nCo-headlined @ Hellbound, Tempest \'11, Marine Engineering College, Kolkata (Nov \'11)\r\nWORME Fest West Zone Finalists - B69, Andheri (Dec \'11)\r\n2nd Place @ West Zone Elims, Hard Rock Cafe and Semifinalists for Livewire, Mood Indigo, IIT-Bombay (Dec \'11)\r\nWINNERS @ Mumbai Leg Prelims, B69 and Semifinalists for Wildfire, Springfest, IIT-Kharagpur (Dec \'11)\r\n2nd Place @ Powerchords \'11, SIES College, Sion (Dec \'11)\r\nDeath Fest 2 along with Gutslit, Atmosfear, etc. - B69, Andheri (Jan \'12)\r\nHeadlined @ DropD Battle of Bands, Symphony \'12, K.J.Somaiya, Vidyavihar (Feb \'12)\r\nUnchained \'12 @ D.Y.Patil, Nerul along with Bhayanak Maut, Abraxas, Devoid & Wired Anxiety (Mar \'12)\r\n\r\n','Prateek Keni [9819881088], Rahul Nair [9768765953]','http://www.facebook.com/grimmortal/info','','http://soundcloud.com/grimmortal','http://www.reverbnation.com/grimmortal','0','2847',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','grimmortal'),(328,0,2,2,'Reptilian Death','Reptilian Death came into existence in May 2001 as a solo project of the Demonstealer (Of Demonic Resurrection fame).The project was meant to be a grindcore/death metal project. At the end of May 2001 Reptilian Death released its 1st recording which was a collection of 5 songs called \"5 Easy Ways To Murder Someone\" with each song representing a different method of murder. The songs were a mix of death metal and grindcore but contained the unusual element of humor which gave the whole concept a sort of spoof feel. After this release the project took a back seat until November 2001 which was when Reptilian Death turned from a solo project into a full fledged band after Husain joined as the bassist and Jaivir joined as guitarist and The Demonstealer took over drums and vocal duties. The band prepared itself with 2 new songs \"No Way To Die\" and \"The 2nd Coming Of Evil\" and traveled to Bangalore City to play its 1st live show at The National Law Schools event \"Strawberry Fields\". Sadly the show never happened and Reptilian Death ended up doing an acoustic death metal set at Planet M due to distortion not being allowed. \r\n\r\nThe band returned to Bombay and did their 1st proper gig at Razzberry Rhino. The bands high energy act and intensity got them a good response from people. Following which they recruited a 2nd guitar player, Girish Menon. The band continued touring the local college and club circuit and even bagged a best drummer and bass bassist at a local competition, which was unusual for a metal band to do.\r\n\r\nAfter the bands gig at the RAIT College festival in 2003 the band more or less stopped playing live as the band members were busy with other commitments. In July 2003 The Demonstealer decided to continue the project solo once again and followed up the earlier \"5 Easy Ways To Murder Someone\" with another concept song called \"Nursery Rhymes For Satans Children\" as well as recording the bands 5 originally composed songs and planed to release an album in August 2003.Things however did not go as planned and the album got postponed indefinitely.\r\n\r\nThe Demonstealer then bought the band back together for IIT\'s Livewire show, where \r\nSunny (Epithap) replaced Jaivir on guitars and Nitin (Morticide) took over the main vocal duties. This is was a one off gig for the band and happened to be the last for Girish who passed away in Febuary 2004 after which the band pretty much stopped existing, but Demonstealer did go ahead and release the much awaited album titled Total Annihilation in July 2004. \r\n\r\nAfter 2 years RD was resurrected for a briefly during the end of 2005 for 2 gigs where Pradeep (Demonic Resurrection) handling guitars and new member Sugath doing vocals. Following this the Demonstealer once again flew solo and wrote a new RD EP titled Intestinal Feast where he handled all the music and Sugath featured as the vocalist and lyricist. The EP was released in late 2006 on a split CD called Defaced and Split on Demonstealer Records. Following which the band started touring again with new guitarist Arjun, Husain (Bass), Sugath (Vocals) and Demonstealer (Drums). The band toured for almost a year after which it went back into hibernation.\r\n\r\nCurrently Demonstealer is writing material for a new release in 2010.\r\n','demonstealerrecords@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/ReptilianDeath/info','','http://soundcloud.com/reptiliandeath','http://www.reverbnation.com/reptiliandeath','0','2845',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','reptilian-death'),(329,0,15,15,'Hence Proved','','','http://www.facebook.com/henceproved/info','http://www.khagta.com','http://soundcloud.com/henceproved','http://www.reverbnation.com/henceproved','0','2814',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','hence-proved'),(330,0,71,11,'Prasanna','Prasannas compositions convey a cosmopolitan harmonic language, rich with passing frictions- New York Times\r\n\r\nPrasanna plays guitar quite simply like nobody else on the planet  Allabout Jazz\r\n\r\nPrasanna is the quintessential Indian Renaissance man. A pioneer in performing Carnatic music on the guitar, an engineering graduate from Indian Institute of Technology, a composer for an Oscar winning film, an internationally acclaimed guitarist in contemporary Jazz, Rock and Blues, a Magna-Cum-Laude graduate of Berklee College of Music, an entrepreneurial visionary in the business of creative music and education and President of a world class music college that uniquely blends the traditional Indian Gurukula system of learning with contemporary western college education pedagogy.\r\n\r\nPrasannas prolific body of work include 15 albums as leader, a concert DVD and an Instructional DVD, collaborative albums  Tirtha, Raga Bop Trio, Aka Moon Guitars and more. He is a member of two critically acclaimed trio projects  Tirtha with Vijay Iyer and Nitin Mitta and Raga Bop Trio with Steve Smith and George Brooks. Prasanna has performed and recorded with Airto Moreira, A.R. Rahman, Joe Lovano, Illayaraja, Esperanza Spalding, Victor Wooten, Alex Acuna, Dave Douglas, Omar Hakim, Larry Coryell, Anthony Jackson, Howard Levy, Trilok Gurtu and others.\r\n\r\nPrasanna has composed music for documentary films such as the 2009 Oscar Award winning Smile Pinki and feature films like Framed and many others. His creative collaboration with two-time Oscar winning film composer A.R. Rahman includes arranging and orchestrating the title score of the 2002 Oscar nominated Bollywood Film Lagaan and numerous other guitar playing sessions. Prasanna has also worked with many top Indian film composers on dozens of soundtracks.\r\n\r\nPrasanna has given lectures, talks, workshops and residencies at MITs Sloan School of Management, Banff Center for the Arts, Berklee College of Music, Harvard University, Osnabruck Institute of Music etc. Prasannas passion for music education led him to establish Swarnabhoomi Academy of Music, Indias newest and largest college of music with a world-class international faculty and a sprawling 4-acre campus near Chennai, India.\r\n\r\nPrasannas web site is http://www.guitarprasanna.com/','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Prasanna/7536103955?sk=info','http://www.guitarprasanna.com','','','0','2786',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','prasanna'),(331,0,1,1,'Dhruva Tara','Two years in the making. Finally the constellations coincided and a new group was born.\r\n\r\nStarted April 2010, these six souls of various influences bonded together under one star. Through their differences they somehow found unity. Amidst the chaos they found their inner tranquility.\r\n\r\nThis is a new beginning. A cosmic alignment. This is Dhruva Tara.','','http://www.facebook.com/dhruvatara','','','','117867574922390','2783',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dhruva-tara'),(332,0,31,31,'X-Mantra','Think of the loyals of metal music in Nepal and youll think of young boys and some adult men banging their heads with metal heavyweights like Megadeth, Metallica, Slayer and Sepultura in the year 2000. And think about the first metal band of Nepal and youll surely think about the one and only X- MANTRA. They have already gained a solid cult following in the valley and their music and their influences have also made quite an impact on other major cities of Nepal.\r\n Their first album made quite good impact on the Nepali metal scene. Now with so much to look forward to and new metallers emerging from the call of the metal pioneers, Nepali music (metal, in fact) can start anew itself.\r\nX-MANTRA comprises of Rojesh Shrestha  on vocals, Sandeep Tuladhar on lead guitars,Ritesh Shrestha on the bass guitar, and Bikram Shrestha on the drums.\r\nTheir first single \"Shaleek\" was featured in Music Isles Compilation, which became one of the most recognized songs in the concerts. Shortly after that compilation, the band released their debut album \"Crying For Peace\".','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/X-Mantra/179825034134?sk=info','','','','0','2746',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','x-mantra'),(333,0,3,3,'Amethysts','Formed towards the end of 2008,the band has journeyed through the months drawing influences from Almah, As I lay dying, Angra, Dream theater,\r\nStratovarius, Mr.Big and the other greats. The band has always been open with different styles of music and continues to try and understand all \r\ngenres to bring out the comprehensive element into the bands rock and metal style to provide an original and unique sound.\r\nThe band\'s original creations have a blend of guitar-keyboard harmonies with melodic bass line forming the basement with the drums laying the foundation for the formation of perfect three piece vocal harmonies.\r\nAmethysts have performed along side widely acclaimed Parikrama and have performed in various high profile events like Virgin Mobile Rockathon, Freedom Jam, Live Gig etc.\r\nAmethysts have performed in various fests both at local and national level and have been awarded the best band in fests like AMC Bangalore, GCC,Bangalore Medical College, New Horizon college, National Institute of Fashion Technology Bangalore, Mount Carmel college, Manipal Institute of Technology, Nitte meenakshi Bangalore,Bangalore Central-YouthOpia 2010 etc.\r\nThe band has also headlined at various college fests and also performed at Vh1 Media Nights.\r\nThe band continues to grow and make a firm stand with its music to bring about a new and different sound to its listeners, keeping it vintage and grand with hints of progression.\r\n\r\ncontact info -\r\n\r\nPrajwal - 9986011412/9886353140\r\nSanjay - 9008473760\r\n\r\nemail- amethysts.india@gmail.com','','http://www.facebook.com/amethysts.india/info','','http://soundcloud.com/amethysts','http://www.reverbnation.com/amethysts','0','2744',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','amethysts'),(334,0,22,1,'Dhruv Visvanath','Dhruv Visvanath is a 19 year old guitarist from the heat ridden city of New Delhi. He has often been labelled a jack of all trades and a one man band as well. He is a self taught guitarist, and has been playing for the last 7 years. Alongside the guitar he\'s a trained pianist, a self taught drummer, bassist and even plays the djembe. He\'s also known to sing from time to time! At such a young age, he\'s been labelled as a musical prodigy, having opened for Swarathma and played on the stage of Siri Fort Auditorium. His style of guitar playing, ie percussive guitar playing is somewhat unique to the Indian music scene. \r\n\r\nOk, enough of the 3rd person stuff! I think it\'s something i\'ve always wanted to try out, sounds weird now haha! anyway, i want to thank everyone for liking the page so far, it has done me a world of good, and i am so happy and grateful that i have been given a platform to write and share my music, and i am all the more happy, because i get to share it with you guys! Every now and then i post up videos of various ideas i have, mostly compositions for all to see, and i do hope you guys like it! I made this page so that i could show my love for music, and i hope you guys feel the love too! Thank you so much guys! i do this for you!\r\n\r\nContact For Bookings:\r\n\r\nDhruv Visvanath: +919910813556\r\nEmail: dhruvvisvanath@gmail.com\r\n\r\nTanu Dogra: +919999215749\r\nEmail: tanu.dogra6@gmail.com\r\n\r\n','dhruvvisvanath@gmail.com | tanu.dogra6@gmail.com | firstnoteproductions@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/dhruvvisvanathmusic/info','','http://soundcloud.com/dhruvvisvanath','','0','2737',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dhruv-visvanath'),(335,0,1,1,'Arcane Deception','    Arcane Deception is a melodic death metal band formed in November 2008. The band members had been playing in different bands before they came together to form AD. All of them bring different inspirations to the band which gives AD a unique sound which essentially comprises of the basic metal elements coupled with symphonic melodies, progressive parts & groovy rhythms.\r\n    The band from the very beginning has focussed on the importance of originality and will be the main element in their music till we meet the reaper.\r\n\r\n    Saurabh - Guitars\r\n\r\n    Manu - Vocals\r\n\r\n    Siddie - drums\r\n\r\n    Akshat - Keys\r\n   \r\n    Akshay-Bass\r\n\r\n    Former members:\r\n\r\n    PC(guitars)(Nov 2008-March 2010)\r\n   \r\n    Kshitij(keys)(Nov 2008-July 2011)\r\n   \r\n    It was only yesterday that we were in the hostels of Delhi College Engineering wrecking havoc in an otherwise peaceful locale. After intense jamming much to the pain of the warden and the guards we started having a cult following in the campus.One such night in a semi inebriated state we structured a song that is now formally known as \"pain arcane\".This is where things really took off.The acceptance and response of the crowds to the single was staggering even to crowds not fans of metchul.\r\n\r\n    Guys we love you for that (\\m/)keep it alive !!!\r\n\r\n    After 2 years of gig exp , and many wins (later) the band is getting ready to record an EP(untitled) with the label Grey and Saurian(ref A).The proposed tracks on the EP will be:\r\n\r\n    1.Pain Arcane\r\n    http://www.myspace.com/arcanedeception\r\n\r\n    2.Arcane Deception(self titled track)\r\n    3.Troops in Oblivion\r\n    4.Ghost in the Ghetto\r\n    5.Bastard\'s Quest\r\n\r\n\r\n    We want to thank each and every fan that, forget about moshing, but fucking so much as bobbed their heads along with our music.You guys are the shit and we love you for it \\m/\r\n\r\n    -Siddie\r\n\r\n   \r\n    Follow us on\r\n\r\n    Twitter\r\n    https://twitter.com/ArcaneDeception\r\n\r\n    MySpace\r\n    http://www.myspace.com/arcanedeception\r\n\r\n    For further details & gigs, contact :\r\n\r\n    Siddie\r\n    +91-9818522933\r\n\r\n    Shashwat Gupta\r\n    http://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=526396620&ref=ts#!/Saurian?ref=ts\r\n\r\n    Ref A:\r\n    http://www.greyandsaurian.com/\r\n\r\n    Last Updated on:15th Sept 2010\r\nSome of our recent achievements:\r\n\r\n','Saurabh Seth - 9718425615','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Arcane-Deception/152635188091684?sk=info','','http://soundcloud.com/arcanedeception','','0','2736',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','arcane-deception'),(336,0,107,107,'WEIRD ANXIETY','YOU MAY ORDER OUR DEBUT E.P. Act I Scene I FROM http://records.sixinchnails.com/?page_id=587&fb_source=message','MY METAL BIN ( http://mymetalbin.com/ ), FRAMESHIFT INITIATIVES ( https://www.facebook.com/?ref=home#!/frameshiftinitiatives)','http://www.facebook.com/weirdanxiety/info','http://weirdanxiety.blogspot.com','http://soundcloud.com/weirdanxiety','http://www.reverbnation.com/weirdanxiety','0','2734',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','weird-anxiety'),(337,0,3,3,'Solder','The Indian sub-continent over the past decade has been nestling an independent music scene, and in 2009 Bangalore gave us SOLDER. Siddarth Abraham,Sylvester Pradeep, Akhilesh Kumar, Joel Rozario and Samson Phillip got together by forces which they now like to call destiny, and started making music almost randomly, and Bangalore saw a band that played their music Live and Loud and contributing their two bits to the independent music movement on India.\r\n\r\nWith a line-up at equilibrium and a defined sound, the gigs and the competitions (runners up Strawberry Fields 2009, Bangalore Winners of Yamaha Asian Beats 2010, Bangalore Winners of Channel V Launchpad 2011, runners up of Chennai Live Band Hunt) kept coming and with it Solder developed a reputation of being electric, energetic and fun on stage. The Solder show is like one big party, completely informal, with the feel good vibe, bringing the house down with funk, soul, rock and twenty-something energy. And with this passion for music and their ability to connect with their audiences, Solder started winning over fans at every gig theyve played, and made audiences feel the vibe that they call Live and Loud!!\r\n\r\nOften described as a unit of five drifters glued together by music, Solder was born with the intent of writing feel good songs, and belting them out Live and Loud. \r\nNow with all the varied influences bouncing off each other, Solder slowly created a sound space underlined by groove and layered with vocal melodies and harmonies, accompanied by screaming guitar licks and reverb laden drum sounds. \r\n\r\nWith their debut album in the pipeline, SOLDER will try and re-create the Live and Loud vibe on record, and when it does release we can all play it on loop and smile, and make the world a happy place.\r\n','joel@soldermusic.com, siddarth@soldermusic.com','http://www.facebook.com/SolderMusic/info','http://www.soldermusic.com/','http://soundcloud.com/soldermusic','http://www.reverbnation.com/solder','0','2710',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','solder'),(338,0,29,29,'Prachir','                                                                                                                                                                                          Prachir  a Sanskrit word it means The Wall. However, for the band members, it is the strong bonding that they have and that they create with their audiences, fans and friends that give meaning to the name. Weve put our thought into it, and through all the thoughts we came to a conclusion, its an unorthodox conceptual thoughts. \r\nThe sources of inspiration behind Prachirs survival and existence are the members passion for music and the experience that they gather in their professional journey, started since the year 2006. \r\nWhat started as a small jamming session within the closed doors eventually gave way to rock solid stage performances at different rock concert, college fests and corporate events. \r\n2008 and 2009 was the most significant years for the band.\r\n\r\n26th September 08  we released our debut album from Asha Audio in West Bengalwith so much competition around we were the only band who got selected and released the album with the  big shots of the circuit .. The album spent 8 weeks on the planet M and Music world regional top charts  .  It has introduced a fresh sound in the Bengali rock scenario, and quickly it drew the attention of listeners nationally.\r\n\r\n	Unish Kuri Magazine reviewed as the best debut album , followed  by telegraph as  New Kids on Row \r\n\r\n	Big Fm n Idea presents big bangle music Award also nominated our song Porichoy in best rock song of the year category. \r\n	    98.3 FM (Radio Mirchi) has started streaming  our song TSUNAMI  as an EXCLUSIVE Song for the entire month of OCTOBER.- 2008\r\n	All the prachir songs from the debut album get airplay on every bangla radio station in Kolkata, including  Uh la la in Tripura, Agartala and Washington Bangla Radio. \r\n \r\n\r\nIn Jan 2009, the band got selected in Channel [V] launch pad III .It was for the first time that Bengali Rock Music came into prominence on a national platform. ....... Being among the top 6 finalist band is just a reward of the bands hard work and determination.                             \r\n They released two videos from their debut album in 2009 .[ Bharat borsho ] - become the most popular song after launch padChannel [V] also used the live footage of the song as a promo for the competition. . [Tsunami]  became the most heart touching rock ballad song.\r\n	Channel 8 featured Bharat borsho as exclusive music video on all month of January 2009 later on the video also got air play in Sangeet Bangla, Tara Music.\r\n	Later on we released the music video of Tsunami  Sangeet Bangla featured it as exclusive video for the month of September 2009.the video got regular airplay on all other major Bengali music channel. \r\n	In 2010 we again came up with a new Music video Porichoy  first HD Bengali music video ever produced in Bengali band industryThe songs speaks about Drug abuseThe cause was supported by a Anti Drugs Ngo, Based in Los Angles. \r\nThe video received a huge amount of critic from all over the country on online sites 2000 views in 48 hours (YouTube)\r\nFeatured as xclusive in Tara Music .Got a regular airplay on sangeet bangle, TV South Asia, Incoda TV (All Metro Stations) and others.\r\n \r\nMusic has no language barrier.   They played gigs all across the west Bengal campuses but the most defining moment was when they invited to perform in G.L Bajaj Institute of Technology, greater Noida . It was for the first time that a Bengali band was invited to perform in national college fest. .and the journey continues                       \r\n  \r\nGetting an overwhelming response from their fans and listeners, the band has started working on their second album which slated for January 2012 release.\r\n','+ 91 9830524736','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Prachir/84782753360?sk=info','','http://soundcloud.com/prachir','http://www.reverbnation.com/prachirz','0','2707',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','prachir'),(339,2,74,1,'Fire Exit','Though for purposes of entirely official nature, we like to categorize Fire Exit as a band that plays Progressive Alternative Rock, we truly believe that it falls in the category of bands that are almost impossible to categorize under one single genre of music. Our music is a combination of rock, metal and electronic sounds. The band essentially blends great vocal melody along with instrument harmony, and is based on experimentation with varied time signatures, jazz-influenced bass-lines and an Indian percussion instrument. But at the same time, we like to keep our music simple. As a group of musicians brewing our styles together, we also lay equal focus on the way we sound live and on record, giving importance to not just what we play, but also how all that playing comes together and mixes when it comes out on speakers; hence immense stress is laid on the production of our tracks. Our focus as a band is to create a sound unique to the band, with varied styles of rock, metal and psychedelia coming together for great listening pleasure to both the common listener and other musicians. We lay stress on improving our songwriting and playing as we grow together as a band, looking to create mature and sensible music. ','Aashish Mandhwani- 09910001312','http://www.facebook.com/fireexitindia/info','http://www.fireexitindia.com','','','0','2707',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 12:46:45',119,'[\"\"]','[\"Aashish- 09910001312\\/ Varun- 09910453565\"]','fire-exit'),(340,0,1,1,'Middle Brother','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Middle-Brother/103491629726576','','','','103491629726576','2699',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','middle-brother'),(341,5,3,3,'Arjun Vagale','Arjun Vagale is arguably one of the most in-demand DJs in India. As one of the countrys biggest EDM exports, he plays over 100 gigs a year, touring regularly in Europe and Asia, often spends his summers in the worlds techno Mecca, Berlin. A man with a true passion for underground music, which he relentlessly plays, produces and promotes. No wonder he was awarded 2011  2012s Best Techno DJ and DJ Of the Year and more recently topped the DJ Mag India Poll.\r\n\r\nHe has played alongside such heavyweights as Fergie, Sasha, Fat Boy Slim, Dave Seaman, Nic Fanciulli, Paolo Mojo and Cari Lekebusch while his live act, Jalebee Cartel, has shared headlining spots with the likes of The Chemical Brothers, The Prodigy and Modeselektor. His knowledge and use of technology in the booth is second to none, often adding drum machines and samplers to create a uniquely raw, funk-laden techno set.\r\n\r\nIt has been almost 10 years since Arjun, along with 3 friends, formed Indias biggest live act, Jalebee Cartel. With its genre-bending sets, the band has generated a huge buzz and has featured in DJ Mag, MixMag and Elles list of Rising Stars, and has even graced the cover of Rolling Stone, India. The live act has released over 50 singles on Ostwind Records, Neurotraxx Deluxe, Vapour, Baroque among others. 2009 saw the release of Jalebees critically acclaimed debut album, ONEPOINTNOTHING.\r\n\r\nBut it is Arjuns solo productions that are now making some serious noise.\r\n\r\n2010 saw the release of Kill the String on Tom Buddens ALiVE Recordings. It quickly caught the ear of Fergie, who played it on Digweeds Transitions to great feedback and immediately commissioned Arjun for an EP on his new Tribal Rage imprint, and followed it with two Vinyl releases on Excentric Mizik. Carl Cox, Karotte, Kaserdisco, Sebastien Leger all supported these heavily. Remixes for Fergie, Denis Horvat, Solead, Dale Anderson, Mabaan Soul and a chart topper for Montero followed. His single with Colognes Traum family - Trapez Ltd, was much applauded by DJs and clubbers alike while his collaboration with Tim Richards on Kaiserdiscos KD Music stayed on the Digital & Vinyl charts for well over a month, getting multiple plays from a certain Richie Hawtin. Further releases on Mihalis Safrass Material Series, Sians Octopus, Berlin based Hummingbird & Monaque Speciale are to follow along with some tasty collaborations.\r\n\r\nNever one to play Top 10 tunes, Arjuns always scouting out fresh underground tracks  the man never sleeps! His latest venture has been to found and manage a young record label, Mak.Tub Music, with partner Logistic Soundz. Over the last three years, the imprint has an impressive roster of artists, including Alex Dolby, Fiord, Jay Haze, Pawas, Jimmy Van M, Dave Ellesmere, Ray Kajioka, and has already hit the coveted Beatport charts.\r\n\r\nTheres good reason that Arjun Vagales name has become synonymous with high quality in the Electronic Music scene. Whether packing in the dance floor or producing yet another monster tune, Arjuns absolute dedication to house and techno is apparent in everything he does.','','http://www.facebook.com/ArjunVagaleOfficial/info','','http://soundcloud.com/arjun-jalebee','','0','2688',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-08 05:45:37',249,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','arjun-vagale'),(342,0,2,2,'\"Musicman\" Mihir','Please head over to Mihir\'s official page on facebook: https://www.facebook.com/mihirjoshipage\r\n\r\nTo follow him on twitter go to: http://twitter.com/mihirjoshipage\r\n\r\nThank you :)','','http://www.facebook.com/musicmanmihirfanclub/info?ref=ts','http://www.mihirjoshi.co.in ','http://soundcloud.com/mihirjoshipage','','0','2682',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','musicman-mihir'),(343,0,2,2,'Panic Attack','Meet Panic. Panic knows when you`ve left that assignment for later and the deadlines tomorrow. It knows when you are truly truly screwed. And then it attacks. So be scared. We are a tr0o br0otal metal band.\r\n\r\nBackstory:\r\nIt started with food. 4 people covering the songs they like. Then came hot food. Tava Pulao was born. On the rainy sad day when Michael Jackson moonwalked away from this planet, we covered Backstreet Boys. We got through to the finals. omg yay.\r\nWrote an original that night. Realised we can actually do this. Changed some things. Panic Attack happened.','bandmemberfirstname@panicattack.in  :)','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Panic-Attack/304289534178?sk=info','','','http://www.reverbnation.com/panicattacka','0','2674',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','panic-attack'),(344,0,0,0,'Amrinder Gill','','','http://www.facebook.com/AmrinderGill.Judaa/info','http://www.amrindergill.co.uk/','','','0','2668',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','amrinder-gill'),(345,0,1,1,'Half Step Down','Formed in 2005, Half Step Down began gigging in 2006 as essentially a rock \'n\' roll band, though it would be more accurate to acknowledge their sound as a versatile mish-mash incorporating elements of the blues, alt-rock, funk and reggae. \r\n \r\nConsciously refusing to let themselves be fenced in by genres, they derive their sound from influences and inspirations ranging from Led Zeppelin, RHCP and Dave Matthews to Rachmaninoff, Marley and Django Reinhardt. \r\n \r\nIn early 2007 the band made it to GIR (The Great Indian Rockshow) with their track Overture to Outerspace, which subsequently launched them on a much vaster platform. They spent most of the following year touring the country, taking time out in June to appear on Channel [V]\'s show Launch Pad. They wrapped \'07 with a highly acclaimed unplugged performance in their city, Delhi, where their cover of Redemption Song stood out as one of the critics\' finest of the evening. \r\n \r\nKnown for their antics on stage, HSD are perhaps as much the performers as they are the musicians. With a hedonistic approach to music, they maintain an air of fun that remains a key quotient despite lineup changes and other minor disruptions. \r\n ','info@halfstepdownmusic.com ','http://www.facebook.com/HSDDelhi/info','http://www.halfstepdownmusic.com','','','0','2663',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','half-step-down'),(346,0,64,64,'Funeral in Heaven','Audio: http://entertheraavancult.bandcamp.com\r\n\r\nVisual: http://www.youtube.com/user/FuneralinHeaven666\r\n\r\nBookings/Press:\r\nWorldwide - Official/Direct - funeralinheaven@hotmail.com\r\nSlovenia - Nokturnal Management - nigrumserpentis@gmail.com\r\n\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/funeralinheaven/info','','','','0','2646',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','funeral-in-heaven'),(348,0,108,108,'Abbie Gale','Abbie Gale are a five-piece band, that took shape during the summertime 2003 in Patras. They record their first album titled Family Life, that it circulates the summertime 2005 from Vacant Records. The album is characterized by its low profile, acoustic sound and the voice of Evira. It takes dithyrambic reviews from the printed and electronic press and the group intensifies their live appearances in many Greek cities. \r\n\r\n  They started to work their new songs on summertime 2006 and two years after the release of their acclaimed debut Family Life, Abbie Gale are back with their second album, symbolically titled 2. The music style of the band changes perceptibly, the sound becomes more electric and the rhythm most intense, without losing the melody that characterizes them. Guided by the charming, wide-ranging voice of Evira, the band appear more mature than ever, as they present their compositions in a solid and determined fashion. The albums excellent production values, combined with Abbie Gales confident playing, make 2 an exciting listening proposition. \r\n\r\n  Starting with the introspective mood of the opening track Life After Life, Abbie Gale guide us through a bright playful conversation in Lovesong (guest featuring Raining Pleasures frontman Vassilikos), sparks of lyricism such as Clown and Air and an agonizing spoken-word manifesto in Danko. The bands dedication to their creative vision, along with their refined sense of songwriting and their honest inspiration make for an aesthetically flawless result. \r\n  Abbie Gales 2 is also the debut release of the new and upcoming indie label Inner Ear.','info@abbiegale.gr','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Abbie-Gale/12753510828?sk=info','http://www.abbiegale.gr','','','0','2585',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','abbie-gale'),(349,0,81,81,'Digital Suicide','Digital Suicide is a Rock Band/performing cultural organization where three young promising artists pooled in their natural music making abilities and started creating their art.\r\n\r\nIt all sparked off in 2008 with contemporary songwriter, guitarist and singer Daniel Langhtasa, bassist and backing vocalist Dpak Borah and Ratan Bordoloi ,drummer and percussionist started the band when they began questioning the self-destructive nature of a confused and chaotic world.   \r\nHailing from a place called Haflong, a small town in North East India, where there is still no proper communication with the rest of the world and torn apart by terrorism and insurgency they found themselves unable to show their frustration. They then resolutely locked themselves in a world of their own and remained in the room for about 6 months trying to understand the gravity of relation between them, music and the rest of the world. Music was no longer just their passion; it became their sole mode of expression.  \r\n\r\nWith the hunger to play their music to people everywhere, they shifted base to Guwahati city. Still not finding enough venues that host rock bands and the absence of a music scene they started sharing their songs online and active discussions/debates in forums soon creating an independent scene where now there is a show every month.\r\n\r\nDigital Suicide is the new voice of independent rock scene of India. Strong bass and drum groove acts as the driving force behind the bands music with the guitar providing simple atmospheric and ambient textures to the songs rather than just carrying the melody. Digital Suicides flirtation with 70s disco and 80s pop melodies reflect on their vocal melodies. Their music has been inspired by the works of R. D. Barman, Bappi Lahiri, Classical Music, bands like RHCP, Placebo, Joy Division, R.E.M., Sonic Youth, Lady Gaga, MJ, Radiohead, etc. \r\n\r\nThe band has proved their critics wrong and continue to play their brand of contemporary alternative music constantly creating positive energy in and around them. They have just released an EP of five songs for which the band is experiencing a rapid growth of fans and urgency among the fans to sing the bands addictive melodies and do dark disco rock dance with them.  \r\n\r\nCatch them at a gig near you!!  \r\n','springboardsurprises@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/digitalsuicid3/info','http://digitalsuicid3.bandcamp.com/','','http://www.reverbnation.com/digitalsuicid3','0','2581',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','digital-suicide'),(350,0,2,2,'GUTSLIT','','Ankit Sinha, Dynell Bangera, Gurdip Singh Narang.','http://www.facebook.com/gutslit/info','','','http://www.reverbnation.com/gutslit','0','2579',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','gutslit'),(351,0,109,109,'The Chosen','The Chosen comprises of a bunch of young and talented girls from Aizawl brought together by their love for Music.They started jamming out at 2009 and got together as a Gospel band(All-Girl band) by the end of that year. ','Parema-9436140649','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Chosen/155253797820243?sk=info','','','','0','2570',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-chosen'),(352,0,109,109,'STACY\'S PENITENCE','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/STACYS-PENITENCE/76978378266?sk=info','','','','0','2567',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','stacys-penitence'),(353,0,3,3,'GORIFIED','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/GORIFIED/187325001570?sk=info','','','','0','2562',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','gorified'),(354,0,0,0,'Last Men Standing','Last Men Standing are Nyimo Nijman and Levin Karcher. \r\n\r\nNyimo Nijman who is known for his activity as Last Men Standing, also known as Magnasonic, was born 1987 in Amsterdam, Holland. He grew up with piano lessons and school music classes. His mother knew Riktams mother and his older brother knew Shanti and Riktam. Thus, Nyimo fell into the laps of the growling mad juveniles. Then he started visiting Ibiza every summer. Back and forth until he was seven. After which he continued going to school in Ibiza with his partner in crime Levin. It was there that he began Djing with only 12 at the one of the most famous club, the Blue Rose. Since then he has been playing in clubs and parties around the Island. His great inspirations are the original crusaders GMS, Shanti, Buschman, Poli, Wrecked Machines. \r\n\r\nRight after his Schooling with 16 bought a Pc and began producing sound. In 2004 Nyimo attended a school of sound engineering. With high-school friend Levin he built Bulldog Studios with a G5 and Logic Pro. \r\n\r\nLevin Karcher was born in Germany in 1986 and moved to Ibiza in 1988. He started Dj\'ing 2002 at the young age of 16. And was producing music a year later. In the beginning it was only a hobby, not as profession. He went to their and half year sound engineering school to further his passion. After which he Dj\'d in France, Germany and Spain. He likes simple and progressive trance, but of high production value. \r\n\r\nLevin has been a resident Dj at the Namaste trance events since 2001, at the full moon events /campo parties and was Djing in 2005 at the Spunout In Ibiza events at Club Privilege. \r\n\r\nBesides working on a new album the two youngsters are also working on several side projects. Namely Dub Dealers with ambient chill out vibrations and some new tunes in the minimal and electro department. Their careers have taken them form parties in Amsterdam to Barcelona and countless clubs in Ibiza like Eden. Sumuum, all Full Moon events and many other open air parties and Namaste. \r\n\r\nBulldog studios have shown themselves to be the promising new talents on the horizon of the prestigious Ibiza label. Courting and hosting huge numbers of guests these two have captivated the audience to new bring new highest not known before. Like GMS before them they have the power and technique to endure, amaze and translate frequencies into sound pleasure. These two kids are destined to become overlords of disco and dance, whatever direction the music style takes. The release of their debut (double CD) album This is Ibiza was released on January 18th, 2008 with ON THE MOVE MUSIC. They still make excellent trance, but now Last Men Standing has become the standard for the new electro sound and down tempo coming from Ibiza.','','http://www.facebook.com/lastmenstanding/info','http://www.lastmenstandingmusic.com','','','0','2551',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','last-men-standing'),(355,0,2,2,'Rang','Rang is a versatile six-member Band from Mumbai performing a variety of genres, allowing them to converge into one unique spectrum of sound. Based in Mumbai since late 2008, they can broadly be classified as an Hindi Pop/ Rock band. They perform a lot of their critically acclaimed originals, interfused with some trademark crowd thumping mainstream covers. You will find young and old grooving to their music, and their strength lies in Versatility, easily in the running for being one of the best Hindi acts in the Indian Music circuit. \r\n\r\nRangs music attempts to bridge the gap between the diverse genres of music and their melodies represent the modern day music lovers interests melted with an Indian element, bridging the gap between urban and the masses. They derive great pleasure in entertaining audiences with both unusual, spontaneous medleys, as well as crowd-thumping Classics. Very few bands have the Vocal chemistry that Rang does, and their original lyrics have got them repute from anyone whos had a chance to experience their compositions. Overall, each member\'s unique musical background lends to Rang\'s sound that richness and a spectrum which connects with the heart of any fan of great music.\r\n\r\nAcclaim and Recent Performances\r\n\r\nRang was awarded the Judges choice award in the TOTO Fund for Music Awards, a Nationwide Band hunt organized by Counter Culture Records in 2009. Since then, theres been no looking back. Rang has been performing at the Revival of music at Bandstands Project organized by Bombay Elektrik project, Thespo at Prithvi Theatre (2009-2011), Funny Rock at The Comedy Store, B-69, and more recently at the Celebrate Bandra Festival, to name a few.  \r\n\r\nRang has also been performing for the 30,000 dream runners at the Standard Chartered Mumbai Marathon the last two years. After starting off with performances at MoodIndigo  and Malhar, Rang has now stepped on to the college circuit by popular demand. Their recent performance for 2500 college students at S.I.E.S.O.N.s was much acclaimed, and the audiences continue to express fond memories of the thumping performance. \r\n\r\nRang has also done the rounds on Radio stations like Fever 104, Radio Mirchi, and Jago Mumbai - making quite an impression on the masses. All in all, If youre looking for Indias music in the years to come, drop in to any Rang gig for fresh, vibrant and versatile music. \r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/FollowRang/info','','','http://www.reverbnation.com/followrang','0','2550',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rang'),(356,0,2,2,'The Other People','\'The Other People\' is a band from Bombay (India). We do not classify ourselves or come under any particular genre, we cover everything from Rock to Pop to Rock n\' Roll to Blues to Reggae and even some Retro! \r\n\r\nWe have been playing around the country for about 7 years now and are soon coming out with our debut album! \r\n\r\nWe were recently the opening act for two big International artists on their tours to India in 2010 ... the first one being American Rockers \'Saving Abel\' and the second being Danish Popstars \'Michael Learns To Rock\'.\r\n\r\nWe ensure that all our shows are filled with energy, Retro & current songs that people of all ages can relate to and just basically alot of fun!','gigs@theotherpeopleindia.com','http://www.facebook.com/theotherpeople/info','http://www.theotherpeopleindia.com','','http://www.reverbnation.com/theotherpeopleband','0','2545',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-other-people'),(357,0,1,1,'Ivan & Alyosha','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Ivan-Alyosha/130165677020912','','http://soundcloud.com/ivanandalyosha','','130165677020912','2544',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ivan-alyosha'),(358,0,10,10,'Bamboo Shoots','Theres something odd about Bamboo Shoots.  Certainly a band of four brown-skinned boys whose collective faces look equally at home on a terrorist watchlist as any promotional poster is, well, unique. That all of the members are of Indian descent at a time when Indian culture is exploding globally is surely noteworthy. We gave up on fitting in a long time ago, states singer/guitarist Avir Mitra with a shrug.\r\n\r\n Mix innovative hooks and lean guitars with urban inspired beats and subtle world flavor, add a dash of Brooklyn cred but temper it with a lyrical openness  now you begin to get at the sound of Armour, their Epic Records debut. Its future-feeling and its retro and it almost didnt happen. \r\n\r\nAs the story goes, Avir was only days away from joining medical school when the band got a life-changing phone call: they had won MTVus Best Music on Campus contest and would be signing with Epic. They would perform on Late Night with Conan OBrien in a few days.  Welcome to Bamboo Shoots world. \r\n\r\nAvir and bassist/vocalist Karl Sukhia began playing music together after bumping heads as kids in the Zoroastrian community to which their parents belonged.  They recorded songs on an old PC with a pencil mic. It was several years before they met drummer Shiv Puri, a brilliant finance student who needed something more to crunch than numbers  Shiv soon found his salvation in drumming with the duo. At their first practice, friend of a friend Ankur Patel showed up with what was to become a key ingredient  an Indian folk drum called the dhol. They covered Hall and Oates. Finally, Ankur, an up-and-coming DJ, wove 808s and percussion into the mix and was in the band by days end to seal the lineup.\r\n\r\nFast-forward through the time spent lugging gear, sleeping on floors and scrounging cash for studio time.  Its 2008 and the band is signed and ready to record. Theyve toured with Plain White Ts, rocked shows with Soulja Boy, locked in a Gibson sponsorship and just finished a national ad campaign with Virgin. Jerry Harrison (of Talking Heads and Modern Lovers) was the first to see Bamboo Shoots potential and signed on as producer.\r\n\r\nTalking Heads style stemmed from rhythm  we saw a common thread there, explains Avir.  Jerry dusted off old Heads synths and guitars that hadnt been touched in years, adds Karl.  Avir played most of the album on the same Strat that was used on Stop Making Sense. \r\n\r\nThe band proceeded to cold call their favorite mixer, UK-based Mark Spike Stent. His familiarity with both pop (Madonna, Beyonce, U2) and indie (MIA, Arcade Fire, CSS) matched perfectly with the bands vision. Despite more lucrative offers, Spike heard something in the tracks and eagerly signed on to mix.  \"Everyone in the studio was curious to see who this baby band was that Spike had chosen to work with,\" notes Shiv. \r\n\r\nThe result, Armour, is a debut that effortlessly sounds unlike any of its peers.  Hey Girl, a throwback to Princes Controversy, sets the tone with a sing-along verse and a bassline that stabs you over and over. From there, the band never loses their laser-like focus on hooks, beats and vibe.  Where the Ocean Meets the Road feels like it should have been on the Days of Thunder Soundtrack.  You would focus on the retro cool, but you are too busy humming it in your head.  Ballads like Whenever Youre Around conjure up comparisons to Justin Timberlakes solo work, until of course a shrieking guitar comes in and throws off the entire comparison. Tracks like Milk, Satin & Silk get the hipsters blogging, while Wrong All Along cuts to the angsty chase and gets the teens bopping.  Bamboo Shoots is equal parts Brooklyn and suburban New Jersey, and Armour reflects it. \r\n\r\nStill, its hard to describe the reaction Bamboo Shoots gets at their live shows, where sets become excuses for all-night dance parties. Things just connect.  A recent media-frenzied tour of India only fuels suspicion that the appeal of Bamboo Shoots could be exceptionally broad. Indeed, there is something unpredictably odd going on here. Lets hope it stays that way.','laura@bigfatcat.net','http://www.facebook.com/bambooshoots/info','http://www.bambooshoots.com','','','0','2518',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','bamboo-shoots'),(359,0,1,1,'THINK FLOYD','\"Wot\'s uh.. the deal?\" [OBSCURED BY CLOUDS 1969] \r\n	Pink Floyd were the pioneers of psychedelic music and one of the biggest selling acts ever on the planet. The group acquired a sensational reputation by performing Sound AND light shows and built a cult following that continues to grow even after years of the bands breaking up.\r\n\r\n	THINK FLOYD - India\'s biggest and only Pink Floyd tribute show - was conceived in 2006 as a collaborative production, featuring select music, surround sound, extravagant lights and visual imagery set to contemporary social themes. Reputed \'floydians\' from bands such as PARIKRAMA, THEM CLONES, ADVAITA, ARTISTES UNLIMITED etc. have entranced many since then, in their earnest attempt to recreate and relive the very relevant, paranormal magic of psychedelia.\r\n\r\n\r\n\"The show must go on [THE WALL 1979]\"\r\n	From their debut great gig in an \'architecture\' college ground, more than a few performances at Hard Rock Cafe\'s across India, THINK FLOYD are now also a part of, and perform live for \"Bring Down The Walls\", India\'s first original Concert-Theatre, which premiered in 2010 at New Delhi.','We Mean Music','http://www.facebook.com/thinkfloydindia/info?ref=ts','','','','0','2514',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','think-floyd'),(360,0,3,3,'Final Surrender','Formed in December 2010,The members of Final surrender quickly set into its genre of Progressive Metal-core, something very new to the Indian metal scene.Drawing influences from many bands such as August Burns Red, As I Lay Dying, Meshuggah, Texas In July, Textures, Soilwork, Inflames, I The Breather, Killswitch Engage, Extol, Demon Hunter, Zao, The Devil Wears Prada, Haste The Day, Living Sacrifice, Veil Of Maya.  Final surrender has managed to find its sound in a very short span. The debut album \"The Expanse\" got out in december 2010, something that is going to create a revolution in the indian metal scene. The band sees \r\nJoseph Samuel on vocals, \r\nSanjay Kumar on guitar, \r\nJames stephanes on guitar, \r\nSudhanshu Nayak) on Bass, and \r\nJared Sandhy  on drums.\r\nThe Band Has Taken Its Stand to go live to rock the world out.','Joseph Samuel- +919738126435','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Final-Surrender/128526020534293?sk=info','','http://soundcloud.com/finalsurrender','http://www.reverbnation.com/finalsurrender','0','2511',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','final-surrender'),(361,0,2,2,'Dischordian','Dischordian is an acoustic project started by Garreth DMello in 2009. Originally conceived as a solo project, Dischordian slowly expanded to a four-piece band with multi-instrumentalists Agnelo Picardo, Howard Pereira, and Nigel Rajaratnam on guitar, saxophone, trumpet, lap steel, melodica, mandolin, and percussion. Their sometimes dreamy, sometimes chaotic sound has found wide appreciation among a varied group of fans, primarily on the basis of their gigs and a bunch of early, low-fi demos.Spanning multiple genres, but primarily grounded in folk, punk, and blues, Dischordians sound is difficult to categorise or describe. As Garreth says, I know what to call the things that go in; I dont know what to call what comes out. The bands own favourite description comes from NH7: Goa-tinged orchestral indie rock.Since the bands inception, theyve been featured twice on Stupid Ditties, the annual compilation of some of the countrys best underground acts, and in 2009 they were named as one of the most promising indie acts of the year by Indiecision. In April 2011, Dischordian released its much-awaited debut album The Feni Farm Riot. The album features the more minimal, stripped down sound of the bands early days, with arrangements consisting primarily of guitars, percussion, and trumpet. Recorded and mixed by Aviv Pereira, mastered by Zorran Mendonsa, and with artwork by Hemant Kumar, the album has received an almost universally positive response from the Indian underground scene. \r\n\r\n\r\nPRESS\r\na stunning debut album showcases Garreths skills as a songwriter as he crafts minimalistic melancholy songs and sinister ballads with accomplished ease. This isnt cheerful guitar-pop, this is an album of simple and achingly beautiful songs about love, hate, and death that remind you of sleepless, lonely nights spent in the warm embrace of mild despair that sneaks up on you in the early hours of the morning a well composed and intimate album by experienced and talented musicians at the top of their game. ...one of the best albums you will hear this year.\r\nBhanuj Kappal - The Big M\r\nDischordians sound took just a little bit to settle in, after the bass-heavy Bombay Bassment but damn, can they write songs. The whole crowd was singing along. The absence of a full drum kit lent their sound a very gypsy feel; all I could think of as I sang along was drinking songs!\r\nRonit Sarkar - Sonic Buzz\r\nDMellos whisky-soaked vocals are served through a finely shaped musical decanter made up of trumpet player Agnelo Aggie Picardo, guitarist Howard Pereira and saxophone and melodica player Nigel Rajaratnam. With a singing and writing style that doffs its hat to everyone from Bob Dylan and Leonard Cohen to Tom Waits and Eddie Vedder, Dischordian is one of those bands that often says the sourest things in the sweetest ways. This is best exemplified on such catchy but caustic material like The Old Whore and Your Right Heel that appear on their brilliantly titled debut album The Feni Farm Riot...\r\nMumbai Boss Editors - Mumbai Boss\r\n...they\'ve slowly and surely fashioned their own effective DIY ethic; one that, given their unique brand of music and their workman-like drive to keep playing as many gigs as possible, will undoubtedly pay dividends in the coming years. the contingent of fans at the venue knew the words to almost all of the 18 songs (including a popular parody of \'La Bamba\' called \'Mera Sabse Lamba\') performed on the night, singing back with feni-powered (the band handed out free shots of the popular Goan hooch) vigour and vociferously demanding an extended encore... \r\nArjun S Ravi - The Sunday Guardian\r\nwhether it was the Feni shots, the strategically placed merchandise, the brilliant set, or a combination of everything, Dischordian certainly launched their debut album in style for anyone hoping to sell their music, Id say that this is way to do it!\r\nArjun Sathe - Whats The Scene India\r\nThe Old Whore has become something of a cult underground anthem, and its not difficult to see why. A very strong melody coupled with cleverly written lyrics make the song instantly likeable. one of the most original and accomplished albums to emerge from the Indian Indie music scene. It is an album that reflects distinctly mature songwriting, captured in an extremely raw and organic form.\r\nAalok Padhye of Something Relevant - What The Scene India\r\nThe band performed a nearly two hour-long set comprised of material from the album and a few cuts that arent on the album as well. Powered by a contingent of hardcore fans, the quartet played the best Dischordian set weve seen to date, totally engulfing the Lower Parel venue with their own private party  a refreshing brand of Goa-tinged orchestral indie rock, the members of the band dressed in suit vests and fedoras, and free shots of feni passed around.\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/Dischordian','','','','55325967345','2495',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dischordian'),(362,0,3,3,'CROSS Legacy','Cross Legacy is an Indian Christian rock band formed in Bangalore, Karnataka in 2006. The band currently consists of Bijoy Thangaraj (lead vocals, guitars, keys), Billy Sunday (lead guitars), Amith Ramos (violin, keyboards, backing vocals), Isaac (bass), Jagan J (drums). The band has performed at many gigs in and around Bangalore. Notable ones include opening for John Schlitt of Petra\'s (4-time Grammy winner) concert in Bangalore in 2012. Cross Legacy released their first single, Legacy on Feb 12, 2012. ','Jagan J (Mobile: +91 9845946768), Bijoy (Mobile: +91 9916032116)','http://www.facebook.com/crosslegacyband','http://www.crosslegacy.com','','','182281488492108','2495',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','cross-legacy'),(363,0,4,4,'Dark Helm','The sound of Dark Helm is the musicalisation of the journey of an ancient warrior through the sands of Persia and his quest to defend his throne, by bending time and cheating dea','Ninad Ingulkar    +919823192483','http://www.facebook.com/darkhelmindia','http://www.reverbnation.com/darkhelm','','http://www.reverbnation.com/darkhelm','321408767564','2482',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dark-helm'),(364,0,54,54,'Rockfour','Widely regarded as Israels best rock export since Minimal Compact, Rockfours signature sound is a tightly knit mesh of guitar driven harmony that hints at Love,  Grandadd, Byrds and Wilco. Rockfour burst onto the world scene in 2000 with the release of its first English-language record Supermarket (Earsay Records), an internationally acclaimed debut which was selected by Rolling Stone music critic Richie Unterberger as one of his ten favorite albums of that year.\r\nThe release of Rockfours second album in 2001, One Fantastic Day, also garnered accolades from top media outlets such as NPR, The New York Times, Rolling Stone and The Los Angeles Times (which dubbed it a world-class band flexing its musical muscles). \r\nOpening for other bands like Dave Matthews, the B-52s and Blondie, together with appearances at festivals like International Pop Overthrow, SXSW and CMJ Music Marathon, has helped seal Rockfours reputation as one of the most explosive live bands in the world (Fufkin.com). \r\n\r\nAfter its first appearance at CMJ in 2001, Rockfour was immediately signed to the renowned American guitar-pop label Rainbow Quartz and subsequently released  two more albums:  Another Beginning (released 2002) and its follow-up Nationwide (released 2004), the latter recorded in Detroit and produced by Jim Diamond (The White Stripes). \r\nMemories of the Never Happened marks Rockfours first release with Anova Music and Cooking Vinyl (US). The album included 11 energy-packed tracks mixed with vaulting jams and melodic harmonies, and was received high rotation in stations like KCRW (on \'Morning Becomes Eclectic\') and other college radio stations.\r\nIn 2009, the band joined Israeli singer Ninet Tayeb to produce her second album. The album was critically acclaimed and the band was praised for its production and playing skills throughout the album. \r\n2010 saw the release of the band\'s new album, consists of Hebrew songs, for the first time in 15 years. \r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/rockfourmusic','rockfour.com','','','8724191867','2471',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rockfour'),(365,0,59,59,'Odio Pars','','info@elgenioequivocado.com odioparis@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/odioparisband','http://odioparis.bandcamp.com','','','136102054159','2464',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','odio-paris'),(366,2,1,145,'The Vinyl Records','The Vinyl Records (aka TVR), is a four piece girl band based in New Delhi that came together in Feb 2010. The band was formed by Banu, Minam and Mithy who all hail from Arunachal Pradesh. In Jan of  2011 they were joined by Cheyyrian Bark (originally from GUWAHATI,ASSAM) as the lead vocalist and keytarist. TVR describe their sound as indie rock, new wave. Their influences include C.S.S. The B52s,The Donnas, Veruca Salt, The ramones ,The strokes,Arctic Monkeys, and The Runaways; fusing indie and post punk with a dash of glam rock kitsch with the keytar! ','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Vinyl-Records/162414153811500','','','','162414153811500','2459',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 13:28:33',171,'[\"email :- thevinylrecords4@yahoo.in\"]','[\"09717283810(delhi), 09206111219(AP), +91-9899346597 (delhi)\"]','the-vinyl-records'),(367,0,2,2,'Zedde','Zedde features 2Blue on vocals, Claver on guitars, Deepu on bass, and Trevor on drums. Our first single Mumbai won the \'Anthem of the Year title at AVIMA 2010. The video frequented all popular music channels and climbed to #1 on the Youtube India charts within 24 hours of upload. The Best Band award at ArtistAloud.com and the regional championship at Hard Rock Rising\'s BOTB followed. We can\'t be complaining. :)\r\n','Hangar Studios 9821090680','http://www.facebook.com/ZeddeLIVE','http://zeddelive.in/','','','26815634893','2458',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','zedde'),(368,0,1,1,'The Last PuFF','The Last Puff is an Indie band from New Delhi, India.\r\n\r\nThe Universe is an equanimity.\r\nIf a certain entity exists, then its counter also exists. \r\nThereupon, its all equitable at the end of the night.\r\n\r\nThe Last Puff was formed in 2009 by two friends Ankit and Kshitiz, after they met through a social networking website and started jamming at a friend\'s play school terrace room. Ankit met Kushagra through the latter\'s elder brother, his classmate back in school.\r\nAfter some random jam sessions in the winter of 2009, The Last Puff was born.\r\nOne of us is a college graduate and was working with a multinational IT company, another a college dropout, third a high school pass out. \r\nJob and education can be tagged as a prerequisite, though on a comprehensive note, these concepts are a bit too materialistic for a life of a rough span of 28,000 days, and in order to traverse the plush dimensions of music, one needs to enshrine himself to it.\r\n\r\nAll the band members are inspired individually by certain various genres, the one on the vocals and guitar is into  \r\nPsychedelic, Jazz, Goth, Grunge and other peculiar genres giving an unexpected raw touch to the music.\r\nThe bass guitarist is more into melodic metal, symphonies giving a subtle and intricate structure to the bands sound. \r\nThe bands drummer is into Thrash, Garage and Speed Metal giving a dynamic touch to the rhythm.\r\n\r\nPushing through the ambit of genres, the permutations and combinations result in some peculiar and stupefying music.\r\nIf one song is about something materialistic and on a serious note, then other might be filled with lush chimera.\r\n\r\nThe band has performed at some of the well known colleges and pubs/ cafes that includes :\r\n\r\nTLR Cafe, New Delhi\r\nCafe Morrison, New Delhi\r\nBlues, CP Delhi\r\nUrban Cafe, Gurgaon \r\nStriker, Gurgaon\r\nZygo, Gurgaon\r\nThe 567, New Delhi\r\nJukebox Cafe and Bar, New Delhi\r\nTryst Musicafe, Saket\r\nBahi, Gurgaon\r\nVibezz | The Lounge, Dehradun\r\nChicane, Noida\r\nBoogaloo Cafe, Delhi\r\nLady Shree Ram College, Delhi University\r\nShri Ram College of Commerce, Delhi University\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nHighlights:\r\n? Played live at the Rolling Stone Jack Daniels Annual Rock Awards in January, 2012.\r\n? Featured in an article in the UK newspaper, \'The Guardian\' dated 5th October, 2010 along with the band\'s live video featured in the newspaper\'s web archive.\r\n? Featured in the UK music magazine, \'Arts Grants Finder\' in October, 2010.\r\n? Played live at the VH1 supported International Music Festival alongside artists and bands from USA, France, Australia in November, 2011.\r\n? Song \'Draw The Line\' gets featured on Hit 95 FM - the only complete English radio channel in New Delhi.\r\n? Statement given by Ankit (vocalist of the band) featured along with the band\'s name on the front page in the daily newspaper HT City dated 4th October, 2011.\r\n? Headlined the Rock band competition the guest band at Race Course, Dehradun in October, 2011.\r\n? Judged the Rock band competition and performed as the headliner band in Academy of Business and Engineering Science, Delhi, India in November, 2010.\r\n? Opened for bands \'Parikrama\' and \'Advaita\' in Lady Shree Ram college, Delhi University.\r\n? Won the Rock event in Appejay College of Engineering, Gurgaon, India in March, 2011\r\n? Won the Rock Event in BBDIT Encore \'09, and ABES IT It Ain\'t Noise \'09, both held in November, 2009 in Delhi, India\r\n? Got the awards for best Vocalist and Guitarist at ABES IT.\r\n? Got 1st position in SRM university annual rock competition held in February, 2010 among 17 bands from all over India.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe band has been working full time on our own compositions, and have fully written and composed more than an album worth of tracks. \r\nHaving enough music in our heads to keep us busy till the end of time.\r\n\r\nLinks:\r\nWebsite                  http://www.thelastpuff.co.cc\r\nFacebook Page      http://www.facebook.com/thelastpuff\r\nYoutube Channel   http://www.youtube.com/lastpuffthe\r\nBand\'s music          http://www.soundcloud.com/the-last-puff\r\nVideo Demo            http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wohSdHAaf5A\r\nPress Link               http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/musicblog/2010/oct/05/scene-heard-indie-india\r\n ','thelastpuff@live.com','http://www.facebook.com/thelastpuff','http://www.thelastpuff.co.cc','http://www.soundcloud.com/the-last-puff','','111856652342','2450',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-last-puff'),(369,0,3,3,'Band Aid ( Orbitual )','Band Aid was formed in the summer of 2010 by 4 guys who wanted to make some good music and enjoy themselves, make people head bang, and see some circle pits \\m/.\r\n\r\nThe band members all have varied influences, from Soft Rock, and Classic Rock to Brutal and Heavy Metal. These varied influences bring a unique sound to the band. The band has started playing gigs around Bangalore and is slowly gaining popularity. With a set list usually consisting of original compositions, we\'re a band you wouldn\'t wanna miss! Band aid started playing small gigs like Saturday jam at central, and over the past couple of months the band took part in freedom jam, various college fests and have come out with good shows and results.\r\n\r\nBand Aid was also a part of \'Cemetery Gates\' Indias largest Metal Festival,where 23 top indian bands played.The event made news across the world.\r\n\r\nBand Aid has also opened for UK Based Metal band Cyanide Serenity on their Consuming India tour 2010 at Bangalore. ','bandaidofficial@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/bandaidofficial','http://twitter.com/bandaidofficial','','http://www.reverbnation.com/bandaidofficial','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','band-aid-orbitual'),(370,0,3,3,'Swarathma','Swarathma is a Bangalore-based Indian Folk-Rock band, that is known for its visually electric, high-energy live act. Their first album came out in 2009 which they supported with heavy touring over the last three years. They have recently brought out their second studio album titled Topiwalleh, that redefines their sound and takes them from indie-midfielders to bonafide headliners','Bobby +91 9820300454','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Swarathma/108146282540470','http://www.swarathma.com','','','108146282540470','2381',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','swarathma-1'),(371,0,3,3,'Hungry','\r\nWe are HUNGRY,looking for the DUNGREE\r\n\r\nOur Interests are :\r\nMusic. Period\r\n\r\nArtists We Also Like\r\nDave Matthews, Jojo Mayer, Victor Wooten,Stevie Wonder,Carter Beauford, Jimi Hendrix, Billy Sheehan, Rick Wakeman,Dennis Chambers','SONAL CHITTIAPPA(7411700446)','http://www.facebook.com/hungrytheband','http://www.youtube.com/hungryblore','','http://www.reverbnation.com/hungrybangalore','119771184737771','2375',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','hungry'),(372,0,117,117,'OVERHATE','Formed out of the ashes of a band that was called mermelada maker in november of the year 2003. Set out to create thrash metal, with touches of progressive rock, a style the band created first to record a demo tape with the songs \"forgiveness and \"tv show\" (later to become \"killing show\" in their \"god in a trench album). The band later spent 3 years getting into the tour circuit of venezuela, by reaching Valencia, Moron, Puerto Cabello, Margarita Island, Maturin, Puerto Ordaz,Ciudad Bolivar and Cali, a city in the neighbour country columbia. First album \"god in a trench\", is completed in 2007 with the eagerness for producing an album that denounces war, speaks about hate and despises human kind, in 14 blasting tracks of pure thrash metal, for a good end of the bands first chapter. Then in 2007, with \"God in a  Trench\" released and distributed through their home land Venezuela, the band opened for the black metal gods Rotting Christ, and played across the country again, and the band started recieving radio and magazine reviews in North, South America and Venezuela, Appeared in 6 different cd compilations with the track blind war. After this, the band obtained their first american management personificated in rising sounds management, which gave the band a good entrance to other markets, placing Overhate in the international map. After all this, the band found themselselvesa in 2009 writing new songs, and leading themselves into the studio in late 2009 to record a new album which is yet to be released. The album \"God in a Trench\" saw international distribution in late 2009, getting album release in India, Dubai and in Itunes for the rest of the world.','Alan Alvarez (India, Dubai, Middle East) Phone: +91 989 0374964','http://www.facebook.com/overhateband','www.overhate.com','','','107710309258083','2375',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','overhate'),(373,0,1,1,'FIVE8','Five8 was created in the summer of 2005 in New Delhi. Beginning as a college band at \r\nDelhi University, Five8 performed extensively within the Indian college circuit, playing \r\nmany college shows and competitions. With this impetus, the members of the band \r\nAdhir, Aveleon, Robin, Shiv and Steve decided to take the band forward professionally \r\nin 2008, consciously writing and performing their own music.  \r\n \r\nWith influences ranging from glam rock to soul, progressive music to pop, Five8s work \r\nresonates through a constantly evolving city life, running parallel and colliding with \r\nconcrete construction, scorching temperatures, traffic jams, insatiable appetites, and just \r\nsome plain wishful thinking.  \r\n \r\nFive8s music tells their story from within, and by stepping outside of the emerging \r\nIndian independent music milieu, using this apparent challenge to create Five8s unique \r\nsound. The band releases its first self-titled EP July 2010 featuring six original tracks, \r\noriginal band artwork and a range of merchandise. In the future, the band hopes to \r\ncontinue writing and performing, and to allow their music to lead them further. As a \r\npart of the dynamic Indian Indie, Five8 believes that this is the time in India to let \r\nyour music speak. Life gives you one shot, there are no retakes (Believe, Five8, \r\n2009).  ','Shiv Ahuja +91 9811375084 shivahuja at gmail dot com','http://www.facebook.com/five8india','http://www.five8.in','','','7332215993','2373',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','five8'),(374,0,103,103,'Motherjane','Like most Indian rock bands, Motherjane traces its origins to one particular day when a bunch of talented college going friends found their calling in rock.\r\n\r\nWhats peculiar about this start was that it was hastily put together by John Thomas (the college arts club secretary) to avert a potential disaster. Motherjane was formed to fill in for the Professional act which had suddenly opted out of the Rock show. The first stroke of luck for Motherjane had sounded!\r\n\r\nIn 1996, featuring the combined talents of John Thomas(Drums), Clyde Rozario (Bass), Mithun (Guitars) and Laji (Vocals), the band went on to make an explosive debut wowing their peers within a week of their formation.\r\n\r\nIn 1997, Motherjane released a 3 song EP that got lost amongst the wilderness of Kerala, where many a poterntaily great rock bands got lost in the 80s and 90s.\r\n\r\nMotherjane then went thru the agonizing process of losing the talents of 2 of its founding members who went in pursuit of their individual dreams. By 1999 the mercurial and talented Baiju took over duties as axeman &, Motherjane entered a partial state of limbo becoming a 3 member team with John & Clyde still holding on.\r\n\r\nFor over a year the band played metal songs (without a vocalist!) at The Ancient Mariner a floating restaurant in Kochi to an unsuspecting & astounded audience that walked into the quaint pier like structure built in the backwaters.\r\n\r\nIn 2000, then a young businessman by the name of Suraj Mani, chanced into The ancient mariner and egged on by his friend, jammed with the band. Almost coincidently at the same time a talented young guitarist called Rex also moved into this loosely bound group.\r\n\r\nWithin a week of juggling his time between work and music, Suraj was already trying to move on. Attempting to excuse himself with an observation on the lack of future that confronts cover bands, his proposed exit lines were, If we were making our own music, it would mean something. At least then 10 years down the line, we cant be just replaced by the next band of talented young musicians who would play these covers with more energy. Baiju looked up and said, lets make a song\r\n\r\nThat moment for any band heralds its real beginning. By 2001-02 the band had composed, performed and recorded 9 songs in an album that they called insane biography. During this period, the band was already coping with the logistical horrors of practice & recording, since Suraj had shifted base to Bangalore. Overcoming its difficulties, the band went on to perform all over the Indian sub continent gaining from strength to strength and winning numerous competitions and awards. Most notable amongst them in the first half of bands career was the award for best Indian rock album in the year 2002-03.\r\n\r\nMotherjane, (the bands guardian angel- named in homage to the bands belief that music is by far the best and purest drug in the world) was making her presence felt and her sons heard!\r\n\r\nThen Rex left in 2002. It was the day before the Great Indian Rock concert, where for the first time a band from the serene and lost state of Kerala had managed to break into. The band was lost again.\r\n\r\nFor 2 years the band went thru stand in guitarists for their rhythm section, all the while performing, learning and growing in stature. Amidst all the turmoil, Insae Biography was creating ripples in the rock circuit. The bands album became the first Indian rock album to be featured in international radio stations across 3 continents. The song Soul Corporations was bought for an international compilation album Geki Teki Metal released in Japan in 2004. Motherjanes live acts were getting rave reviews across the country. DNA networks rated the band as one of the top 3 live acts in the country. Always working for the inevitable success that they craved, Motherjane welcomed Deepu in late 2004. Once again the vibe was back and within 6 months the band was composing new material.\r\n\r\nThe band will be bringing out their new album titled Maktub in 2007 and has further developed their sound into something that is uniquely Motherjane and attracts a cult following amongst the thinking rocker. The songs from the latest recordings got the boys laurels with Baiju winning the award for the guitarist of the year 2007 at the JD Tennesse Annual Rock awards and Suraj being nominated for the vocalist of the year. What most bands from the so-called rock hubs of India could not achieve in years in the Indian rock circuit, Motherjane - a band hailing from the remotest islands of Kerala did so in no time with their perseverence, thereby, becoming an inspiration for most rock bands that have gained fame over the last few years.\r\n\r\nMotherjanes fascinating musical style flows with the melody of rural India, seethes with the raw aggression of rock and is inlaid with lyrics of exquisite insight .The band is going to re-record insane biography along with Maktub as a special tribute to its fans.\r\n\r\nIf there is one thing that Motherjane has lived by, it is the gut feeling that success is more about what one overcomes than just achievements.\r\n\r\nThis band has overcome much more than the milestones it is known for and is still growing stronger and stronger on its journey to reach its world wide audience.\r\n\r\nIt seems apt here to leave with the lyrics of walk on from the album Insane Biography-\r\n\r\nIm the immortal, baptized in fire\r\nUnable to die unless I desire\r\nIm the light piercing the darkest dawn\r\nIm the human spirit, walking on.\r\n\r\nWelcome to the band .\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Motherjane/10612624134','http://www.motherjane.net','','','10612624134','2351',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','motherjane-1'),(375,0,64,64,'Thriloka','Resonances of Raskhas & Nagas \r\n\r\nHumanitys most precious gift is the ability to appreciate art  The most natural tendency of the human psyche To appreciate art is to recreate our five senses: Unlike smell, taste & touch Sight & Sound evolved in tandem, & are now primary forms of communication.\r\n\r\nEven before birth, we learn to decipher sounds in the womb Rhythms fused with our own heartbeats, engulfed soon by the sounds, movements & changes of the world: Appearance & Disappearance, Silence & its absence, Our entire being soon embraced & rocked by these Rhythms.\r\n\r\nIs not just another band. Thriloka is an Overflowing of the Diverse Sublime Emotions & Yearnings of Youth Now come together  Yes, this is the best definition for Bisura!\r\nDedicated to making music all through our lives We are of one heart! Our genuine wish is to rhythmicize the inner heart-felt desires we all feel in our lives!\r\nThis is not about politics, conflict, race or tribe, east or west: When needed there is calm, when needed there is storm.\r\nThriloka is an island on which you might build anything reflecting the natural world, evoking the best of world music. Music produced of a blend of themes to maximize listening pleasure.\r\nOur main aim is an authentic experience of what the heart hears! ','','http://www.facebook.com/thriloka','http://www.thriloka.com','','','9983743367','2333',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','thriloka'),(376,0,2,2,'Sahil Joshi Productions (Official)','Music Speaks Louder Than Any Description. http://soundcloud.com/sahiljoshi','Nishant Dharamshi: +91 9920909910','http://www.facebook.com/sahiljoshiofficial','http://sahiljoshi.com','','','126969014006773','2324',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sahil-joshi-productions-official'),(377,5,2,2,'Bay Beat Collective (BBC)','The Mumbai-based BBC (Bay Beat Collective) formed in response to the abundance of standard-issue electronica so often churned out in clubs and bars across the country. Influenced by artists across the board like Rockwell, Nymfo, Klute, Chase and Status, Opiuo, Koan Sound, Zeds Dead, Jazzsteppa & more, BBC explores new aural territory, dabbling in styles ranging from breaks to drum n bass, and glitch hop to dubstep, with a partiality to \"phat\" basslines and high voltage grooves that are infectious, delicious & supremely funky.\r\n\r\nBBC have toured with some of the biggest international names in the electronic and bass music circuit including artists like The Prodigy, LTJ Bukem, Klute, Nymfo, Concord Dawn, DJ Marky, Jazzsteppa, Asian Dub Foundation, TC1, Bother Culture, Dub FX & Pendulum. The collective has played extensively in the festival circuit including Three years at the Sunburn Festival in Goa, Two years at the Bacardi NH7 Weekender and Once at Invasion Festival. In addition to this, BBCs successful tour of Europe in August 2010 through Germany and the UK have put them on the world map. They are also scheduled to play at Outlook Festival in Croatia to be held in August 2012. Outlook Festival is Europes largest bass music and sound system culture festival. They will be the first ever Indian artist to take on the stage at this festival.\r\n\r\nBBC have injected fun into a scene, which was mutating into an increasingly austere and po-faced arena. Their DJ sets continually re-affirm the potency of dancing the night away in a sweaty club, surrounded by completely like-minded strangers.\r\n\r\nA prime time BBC show is a combination of high end and accessible musical generators like time coded vinyls, ableton synced laptops, midi controllers, projectors and even I-Phones. The BBC are changing trends and inspiring newer players in India with regularly packed alternative beat nights all over the country and are truly one of the emerging collectives of a much required alternative, intellectual order. Speaking the language of bass and translating every other musical vocabulary into a bass line, BBC is a non-stop party. \r\n\r\nHighlights >>\r\n\r\n	Outlook Festival 2012, Croatia \r\n	Invasion Festival 2011 with The Prodigy & Pendulum\r\n	Sunburn Festival 2009, 2010, 2011\r\n	Bacardi NH7 Weekender 2010, 2011\r\n	Best Indian Act  Time Out Mumbai 2009\r\n	Voted # 1 Drum N Bass / Dubstep DJ by MyFavDJ.in for 2009  2010\r\n\r\nWhat the press has to say >>\r\n\r\nWhen youre seeking killer beats and bass-driven foot-stomping events, you know youre not going to stray too far from Bay Beat Collective Bombay Times\r\n\r\nBBC developed basslines and percussive beats that could stand alone amidst the beautiful chaos and decide the future direction of all sound, much like a policeman at a traffic signal. Big M Magazine\r\n\r\nThey\'ve been able to excite, entice & energize crowd after crowd, night after night for about 3 years now Platfor