ressive house, desi and bhangra to create a new sound.He began playing in local parties in his hometown. He soon blew up in surat and began playing in all over gujarat. since he has enjoyed immense success, blowing up dancefloors. He is also a prolific and respected producer, having released Many single bootleg remix and one album called Dj Rahul Vaidya\'s \"Z+\" the album since he got up this morning.\n\n Contact Details:\n Facebook:\n http://www.facebook.com/djrahulvaidya \n \nFacebook Fan Page:\nhttp://www.facebook.com/DJRAHULVAIDYAOFFICIALPAGE \n\n twitter:\n http://twitter.com/DJRAHULVAIDYA \n\n Reverbnation:\n http://www.reverbnation.com/djrahulvaidya \n\n Gmail:\n djrahulvaidya@gmail.com \n\n\n BB Pin : 23983592','','http://www.facebook.com/DJRAHULVAIDYAOFFICIALPAGE','','','','219103911464301','2268',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-rahul-vaidya'),(383,0,1,1,'Bare Faced Liar','This is a band with a truly unique sound, experimenting with genres ranging from Heavy Metal to Blues to Classic Rock and drawing inspiration from all of them to create their individual sound. Their passion for song-writing and creating catchy music coupled with their proficient guitar-playing, makes BFL one of the top bands in India today. \r\n\r\n','bflbookings@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/barefacedliar','http://www.barefacedliar.com','http://soundcloud.com/barefaced','','131769313526015','2266',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-17 21:50:58',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','bare-faced-liar'),(384,0,81,81,'Dark Carnage','As individuals, we have all, been let down; tormented by how our Governments choose to treat us. Innocent lives wasted, hard-earned property destroyed, lives sold, souls molested. \r\nIs this really the life that you want to lead? Do you really want to see your mothers and daughters being raped? \r\nIs this so called civilization- the true progress of the human society?\r\n\r\nWe can be the change.\r\n\r\nAll of us have become mere puppets and this we should choose to defy.\r\n\r\nForget what your textbooks tell you.\r\n\r\nDont be at ease thinking that you will see a better tomorrow, unless you can make one for yourself.\r\n\r\nDefy the system, for the system is nothing but a set of rules that bind YOU and no-one else. Defy your leaders, because your leaders forget who you are once they are elected. Defy the government, for the government is nothing but a bunch of cannibals happily feasting on your miserable lives.\r\n\r\nCivilization is a failure- lets get together and decide what we want to do next.','darkcarnageofficial@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/darkcarnageofficial/','','http://soundcloud.com/darkcarnageofficial','','0','2260',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dark-carnage'),(385,0,3,3,'PARVAAZ','Parvaaz is a Bangalore-based rock band.It comprises of Khalid Ahmed(vocals,guitars,song writer),Kashif Iqbal(lead guitar,vocals,various instruments,lyrics) ,Fidel Dsouza(bass) and Sachin Banandur(drums & percussion).\r\nThe band was formed in early 2010 by Kashif,Khalid and Neil.After a different initial lineup the band finally went four piece when Sachin Banandur joined in November 2010.\r\nThe band came into prominence after playing at The Great Indian October Fest and then The Fireflies Festival Of Music held in Febuary 2011 at Bangalore.\r\nThe band is currently working on their debut E.P.The band mostly writes in Urdu and Kashmiri.','parvaazmusic@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/parvaazmusic','http://parvaaz.net/','','','0','2257',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','parvaaz'),(386,0,40,40,'RAM','RAM was created back in \'99 by Harry Granroth, who wanted to form a real heavy metal band; he was sick of the misinterpretation of metal that ruled the scene back then and had a pile of material that he wanted to bring to life. He soon found Daniel Johansson, a young but experienced and very talented guitar player who welded a traditional metal guitar style. The two started working on some of Harry\'s earlier material and began to write new songs. After a long and tiresome search, Harry then found Oscar Carlquist; a powerful heavy metal vocalist with a mutual hatred for the current metal scene. Oscar quickly became involved in the song writing process and quickly crafted interesting lyrics to accompany the music. The backbone of RAM was formed. Oscar brought in drummer Morgan Pettersson, one of the few drummers left who still played the 70/80\'s hard and heavy drumming style. They then recruited the legendary Leif Larsson, an icon in Gothenburg metal as he had previously been a member of \"Frozen Eyes\".\r\n\r\nThe five members started to rehearse and write new songs and in 2003 they released their first E.P., Sudden Impact, through partly their own label \"Black Path Metal Recordings\". The EP created a sudden impact on the underground metal scene, the first 1000 copies were sold out in a few months. RAM hit the road and played a number of festivals in Europe and went on tour as support for Sebastian Bach. The band was also recognised by Germany\'s Rock Hard magazine as one of the best newcomers of 2004.\r\n\r\nRAM kept on playing live throughout most of \'05 and started working on their full-length debut album Forced Entry, which was released in late 2005. Forced Entry brought the entire old school heavy metal community to its knees. The album is a pure sonic attack of real and innovative heavy metal. Great reviews followed and the band grew even bigger. In December \'05, RAM hit the road with Dark Tranquillity and in Jan \'06 they performed at several Scandinavian shows with Gamma Ray.\r\n\r\nPlaying live is what RAM does best and in 2006-2007, the band delivered a devastating metal crusade over Europe. Reaching places such as Greece for the first time and Spain for the second time, the Teutonic hordes went wild. In the summer of 2007, bass player Leif Larsson was asked to leave the band due to personal differences and Tyrant of the Black Metal ultra cult act Nifelheim answered the call and joined RAM as a session bassplayer.\r\n\r\nIn 2008, the band returned to the studio with producer Johan Reivn to record the album Lightbringer. This time they really took the time to explore the true heavy metal sound. The recording of the album took 10 months of nothing but strife for pure heavy metal perfection.\r\n\r\nIn 2009, RAM signed a deal with AFM records and released Lightbringer, which received very good reviews. It landed a spot as one of the best albums of 2009 in Sweden Rock magazine. The band also headed out on headline European tour to promote the album. Tobbe Peterson joined the band and through his amazing bass skills made this the strongest RAM lineup ever.\r\n\r\nIn 2010, RAM went back into the studio to record their yet unreleased third album called Death. This time they worked with producers Per Stlberg and Olle Bjrk to create their best album to date by far. Live shows as support for Swedish extreme black metal band Watain followed as well as destroying some festivals. Now in 2011, the band has signed a Worldwide deal with the iconic metal label Metal Blade and the world trembles in fear before the release of the metal behemoth that is Death. RAM are back! Necks will be broken!','live@ram-metal.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/RAM/128575340510564','http://www.ram-metal.com/','','','128575340510564','2237',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ram'),(387,0,1,1,'Dj Sonee','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Dj-Sonee/111134815628562','','','','111134815628562','2233',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-sonee'),(388,0,31,31,'Lost Oblivion','Lost oblivion had launched their Debut album/EP/Demo/split \"THE LAST VERSE OF MADNESS\" (with ktmROCKS Records) whatever you call it, and they have started working on their second album that will be titled \"REMAINS OF THE SIN\"(we guess). Cause their music will be going in a little different direction in the next album...it will have a lot more modern and New age/Mathcore/a little progressive influence this time(but still keeping some of the old oblivion vibe) and the sound will be much better. So u can expect a lot more this time. This album will probably have around 10 tracks..excluding the outro and intro stuff ....so all i can say is support us ...and this is just the beginning....looking forward for ur support, comments, deaththreats and everything else..... keep Metal alive....','','http://www.facebook.com/LostOblivion','http://www.myspace.com/undergroundlostob...','','','90995281795','2229',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','lost-oblivion'),(389,0,31,31,'Horny Monks','soone soon nasoone hamro paadh soong.......................','9803506615','http://www.facebook.com/hornymonks','','','','168562746510879','2227',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','horny-monks'),(390,2,1,1,'Silent Existence','Formed in the latter half of year 2008, Silent Existence has come a long way in terms of song writing and performances. Withstanding the line-up changes in the first few months and trying to play louder and faster every time they got onto a stage, the band today commands a considerable fan following and is known in the New Delhi circuit for their radically tasteful fusion of nu-metal and thrash and the energy they bring with their music. Their lyrical content inspired mostly by religious texts and writings, the band tries to focus on issues that are close to their hearts. Silent Existence has played gigs all over Delhi over the last three years since their inception and have made fans all over Delhi. One of the band\'s songs titled \"Haunting\" was aired on the Indonesian Radio Broadcast Metal Channel called \'World Metal Podcast last year November, Silent Existence was chosen by the producers of the show as the representation for the whole of India. 