oise Cottage, Caf Morrison, Caf Chinese and Thai, Mocha Bar, Rock in Rio(Chandigarh), Orca Lounge(Jaipur), Not Just Jazz By the Bay(Mumbai), 10 Downing (Hyderabad), 1 Lounge (Pune). October was declared Runners up at IIT Kanpur 2008 Synchronicity, 3rd place at BITS Pilani 2009 and has taken part in several other competitions such as IIT Mumbai Mood Indigo as well as played in college festivals at Miranda House, JMC and DCAC. The band is anticipating the release of its debut album in August 2010, which the band will be actively touring for in the 2010 gig season.','Anoop - 9818767662, Arnav - 9818956897','http://www.facebook.com/October.the.band','http://octobertheband.bandcamp.com','','http://www.reverbnation.com/octoberdelhi','0','2147',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','october'),(405,0,89,3,'The Family Cheese','Three musicians from various parts of India and the world meet at music school and start making music together; they love it, people seem to love it too. So they head out into the world to spread their music to anyone and everyone they can. So the story goes..........\r\n','Shreya Naik, Yohan Marshall, Apurv Isaac, Homi Rustumji','http://www.facebook.com/thefamilycheese','http://www.soundcloud.com/thefamilycheese','http://www.soundcloud.com/thefamilycheese','http://www.reverbnation.com/thefamilycheese','220631707991723','2141',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-family-cheese'),(406,0,3,3,'Myndsnare','MyndSnare first started out when KP released his solo effort MindSnare  1, a 4-track demo, which was sold in India and made its way to Malaysian radio and Singapore, among other places. The evolution game was played, and after various mutations, MyndSnare attained equilibrium in its current line-up. With the recording of a three-song demo  A Preliminary Quest in 2004, the band finally put their sounds to disc, and received excellent response from fans and\r\ncritics alike. MyndSnare\'s debut album, Conditioned: Human was released under the Demonstealer Records banner on 19th September 2008 and was launched with gigs in Mumbai,\r\nDelhi and Bangalore, to overwhelming response.\r\n\r\nSo, basically, if you like snapping your spine on an off-beat, enjoy running across rock-show venues to randomly fall upon another like you, find yourself growling without reason in broad daylight long after the full moon waxed away - or just enjoy woodenly staring at a bank of speakers while a mercurial flow of metallic noises winds around your mind... you\'re at the right place. We understand you. We may even like you. Be like you, even.\r\nSo, the Mynds are Snared as of now, and will keep the metal\r\nfaith alive. As they say, the show must go on.\r\n\r\nFor more details of the early MyndSnare history, visit the\r\nofficial site.\r\n\r\nUS Booking agents and Promoters can also contact the band directly at:\r\nemail: kpkrishnamoorthy@hotmail.com\r\nphone: +1-562-716-7449','Ashin Sharma (ashwin@greyandsaurian.com)','http://www.facebook.com/myndsnare','http://www.myndsnare.com','http://www.myspace.com/myndsnare','','362948752650','2127',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','myndsnare'),(407,0,88,88,'DANIEL HAAKSMAN','RELEASES\r\n\r\nMore Rambazamba (Man Recordings 2012)\r\nRambazamba Album (Man Recordings 2011)\r\nRap Da Silva EP (Man Recordings 2011)\r\nHands Up Remix EP (Man Recordings 2010)\r\nHands Up EP (Man Recordings 2010)\r\nGostoso Remix EP (Man Recordings 2009)\r\nGostoso EP (Man Recordings 2009)\r\nRio Baile Funk Breaks Album w/ DJ Beware + DJ Sandrinho (Man Recordings 2008)\r\nWhos Afraid Of Remix? EP (Man Recordings 2008)\r\nWhos Afraid Of Rio? EP (Man Recordings 2008)\r\n\r\nREMIXES\r\n\r\nLord Nelson \"Shango\" (Soundway 2012) w/DJ Beware\r\nKry Wolf \"Black & Blue\" (Sounds Of Sumo 2012)\r\nBig Dope P & Puto Prata \"Beat Dat Bitch\" (Moveltraxxx 2012)\r\nMakina Del Karibe \"Maki Man\" (Chusma Records 2012)\r\nJoe Fleisch feat. Jewish Mon