orsaken-india'),(422,0,31,31,'Jugaa','Sangharsha/Jugaa - The Sickness That Never Sleeps (2011)\r\n\r\nhttp://www.mediafire.com/?6u666agbe5kow9q\r\n\r\nHamal Hardcore [EP] (2010)\r\n\r\nhttp://www.mediafire.com/?tmcwoddmz52\r\n\r\nFuck The Scene [EP] (2008) \r\n\r\nhttp://www.mediafire.com/?ewncdzgnjy0\r\n\r\nJugaa/Shannon Scam split (2007) \r\n\r\nhttp://www.mediafire.com/?zywyjeymz1r','','http://www.facebook.com/jugaahc','http://jugaa.bandcamp.com','','','51344200867','2018',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','jugaa'),(423,0,64,64,'Wagon Park','Founded by Buddhima De mel and Mohamed Firash in the summer of 2007 Wagon Park have marched on from an unforgettable debut performance, consisting only the two founding members (at American National College) to unquestionably Sri Lankass only and most Potent Hard Rock outfit. \r\n\r\n\r\nThe journey was never going to be one for the faint hearted, and it was this very fact that founding member Buddhima De Mel used as inspiration to stand up, and single handedly push the envelope of Original Sri Lankan Hard Rock to heights that were never before seen.\r\n\r\nFrom the dawn period of the band, Wagon Park have continuously strived to create music that not only encapsulates its audience with awe and splendor but also leave a significant imprint on the audiences psyche with compositions that are uniquely different and uncompromised when voicing the bands ideals and beliefs.\r\n\r\nIt was the need for such captivating musical compositions that created the openings for the following brigade of four members that would later together be known as The Wagon Park we know today! \r\n\r\nThe entry of Madda & Mahesh both of whom were blessed with unparalleled talent and exuberance brought a new and distinct sound to Wagon Park as the duo took on the duties of Rhythm Guitar and Drums respectively! Yet still Buddhima felt the apparent need for a lead guitarist and it was this very need that inspired a new head hunt! \r\nThe Man they were looking for came in the form of Milo, Guitarist extraordinaire/ songwriter, it goes without saying that it was indeed his addition that propelled Wagon Park into what they stand for today! \r\nUndying Passion, sincere dedication and pure home bred rock and roll!!!\r\n\r\nSumedha Nuwan then stepped in as Band Manager and it was his inclusion that brought the band a great deal of professionalism which was certainly a prerequisite for any band that was pretty serious about their Music! Wagon Park was and so the addition was more than welcomed! \r\n\r\nWith the band now Complete and all raring to go, along came TNL Onstage a significant event in the sri lankan music calendar ,Onstage provided young artists and bands with the opportunity to deliver their music to a wider audience and go places! Or so IT claimed!\r\nTaking part in a competition of such magnitude was no easy task as the band found out for themselves. \r\nCountless rehearsals, interviews and the various other nitty gritties   that go into taking part in a Competition and being in the spotlight had to be seen to! \r\nAnd finally when the time had come to perform, Wagon Park delivered, and delivered in every sense of the word!\r\n\r\nFrom never before seen showmanship, to brilliantly executed compositions Wagon Park stunned audiences with a truly intense live performance of both originals and covers! The band entered the Finals of TNL Onstage as expected and once again provided a packed house of nearly 3,000 people with a truly spellbinding performance of Pink Floyds Classic Comfortably Numb. Unfortunately the band did not emerge winners but it was this very fact that served as the driving force to achieve what they termed at that time Bigger Things in music!\r\n\r\nSadly soon after the Finals Lead Guitarist Milo had to leave for a year due to prior commitments and it was his departure that created the opening for keyboardist Nuwan Tharanga to join the band! He soon blended in well and was unanimously selected as a permanent member of the band!\r\n\r\nAs the band continued on its quest to taking Original Sri Lankan Hard Rock to a wider audience Video Image Sri Lankas premier Production House approached the band after identifying the bands prowess as musicians! And it is with this collaboration that Wagon Park will release their Debut album in 2012 appropriately titled Stoned!\r\n\r\nWhile the final rites are being performed for the album launch, Video Image and Wagon Park have taken another Giant step in revolutionizing the Sri Lankan entertainment industry with a strikingly different video concept for Wagon Parks Hit Single Flat by the use silhouettes and never before seen Light and shadow effects! \r\n\r\nWagon Park has also independently released a Patriotic Sinhala Song titled Jayaganwan for which the band has received rave reviews for the songs lyrical content and seemingly picturesque video!  \r\n\r\nWagon Park has also independently Released a Live performance CD titled NOW IS HERE which contains band originals, plus covers from renowned artists such as Johny Cash, The Beatles, Bob Dylan and Bob Marley!  \r\n\r\nWhile the world awaits the official album release of STONED the band continues to innovate, motivate and tirelessly tear down the boundaries of a false prejudice that Asian Bands are no more than a farce! \r\n\r\nIt would be more than fitting to end this note with the very words of Milo Music is a way of revealing one\'s inner reflections and we find our counterpoint in the music of that era as it truly describes who we are and what we truly believe in.\r\n \r\n','Sumedha: +94777752070 / Milo - 0777666305','http://www.facebook.com/WagonPark','http://www.wagonpark.com','','','348456844742','1995',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','wagon-park'),(424,0,1,1,'TECHNODROME FESTIVAL','TechnoDrome is an electronic music & urban arts festival started by BLOT! & Qilla records in 2009.\r\n\r\nWith electronic music as the backbone of the series, the programming for each festival episode pulls in forerunners from the global music and arts scene, and pitches them with leading Indian artists and performers.\r\n\r\nTechnoDrome has hosted acclaimed electronic musicians including SQL (Netherlands), D.Sens (France), Child (Australia), Jitter, BLOT, Nucleya and Kohra (India) and widely regarded visual artists Evgeny Kiselev (Russia) & 4youreye (Austria) in its past editions.\r\n\r\nThe 2012 edition is poised to be the biggest episode yet, with Oliver Huntemann (Ideal Audio)(DE) & Light Surgeons (UK) headlining the festival alongside the leaders of electronica within the domestic circuit. Technodrome will also feature workshops on the Reactable, Ableton Live, VDMX and interpretation of music via video and graphic imagery.\r\n\r\nOliver Huntemann will transport his acclaimed Reactable Live Tour to India, when he will utilize the uniquely tactile shifting cubes of the Reactable Live hardware/software to bring his music to life, all the while encased in a bespoke cage and lighting rig. \r\n\r\nFEB 2-5, 2012 Delhi, Mumbai and Bangalore.\r\n\r\nOLIVER HUNTEMANN \r\nwww.huntemann.tv\r\n\r\nTHE LIGHT SURGEONS\r\nwww.lightsurgeons.com \r\n\r\nBLOT!\r\nwww.facebook.com/blottin\r\n\r\nARJUN VAGALE \r\nhttp://www.facebook.com/ArjunVagaleOfficial\r\n\r\nKOHRA\r\nwww.kohra.in\r\n\r\nJITTER\r\nhttp://www.facebook.com/groups/12698528147/\r\n\r\nVINAYAKA\r\nhttp://www.facebook.com/Vinayaka24\r\n\r\nTechnodrome 2012 is brought together in association with The British Council, The Goethe Institute, Pro Helvecia, TimeOut, Quicksand, Codesign, BLOT!, Qilla Records, thewildcity.com, and is a partner festival of UNBOX 2012.  \r\n\r\n','gaurav@blot.in','http://www.facebook.com/technodromefestival','http://www.facebook.com/technodromefestival','','','326275442213','1992',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','technodrome-festival'),(425,0,64,64,'Ablaze','Ablaze is a young, Progressive thrash metal band formed early 2010 in colombo, Sri Lanka..\r\n\r\nthis band was formed because of an idea three kids had who were apparently deeply in to the unique genre heavy metal. early 2010 they managed to find two more members into the ablaze family who had the same taste of music. and they all had the same favorites that was thrash metal. so they decided to play thrash with influences dragged off towards progressive/technical side and experimental side.\r\n\r\nAfter even going through school, home, society issues they still managed to go on because of the love they had for heavy metal and they know \"you can\'t stop rock n\' roll\" -AC/DC-   \r\n\r\nAfter their first few successful gigs and the releasing of their debut (demo)single \"Roots To Nowhere\" they made their mark as of one of the top thrash bands in the local scene and managed to drag a large number of fans quicker than any band achieved so far in the local scene.\r\n \r\nlyrics were basically born through the political , religious exploitation ,mass media corruption.. ,the darker side of life, craving of men..and Dehumanization..\r\n\r\n','Shamika Makalanda','http://www.facebook.com/Ablazesl','http://www.myspace.com/ablazesl','','http://www.reverbnation.com/ablazesl','316502800905','1983',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ablaze'),(426,0,0,0,'BAI - Bands Association of India','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/BAI-Bands-Association-of-India/183188318375648','','','','183188318375648','1970',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','bai-bands-association-of-india'),(427,0,103,103,'Black Letters','A four piece band known for its infectious energy and significantly variant song writing, Black Letters is often compared to a high speed train.  With a wide variety of shows ranging from pro-shows to music festivals and pubs to hotels  as well as lots of high profile competitions in the bag, theyve proven over and again that they can captivate an