e mantle of bassist and Alles was incorporated into the ranks of Dhishti in December 2010 for a landmark tour within the Black Metal history of two countries: Dhishti toured Mumbai, India and performed at the first ever  Black Metal Fest in India; The Black Metal Kreig, 2010. Alles continued on as the band\'s drummer with his dark style which sets the atmosphere for Dhishti\'s deviant progression of pounding viscous war beats.\r\n\r\n\r\nUpon returning to the Motherland after their successful tour, Hewakoparage was was recruited to bring a unique element of  lead guitar solos to the music of Dhishti.In early 2011 Kirindage was replaced by Lord Bhahirawa of Wawul Kale. With the truly Sri Lankan roots, Dhishti\'s music can be identified as Depressive Atmospheric Black Metal of an impressively unparalleled nature. \r\n\r\nDhishti was formed to encompass the pure hatred felt over thousands of years towards the brutal invaders who ravaged the peaceful land of Sri Lanka. We base our music in the ominous and monotonous sounds of Black Metal, splicing it together with generations of acutely honed ancient Sri Lankan music to produce a truly unique sound for which the band is known. Screeching, ululating vocals pouring forth blasphemous lyrics filled with pure rage, hatred and pain accompanied by sighing guitars and powerful bass being supplemented by the steady drone of consistent drums with uniquely identifiable rolls and breaks would describe the characteristics seen up to now in music which Dhishti. This will of course be varied and changed over time as we do not stick to a single form of expressing the pain and suffering of the people of Sri Lanka over the cruel invaders and rulers over the years to the present.\r\n\r\nWe Do not support suicidal, anti-life, pessimistic, Nazism ideas or killing yourself trends. We do not believe in Suicide being the answer to the despicable behavior of humanity. Dhishti is all about our Emotions and the will to fight back and regain what is truly ours.','Jayakody: 0094775488860','http://www.facebook.com/dhishti','','','','143433192366781','1680',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dhishti'),(472,0,101,101,'Grungy Morphins \"The Gorkha Metal Warriors\"','One of the Pioneers of Extreme Metal Music in India, Grungy Morphins hails from the very beautiful and peaceful Queen of The Hills that is Darjeeling. But the music the Band plays is everything but peaceful.  \r\n\r\nAlthough the band existed in the hills ever since the year 2000 they only faced the stage for a public performance in the year 2003 and made their presence felt loud and Strong by their extreme stage act and the tightness of the band.\r\n \r\nIts been about a decade now that the Grungy Morphins has been making the hills proud by not only winning major Rock Contests in and around Darjeeling but also by winning major Rock Contests and playing gigs all across the country and touring the whole nation headlining Gigs. \r\n\r\nIn the year 2009 the band not only made the hills proud but made the whole country proud by making their appearance and being the First ever Indian Band to be featured in an International Extreme Metal Compilation Album Shrouded In Silent Omens III by T.U.G. Records from Canada www.theundergrowth.com featuring 5 bands from Canada,2 from the U.S.A.,and a band each from England,Poland,Australia and Israel. Grungy Morphins has now brought Darjeeling in the World Map of Extreme Metal Music where no-one even knew that there was or is metal in this part of the world also. Theyve told the whole world Loud and proud that Darjeeling is not just Tea, Tourism, Toy Train and Kanchendjunga but Metal Heads also.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Band is Currently Working on a 3 Way Split Album to be Released Later in 2011 with GRUNGY MORPHINS \"The Gorkha Metal Warriors\" (Darjeeling,India), SANGRE (California, U.S.A.) & NECROCEST (Wales, U.K.)\r\n\r\n\r\nWell going on with the milestones of the band here are just a few Details of the band::\r\nConcerts/Contests/Headlining Acts ::\r\n1} Opened for Nervo Chaos {Brazil} @Metal Mayhem III,2011,Guwahati Leg,\r\n2} Opened for Nervo Chaos {Brazil} @Metal mayhem III,2011,Kolkata Leg,\r\n3} Headlined Oktoberfest 2011 Open Air Show @Kathmandu, Nepal,\r\n4} Decibelz 2005 {Xavier Institute of Management Bhubaneshwar} , Orissa\r\n5} Dhanaulti Rocks music fest for in aid of Kashmiri Earthquake Relief Fund,\r\n6} Rock Idols 2005 Kolkata,\r\n7} All India Grand Finale of the Rock Idols 2005 in Goa.\r\n8} Decibels, Saarang , IIT Madras 2006\r\n9} Rockers 2006? {Indian School Of Mines , Dhanbad} Jharkhand,\r\n10} Winter fest 2004 Kalimpong,\r\n11} Mangan Music fest Sikkim 2008 in Mangan\r\n12} Rock Aid 2004 Darjeeling,\r\n13} A New Beginning 2005 Darjeeling,\r\n14} Rock Yatra 2005 Darjeeling,\r\n14} Brutal Fest 2011 in Pokhara, Nepal and many many more,\r\n        \r\nNational / Internatinal Compilation Albums ::\r\n\r\nThe band has also given songs in 2 National Compilation Albums ::                                                                                                              \r\n1} Dark-Ula  in Absolute Indian Metal out from Mumbai by EMP Records  \r\n \r\n2} Dark-Ula I in First Mutiny  The Dogmas Of Indian Rock out from Bangalore by Dogmatone Records\r\n\r\n3} Gorkha Rocks Vol. 4 & 5\r\n\r\nRecently the band also gave their new song to INternational Compilation albums ::\r\n\r\n1} Darkness Without Pain in an INternational Compilation Album Shrouded In Silent Omens III from Canada with 5 bands from Canada,2 from USA, and a Band Each from Isreal,Australia,Poland and England\r\n\r\n 2} Wolf HOund Metal Radio Compilation Album Winners from Public Votings \r\n\r\n 3} Occult Science of MEtal a compilation of Extreme Metal featuring bands from all over the world by Brutal Pokhara\r\n\r\nMedia/Press/Magazine ::\r\n\r\n1} Featured in VH1s Exclusive coverage of ROCK IDOLS TOUR OF 2005\r\n\r\n2} Featured in Zsentient MetalCast Radio {U.S.A.} In exclusive shows Beyond Brutality Edition & New Age Of Brutal Metal :: Songs :: i) Darkness Without Pain & I.T.N.O.T.G\r\n\r\n3} Featured in MetalExpress Radio {Canada} :: Songs :: i) I.T.N.O.T.G. , ii) Dark-Ula & iii) The Curse Of The Ravens In The land Of The Black Jesus Where Wolves Howl In Harmony.\r\n\r\n4} Featured in Rock N Rollica F.M. {U.S.A.} :: Songs :: i) I.T.N.O.T.G. , ii) Darkness Without Pain , iii) The Curse Of The Ravens In The land Of The Black Jesus Where Wolves Howl In Harmony , & iv) Dark-Ula.\r\n\r\n5} Featured In Headbangers F.M. {U.K.} :: Songs :: i) I.T.N.O.T.G. , ii) Darkness Without Pain , iii) The Curse Of The Ravens In The land Of The Black Jesus Where Wolves Howl In Harmony , & iv) Dark-Ula.\r\n\r\n6} Exclusive Interview With Radio Misty Sikkim 95 F.M.\r\n\r\n7} Exclusive Interview With Spin F.M. WorldSpace F.M.\r\n\r\n8} Exclusive Interview With Himali Channel A local T.V. Channel Of Darjeeling,\r\n\r\n9} Darjeeling Times Magazine and Online :: \r\nhttp://www.darjeelingtimes.com/news/Entertainment/Grungy-Morphins--The-Gorkha-Metal-Warriors.html\r\n\r\n10} Himalayan Beacon :: \r\nhttp://beacononline.wordpress.com/2010/01/13/vote-for-grungy-morphine-to-represent-india-at-metal-fest-in-austria/\r\n\r\n11} The Telegraph :: http://www.telegraphindia.com/1090525/jsp/siliguri/story_11016097.jsp\r\n\r\n12} Times Of India :: Calcutta Times \r\n\r\n13} Himalya Darpan :: Local Newspaper Of Darjeeling\r\n\r\n14} Deccan Chronicle :: Newspaper From Bangalore\r\n\r\n15} Split Magazine :: Rock Magazine From Bangalore\r\n\r\n16} Metakixs Zombs reviews on Metakix .com on Grungy Morphins :: Quote Song 09: Grungy Morphins:   Drak-ula Again, yet another band that I was not aware existed. I was pleasantly surprised to hear the song. This music is in the same vein as Cradle of Filth. Havent heard any band in India doing it this well. Hozo\'s vocals are a replica of Danni Filths vocals but also have its own unique sound. I found this song very impressive at the