s-the-gorkha-metal-warriors'),(473,0,2,2,'The Pulp Society','After years of individually playing in other outfits and setups, The Pulp Society has finally come together to add a little skanky funk to the burgeoning indie Indian music scene. With their complicated and messed up (read: varied) roots as a huge strength, they tackle material that is irreverent, sexy, disrespectful and always very groovy.\r\n\r\n A deep love for the songwriting traditions of the old school funk and disco of the 70s-80s combined with a modern outlook and sense of sound design, veering towards nu-jazz and a fair degree of rock and roll, held together by a double guitar attack, are what make one part of the sound. Aided by basslines set in the heart of disco and funky percussions and violin, lyrics are a major point of focus, and songwriting is key to the bands vision for a revival or a modern take on this classic black power sound.    \r\n\r\nHow do you try and control a complicated country with dozens of languages and intense situations? Answer: you dont. You just dance and celebrate the complications! The only sensible thing left to do in this scene with people judging and mudslinging each other, is to dance baby! And make people dance.\r\n\r\nExpect some seriously high energy sets, with disco style bass, groovy pockets, some jazz coloured mode playing, and tongue in cheek lyrics that have no respect for genre and culture divisions.  \r\n \r\n \r\n\r\n*******','thepulpsociety@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/thepulpsociety','http://www.myspace.com/thepulpsociety ','http://www.soundcloud.com/thepulpsociety','','451816530005','1673',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-pulp-society'),(474,0,0,0,'Clubfeet','','','http://www.facebook.com/HelloClubfeet','','','','195378643840801','1669',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','clubfeet'),(475,0,3,3,'Verses','VerseS debuted in 2008 through various inter-collegiate gigs. Impressed by their consistent successes at various venues, Flying Machine endorsed them for a year (2010-2011). They consolidated their success streak by releasing an EP on May 1st 2011, subsequently signing on to MCube Records Label. Their EP Threshold, the title track of which coalesces the themes of a potential musical revolution with enchanting mystic undertones, sold over a thousand copies within the first five months of its release.\r\n\r\nBesides headlining a host of shows in and outside Bangalore, this Bangalore-based band has also opened at the Octoberfest 2010, finished as runners-up in the band-hunt to open for Metallica; supported international acts such as Lacuna Coil, Cypher 16, Fractalline; regularly winning both critical and popular acclaim, even for their individual performances. They are fresh from their Strawberry Fields Victory as well as IITM Live wire and will be representing India at the Global Battle of the Bands to be held in Bucharest, Romania later this year.\r\n\r\nAdditional Info\r\n\r\nCompetitions won: \r\n	VIT, Bangalore, 2008\r\n	Vibes 08 and 09, Sambhram college (twice) \r\n	MVIT  June 2008\r\n	MSRIT, 2009\r\n	Dayanand Sagar Institute of Technology, 2009\r\n	Reva Institute of Technology, 2009\r\n	Vistas 11, PES BBM Sept 2010\r\n	Festember 10 NIT Trichy Sept 2010\r\n	Autumn Muse, 11. St Johns Bangalore Aug 2010\r\n	Reliance Time-Out 11 July 2011\r\n	Riviera 2011, VIT, Vellore Jan 2011\r\n	Ananya 11, KSIT April 2011\r\n	Sea rock 11, BITS-PILANI GOA November 2011\r\n	Strawberry Fields 11, Nov 2011\r\n\r\nShows headlined at: \r\nHeadlined the following shows\r\n	R. L. Jalappa Institute of Technology \r\n	VIT, Bangalore \r\n	PES BBM, Bangalore\r\n	St Francis College, Bangalore\r\n	JSSIT, Bangalore\r\n	DBIT, Bangalore (Co-headliners with Swarathma)\r\n	UVCE, Bangalore, \r\n\r\n\r\n All the band members are accomplished in so many other ways and pursue their rocking dream that they share in common, even though their individual influences are varied. Fresh from their Strawberry Fields victory, Verses is looking forward to the release of their album and an All India Tour in the near future.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','verses.india@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Verses/149157301792922','	http://www.myspace.com/versesindia','','','149157301792922','1656',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','verses-1'),(476,0,29,29,'Dark Project','\"A project aimed at the formation of the band\" - Dark Project was always subscripted with this tagline in it\'s inception years(2002-2005); In 2005, the tagline lost the value because the project reached it\'s completion. A band was formed with 5 people in it from 3 different Engineering institutes: IIT KGP, Jadavpur University and HIT, Haldia.\r\n\r\nDark Project is an English band that composes music that can be classified as an eclectic blend of Alternative and Progressive Rock.Using their proficiency with technology that they got as a freebee as a part of their Degrees, Dark Project slowly started recording songs adopting a complete DIY philosophy. In the year 2007, they came out with their first offering in the form of a 9 song album titled Chaos Sessions. This album was recorded with a guitar processor completely self made by the band for a megre 150 bucks, since the band couldnt afford enough cash with their pocket money.\r\n\r\nPost completion of their degrees, Dark Project re-grouped and re-shuffled its lineup. Amidst all the adversity, they did not want to stop the production mill and came out with their second full length album titled as Liberty & Entropy in the year\r\n2009. The album was eventually reviewed by the Rolling Stone Magazine, Rock Street Journal, IndiarockMp3, Indiescion and was also released on iTunes and Amazon for the worldwide audience. The band followed it up with shows in Some Place Else, Opus and the Pub Rock Fest in the same year.\r\n\r\nThis was followed by a hiatus for 2 years that involved a bassist change and a relocation of the band to Bangalore. The band made a comeback into the Independent circuit with its two latest offerings  Magic and Tale of the Liars in July this year(2011).\r\n\r\nDark Project is not just a band, it\'s a relationship that has survived, struggled and bruised through the odds for the last 6 years. Even with a limited English music listener base in the country, the band wants to inspire people through their work as they prepare themselves up for a mission that only reads - Follow your dreams, no matter how bad the situations get, feel the \'Magic\' that happens because of it.\r\n\r\n\r\nDark Project is:\r\nSauvik Biswas - Guitars, Sequencing, Programming\r\nKorak Sarkar - Drums\r\nAnant Saxena - Bass Guitar\r\nUgyal Tshering Lama - Guitars, Keyboards, Harmonica\r\nSudipto Biswas - Vocals, Acoustic Guitars','Anirban Ghoshal','http://www.facebook.com/darkprojectband','http://darkproject.co.in','','','108262605719','1655',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dark-project'),(477,0,1,1,'ScYthuS','Formed in 2010, ScYthuS is a 5 piece metal act from New Delhi. With influences ranging from a variety of genres, the band has a unique and heavy sound, With a combination of brutal breakdowns and melodic solos. The band has certainly earned a reputation of being one of the most promising Metal acts around being the Second runners up at TNT (NSIT) on their first ever gig, the band is here to stay and make you mosh till you drop.\r\n\r\nOpening act for \"Cyanide Serenity-UK\"\r\nOpening act for \"Social Suicide-Norway\"','','http://www.facebook.com/scythusindia','http://www.myspace.com/scythusindia','','','108381745857385','1647',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','scythus'),(478,0,15,15,'The Old School Tie','Four years after passing out of the same high school, Kshitij (vocals) and Vaibhav (bass) bumped into each other while looking for musicians to start a band with. A few months after the first, rather bizarre jam in a friends basement - Abhishek and Abhinav joined in on lead guitar and drums to complete the rather eccentric group. With influences as diverse as funk, classic rock and alternative modern music - old school tie (named after the common high school that \'ties\' them together) concentrate on making original music that they believe is the only thing that comes closest to expressing them as they truly are.','','http://www.facebook.com/oldschooltie','http://www.myspace.com/oldschooltieindia','','','40159077141','1644',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-old-school-tie'),(479,0,10,10,'GRAND PIANORAMAX','Winner of the first Montreux Jazz Festival International Piano Solo Competition, Swiss born, NY bred pianist Leo Tardin conceived Grand Pianoramax as an all-live keyboards/drums duo blending fiery analog-synth bass, maddening arpeggios, organic drumming and freestyle spoken word from occasional guest vocalists.  \r\n\r\nAmong the collaborators that contributed to Grand Pianoramax one can mention Zrich-based Dominik Burkhalter (official and current drummer of the project), as well as first-class NYC musicians and past drummers Deantoni Parks (The Mars Volta, Meshell Ndegeocello), Jojo Mayer and Adam Deitch (Talib Kweli, John Scofield). On vocals, an impressive rotating cast of US underground hiphop legends and poets have lent their talent to the project, including Mike Ladd, Invincible (Platinum Pied Pipers), Mr Lif French hip-hop/folk artist Spleen and full-time member Black Cracker (CocoRosie, Buuny Rabbit).\r\n\r\nGrand Pianoramaxs first CD, the self-titled Grand Pianoramax was released worldwide in 2005 by ObliqSound. The album generated more than 43,000 downloads via iTunes USA and top-notch reviews from both sides of the Atlantic. The Starlite single was also released on vinyl in 2005, featuring remixes by Nuspirit Helsinki and Domu, and frequently appeared on the playlists of tastemakers Laurent Garnier, Rainer Trby, Mr Scruff, Patrick Forge, Osunlade.\r\n\r\nGrand Pianoramaxs second album, The Biggest Piano In Town, was released worldwide by ObliqSound in 2008, generating rave reviews and features in publications including BPM, XLR8R (USA) Metro, Time Out London, (UK) lUomo Vogue (IT).  DJ Spinnas remix of the albums single The Hook was digitally released shortly after. It is now available on vinyl as well.\r\n\r\nGrand Pianoramaxs third album, Smooth Danger, was recorded and mixed between Mumbai, Berlin, Paris and Bristol (and masterised by Sahwn Joseph, collaborator of Portishead) and will be released in Europe and the USA in October 2010, supported by a European release-tour in November-December. In addition to the core duo of Leo Tardin and Dominik Burkhalter, various guests appear on the album, including Grand Pianoramax long-time collaborators Mike Ladd, Black Cracker and for the first time Karsh Kale on tabla.\r\n\r\nPrimarily a live project, Grand Pianoramax was recently on a 10-city tour in the USA opening for jazz/funk legend Maceo Parker at legendary venues including the Fillmore in San Francisco and the Roxy in Los Angeles. The band also extensively toured in Europe in major cities including Paris, Berlin, London, Milan, Rome, Zrich, Lisbon, as well as more eastern destinations including Istanbul and Mumbai (where two Tracks from Smooth Danger were recorded at the Blue Frog music venue/production house).\r\n\r\nFor additional info about \"Smooth Danger\", please visit: www.myspace.com/leotardin\r\n\r\n','Switzerland: chloe.brunner@gmail.com / Germany: tobi.kirsch@passionate-pr.de / France: belloir.sebastien@gmail.com US: kevin@obliqsound.com','http://www.facebook.com/grandpianoramax','','','','32683523458','1640',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','grand-pianoramax'),(480,0,103,103,'Wrenz United','','','http://www.facebook.com/wrenzunited','http://www.wrenzunited.com','','','176188809068360','1636',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','wrenz-united'),(481,0,121,121,'A4apple','+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\r\n\r\nINFORMATION LOADING... \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPLEASE WAIT...\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nACCESS DENIED...\r\n\r\n\r\nTRY LATER...','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/A4apple/88409240989','http://www.myspace.com/a4apple','','','88409240989','1634',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','a4apple'),(482,0,74,74,'IAFWAY','IAFWAY is a Hardcore/Metal band from Delhi, India.\r\n\r\n','Vishnu - +91 9819955368','http://www.facebook.com/pages/IAFWAY/37558498015','http://www.myspace.com/iamfakewhoareyou','','','37558498015','1630',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','iafway'),(483,0,0,0,'Abandoned Agony','Abandoned Agony is one of the acts which is inspired by the \'in ur face brutality\' concept which has been established by some bands like cannibal corpse, suffocation, cryptopsy, nile, dying fetus etc... We believe in delivering power packed performances of our own version of brutal death metal without giving heed to the actual expectations of the general crowd. We believe in staying true to ourselves n making unadulterated music... We have recently released our demo titled \'Infected Unborn\'...','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Abandoned-Agony/62991857575','','','','62991857575','740',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','abandoned-agony'),(484,0,82,82,'Vidwan','Anoop Mohandas : Vocals  Anoop is a versatile singer and a trained hindustani vocalist.\r\n\r\nYakzan Gary Pereira : Keyboards And Synth Yakzan is a seasoned performer and music programmer who is one of the most sought after session artists in south India. He has extensively toured the world with Daksha Seth Dance Co. and Asima, which includes performances at the famous Royal Alberts hall and BBC Proms. He is also actively involved with renowned Malayalam music directors like George Peter, M Jayachandran and Mejo.He\r\ngained recent popularity following a colab on an album with Job Kurien and Charan entitledThaalam which was released under Manorama music label. He has performed alongside playback singing sensation Karthik at the IPL inauguration ceremony for Chennai Super\r\nkings.\r\n\r\nBen Sam Jones : Bass And Guitars Well known among musicians as one of the most versatile bassists in South India. He is a prolific session artist working closely with big names of the malayalam film music industry. He has also played live with Avial , Job Kurien and the\r\ncochin based metal band Heretic.\r\n\r\nVivek Thomas: Vocals,Guitars and Synths Vivek is the frontman and primary songwriter for the Trivandrum based progressive psychedelic band Soul Burn. He is known for his versatile vocal technique. He was awarded best vocalist at IIT CHENNAIs Saarang 2008. A lawyer by profession he has also qualified in sound engineering from Chetana Sound Studios. He has performed with Evergreen , Rex Vijayan (avial) and is also noted for his contribution on vocals for VH1s ROCK IN INDIA 2010 promo ad.\r\n\r\nArpith Easo Samuel : Drums Worked previously as a composer/drummer for Cochin/Banglore based metalcore band Heretic who were known for their live acts and\r\noriginality. He is the latest addition to the Vidwan family and is a self taught drummer who draws influences from John Thomas (motherjane), Mithun puthanveetil(avial), Gavin Harrison and Jojo Meyer. Heretic was featured in a cover story segment of Rolling Stone Magazine and has played numerous gigs alongside motherjane , Avial, headlined Octoberfest Banglore, June Rock Out Chennai and played over 50 shows in India.\r\n\r\nRex Vijayan : Guitars (live)\r\nRex Vijayan is a guitarist, composer, producer & multi-intrumentalist most popularly known as the axeman for the alternative malayali rock band Avial. Rex was one among the few Indian guitarists sought out by Gibson guitars USA for an exclusive deal to play their guitars.\r\nHe recently received much applause as background scorist/music director for the highly acclaimed Malayalam film Kerala Caf\r\nHis latest venture is \'\'Chappa Kurish\" \r\n','Midhun Raj aka MunZ TDT, 09961-545272','http://www.facebook.com/vidwanfolk','','','http://www.reverbnation.com/vidwan','123201064404331','1630',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','vidwan'),(485,0,11,11,'Wolf\'s Lair','Hmmmmm... Where do we begin?\r\n\r\nAfter a 5 year scene and two albums .. When a little hurdle could not be crossed, \'Wolf\'s Lair\' was formed in (Mid of August 2010) .. When Mark, Vivin, Arun and Manu split from their previous band  Blood & Iron and  decided to form a new Sound and line up along with Anshuman (Escher\'s Knot) & Pharez (Divine Dust) ..\r\n\r\nWith the New members came the powerful sound and a wave of pure-aggressive music. They are recognisable with their intensely powered grooves & smooth vocals. The amalgamation of the Six passionate musicians are evident in their Live Gigs.\r\n\r\nPart of the success of the band totally relies on the mutual respect and musicality involved as a band in the Song-writing process. Their profound diverse backgrounds & influences emerge to create a Unique yet powerful compositions. While still taking every opportunity to perform, they are working on various projects in the upcoming year ..\r\n\r\nThe band now delivers a Unique sound which is a collaboration of the various members and their influences, bringing out a sound ranging from Power to Epic to Symphonic to Thrash to Speed to Melodic to Death to Black and Absolute HEAVY METAL! \\\\m//','Amaranta Entertainment - Geoffrey G Thomas - 0-9962551048','http://www.facebook.com/wolfs.lair.chennai','','','','121263544598692','1629',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','wolfs-lair'),(486,0,4,4,'What Google Can\'t Find.','','Ajinkya Joshi -  +919766262682;  Akshat Vaze - +918087790302','http://www.facebook.com/whatgooglecantfind','http://nh7.in/whatgooglecantfind/','http://soundcloud.com/what-google-cant-find','','125352590852330','1626',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','what-google-cant-find'),(487,0,3,3,'Lagori','Lagori is an eclectic group of musicians with varied musical influences, who have come together to dish out foot tapping, soul stirring music. \r\n\r\nAlthough Lagori draws influences from the flavour of each musician - ranging from Hindustani, Soul, Funk, Rock, Blues and Metal, the end result is a unique sound which at the same time has a tinge of familiarity to it. \r\n\r\nWhile the band uses Hindi/Kannada to communicate their inspirations and message, the music is something that everyone - despite lingual differences - will understand.','Gaurav Vaz - +919900516145','http://www.facebook.com/LagoriIndia','','','','203664166356560','1622',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','lagori'),(488,0,2,2,'Karmaasa','Karmaasa has a deep meaning in itself which is a part of ethnic Punjabi Roots , Its deeply a combination of two  Words  Karma  derived from Sanskrit language word which means \"action\" or \"deed\". And Assa which is been derived from Shri Guru Granth Sahib Ji , the holy book of Sikhs meaning Ray of Hope . Combination of both the words leads to the deep meaning which states To keep the hope alive through our positive actions by successfully defeating all obstacles of life  \r\nFew group of young Musicians believed in this strong word and formed a Band named KARMAASA in the year 2007 which completely focused on Punjabi Folk with the element of Western Rock , Metal ,Sufi & Heavy Hard Stuff\r\nIt was for the first time in the histroy, the  Indian Audience got a taste of Rock & heavy metal fusionised with the Punjabi Folk Music which was been heavily appreciated by the Indian Masses and Indian Media.\r\n\r\nThis leads to the formation of the First ever PUNJABI ROCK FUSION BAND of INDIA named KARMAASA . \r\n\r\nKarmaasa has been successful in driving a spirit of love & passion the masses which which appreciates the Music & Lyrics of the band majorly comprises of Love , Affection , Realization of social Evils & about the Great warriors of INDIA . \r\n\r\nTaking the Indian Punjabi Folk blended with western Rock music to the next level competitive level,  Karmaasa had sung Various hits like Mein vassi haan , Bol Mitti Da Bawa , Shiv Kumar Batalvis Poetries , Fansi , Mahi & had sung the lyrics of the Pakistani Lyricist AHMED JAFFAR . \r\n\r\nWith the commitment of producing more music in the future for the Indian Audience Karmaasa is regularly focusing to produce more songs for its lovers . \r\n\r\nKarmaasa is always been quoted as a synonym to the  SOUND OF REVOLUTION.\r\n','9988301983 (Manpal Singh)','http://www.facebook.com/karmaasatheband','http://www.karmaasa.com','','http://www.reverbnation.com/karmaasatheband','149904081736512','1619',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','karmaasa'),(489,0,0,0,'Satinder Sartaaj','Dr. Satinder Sartaaj is an emerging sufi singer. The substance of sufism is the Truth and the meaning of sufism is the selfless experiencing and actualization of the Truth.\n\nDr. Satinder Sartaaj has a magnetic personality with the glow of sufism, wisdom and peace and tranquility on his face and every single soul listening to him gets drowned in his thoughtful poetic songs. He bridged the generation gap and relates sufism to present life and today\'s generation.\n\nDr. Satinder Sartaaj has dedicated several of his songs to nature because from the beginning he was drawn to the beauty and fragrance of flowers, rainbows and the tranquil flow from the water creating rhythmic patterns. Gifted with mellifluous voice and a remarkable range in all octaves, Sartaaj followed the dictates of his inner soul and chose to reveal the glory of mysticism.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Satinder-Sartaaj/160625373984951','','','','160625373984951','1617',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','satinder-sartaaj'),(490,0,1,1,'H.I.D.E (Hope In Dark Evolution)','Hope In Dark Evolution ( H.I.D.E ) started in late 2010 when five aspiring  musicians got to know each other individually .At that time most of the members were involved in small musical projects, But the members who were involved had a common thought in their mind to settle down with in one band and to put their blood and sweat into something really special. After a while they started jamming as a band and covered most of the artists who influenced them.That was the time when the name Hope In Dark Evolution came to life. After their coordination was precise guitarist Karan Singh presented his first song to the band and the band worked on it and named it This World Of Hate.\r\nLater-on the band had planned to launch atleast two Original Compositions that they could present as a piece of their own creativity. Holding on to this thought the band worked on another song that turned out to be The Atheist.\r\nThe Band then wanted to release their demos and the songs were produced by Arsh Sharma (Guitarist:- THE CIRCUS).The songs were released on 2nd February 2011 and now they are on their pursuit to be one of the most rememberable bands in the Indian metal scene.\r\n\r\n\r\nLine up at present:\r\n\r\nKaran Singh - Guitars/ Backing vocals \r\nGaurav Sharma -  Guitars\r\nSamir Leonard - Bassist\r\nAmrit Singh - Drums\r\n\r\n\r\n','+919999328048','http://www.facebook.com/HopeIndarkevolution','','','','155358157850456','1617',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','hide-hope-in-dark-evolution'),(491,0,1,1,'DJ NICK ( Shivlink Records )','From the land that bore the ilk of great musicians like TANSEN, rises another son with the same penchant for creating celestial sounds. NICK aka Manish Arora, is one of the few new age Indian musicians to have touched the epitome of EDM and are around to share the great vibes with their audiences. Performing across the globe, enthralling audiences the wo