usic.','','http://www.facebook.com/CorrodedDreams','http://www.redbullbedroomjam.in/corroded-dreams','','http://www.reverbnation.com/corrodeddreams ','151789848041','1589',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','corroded-dreams'),(497,0,29,29,'!Banned.','If you find yourself wandering amidst the thickets of Tollygunge, Baghajatin or Ramgarh, you might stumble upon the raucous mixture of an apparently motley gang of youngsters. These young guns might seem to be insane to some, blatant to others, unruly to the rest but thats the way they swap their ideas (preferably in a crazy way) in one of the busiest tea shops around. \r\n\r\nWelcome to the Banned Family!\r\n\r\nBanned, as the name suggests, specializes in the prohibited ways of doing their own thing for quite some time now. They wear their beliefs on their sleeves, and it permeates into their music, be it the political issues of today and yesteryear\'s, or social issues gnawing at the countrys developments, or even economic issues, albeit in a satirical fashion. Their genre is one that hasnt been heard; they call it Aggressive Poetry that is entirely lyrics driven. \r\n\r\nYou dont need to a rocket scientist to understand us, all you need is to keep yourself updated with the current affairs, says vocalist EPR, though he prefers to call himself the MC.\r\n\r\n When it comes to the performance, their aggression is what that boils up the stage and thus creating powerful act of their own.\r\n\r\nBanned, with its fresh sound and great stage presence, has been making waves across the city. It seems as if Aggressive Poetry is here to stay.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n-Nishant Chhinkwani  (PR manager)\r\n\r\n\r\nAchievements (till date) :\r\n\r\n[In the competition circuit]\r\n\r\nTimes of India, (\'Times youth challenge\') -band competition Winners \'010\r\n\r\nNUJS, \'Outlawed/Rivet 2010\' - battle of bands Winners\r\n\r\nISM Dhanbad, Srijan 2010, Avalanche (Band competition) winners \r\n\r\nNIT Durgapur, \"