media. \r\n\r\nKaavs epynomous EP was the #1 Indie Indian EP of the year 2010 by Indiecision Magazine. Kaavs song Daya represented India in the international Indie Music Compilation Album MAP (Music Alliance Project) comprising 35 countries which was featured by The Guardian UK. Kaavs video for the song Daya was featured on Coldplays official website in September 2010. Kaavs EP was given a rating of 4/5 by MyOpus Radio  and the band was also featured by leading newspapers such as the Times, Indian Express and Mathrubhoomi. \r\n\r\nAfter the immense success of the debut EP Kaav is scheduled to record a full length album by March 2011. Kaavs usual set list comprises of ten plus songs which include the songs featured in the EP and other compositions which may make it to the upcoming album. Kaav has been playing gigs around Kerala and is planning to tour rest of the country soon.\r\n\r\nThe band is based in Vypin Island, Kerala, India. The seclusion of the place brings several limitations. But the natural beauty and the coastal lifestyle have an immense influence on the nature of the bands music. Kaavs music draws influences from Indian classical & Folk music, Rock, Metal, World Music, Jazz Fusions, Blues, Prog, Psy and Alternative.\r\n\r\nThe word Kaav was taken from Kaavu or Kaavukal which in Malayalam means the traditional shrines, forests where so many folk stories, art forms like Theyyam, Koodiyatam etc. originated. Fears, mysteries, superstitions, religion and spirituality were always associated with Kaav which is also the meeting place of the human psyche.\r\n\r\n\'Kaav\' in Media\r\n---------------------\r\n\r\nThis Vypin Island trio appeared out of nowhere this year and quietly defined something very important for music in India  you dont need a tabla, a sitar or even a vocalist to make music steeped in Indian-ness. Kaavs eponymous E.P. is the best we have heard this year \r\n Indiecision  \r\n\r\nWith a set of talented musicians and a lot of enthusiasm, Kaav is set to go places \r\n The New Indian Express  \r\n\r\nKaavs music blends lot of influences but the final product sounds fresh. A definite recommendation to all. \r\n MyOpus Radio  \r\n\r\nJust like their music, Kaav has created waves and exploded music scene \r\n Kochi Vibe  \r\n\r\nAn album that is sure to catch attention \r\n Indian Music revolution  \r\n\r\nThe band is really making its way to the listeners hearts with its slight Indian-ness. \r\n Yentha  \r\n\r\nThe young rock band which is a mix of great talent and passion for music is gaining listeners day by day  \r\n Cochin Square  \r\n\r\nThe three piece band has managed to intrinsically weave their inherent heritage without being too loud about it. So the much sought Indian-ness could easily be relished in the sound which is as original as it gets\r\n Demrockritic  \r\n\r\nThis enthusiastic young rock band with promising music has miles to go! Listen to Kaav and feel the energies pouring out \r\n The Times Group\r\n\r\nYoung band with promising sound\r\n Rocktantra, UK.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nKaav is\r\n\r\nSyam N Pai     - Guitar\r\nShabeer P Ali   - Bass\r\nArun S Kumar  -  Drums\r\n\r\n','info@kaav.in,09446597969, 08606312297','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Kaav/150886178268289','kaav.in','','','150886178268289','1582',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','kaav'),(499,0,31,31,'Rock Nepal','To provide information on Nepalese Rock and Metal music industry\r\nCompany Overview\r\n\"An Independent Page Dedicated To Nepalese Rock n\' Metal scene\" -ok N?P@l !? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? \\m/\r\nDescription\r\n.**.....? \r\n\\.????? ,.,<\r\n.\\.**...?\r\n..\\\r\n?/\r\n/?\r\n/ \\ Rock Nepal \\m/\r\n\r\n(....\\............../....)\r\n.\\....\\........... /..../\r\n..\\....\\........../..../\r\n...\\..../.|.`\\./.../\r\n.../... |....|.... ( `\\\r\n..|.....|.|.|\\....\\\r\n..\\......` .. ......\r\n...\\_.............. _.','rock_nepal@ymail.com','http://www.facebook.com/werocknepal','','','http://www.reverb