e-Existence-Is-Here/150755594935245','','','','150755594935245','1570',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','wajud-the-existence-is-here'),(502,0,4,4,'Halahkuh','Halahkuh is a four piece thrash/death/ power groove metal band from Pune, India formed in January 2011.\r\n\r\nThe name \'Halahkuh\' is derived from the archaic Hindi word \'halaku\' which means fallen angels. These angels disobeyed god and were damned forever.\r\nNow they lurk in brimstone and fire waiting to torture your souls, slowly rising from the throes of feeble denial and misery, a monstrosity, the Halahkuh.\r\n\r\nTapping into the recesses of the unconscious, feeding off despair and dread that flows through the nerves of a crumbling, fractured, yet carnal, instinctual society, to bring you the spine numbing, head spinning wrecking ball called thrash with a chewy power groove centre and every flavour of good old cold steely metal. \r\n\r\nBrought to life by founders Subhrajyoti and Sarvesh at the beginning of 2011, Halahkuh arrived on the scene and since then have dedicated themselves \r\nto putting on brutally energetic performances of pure thrash and groove metal in all its glory.\r\n\r\nWith the creation of their very first original piece, the stage was set and Halahkuh began its growth from their first gig at the Armed Forces Medical College on the 17th of February, coming in 3rd, but blowing everyones minds and so started the journey to the next gig on the 25th of February at the National Insurance Academy where they won the title of number one band along with earning some sweet respect with the best drummer and best bass guitarist awards. \r\n\r\nNow having the momentum they needed, they ploughed on,uprooting anything that came in their way.Underground gigs accompanied by many a prestigious venues,halahkuh stunned one and all , and at many competitions, they not only came in first but also took home best drummer, best lead and bass guitarist titles multiiple times.\r\n\r\nCurrently working on new material, Halahkuh waits to unleash its ferocity to the community and spread the word that it is time to rise.\r\n ','+91 9960565423   , +917709111907  or halahkuh@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/halahkuh','','','','186518201388458','1568',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','halahkuh'),(503,2,1,1,'The Urban EarlyMen','The Urban EarlyMen, formed in the summer of 2011, is an alternative band that draws its influence from, Radiohead, Pink Floyd, Red Hot Chili Peppers, The Beatles, The Doors and many others that have an element of psychedelia. The band was formed after several line-up changes during the jamming sessions that lasted for more than 7 weeks before the final line-up was decided. The original line-up included Roshan Roy on the drums, Abhijeet Saniyal on the bass, Mridul Luthra on the lead guitar and Adityan Nair on the vocals. Later Siby Mathew, a dear friend of Mridul, was introduced as the rhythm guitarist and the band started jamming under the temporary name \"The Chawla Band\". Siby\'s introduction to the band encouraged the psychedelic influence in the music that the band made that primarily intended to be a funk/alternative band. After the band\'s first performance at The Summer Jam \'11, bassist Abhijeet Saniyal left the band due to creative differences because of which Roshan Roy took up the bass and Rohan Arora took up the drums. \r\nThe name \"The Urban EarlyMen\" was finalized after considering each of our musical preferences, which coincidentally proved to be similar. All the band members share a common interest in old, classic rock songs, sometimes calling us as Earlymen metaphorically.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPast Performances: \r\n\r\n Club Sirrocco (Summer Jam 2011) - 8th July 2011 \r\n Pulse 2011(AIIMS) - 17th September 2011\r\n Manajsa - 22nd September 2011\r\n Manajsa - 6th October 2011\r\n Turquoise Cottage - 9th October 2011\r\n Striker Pub And Brewery - 27th October 2011\r\n Turquois