06 07:27:31',0,'','','asylum'),(509,0,1,1,'Heisenberg','They just got up. Jammed and nailed a few places and like to define themselves as bunch of simple guys playing some good music keeping in mind that their listeners aren\'t the tone deaf kids companies are cashing on.  O_o  Played for various bands back then, which disbanded later on and merged to form the group we call \"Heisenberg\". Jokes apart, the guys are known for their unique way, onstage-offstage, and blowing away the crowds with their act.\r\nOh yes, Their drummer is only 15.\r\nThey are still unsure if they play for the band. \r\n\r\nYatin \"Fucking Awesome Fat Boy\" Gera - Ex- Member/Rhythm Guitars\r\n\r\nRAUNIQ \"R?nin\" BAGGA --- Groupie/Our best critic\r\n\r\nGuest Members:\r\nAlam - Vocals \r\nDhruv Saxena - Guitars -- IIT Kanpur 2010\r\nAnkit \'Vedic\' Rawat- Bass --IIT Kanpur 2010\r\nParth Sharma -- IIT Kanpur 2011\r\n\r\nPlaces where we have played so far ::\r\n\r\nBattle Of The Bands, Garden Of Five Senses 2010\r\nAIIMS Pulse 2010\r\nIIT Kanpur Synchronicity 2010\r\nHansraj College Fest, Delhi University 2011\r\nHindu College Fest \"Mecca\", Delhi University 2011\r\nJamia Milia Islamia IEEE Fest 2011\r\nGuru Teg Bahadur Institute Of Technology \"Gates 2011\"\r\nGGSIP University School Of Chemical Technology Fest 2011\r\nOne Boulevard \"Monster Balls - Metallica Night\", Select City Walk, New Delhi 2011\r\nTurquoise Cottage, New Delhi 2011\r\nCafe Morrison, New Delhi - October 2011\r\nIIT Kanpur Synchronicitym 2011\r\nBITS Pilani Rocktaves 2011, Pilani\r\n\r\nOther than that, we have been shortlisted for big events/fests like:\r\nIIT Roorkee 2010\r\nIIT Mumbai 2010\r\nBITS Goa SeaRock 2011\r\nIIT Mumbai 2011','+919717354549/+919910260699','http://www.facebook.com/heisenbergtheband','http://www.youtube.com/heisentube','','http://www.reverbnation.com/heisenberg','137775896264167','1546',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','heisenberg'),(510,0,63,63,'Dwar','','dwarband@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/dwar.shillong','http://www.youtube.com/dwarband','','','143141911404','1541',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dwar'),(511,0,4,4,'Infidels of Sanity','Infidels of Sanity, affectionately called IOS or just Infidels, is a five-piece band hailing from Pune. Our genre, after a whirlwind of changes that started from Power Metal and Speed Metal, now has been given the name Hypnotic Progressive Rock (by the fans themselves) because of the deep psychedelic elements thrown into the progressive, deep lyrically themed songs. Like our name suggests, our music is different from the rest but still something that will appeal to all. We aren\'t afraid to use our technical knowledge to make our music more worthwhile to the listeners. \"Infidels (non-believers) of Sanity (or whatever the world/society feels is sane)\" will always want to cross new boundaries of sound and thoughts through our music and words. Our songs are usually themed on complex human emotions which are evoked at their prone extremity.\r\n    Pune Mirror seemed to describe us best: \"Infidels of Sanity play hypnotic progressive rock with an inkling of psychedelic sounds thrown into the mix. With trance inducing polyrhythms, and dizzying melodies the band plays esoteric music that grows on the listener. True to their name, Infidels of Sanity bend the very boundaries of music.\"\r\n','infidelsofsanity@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/infidelsofsanity','','','http://www.reverbnation.com/infidelsofsanity','229383693979','1537',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','infidels-of-sanity'),(512,0,0,0,'Harpreet','Harpreet is a Singer, Songwriter, Guitarist and a performer by heart. he got inspiration towards music from his father, and started singing at a very early age. Afterwards his keen interest in music, and support from his family and loved ones, took him to the next level, and he started writing, and composing.\n\nOn the other hand he is been performing on stage from his school time itself. Also, he had performed for Taj Mahal on Taj Mahotsav(Festival),7th July,2007 which was live on star news, and many festivals/occasions throughout the country.\n\nHis music/songs are derived from his life and free from the boundaries of Language, Genre, Region. As people say \"The freedom and the truth in his thoughts you can feel in his music\".','','http://www.facebook.com/HarpreetOfficial','','','','108838153888','1519',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','harpreet'),(513,0,3,3,'Blood & Iron','Blood & Iron was formed in early 2005 by Ashish with the aim of forging a new kind of band, combining the best the various sub-genres of Metal have to offer. After numerous line-up changes, for about a year and a half, the band stabilized  and since then theres been no looking back.\r\n\r\nEach member of the band brings a variety of influences which makes the synthesis  the music  of Blood & Iron so unique.\r\n\r\nWhile firmly rooted in Metal, the band effortlessly displays unbridled innovation and virtuosic skill combined with catchiness, raw power and melodic passages. Blood & Iron is accessible to a wide spectrum of listeners without ever sacrificing the integrity required to play this form of music from the heart.\r\nInfluenced by such great bands like Iron Maiden, Megadeth, Hammerfall, Nightwish, Manowar, Primal Fear, Death, Judas Priest, Kreator and more  the band captures the specialties of the various sub-genres of Metal without ever compromising on originality. \r\nThis is evident while listening to the songs, as a single song will show multiple characteristics  adding new dimensions to the music.\r\n\r\nDiscography:\r\n2007 - self titled/Blood & Iron\r\n2009 - Dynamite World\r\n\r\n\r\nBlood & Iron released a self-titled demo album in 2007. It received an amazing response in the underground metal scene and has encouraged the band to strive for greater things.\r\n\r\nThe second album \"Dynamite World\" was released in July 2009.\r\n\r\nBlood and Iron later opened for heavy metal gods Hammerfall in Feb 2010.\r\n\r\nThe band has recently started work on the third album, which can be expected to be released mid 2012. Also, there are lineup changes for this album, which is expected to employ comparatively less keyboards. \r\n\r\nThe new lineup will be revealed soon.\r\n','Vikram: +91 9008 230 656 ; Ashish: +971 317 3509','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Blood-Iron/93348489109','http://www.myspace.com/bloodnironx','','http://www.reverbnation.com/bloodnironx','93348489109','1518',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','blood-iron'),(514,2,1,1,'Another Vertigo Rush','Another Vertigo Rush has been defined under several genres such as Experimental-Psychedelic-Post rock-alternative-metal. However, The band would just like to remain within the confines of the Experimental/psychedelic definition. Musically the band aims at Mixing Ambient soundscapes with heavy breakdowns. However, there is no one set pattern for AVRs songs. \r\n\r\nThe band creates music through an organic process of composition - ie, jamming it out as opposed to construct parts and rehearse them in the studio. With varying musical influences within the band members, AVRs sound is a mixture of conventional musical arrangement with ambient textures, aiming at creating a virtual wall of sound. There is an emphasis of music being the real source of the cycles/waves that AVR aims at taking its listeners through and hence there is more emphasis on expression through music, which is more dominant in their sound than vocals.\r\n\r\nSince the Lineup change, AVR nas setteld into their current sound, though the band feels that musical evolution, as with life, is a constant part of their existance. The bands progression is evident from the transition from their earlier songs like Om, Anger Management ,Prevail and Conclave to newer songs like The Vibe. But nothing defines this process of evolution better than the Instrumental Track titled - Phase II\r\n\r\nThe band is heavily influenced by the likes of T00L, Queens of the Stone Age, A Perfect Circle, Nine Inch Nails and the likes.\r\n\r\nDespite being a niche sound, with almost no target audience in a place like India, over the past year or so AVR has built a reputation on the basis of its powerful live performances, and people are beginning to understand the idea behind the music.\r\n\r\nBreaking through to the mainstream scene was/is/never will be the bands top priority, however, An understanding of their music - whether with approval or disapproval is something that the band feels strongly about. \r\n\r\nJust the understanding','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Another-Vertigo-Rush/15587664611','http://anothervertigorush.com/','','','15587664611','1504',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-10 14:51:29',107,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','another-vertigo-rush'),(515,0,3,3,'Illuminati','We kicked off in the college dumpster way back in 2006; and from then it has been a good trip. The first, virgin hit was for ECHO-a charity event hosted by Mallya Aditi school at Guru Nanak Bhavan. At Dayanand Sagar College of engineering was the first win for the band. From then we have gathered quite a lot on our platter.\r\n\r\nThe band bagged the Regional winner\'s title of Campus Rock Idols 07-08 and toured with Kingfisher across the country performing gigs in cities like, Bangalore, Pune, Chennai, Hyderabad, Cochin, Calcutta etc.\r\nThe band has also had 2 consecutive wins at Whiplash \'07 and \'08(BMSCE), Hellraiser \'08 and \'09(IIML), Unmad \'08 and \'09 (IIMB), Spandan \'07 (JIPMER).\r\nThe list goes a little longer, but skipping that to the influences, bands, people, friends and all those things living and non-living that have kept us going in this journey.\r\n\r\nFrom Pink Floyd to Tool this is the spectrum of our influences. Our parents and well wishers have only added more to what we have. Our one aim, make music which even the pan walla can headbang too! Keep it catchy and keep it fresh!\r\n\r\nWe have a few tracks scratch recorded give them a listen here, http://www.myspace.com/illuminatibangalore, but we are aiming for a full release soon, for that info you will have to follow us on facebook, https://www.facebook.com/IlluminatiIndia.\r\n\r\nWith Ravish on guitars, Shubho on bass, Yadhu on Drums, Sid on keys and Venky on vocals, the sound from here is only gonna get heavier.','Venky - venky.junkie@gmail.com ','http://www.facebook.com/IlluminatiIndia','http://www.illuminati.co.in','','','0','5962',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','illuminati-1'),(516,0,2,2,'Aftertaste','Four catholic boys, with a penchant for music and true devotees of the Sunday Morning Mass, heralded the spirit of the parish choir. They sung their praises to the Lord above and lifted the courage of the clergy below. However, their goodwill notwithstanding, the solemnly-high priests banished these bachelors from the cathedral, citing safety for the fairly outgoing catholic women. \r\n\r\nThe judgment was harsh. Its repercussions, even severe. These four catholic boys are now on a mission to save the church from the impious hands that raise the chalice. They are out to defy the very establishments that support the walls of spiritual impediment. Or have they used too many words to get to the point and whoop that Roman Catholic ass???\r\n\r\nMeet Aftertaste, the antidote to a lukewarm regiment of traditional practices passing under the faade of religion. A brave new front fighting against the pretense of preachers while making every parochial house dance to their tunes of their hymns. The purpose: To serve the Lord with all their heart and their weapon of choice: sound. For the past two and a half years, these missionaries have led the crusade by touching the lives of people across the country. \r\n\r\nIts been a journey that has borne witness to the communion of four God-fearing souls. With Michael Lee pounding an all-strings-attack on the stained glasses of corruption.  Ruel Barretto, slapping the faces of the stiff-upper-lipped with some flavour-filled funk. Keegan Pereira, sermonizing the congregation with candid confessions of a catholic rebel. Levin Mendes, exorcizing the demons out of the monastery while pounding those tribal beats. And last but not the least is the new found sheep in the flock, a staunch convert and the first of the many to follow, Amit Bharadwaj a.k.a. Dj Mit, who will scuff and polish the edges of this newly baptized band.\r\n\r\nTogether, this act of faith will demolish the vices of the vatican with a brand of music that will anoint the deacons and salvage them from the pagans of society.  And as they stand on the pulpit of the Lord, these apostles will plead the blood of thy saviour, lift themselves into his hands and rapture the audience with an aftertaste that will be longed for and looked forward to in its second coming. Amen.','aloysiuslobo@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/aftertasteband','','','','23526758633','1490',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','aftertaste'),(517,0,1,1,'Route 3','Route 3 is a three piece band that was formed in the summer of 09. We are not \r\nthe same old band that you hear on the radio everyday. Our music is a mlange of\r\nalternative rock and pop rock consisting of some feet tapping beats thatll make \r\nyour  head bounce, groovy bass lines thatll make your head spin,catchy and crispy \r\nguitar riffs like fried chicken, trippy guitar sound thatll take you on a disco trip, \r\ntopped off with some powerful vocals thatll blow your mind.  \r\nWe have a wide range of influences like Incubus, Collective Soul, Audioslave,\r\nKings of Leon, Velvet Revolver, Zero, Jet, The Beatles, Led Zeppelin,\r\nRolling Stones, Foo Fighters, and Dave Matthews Band.\r\nRoute 3 has performed at various places like Hard Rock Cafe, Cafe Morrison, Manajsa, Turquoise Cottage,Tryst Music Cafe, TLR Cafe\r\nBlues Caf, Caf Oz, cafe 567 Hotel Grand Sartaj, Hotel Taj Mansingh, Miranda House college fest:Tempest09, Shri Ram School as\r\na part of a fundraiser for the Leh victims along side Them clones, Cyanide, Half \r\nstep down, Five8 and opened for Parikrama at LSR - Tarang 2011.\r\nRoute 3 have also competed and won competitions \r\nlike NBS Dwarka and IMS-DIA Noida, LSR-Tarang 2011, Amity university,\r\nYMCA University of science and technology. They were also awarded the most original band in the Rolling Stone Open Mic @ TLR','Bagus Kusuma:+919953053008','http://www.facebook.com/route3india','','','','108487389553','1487',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','route-3'),(518,0,1,1,'Frequency','Formed in September 2006, Frequency is a Delhi based Nu-Age/Electronic band which is getting noticed immensely due to its unique sound. Rony (Ex Vocalist), Kushal and Akshay knew each other well and were later joined in by Abhishek and Noel to complete the line-up. The band got its major recognition when got selected for Channel [V] Launchpad 2007 and later landed up as one of the top four finalists. Since then the band has been gigging regularly in the circuit. Later down the year 2007, Rony had to leave giving way to Lalit to do the vocal duties. Lalit gels well with the band and in his very first performance got us to win Campus Rock Idols 2007 - Regional Finals. \r\n  \r\nStarting the New Year on a high note, Frequency headlined Yamaha Roxx Asian Beat with Pentagram and got a chance to perform at Jack Daniels Legendary Mash Annual Rock Awards 2008  The Awards Night at Ministry Of Sound. At the same event, music director Mr. Sandeep Chowta got impressed and liked the vibe of the band. Since all the members are from different backgrounds in terms of their individual music tastes, it gives rise to a totally new and original sound.Now, the band is nothing less than a force to reckon with.\r\n\r\nThe bands growing popularity also got them covered by NDTV Metro Nation in the year 2008.\r\n\r\nSince all the members are from different backgrounds in terms of their individual music tastes, it gives rise to a totally new and original sound.\r\n\r\nAfter a hiatus of one year, the band is back with a slight change in their line-up and a strong change in the sound. Keeping others intact, and getting Varun Sood behind the drums, and Abhishek Jha a.k.a. East Stepper churning out massive synthesis from his workstation, the bands sound is tighter and groovier than ever before. So hop in and witness this insanity, while the quintet gets your body, stomping the floor with all that adrenalin rush that they just gave you.\r\n','+91 9999-680-663','http://www.facebook.com/FrequencyIndia','','','','8281576506','1484',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','frequency'),(519,0,11,11,'Brute Force','[ not available on the internet ]','','http://www.facebook.com/BrutalByBirth','','','','14375552413','1482',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','brute-force'),(520,0,0,0,'Girish And The Chronicles','Girish and The Chronicles was formed on 18th of October, 2009 in Gangtok, Sikkim (India). Already gaining some reputation as one of the finest rock singers in the country, through You Tube (Search Girish Pradhan), Girish Pradhan formed this band with a motive to revive Hard Rock, Slow Rock, Blues Rock and Heavy Metal. After a few concerts and gigs in their home town, such as Sikkim Area Convention Narcotics Anonymous III, the band decided to start taking part in some of the major Rock competitions in the country (2010), such as Rock o Phonix - IIT Guwahati. After winning and gaining positions in a few such competitions (-Pyrokinesis, Assam Engineering College; - Sinchisis, Guwahati Medical college; - Rock o Phonix, IIT Guwahati; - Eclecia, Heritage College, Kolkata; - Srijan fest, - Avalanche, ISMU Dhanbad etc.) and also the frontman  Girish Pradhan, bagging the best vocalist awards in all of them, and Guitarist, Suraz Karki bagging the best guitarist awards in most of them, the band immediately started getting headlining acts in the College Festivals such other Rock festivals, quickly gaining a lot of popularity in the press and media and creating a big fan base. The Media became aware of this. Girish and The Chronicless performance at Rabindra Bhawan, Guwahati, on 27th of June, 2010, was telecasted live, nationally on the NE Doordarshan channel.\n           The band was just doing good, when they took it to another level by participating and winning the auditions held at Shilpgram, Guwahati, for the Suncane Skale Festival, Montenegro, Europe. Their song Angels Angel or more popularly known as The Yester Years was selected to be compiled and judged at the Suncane Skale Music Festival, held at Montenegro, Europe, thus giving the band a chance to represent India on a Global Scale. Out of the many participants from Europe, Girish and The Chronicles represented India in foreign soil and bagged the Silver Trophy for their song The Yester Years, or Angels Angel. This created a huge rush in the media and the press giving the band a new status. This helped band in a lot of ways. Getting more concerts and they could now easily be found over the internet. The band was invited in  many National Rock Festivals, College Rock Festivals, Pub Rock festivals; as headlining acts/Guest bands covering a huge part of the country, almost the whole of the North East India and ended the year with 5 consecutive concerts in the States of Meghalaya and Assam, playing live at India Club, Guwahati on 31st of December. \n\n                   Girish and The Chronicles competed yet one more time in a competition named the CONVERSE ORIGINAL BAND HUNT held at Guwahati, India on 24th of February, 2011 this time keeping in mind, rock Magazines and more exposure of their recorded material. After winning, the bands songs got a chance to be featured in a compilation created by CONVERSE, which would be available in CONVERSE stores all over India and the also giving them a chance to be featured in the ROLLING STONES magazine. \n\nIn the month of September, 2011, the band had a one month Bangalore tour and played at venues such as HARD Rock Cafe\', Kyra, Tango, Jagriti theatre making a fan base in the southern part of the country as well.\n\nRecently the band participated in one of the major competitions of the year, Hornbill Rock and grabbed the second runner\'s up position, along with the \"best guitarist\" and \"best vocalist\" title.\n\n             Presently, touring, Girish and the Chronicles are releasing a Rock/Hard Rock/Heavy Metal album soon, yet upgrading their list of ventures and Chronicles.\n\n\"Girish and The Chronicles\" are :\n\n                                             Girish Pradhan    - Vocals/Guitars\n                                             Yogesh Pradhan - Bass Guitars\n                                             Suraz Karki         - Lead Guitars\n                                             Nagen Mongrati  - Drums ','+919593985951','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Girish-And-The-Chronicles/114384545303601','','','','114384545303601','1479',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','girish-and-the-chronicles'),(521,0,0,0,'Elephant Stone','Elephant Stone is the brainchild of multi-instrumentalist Rishi Dhir. As one of the most highly sought out sitar players in the psychedelic music scene (Skiddle.com) he has toured and recorded throughout the world with the Black Angels, the Earlies, the Soundtrack of Our Lives, and Brian Jonestown Massacre.\n\nIn 2009, Elephant Stone released their debut album, The Seven Seas. Perfectly melding Rishis obsession with the perfect pop song and the trippiest raga, The Seven Seas, was warmly embraced by the global indie-scene and long-listed for the coveted 2009 Polaris Music Prize. 2010 saw the release of The Glass Box EP, a 5-song suite of inspired power-pop/psyche classics, a supporting slot on the Brian Jonestown Massacres North American tour, an inaugural tour of Europe with sold-out dates in London and Berlin, and showcases at both CMJ and M for Montreal.\n\n2011 has shaped up to be an even busier year as they toured the US/Canada that included showcases at CMW/SXSW/NXNE, festival appearances at Osheaga (Montreal) and Iceland Airwaves, a new EP, and their return to UK soil.\n\n2012 will see the band release their sophomore album and continue to spread their sitar-inflected psyche-pop throughout the world. \n','kb@killbeatmusic.com (Canada) | info@elephantstonemusic.com (ROW)','http://www.facebook.com/ElephantStoneHQ','','','','21623169144','1464',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','elephant-stone'),(522,0,0,0,'DAGYAP','Sonam Chopel, born in Gangtok / SIKKIM -INDIA (March 10th 1959), is better known by his stage name DAGYAP. He is an unsigned recording artist and a professionally trained Thanka  Artist (traditional Tibetan religious art) , \nDagyap has released many underground tracks (All I want is freedom - Across the Himalayans -  Victory -  Im Tibetan - Brothers on fire ) \n',' ','http://www.facebook.com/pages/DAGYAP/286757902010','','','','286757902010','1460',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dagyap'),(523,5,1,146,'Hashback Hashish','Hashback Hashish is the stage name of Ashish Sachan, an incredibly creative and persistently innovative DJ/ Producer, based in Delhi, India. Beginning by experimenting with the fascinating music scene in Perth regularly, he was quickly getting recognized because of his distinct sound at Rise. Upon his arrival home, his in-arguably superior taste in music mated with his creative streak - the lovechild of which is Hashback Hashish.\r\n\r\nIn each one of HHs projects, be it the tightly-themed and executed Audio Visual Daft Punk, Deadmau5 & LCD Soundsystem Tributes or the proper techno gigs at venues like Blue Frog (DEL, MUM), Rise (Australia), TLR Caf (DEL), and Gulmarg Winter Festival and Woods Talk Festival, etc. his constant drive to create something unique shows clearly through.\r\n\r\nApart from performing DJ and Audio Visual (with VJ ThatGirl) sets across India, he recently released his debut album The Grinning, Naked Bunch independently to rave reviews by NME India, Wild City, Indiecision (NH7), TimeOut Mumbai, and more. \r\n\r\n5 songs from the album; Analog Air, Cascade, Crystalline Nightmares, Bring Her Back, & Lather, Rinse, Repeat; have also been featured on the national MTV show, MTV Sound Trippin.\r\n\r\nMore recently, 2 tracks, \'A Light Year\' and \'We\'re So Many\' from the EP \'Regret\' by Hashback Hashish\'s collaborative project with Jishnu Banerjee, were also featured in behind-the-scenes video of the Marie Claire August 2012 Issue.','hashbackhashish@gmail.com, +91-97110-79850','http://www.facebook.com/minimalesque','','http://soundcloud.com/hashbackhashish','','0','1453',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 15:15:06',289,'[\"hashbackhashish@gmail.com\"]','[\"+919711079850\"]','hashback-hashish'),(524,0,0,0,'Chaos','Chaos, as the name suggests, is a band which believes in music in its purest and most aggressive form - metal. From the humble beginnings of 2004, when we played at small local fests to the present, when we are headlining prestigious rock fests, its been a long and arduous journey. With the emergence of various subgenres, Old school thrash has almost disappeared from our gig circuits. Our endeavour is to remain true to our roots and put this great genre firmly back on the national gig map','09566249047 , 09961469372','http://www.facebook.com/chaosindia','','','','213360536030','1452',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','chaos'),(525,0,0,0,'Naveen Thomas Joseph - Fan Page','','','http://www.facebook.com/naveenthomasmusic','','','','152070521503034','1449',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 