(Special guests)\n','Sandarsh Srivastav @ 09736582563','http://www.facebook.com/ELVISH.MIRAGE','','','','153443698013590','1406',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','elvish-mirage'),(536,0,0,0,'Hollow souls','Hollow Souls is a metal/alternative/blues band from Shimla.Formed in 2009 by its former vocalist and guitarist Tejaswi Lohumi and bassist Jatin Singh. Now headed by Nishant Marwah and Chirag on Vocals and guitar and Varun Dhir on drums.Current Bassist Abhishek Negi and on lead guitar Ashish Yadav.\n\nAshish Yadav and Varun Dhir have kept the Band together and are still keeping it alive by plying at various venues and making new music.','','http://www.facebook.com/hollowsouls','','','','110162388996651','1405',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','hollow-souls'),(537,2,63,63,'Afflatus','AFFLATUS began their inspirational journey in 2004, a journey that has had its share of hurdles, obstacles and constraints though the band has never lost sight of the one thread, one passion, one love that binds them togetherthe love of creating MUSIC.\r\n\r\nFormed by Grace Miller (Vocals), Karen Donoghue (Guitars), Sharon Zadeng (Bass) and Mercy Miller (Drums), Afflatus are made up of experienced musicians in their own right with Mercy, Karen and Sharon having earlier been members of bands and Grace vocalist in her fathers gospel group since she was a child.\r\n\r\nTheir debut performance as Afflatus in 2004 won them a prize and that too at the national level!!! Since then, Afflatus, have come a long way with a debut album in the making, numerous high profile concerts under their belt and the emergence of a truly international sound.\r\n\r\nSays MERCY: Every gig has been a new learning experience for me. Sharing the same stage with different bands, meeting and interacting with different musicians especially drummers has been a real encouragement and I look forward to more.\r\n\r\nSays KAREN: A special moment for me was playing at Mizoram because it was a great gig that was exclusively an Afflatus concert. Moreover, the crowd was great! There was this one scary moment though when I almost got pulled off the stage (almost cried... LOL) but in retrospect, it was an awesome gig.\r\n\r\nSays SHARON: For the first time in my life, performing open air, in the middle of winter made me realize how truly COLD Shillong is. But it was a learning experience and Ive learnt to always have my gloves handy, although Ive lost the gloves I wore that night.\r\n\r\nSays GRACE : Coming home to the Autumn Fest, an annual event in Shillong involved an added bonus of fun when we were invited to play in the finale. The privilege and honour of sharing the stage with Shillongs most renowned musicians made me glow with pride. The pride of gathering together in one place, on one stage doing the one thing I love, cherish and treasure most!\r\n\r\nAfflatus are in the studio working on their first album, keeping their hopes and dreams alive!\r\n\r\nAfflatus is exclusively managed by Keith Wallang for Springboard Surprises.\r\n\r\nContact 09436119961, keith@springboardsurprises.com','springboardbands@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/AfflatusShillong','','','','160516707340525','1396',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-06 02:01:02',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','afflatus'),(538,0,0,0,'Marcelo Ezquiaga','BIO MARCELO EZQUIAGA\n\nMarcelo Ezquiaga es un musico y artista porteo pero viajero,. Inicia\nsu carrera solista con Un Buen pescador (2009). y continua con\nHOMBRE GOLPE (2011) Luego de varios aos al frente de Mi tortuga\nmontreux, formacion con la cual edito \"Mar del Plata en invierno\"\n(2002), \"Mapa\" (2005) y \"Mi Tortuga Montreux\" (2006).\n\nAunque la cancion es la protagonista de su obra, y la letra es parte\nfundamental de lo que quiere contar, su busqueda juega siempre con\nlaexperimentacion sonora en relacion con la cancion. Asi sus discos\nson una exploracion constante e inquieta de los margenes de este\ngenero. Y las letras la forma de decir como ve el mundo que lo rodea.\nLa combinacion de la musica y la letra una forma critica de hacer\narte.\n\nDurante su breve carrera ha girado por los mas destacados escenarios\nporteos como el Personal Fest, el Ciclo Nuevo, Estudio Abierto de\nBuenos Aires, BAFICI, escenarios de verano del Planetario y el Teatro\nND Ateneo (donde se realiz la presentacin oficial de su tercer\ndisco). Participo en compilados como Estudio Abierto. Ademas toco en\nMendoza, Cordoba, Rosario, Tucuman, Santiago del estero, Salta, llevo\nsus canciones al exterior por Uruguay, Chile, y Espaa\nRealizo la musica incidental de dos peliculas, Nadar solo (Ezequiel\nAcua - 2003) y El sueo del perro (Paulo Pecora  2009) ambas\nganadoras de varios premios y menciones.d Mar del Plata\'s Film Festival.','marce.ezquiaga@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/marceloezquiagamusica','','','','288522712483','1394',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','marcelo-ezquiaga'),(539,2,128,128,'The Dirty Strikes','It all started with a bang and now BOOOOOOOOM...and its getting louder and louder...well, the band was formed back in 2010, January 3..the original line up has changed after some months some gig..blah blah blah...and now the band is moving on....with the new materials....blah blah...watever\r\n\r\nRecent performances:\r\n\r\n*17th Sept.2011-The Stage,Manajsa,Huaz Khaz,New Delhi\r\n*23rd Sept.2011-Give music a chance-A house n guitar,New Delhi\r\n*Manipur tour powered by CONE.\r\n*10th Nov\' 2011,Vote 4 Change concert\r\n\r\n\r\nAchievement :\r\n\r\n* Maximum numbers of concert played on the year 2010\r\n* Winner -First Manipur Idol Contest-Imphal-East,2010\r\n* First runner-up at Manipur Rock Fest,2010.\r\n* Released self-title EP-TheDirtyStrikes-2011.\r\n\r\n\r\nFuture plans of the band:\r\n\r\nThe band has been working for their album, and has already fully written and composed an album worth of songs. \r\nHaving enough music in their heads to keep them busy till the end of time.\r\n','Bpin +918014546720','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Dirty-Strikes/101724996544287','','','http://www.reverbnation.com/thedirtystrikes','101724996544287','1394',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-17 12:12:28',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','the-dirty-strikes'),(540,0,0,0,'MPKK (Midival Punditz & Karsh Kale)',' MPKK is a production team formed in 2008 consisting of Gaurav Raina and Tapan Raj of the Delhi electronica duo Midival Punditz and New York based composer producer multi-instrumentalist Karsh Kale.  \nOver the past few years MPKK has specialized in producing and composing original music for films , television as well as their own collaborations including the recent Midival Punditz release \'Hello Hello\' and the upcoming Karsh Kale release \'Cinema\'.  \nMPKK made their debut in 2008 after being commissioned to create a brand new score for the classic 1973 Bruce Lee Epic, \'Enter The Dragon\'. \nThe team has also toured the live performance of this score alongside the film at festivals worldwide.  \nThey came together again in 2009 for the score of \'Ashes\', a film written, directed and starring Ajay Naidu (Office Space, Suburbia) . \nIn 2009 Bollywood came knocking as the trio made their debut as Background Music Composers in the bustling Hindi thriller \'Karthik Calling Karthik\' , starring Farhan Akthar and Deepika Padukone.\nSince then MPKK have expanded their palette to creating original music for theater, as they recently scored \'Circus Of Life\', a musical directed by Academy Award nominated director Shekhar Kapur.  \nThe Trio are poised to bringing cutting edge production and composition to the world of film and music in the years to come.  \n\nFor Further Information:\nwww.facebook.com/karshkalemusic\nwww.karshkale.com\nwww.facebook/midivalpunditz\nwww.punditz.com','Neysa Mendes (neysa.mendes@gmail.com), +91 9821336963','http://www.facebook.com/mpandkk','','','','188178381223667','1386',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','mpkk-midival-punditz-karsh-kale'),(541,0,0,0,'Remember Shakti','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Remember-Shakti/105556352811577','','','','105556352811577','1371',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','remember-shakti'),(543,0,0,0,'Retarded Cop','I am on some kinda mission.','Gaz ','http://www.facebook.com/RETARDEDCOP','','','','162318487143946','1367',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','retarded-cop'),(544,0,0,0,'Bhoomi','Hailing from city of Bangalore, India, Bhoomi was formed in April 2002 quickly rising to prominence in the Indian metal circuit and soon established a rapidly growing fan base all over the country. Arguably one of the most eclectic metal bands around, Bhoomi have since gigged extensively all over India building a reputation as one of the most enthralling live acts to have surfaced from the rising metal scene in the country.\n\nWith their roots firmly entrenched in the classic metal of Judas Priest, Iron Maiden, Queensryche and other seminal hard rock and metal bands of the 80\'s, Bhoomi are arguably one of the finest exponents of pure, melodic metal anyone is likely to find. Using traditional hard rock and metal as their base, Bhoomi stand out from the crowd with their unique incorporation of three way vocal harmonies into their music, which instantly gives them an identity and sound that is all their own. Throw in some classy songwriting and technical prowess into the mix and you have a band that can make you bang your head with pounding riffs and dazzle you with a catchy and superlatively melodic chorus before you get a chance to catch your breath. Another aspect of the band that has further endeared them to their fans is their lyrical stance,which rages against corruption and champions the cause of the common man.\n\nWith more than 200 gigs under their belt since their inception and a fully developed and mature sound, 2010 promises to be the year that puts Bhoomi on the international map with acclaimed grammy nominated producer Neil Kernon (Nevermore, Queensryche) set to work with the band to release their highly anticipated debut album on an unsuspecting world.','Srinivas V T','http://www.facebook.com/metalbhoomi','','','','138717726169011','1365',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','bhoomi-1'),(545,0,0,0,'I Quit','Once upon another time, four friends were sitting in a lawn; they were agitated by the power cut, mosquito bites and Gigs headache.\nSuddenly Tau said I Quit, he was fed up of playing off beats in the band, as they were obsessed with it!\n\nTau, a self taught Haryanavi bassist, always inspire band to make simple note to note music but Sushil being musically illiterate, always makes it a bit  complicated.\nSo Taus words turned out to be the bands name later.\n\nWell talking about I quit, its a punk rock band from Chandigarh, consist of four fucking PIAs\nWho always quit easy ways to do things and get themselves in troubled ways all the time.\nHere they lie, disgracefully:\n\n\n1. Kunal - He is a virtuoso drummer and the Hip of the band. He always wanted to be a singer but people never listened to his crispy, high pitched voice (which he adapted from Blink 182).\nLater he quit singing and became a PIA for all by starting drums. He draws his influence from Blink 182, only. And Utube.\n\n2. Amit aka Tau He began his musical journey with singing, (who doesnt) later he quit singing and picked a guitar (who doesnt), then again he quit guitar. And now hes currently playing Bass (dont know till when?)\nHe shows how strong the band is physically, as he also serves the purpose of a body guard for the members. He hates plectrums and loves drumming (may be one day hell quit bass too).\nHe draws his musical influences from all the metal bands like Metallica, Iron maiden, Clarion!\n\n3. Nikhil He always wished to be a shredder but never wanted to practice scales. so he quit the shredding and got inspired by Billie paaji and became an awesome rhythm guitarist. He never pictured himself to be a singer, but what the hell! Expect the unexpected. \nHe is fantasized by all three chord bands, and other alternate bands like Breaking Benjamin, Yellowcard, All time low, New Found glory.\nHe always support the band by coming late in jam sessions, forgetting lyrics, doing vocal exercise(while band is playing live) lip rolls and all! \n\n\n\nIn every ones life there comes a point when you say I Quit and thats the time when you would be seeking this kind of music.\n\nBands genre comes out to be pretty confusing alternate, punk-pop.\nBand has versatile originals ranging from Punjabi up beat to western off beat!\nWhenever Band Plans to make it big, someone quits it. Band is still finding its directions and its future is still unclear and covered with mist of non-punctuality, low-finance, job headaches, detain classes, lack of supplies. \n\nHOPE ONE DAY BAND WILL QUIT EVERY OBSTACLE AND BECOME A SHINING STAR IN INDIAS GROWING ROCK MUSIC SCENE.\n\nPS- LISTEN TO US, BEFORE WE QUIT!\nAGAIN!\n\n-- Sushil.','','http://www.facebook.com/IQuitTheBand','','','','143792528992612','1364',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','i-quit'),(546,0,0,0,'Sathyajith Fan Club','He started his music life in 1989,when he was just a kid (only 4 and half years). Under the guidance of his music teacher, Mrs. Shriyanthi Siriwardena, he has completed all the grades in both theory and practical (pianoforte) in the western music exams conducted by IWMS, IMSS, and the Government.\n\nHe studied in Nalanda college, Colombo, which contributed immensely for his achievements in Music, as well as for his academic performances.\n\n\n1998,2000,2001 and 2002 - won the piano solo own choice 1st place from negombo center in music festivals Conducted by the institute of music speech and speaking skills which is an institute affiliated to the British federation.\nIt  included 3 gold medals\n\n2003 won the all island prizes in piano solo, organ solo(single key board),junior band(performed piano), and senior band ( played the drums), in the music festival by the same institute.\n\nin the IWMS final grade theory examination, he scored the highest marks from Sri Lanka.\n\n2004 won the best instrumentalist award(performed 3 solos including piano, key board and the guitar) in the competition conducted by Interact clubs, in Kandy.\n\nMeanwhile, since he got selected to the Faculty of Medical Sciences, Sri Jayawardenapura from his A/L results, he couldn\'t complete the diplomas in Music\n\nStarting from the school times, until recently he had played in several bands.  While he was still a student in Nalanda College, he played the key board in a hip hop band called Urbans, from 2001 to 2004. From 2005 to 2006, he played the bass guitar in the well known Metal band, Nemesis.  Then he joined the psychedelic metal/ grunge band, Karmic Sulphur (TNL On stage finalists, 2006), where he played the bass guitar from 2007 to 2009. \n\nWhile contributing to the accomplishments of these bands, he had also done his own creations, to come up as a solo artist. Up to now, he had done several tracks, and music videos, including Oba mage, an experimental tract which was a blend of Rock and funky free style music, released in 2007. The music and the lyrics were by Sathyajith, mixed by Lanthra Perera (Doctor Band) and the video was directed by Skit Digital Videos.  It was played in many media stations and was appreciated by many artists and fans in Sri Lanka and around the world.\n\nhere is the link to Oba Mage video\n\nhttp://www.elakiri.com/forum/downloads.php?do=file&id=1912\n if you haven\'t seen it until now,  please check it and see... \n\nCurrently, he has released his new  music video, the coffee song.  The song is a blend of Baila, which is a quite popular music style in sri lanka, and classical rock which gives a modern taste. It is a special music tract with an original musical concept of Sathyajith, which was written by Sathyajith himself, and mixed by Lanthra Perera.  Video was done by the currently most popular and successful production house, Aryans Films. It has been  quite a new experience for all his fans. \n\nhttp://www.music.lk/download.php?index=4980\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xOAq9KN8PDE\nplease check it and see... ','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Sathyajith-Fan-Club/22086026797','','','','22086026797','1363',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sathyajith-fan-club'),(548,0,0,0,'Colours','COLOURS a pro rock band was born in 2004 with a combinations of Ribhalang, Phalangri and Arwel. The trio somehow manage to get Pynhun who later agreed to sing for the band and this makes the band fully equipped and ready for a performance and tours.\n\nThe COLOURS went onn for 2 years performing all over India and finally decided to have a keyboardist in the band which was later joined by Hubert.\n\nThe COLOURS got its 1st break by performing for a huge crowd who attended the Northeast Youth Fest iin Kolkata in 2005.\n\nIn 2006 Pynhun the vocalist had to leave the band for some personal reasons and the band had a hard time in getting a new vocalist but in short time the emptiness has been blessed and filled by Danny a popular and well experience vocalist who had been with a few well known bands of Shillong who was planning to return back to his hometown from Bangalore where he was involve with popular Bangalore band Dharna.\n\nAs soon as Danny reached Shillong the COLOURS started a jam and he did click so well with everyone and became a permanent member till this very day.\n\nThe Colours is indeed proud to say that Arwell was once upon a time awarded the IIT Best Basses of the Year and Danny as IIT Best Vocalist of the Year. This give the COLOURS  a unique quality especially with the combinations of Ribhalang the drummer who have full control over beats and metronomes. Phalangri the coolest person of COLOURS who give a magical touch in every field of genre with his different series and brands of Guitars like Ibenez, Fender and Kort along with Hubert\'s Rhythms on the Roland keys.\n\nThe COLOURS dream in moving ahead with its project and welcome everyone who wishes to listen and have a good time with the band. All well wishers, corporates, organisers who wishes to have COLOURS on their stage can simply call Hubert @ 09774365406 or email to hubcolours@gmail.com or Lanz @ 09863089460 email to /lanzcolours@gmail.com.\n\nTHANK YOU and COLOURS love u all. ','hubcolours@gmail.com/lanzcolours@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Colours/355531858479','','','','355531858479','1323',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','colours'),(549,0,0,0,'Filter Coffee','Put together some guitar riffs, the sound of a bamboo flute, a tabla and throw in a funky electronic groove, Brew it with some earthly vocals and you get FILTER COFFEE. \n\nElectro-Folk  is when folk music meets electronica.   \nThe bands influences are from Indian classical, Western classical, Jazz to folk music and the compositions range from instrumentals, folk songs to impromptu acts including from vocal percussions to jugalbandhis. \n\nA duo, Swarupa & Shriram have been performing together for more than 5 years & performed at some of the most prestigious festivals in India like Prithvi festival, The Kovalam Literary Fest, The Delhi International Arts festival, Celebrating Unity Festival, Tansen Thyagaraja Festival, India  Pakistan youth forum, The Mysore Dussera Festival, The Kalaghoda festival, World Music Day festival at Alliance etc. \n\nFestivals abroad include The Balispirit festival (Indonesia), Culture day @ The Kuala Lumpur Center. (Malaysia), The 2010 tour of UK and Channel Islands etc.  \n\nThe Members: \n\nShriram Sampath | Bamboo Flute & flutes from around the world/Electronica\n\nOne half of Filter Coffee, Shriram is a disciple of the World-renowned \nFlute Maestro Pundit Ronu Majumdar, Shriram specialises in playing the \nnorth Indian Bansuri. Apart from the Bansuri, he\'s also well versed with \nplaying flutes from different parts of the world. \n\nSome of the woodwinds he plays include Dizi  Chinese flutes, Bamboo \nSaxophone, Metal Flutes, Penny whistle, Didgeridoo, Ney  Egyptian flutes,\n Algoza  the twin flute from Rajasthan, Morchang . Apart from all of this \nShriram also simultaneously handles the electronica bit    \n\nSwarupa Ananth | Tabla, Percussions, Vocals\n \nThe other half of Filter Coffee-  Swarupa, a powerhouse performer,\nIs a disciple of Late Ustad Allarakha & Ustad Zakir Hussain \nhas been learning the tabla for more than 15 years. \n\nA multitalented artiste, with her training deeply rooted in \nIndian Classical music, she plays the tabla, drums, djembe, darbuka, the bagalbaccha and a variety of percussion instruments from \naround the world. \n \nA multi facetted musician Swarupa also is a very good singer. \n\nRajendra Vallury  Guitars \n\nA student of renowned guitarist/composer-arranger Chintoo Singh. What differentiates him from the other guitarist is his ability to play Hindustani classical on the guitar in Gayki (Vocal) style, which is very rare amongst guitarist. His capabilities have been used for the background score of many short films & documentaries. Apart from playing in PRAYAG & a few rock bands, he has been playing with Padmashree Hariharan in his fusion band \'Soul India\' and has toured all over the country & internationally. ','Swarupa - 9820534318 / Shriram - 9819819074','http://www.facebook.com/filtercoffeetheband','','','','92284719361','1320',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','filter-coffee'),(550,0,0,0,'BULL ENGINE','- Winner at SRM University, Ghaziabad\n- Performed At Select City Walk Saket for the Brand Name \'Tissot\' for CWG 2010\n- Performed at Pragati Maidan for Govt. Organization PCRA, Composed the Title track\n- Selected for the Unseen Underground Pub Rock fest 2010\n- Runner up of CRI 2007 Zonal Heats\n- Headlined at Cafe Xtreme, Shillong\n- First runner-up at Global School of Science, (Saket)\n- Winner of Genero 2010 at ABES Ghaziabad\n- Winner of Distortion 2010 at VIPS, New Delhi\n- Runner up of IIM Indore 2011\n- Quarter finalist at Hard Rock Cafe Battle of Bands 2011\n- Performed at Boogaloo Caf, New Delhi\n- Performed at Attitude Cafe, Gurgaon\n- Performed at Chicane pub\n- Performed at Hard Rock Cafe, Hyderabad\n- Performed at Leon\'s Club, Gurgaon\n- Performed at Cafe Morrison, New Delhi\n- Performed at Cafe Oz, New Delhi\n- Performed at Caf Mozart, Gurgaon\n- Performed at Peddlers, Chandigarh\n- Performed at Kyra Theatre, Bangalore\n- Performed at Hard Rock Cafe , Delhi\n- Performed at Torquise Cottage , Delhi for Metalloid\n- Performed at Torquise Cottage, Delhi for Pub Rock Fest 11\n- Performed at  The 567, Delhi for International Music fest\n- Performed at Tryst Music Cafe, Delhi\n- Performed at Blues, Delhi\n- Performed at Hard Rock Cafe, Delhi for Independence Rock\n\nA 1000 HP engine that generates 700 PS of Musical Power. Or better still \"THE GRUNGE DRIVERS. Essentially, a 3 cylinder (member) engine, Ladies and Gentlemen, please welcome..\n\nSonic- Vocals/Guitars  - The headlights, handle bars and the front tyre.\nhttp://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=1218637974\n\nRambo  Drum/Back Vocals  The fuel tank, engine and the gears.\nhttp://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=1466746428\n\nAkshit - Bass Guitar\nhttp://www.facebook.com/#!/profile.php?id=100000443226608\n\n\nThe reason we dont have BREAKS, is because we dont believe in STOPPING!\n\nWondering what is FUEL ? Thats something we get as soon as we climb the stage\n\n\\m/ ( - _ - ) \\m/\n\n\nhttp://www.reverbnation.com/#!/bullengine7\nhttp://signmeto.roadrunnerrecords.com/artists/bull-engine\nhttp://www.myspace.com/bullengine7','+91-9711457107','http://www.facebook.com/BULLENGINE','','','','375442273912','1318',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','bull-engine'),(551,0,0,0,'Urban Soundscape','There is no vibrant and or, interesting story behind the formation and founding of this band. There was, as most bands see, that one miraculous jam that brings them together. Like everything else in life this too was and is still a process and it has taken time and effort on our part to get where ever we are and today, through a continuous struggle, for recognition and more of an effort to find ourselves through the music and the music changing as we slowly discovered how we worked together.\n  \nSome say our music is ambient and some say its loud and other say it doesnt make any sense, well all of this is true; the music that we produce is a living-breathing thing, a person that we build together. Sometimes it looks ken and Barbie the epitome of human perfection (which is a distant dream for us) and most of the time and generally resembling Frankenstein and Dolly Singh. \n\nIn the middle the band went through a rough phase, our drummer, Sarthak Kapoor was forced to leave the band. He was the backbone, in almost every sort of way. For us the band was coming to an end even before it started, our performance graph was one that was steadily rising and with his departure we really thought we were done for. In the interim period before Ruttajeet Mukherjee joined us and we were able to regroup and work, we played with a couple of drummers. One of them told us that the way we made music was very different and very interesting. He told us that, Abeer  the bassist, would bring the skeleton while Saksham, on guitars, would give him his flesh nerves and basic features, and Sahej, through his dynamic vocal range would give him thoughts and a voice so he can scream and profess his love for all the decadent things in life and all the lewd and crude things we indulge in so freely. The drummer the last addition to the mix would give him locomotion, freedom of his arms and legs to roam and see the world so he can have an opinion, so he can learn to dance and walk around and run away from home to join the circus. Ruttajeet, or who is better known as reet, does just that.\nWe dont believe in the classic verse- chorus- verse song structure, we make music, and the world is our canvas. Our sound is our sound in every sort of way, we make it and we break it. \nThe deal for us is very simple and here I want to be as honest with you as I can. The music scene in India is very small and the number of people who actually get up and come for the shows are very small, and to become renown is very tough. The opportunity for upward mobility is very small and often studded with obstacles, which most bands cant over come. We the soundscape dont care very much for upward mobility and the obstructs to progress, what we care about is making our little place where ever we are in the social ladder and if people like us well and good if not then there is little one can do about it. The only thing is we want something to motivate us and push us and that till now has been our sound and I guess always will be, the opportunity to build upon and change it, strip it down and recast it and make it look like our perception of the world, is something that drives us. What we would call, true artistic aspirations.\n\nWe have reached the finals in a couple competitions and won one. But that doesnt matter. It really doesnt matter how many articles have been published and how many times weve come in the newspaper. It really doesnt matter how many likes we have on Facebook what matters at the end of the day, that you who would have read this and gone through this slightly confusing piece would listen to our song and like it. \n\n\n \"You, me and \'us\' is all that is all to the world. We are very much part of the world and so are you, together we are us. The sound is slightly louder and slightly softer, the range that is beyond a genre but we try. Welcome to the Soundscape.\"\n\n\n\n','Abeer Kapoor +919811078296 Sahej Bhatia  +919910527906','http://www.facebook.com/urbansoundscape','','','','313575812894','1318',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','urban-soundscape'),(552,0,0,0,'Treble','Just after Aseem ( Vocalist) and Raghav ( Lead Guitarist) finished with their S.S.C. board exams, they began their journey in Indian Music. Initially, they started with Sufi Rock as their genre. After performing at several events such as IIT Powais Mood Indigo, Battle of Bands etc. at a point they realized that they were not finding the right way to move ahead with their band called Infiniti. It lead to a break-up of their band. Very soon, Aseem found different set of people with similar ideas of creating Sufi numbers. He joined a band called Qafia. But, over a period of time he was really bugged off with that as well..He left the band. Raghav, at the same time was totally out of the scene, concentrating on his academics. \n        On the contrary, Aneeket Kate (Drums) and Ishan Oka (Bassist) were jamming up with their band Aardra,a hindi alternative project .Both of them met Aseem at IIT Powais Mood Indigo.According to Aneeket Kate,it was stated that Aardra had reached its limit and was slowly breaking up.After Mood Indigo they (Aardra) did their last show at a fest in Kothrud,Pune (KHS Fest).\nOur rhythm guitarist Manas Mali,while completing his B.Cs in M.I.T college used to play the guitar as a hobby.\nLater on it became his passion.His dedication towards the guitar paid him off when he got a chance to record for several FTII projects as a guest artist.He joined a band called Maqlukh and performed with them at IIT Powais Mood Indigo.\nUltimately,all five of us with the same ideology to create music in a very different way formed the band called Treble. \nSo here we are to enthrall you guys with our mixed bag of English Alternative music.\nKEEP UP THE TREBLE!!! \\m/','+919763636362','http://www.facebook.com/thebandtreble','','','','111627968882619','1316',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','treble'),(553,0,0,0,'Funk The System.','The love for playing some really funky grooves, wrestling, and slap bass brought 4 friends together to form this band. With no intentions of pursuing the venture full time, the quartet set out to play a couple of random competitions at a mall which they eventually won. Since then Funk the System has dominated the College Circuit with their energetic performances and massive stage presence. \n\nAchievements-\nJuly\'10-Youthopia Battle Of The Bands Finalists.\nDecember\'10-Blitzkrieg,KC College,Churchgate(Winners).\nDecember\'10-MMK College Finalists.\nDecember\'10-Headlined the Band-Event at Brouhaha, Sydneham.\nDecember\'10-High Voltage, Ruia College(Winners).\nJanuary\'11-Headlined the Band-Event at Impressions,VES College, Chembur.\nJanuary\'11-Sympulse\'11,Symbiosis,Pune(Runners-Up).\nJanuary\'11-SIESONS, SIES Nerul(Winners).\nJanuary\'11-Manzar,UDCT College,Matunga(Winners).\nJanuary\'11-Vividh,NM Law College,Andheri(Runners-Up).\nJanuary\'11-Pratibimbh,Vjti College,Matunga(Runners-Up).\nJanuary\'11-Spore,Jaondhale College,Dombivali(Winners).\nFebruary\'11-KEM College,Parel(Winners).\nMarch\'11-Sattva,Mukesh Patel College Of Engineering,Andheri(Runners-Up).\nMarch\'11-Akarsh,Bhartiya Vidyapeeth,Kharghar(Winners).\nMarch\'11-Fusion,Vasant Dada Patil College,Sion(Winners).\nWin Best Vocalist,Best Guitarist,Best Bassy,Best Drummer.\nMarch\'11-Zephyr,Lokmanya Tilak College,Koparkhairane(Winners).\nApril\'11-Shah And Anchor(Winners).\nApril\'11-RGIT(Winners).\nApril\'11-EOS,IIT Pace(Winners).\nJuly\'11-Win Best Bass Player at Yamaha Asian Beats 2011.\nAugust\'11-Headlined Wilson College\'s Fest Adorea 2011.\nOctober11-Headlined RAIT Colleges Fest Rock RAIT 2011.\n\nFunk The System performed at The Indian Ink Tattoo Convention-Indias 1st Tattoo Convention at WTC.\n\nFunk The System performed at God Gave Rock n Roll to You along with Devoid,Split and Albatross.\n\nFunk The System performed at Soul Alive,the Album Launch by Para Vayu.\n','Nikhil Warrier +91 9930112805','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Funk-The-System/191604637551829','','','','191604637551829','1315',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','funk-the-system'),(554,0,2,2,'Cobbled Street','Cobbled Street was formed on 11 May 2010 by the three singers of the group, who came together after meeting at Artistes Unlimited, New Delhi.\r\n\r\nThe idea was essentially to form an A capella group, however a consensus was reached to experiment with different kinds of sound without actually limiting ourselves to one particular genre.\r\n\r\nGathering influences from varied genres, essentially we believe we sound Jazz+Funk (NOT JAZZ, for those who ask where the Jazz in our music is!). Our music is the result of experimentation and our lyrics are derived from realistic experiences and social issues, among other things.\r\n\r\nHaving a unique line up consisting of a guitarist who pretty much exploits his processor and then an acoustic guitarist who uses nothing more than a delay on his sound; three dedicated vocalists almost always in harmony; a drummer and bass player who make life very difficult for the others with complex grooves; all of this is a challenge we all really love, and that is what creates the Cobbled Street sound!','cobbled.street10@gmail.com','https://www.facebook.com/cobbledstreet/','','','http://www.reverbnation.com/cobbledstreet','0','1311',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','cobbled-street'),(555,5,104,104,'Kini Rao','With rhythm in her soul, funk in her attitude, Kini has been steadily creating waves in the house music scene in India. \r\n\r\nStarting off as resident DJ at Poison Hyderabad, Kini rose through the ranks to open for massive headline acts such as dOP, Dale Anderson & Anil Chawla (Global Underground), Djuma Soundsystem, James Harcourt (Twisted Frequency) and Jody Wisternoff (Way Out West). Her popularity continues to grow- performing at festivals such as GO: Madras as well as opening the party at India\'s biggest electronic music event - Sunburn in Goa.\r\n\r\nHer passion for a deeper sound was showcased on a regular basis at Zenzi Mills (Bombay). Her other notable gigs include an after hours set at Bar25 (Berlin), Villians Club & Oakroom (Copenhagen) & Public Life (London). She is currently a resident DJ and an artist programmer at F Bar Mumbai, a brand extension of international lifestyle channel Fashion TV. \r\n\r\nDoing complete justice to her cheeky self, Kini\'s sound can best be described as an ambivalent mlange of distorted kicks, crispy hats, funky basslines & quirky melodies.\r\n\r\nWith four releases already under her belt on respected labels such as Maktub and Whose Haus and more to come, Kini is quickly becoming a force to be reckoned with.','Sohail Arora +919820546976 ','http://www.facebook.com/kinirao','http://www.twitter.com/kinirao ','http://www.soundcloud.com/kinirao ','','0','1300',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-06 22:46:34',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','kini-rao'),(556,0,0,0,'The Dhas Brothers','Vije, formerly bass guitarist of Hi Octane, Whirlwind, and Stigmata,\nis currently exploring the possibility of\nestablishing a concert circuit through India\nand the possibility of its extension\nto the Middle East,\nSouth East Asia,\nand more.\n \nArjun, formerly guitarist and backing vocalist\nfor Tantrum and Sword Of The Spirit,\nis moving deeper into research and experimentation\non the use of music as a mode of communication\nand perceptual modification.\n \n\nVije and Arjun\nare the Great Great Grandsons of\nthe famous Arulanantham Vaathiar of Nagercovil in South India;\n\nThey are the Great Grandsons of\nArulanantham William Dhas and Rose Kani Rajammal Dhas\nwho established Beth El Estate in Melsiripura\noff Kurunegala in the North Central Province of Sri Lanka;\n\nThey are the Grandsons of\nArnold Harisson Dhas, a successful businessperson\nin Colombo, Sri Lanka,\nand Mabel Ruby Suganthawathie Dhas;\n\nThey are  the Children of\nNirmalan Dhas\none of the first professionally practicing psychological counsellors in Sri Lanka,\nconsultant Human Resource Development Trainer,\nSpecialist in Organisation Development,\nthe only professionally practicing psychosynthetist in South Asia,\nand one of the founders of\nThe Foundation for Civilizational Transformation and Conscious Evolution,\nThe Synthetist Mission, The New World Movement\nand of AdvaitaLoka, one of the few available portals that leads from the dual (Dvaita)\nto the non dual (Advaita) world;\nand Pushpalatha Dhas,\na fashion designer for the past thirty five years and\nfounder of PushpasPlace, a leisure lounge and creative centre that has no peer.\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Dhas-Brothers/125644610820146','','','','125644610820146','1298',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-dhas-brothers'),(557,0,0,0,'DOWN Syndrome','Down Syndrome was formed in 2009.....the members of down syndrome comes from different band....mingled up and formed for sumthing good and heavier.\n\nwithin a short period Down Syndrome gained many fame and was recognised as the pioneer of bangla metalcore....and progressive.','+919832334111,  +919733411233','http://www.facebook.com/pages/DOWN-Syndrome/142639009104220','','','','142639009104220','1288',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','down-syndrome'),(558,0,0,0,'Blood Meridian','Blood Meridian was formed by Aurko (Guitars) and Bhaskar (Vocals) in early 2009 and were soon joined by a close friend Anuj (Guitars) who shared a love for extreme. Unable to find a drummer the band started gigging with a drum machine and stand in bass player Abhishake.\n\nThe search for a live drummer ended when Pushkar (Drums) joined the band in 2010 at the same time the band recruited Ashwin (Bass) as a full time member and completed the line-up.. The band immediately got down to writing material and hit the studios in the month of August to start working on their debut EP titled \'Elements Of Brutality\'. \n\n','','http://www.facebook.com/bloodmeridian','','','','113640278667784','1287',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','blood-meridian'),(559,0,0,0,'Imphal Talkies','Pull The Trigger, the Music will start.','9911811139(delhi)','http://www.facebook.com/imphaltalkies','','','','203775598273','1276',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','imphal-talkies'),(560,0,0,0,'Soul\'d Out','Soul\'d Out was formed in the summer of 2011. However, the idea for the band had been floating around in some of the members\' heads for quite a while. 4 of it\'s members -  Rohit, Bhaanu, Abhay  and Abhijit -  had been jamming occasionally before that, being students of the same college, so the band had no problem starting things off with a bang!\nEach member of the band has a very special relationship with music. Their love for the art is quite extraordinary.\nWith influences ranging over different genres of music, Soul\'d Out quite naturally has a very interesting sound, and the members aren\'t really concerned about how that sound can be defined/categorised. All that matters to them is that they have fun playing, which eventually spreads contagiously into the crowd! Whether you\'re in the mood to bust a move, or just chill out with some friends over a few beers, this band can certainly leave you satisfied!','','http://www.facebook.com/sodelhi','','','','262825237077116','1276',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sould-out'),(561,0,0,0,'Washed Clothes','','','http://www.facebook.com/Washedclothes','','','','22196384185','1273',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','washed-clothes'),(562,0,0,0,'ADAMANTIUM','(Hit \"Read More\" to read Individual Bio\'s)\n\nSean Littlejohn came across Roxanne Rodriguez at their high school, Carver, and instantly noticed her singing ability. They decided to write songs together and get a closer relationship with their \nmusic. Keenen Martin and Alex Reyes(in another band at the time) joined Roxanne and Sean and became more serious about their dreams for a music career. Amethyst(band name at the time) brought in Ricky Vasquez to be the drummer to complete the music group. Ricky gave them a solid foundation, but it wasn\'t for him. The group went months without a drummer, until Irving Lira stepped in. ADAMANTIUM is now growing musically and is more serious than ever about thier music. They try their best to reach out to all crowds and hopes to live the Rock Star life some day.\n\nAlex King (Lead Guitar)-\nI grew up in a traditional Mexican American household. i have two sisters and i am the youngest out of the two. i have been around music my whole life because my sister were dancers n they always had music flowing in the house. when they practiced i listened to spanish music, hip hop, R&B, and occasionally rock. but it wasnt until 8th grade that i started to listen to rock and of course the first band i ever listen to was METALLICA!!!!!!!!!!!!....... it was then that my eyes where open to the enormous pounding drums, the face melting guitars n bass, and the grungy piercing vocals that drew me in. after that i wanted to learn how to play music and the following year i did. In 9th grade i was enrolled into G.W. Carver High school. this is where my love for music grew enormously and the fire that is my passion was lit. i learned how to play guitar while attending Carver and i have never put it down since then. it took me about six months to get the basics down, like chords and chord changes and rhythms. Nowadays i listen to everything ranging from Rock to hip hop to all types of music.....some of my favorite bands are Trivium, KSE, Alterbridge and Breaking Benjamin to name a few. Some of my Influences Would be Mark Tremonti (The MACHINE!!!!!!), Matt Heafy, Jim Root, Synester Gates, Carlos Santanna and Michael Angelo Batio. I have more people that influence me but it will take me awhile to put them all down. But yea this is my short bio and a quick look into the kind of musician i am....and if you have any question to ask me feel free to ask i do not mind at all. until next time guys and hopefully i see yall out on the road\nPEACE!!  \n\nKeenen[K-mart] Martin (Bass)-\nI was always a smart kid, but ever since the sixth grade I\'ve been kinda slack. Games were my original passion until freshman year of high school. A friend of mine, \"the Fatboi\', needed a bass player, and I haven\'t left \"The Low End\" since. I\'ve always played with Alejandro, first with\'the Fatboi\', then with the Sean and Rox.  Irv, aka \"El Sabor\" Lira came along and cemented the deal. badass drums, in-your-head, melodic riffage, and guitar solos. What more could I want? The people who shaped the way I feel out the bass are Mike McCullough, Arif Mirabdolbaghi, Gustavo Dal Farra, Mike D\'Antonio, Ryan Martinie, and a long list of other great guys on the ass end of the sonic palette. I\'ll listen to anything, but I prefer music with real instruments. Hit me up if you feel like chatting, gaming, or just jamming. I\'m always down to jam. To the top of the world, and back!','Suzanne Penley: 713-592-8282','http://www.facebook.com/pages/ADAMANTIUM/161110086418','','','','161110086418','1268',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','adamantium'),(563,0,0,0,'Dark Desolation','We dig into gruesome  and raw genre black  to give the misanthropic sickest feel till your ears fuckin bleed you to demise. Dark Desolation also was featured in Metal Hammer.','http://www.facebook.com/ajaya.bhat','http://www.facebook.com/dark666desolation','','','','139348382754629','1265',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dark-desolation'),(564,0,0,0,'Rampazze','Rampazze is a Delhi based band that was formed by songwriter/lead guitarist Abhishek Boro & bassist Joshringdao Phonglo over a bottle of whisky and a case of beer in the fall of 2006. There were many line-up changes and several vocalists and headaches later.Rampazze sticks to their bluesy roots while delivering their music in an edgier fashion.\n\nThey\'ve been classified by some as glam/classic rock/blues but their sound is their own and the Rampazze experience is a electrifying, high energy act out to rapture rock music lovers. With their impressive, groovy and interesting riffs; wild stage histronics; and their tongue-in-cheek lyrics they are bound to rip the stage apart and blow you off. The recently released a 5 songs EP called \"Cheap Liquor... Wicked Hangover\" featuring their widely wlel recieved original songs including \"Lady Killer\", \"Roll with me, Mama\", \"Son of a Gun\", \"Cheap Liquor... Wicker Hangover and \"Feel the Heat\".\n\nRampazze opened for the Finland band \'Poets of the Fall\' at IIT Kanpur in 2007 and have performed at various other top notch shows including June Rock Out (JRO) in Chennai, Underground Pub Fest, Fete De La Musique, Kryptonite (Jamia Milia - headlining act), Independance Rock XXIII Delhi Finalists, Campus Rock Idols, SPA (Delhi), BITS Pilani and Jack Daniel\'s Indian Rock Music Awards just to name a few where they have won many accolades as the best band, best original composition,st band, best original composition, best guitarist, best vocalist, best drummer, best bassist (all included!).','','http://www.facebook.com/rampazze','','','','110584182320967','1260',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rampazze'),(565,0,2,2,'Whirling Kalapas','Whirling Kalapas is the acoustic(ish) side project of Mahesh Tinaikar and Uday Benegalguitar player and singer of Indus Creed, respectively. \r\n\r\nKenneth Rebello, Sankarshan \'Shanky\' Kini and Ashwin Andrew complete the band. \r\n\r\nZubin Balaporia, also ex- of Indus Creed, sometimes whirls wid da boyz and dey be really happy when he do.\r\n\r\nTheir music is a whimsical take on a bunch of thingsnew songs, past hits, obscure covers and then some...\r\n\r\nContrary to the belief of some, kalapas are not testicles. But you\'re free to call yours that if you want.','Benny Udaygal: uday@udaybenegal.com','http://www.facebook.com/whirlingkalapas','http://myspace.com/whirlingkalapas','','','0','1259',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','whirling-kalapas'),(566,0,0,0,'Ninaad','Formed in the year 2008 in the easternmost corner of the\ncountry(Dibrugarh, Assam) this five-piece psychedelic\nprog(experimental) outfit has been active in the North-East rock scene\nsince its inception. Their sound can be best described as an\namalgamation of various styles of music particularly progressive rock,\nmetal, psychedelic and the blues.','+919864904834','http://www.facebook.com/NINAADPRODUCTION','','','','153240281370542','1256',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ninaad'),(567,0,0,0,'Night Wings III','','+91-9636599105','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Night-Wings-III/145605518811902','','','','145605518811902','1252',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','night-wings-iii'),(568,0,0,0,'Sulk Station','http://www.sulkstation.com','sulkstation@gmail.com // +919739441029','http://www.facebook.com/sulkstation','','','','118401367565','1249',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sulk-station'),(569,0,1,1,'DJ AmoGH','What Amogh Says about him:\n\nHey, this is my homepage, so I have to say something about myself. Sometimes it is hard to introduce yourself because you know yourself so well that you do not know where to start with. Let me give a try to see what kind of image you have about me through my self-description. I hope that my impression about myself and your impression about me are not so different. It is more challenging to write a page about oneself than it seems at first. People tend to say some peculiar things when they describe themselves or their lives; some try too hard, some make fools out of themselves. I will try my best not to make the same mistakes, however, also remember that reading this is voluntary. So here it goes: \n\nIve been a busy chappy as of late though work load is creeping up again, along with socializing, driving, dancing, music and majorly sleeping.\n\n\"Call me Amogh. Some years ago--never mind how long precisely, nothing particular to interest me on shore, I thought I would sail about a little and see the watery part of the world.\" Since the quote, ever so perfectly, captures my state of mind while having left my home country and exploring the New World, I decided to have it as the opening sentence on my profile. I have been told that I have a colorful personality and perhaps that is why my friends have given me more nicknames. Each nickname has its own saga to go with it. However, for those who are not familiar with the stories, \"Amogh\" works fine.\n\nForemost, I would consider myself a very modest person. Nevertheless, if I would absolutely have to promote myself, which certainly should be the case when writing ones own profile, I could borrow some of the adjectives that my friends have used when describing me: \"friendly, ambitious, unique, fun, lovable, crazy, frank, honest among some others. O, and did I already mention \"sexy?.\n\nI would like to pay tribute to all the wonderful friends that I have around me. I share many incredible memories with these friends and I am looking forward to many more adventures, as I will be preparing myself for the adventurous life that is lying ahead of me. My friends are one of the most important aspects of my life and I try treating every single one of them accordingly. \"Treat others the way you want to be treated\" - my motto. I wish that more people lived by my motto.\n\nI am a person who is positive about every aspect of life. There are many things I like to do, to see, and to experience. I like to read, I like to write; I like to think, I like to dream; I like to talk, I like to listen. I like to see the sunrise in the morning, I like to see the moonlight at night; I like to feel the music flowing on my face, I like to smell the wind coming from the ocean. I like to look at the clouds in the sky with a blank mind, I like to do thought experiment when I cannot sleep in the middle of the night. I like flowers in spring, rain in summer, leaves in autumn, and snow in winter. I like to sleep early, I like to get up late; I like to be alone, I like to be surrounded by people. I like countrys peace, I like metropolis noise; I like the beautiful oceans while flying. I like delicious food and comfortable shoes; I like good books and romantic movies.I like Rock Music, I like remix songs I like the land and the nature, I like people. And, I like to laugh. Sometimes I like to be romantic and keep staring at the rainbow, smelling the first rain and listening to rain drops. I like the sound of guitar strings when its played in silence.\n\nMy goal of life is to try experience all the wildest things in life (defining \"wild\" is up to you) and never look back or regret about anything. I like to dream a lot and challenge myself to fulfill them. I always wanted to be an Disc Jockey for its passion and hard-work which helps earn self-respect. I also dreamed of going crazy on the road and driving fast as I can. I like to make my parents proud. I want to walk on the footsteps of persons who have immense desire and courage to change this world. Of course, I am nowhere close to these people, yet. I am just someone who likes to help people with care and gentle smile, some love, and some care. But my dreams are still alive.','James P.','http://www.facebook.com/djamogh.official','','','','137707096325430','1247',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-amogh'),(570,0,0,0,'Santhanam Srinivasan Iyer (E.P.R)','','','http://www.facebook.com/epr7a','','','','135602726502109','1245',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','santhanam-srinivasan-iyer-epr'),(571,0,0,0,'Orbitual','','orbitualofficial@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/orbitualofficial','','','','244987482194493','1243',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','orbitual'),(572,0,0,0,'Safar','Safar is an alternative rock band from Mumbai, India.\r\nSafar\'s music captures the spirit of timeless Indian folk, blended with an urban pop/rock flavor. Their foot-tapping, yet introspective melodies will put a smile on your face and transport you into a better world. The essence of Safar is their ability to project their journey through life through the universal language of music.','Ryan Medeira +91 9820189159','http://www.facebook.com/SAFARmusic','','','','12099733194','1239',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','safar'),(573,0,0,0,'Rhythm Of Time','','','http://www.facebook.com/rhythmoftime','','','','163024870428947','1230',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rhythm-of-time'),(574,0,0,0,'Jehovah','Jehovah is undoubtedly one of the freshest and the most unique metal acts to hail in a long time. Blending a vast spectrum of genres and incorporating them in prcised structures, the band has developed an organic, yet heavy as nails sound enhanced by worldly melodies and harmonies, which is a rare breed. Primarily, the bands musical direction could be categorized under Groove/Deathcore Metal. Jehovah has had many notable wins to its name including the prestigious Avalanche (NSIT) and has also shared stage with a major international act  Viatrophy (UK). Besides the pub gigs at venues like Caf Morrison and Turquoise Cottage, the band has been actively contributing to the writing process and is on its way to producing material for an upcoming EP! Gathering vast audiences in a very short span of time, Jehovah is on a roll, playing the most extreme yet true to the soul music which really defines their attitude towards music. \n\nAccomplishments\n\nCompetitions \n\n	Channel [V] Launchpad, North-Zone Finalists \n	Avalanche (NSIT), Winners \n        IIM  Ahmedabad, Winners\n        Pulse (AIIMS) 2011, Winners \n	Campus Law Center, Winners \n	Jamia Hamdard (Pharma), Winners \n	Thunderstruck 2012, winners\n        Woodstock (SRCC), Runners-up \n	IIFT 2010, Runners-up \n	Nerdz (Jamia Hamdard), Runners-up \n	IIT  Roorkee, Runners-up \n	Faculty of Law, Runners-up \n\nPub Gigs \n	Caf Morrison \n	Turquoise Cottage\n        567\n\nFeatured on Metal Assault (Los Angeles, California) episode-8. Joining the ranks of the only other Indian bands featured on it  Slain, Exhumation, Undying Inc., Scribe, Demonic Ressurection.\n\n\nInternet Presence\n\nFacebook - https://www.facebook.com/JehovahIndia\nSoundcloud - http://soundcloud.com/JehovahIndia\n\n\nVideos\n\nMoments Away, Cafe Morrison\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LGcAXBf4Rsg\n\nLeash, Cafe Morrison\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LphPJvpsj20&feature=share\n\nLeash, NSIT\nhttp://www.facebook.com/video/video.php?v=1889369472218\n\nEchoes in my Head, Turquoise Cottage\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zUCV_fcd-5M&feature=related\n','','http://www.facebook.com/JehovahIndia','','','','138413282862687','1228',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','jehovah'),(575,0,0,0,'Spud In The Box','A fresh-on-the-scene band from Mumbai, \'Spud in the Box\' is an act founded by Ankit Dayal and Rohan Rajadhyaksha, around March 2011. \n\nThe duo started small by playing early sets at Blue Frog, but soon saw the need to expand the sound; enter drummer Vivaan Kapoor and bassist Zubin Bhathena. \n\nWith guitar duties split between Siddharth Talwar and Hartej Sawhney, Spud in the Box was good to go. \n\nSo far, the band has performed at the Revival of the Bandstand festival on two occasions, at the Blue Frog alongside Ankur Tewari and The Ghalat Family, at Live From The Console alongside Peter Cat Recording Co., Celebrate Bandra festival...\n\nIn August 2011, the band took part in the St.Xavier\'s College\'s fest, Malhar, and stood 1st in the band event. Vivaan Kapoor and Ankit Dayal were awarded the best drummer and best vocalist respectively as well.\nIn the same month, they went on to the Sophia\'s College fest, Kaleidoscope, placing 1st in the band event here as well.\n\nAs far as sound goes, the band does not wish to be limited to any genre, freely experimenting with jazz, blues, pop, folk, alt rock, progressive, classical (Western and Indian), and so on; while covering artists from any and every field of music. Developing a unique sound is the law of the land as far as Spud in the Box is concerned.\n\n\n\nCheck out their recorded singles here!\nhttp://www.reverbnation.com/spudinthebox','Shreya Naik, spudinthebox@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/spudintheboxmusic','','','','158976690842218','1227',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','spud-in-the-box'),(576,0,0,0,'WarTorN','','Ninad Ingulkar: +919823192483','http://www.facebook.com/wartorn.india','','','','102231603175591','1224',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','wartorn'),(577,0,0,0,'Sceptre-India','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Sceptre-India/111032555614752','','','','111032555614752','1222',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sceptre-india'),(578,0,0,0,'Erased UnDEAD','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Erased-UnDEAD/124101954305867','','','','124101954305867','1222',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','erased-undead'),(579,0,0,0,'Rohit Shakya','Rohit Shakya is a freelancing Music Producer/singer/session artist in his early 20\'s based in Kathmandu,Nepal.His credits include  Astha Tamang Maskey, JINDABAAD, Looza: and many other mainstream as well as underground names.He is Currently producing JINDABAAD\'s upcoming EP and is also  involved in a synth/sub-pop duo with Astha Tamang Maskey which has yet to be named.\nHe is also producing as well as directing music videos for artist such as Astha Tamang Maskey,JINDABAAD,Hari Maharjan Project, Upendra lal Singh.\nHe is working as a session engineer/producer/session player at REC studio.\nHis session  career is linked with names such as Sabin Rai,The Uglyz,The Shadows,Dibya Subba,MT.8848.\nHe is also part of an Artist Mangement and Welfare NGO named \"KALAKUTI\".\n \n','','http://www.facebook.com/Rohitshakya.fuzz','','','','88383423842','1221',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rohit-shakya'),(580,0,0,0,'Reji','Reji Ravindran (a.k.a rayG) has a musical experience which has spanned for nearly 15 years now. Born in Mumbai, Reji was bitten by the music bug during the mid-90s. After collecting loads of music cassettes, CDs & vinyl in his youth, in 1998 he decided to give DJing a shot by learning from veteran DJ, Jo Azaredo. Since that year, there has been no stopping for this multifaceted wizard as today, Reji is one of the most prolific names in Mumbai\'s booming alternative & electronic music scene.\r\n\r\nFor the longest time in his career, Reji has been recognized as an educator within the music fraternity. After understanding India\'s unique music scene in the early 2000s, the DJ professor designed & implemented his own syllabus at some of the best DJ schools in the city; training more than 500 men & women in the art of DJing, turntablism & music production. By putting his mouth where the money is, Reji has been a successful battle DJ by winning the DMC Champion (Pune - 2000), Times War of the DJs winner (Mumbai - 2007) & Kingfisher Ultra DJ (2010) titles through the years. Reji was the first ever turntablist in an Indian nu-age metal band called Scag and also the brains behind India\'s earliest hip hop collective called \"itch\". In December 2008, world renowned travel magazine, Time Out Mumbai, mentioned him as one of Mumbai\'s most influential DJs\" in its cover article. Reji has also been promoting fresh talent & sounds through his DIY One Sunday nights (2008-2009) & through his current role as a label DJ/promoter/talent scout for Air Snare Records.\r\n\r\nrayG is an alternative side project (read alter ego) of Reji Ravindran. Under this moniker he is known for dishing out a whole different spectrum of music where he fuses his turntablism skills with eclectic beats & breaks (irrespective to tempos, genres & styles). His vast knowledge & interesting music selections have got him gig bookings within India\'s elite music, art & fashion circles. This also helped him clinch the resident DJ title at Mumbai\'s hippest nightspot, Bonobo, since early 2011. By always keeping an emphasis on quality music with longer shelf life (minus short term crass commercial appeal), you can always expect Reji to dish out an unpredictable blend of indie, reggae, rock, dub, dance hall, funk, soul, breaks, disco, baltimore, classic house/prog house/tribal house/techno, hip hop, electro, drum n bass/jungle, swing, retro, dub step, mash ups & much more.... ','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Reji/45751202984','','','','45751202984','1214',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','reji'),(581,0,0,0,'Radial Dispersion - The Band','Radial Dispersion, a 6-member ensemble of young musicians from Mumbai, consists of Anupam, Aditya, Akshay, Naval, Prashin and Shabarish. It all started on a building terrace where Anupam and Akshay brought their flute and tabla to jam for their own amusement. A couple of weeks later, they drew the foundation of a band, coming together for a project called 10th Bass which after a few gigs and lineup changes evolved into Radial Dispersion.\nFormed just before the summer gig season of 2010, we fevicoled our ideas to bring  our music out. We believe in the concept of music having no boundaries, so genre has never been our limitation. This is the very thought that binds us together and brings musicians like us from diverse backgrounds ranging from Indian Classical to Funk & Blues to Rock. \n\n\"Naval\" tries to incorporate everything he listens to in his playin style,the outcome resulting in solos and catchy riffs that tend to keep ringing in your mind.He also eats for the band:D\n\n\"Prashin\", the latest addition to the band, brings his western influences into the band\'s music and always wants to keep moving around his groovy bass lines.\n\n\"Aditya\" with his sound support provides us rhythm and backing harmony vocals He is one of the craziest members on stage and the chocolate boy of the band.\n\n\"Akshay\", the saint in disguise having learned the tabla for quite a few years picked up the drums & has retained his style of playing but now with two sticks.\n \n\"Shabarish\", a thorough Carnatic percussionist who decided to venture into fusion has beautifully stitched himself into the band. He along with his different sounds of percussion gives the band a unique touch and brings the aura to each song.\n\n\"Anupam\", our vocalist, is a versatile musician, passionate about music irrespective of which instrument it is, elevates the band with his mesmerizing flute melodies and vocals.\n\nCall us Radial Dispersion. Keep dispering music fellas !','radialdispersion@gmail.com, prashin.jagger@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/radialdispersion','','','','253595859511','1214',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','radial-dispersion-the-band'),(582,0,0,0,'Dhruv Ghanekar','TO BUY DHRUV\'S ALBUM OR TO DOWNLOAD IT ONLINE VISIT THE BLUE FROG MUSIC STORE.\n\nwww.musicstore.bluefrogsounds.com\n\nDhruv Ghanekar began studying Indian classical music at the age of nine. His love with the guitar began while still in school and in a few years he founded Chakraview, a rock band.\n\n1996 saw the end of Chakraview, and the beginning of his working relationship with Ashutosh Phatak. Dhruv & Ashu co-founded Smoke Studios and begun an extremely successful career at music-makers for ad films and alternative movies, with over 3000 projects delivered to date.\n\nDhruv continued to study music, and learned under the great sarangi exponent Sultan Khan. In 1997, Dhruvs desire for a more formal education in music, mainly jazz, led him to the Musicians Institute in California and the Berklee College of Music.\n\n\'Distance\' is Dhruv\'s debut as a solo artist. This fusion/world effort will set precedents for all World Artists emerging from the continent. With virtuoso arrangements, peaceful orchestration and an ability to bridge Jazz and contemporary Indian sounds, Dhruv is a complete guitarist, musician and song-writer. We think so.','carmelita@wahwahmusic.in','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Dhruv-Ghanekar/10884592294','','','','10884592294','1207',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dhruv-ghanekar'),(583,0,0,0,'Orator','Orator was formed in the year 2008 AD after tearing apart the demiurgic womb of Barzak.Rejecting the foul prayers of the filthy demiurge and being inspired by their Ancestors who were mostly Kapalikas and Aghoris, the orators have taken up their trishuls to preach the ancient tantric doctrines.Uttering ominous creeds they have chosen this path of liberation and to indoctrinate the hylic mortals with the gnosis of immortality.To some extent Orator also preaches the hidden black gnosis of Qliphoth, keeping it within the limitations of secrecy.\n','crematoration@yahoo.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Orator/320273501690','','','','320273501690','1206',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','orator'),(584,0,0,0,'Atmosfear','Atmosfear is a 3 piece Death Metal act from Mumbai India. The band has been around since 2006 / 07. The band was formed by Ulhas, Bruce and Frank and later joined in by Mayank and Shezan. They started generating a good following by playing live in a lot of college events and competitions. They formed the band with one single vision in mind, to play extreme death metal music. In 2007 Shezan and Frank left the band, one citing musical differences and the other being busy with his other band. During this time Vincent \"The Beast\" Periera joined them on bass, and the band started playing club / pub events.       \n\nOn 22nd Oct-07, Vince passed away cause of a severe asthma attack. It was a major blow to the band. The song Visions Of The Dead was changed by Bruce over to Visions Of The Beast as a tribute to Vince. Frank came back on the bass for few shows as the band was unable to find a stable bassist at the time, and played some major events in the Mumbai metal circuit.\n\nThe search for a permanent bassist was finally over in a couple of months, when Orenstein joined in the band. His first show with the band happened to be on his 20th birthday. Due to the constant line up changes, the band had never gotten the chance to perform outside the city of Mumbai. This changed from the mid of the year 2008 onwards; shows in Pune, Hyderabad, Chennai and Bangalore etc. were played by the band with some of the best bands from the country. Headlined few college events in Mumbai as well. \n\nIn the end of 2008 the band hit studios and recorded a couple of demos which was supposed to be released as an EP in 2009; but the band were unsatisfied with the quality of the recordings and decided to hold on to the release and wait for a better recordings. The band later on decided that they will release an album instead. \n\nIn the mid of 2010, Ulhas cause of personal and professional issues had to leave the band. Vocal duties in the band from that point onwards are being handled by Bruce who is also the main composer of the music. After a lot of line up changes the band has finally settled down on the current line up. Their songs talk about social evils, corruption, rape, injustice, pollution and environmental degradation and the compositions are influenced by old school, groove and progressive death metal sounds. \n\nThe band has made a mark in the local metal scene and are roaring for more gigs and shows across the country. \n\nAtmosfear is planning to record and release an album soon watchout for the same!!\n','atmosfear.theband@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/AtmosfearIndia','','','','112305282181442','1201',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','atmosfear'),(585,0,0,0,'Punarjanma','Punarjanma started off in May 2009 with a vision in mind to acquaint Indian Classical music to the rock n metal ears. It underwent several line up changes ever since its commencement. Somehow, now, a sort of permanancy is attained in terms of a desired line up. A violin has been recently added up in the crew. Still in the underground stages, Punarjanma will soon emerge in the mainstream..','punarjanmatheband@gmail.com, vctrdb@hotmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/punarjanmatheband','','','','110046042403711','1201',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','punarjanma'),(586,0,0,0,'DARK OCTAVES OF SIN','The band started off as a college band, playing some live shows locally till they finally found their present groovy sound after a few highly needed and successful line-up changes. The band didn\'t take much time to find recognition in the local scene, but then playing in a conservative region has its own set of drawbacks. Influences vary from acoustic blues stuff to the very distorted and groovy genres such as metalcore , thrash and death metal.\n\n','+91-9711078053, +91-9888443937','http://www.facebook.com/darkoctavesofsin','','','','373414279686','1199',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dark-octaves-of-sin'),(587,0,0,0,'Varcas','VARCAS is a six piece Extreme Melodic Metal band from Mumbai. \'Varcas\' , which is a sanskrit word, simply suggests Vital Power which is the key essence to life. We choose to spread this power through our music.All band members are influenced by several different genres and styles of musical composition all the way from jazz to extreme metal. With all this talent put together in one band what you could expect is brutal drums beats accompanied by aggressive guitar riffs & vocals that progress with or layer upon solos & keyboard patterns that further amplify the bands Indian Mythological theme and helps to create music that can not only wreck mayhem in the moshpit but also send the crowd into a subtle melodic trance. ',' Atul Pandey +91-9773323148','http://www.facebook.com/varcastheband','','','','206842669329213','1197',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','varcas'),(588,0,0,0,'Quakers And Mormons','FUNERALISTIC\n (La Valigetta / Anemic Dracula)\n\nIs the second full lenght of  Italian duet QUAKERS & MORMONS, the Experimental Hip-Hop project of Maolo and Mancho (also known for My awesome mixtape), produced by Riccardo Gamondi aka Rico (Uochi Toki)\n\nFollowing the path started with EVOLVOTRON, this new album has the same dark tones with some evolutions: all the samples, while still deconstructed and built anew by the skillful hands of Rico (Uochi Toki), are somehow more orchestrated: strings, flutes, brasses, piano, arabesque or mystic tunes weirdly mix with power electronics, dubstep and drum n bass hints, all layering heavy and thick on a sheet of lyrics dealing with death (from the very moment before exhaling the last breath to the burial), expressed through extremely pop, obsessive and ritual-esque choruses struggling with harsh, ragind and fast verses.\n\nFUNERALISTIC is incredibly intense, deep and sincere, but not really easy at first contact: it will require you some listenings to absorb it, but it will definitely be worth the time spent.\n\nItll be in whole FREE DOWNLOAD from Tuesday, February 14th 2012 as a real shy St. Valentine gift\n\nRecorded, mixed and mastered at Fiscerprais by Riccardo Gamondi (www.fiscerprais.com // info[at]fiscerprais[dot]com).\n\nReleased by \"Anemic Dracula\" (anemicdracula.wordpress.com // anemicdracula@gmail.com) and \"La Valigetta\" (www.lavaligetta.it // lavaligetta[at]lavaligetta[dot] it).\n\nManagement by Michael Di Genova at Metatron (michael.digenova@gmail.com // www.metatongroup.com // angelo[at]metatrongroup[dot]com). \n\nArtwork and graphic Layout by Iacopo Gradassi (iacopo[at]sonsofvesta[dot]it).\n\n\nNobody knows the real identity of Quakers and Mormons. Only their Verb is known.','quakerskillsmormons[at]gmail[dot]it; angelo[at]metatrongroup[dot]com). ','http://www.facebook.com/quakersandmormons','','','','189038164326','1194',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','quakers-and-mormons'),(589,0,0,0,'Kevin Lester','When an artiste begins to exceed expectations, its only natural for his or her name to be whispered in the classrooms, halls and board meetings. A landmark is about to be made and a milestone is fast approaching for the Singapore music industry.\n\nNever before has the Lion City met an original artiste and entertainer with such enthusiasm and ability to change the perception of local music from the ground up.\n\nKevin Lester, 26, is a rap artiste, songwriter and producer.\n\nKevins debut album, Lets Talk About Kevin Lester, was released 15th November 2010. It was made available online for free download at his website, www.thelioncityboy.com. It features 8 original songs produced by an award-winning group of producers from Bedsty Music, Kevin Lester himself, and an up-and-coming producer The Architek.\n\nSince its release, it has garnered high rotation and rave reviews by critics in Singapore and internationally. UKs The Guardian picked Rockstar 2.0, the first official radio single from the album, as its top 35 songs from around the world for January 2011. Kevins next single Kidhood saw remixes from veteran dance producers, Thangka Satellites & DJ Ko Flow.\n\nMost recently, Kevin was chosen to represent Ciscos Flip facebook profile video app, which was featured on Mashable with Fresh Pair serving as the cool soundtrack for the international online campaign!','syaheed@bedsty.com','http://www.facebook.com/thelioncityboy','','','','370177173323','1194',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','kevin-lester'),(590,0,0,0,'Then and Now','The band was started by two songwriters garnishing each other\'s songs with the magical tone of Abhishek Joshi\'s voice and soulful guitar play of Kshitij Bhargava. After establishing a solid songwriting partnership music enthusiast Pawan Anand was recruited on the bass adding immensely catchy bass lines to the songs. Drummer Vijay Agarwal joined the band on drums adding power to the sound. \nWith mutual belief in the songs the band has started its journey to the dream of making these songs bigger than any popular charts. World will rock n roll yet again.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Then-and-Now/146866092048220','','','','146866092048220','1193',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','then-and-now'),(591,0,0,0,'The Avalanche','The Avalanche was formed in December 2008.\n\nThe band did its 1st gig at campus rock idols 2009.\nBand Achievements : \nIndependence Rock XXVI\nCampus Rock Idols Edition 5 (Regional Finalist) \nYouth Nexus 2011 (Finalists)\nYamaha Asian Beats( Short listed for Delhi beat)\nShivaji College Thunderstruck 2011(Winner)\nLBSIM Fort Rock - Tatva 2011(Winner)Dwarka Campus\nLBISM COLLEGE 2010 (Winner) ( R.K. Puram, Campus)\nEXUBERANCE 2011-THE ANNUAL FEST of DCAC(Winner) \nGTBIT COLLEGE 2010 (Winner) \nPGDAV College Aaghaz 2011(Winner)\nPulse 2010 @ Aims (Runners up)\nDelhi college of Arts & Commerce 2010 (Runners up) \nM.A.I.T College 2011(Runners up) \nSRCC Woodstock 11 (2nd Runners up)\nJIVE - Runners Up\nSYNAPSE,11 ,MAMC (Runners Up)\nPlayed Boogaloo along ThemClones & The Circus\nLast band standing @ Crescendo 2011(2nd Runners up)\nBesides that The Band went to IIM Ahemdabad, IIM INDORE(*2), Qualified For IIT Rorkee (*2). Performed at Cafe Morrison(*3), Blues(*2),Turquoise Cottage,Chicane(*3), SRCC, DCE, S.P.A,NSIT.\n\n','+91-9711703522/9999796175','http://www.facebook.com/theavalancheindia','','','','141217579232780','1190',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-avalanche'),(592,0,0,0,'Shor Bazaar','Shor Bazaar is a five-member band conceptualized / formalized / broughttogetherized in September07. With a heavy dose of serendipity, the band finally completed its line up in the last week of December 07. Since then its been one dizzying ride - from getting disqualified at our first music fest (for purely non-musical reasons  let me mention) to recording our first album.\n\nWe love only four things in this world - Music, South Park, Chicken soup and quoting ourselves! And we quote \"We specialize in wasting our time trying to make money through music. Till date, our earnings total zero.\"\n\nOnce upon a time, we were signed with Phat Phish Records, and laid down tracks for our debut album. Now, the tracks are still in the studio. But we are independent. We are also recording some new songs to be released as singles.\n\nWe released our first single titled \'Savita Bhabhi\' on the 29th of July, 2009. The video will be released soon. We are interested in performing at venue across the country. We would love to hear from you regarding such enquiries.\n','Krishna Kumar Venkitachalam (+91 9833181139; krishnakumarv@gmail.com), Kanishka Chaturvedi (+91 9920426381)','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Shor-Bazaar/32153298625','','','','32153298625','1189',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','shor-bazaar'),(593,0,0,0,'Pin Drop Violence','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Pin-Drop-Violence/109422982410460','','','','109422982410460','1188',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','pin-drop-violence'),(594,0,0,0,'Sridhar / Thayil','ALL BOOKINGS CONTACT sridhar.thayil@gmail.com\n\nInterview on the Strand, BBC World Service with Mark Coles: http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p005zl8x\n\nShe sings jazz, western classical and Indian classical. He does spoken word, plays blues and funk guitar. When they play together, expect operatic scat and pirate growl over home-made broken beats. They\'re called Sridhar/Thayil, and they make for one dirty sexy act. Rolling Stone Magazine India calls them \"two of the most uninhibited people that ever came together to play with music.\"\n\nThe duo has taken their signature lyrical-melodramatic-punkery to stages such as the Great Escape (Brighton), the Southbank Centre (London), Galle Literary Festival (Sri Lanka), and the Prithvi Theatre Festival (Mumbai).\n\nS/T \'s live gigs are known for their improvisational chaos and random guest collaborations such as Noush Like Sploosh (theremin), Dr Das of the ADF (bass), Kishore Sodha from RD Burman\'s original horn section (trumpet) and Stefan Kaye of Emperor Minge (keys) amongst others. \n\n\n-------------\n REVIEWS: \n\n\"Sridhar/Thayil are redefining indie music in India.\" -Rolling Stone, July 2009.\n\n\"One of the kookiest bands to emerge from Mumbai\'s music scene.\" \n-Times of India, 2011\n\n\"Its a rare thing to chance upon an act that surprises. Sridhar/Thayil, composed of Suman Sridhar on vocals, keyboards, and programming, and Jeet Thayil on guitar and vocals, are standouts with their wonderfully peculiar blend of Billie Holiday-esque vocalising, blues, jazz, poetry, and electro-pop-swing.\" -Uday Benegal, June 2010\n\n\"juxtaposing the absurd with the profound\" -Rolling Stone, July 2009\n\n\n\"You need to hear the man [Jeet Thayil] tell it on This Be the Beat to truly believe that he knows his jazz! He has that sensibility of the vein-and-bone four piece blues band, where it takes four tired, jazz-souled people to swing an entire club through the night.\" -Times of India, May 2008\n\n\"If there\'s one woman who can make a wail sound beautiful, it\'s her...Suman Sridhar can sing the phonebook...[She] is one of those rare singers who combine an old-world voice with a very contemporary sensibility.\"-Harper\'s Bazaar, July 2010\n\n\"Jeet (Thayil) wove wicked blues licks on his guitar, emphasising a punch line, riding a tricky vocal passage, dropping some gravelly witticisms in a forest of midis and occasionally switching to play a rather grating keyboard.\" -Rolling Stone Magazine, India\n\n\"The classically trained Suman Sridhars surreal, beautiful voice and expressive face made a perfect foil for poet Jeet Thayils sardonic stage presence.\" -The Caravan, December 2009\n\n\n\"An unabashedly intriguing act\" -The Asian Age, September 2008.\n\n\"Sridhar/Thayil strip opera of its pretensions.\" -Midday, November 2009.  \n\n\n\"bare-foot, lo-fi rhythmic magic...\" -Times of India\n','','http://www.facebook.com/Sridhar.Thayil','','','','30563747417','1186',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sridhar-thayil'),(595,0,0,0,'Rosez On Ashez','AND IT WAS WHEN THE SUCKTARDED SAGA HAD JUST BEGUN...\n\nAHmm.. this  previously  3 piece sucktarded \'band\' was framed by Saurav and Gaurav (who by the way are not brothers) somewhere in the summer of 2009 in the town itself! Initially we had Abhishek on the BASS. We had named ourselves as \'\'CYCLONIC CHAOS\'\', but later on Abhishek had to leave the SUCKAZ to make his life MORE WORTHY!! And then the band almost went out of trace for almost 3-4 months ,until Saurav befriended The EARSPLIT\'s, Anshul, and allured him to join the scene..!! Back then the multitalented Anshul was on a hunt for a secondary project, and he almost formed some other band ,but thanks to some CRAZY incidents this dream was sortov left undone.  Mean while when Mr.Saurav was too busy sleeping or chatting all day long and randomly changing the name of his AIR BAND , Anshul showed some interest in being the third idiot in his VISIONARY PROJECT..!! Hence Saurav agreed and assured Anshul all the NAME, FAME and most primarily the CHIKAZ in the world (i.e. in the TOWN).\nSo the bands final 3-piece lineup came about in DECEMBER 2009 and we got the chance to make a fool of ourselves for the first time in FEBRUARY 2010 in the hometown itself. Impressed by our weirdness another SUCKA named Shubham approached us to join the band and therefore with a 4-piece lineup we were back on stage in June,2010.\nAfter this, to add drama in the sucker\'s group, Anshul decided to leave the band for the betterment of his primary project THE EARSPLIT, and we stood \'\'baseless\'\' for an entire year, doing nothing except nosepicking!\nAnd then after an entire year of dramatic seclusion, Gaurav woke up and came to the rescue by introducing 2 newest members to the gang....with Dikshit (on Bass), and Fat Shady (on Rhythms). The band once again rose and performed in 5 different stages in less than a month and set a \'\'world record\'\' for themselves in their own little world!!\n\nWith a lot of ups and downs and some edited line ups here we are today, with only a few gigs done and NO SATISFACTION , all bankrupted, girlfriends turning to EX-girlfriends, hearts stitched with nylon strings, and young boys turning to \'\'lameted\'\' businessmen!!\n\nBut we\'re RESPECTED (in our own lil\' world), and thats what matters.  \nYO!!  [PEACE OUT]\n\n','09418003475 ','http://www.facebook.com/rosezonashez','','','','124007517624452','1185',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rosez-on-ashez'),(596,0,0,0,'De\'SaT','In a World of Pride, Greed and Pain we live. \nThis chaos we deny, letting the evil get stronger around us.... \nWe must Blame but our Selves for not standing up for our future!\nDe\'SaT is a Humanitarian Band trying not to only Save our Future but to Save our Race. \nPeace is the only way out now! But with our Greed which we do not want to compromise on, our Peace is at stake. \nFor all Humanity are one blood!','Sangeeth : 953-533-6383, sangeethram@gmail.com,Sandesh- 998-670-6253,','http://www.facebook.com/desatindia','','','','189173607789101','1177',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','desat'),(597,0,0,0,'Jester','Jester: Food and Funnies.\nSharing space with a Indian classical choir and a rather quirky bunch of musicians in Musoc,Kirori Mal College, Jester is a funk band open to a lot of experimentation. Jester finds its inspiration in everyday ironies and general tomfoolery. The vocalist, Dhruv- Nawab of the band, is an air bag with a lunatic glint in his eyes. He\'s quite good when it comes to crazy harmonies and he always wants to change everyones parts. Hes survived the band in spite of the on-off button he carries hidden somewhere within his \'nawab\' intellect. Our lead guitarist, Pahwa (no one knows his first name) wants to shred a lot, though we really dont let him. He does manage to play the coolest chords with some quirky melodies some funky phrasing yes a little shred thrown in. For Shiv, struggling to keep his keyboard from perishing because of voltage fluctuations, its all about the groove and his unique one legged dance. Akshay, on bass, is the color quotient of the otherwise sober band. He owns a fluorescent green bass,an orange sweater and yellow eyes. Shantanu shanty Sudarshan with his South Indian awesomeness keeps it trendy with Swirlies, high fives, fist bumps, soccer calves and crazy hits.\n\n\nachievements\n1st youth nexus 2009\n1st acoustic band iit kanpur\n1st acoustic band lady shri ram college\n1st delhi zone campus rock idols 2008\n1st regionals campus rock idols 2008\n2nd at iit guwahati rockophonix 2010,doodie also got best bassist\n2nd at hansraj 2009\n3rd nationally campus rock idols\n3rd srcc woodstock\nshortlisted for moodi livewire\nplus jsitar which is jesters hindi project came 3rd at iit guwahati indian band competition raga high\n\n gig info\n5th August hard rock cafe delhi\n17th August Turquoise cottage Vasant Vihar\n26th August Aura Lucknow\n2nd September Blues Cp\n19th october turquoise cottage vasant vihar at the 