 Kingfisher The Great Indian October Fest 2010, etc...Apart from this, they have played in many colleges in Bangalore and were the headlining act at The Maharani Ammani College Fest 2010 and X-Jam, Imphal.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Velvet-Trap/127277080644733','','','','127277080644733','1141',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-velvet-trap'),(605,0,0,0,'Blood Orchid','Blood Orchid is a Progressive/Thrash Metal band based in Bangalore. The band, initially known as \'Echo Of Silence\', was started by drummer, Mayur and bassist, Rahil in month of April, 2009. Ex-guitarist Darryl and Vocalist Kaushal joined the band in the month of June and henceforth, continuous sessions started taking place. Guitarist, Pavan joined the band in the month of March, 2010. In the month of May 2010, Blood Orchid received its newest and final member, Guitarist Prashanth, replacing former Guitarist, Darryl, who left the band for higher studies.\n','Mayur Nanda- +919538494781, Rahil Ahmed - +919742323353','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Blood-Orchid/207569037359','','','','207569037359','1134',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','blood-orchid'),(606,0,0,0,'Spiked Crib','Spiked Crib has played at several venues across Mumbai, including pub shows, college gigs and metal gigs. We\'ve played and headlined shows in Kerala, Goa, Gujarat and Vikramgarh. \nFrom personal experiences of our listeners, we\'ve learnt that the ambiance of the music mixed with doses of aggression and atmospheric effect make us an experience worth listening to.','9769335676 (Gareth), 9833046810 (Khyati)','http://www.facebook.com/spikedcrib','','','','172461392783817','1130',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','spiked-crib'),(607,0,0,0,'White(Band)','Formed in September, 2010\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/WhiteBand/177877385593251','','','','177877385593251','1121',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','whiteband'),(608,0,0,0,'The Lightyears Explode','The Lightyears Explode are a three piece garage/Indie/punk band from Mumbai , Maharashtra.Formed in 2009 The band comprises of Aaron Carvalho on Drums , Shalom Benjamin on Bass and Saurabh Roy on Guitar/Vocals.\r\nSince their inception the then The Lightyears(named changed due to copyright issues) hit the Mumbai college circuit, strong performances and positive word of mouth eventually resulted in them breaking into the legitimate scene with gigs with likes of Rosemary , Blakc And Khiladi.Their song The Weapon was featured on Stupid Stupid Stupid The third installment of the nation wide un-metal compilation album Stupid Ditties and \"She Probhably Still Is\" was featured in the fourth edition of the same .\r\nThe Lightyears explode are set to release their debut EP In the month of January 2011.','+919867263038-Himanshu / +91 9920842043 - Shawn','http://www.facebook.com/TheLightyearsExplode','','','','163870840323518','1118',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-lightyears-explode'),(609,0,0,0,'Overdrive Records','','','http://www.facebook.com/overdriverecords','','','','122006927814705','1113',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','overdrive-records'),(610,0,0,0,'Drop Doubt','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Drop-Doubt/102039219873126','','','','102039219873126','1109',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','drop-doubt'),(611,0,0,0,'Ranjit Barot','Raised at the intersection of two cultures, drummer, composer, producer, and improviser Ranjit Barot comes from a family with deep ties to Indian classical traditions of music and dance, yet he spent considerable time absorbing western culture in England. That palpable dichotomy inhabits his music, as illustrated by his captivating international debut album Bada Boom  to be released on November 16th, 2010 by Abstract Logix.\nAs a writer and producer, Barot honed his skills by crafting songs and scores for the thriving, prolific Indian film scene and working closely with other artists. Although capable on a range of instruments, his weapon of choice as a performer remains the western drum kit, on which he has cultivated a unique voice that internalizes and refracts his musical and cultural influences. As a drummer, he has performed alongside such formidable improvising composer/instrumentalists as John McLaughlin, Ustad Zakir Hussain, Pandit Ravi Shankar, Charlie Mariano and Don Cherry. \n\nThe son of the legendary Indian classical dancer Sitara Devi (who specialized in the Northern Indian Kathak style), Barot was raised in a musically rich environment. His home played frequent host to jam sessions, where formidable musicians would gather to stretch out, experiment, and freely explore their art. He was drawn to the drum set at age 12, and despite the fact that the trap set is a western instrument, he was nurtured and supported by those around him. By the time he was seventeen, Barot was one of the leading drummers in India, equally inspired by the music around him and the fusion revolution happening in the west  all without any formal training on the instrument. After an extended period working in studios and drumming rarely, the past decade has found him reinvesting himself as an instrumentalist, resulting in a series of high-profile performance opportunities, including his participation in John McLaughlins stunning 2008 album Floating Point, which featured McLaughlin alongside a cast of stellar Indian fusion musicians. \n\nCiting the pathbreaking music of Mahavishnu Orchestra and Shakti, Ranjit counts McLaughlin and Zakir Hussain as two of his biggest influences  a respect that is reciprocated as McLaughlin contributes a blistering solo to Bada Booms opening track, Singularity, and Zakir Hussain provides the driving force for Supernova. Composed of four original pieces and two striking reinventions of traditional Indian themes, Bada Boom brilliantly explores Barots musical and cultural dichotomy. Rather than simply recast one culture in the guise of another  transposing tabla parts onto the drum set, playing funk guitar licks on the veena, etc.  Barot composes and arranges provocative, thoughtful dialogues from which these varied influences, textures, and techniques eventually emerge as one voice. The meeting point of all art is the same, at least to me, Barot concludes. When you strip away things like genre, ethnicity, art form even, then you are left with just intent and spirit.\n\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Ranjit-Barot/142525269120380','','','','142525269120380','1106',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ranjit-barot'),(612,0,0,0,'Captain Crunch & the Naina Kundu Trio','Floyd Fernandes  is a progressive blues rock guitar player who has played in numerous setups in and around Mumbai. His roots are in the blues and in this line up he also sings.\nCaptain Crunch is an inventive blues and funk band that thrives on an energetic set and improvisational spaces.The band is an aggregation of musicians who play with conviction and lend their unique voices to the set.The music ranges from funk to hard-edged blues to R&B  ballads, to jazz and even reworked pop standards.\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Captain-Crunch-the-Naina-Kundu-Trio/353268362052','','','','353268362052','1105',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','captain-crunch-the-naina-kundu-trio'),(613,0,0,0,'Mescalin, baby','MESCALIN, BABY is a band with a love for wry fates and stories about the life that we all walk through with more or less luck. It is music to back the chaotical dance that life asks us to dance.\n\nIn our own words we\'re playing rock music in most its forms. We see it as our quality to be free of everything else but our instruments and the stories we want to tell you. \n\nMescalin, baby is currently recording new material with Tobias Kippenberger of The Floor Is Made of Lava and Sebastian Wolff of Kellermensch.','Mescalin, baby','http://www.facebook.com/mescalinbabyofficial','','','','118864421500309','1100',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','mescalin-baby'),(614,0,0,0,'Rodney Branigan','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Rodney-Branigan/223380159398','','','','223380159398','1098',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rodney-branigan'),(615,0,0,0,'Vasuda Sharma','Vasuda Sharma, is a young, vivacious, extremely talented songwriter-musician from India, who first shot to fame when she got selected to be a part of the band Aasma, who were declared Indias official pop stars by Channel-V, one of the top entertainment and TV channels in India in  She went on to achieve great fame with Aasma, who released two albums, namely Aasma and Aasma Infinite. She is known to blend Indian and western influences to create beautiful music, and is the only artist in India to have perfected the Loop Station technique  a rather innovative style of performance that involves composing and recording live soundtracks comprising of vocals and instruments.\n\nHailing from Delhi, Indias capital, Vasudas childhood memories are full of the music that she learnt, first from her aunt, and later, as she pursued a year-and-half of classical Indian music. Her music is influenced by Alanis Morrisette, to a great extent.\n\nVasuda remains, till date, the only Indian artist to have performed with Bryan Adams, with her band Aasma, in Delhi & Bangalore during his last tour to India in 2004.\n\nVasuda has performed with her band for many Bollywood concerts including Salman Khans show in Hyderabad, the Sanjay Dutt Macro Ricci peace concert, Indian Telly Awards, S Times War of the DJS, Channel [V] Big V Concert and the like. She hopes to introduce a new wave of music in the Indian music industry through her upcoming project as a music director, where she will be teaming up with maestros of Indian music like Jagjit Singh and Shankar Mahadevan.\n\nVasuda  is currently pursuing her music studies in Berklee College of music for a year in Boston,USA.','','http://www.facebook.com/VasudaSharma','','','','121606031244444','1091',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','vasuda-sharma'),(616,0,0,0,'Noyze Akademi','Long story short\n(If you want to know how this band was formed, How this four guys met each other & what music do they like & allplease go & watch \"Jab We Met\" instead.)\n\nHistory Days\n\nYear 2009 - 2010\nNA burst in the Kolkata underground metal scene with resounding success.\nHome recorded demos got major hit among the local crowd.\nLive acts & accolades follows.\n\nThe Time Ahead\n\nYear 2011 -\nBack after a short hiatus of 6 months & a minor lineup change, NA is now armored with an unparalleled sound of their own.\nAn accent of their own.\n& a voice of their own.\n\nMajor Gigs Till Date\n RSJ Pubrockfest 2009\n\nThe Pit [Kolkata\'s Numero Uno Metal Fest]\n     The Pit I , Jan 27,2009.\n     The Pit II, April 18, 2009.\n     The Pit III, August 11, 2009.\n     The Pit V, 2011.\n     The Pit V Pub Round, 2011.\n	\n     Frequency Test 100.0 Hz [July 31, 2011]\n     The Lizard Turns One [Basement Kolkata]\n     Ragefest Chapter II [Club Xstasy Bhubaneswar]\n     Ragefest Chapter III [Club Xstasy Bhubaneswar]\n     Metal Mayhem III \n\nMedia Coverage\n\n  RSJ July 2009\n    Bands to Look Out For\n  RSJ June 2011 \n    Livewire Section\n\nLocal Print Media\n   The Telegraph, The Times Of India & The Hindustan Times.','Not Interested.','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Noyze-Akademi/167320986653821','','','','167320986653821','1089',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','noyze-akademi'),(617,0,0,0,'Annette Philip','Annette Philip is an Indian vocalist, composer/arranger, recording artist and choir conductor who thrives on experimenting with the human voice. \n\nIn 2003, she co-founded Artistes Unlimited (AU) in New Delhi, India, a performing arts ensemble, promoting collaboration among musicians in the city. With a vast repertoire spanning genres such as jazz, rock, R&B, funk, a-cappella, Gospel, Indian and Western Classical, Sufi and folk music, AU is now Indias largest and most diverse youth platform for musicians, with a rotating line up of over 250 artistes.\n\nAnnette began working in the professional media circuit in New Delhi at the age of seventeen. She has since become an established recording artist, lending her voice to albums, jingles and voice-overs in nine languages, for television and radio. She also finds inspiration in musical theatre; performing, writing, and recording for various productions in India, besides continuing to perform live with AU and other bands. \n\nAfter being awarded a full scholarship, supported both by the college and the Inlaks Foundation in India, Annette recently graduated from the Berklee College of Music in Boston, Massachusetts, in the United States.  She received her degree in Professional Music, with courses providing an emphasis on improvisation, composition, and arranging.\n\nAnnette was also the 2009 Berklee recipient of the Sylvia Zunz Memorial Scholarship, for her commitment to learning and performing music from the Great American Songbook tradition. \n\nShe has been privileged to share the stage with artists such as Buster Williams, Victor Lewis, Jack DeJohnette, Fritz Renold, Barrie Lee Hall, Mark Gross, Mark Soskin, Adam Nussbaum, Reggie Hamilton, Walter Beasley, Lawrence Watson, Dennis Montgomery III, Gabrielle Goodman, Joey Blake and Christiane Karam amongst others. \n\nAnnette is not only currently recording and performing with her own jazz fusion ensemble, The Annette Philip Quintet, but is also touring with the Boston-based vocal group Women of the World. \n\nIn April 2010, she will be presenting original music at JAZZAAR, a jazz festival in Aarau, Switzerland, sharing the stage with music legends such as Airto Moreira, Lew Soloff, Ghatam Giridhar Udupa, Pandit Anindo Chaterjee and Christian Jacob, amongst others. ','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Annette-Philip/107250222873','','','','107250222873','1089',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','annette-philip'),(618,0,1,1,'DJ Deep','\"The truest expression of a people is in its dances and its music. Bodies never lie.\" - Agnes De Mille\n\nThis classic quote aptly forms the foundation for DJ Deep\'s music. With a mere experience of 6 years, Deep has climbed his way to the upper reaches of success in a rather enviable time. \"My style usually varies from some delicious progressive to a bit of super groovy techno, a pinch of the commercial sounds for the saturday night clubbers, heading all the way into some power packed trance and psychedelic goodies\", adds this powerhouse of talent. His sounds have an immense hypnotic groove and pack a punch in every single set that he seems to deliver so effortlessly, all owing to his vast knowledge and a supreme taste in electronic dance music. As he puts it, the uniqueness of his sets comes custom tailored to every single floor that he takes charge of. He has a flare for evolving his sounds to the latest cutting edge music that technology would permit and has a unique ability to keep a packed house together and moving in sync going complete nuts.\n\nDeep is also the founder of Phunk.in, a revolutionary nightlife property - promoting and organising a whole array of international DJ tours and some of the most sought after parties across clubs in India. Phunk.in also caters as a DJ booking agency promoting some of the top artists from the national circuit.\n\nAs a DJ, Deep has shared the stage with some of the world\'s best acts including legends like Ronski Speed, Pete Gooding, Norman Doray, Robert Babicz, John 00 Fleming, Sied Van Riel, Ahmet Sendil, Super8 & Tab to more new age stars and psy gurus like Ananda Shake, Perfect Stranger, X-Noize, Pixel, Freaked Frequency, Slater, Sirius Isness, Gordon Edge & Filthy Rich to name a few. Apart from that he\'s played alongside some of the top Indian DJs including jalebee Cartel, Pearl, Nikhil Chinapa, Bandish Projekt, Ivan, Ryan Beck, Sanjay Dutta, Ma Faiza, Nawed, Tatva Kundalini, B.L.O.T, Brute Force & Inferno amongst others.\n\nCurrently based in Pune, Deep has played in clubs and gigs all across the nation in cities like Mumbai, Delhi, Hyderabad, Bangalore, Kolkata, Nagpur, Ahmedabad and continues to wreak havoc on dancefloors with the sole aim of playing and promoting electronic dance music with integrity and filled with colossal energy. Expect to hear a lot more and about Deep, this year and beyond.','+919890878454','http://www.facebook.com/djdeepofficial','','','','39546707775','1088',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-deep'),(619,0,0,0,'Iota Vapors','the false iota about rn\'r now vapors','','http://www.facebook.com/iotavapors','','','','152432921458121','1084',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','iota-vapors'),(620,5,1,1,'Nucleya','Nucleya started his musical journey towards the end of \'90s when he co-founded Bandish Projekt. Since then, he has released 14 singles, a studio album \'Bhor\' and numerous collaborations. Besides this, there are four more international releases lined up for this year. Nucleya has frequently made it on the playlists of BBC Radio 1 and many other radio stations around the world. He has performed at numerous music festivals around the world including Glastonbury, Edinburgh Fringe Festival, Lille 3000 and the Electron Festival, where he performed alongside artists like Diplo and Modeselektor. \r\n\r\nIn 2010, he completed a massive 8-city tour of India with Radio Mirchi and Rolling Stone magazine on board to promote is Indian Electro/Dubstep/DNB album \'Horn OK Please\'. Over past few years, he has produced original sound tracks and background scores for feature films like Dubai Return, short animations, as well as ad films. He has worked with brands like Tata and has also designed a background score for an animation film by a student of National Institute of Design, India. He\'s also worked on high-profile remixes, including a track for Zoya Akhtar\'s film \' Zindagi Na Milegi Dobara\' as well as a remix of the Scottish bhangra group Tigerstyle\'s next release. ','nihaal@oml.in & udyan@nucleya.com','http://www.facebook.com/nucleya','http://nucleya.com/','http://soundcloud.com/nucleya','','0','1077',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 13:27:33',302,'[\"nihaal@oml.in\"]','[\"Nihaal: +91-9920585595\"]','nucleya'),(621,0,1,1,'Agastya','gastya is a Classical Sufi Rock Fusion band from Delhi, India.\r\nThe band was officially formed in August, 2010 in Delhi. \r\n\r\nMembers: \r\n\r\nThe band consists of: \r\n\r\nUmang ( Lead Vocals )\r\nhttp://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100000718997746\r\n\r\nManpreet ( Guitars )\r\nhttp://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=1374732898\r\n\r\nNaveen ( Lead Guitars )\r\nhttp://www.facebook.com/nike.10055\r\n\r\nJammy ( Keyboards & backup vocals )\r\n\r\nVansh ( Drums )\r\nhttp://www.facebook.com/vanshw\r\n\r\nAshish (Bass)\r\nhttp://www.facebook.com/ashish.deydu?__adt=8&__att=iframe\r\n\r\nCREW : \r\nSantom Jose','09716934458','http://www.facebook.com/agastyatheband/','','','','0','1071',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','agastya'),(622,0,1,1,'Adam & the fish eyed poets','Adam & the fish eyed poets is the working name of chennai based singer-songwriter kishore krishna , who after having released 2 self produced albums \"snakeism\" (2010) and \"dead loops\" (2011) has decided to put a band together featuring the most talented musicians from the chennai cesspool ,with a sound that finds a volatile balance between the sexually charged stax/volt era rhythm and blues and the sneering, passive aggressive precision of post-punk/new wave acts such as the smiths, echo and the bunnymen and the cure , the fish eyed poets are ready to start a meaningful fire or two.\r\n','Bushra Shariff (ZENSLAP) - 09844146919','http://www.facebook.com/afisheyedpoet/info','','','','0','1065',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','adam-the-fish-eyed-poets'),(623,0,0,0,'Nigambodh','May\' 09 - landed a slot in a compilation album sponsored by Tata indicom.\nOur track \'Fakeer\' was featured in the album.\n\n2nd oct 09 - Featured on a CNN IBN show about gandhi\n\n23rd - 24th Oct 09 IIT Kanpur\n1st runners up at synchronicity.\nBest bassist and Best vocalist.\n2nd runners up at antaragni fusion\n\n7th nov\' 09 - Headlined at EIT faridabad along with FARIDKOT\n\n18th Dec\' 09 - Headlined at IP college, DU along with PHOBIA and RABBIT IS RICH\n\n6th feb \'10 - IIT Guwahati.\n1st runners up at Raaga High\nBest Guitarist\nBest Drummer\nFinalists in rock-o-phonix\n\nMarch \'10\nReleased 2 singles - bhaago paagal aaya & stuti\n\n28th March\'10\nheadlined at BITS, PATNA along with the fantastic GIRISH & THE CHRONICLES\n\n9th april \'10\nHeadlined at CCET\'s cultural event in Chandigargh\n\n18th july \'10\nheadlined at IAMR sponsored BATTLE OF BANDs at the GARDEN OF FIVE SENSES, Delhi\n\nAUg\' 10\nGigged at the pubrock fest @ The mezz, NFC\n\nOct\'10\n1st runners up at synchronicity IIT Kanpur\n\nNov \' 10\nGigged at Blue\'s CP New Delhi\n\nDec\' 10\nGigged at Polka Kalish Colony  New Delhi\n\nJan\'11\nShortlisted for Channel V launchpad\n\nJan\'11\nWon northern leg of Channel [V] launchpad\n\nfeb\'11\nRunners up at Channel [V] Launchpad\n\nFeb\'11\nHeadlined PSIT Kanpur\'s annual tech fest, Ignitia.\n\nJuly\'11\nGigged at Blue\'s CP New Delhi \n\nSept\'11\nGigged at Route 69 Gurgaon\n\nSept\'11\nGigged at Peddlers Chandigarh\n\nNov\'11\nHeadlined TERI University\'s aanual Fest, Aahvaan\n\nDec\'11\nHeadlined Winter Rock Fest, Shimla','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Nigambodh/101446579933108','','','','101446579933108','1063',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','nigambodh'),(624,0,0,0,'Blue Blood','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Blue-Blood/93635515996','','','','93635515996','1061',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','blue-blood'),(625,0,0,0,'RedEnergyDarkProject','	\n\"A project aimed at the formation of the band\" - Dark Project was always subscripted with this tagline in it\'s inception years(2002-2005); In 2005, the tagline lost the value because the project reached it\'s completion. A band was formed with 5 people in it from 3 different Engineering institutes: IIT KGP, Jadavpur University and HIT, Haldia.\n\nDark Project is an English band that composes music that can be classified as an eclectic blend of Alternative and Progressive Rock.Using their proficiency with technology that they got as a freebee as a part of their Degrees, Dark Project slowly started recording songs adopting a complete DIY philosophy. In the year 2007, they came out with their first offering in the form of a 9 song album titled Chaos Sessions. This album was recorded with a guitar processor completely self made by the band for a megre 150 bucks, since the band couldnt afford enough cash with their pocket money.\n\nPost completion of their degrees, Dark Project re-grouped and re-shuffled its lineup. Amidst all the adversity, they did not want to stop the production mill and came out with their second full length album titled as Liberty & Entropy in the year\n2009. The album was eventually reviewed by the Rolling Stone Magazine, Rock Street Journal, IndiarockMp3, Indiescion and was also released on iTunes and Amazon for the worldwide audience. The band followed it up with shows in Some Place Else, Opus and the Pub Rock Fest in the same year.\n\nThis was followed by a hiatus for 2 years that involved a bassist change and a relocation of the band to Bangalore. The band made a comeback into the Independent circuit with its two latest offerings  Magic and Tale of the Liars in July this year(2011).\n\nDark Project is not just a band, it\'s a relationship that has survived, struggled and bruised through the odds for the last 6 years. Even with a limited English music listener base in the country, the band wants to inspire people through their work as they prepare themselves up for a mission that only reads - Follow your dreams, no matter how bad the situations get, feel the \'Magic\' that happens because of it.','','http://www.facebook.com/RedEnergyDarkProject','','','','162108877217903','1059',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','redenergydarkproject'),(626,0,0,0,'_{ TaKe OfF __','','+91-7696355241','http://www.facebook.com/takeofftheband','','','','168406859844721','1059',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','take-off'),(627,0,0,0,'Aisha Ali','','ali.aisha123@gmail.com,9886221133','http://www.facebook.com/AishaAli12','','','','189437607760963','1056',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','aisha-ali'),(628,0,0,0,'Moksh','Moksh started off as a college band in a small city called Davangere, Karnataka, India, which was formed to perform at one of the college festival in the year 2007. Later realizing the unison of interests in metal the band proceeded to get a little more serious towards music which was in the year 2009 when the band really started to fine tune the sound. The line up by then had faced several changes with our keyboardist Anson Cherian wanting leave the band in order to persue his further studies. Later during 2010 the band had their original first set of compositions, which included \"Kill the Beast\" and \"Spring up o\' well\" which were musically inspired by some of the bands like Metallica, Alter Bridge etc. Since metal was not an acceptable genre in the town, the band still continued to play metal which attracted few but genuine fans. The journey of Moksh continued as they played in many small venues, while their music caught the attention of people. \n\n The content basically positive and reflects the message of salvation, truth and the mistakes that we humans commit. The Moksh music mainly consists of  the essential heavy metal sounds with heavy guitar riffs and an influence of blues, a combination of modern rock and metal drumming blended with a crunchy vocals turned out into a unique sound comprising of both heavy metal and modern rock.','9880773550,8892274646','http://www.facebook.com/mokshrock','','','','180632911560','1052',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','moksh');
INSERT INTO `core_artists` VALUES (629,0,0,0,'Dream Diabolic','Dream Diabolic was formed in 2008, and went on to win IIT Guwahati\'s Rock O\' Phonix 2009, which is one of most prestigious college competitions \nin India, along with winning individual prizes. \n\nDream Diabolic are also the Winners of CAMPUS ROCK IDOLS Regional(Kolkata) Leg 2009.\n\nDream Diabolic also have won Kaal Rav Festival, Rangpo in 2008 and have headlined various festivals, such as NIT Silchar\'s Thundermarch and other festivals around India.\n\nAfter a long hiatus, they returned to perform at Winter Rock Fest Shimla, and won it on their first comeback Performance in December 2011.\n\nRecently they performed at Metal Evolution, Sikkim\'s First Ever Metal Festival.','8509438211, 9547992353, 8768769039','http://www.facebook.com/dreamdiabolic','','','','162132670501199','1049',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dream-diabolic'),(630,0,0,0,'INHERITED INFECTION','Inherited Infection is a Metal/Rock Band from Delhi, India. Band\'s current line up includes Prabhat Ralhan on vocals, Jitin Kumar and Mohit Vig on guitar\'s Gaurav Yadav on Drums and Anurag sethi on Bass. The Band is influenced by many bands like Bullet for my valentine, Metallica, Dead by April, Dream Theater etc. Inherited Infection believes in making melodic music full of harmonies and melodic riffs. As the band is influenced by artist of different genres they wanted to mingle up their experience in music and wanted to make music as stupendous as they can.','','http://www.facebook.com/inheritedinfection','','','','135592823141990','1049',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','inherited-infection'),(631,0,0,0,'Indian Death Metal','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Indian-Death-Metal/100645856643520','','','','100645856643520','1048',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','indian-death-metal'),(632,0,1,1,'TighT aka dj sanuk','- electronic music productions\n- mix down & re-mixing\n- professional disc jockeying\n','','http://www.facebook.com/sanukproductions','','','','30850535833','1046',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','tight-aka-dj-sanuk'),(633,0,0,0,'D.E.V.A.A','D.E.V.A.A\n  \nBorn in 1983,for this indian dj/producer ,Pure love of \nmusic made it easy  to choose his carreer and he decided \nthat his future has to be in music.so,started learning the \nart of Dj,in 2003, and then he got aquainted with the \nelectronic dance music.since then he\'s been gathering \nexperience of playing his sounds in almost all the \nnightclubs of india.Also holding the residency of one of \nindia\'s premier nightspots in calcutta.\n\nbut the real transformation came in his carrer when he \ncame in contact with deep,dark underground progressive and  tribal sounds and then he dedicated his musical carrer for deep sounds.\n\nInspired by the greats like Moshic,Hernan cattaneo,fady ferreya,kintar,ivan nikusev,frangellico,kliement,hypntic duo,phonic deep,michael & levan,cj art,francisco diaz.with his experience as a radio dj since 2008,he\'s done several shows for different internet radio stations and  also guest sets for different big names in the progressive scene.\n\nHis main aim of playing music is to share his energy and \ngood vibes throughout the globe,and also to grow the \nelectronic music scene in India.\n\nApart from this,he has been producing progressive stuffs \nand got signed under one of the biggest indian record \nlabel called CHILLOM RECORDS,and soon after he got his \nfirst ep release called \'Plush\' .\n\nDeep trancy melodies and synths with strong progressive \nbass and tribal elements ,is what you can expect in his \nsets.','+919830691233','http://www.facebook.com/pages/DEVAA/113450345362693','','','','113450345362693','1045',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','devaa'),(634,0,0,0,'Flying Souls','','','http://www.facebook.com/Flying.Souls','','','','223009307745785','1043',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','flying-souls'),(635,0,0,0,'Petrichor','Petrichor\nAn Extreme Progressive Metal Band from Mumbai\nPronunciation: pe-tr-kor \nMeaning: That distinctively pleasant fragrance of rain falling on dry ground \nPetrichor is an amalgamation of ideas of a bunch of musicians with insanely varying musical tastes and styles who have come together to create music as a single entity\n','petrichorindia@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/petrichorINDIA','','','','202459436487325','1035',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','petrichor'),(636,0,0,0,'One Nite Stand','One Nite Stand began humping around the Adelaide scene in early 2010\n\nSince then they have played at Festivals such as Stereosonic 2011, Schoolies Festival 2011, Future Music 2012 & have been booked for the upcoming event: Planet Cream 2012 \n\nSince 2010 they have played at some of the biggest nightclubs in Adelaide including:\n\nHQ\nHeaven\nGarage\nDog & Duck\nMarble Bar\nCity\nSol Bar\nSavvy\nMybar\nThe Highway\nHighjinks &\nCatalyst\n\nNot to mention countless Underages including:\nRemember the Days, HQ Digital & Entourage Underage.\n\nSo whats Next?2012!!\n\n','For Contact Email: Jasetkemp@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/onenitestandjs','','','','248645706596','1034',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','one-nite-stand'),(637,0,0,0,'White Beryl','Genre->Alternative/funk/rock and roll\nInfluences-> Incubus , Alterbridge, Creed, Red hot chili peppers, Arctic monkeys, Switchfoot, john mayer(Any random band having blues jam) and more.\n\nCheck us on reverbnation- http://www.reverbnation.com/whiteberyl\nor soundcloud- http://soundcloud.com/white-beryl\nand NH7- nh7.in/whiteberyl/\n\nWhite Beryl was formed in october 2010,\nThe main motive is to showcase a unique sound and not to cage it with any particular genre. its a mixture of funk/ rock and roll/ alternative rock.\nevery member of the band boasts of previous experience and represent either one or another  Delhi bands . So, although being a new project, its not a naive one.\nBecause of their passionate interest in the music, they achieved a lot right from the starting like, Getting selected for channel v launchpad 2010,played at blue frog, played at many universities and colleges etc.\nWe stay together to create better music, not just sound and mesmerize people through our music.\n \nBand Members ->\n1. Ishani Lahiri (vocalist)->  have been singing in Delhi on and off since her school years, having first recited an Indian piece in kindergarden, after which she is pursuing training in Indian Classical vocals, which she believes equips her to sing any genre of music that she might want to in the future, as well as the present.\n2. Vishal Chandra(lead guitarist) -> have been playing guitars as a lead guitarist in more than one bands in Delhi since past 3 years,  inspired by blues, rock and roll, alternative music.  Likes to mix different genres of his influence to produce a sound that defines his sense of music with a better feel.\n3. Sagar Arora(drums) -> have been playing drums since last 2 years, he developed his own style of groove drumming by mixing up different genres. Presently he is pursuing  sound  production and used to play with very known Delhi metal band.\n4. Aditya Mall(bass guitars) -> started playing bass guitars two years back, his know for his crazy presence over the stage and attracting people by mixing his tapping skills with jazz techniques.\n \nBand Previous appearances ->\n>> Winners at battle of bands(BOB) at Hell Pizza , gk , new delhi .\n\n>>Played at THE BLUE FROG, Mumbai , The Punk Night ,sponsored by Tuborg. \n\n>>Played for CHANNEL V LAUNCHPAD PRELIMS 2011 at attitude alive gurgoan.\n\n>> played at zook , saket powered by \"we mean music\" and kingfisher . \n\n>>>>Recently played at Turquoise Cottage on the event \"Deception night\" by Caesars Inc ,along with other various artist\n\n>>Guest performance at Blues, Connaught Place, Delhi (Kingfisher rashrockdrum).\n\n>>HEADLINING performance act at ITM, gurgoan , robotic fest.\n\n>>Played in PECFEST 2010 , Chandigarh.\n \n>>Guest performance at Last Drop Cafe, New Delhi .\n \n>>Headlining Act at Hindu college fest 2011, New delhi\n \n>>Played at SRCC college fest 2011.. (got interviewed by bindas tv show campus rock ) interview link- > http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hTpWN74zlJE\n \n>>Played at Shivaji college fest 2011, New Delhi\n\n\n\ncheck out our link.. listen .. and if you like it.. \ndo support us .. cheers..!!','91-9717268242, 91-9953775041','http://www.facebook.com/pages/White-Beryl/154696951231691','','','','154696951231691','1033',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','white-beryl'),(638,0,0,0,'Dream Out Loud','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Dream-Out-Loud/8171634308','','','','8171634308','1032',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dream-out-loud'),(639,0,0,0,'Revival Stage.','','revivalstage@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/RevivalStage','','','','131230743595053','1028',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','revival-stage'),(640,0,11,11,'La Pongal','La pongal simply put, is a platform for folk music created by Darbuka Siva, that is on a continuous journey exploring indigenous and traditional forms of art.\r\n\r\nIt is our vision to bring the rustic folk styles and the experimental contemporary styles together. By bringing this new expression to already vast folk artforms, we hope to make them more accessible to people all over the world.',' Debayan +91 99860 58255 ','http://www.facebook.com/LaPongal','http://www.artseek.in','','','0','1028',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','la-pongal'),(641,0,0,0,'Anup and Kenneth','Started in the year 2010 (Feb) , Anup and Kenneth being classmates at CKP for more than a year discovered that music would eventually bring them together to start a one of a kind young acoustic blues band in Bangalore. While Anup comes up with the tunes , Kenneth does the writing. They have so far composed 12 original songs. Playing at pubs and restaurants, the band has an EP along with a documentary on it and soon will own half of austria. Future plans include gig\'s featuring varied musicians and buying a time machine.\n','','http://www.facebook.com/anupandkenneth','','','','127049077321927','1023',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','anup-and-kenneth'),(642,0,0,0,'Wasted Soul','We are not just a band, we are sin itself...\nDemonic rituals, loud & disturbing music- our field of expertise...\nFive sinners got together in 2004 to form a band, a religion...\nPioneer of dark, aggressive, sinful, wasted metal music in chandigarh...\n\nBand includes:\nAtul (virgin necromenor- rhythm guitarist)\nRishi (insanity personified- drummer)\nIsha (angel of chaos- bassist)\nKuku (barbaric- lead guitarist)\nAshish Negi (epitome of sin itself, wasted one- vocalist)\nJai (i\'m a loser baby, so why dont u kill me....god v hate him so much!!!!- manager)\n\nBENEATH THE REMAINS WERE:\nCorni (sex, drugs n rock- explain his life & he\'s dead coz of that)\nJindal (partner in crime, hail to the master of puppets)\nKaandhal (the only positive thing about us & we hated him for that) \nBansal (sentiyaap personified)\n\nSome people are gifted\nSome are cursed\nWe are wasted...\nJoin the cult,\nLight the candles for the sinners,\nSet the soul on fire!!!','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Wasted-Soul/57741130755','','','','57741130755','1017',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','wasted-soul'),(643,0,0,0,'Shabd','','','http://www.facebook.com/shabdtheband','','','','173077122704809','1012',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','shabd'),(644,0,0,0,'Cabrura','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Cabru%C3%AAra/104012386301548','','','','104012386301548','1010',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','cabruera'),(645,0,0,0,'Traveling River Band','Traveling River Band is an original Mumbai-based outfit that was founded in 2009 by Akash Sharma. The music is Folk / Blues / Alt. Rock / Experimental\n\nRony Jose (Vocals/Harmonica/Guitar) \n\nOne of the original members of the band, he is back after a year long sabbatical. And he is better  than ever. The voice of the band, he even plays the harmonica and guitar if he is in the mood. Performing live gives him the ultimate high. He can be found around anything and anyone related to music and art, and spends his time sketching, drawing or making music on the software. An avid traveler, for him, playing music in new places is a step closer to nirvana.\n\n\nAkash Sharma (Guitar/Vocals/Synth)\n\nIt was the magic in music that drove him to form the Travelling River Band. His expertise lies in composing music and his first love is his guitar. A passionate sound engineer, he believes in using technology to the fullest when it comes to recording, postproduction and band rehearsals. His bedroom studio is testimony to his love for sound. When not online exploring the latest gadgets, or recording, he can be found with his second love, his bike. He loves riding to unknown destinations, the plains, the hills, nothing is beyond reach and he always takes the longer routes. Despite being a recluse, he is surprisingly the most socially active person in the band. Also, he is also the one man solution to all your IT problems. \n\n\nAsit Adsul (Keyboard/Vocals) \n\nMusic flows through his genes; his grandfather is Pt DP Adsul, the noted khayal singer. The strong family musical culture opened him up to classical music from a young age. His inputs are valuable when it comes to fine tuning a note or a rhythm in a track. The flute is his companion of choice, keeping him busy quite often. Inspiration for him comes from long drives usually to a serene riverside or a calm beach.\n\nJack Saha (Bass/Vocals)\n\nOnce a lead guitarist; he has come a long way from the hills of Darjeeling to the congested streets of Mumbai and picked up bass during this journey. In Mumbai he has been part of bands that have played everything from gospel music to Hindustani classical. He normally gives a single take while recording, and very rarely struggles with melody and bass lines. He rarely complains and prefers to go with the mood and flow of the song. His improvisations add a rustic flavor to the bands compositions. \n\n\nManas Baruah (Drums/Sampler)\n\nAt the age of 10, he got his first drum kit, starting off a love story with percussions that has endured to this day. The time spent in the concert circuit in and around Assam and Mumbai has given him musical influences from hard rock, jazz and pop to progressive and funk.A lesser known fact is that he is a fabulous cook. He is also highly possessive about his electronic drum kit and could kill for it. Dont believe us, proceed at your own risk. \n\n\nThe band loves to do a lot of experimental impromptu jams.','y.sengupta@gmail.com / travelingriverband@gmail.com +91 9769377732','http://www.facebook.com/trbindia','','','','248437171025','1009',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','traveling-river-band'),(646,0,0,0,'Corrode','Corrode was formed by Vinay Ganesh, aka Goldy and Sidharth Manoharan during the fall of 2007. Formerly known as Atharva, Sidharth and Goldy began rehearsing as a two-piece band with Sidharth on vocals and keyboards and Goldy on Guitars. Sidharth\'s black metal influences and Goldy\'s Melodic Metal influences merged to form Corrode. \n\nCorrode\'s music has been consistent with no shift in genre from the time of the bands inception. Harsha Neelakantan joined the band as the bassist in the winter of 2007. Sidharth, Goldy and Harsha had been the permanent members of Corrode which as a band has had quite a few line-up changes! A few of Corrode\'s ex-band members are - Jayanth (Guitars; who is currently the endorsement engineer for the biggest band in India - Kryptos), Rijo (Drums), Shreyas (Drums), Manish (Guitars) and Yash (Drums).\n\nIn March 2009, Ashwin Alexander (drums, Sptifire and ex-Macabre Intent) and Benjamin (Crucifix Guide, ex-Macabre Intent) joined the band to complete Corrode\'s five-piece line-up. The band played at many college fests and local gigs. In May 2009, Goldy suffered a severe neck injury while performing on stage which put him out of action for a couple of months. This resulted in a temporary break for Corrode. After Goldy recovered, he continued with his side project, Nihilus along with Harsha on bass guitar, Sidharth on drums and Amar (Clipped Wing Satellite and Venator) on vocals. In December 2009, Sidharth announced his departure from Nihilus and Corrode, consequently disbanding Nihilus and further extending Corrode\'s break.\n\nIn April 2010, after nearly a year of hiatus, Corrode was revived when Nikil Kumar (bass, ex-Macabre Intent) and Aditya Rajan (vocals, ex-Macabre Intent) joined the band. Harsha shifted to guitar to fill the void formed when Benjamin went on to join Crucifix Guide, thus once again completing Corrode\'s five-piece line up.\n\nIn September 2010, Harsha left Corrode to pursue his studies in Philadelphia, USA. Aditya took his place on guitars and a new vocalist- Achish Jeremiah was added to the band for a short period of time, till his departure in March 2011 due to musical differences.\n\nThe band with its present line-up (four-piece for the first time since its inception),  is going steady, and is in the process of writing and producing their debut album with a distinct and more melodic sound as compared to the singles formerly released. ','','http://www.facebook.com/corrodeband','','','','102397049800655','1005',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','corrode'),(647,0,0,0,'Janmoksh Rock Band','\nBorn Sumtime Back..\nEnjoying Present..\nBuilding Fut