 and Xulfi in Lahore. The recording of the album led to film OST projects  Raat Gayi Baat Gayi & Aao Wish Karien. He was nominated in the Best Upcoming Music Director category at the Mirchi Music Awards 2010. At the live circuit he plays with his four-piece band  Ankur & the Ghalat Family. The sound of his band ranges from Urdu/ Hindi Rock n Roll to easy acoustic ballads & folk rock.','+91-9819-257-005','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Ankur-The-Ghalat-Family/102360416490973','http://www.myspace.com/ankur.tewari','','','0','999',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ankur-the-ghalat-family'),(649,0,0,0,'Pseutopia','Pseutopia pursues its path to create hard hitting music that is bound to provoke your thoughts while it kicks your ass. As the name goes, pseudo-utopias are all around and they say it just like they see it. With raw and powerful lyrics, the music of Pseutopia is bound to get your heads banging on the inside and the out. From their formative years in their high school band to present day Pseutopia, the band has evolved and matured in its outlook on music, politics, society and life. Making a stand on social issues is a very. urgent. priority.\n','','http://www.facebook.com/Pseutopia','','','','180058338673718','999',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','pseutopia'),(650,0,0,0,'AfterLife','','','http://www.facebook.com/AfterLifetheband','','','','130813963627027','993',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','afterlife'),(651,0,0,0,'The Aphids','The Aphids originally formed by Vinu George in 2009 was an enormous success throughout Delhi and Jaipur. The songs like Pump it Up and I can see everything were loved by people everywhere who later became their fans. But due to unforeseen circumstances, the band drifted apart and their music journey came to a halt in Oct 2010. And after almost a year of hardships Vinu George again started working towards his dream project and in Oct 2011, The band was joined in by 3 new members . Harry on vocals/lyrics, Adarsh on lead guitar and Sanyam on bass and the band played superbly but it could never be a band. Luck wasn\'t favoring the band at all. Everywhere they played hard, things just wouldnt go in their favor and after Nagaland, Adarsh the Magic boy and Sanyam (gumy bear) decided to work on their own project called Madhouse. \n\nI had to stay back at my hometown while coming back from Nagaland. I wasn\'t even there but when I got back to Delhi with the news and money for the gig in Varanasi, Vinu shocked me. \n\nShit happens. But then how do we manage the performance in Varanasi? \nJesus sends three of his angels for rescue. Jerin Jose, Renin Raphael and Allan Thomas. Along with a gig at IIM Lucknow. Courtesy Mr. Khalid Wani (RSJ). It\'s a different story altogether. Anyways so the date is 17th of Jan (2012). The first day we met and jammed and the feeling was really good. Maybe it was all meant to be. Maybe God wants us to be together. Maybe coz the results were AWEsome... \n\\,,/ Nailed Lucknow.\nRocked Sunbeam Academy.\nAlso since Oct 2011 we\'ve started our journey to the other side with 2 new originals Blind &  Beer and Bong. The songs have been loved and appreciated by the audience everywhere performed.(and most of them weren\'t even drunk). We never try to be left unloved by our audience.\n\nMoral of the story: THE APHIDS is an alternative rock & roll band living for freedom. Freedom of speech and existence. Freedom from commitments when you don\'t even want to commit and freedom from lies that you need to tell to survive within your house. Freedom from the chains of responsibilities and unnecessary demands which we could only cater to if we kill our dreams and live a life they want us to lead. Freedom to be with the one you really want. Freedom to love. Freedom to be respected even when you do your own thing. Freedom to feel life in every form. Freedom to make a choice. And Freedom to choose the right thing. Freedom to choose your own GOD. \n\nLove \nTHE APHIDS ','','http://www.facebook.com/theaphidsband','','','','171213469595209','990',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-aphids'),(652,0,0,0,'Third Eye','\"BEHIND\", the first band\'s ep, is the METAL HAMMER\'s demo of the month in July 2010.\nThird Eye, now named DISSEQUENCE, formed in Palermo, Italy in October 2005 with the purpose of creating such a sound capable of expressing what could be described as a feeling of grudge and a deep interior dissatisfaction. The context in which the band lives is characterized by a society that basically ignores the extreme music. This because of limited chances the town itself offers, heres what fed the desire of screaming a message against a wrong reality that doesnt pass unnoticed to the eye target that only the truth can perceive.\n\nSo two friends, Enrico La Corte (drums) and Luca Delfino (vocals), who previously had shared together this philosophy, decided to bring about this new project in which he was immediately involved Gianluca \"Ske\" Schepis (guitar) and later Vittorio Ziino (bass) who was a childhood friend of Enrico. Giuseppe Musso (2nd guitar) joined the band in March 2008 thus enriching the sound and the final line-up.\n\nEach individual member of the band holds a great passion and a fairly good musical experience that has contributed to try out new sounds, even more mixing different kinds of music, but always keeping a powerful and incisive sound.\nThe agreement absolutely not indifferent among the musicians surprised the expectations of themselves that in a few months carried-out a dozen songs well-defined and accurate in every detail.\n\nThe band matured so different live experiences in pubs and festivals, reaching an excellent feedback from the public and much support from friends and other people.\nCurrently the band owns a 5 track EP called Behind (METAL HAMMER\'s demo of the month in july 2010), recorded at Circle of Power studios in January 2008 and actually it\'s working on new songs for its first full lenght.','dissequence@libero.it','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Third-Eye/159748613279','','','','159748613279','979',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','third-eye'),(653,0,0,0,'Indo Gypsies','Story Till Now:\n        INDO GYPSIES is a 7 piece band formed in 0ctober 2011 with an idea of fusing indian classical with western genres. It all started way back in late 2010 when Nayan, Mahant and Durgesh met in a college fest. After which they came up with an idea of forming a 3 piece instrumental band \"FAROL TRIO\" wherein they performed in many events. Then they decided to form a band through which they could make their way out towards World Music. In the journey, they found a versatile singer, Saurabh. They started composing music and in the process they found the percussionist Ameya who introduced the band to the drummer, Sanchit and the tabla player, Sukrut. Their inclusion provided a mix of indian classical and western rhythms for the band.Then Rohan joined the band as a Bassist.Rohan continued with the Band till March 2012.He recorded Bass for 3 Original Songs & also played in gigs.But due to his busy schedule he found it too difficult to continue the band.Then Mahant shifted on Bass Guitar.\n        On 22nd Jan, 2012 Indo Gypsies were Honoured to receive \'Responsible Youth Talent\' Award by Rotaract for the song \" I\'m Sending India To School \". Now the Band is on their way to make their mark in the World of Music.\n  \n\nPerformances till now:\n- Bits pilani waves searock 2011, Pune (7th oct 2011)\n- Freedom breakthrough fest 2011, Mumbai (16th Nov 2011)\n- W.O.R.M.E fest 2011 at B69, Mumbai (3rd Dec 2011)\n- Live on Air at Jago Mumbai 90.8 FM (3rd Dec 2011)\n- Rotaract Entertainment Destination 2011 VJTI Quadrangle, Mumbai (10th Dec 2011)\n- Tele-Interview with The Score Magazine (16th Dec 2011)\n- Taaraangan Festival at Thakur College, Mumbai (16th Dec 2011)\n- Battle Of Bands Elims at R City Mall Ghatkopar, Mumbai (18th Dec 2011)\n- Battle Of Bands Semi-Finals at R City Mall Ghatkopar, Mumbai (31st Dec 2011)\n- Battle Of Bands Finals at R City Mall Ghatkopar, Mumbai (1st Jan 2012)\n- World Responsible Youth (WRY) Festival at Rotaract 3140,Mumbai (8th Jan 2012)\n- 43rd Annual Rotaract Conference, Mumbai (22nd Jan 2012)\n- Harmonix, IBS Pawai, Mumbai (1st Feb 2012)\n- KalaGhoda Festival, Mumbai (7th Feb 2012)\n- Zeal Festival IBS Pune, PAN Card Club, Pune (11th Feb 2012)\n- Etamax 12 , Inorbit , Vashi, Navi Mumbai (17th feb 2012)\n- Father Agnel College, Navi Mumbai (22nd Feb 2012)\n- High Octane Elims, Sardar Patel College, Mumbai (26th Feb 2012)\n- High Octane Finals, Sardar Patel College, Mumbai (1st March 2012)\n- Bandz N Raaga Elims, R City Mall Ghatkopar, Mumbai (25th March 2012)\n- Bandz N Raaga Finals, R City Mall Ghatkopar, Mumbai (26th March 2012)','','http://www.facebook.com/IndoGypsiesMusic','','','','192795134124323','977',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','indo-gypsies'),(654,0,0,0,'Phlegmatic','The precursor to Phlegmatic started off sometime around November 2010 in NITK, Surathkal when Vivek Kannan, Rishav Mallick and Sriranjan Thirumalai (Ex-Bevar Sea) decided to start off covering bands such as Opeth. The drive to create original music started shortly after, and Nishaanth Reddy joined in.\nAiming to play Death Metal with progressions and technical overtones, Phlegmatic have since played gigs in Chennai, Mumbai, Mangalore, Surathkal and Bangalore.\nThe band is currently looking to gig extensively and is working on releasing its debut EP sometime later in 2011.\nRecently \"Conscientious Outcast\" was featured in an International Compilation Album \'Xtreme Compilation Online\' by an Indonesian Metal Webzine \'Xtreme Zine\'.\nPhlegmatic was recently interviewed by the country\'s leading radio station Radio One on the show \"One Music One Bengaluru\" and gathe