2383','','','','139902336062383','961',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','evil-conscience'),(661,0,0,0,'Exalt(HAFLONG/GHY)','Exalt was reborn in the end of the year 2010...After completing their school studies, progressive/hardcore metal was the only kind of music that they wanted to play after gaining inspirations from bands like Dream Theatre, Periphery, Protest The Hero & the like...Each of the members belonging from the small hill-town Haflong, it didn\'t take long for them to realize that Exalt was not just a passion for them...So they recorded their debut demo song \'Change\' in the beginning of the year of 2011 & since then the band has never looked back...Switching between studies & music from time to time, Exalt is always busy composing originals & evolve out as a tight band all together.......\n\n GIGS PLAYED:\n1. STORMBRINGER I (BLUES,GUWAHATI)\n2. HOPE 2011 (HAFLONG)\n3. NOKIA LAUNCHPAD AUDITIONS 2012 (GUWAHATI REGIONALS)\n4. AEC PYROKINESIS 2012 PRELIMS\n5. IIT GHY ALCHERINGA ROCK-O-PHONIX PRELIMS 2012\n6. NIT SILCHAR THUNDERMARCH FINALS 2012','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/ExaltHAFLONGGHY/136226703105920','','','','136226703105920','960',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','exalthaflongghy'),(662,0,0,0,'Vendetta','One day Rajeev got thrown away from his village \"Rampur\" by Thaakur Saab(some other story..:-p)...tired and broken he made his way towards Delhi hoping for a new life and of course, a new kick-ass band. \\m/\n\nWhile he was traveling on the train, he thought of ways he could make it big and it was right that minute when he saw Rohan who was selling tea and going \"CHAAAIYEEEEAAAA\" wearing his favorite LOG T- shirt...\nThe rest as we know, is the stuff epic legends are made of.\n\nRajeev approached Rohan to make a band....He agreed(he had no option.... and besides, he didn\'t want to sell Chaaai all his life)\n\nBoth of them got down at Gorakhpur station where the very own son of Gorakhpur, Rohit was handling cow dung. He said yes when he was approached to be a a part of the band and excitedly shook hands with Rajeev and Rohit(without really washing his hands...eeewwww....)\n\nThen, in a twisted turn of events,  Gorakh Bhaai\'s gay partner Kalwani(no offense Ayushi..:-p) came running and caught his hand while the train was moving(Full-on DDLJ Scene!)\n\nHe was given a bass as we had no option...and finally completing the band line-up was Antiriksh(I\'m sure I spelled it wrong)...And I can\'t really write much about him as I\'m afraid he might come and eat me (Zombie)\n\nFriends,  \"WE ARE VENDETTA\"...\\m/','Vikas Kalwani 9582494142 , contact.vendetta@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/vendettaindustrial','','','','204117042936796','948',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','vendetta-1'),(663,0,0,0,'Zzid','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Zzid/249380598434901','','','','249380598434901','945',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','zzid'),(664,0,0,0,'Day69','_We are day69__An experimental death metal band from ghy.Formed by the end of 2010. We are hardcore metaloholics.... ','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Day69/194680920549614','','','','194680920549614','943',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','day69'),(665,0,0,0,'Misha Mansoor','Bulb (2009) \nPeriphery - Periphery (2010)','','http://www.facebook.com/mishaperipherymansoor','','','','166737803377065','940',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','misha-mansoor'),(666,0,0,0,'Mad Orange Fireworks','The band was put together as a desperate act of survival by singer/songwriter Michael Dias. With a song bank in his head building up for over 7 years now, he needed to let it all out somehow. After around a year of hunting down the right accompanies, it was just by chance that he met metal head Shravan Bendapudi. The two jammed up and hit it off right away. The same chemistry came about previously when Michael started playing with the ever groovin Kaushik Kumar on the bass. And when the three came together, the fireworks just lit up the atmosphere... The creative conflicts that came about when Michael introduced his unique guitar sounds to Kaushik\'s funkiness were immense. And all this was hammered down to a perfect combo when Shravan layered his beats in. As a result, we have \"MAD ORANGE FIREWORKS!!!\"','','http://www.facebook.com/MadOrangeFireworks','','','','184627381581832','938',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','mad-orange-fireworks'),(667,0,0,0,'Absence Of The Sacred','ABSENCE OF THE SACRED has grown to be one of the leading forces in the Asian Metal scene since their inception in 2005 with three full-length albums, two EPs and an official music video. \n\nA constantly evolving band, ABSENCE OF THE SACRED infuses elements from various sub-genres of Extreme Metal into a flowing yet twisted technical attack on the senses. \n\nABSENCE OF THE SACRED has been featured and well-received in numerous local and international publications including METAL HAMMER (UK), ZERO TOLERANCE (UK), METAL MANIACS (US), THE NEW PAPER (SG), TODAY (SG), LIVE MAGAZINE (SG), JUNK MAGAZINE (MY), TIMEOUT MAGAZINE (SG), BLABBERMOUTH.NET, METALSTORM, METAL MAGAZINE (TH), CHERISH THE DARKNESS MAGAZINE (TH), MTV HEADBANGERS BLOG, THE SUNDAY LEADER (LK), etc. The band has also received international airplay of their songs on radio, featured on National TV in Asia as well as web podcasts and their albums distributed in Asia, Europe and the US. \n\nThe band has played in major local Metal Festivals as well as notable Metal Festivals around the region such as COLOMBO OPEN AIR 2011 (Sri Lanka) and BANGCOCK 2008 (Thailand). ABSENCE OF THE SACRED was also the first professional Metal act in Singapore that was given a resident spot in a weekly event Heart of Darkness (sponsored by Jack Daniels) at a local club called The Gas Haus, which ran successfully for almost a year. Plans for tours are in the works for 2012. \n\nWith their latest third full-length studio album Come Hither O Herald of Death, the current line-up of the band features members and ex-members from IMPIETY (SG), DAATH (US) and DYING FETUS (US). Guest musicians on the album include members from visceral and established Metal acts such as CHTHONIC (TWN), DAWN OF AZAZEL (NZ) and SPEARHEAD (UK).','','http://www.facebook.com/absenceofthesacred','','','','15044342684','919',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','absence-of-the-sacred'),(668,0,0,0,'Dead  Incarnation','Dead Incarnation is a Bangalore-based Metalcore/Melodic Death Metal/Heavy Metal band.It comprises of Ashish(lead guitars) , Ramiz(rhythm guitars) ,  Abhimanyu(bass) , Siddhanth(vox) & Somarshi(drums).\nThe band was formed in mid 2010 by Ashish .After a different intial lineup the band finally went 5 piece when Siddhanth  and Ramiz joined in recently in June 2011.\nIt seeked its prominence after being the city round winners of \"ICICI DIRECT.COM ASPIRE MUSIC TO MONEY CHALLENGE ON ZEE BUSINESS\" 2010 along side 3 other bands. ','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Dead-Incarnation/113678805370355','','','','113678805370355','912',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dead-incarnation'),(669,0,0,0,'Feathers of Jatinga','The name Feathers Of Jatinga is derived from Jatinga,a small village in North Cachar Hills (Assam, India). The place is famous for the mass suicide of migratory birds in between October to January. These birds come out at night and straightaway hit the various lights being lit in the village. The reason is still unknown and many researchers or scientists have failed to answer the same\n\nFeathers of Jatinga was formed in July,2010 by Vedant Kaushik (Former\nVocalist of IIIrd Sovereign and current Shades Of Retribution) and Vishal J. Singh\n(Amogh Symphony, Acrophase, Robots Pulling Levers). The idea was to create a cold and dark  ambience with the sound giving an atmospheric feel of the North-Eastern winter on a Doom/Alternative/Ambient bed. The concept of the songs deals with human instincts, paranormal behaviour, mixed emotions and feelings. Currently, they are working on their debut album which will be out soon.\n\nP.S - Guest slide guitar and solo in \"Frozen lies\" by Mark Hawkins(Soul Cycle, Assimilated Mind Phase, Robots Pulling Levers)\n\nOfficial email :  feathersofjatinga@gmail.com','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Feathers-of-Jatinga/142332369154070','','','','142332369154070','912',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','feathers-of-jatinga'),(670,0,0,0,'Blues Before Sunrise','','','http://www.facebook.com/Blues.Before.Sunrise','','','','156177164004','908',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','blues-before-sunrise'),(671,0,0,0,'Aks','At Aks, we do not conform to a single genre of music, as such. We make music according to what we \'feel\', and our genres vary from reggae to rock, electronica to sufi, and so does our themes, from patriotic to mischievous, sad to funny, etc.\n\nAks became the first Indian band to launch their track, \'Ek Ladki\' in 2 different countries (Indonesia & India) on the same date over 2 different mediums (Radio dBs 101.9 FM, Banjarmasin & Internet).\n\nWe have also been interviewed and our tracks have been played on \'One Bengaluru, One Music\' on Radio One 94.3 FM (Bangalore). We brought out our first single \"Kisse Aise Bhi Hain\" on Independence Day, 2011 and plan to bring out one produced single every month.\n\nWe are presently ranked #8 on the Reverbnation Rock Charts for Bangalore (as of November 30th, 2011), & were at #8th from #44 in just over a night of the release of our debut single with more than a thousand plays & hits already, to our Reverbnation Profile. We have hit a high of #4 in the past.\n\nAks has played at Legends of Rock, Kyra, Italia Ristorante & Bar in Bangalore, with more gigs in the pipeline in the coming months. Aks has won the Bangalore prelims to represent the city at Tata Photon Max presents WORMEFEST \'11 with VH1 in association with Vladivar on 18th December, 2011 in New Delhi.\n\nAll the band members are individual artists too. We live music & draw inspiration from two essential things: Life & Love. Everything we play, write and sing portrays our experiences & belief; reflections of our true self.\n\n\'Aks\' is not just a band for the five of us. It is who we are.\n\nOnline Links:-\n\nReverbnation Profile ~ www.reverbnation.com/akstheband\nFacebook Page ~ www.facebook.com/akstheband\nTwitter Page ~ www.twitter.com/akstheband\n','reach.aks@live.com, aksmusicbangalore@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/akstheband','','','','178505278863074','906',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','aks'),(672,0,0,0,'Gino Banks Official','Gino has been fooling around with the drums since he was 8 years old and took it up seriously at the age of 15. He is the son of Louiz Banks, India \'s legendary jazz pianist and composer. He toured Australia and China with his fathers\' indo-jazz fusion band SANGAM playing percussion when he was just 9 years old.\nGino is a versatile player, this trait leads him to performing and recording with artists and bands of all types of genres, artists like his father Louiz Banks, Pt. Hariprasad Chaurasia, Pt. Shivkumar Sharma, Ustad Rashid Khan, Fazal Qureshi, Taufique Qureshi, and Pt. Vikku Vinayakram; to Bollywood sessions and gigs with Shankar-Ehsaan-Loy, Salim-Sulaiman, Vishal-Shekhar, Pritam, and Hariharan; to fusion groups SILK, Yuva, Niladri Kumars Sitar Funk, Rakesh Chaurasia, Amaan & Ayaan Ali Khan and Bala Bashkar; to rock bands like Helga\'s Fun Castle, Gary Lawyer, Skinny Alley, Joe Alvares and Zero. He has performed with international musicians like Mike Stern, Guthrie Govan, Tony Lakatos, George Brooks, Leni Stern, Jay Oliver, Angela Hagenbach, Jonas Desai, Carl Clements and The Maske Trio. As well as with Dance Troupes like Pt. Birju Maharaj\'s Kathak Group, Aditi Bhagwat, Kaveri Sageder and Terence Lewis Contemporary Dance Company and many more.\n\nHe has also had the Honor and Privilege of playing a few tracks on the Miles From India Album produced by Bob Belden, nominated for a 2009 Grammy in the Contemporary Jazz Category with Times Square Records, NYC; a fusion of Great Indian Classical Musicians and Miles Davis Alumni Musicians.\n\nGino Banks Endorses:\nTama Drums\nZildjian Cymbals\nEvans Drumheads\nVic Firth Drumsticks\nLP Percussion \n\nGINO BANKS DISCOGRAPHY\n\nBOLLYWOOD:\n SHANKAR EHSAAN LOY  DON\n SHANKAR EHSAAN LOY  WAKE UP SID\n VISHAL SHEKHAR  ALADIN\n VISHAL SHEKHAR  I HATE LUV STORYS\n VISHAL SHEKHAR - BREAK KE BAAD\n SANGEET AND SIDDHARTH HALDIPUR  FRUIT & NUT\n SOHAIL SEN  WHATS YOUR RAASHEE\n SALIM SULAIMAN - 8X10 TASVEER\n SALIM SULAIMAN  LUCK\n SALIM SULAIMAN  KURBAAN\n SALIM SULAIMAN  PYAAR IMPOSSIBLE\n SALIM SULAIMAN  TEEN PATTI\n SALIM SUALIMAN - BAND BAAJA BAARAAT\n PRITAM  BADMAASH COMPANY\n PRITAM  NEWYORK\nJAZZ:\n LOUIZ BANKS - LABYRINTH\nFUSION:\n VARIOUS ARTISTS (LOUIZBANKS/BOB BELDEN)  MILES FROM INDIA\n RONU MAJUMDAR/LOUIZBANKS/SATYAJIT TALWALKAR\n FUSION YATRA\nPOP:\n SUNEETA RAO - WAQT ','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Gino-Banks-Official/205184539491664','','','','205184539491664','899',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','gino-banks-official'),(673,0,0,0,'Snatch D\'Monk','The band began with a group of five students teaming up to represent Xavier Institute of Communications at the citys most prestigious inter-collegiate festival, Malhar held in August last year. On realizing that they shared a lot in common besides their musical inclinations, the band decided to take this group a step forward, roped in a bassist and thus formed, Snatch DMonk.\n\nSnatch DMonk is a Mumbai based versatile rock band that cuts through varied genres of music with musicians from across the country and from an array of backgrounds. With influences ranging from funk to alternative rock and blues to progressive rock, the band is slowly gaining recognition for their unique style of music. Capitalizing on a catchy name which does have a lot of sub-text and connotations to it (will be revealed soon!); the band hopes to make a strong impact in the Indian rock scene with their live acts and records.\n\nSome of the bands influences include the likes of Jamiroquai, Alice in Chains, Bob Marley, Days of the New, Dave Matthews Band, Eddie Vedder, Eric Clapton, Frank Zappa, Incubus, RHCP, Hendrix, John Mayer, Jose Gonzalez, Led Zeppelin, Nick Drake, Phish, Porcupine Tree, Zakk Wylde, Tenacious D, The Grateful Dead, The Beatles, Blues Traveler. The band doesnt believe in covering music literally but making each cover their own.\n\nThe band has recorded two rough demo tracks at present and intends recording loads more in the near future. Something Else and 6 March, 2111, though very different from each other, both stem from the variety, versatility and different styles of the band members.\n','Keegan D\'Mello @ snatchdmonk@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Snatch-DMonk/197151486753','','','','197151486753','896',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','snatch-dmonk'),(674,0,0,0,'Howlin\' Lord','Country rocknroll with a world weary authority \n\nDebut album \'GOLD FURY\' out now!!\n\n\'This could be the best album of 2011\' Maverick Magazine\n\nIn keeping with the spirit of Hank Williams, bleak, broken and classy. \n**** Venue Magazine\n','littleparadiseinfo@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/howlinlord.fb','','','','17968074332','895',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','howlin-lord'),(675,0,0,0,'Sanguis Imperem','UPCOMING ASSAULTS:\nSanguis Imperem- \"In Glory We March Towards Our Doom\" CD/LP\n  (Invictus Productions and Hell\'s Headbangers Records)\n\nSanguis Imperem was formed during the waning months of 2006.  It is a celebration of the natural and a castigation of the cancerous.','blood_command@yahoo.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Sanguis-Imperem/253429157619','','','','253429157619','895',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sanguis-imperem'),(676,0,0,0,'Siddharth Sharma','Basically I am an engineer who graduated from \'Manipal Institute of Technology\' but failed to adhere to the corporate calling.\n\nA never ending passion for music left me venturing into the blissful and engaging world of music and chasing the dreams of becoming a music artist and composer.\n\nMy strengths lie in me honing my skills as a lead Guitarist and Vocalist.\n\nI\'ve been tinkering with the axe and have been composing for 4-5 years and am ready to reveal it all to the world. \n\nAlways had a penchant for writing and composing originals and singing.\nThe greatest feeling i\'ve experienced is seeing people\'s reactions to my creations and how they move to it.\n\nThis page has original sound tracks laced with a strong message.\n\nCheers, \nStay happy :)\n','9953269110, ','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Siddharth-Sharma/186911318014332','','','','186911318014332','891',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','siddharth-sharma'),(677,0,0,0,'The Pictish Trail','','Trailer Park Press','http://www.facebook.com/thepictishtrail','','','','161776723869741','891',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-pictish-trail'),(678,0,0,0,'Zehen (Manipal)','Zehen started off in 2008 as a casual project started by 4 friends jamming on ear friendly tunes based in Manipal. It was only after a month of simple fun, they realized the real potential of the band when around a 1000 people turned up for their first gig, singing along to their songs. Gaining immense popularity locally, they started working on setting up a good-big-live act. \n\nWith a few additions and lineup changes, Zehen now consists of four core members AniRudh(Guitars), Utkarsh(Vocals), Mahak(Keyboards) and Aditya(Bass). In 2011 Zehen decided to self produce their songs as they wanted to have full control over each element in the process, with AniRudh handling the duties of the producer/engineer. \n  \nFulfilling educational duties as engineering students, the band utilizes all its free time composing, recording and playing music and has managed to play shows, headlining a few with a crowd attendance of more than 5000 thus creating a good fan base. \n\nThe band is currently working in the studio and are expected of a release in 2012. \n\nStay tuned for updates.','','http://www.facebook.com/ZehenManipal','','','','155822474474269','888',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','zehen-manipal'),(679,0,0,0,'SertOne','','mail@meltedmusic.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/SertOne/148202888540558','','','','148202888540558','885',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sertone'),(680,0,0,0,'TaTvA','Tatva is headlining the musical peak of Indias entertainment industry as one of the most prolific and energetic artists for nearly a decade now. The Artiste has had support from the Various Dj\'s/Producers such as Cheb I sabbah, Bobby Friction, Pathaan, Nihaal (BBC UK Radio), etc.\n\nHIs Latest Ep Release saw him gaining support of the biggies such as Markus Schulz, Global Dj Broadcast, Suffused, Hypnotic Duo, Aurl Frequency, Frangelico, Michael and Levan, etc.\n\nTatva Kundalini is of Indian descent and works from his sunny studio based out of Delhi. His musical journey started from a very young age and Tatva realized that he was musically inclined all the way to make it his business and excel at it, so he went on to train himself in various instruments, classically inclined and that which helped him hone his skills to strumming the Guitar to taking on Keyboards at a tender age and even lending his vocals to the music he so intelligently puts forth.\n\nHe is sought after for his competent intelligent productions & Dj sets in the arena of big Chill, Trance, and Progressive with Tech edged goliaths. He also enjoys a weighty presence in the Psychedelic scene of India and internationally as well.\n\nTop the busy musical sojourn with the wonder starter of the fiery label called Chill Om Records keeps the mighty music man busy with productions of heavy gold in Electronic dance music.\n\nThe future is packed with dynamite Remixes/ Productions for major renowned dance Djs as well for his own, plus studio time is the order of the day, album releases from the house of Chill Om along side guest dj sets and live performances making up for a busy musical calendar.\n\n TaTvA Kundalini also has 2 regular radio shows on Eilo. Org (Sugar Gets Me Hi Sessions) and Pure Fm (Kundalini Rising), Both leading radios in the global dance music market.\n\nFeel Free to Listen to TaTvA Kundalini\'s tunes on Chill Om\'s online music player on this site!','info@chillomrecordsindia.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/TaTvA/105024190602','','','','105024190602','882',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','tatva'),(681,0,0,0,'The Captains Of Hook','','thecaptainsofhook@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/thecaptainsofhook','','','','186574558092051','882',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-captains-of-hook'),(682,0,0,0,'HFT','HFT play a style of music that could easily be called world jazz, jazz that is urbane and savvy, a well-travelled, warm music that is equally at ease being in the sun as resting in the shade. \n\nAJmellifluous melody line maker on the guitar and sometime scatman in a hat, Lewfunky bass line plucker and creator of psychedelia in song, and Suchetseated beatkeeper on drums from as far afield as Peru and Uganda, make up this trio. \n\nInfluences for the band range from Miles Davis to Baaba Maal. Listening to them live, youd hear jazz through the guitar melodies, bass runs & cymbals, fusion through the raga-esque phrasing and scat, world music in the Afrobeat drum grooves \n\nDrawing inspiration from everywhere, HFTs music speaks of the here and now. Music as it is, sounding the best it can.','','http://www.facebook.com/hftmusicindia','','','','172845989425536','286',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','hft'),(683,0,0,0,'Renegade (INDIA)','Formed in 2009 by Mario and Michael, the band was complete when Antony and Steven were roped in.\nThey started off by taking part in college competitions and in 2010 they began playing in the main stream.\nThe 4 of them studied together for 10 years in school and have been friends all their lives!! They concentrate on blending melody and aggression.\n\n About our music we say \" We try to fuse primitive styles with an excess of heavy metal, a tinge of melody and clean vocals to create simple yet orchestrated and socially relevant music.\"','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Renegade-INDIA/155788054459058','','','','155788054459058','877',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','renegade-india'),(684,0,0,0,'Vichitra','Vichitra is a band formed by Amyth and the bass guitarist Ruthvi by the name suggested by the vocalist Sujith in 2010 from Bangalore, India.\nIt was a band meant to be in kannada for all the rock enthusiasts who would have a new taste of rock in their native language.\nThough an idea born a couple of years ago, it was not fully a full fledged participation. An year later, in 2010, the band members had found a very talented young drummer Aniketh, barely 13 years old, completing the band lineup.\nFrom there on, the band has been actively involved in composing their own tracks, experimenting with all sort of genre.\n\nTheir first song titled \'bodhane\' has been a huge hit, though recorded as a demo version, on the Internet.It is a song touching the depth of spiritual awareness that actually touched the tastes of many  rock lovers.\n\nThe band eventually came up with their second hit \'kanna mucchale\' which describes the turmoils of the transition from childhood to adulthood. It was only an acoustic version recorded by sujith and amyth which took the band  among the top five on reverbnation.\nThe band later came out with a rock devotional song dedicated to lord ganesha which was brilliantly improvised by the band mates and gained huge accolades when they played it live at kyra, bangalore.\nThe band have also been concentrating on social issues like current politics, the position of Indian farmers and so, for which the songs have been worked out.\n\nThe band\'s founder member Amyth (19) has been a guitarist since 2008 and is pretty well known for playing at several live performances throughout bangalore. He is also an amateur photographer whose works have been appreciated even among the professionals. He is also well known as the front man of another english punk band \"Skrewd\" with a different set of band mates. His dream to revolutionize rock in kannada was fulfilled by his brother Sujith, and his band mates Ruthvi and Aniketh. Today he is the lead guitarist and also a composer who also provides backing vocals to Vichitra.\n\nAmyth and the band co-founder Ruthvi (16), met at battle of the bands 10, and discovered they had similar interest and their dream of building a kannada rock band was further strengthened. Ruthvi a student from Jain college also plays and composes for the band. He also works on music projects, plays and composes for Primal Theory with Aniketh, the drummer of Vichitra too.\n\nThough he seems little, he can never be underestimated with a sheer amount of talent he displays. Aniketh (14), a school kid from Sri Aurobindo Memorial School, preparing for his 8th grade exams is a killer drummer for this band. With those deceptive innocent eyes, nobody can guess that this kid is capable of also playing keyboard, guitar,tabla, mrudanga and also classical instruments. A very jovial kid, Aniketh is a gift for Vichitra!\n\nThe band\'s lead singer and lyricist Sujith (23) is a CS engg graduate who also was a poet since childhood and had diverse interests in the field of story writing as well. During his college days, he has also collaborated with his friends and made his own movies and finds huge interests in the field of script writing and cinema. His choice of topics for their songs varies from spirituality to politics to the dark aspects of life. A simpleton by his looks and life, he never really appears as a person who actually hides such an amount of talent within him.','vichitraband@gmail.com ','http://www.facebook.com/vichitraband','','','','165624073466765','874',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','vichitra'),(685,0,0,0,'Sumith Ramachandran','Often labeled one of the most jaw-dropping guitar players in the country, Sumith Ramachandran has been performing professionally since the age of 9! When his friends were discovering the joys of reading and writing, Sumith was unknowingly honing his perfect pitch skills.  \n\nWith a performance average of 250+ gigs per calendar year, Sumith spends the remaining days perfecting his art, composing, programming, arranging and sequencing his upcoming album, and updating himself and his home studio on latest trends in the music world.\n\nSumith Ramachandran is clearly among the most skilled and talented guitar players in India who can straddle varied styles such as jazz-rock, classic rock, country, blues and Carnatic genres with equal ease.  It is this versatility that is his U.S.P.\n','Plan B Entertainment','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Sumith-Ramachandran/180835085262630','','','','180835085262630','873',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sumith-ramachandran'),(686,0,0,0,'ghost wave','inspired by skate vids, persian rugs and little richard','','http://www.facebook.com/ghostwave','','','','149969124495','872',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ghost-wave'),(687,0,0,0,'God Particle','','','http://www.facebook.com/godparticleband','','','','158163517540394','871',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','god-particle'),(688,0,0,0,'Suicide Avenue','','','http://www.facebook.com/SuicideAvenue','','','','235287556521738','865',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','suicide-avenue'),(689,0,0,0,'Pitch Black Symphony- India','PITCH BLACK SYMPHONY popularly known as PBS, is a Pune based Progressive, Psychedelic Rock outfit. Playing for almost three years in the Indian rock circuit, PBS has discovered its own unique sound. We love to fuse the feel of old school rock with new age sound, thus not only relating to todays youth but to people of all ages.\n\nImagination has no boundaries- thats our principle. Individually all the members are inspired by artist from over a variety of genres. When all of these inspirations, imaginations, thoughts and emotions come together in the jam room the creation of our unique sound happens...\n','+91-9769626294,+919845015183','http://www.facebook.com/pitchblacksymphonyindia','','','','131345573583856','864',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','pitch-black-symphony-india'),(690,0,0,0,'Feedback - BBSR','Feedback is a junction of a lot of various streams of music, from western classical to metal. These varied interests are brought together by the shared passion for music amongst the members. Formed in august 2010, it consists of Vivek JC and Abinash \'Daga\', along with Argal and Alok \'paki\' from the erstwhile Negative Feedback. Feedback is basically an offshoot of the same with new sounds brought in by new members. The originals of the band showcase these confluences of cultures. The band has also played at XIM-B Xpressions, The first band from the state to ever feature in this event. It has also played at a number of pub gigs and other public performances to establish itself as one of the city\'s and state\'s foremost band.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Feedback-BBSR/151068364929647','','','','151068364929647','859',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','feedback-bbsr'),(691,0,0,0,'Insane Prophecy','Formed back in 2008 by Ifty (Drums) and Parvez (Former vocalist), Insane Prophecy, with five members in the band played its first gig in the Assam Engineering Colleges annual rock fest  Pyrokinesis 08, and made it to the finals. At that time, it played stuffs from Napalm Death and their then original numbers  War Cry, Resurrection and Rape of Democracy.\n\nUnfortunately, after a couple of months, the band had to split ways to pursue higher education which resulted in the exit of its guitarist and bassist. After a hiatus of two months, the band reformed with Xulfi on bass, Bikash on guitars and Abhishek on keyboards. With this new line-up being heavily influenced by some Symphonic Black Metal acts like Dimmu Borgir, Cradle of Filth, etc, the band changed its genre to Symphonic Black Metal which also resulted in discarding all of their previous original numbers and started covering songs from the said genre.\n\nThen there a time came when Parvez and Abhishek walked out from the band and with their exit, Insane Prophecy fluctuated from Symphonic Black Metal to Black Metal with Valefar joining in on vocals. On basis of its new sound, i.e, Black Metal, Insane Prophecy recorded its first single  Blasphemy ov a Diabolic.. Their sound clearly concentrates on stuffs from Norwegian Black Metal fused with other Death Metal sub-genres. They combine the sound perfectly with Black Metal elements full of blast-beats, scratching riffs with screams and Death metal growls and groovy guitar riffing alongwith some sturdy and melodic bass lines. With the new sound, the band also started following up more extreme metal bands such as Immortal, Behemoth, Belphegor etc. Ifty writes all the lyrics, drums and vocal patterns, whereas Xulfi and Bikash write their respective music.  \n\nSubsequently, Valefar quit the band, which led Insane Prophecy to be a three-piece outfit with Ifty & Xulfi doing Vocals along with Drums and Bass respectively & Bikash on Guitars which is presumed to be the permanent line-up of the band. \n\nTheir song, Blasphemy ov a Diabolic got featured in Episode 13 of the Flaming Skull Metalcast which also featured an interview with Galder (Guitarist) Dimmu Borgir. IPs debut EP Apogee of An Inquisition is finally released on January 21st 2012 at Mumbai. It has been accepted pretty well by the underground music scene in India.  Brutalism.com rated AOAI 4/5.','Xulfi Nawaz : insaneprophecyband@gmail.com / llxulfi@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/insaneprophecy','','','','116779861685393','858',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','insane-prophecy'),(692,0,0,0,'Aayudh The Band','The band was formed in the fall of 2010, a result of the realization that dawned upon the two leading men of the band - Jayant (vocals) and Pravesh (guitars); who on realizing the magical potential of music and the joy that it could bring to a troubled world decided to start a Hindi Rock/Fusion band with the sole aim of promoting music to everyone they met in their lives and strifes.\n\nThey, understanding that any good band needs a solid time keeper,  searched and found their backbone to the band - their percussionist and drummer Omkar. Omkar has been the Man in the band whom everybody came to love and trust and who always makes sure the band is always in time with the jive. \n\nEven with a line up of three talented musicians they realized something was missing. The most important factor that makes a song complete - the bass. The hunt for a bassist led them to Karan who was a prolific musician in his own right. A splendid bassist and to everyone\'s wonderful surprise he also had the ability to produce brilliant melodies on the go. In Karan they thus found a holistic musician and a humble person who has become a more than valuable member of the band.\n\nNow, its time to give a soul to our Lineup.We found our keyboardist Shantam goel. He touches a distinct feel to the tracks.He knows what keys are to be pressed and when to give the soulful n electronica feel to the tracks. Here we complete our Line up for Aayudh.\n\n\nThe band is essentially comprises of 17 year-olds whose passion for music knows no bounds. Talent is on their side, youth is on their side and with the support of a large circle of family and friends they hope reach the pinnacle of success while moving in a straight line across the apexes of the curving roads ahead. \n\nHere is hoping that you will become a part of their travel towards fame and fortune\'s glory. See you at their next gig.\nGod bless and Godspeed.','','http://www.facebook.com/aayudhtheband','','','','116392941707297','857',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','aayudh-the-band'),(694,0,0,0,'Delhi Kings','Delhi Kings, the unapologetic Violent, Sexist, dramatic, romantic and fully happening Kings of Hip-Hop & Rap music.\n\nDelhi Kings was formed by RENO, GD, Master Miz and Rapper Keher. \n\nIn many ways this is the most Talented and Happening group in the history of Rap & Hip-Hop with their own Choreography and music production (DK Production).\n\nGroup has everything what it takes to give you a real feel from life struggle to Love, sex, money, High Roll and Gang Bang from their music. They are very well committed working to bring in more stuff to fulfill the fantasies of teenagers & fans across the globe.\n\nDelhi Kings are the masters of Live performances with the experience of 100+ shows, concerts, club nights, college fest & private parties all over the country in Solo, dual & Group performances..\n\nDelhi Kings bringing you the hottest and different experience in Music Entertainment industry bringing you the best Rap & Hip-Hop music.\n\nFor more updates Please stay connected with us on \n\nwww.reverbnation.com/DelhiKings\n