rums and Mansur Farhat Yusufzai on the bass.\n\nOver the years, there were a few changes in the lineup.\n\nThe current lineup is\nAnandit Sachdev- Drums\nMansur Farhat Yusufzai- Bass\nSajjad Zaidi- Vocals\nTarun Cotra- Lead\nHammad Ur Rahman- Rhythm\n\nOur music is all about the fusion of different styles of playing to create something new with a strong lyrical base. \nIn the expression of our emotions through our music, we do not let the genres limit us, not even language. Yet we have a certain \"sound\" to our band which is hard to ignore. \nThe lyrics are inspired from the feelings we\'ve all felt at a point or another. \nWe\'ll let our music speak the rest..','Mansur Farhat Yusufzai: 9999257734','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Big-Foot/132005706850504','','','','132005706850504','840',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','big-foot'),(700,0,0,0,'Heathen Beast','Heathen Beast believes in no god and no religion. We write about the world and it\'s religion as we see it, we write about how it encompass and controls the masses in our country India. Our music symbolizes self belief and the fact that we choose our own path and make our own destiny. There is no God that writes your life and not everything that is bad in this world is a consequence of that karma. You are responsible. Heathen Beast plays a form of brutal metal to connect with those who think like we do. The Heathen Beast Shall Be Unleashed Upon Thee.\n\nHeathen Beast is the formation of three.\n\nCarvaka who believes religion was invented and made up by men, having no divine authority.\n\nSamkhya who denies the existence of God.\n\nMimamsa who rejects the notion of God and says that human action itself is enough to create the necessary circumstances for the enjoyment of its fruits.\n\n','theheathenbeast@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/HeathenBeast','','','','158845830811524','837',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','heathen-beast'),(701,0,0,0,'Purple In GreeN','Purple In Green was formed in Late 2010 by Mayurath with the intention of being solely a studio project . But soon, the project was to be turned into a live act and so after many a line up changes mukund joined the band filling up drum duties . The collaboration of these two creative minds resulted in a mix of ambient music with metal .The two continue to be the only studio members who are involved in the songwriting process along with Deepak on bass .','Mayurath Gupta (09678071325)  Mukund Pandey (9999840086)','http://www.facebook.com/purpleingreen','','','','102336559832762','832',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','purple-in-green'),(702,0,0,0,'Sankraman','Sankraman formed in 2008 with some music lovers who want to create music with their own style of playing but due to some problem it was not done and sankraman got inactive but then after some years it started again in 2011 when all members start meeting each other after a long time n start jamming and then some nice things happend and after that Sankraman formed completely...\nWe are inspired from Indi - pop,sufi, Rock, blues or jazz & Bollywood commercial music. Every kind of music have its own importance so we are totaly inspired from all genres..\nMembers of this band are eager to play the music, which touches the soul of people. Sankraman band belongs to the people, who did not know each other earlier but the thing which brought them together is Music!!\nwe love to play instrumentals n try to make a rock, pop, fusion kind of stuff.\nwe play music because we love music.....\nWe have performed as a Guest Band in many College festivals, Clubs & Lounge, Night Clubs & Discs ,Corporates Companies & Events across India!!\n\nAchievements by Sankraman:-\n\n- Sankraman Won the Youth Nexus 2012 Rocknova title at Moti Lal Nehru College and Selected For Delhi Daredevil Team to play at IPL matches.\n\n- Won the Battle of Band Title Winners at Accenture\'12 fest by Acharya Narend