ared stage with Midnight garden factor, DOTH, silver tears, incipit, melodrama, Bhayanak maut, etc.farrago is working on its improvisations n developments in musical interest with a dream to win peoples heart n reach the acme.FARRAGO means mixture of a blend of heterogenous or homogenous elements , living or non living..FARRAGO would be experimenting with glam ,grunge, and power metal too... they would also prefer hard rock.to notify it is an exerimental band ,trying to touch every possible corners of different genres.every member of it is a learner of course but still ON ITS WAY TO MAKE JORHAT PROUD,AXOM PROUD ,INDIA PROUD ... AND THE WORLD if, its possible with all of their hard work n its fans blessings and best wishes','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Farrago/178278918883971','','','','178278918883971','784',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','farrago'),(722,0,0,0,'Shilpa Ananth','I\'m Shilpa Ananth. I love music and experiment with all kinds of music. I just got into my dream school - Berklee School of Music and intend to make my dream career come true. \n\nI want to create. something.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Shilpa-Ananth/170605449621300','','','','170605449621300','781',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','shilpa-ananth'),(723,0,0,0,'Blue Temptation','Nathan and Greg formed \'Blue Temptation\' on 28 Jan 2010. Well, the name speaks for itself that when the band pays any song regardless of which genre, there is always a feeling involved and the Blues is all that comes out. There is always like a temptation to play the blues and to dwell in its warm embrace.\n\nAs session musicians, Nathan and Greg have played some gigs around Shillong, which is their home time, with well known local artists.\n\nAs time goes by and love for music grows, these two brothers decided to take their musical abilities to the next level - influencing many with the music they produce.\n\nShepherd Najiar a close friend and musical companion of the brothers decided to join in their musical journey a day after it was formed.\n\nThe band started out as a three piece with Greg on drums, Nathan on bass and Shepherd on guitars. \n\nWith many gigs and shows in their book, the band came to know many people and among them, came along a friend who instantly bonded with the band. Realizing the need for a second guitarist, Greg shifted to guitars and Daryl who is the drummer from the band Polyticks, stepped in to experience the \' Blue Temptation , which is a feeling that sometimes take the band to a place out of this world  ','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Blue-Temptation/307859470139','','','','307859470139','772',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','blue-temptation'),(724,0,0,0,'Turfe','Starting out in December 2009 as an acoustic ambient project, Turfe evolved into an indie/ambient/alternative band. They took a year off writing songs and then went on to play in venues such as:\nLive from the Console (Mumbai)\nThe Escape festival for Arts and Music (Naukuchiyatal)\nTurquoise Cottage (Gurgaon)\nThe Living Room (Delhi)\nSomeplace Else (Calcutta)','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Turfe/138106152927028','','','','138106152927028','770',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','turfe'),(725,0,0,0,'Microphon3','Microphon3 is one of the front runners of the Indian Desi Hip Hop scene. A poet for the past decade and a half this 27 year old writes and raps everything he knows about. Also the only rapper in the country to have back to back releases on a Youth National Channel. Has performed for social causes and rocked clubs from Bluefrog to massive festivals like NH7 weekender.','microphon3.in@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/MICR0PH0N3','','','','148284461849031','769',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','microphon3'),(726,0,0,0,'Contaminated','Contaminated is a metal band from the city of Allahabad,U.P. Formed in October 2009. The band consists of Vocalist Pranav, Guitarist Emmanuel,bassist Pushpank,drummer Victor.','victor- +919005409490 | Emmanuel- +918601695720','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Contaminated/135479586506963','','','','135479586506963','767',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','contaminated'),(727,0,2,2,'The Hoodwink Circle','The Hoodwink Circle is an eclectic mix of performers from all over Bombay. The members also play for or have played for bands like Louis Banks, Toufeeq Qureshi, Shibani Kashyap, Ash Chandler, Nandoo Bhende, Merlin Desouza, Manasi Scott, The Bombay Rock Project, Gino Banks, Para-Vayu, The Echoes, Sheldon d Silva, Asha Bhosle, Susie Q etc; and have come together to pursue their true musical roots, which are primarily based on Funk, Alternative and their derivations.\r\n\r\nThe band was initially called Wasabi, and gained local fame by competing in a few college competitions. Around October 2008, guitarist Sanju and bassist Ishaan met through the Nandoo Bhende Band; and the band hasnt looked back since.\r\n\r\nThe Hoodwink Circles primary musical influence is the Red Hot Chili Peppers. Apart from this, Jazz Funk, Pop/Alternative Rock, and Progressive Rock/Metal influence the band.\r\n\r\nImpeccable music is not meant only for a niche. The band strongly believes in making technical music, at the same time making it appeal to a light listener. The band also believes in making music that is universal that stems from day to day experiences in urban India.','Akhila Shankar +91-9920200655','http://www.facebook.com/thehoodwinkcircle','http://www.reverbnation.com/thehoodwinkcircle','','','219319718110792','764',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-hoodwink-circle'),(728,0,0,0,'The Thirteenth Note','Formed in 2010, worked on our skills and originals. \nStarted competing in 2011\nBKBIET, Pilani : DECIBEL War of Bands \'11 - Winners\nGHEC, Solan : OPUS \'11 - Winners\n','9873035718','http://www.facebook.com/thethirteenthnote','','','','124542330923733','764',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-thirteenth-note'),(729,0,0,0,'Blackheart','We all Were just Old time freinds ! since very childhood !\n\nAnd JUst Want tO sAY thAt We cAn FuCkInG bAnG yOur HeAd \\m/\\m/ ','Abhishek Sinha ( 9878842220 ) , Aman Sharma ( 8054256726 )','http://www.facebook.com/Blackheartindia','','','','199769946703357','764',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','blackheart'),(730,0,0,0,'Silver','   :! National winners of Yamaha Roxx 2008\n\n   :! Represented India in Taiwan at the Asian Beat 2008\n\n   :! Independence Rock XXIII winners\n\n STAY TUNED: coming soon to a city|town near you !!!\n   \n','','http://www.facebook.com/silverpune','','','','142825675782910','764',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','silver'),(731,0,0,0,'Clown WiTh a Frown','Coming out of the heavily influenced metal scene in Bangalore, guitarists Jonathan Reuben & Reuben Jacob and Drummer Pramod Pratap decided to move out and do something unique, different and fun.\n\nWhat began as a random jam one summer afternoon soon gained momentum and we began experimenting with different sounds, trying to fuse elements of rock, blues, funk and reggae into a fun listening experience. Soon Abheet Anand joined the band and began covering the bass side of things and Abigail soon followed as lead vocalist ultimately comprising Clown with a frown.\n\n\nMembers:\nGuitarist and Songwriter Jonathans style is a mix of funk, blues, reggae and jazz, he says he isnt influenced by anyone in particular but admires musicians like Freddie mercury, train, van halen, Alanis morisette.\n\nLead guitarist Reuben kicks things into overdrive, provides backing rhythm and helps build on the soundscape and draws influences from  Kings of Leon,Seventh wonder, Lincoln Brewster and Rascal Flatts among others.\n\nAbheet who plays bass, draws inspiration from bands such as Tool, Blink-182, Dream Theater, Red Hot Chilli Peppers, Dave Matthews Band, Incubus, This Town Needs Guns. He also admires and is majorly influenced by artists such as Brandon Boyd, John Mayer, Dave Matthews, Maynard James Keenan and Chris Cornell.\n\nAbigail who does the lead vocals further adds to the music  with a wide vocal range. In addition, she also plays the guitar and is a metal-head. She looks up to artists like Lou Rhodes, Nina Simone, Holly Brook and Maarko Saaresto.\n\nDrummer Pramod Pratap is a big fan of reggae and his influences are travis barker, the who, bob marley, john Bonham, mike portnoy.\n\n\nIn a time where metal ruled the music scene,\nTo bring out soulful melodies, we were keen.\nA mix of indie, pop, funk and alternative,\nAnd lyrics that capture everything that\'s sensitive.\nTogether we\'ve set out to capture your hearts with our sound,\nOne that\'s unconventional and new found.\nOne day you\'ll be a king with a crown,\nBut till then, you\'re just a Clown WiTh a Frown!\n','','http://www.facebook.com/ClownWiThaFrown','','','','218841608158929','762',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','clown-with-a-frown'),(732,0,0,0,'Tails On Fire','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Tails-On-Fire/226065844097958','','','','226065844097958','761',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','tails-on-fire'),(733,0,0,0,'Profane Death','','Gauravjeet -+917827740492  Ritvik-+919829404511','http://www.facebook.com/ProfaneDeath','','','','126572194035438','757',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','profane-death'),(734,0,0,0,'Lavender Carnage','Well now, the story of Lavender Carnage goes back to the summer of 2008. It was a very dry summer when (now ex) bassist Bharat and Srijan met for an informal jam at a CCD outlet. And this went on for every weekend until, pushed beyond even their remarkable tolerance, the good people frequenting the outlet begged them to stop the strangling cats and get a job or something. Huh!!! But SOON, they realized their mistake as the band went all (over) India, with receving le Cafe Coffee Day Grammie 2008 for the best Rock group....\n\nAnyway, time went by and the duo kept wondering whether to form a band at all or just play with the gold already received. They met a few drummers who didn\'t quite cut it, but did  kick-start with an old drummer friend. With hardly any practice, LC were  invited to participate in Independence Rock XXIII. Not their best gig. Pro - the band were called \"hawt\" by some chixs in the crowd, LC learned NEVER to cover Nickelback again, and the audience got to know about this oh so bright band from Delhi. \n\nThe next gigs were in Cafe Morrison (Delhi), Hard Rock Cafe, (Mumbai), and Independence Rock XXIV. LC went on to perform at quite a few College fests around the country, most recently headlining the D-School Annual Fest in Delhi 2010.\n\nLC\'s USP is simple. We are baby Green Day. We get that a lot and honestly we kinda like it. Our antics, style, and even fashion sense owe a lot to their influence.  But we\'re SLIGHTLY novel when it comes music.  While influenced by Green Day, it\'s still unique when it comes to our own songs. So, if you don\'t like us at all then go cry your heart out to Green Day. If they weren\'t alive and kicking neither would we, so you know who to blame. We;re trying to develop our versatiliy as well. We love punk, but that\'s not all we\'re gonna be playing. \n\nCheck out the left side for the names of the current members. Contact us for more details - weight, solvency, telephone numbers etc.\n\nSo, you want write to us, contact us, complain, bitch about something, brood about life kicking your sorry ass or compliment or interact with the members or whatever then write to us at lavendercarnage@gmail.com.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Lavender-Carnage/178249664203','','','','178249664203','753',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','lavender-carnage'),(735,0,0,0,'Ageless Yard','','','http://www.facebook.com/agelessyard','','','','115318608532970','753',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ageless-yard'),(736,0,0,0,'Once Chosen','Once Chosen is a Christian alternative experimental project spearheaded by guitarist/songwriter Lincoln Samuel and singer Arun Joseph. Around late 09\' an impromptu jam session between the duo ended in what became a genre bending bowl of alternative music that had a new and unique feel combining elements of spacey alt rock guitars and an un-orhtodox approach to fusing the same with karnatic vocal melodies. This was followed by the birth of their first ever single entitled \'Presence\'.\n\n\'Presence\' was eventually released as a demo on MyBand.com and went on to win at #6 on the MyBand music charts for their online music competition.\n\nThe band later released their EP SuperLiminal as a free digital download on their Reverbnation page in early 2010. The release was followed by rave reviews from Christian and Alt E-Zines, features on podcasts and compilations albums and radio airplay and interviews.\n\nThe ultimate aim of their music, songwriting and its direction as evident in their work is focused on the Christian faith and its values and its influence in their personal lives and on society and the world today.\n\nThe band has currently declared hiatus owing to personal reasons and have promised a possible return with a full length album and live shows.','','http://www.facebook.com/oncechosen','','','','119780981410125','753',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','once-chosen'),(737,0,0,0,'Naveen J. Anthraper','Lonely Im Crying music video:\n\nHis latest music video \'Lonely I\'m Crying\' has already been aired internationally on MTV !!\n\nAlso airing on National TV Channels VH1, Z Cafe, Channel V, Z Trendz, Zoom, SS Music, Asianet plus, Rosebowl, India vision, Kairali We, Asianet news, Surya news, Jai Hind news, Manorama news.\n\nLonely Im Crying is a song about loneliness, a feeling that anyone can relate to as its a universal theme.\n\nMy aim through this song is to send a glimmer of hope to those who have been left alone. I have spent five years in the making of this song and music video and its after a lot of hard work and dedication that I have managed to do so says Naveen.\n\nThe song has been recorded and mixed at the Yash Raj Films studio in Mumbai.\n\n\nContact:\n\nTo Book Naveen J. Anthraper & his team of musicians for live performances contact:\n\nMob: +91 - 9869941898 (Mumbai, India)\n+971 557206088 (UAE)\n\nEmail: njateam@gmail.com\n\nWeb Links:\n\nArtist profile: www.naveenjanthraper.blogspot.com\nYou Tube: www.youtube.com/naveenjanthraper\nFree Mp3 downloads: http://soundcloud.com/naveenjanthraper/lonelyimcrying\n\nFace book page: http://www.facebook.com/naveenjanthraper','','http://www.facebook.com/naveenjanthraper','','','','125588374140967','751',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','naveen-j-anthraper'),(738,0,0,0,'Lakhey band','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Lakhey-band/324012510958409','','','','324012510958409','750',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','lakhey-band'),(739,0,0,0,'Prosody','','','http://www.facebook.com/prosodypune','','','','61826069714','748',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','prosody'),(740,0,0,0,'P R O V I S S K','The band did not have a specific genre but with gaurav, entering the scene made the band go black. The mates are from different regions of india who met at a university campus; savy, parth and gaurav and akshay from delhi and kanav from himachal,and dev from Gorakhpur. After regrouping to its core line up provissk started playing live in a matter of few weeks and took the metal scene .Provissk brings forth a fresh approach to Black Metal digressing from the new abrasive sound, concocting a mixture of extreme tremolo picking riffs and mellow solos. Bounded to the sacred, band\'s first eva black song is about the sacred spirits being praised by human, asking for exponents to eliminate his enemy.Melodic synth by Gaurav in the intro and the chorus has uplifted this song to a new level. \n\"It can\'t be better than that \" says savy. \nWe are still working on few more blacks, lets see how this black shit comes out like says parth. ','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/P-R-O-V-I-S-S-K/133452493389026','','','','133452493389026','748',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','p-r-o-v-i-s-s-k'),(741,0,0,0,'Mystixz','The band was officially formed in early 2011 although the members have\nco-ordinated on various side projects over the past couple of years.\n\nOur music has emerged from a mix of heavy metal, progressive ,classic rock and acoustic melodies. With each member having varied musical influences and musical styles, our sound is a culmination of music from across genres,resulting in it being melodic,powerful and unique.\n\nTom was the vocalist of Distorted Frequencies and has a wide vocal\nrange with main influences being AlterBridge, GodSmack, Metallica to name a\nfew. Tom is also a radio personality and writes a lot of jingles.\n\n\nSagar Rao was the guitarist of Lucid Dreams and an Instrumental side project with Nitesh on Drums. A complete feel based guitarist and is the backbone of the melodic part of our sound. Experienced Jazz and Blues musician, his influences are Pink Floyd , Led Zepp ,Nick Drake , Opeth, CCR, BB King to name a few.\n\nEshwaran was the guitarist of Abandoned Wreckage and Tensyle. Mainly a thrash and heavy metal musical style his influences include Megadeth, Pantera, Dream Theater and various solo artists. He is also a session guitarist for a lot of musicians & has contributed a lot almost towards all genres of music.\n\nVivek was the bassist of Distorted Frequencies, Valhalla, Bifocal brothers and a couple of other side projects. He is versatile in playing a lot of styles on bass and is the groove king. His influences are Pink Floyd, Metallica , Megadeth, Opeth, Lamb Of God, to name a few.\n\nNitesh Nataraj was the drummer of River Sagittarius, Aathma and Lucid Dreams. He had also played Keyboards for Organised Chaos. He has done session drummings for various bands including Esperanto & Baja and has also collaborated with various top artists on a wide range of projects. Having a strong classical musical background he is adept with a variety of styles including Jazz/Latin, Reggae and Technical Heavy Metal. His main influences are Opeth, Dream Theater, Riverside, Meshuggah, Behemoth, Porcupine Tree, Textures, Gojira , Unleashed to name a few. His main inspirations are Buddy Rich, Steve Gadd, Dennis Chambers, Mike Portnoy, Gavin Harrison, Martin Lopez, Martin Axenrot & Tony Royster Jr.\n\n','','http://www.facebook.com/mystixz','','','','120586394703176','748',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','mystixz'),(742,0,0,0,'vairabi','','9803965596 / 9841332745','http://www.facebook.com/pages/vairabi/110249695659500','','','','110249695659500','748',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','vairabi'),(743,0,0,0,'Totem','Alternative/Experimental Rock','','http://www.facebook.com/TotemOfficial','','','','175527549145669','746',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','totem'),(744,0,0,0,'megal iNSANES','It all started long back, in the September of 2010, when 2 school buddies, RTR and MOJO thought of coming up with a band with their friend Key-ller (Sourabh Chatterjee), who played keyboard. These guys then met RDR (Anand Lama), a hip-hopper, club-tripper, insane rapper. The band then worked on various rap shits. And, introduced Hindi Rap Rock Scene. RDR had to leave in span of an year for his higher studies.\n\nSoon they met the other duo at the coffee shop, Micky and Dominick. Micky (the then vocalist), along with RTR, Key-ller and MOJO decided to jam.\n\nAfter a series of random jams and hangouts they discovered similar wave of Insanity. And, when the four of insanes collided they formed a completely different - MEGALiNSANES.\nAll they needed was the fifth insane to get in.\n\nSoon they had local shows along with various Bass players. Ritam, being one of them, joined MI for few shows and competitions but after finding dissimilarities in their music interest, he had to part. Later, Key-ller gave up his key-board and decided to manage the band since then.\n\nThen Micky buzzed his buddy Dominick from his old band who was in through his exile at the foot hills of Himalayas. Soon, after being called, Dominick ended up to be the Bassmonster for MI.\n\nSince their formation MI is considered to be one of the most promising band. Along with the combined abilities of the Frontman Micky, Guitarman RTR, Drum machine MOJO and the Bassmonster Dominick; the band is known for its adrenaline injecting, alarming stage performances.\n\nAfter their first single Detained Love made a serious rush in the Underground metal scene, MI is currently working on their upcoming EP.\n\nAnd, then the Bassmonster Dome had to part; Key-ller then decided to take over the job and was the bassist. Soon, Nizel Benn came in and picked up the bass. Since then, Key-ller acts as the Band Manager.\n\nA lot has to be brought up, a lot is left, as they say.\n\nApart from all the local achievements around Central India and Chhattisgarh, the greatest achievement of the band was getting featured and selected for its debut single Detained Love in UNHOLY MAUNDERs INDIAN ROCK Vol. I compilation disc, along with 5 International Bands and 20+ Major National Bands.\nhttp://www.unholymaunder.com/2011/08/download-um-indian-rock-vol-i.html\n\nThe band also got featured in Portuguese Webzine Heavy Hard Metal Mania for its debut single Detained Love\nhttp://www.heavyhardmetalmania.net/2011/06/megalinsanes-detained-love-world.html\n','9993626752, 9993322281','http://www.facebook.com/MEGALiNSANES','','','','102081739826892','746',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','megal-insanes'),(745,0,0,0,'Nostalgia','Four random guys  for d love of playing music and getting blitzed formed a band.It all started when Aaftaab (vocalist) and Angad (guitarist) were Sick of finding a good drummer in \"LUDHIANA\",  thought of joining a band in Chandigarh where they started  meeting an Alternative/Grunge band \"KHUNDAKK\" who knew nothing above Nirvana. Then after some jam sessions  they found out that the rythm guitarist of the band, Vyom, had a great potential at drumming (and almost any other musical instrument)(dats  what he still thinks .. ). After some bassy problems  they found Shubham who played for one of the best bands in Ludhiana. The band was formed as soon as the drummer bought a double bass pedal although he doesnt still have what people can call a \"DRUM-KIT\". Their  OC\'s have technical guitars and Aggressive vocals based on, backstabbing friends, injustice, teen rage i.e the OC\'s have everything but good drumming as the drummer doesnt know shit about metal drumming or even basic drumming. Heavy riffs , emphatic beats, thick bass and rumbling vocals are the main concerns these guys deal with...\\m/....','9779159115 - coolguitarist13@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/thenostalgia','','','','116201061762924','743',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','nostalgia'),(746,0,0,0,'Sajid Akbar and the Lost Boys','Sajid began playing guitar in school and realised the need to delve further into music . His first band Killer Tomatoes (1998-2003) made headlines as soon as they started off, creating a buzz in Delhi with charged performances and a blooming fan base. K.T. went onto winning Mood Indigo (Bombay) and a string of other rock festivals in Pillani, Kanpur and Chennai. Success and acclaim followed thereafter. Sajid went on to work with television media soon after.\n\nAn acute sense of observation coupled with musical sensitivity made way for new inspiration. He stepped out to form a simplistic yet evocative way to play his music. A careful blend of synthetic textures and electronic sound creates a counter energy in his music.\n\nMira, the first song, recorded recently is a reflection of the yearning for a perfect balance of acoustic guitar and moody lyricism The song is about feelings of obsessive and unrequited love. Love and life\'s bitter sweet ironies are the central theme of Sajid\'s music.\n\nHis songs have appeared on compilation CD\'s such as Sahi Bol The Urban Transmission (HMV SaReGaMa) and The Traffic Jam.','','http://www.facebook.com/boyslost','','','','13347436941','736',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sajid-akbar-and-the-lost-boys'),(747,0,0,0,'joasihno','Grenzen verwischen. Eines der schnen Dinge, im Jahr 2010 zu leben.\nNehmen wir Christoph Beck alias Joasihno, den seine Freunde im brigen Cico nennen.\nEr ist ein Produkt aus dem Umstand, dass Grenzen - wenn berhaupt - nur noch da existieren, wo man sie selber zieht.  Internet sei Dank. Reisen sei Dank.\nUnd  im gleichen Moment ist Joasihno einer, der diese Grenzen verwischt.\nZu abstrakt? Lasst uns konkret werden:\nEin junger Musiker aus einem kleinen oberbayerischen Dorf in der Nhe von Eichsttt (Umgeben von rechteckigen ckern  es war ihm wichtig, dies zu erwhnen) wandelt auf den Spuren von islndischen Musikern wie Mm, Sigur Rs oder Seabear. Wie ein musikalischer Karl May war dieser junge Musiker selber noch nie in Island, im Land seiner Trume. Und doch beherrscht er diese auf der Welt einzigartige musikalische Sprache so perfekt als wre sie seine eigene (was mittlerweile im brigen auch schon die Islnder von FM Belfast gemerkt haben, mit denen er bereits live gespielt hat.)\n\nDer selbe junge Musiker reist durch Afrika, seinen anderen musikalischen Sehnsuchtsort.\nEr saugt die Eindrcke auf wie der berhmte Schwamm. \nDie Rhythmen, die von einem ganz anderen Pulse geprgt sind, als die europischen. Den Klang fr ihn (noch) fremder Instrumente. \nDie Menschen und ihren Zugang zur Musik. \nSchon lange hat er die Minimal-Musiker Steve Reich und Philipp Glass verehrt.\nHat begonnen, sich an der Musikhochschule Mnster zum klassischen Schlagwerker ausbilden lassen, eine Arbeit als Musiklehrer in einer Frderschule begonnen und dort hauptschlich mit Kindern mit Behinderung gearbeitet. Hat neben seiner eigenen Musik auch in einer Band zu spielen begonnen (den inspirierenden Missent To Denmark aus Mnchen). Nebenbei hat er auch noch sein Knnen an der Loop-Station perfektioniert, um all die musikalischen Ideen live alleine umsetzen zu knnen.\nUnd pltzlich fgen sich die Teile zusammen. Ohne Hammer, ohne Meiel.  \nEs passt einfach: Island, Afrika, Eichsttt, Klassik, Pop, E und U, kalt und warm, bunt und grau, Intuition, professionelles Knnen und es im richtigen Moment abstreifen knnen. Kopf, Bauch. Es passt. Es passt, weil Joasihno in der Lage ist, Grenzen zu ignorieren und sie wie selbstverstndlich nicht als Hindernis, sondern als Chance zu begreifen.\nEinen ersten Eindruck davon konnten wir alle auf seiner ersten EP Papiertonnentigertum bekommen (erschienen 2009 im Eigenvertrieb).\nDie volle Ladung dieses groen Talents dann Anfang nchsten Jahres:  Joasihnos Debtalbum mit dem Titel We Say: Oh Well. \n\n\n\"Einen groen Musikspielplatz hat sich Joasihno in dieser kantigen Papiertonnenwelt geschaffen. Und dahin will er auch den Hrer mitnehmen: in einen musikalischen Rckzugsraum, irgendwo zwischen Expressionismus und Wohlstandsmelancholie. Seine Melodien sind vielschichtig und einfach zugleich, eindringlich und nah. Zwischen Emotion und Struktur bewegen sich seine Songs, da ist er Bands wie Mm, Lali Puna und Hjaltaln ganz hnlich.\" (Bayerischer Rundfunk)\n\n\"Seine Performance der Songs der neuen EP \"papierTonnenTigerTum\" beeindruckt nicht nur akustisch, sondern auch visuell durch die Projektion von Dia-Bildern.\" (Sueddeutsche Zeitung)\n\n\"Joasihno ist einer, und der holt das Leben ins Zimmer: Geloopte Gerusche, seltsame Instrumente, eine Gitarre wie eine steigende Hoffnung und Sonnenlicht am Dachfenster. Alles gar nicht so abgehoben, und doch ein kleines Wunder: Ein warmer, erlebter Moment Mnchen. Da ruft die Sddeutsche Zeitung schon mal die Avantgarde aus. Dabei war genau das doch nur berfllig.\" (fallen-legen.de)\n\n\nEin bisschen Raum in die Stille. Ein bisschen Stille in den Raum. ','','http://www.facebook.com/joasihno','','','','213989737818','735',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','joasihno'),(748,0,0,0,'Assault (india)','Assault is a metal band formed in Summers of June 2010. All members bring different inspirations to the band which gives Assault a unique sound which essentially comprises of the basic elements coupled with melody and progressive, groovy rhythms.\n\nBasically know for there original compositions (Ocs):\n\n1. Cardiac arrest\n2. Cry\n3. Hate Remains\n4. Assault\n5. Tripod\n6. Tragic Circles\n7. Aritmath\n8. Caosfear','+91-9425921679','http://www.facebook.com/assault.india','','','','153369561342130','735',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','assault-india'),(749,0,0,0,'Auditorium','','Publicity By Design: Melani Rogers - MelaniRogersny@aol.com, 212-982-0159','http://www.facebook.com/auditoriummusic','','','','153094354709381','729',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','auditorium'),(750,0,0,0,'Pariah Demise','Giving the breath of being by H ,Martyrdom & Dilshan in 2007 to a musical abomination not themed on a single aspect of misanthropy, Pariah Demise captures undisputed Sri Lankan black metal dealt & summarized within the realms of Darkness, Evil, War & Sri Lankan History, The band comprises of four cursed souls who are born, bred & still breathe in the hills of Kandy, Sri Lanka & has shared the stage, flags, & war torches with the fellow Sri Lankan rankers which include Folorn Hope,Funeral In Heaven, Dying Declaration,Spleen Saint as well as Dhishti.\n\nOffering the purified raw in its utmost essence live, Pariah Demise is currently marched by H on guitars, Martyrdom on vocals, Dilshan on bass to the war drums of Dinesh .\n\nHence the signs were true & the occurrences just started twisting into forms, Let it bleed & may the contagious pestilence of SLBM spread amongst the CHOSEN FEW..','pariahdemise@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/PariahDemise','','','','384600022296','728',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','pariah-demise'),(751,0,0,0,'Dark Moon Eternity','Dark Moon Eternity came into existence when two 17 year-old metalheads Abhilash Nanduri & Umang Bhardwaj decided to make some great Metal music. The line-up was confirmed when the band members Abhilash Singh and Nishant Varshney met up on a Social networking site. The need for another Guitarist was completed when \nAbhilash Nanduri suggested Manas Mishra whom with he attended his High school. Through our music, we aim to revolutionize the Metal scene in India and hopefully we will be successful in doing so.\n\n- Performed at Ice Cube, G.I.P.\n- Participated in War Of Bands I, Noida,2011.\n- Performed twice at RPMZANZI, Sector - 18, Noida.\n- Performed at The 567, New Delhi. \n- Performed at IMT Ghaziabad, PASSION 2011.\n- Headlining act in a Battle Of Bands @ Quantum, Centrestage Mall, Noida \n- Performed In Gurgaon @ ZYGO CLUB.\n- Performed in Battle Of Bands @ L.S.R TARANG \'12 \n- Performed in SGGS College of Commerce @ MIZRAB \'12.\n- Performed at the main stage @ MOSAIC OVERLOADED \'12 in Ramjas College.\n- Performed in Delhi Technological University @ ARPEGGIO \'12.','+91 - 9013851295,   +91 - 9899042006','http://www.facebook.com/abhimangchashney','','','','210346448999384','728',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dark-moon-eternity'),(752,0,2,2,'BLEK','Blek is the mumbai based indie-alternative trio of Jared Creado, Rishi Bradoo, and Varoon Aiyer. They like chai, Bill Murray movies, and songs with strange names. Blek have been making quite a name for themselves and were recently one of the 5 all-India winners of the Ray-Ban Never Hide Sounds talent hunt. They have been featured in the January issue of Rolling Stone India as well.\r\n\r\nBlek launched their debut EP \"Hexes + Drama, & Other Reasons for Evacuation\" on ennui.BOMB Records on 14th February 2012. The EP is being hailed all over including a CD of the Fortnight review from Timeout Mumbai. The entire EP can be downloaded for free from www.ennuidotbomb.com.\r\n\r\nThe band just started a national tour to promote the EP starting with the Eastern leg covering Kolkata, Guwahati, Dimapur and Shillong in a back-to-back gig series receiving a fabulous response from audiences at each gig. \r\n\r\nUpcoming plans include the Southern and the Northern legs of the tour and a video for their first single off the EP Fog + Strobe.\r\n\r\nFor critical descriptions and analysis of their music find the nearest play button','Rishu Singh +91 98192 88798 ennui.BOMB','http://www.facebook.com/BLEKMUSIC','http://www.ennuidotbomb.com','http://soundcloud.com/blek','','0','724',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','blek'),(753,0,0,0,'Zero Impedance','Winners @ LetItRock\'12 , AISSMS\'s Annual Rock Fest\nWinners @ Techelligent \'12 , PCCoE\'s Annual Fest\nWinners @ Crescendo \'12 , ISBM\'s Annual Fest\nRunners Up @ Crescendo \'11 , ISBM\'s Annual Fest\n4th Position @ Blizzard \'11, Ishanya Mall','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Zero-Impedance/143424392352501','','','','143424392352501','723',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','zero-impedance'),(754,0,0,0,'Pravvy Prav/Pravin Mukhi Drummer','Having grown up in the UAE and England, Pravin has played in many bands of many different genres of music, be it fusion, folk, soul, hip hop, rock, or even death metal. In Dubai, Pravin was a part of Abhorred, Abstrakt Collision and numerous other projects, and also spent his time Dj\'ing drum\'n\'bass on local radio shows, as well as teaching young kids how to play drums. In the UAE, Abstrakt Collision began to find international acclaim with radio stations in America, Australia, Japan and Europe playing their music. Pravin has also been seen gigging in numerous countries including Canada, Amsterdam, Dubai, Lebanon, all over the UK, Norway, Germany, and all over India. \n\nAfter having left Dubai, he has been playing as a session drummer for a range of different musicians of different styles. Pravin has also played with/ for the Foreign Beggars Live Band and numerous other projects such as with UK hip hop legend JEHST, SWAMI, Brooke Supple, Jimmi Nolan, MEDISON, Claudia Georgette, Jelone, The FOCUSED FEW, Pamela Fay-Weekes, Pawn, Amar (Timbaland Shock Value), the highly acclaimed Focused Few, Kyza (formerly of Terra Firma fame), Solenca, Jennifer Crestol, Skrein, Dubbledge, Syntax, Asavior, Shaair and Func (Mumbai), Abhorred, KELBIE, and Daniel Ward-Murphy, and Les Davidson amongst others. \n\nPravin has also been increasingly in demand for his session work, and has worked with numerous London studios such as Abbey Road Studios, Livingston Studios, Mindloop, People\'s Studios, Premises Studios, Strongroom Studios, Saffron Media, and more. \n\nPRavin\'s drumming has also featured on the release from the UK hip-hop giant JEHST who remixed a track for the Foreign Beggars on Dented Records for their album \"Stray Point Agenda\". Pravin has now joined with Daniel Ward-Murphy and recorded a full length album with him which has been produced by the legendary Tony Platt. \n\nSeptember this year saw another release with Pravin\'s drumming on Dented Records on the \"Harry\" EP produced by Medison featuring Skrein. \n\nPravvy Prav is also a founding member of what has shaped up to be Mumbai\'s dopest party called WOBBLE. His unrelenting d\'n\'b sets along with DJ URI, BANDISH PROJECT and FUNC INTERNATIONAL are causing a massive stir, and are not to be missed. \n\nPravin Has been seen playing at numerous festivals globally.\nBIG CHILL UK - 2008\nGLASTONBURY- 2007/2008\nOYA FESTIVAL NORWAY 2008\nINDIA MUSIC FESTIVAL AMSTERDAM 2008\nCO/POP FESTIVAL GERMANY 2008\nNORWAY 2009\nNXNE FESTIVAL CANADA 2009\nMOSAIC FESTIVAL CANADA-2009/2010\nSUNFEST- LONDON ONTARIO 2010\nNH7 FESTIVAL - PUNE 2010 \nINDIA FEST - GOA 2011','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Pravvy-PravPravin-Mukhi-Drummer/131513673566787','','','','131513673566787','722',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','pravvy-pravpravin-mukhi-drummer'),(755,0,1,1,'DJ URI','With a career spanning over 2 decades, DJ Uri aka Mr Manali, has been consistent and true to the Underground. The mid to late 80s saw him playing Classic Soul & Funk to Hip Hop, Acid House and Rave, and with gigs at the Legendary Amnesia House and Total Kaos in the early 1990s, Uri has and still is enjoying the musical ride of life. \n\nBorn in East London in 1974, Uris journey has been in full flow since the early 1980s. Influenced by the Street Sounds Electro Compilations, and the whole Break Dance Era, when he first saw a DJ on 2 Turntables, through the Acid House explosion in the mid 1980s, to the Rave and Jungle Culture of the early 1990s and the House and Trance movement in the mid 1990s. Uri has had a solid musical upbringing from an early age. \n\nHis versatility and DJ skills have allowed him to play many different genres, and fuse many styles and influences, with a no holds barred attitude. Uri is at ease playing anything from Trip-Hop, Glitch-Hop, Dubstep, Minimal Techno, Hip-Hop and Funk to Breaks, House and Drum & Bass.\n\n1995 was the year that India became his second home, and with various gigs across the country over the next 15 years, from beach parties in Psychedelic Goa to the Underground revolution that was taking place in major cities such as Mumbai, Delhi and Bangalore, he has become a household name within the scene.\n\nUri has been an unsung hero for Indias emerging Electronic Music Scene. Since the mid 90s, he has been training Indias first wave of Turntable enthusiasts, giving personal tuition on Scratching, Beat Juggling and various other Turntable Techniques to now, some of Indias Leading DJs. Still to this day he is the source of Fresh Music for many DJs in India that are looking for That Cutting Edge.\n \nHe has a passion for sharing and passing on his skills and knowledge to the next generation of DJs, and after 3 years working for Access to Music and Rock School, he opened his own DJ and Music Production Academy Start From Scratch in April 2006, in Leicester (UK).\n    \nIn 2008, a Summer Tour of France with the MoM Collective saw Uri playing 2 massive Festivals in the process, one being the Woodstower Festival in a natural park in the Rhone Alps region, and the other was the Visual Invaders Festival, up in the mountains in the French Alps, close to the Swiss/Italian border.\n\n2009 saw the Mosquito Massala Collective (MoM), performing tirelessly, starting in May where they will be touring France, playing in Paris, Lyon, St Etienne and Nimes, with the highlight being a 2 Hour Set @ The Nuits Sonores Festival in Lyon, one of the biggest Electronic Music Festivals in Europe.\n \nDJ Uri lines up gigs in the UK, New York, Amsterdam, Paris and India in 2010, twinned with the Start from Scratch DJ Academy opening up in Mumbai, Uri is truly an International DJ.\n','','http://www.facebook.com/DJURI.UK','','','','133742416668486','720',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-uri'),(756,0,0,0,'Fire and Neon','Fusing together various styles such as indie, rock, dance and pop dedicated to creating a sound that can appeal to just about anyone.','','http://www.facebook.com/fireandneon','','','','44314044247','719',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','fire-and-neon'),(757,0,0,0,'Dhwesha','Dhwesha started off as a two piece band in 2008. Rooted to Old school Death Metal with a few doom/atmospheric elements, the band quickly carved quite a niche for themselves. Initially consisting of Somesha on guitars and Ajay on vocals, the band recorded four songs and received  quite a commendable response from the metal community. The band was joined by Adarsh (the then bass player of Culminant) in 2011. Playing to drum tracks, the trio began practicing to play gigs, while at the same time scouting for drummers both on and off the internet. The search eventually resulted is finding Tushar Bajaj, through a mutual friend. A few younger yet a very good fit, he gave complete form the to the band and the band have been playing live ever since, doing shows in and around Bangalore.\nIn January 2012 Dhwesha released their demo titled Yuddhabhumi on tape. The tape contained all 6 songs written till then and found its way around and outside India. Dhwesha supported Japanese black/thrash band Abigail at Trend Slaughter Fest 2012 held in Bangalore in early 2012. The band is currently looking for shows within the country. ','metal.dhwesha@hotmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Dhwesha/203586443016525','','','','203586443016525','718',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dhwesha'),(758,0,0,0,'Rafiralfiro','Rafael Aragn aka Rafiralfiro is a latin/arabic rooted french musician / dj / composer / producer. Born & raised in Paris, between downtown and suburbs, he grew up surrounded by different cultures that really built him, first as a human being and later as an artist.\n\nHe started composing beats at the age of 20 under the name of Rafiralfiro, after spending a childhood possessed with music, from afro-latin, jazz & classical to modern rock and hip-hop. He soon became obsessed with the idea of mixing traditional, folkloric music with modern electronic patterns, looking for the perfect balance between organic and synthetic, old and new, art music and popular music, the holy and the profane, the darkness and the light, the brain and the feet. His musical technic also became part of his identity, dealing with the smallest musical slices to create unique and original patterns from existing music, extracting a texture, a color, a short piece of melody or rythm. Assembling several musical layers to create new soundscapes, ambients & grooves, he works with passion to transform his computer in a dream machine, not just another beatbox.\n\nHe soon started acting in various music fields, composing scores for movies or documentaries, producing beats for rappers / singers, releasing free albums on the web and displaying unique live performance in France and beyond. Next to his solo, main project, he played in some bands or side projects with different musicians and singers. Obviously, the travel (through both time & space) and culture crossing is at the center of his music, and his vision is global, outshining the obsolete concept of world music. Between latintronics and oriental bass, not to forgot african or balkanic flavoured electronics, his music has no label and keeps evolving in several directions at the same time.\n\nIn 2011, after some of his side projects came to an end, Rafael decided to take a fresh start and to get rid of his old aka Rafiralfiro. So he choosed to use his real name as he signed for an EP with the uprising spanish netlabel Caballito, based in Granada & Berlin. Run by two very active dj / producer / visual artists, Grita & Bigote, this one-year-old label releases the finest, freshest music from the nu-latin / tropical bass scene.\n\nCurandero EP gathers the newest latin-oriented tracks from Rafael Aragn, from the wildest sambatronics to the sweetest nu-cumbia. Sweaty dancefloor killers and soulful, enlightened anthems to cheer up and enjoy the beauty of life. With a very special, magic touch inspired by the ancient traditions of shamanism from all around the world. Mystic chimes, ritual drums and witchcraft incantations meet club kicks, filthy basslines and electronic batucada to provide a rich, dancy and psychedelic music for hips and ears !\n\nCurandero EP will be available for free download (high quality 320kbps mp3) on october 21th, 2011, on Caballito netlabel [CBLLT013]. ','rafiralfiro@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/rafiralfiro','','','','75283974026','717',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rafiralfiro'),(759,0,0,0,'Zepheroth','','Tanay Apte - 9767899307','http://www.facebook.com/ZepherothBand','','','','181576578540733','717',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','zepheroth'),(760,0,0,0,'May Roosevelt','','mayroosevelt@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/May-Roosevelt/139002596165084','','','','139002596165084','715',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','may-roosevelt'),(761,0,0,0,'RudraXsha','RudraXsha is a Pune based band which was formed with the intention of re-inventing Hindi/Indian Classical music by fusing it with Rock music elements.\n\nThe band took shape when people with different musical influences and interests came together and started contributing to the band with their individual sound during the initial jamming sessions.\n\nTo get a feel of the band\'s sound, listen to the recently recorded original composition (rough mix) uploaded here:\n\nhttp://www.reverbnation.com/rudraxsha\n\n\nAchievements :\n\n*Won Alacrity 2010, Annual festival of AISSMS IOIT Pune*\n\n*Won Youthopia Inter College Competition 2010 organised by Sakaal Papers*\n\n*Won Crescendo 2010, Annual festival of ISB & M College Pune*\n\n*Won Vedant 2010, Annual festival of BJ Medical College Pune*\n\n*Runners up at Groove Junction 2010, Annual fest of AISSMS COE Pune*\n\n*Best vocalist award for Gaurav Burse at Groove Junction 2010*\n\n*Headlining act at Alacrity 2011, Annual festival of AISSMS IOIT Pune*\n\n*Performed at Ishanya Mall Pune in August 2010 and March 2011*\n\n*Performed at the Hero Cycles India Cyclothon National Event held in Pune*','','http://www.facebook.com/RudraXsha','','','','195644027125275','712',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rudraxsha'),(762,0,0,0,'AXIS 6','Initiated and conceptualized in 2009 by the two permanent members of the band (Abhishek and Abhinav), the band\'s lineup was finally completed by the end of the same year. \n  \nIn January 2010, the band started performing and touring in different parts of the country. For more than an year until March 2011, the band performed with its original lineup. The 14 month long journey helped it evolve as a strong competitor amid bands playing metal. It helped the band win a strong name and a decent underground support, despite the limitations and constraints in terms of resources. \n\nAs of now, the band is NOT performing live. But that doesn\'t stop us from making music (no matter what the reasons and circumstances be). \n\nThe band believes in its music and continues to compose and produce it under its own independent label.\n\n\n','+919415310925','http://www.facebook.com/pages/AXIS-6/277061668251','','','','277061668251','707',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','axis-6'),(763,0,0,0,'Topi','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Topi/106172622786080','','','','106172622786080','706',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','topi'),(764,0,0,0,'Midnight Garden Factor','Midnight Garden Factor (M.G.F.) started at the tail end of 2007, out of sheer love for progressive music, influenced and inspired by artists like rush, circus maximus, porcupine tree, Xsaviour, Dream theater and many more. The band gradually gained popularity in the scene for their unique approach to music. Their sound is instantly recognisable with catchy melodic heavy grooves, Smoky vocals, driving rock bass and thundering drums and their clever use of odd time signatures.\nTheir musical collage is evident in their live performances. Part of the magic lies on their mutual respect and understanding of each others musicality, with their diverse musical background and taste all adding to the creative mix.\n The band has travelled in and around  Northeast  India and has won several contests in the region. M.G.F had the opportunity to open for Mr.Big (Reunion World Tour) in Shillong and three members of the band have also accompanied Mr.Lou Majaw for a certain period of time. The band is currently working on the first album and is looking forward to travelling and reaching music lovers in and around the country and the world. The Band is passionately carrying the torch to promote progressive music in the region. \n\nAchievements:\n2007 Hornbill National Rock Beat Contest 	 2nd runners up\n2008  5th Mangan  Music Festival		         Finalist 	\n2010 Meghalaya  Icon 				         Winners\n2011 IIT Guwahati				                 Finalist\n2011 AIMT  					                 Finalist\n2011 JEC					                         Winners	\n2011 2nd North East Youth Festival		 Winners\n2011 Lets Rock (Shillong)			         Winners\n2012 Lets Rock (Northeast)			         Winners\n2012 Nominated  by Artistaloud.com nominated for Best Rock Group and Best Rock Song\n','mgfshillong@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/midnightgardenfactor','','','','155517644463573','704',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','midnight-garden-factor'),(765,0,0,0,'Blind','Formed in Mid Feb, 2011.... Blind is a four piece experimental/metal band from Delhi. Blind\'s genre has the elements of Grunge, Progressive, Speed Metal and Trash Metal. Blind\'s lyrical structure normally talks about Psychological topics, introspection and social issues which the Govt. or the common people blindly ignores and avoids. Since the very first jam, Blind laid more emphasis on creating a strong and unique sound and started working on with their originals & covers. Blind plans to unleash their music on higher ground and hope to spread awareness with their music someday.','blindintrospection@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Blind/185488884802057','','','','185488884802057','702',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','blind'),(766,0,0,0,'Dave O\'Grady',' Dave OGrady is a  gifted Singer/Songwriter from Ireland. \n\nNow living in the musically vibrant City of Liverpool, Dave is a much admired and respected stalwart of the local music scene.\nHis unique style of musicianship harmoniously fuses Blues and Folk creating a most \nsympathetic sound, which when paired with his haunting voice defines him as an outstanding live performer. \n\nNow 21, Dave first picked up a Guitar aged 12 and played his first Live Performance at 13. \nGrowing up within sight of the Guinness Factory in Dublin, Daves Father, himself a local musician of some note, ensured his lad sampled many a heady draught from the musical well.\n From Creedence Clearwater Revival, Jeff Healey and Rory Gallagher to Christy Moore, Steve Earle and Tom Waits. The effects of exposure to such a rich medley of influences permeate the fabric of every Dave OGrady track. \n\nSince embarking on his musical journey he has shared the stage with such Legends as Jon Bon Jovi, Seal, Russell Watson, Ringo Starr and most recently supported Sandi Thom on tour throughout the UK. \n\nHis Debut Single Walking through the Desert has sold well in several countries and saw him tour the UK and France for the past two years.\n\n\nWhat the critics have to say:\n\n\"amazing bluesy voice\"\n- Joe Speak GIGAPE.COM\n\n\"O\'Grady delivers\"\n-Niamh Horan Kildare Post\n\n\"this guy is great\"\nMarie O\'Riordan KFM\n\n\"Top Man,Top Voice\"\n-Russell Watson\n\n\"If his job was to impress, Id say thats easily mission accomplished\"\n- Joe Speak GIGAPE.COM\n\nRecent News\n\nWhile he is working on the debut album he has taken time out to record a three track single entitled \" LIVE AT HOME\" which is exactly what is says on the tin, three songs, one mic and one room, (his sitting room in Liverpool to be exact). This single is a glimpse of Dave\'s more rootsy/country side and is a lovely warm collection of songs.\n\nRecently Dave was invited to a special gathering in Liverpool by a New York collective to record one song live that was cut straight to vinyl which Dave says was a very special day.\n\nContact info:\n\nwww.daveogrady.com\n\nmyspace.com/daveogradymusic\n\nyoutube.com/daveogradytv\n\ntwitter.com/daveogradymusic\n\nreverbnation.com/daveogradymusic\n\n','Chris Thom','http://www.facebook.com/daveogradyofficial','','','','118974928115843','698',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dave-ogrady'),(767,0,0,0,'Shavasva','','shavasvaband@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/shavasva','','','','193296144034094','693',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','shavasva'),(768,0,0,0,'Rise Of Uncertainty','ROU was formed in sept,09 with the completion of the 1st line up...Since then we have been active on the delhi circuit with participating n nailing some of the major comps.The band has evolved from the initial alternate sound to the current progressive sound.The influences are varied n come from all genre from hard rock-alt-metal core and amalgamates into a progressive sound...','','http://www.facebook.com/RiseOfUncertainty','','','','109554069083562','693',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rise-of-uncertainty'),(769,0,0,0,'Curves','\"Curves\" was mainly formed when two friends met and started sharing their ideas on the sound they were searching. They started writing materials together, never thinking of whether to do it live or not, resulting in their songs having multiple guitar layers looped one over another. Their sound can be best described\nas a combination of Progressive and Experimental Metal coupled by Ambient structures lingering here and there.\nAfter a few week\'s jamming and toil, they (Anurag Hazarika & Sanandam Bordoloi) came up with the raw structure of their first original . Soon they brought in Sourav Nandi (filling in the bass) and guest vocals (Johnny Marak) to fill in their song.\nThey are currently working their way into the Guwahati Rock scene with their debut single \"Divided We Fall\" which they recorded at the Lucid Recess Studio.\nThey are looking forward for all your support.','curvesofficial@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/curvesofficial','','','','250870934944309','692',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','curves'),(770,0,0,0,'Prime Rage','Prime Rage was conceptualized in 2009 by the current vocalist Anto and drummer Julian who shared the similiar musical interests. And started off as a cover band with Lamb Of God And Pantera being their early influences. After different line-up changes Charles was roped in by 2010 and they started off with their original compositions. Their line-up was complete when Meeth joined up in May, 2011 who provided a different dimension to the band. \n\nThey have played  numerous fests in Bangalore and was the Headlining Act in Headstrong (Battle of the bands - 2011)\n\nThey were also featured in the Freeman Music Website as an upcoming Band in the circuit  -  http://thefreeman.net/journal/?p=5069 ','Meeth Medappa - [+919743678327]','http://www.facebook.com/prime.rage.india','','','','219893078039239','692',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','prime-rage'),(771,0,0,0,'Emperor Minge','Emperor Minge are a New Delhi based 6 piece band. They are known for being unpredictable, audacious and unlistenable to some, and to others, the best thing that has happened to music since Franz Schubert contracted syphilis.\n\nThe group was formed by musician/would be actor Stefan Kaye and special needs drummer Nikhil Vasudevan in Delhi some time back; they collaborate with beatnik poet Jamie Kelsey.\n\nOpinions on the band vary somewhat with some music journo types claiming influences from obscure acid jazz outfits  that no-one in the band has heard of (or would think of listening to), and others elevating them to the status of a 2nd rate school band.\n\n\nIn essence, they  inspire the kind of love em or hate em qualities that will either incite people to deem them a classic or make them the stuff of childhood nightmares. \n\n','stiffkittensinc@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Emperor-Minge/13710380582','','','','13710380582','690',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','emperor-minge'),(772,0,0,0,'Public Issue','Who are we??\n \n\"We dont know!!! The music \ncomposes itself... We just add the funkin garnish!\" \n ','Call- +91 9841813322 or Mail pitheband@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/PublicIssue','','','','129526913779057','685',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','public-issue'),(773,0,0,0,'Moksh','As the word says MOKSH literally means the last state after self actualization where the human being is far beyond satisfied in all walks of life and he attains the utmost place of satisfaction where he becomes free from all the ropes and ties of relations which were anchored on him through his lifetime. In the same sense the main philosophy of MOKSH as a band is to let people expereince this state of satisfaction in this age through the magic of music. A 20 day old band formed with an only perspective of inspiring , influencing people for what they had considered as extincted native music forms of INDIA. We as a band always tried to put up all the native art forms , music forms , sanskrit shlokas and a variety of cultural treasure through the medium of rock music because rock is the music of the day but we want to let all people know that we want our rock to be based on OUR ROOTS which far divine and flourished than any other culture. MOKSH is also working on native music forms of different countries like the african traditional folk music or the orchestrational symphonies of mozart , bach to oriental music form the eastern countries and so on. Overall we are aiming to add those magic notes from all religious backgrounds and to blend it into our music where u cannot differentiate between religions , races and thats what we want our world to be \" ONE \" . People generally ask us to what genre you belong and we say \" u name it \" . That\'s the main concept beyond MOKSH ... we want to get closer to people\'s heart and not to get commercialised and recognised unnecessarily by getting into competitions of genres n technicality.','Sagar Joshi - 9004691953','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Moksh/210481842305322','','','','210481842305322','684',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','moksh-1'),(774,0,0,0,'V Society','V  Society is the solo project of Vishal Sinha, currently based out of Kolkata.\nWith over a decade of experience behind the decks and a streak of\nappearances in underground festival arena\'s across the sub-continent, it can be\nsafely concluded that V-society is one of the best kept secrets of Indian\nelectronica...\n\nHe started his journey a decade ago at the heartland of the electronic music\nmovement in India  Goa. There he took over the reigns of the legenrady\nTitos and has gone on to play at the finest venues such as One Lounge\n(Pune), Blue Frog (Mumbai) and a smattering of festivals like Mountain\nMadness 2011 (Nepal) and Mahashivratri 2007 (Nepal).\n\nDelivering a strong mix of powerful and melodic sounds, V-Society creates a\nvibe that is unique and full of uplifting \'euphoria\'.\n\n\nhttp://www.facebook.com/pages/V-Society\nhttp://www.myfavdj.in/vishal\nhttp://loveoftrance.com/site/profiles/artists/v-society','digitalombombay@hotmail.com, hemdhillon@gmail.com, dj_vishal10@hotmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/V-Society/118697808210757','','','','118697808210757','684',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','v-society'),(775,0,0,0,'The Fallen Race','TFR was formed in April 2011, by the three members Pratik Sapkale, Ujas Vaghani and Mohit Bhargava, sharing the same interest in metal. Later, after 2 months of the formation of the band, Sahil Manohar and Akhlad Ahmed pitched in to create a full fledged band. Now these 5 music junkies trying to make such kind of music and concepts on which the songs are supposed to be.\n\nThe First OC created was \'Six Degrees\', After that \'Enough\' and finally came up with a heavy riff song called \'Vengence\'. Along with this the band also covered  songs like Walk with me in hell, Laid to rest, Now you\'ve got something to die for- all by Lamb of god. and also covered some songs from bands like -->Trivium, A7X, Iced Earth.','Mohit Bhargava - mohit_bhargava_619@hotmail.com / 9930247611 - 26C68028 (BBM Contact)','http://www.facebook.com/The.Fallen.Race','','','','210539018970185','681',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-fallen-race'),(776,0,0,0,'Mental Martians','Taking the Indian bass-scene by storm and bringing a fresh new sound, seeing never before used Indian percussion with dubstep, breaks and drum n bass to fuse together , a rich, melodic and aggressive sound that rips through sound systems. \n\nIntroducing to the world and the masses of India the MENTAL MARTIANS are Piyush Bhatnagar, Sarvesh Shrivastava and Tarang Singhal and with their brand of techno-analogue sound, you are guaranteed to be snared.\n\nInfluenced by Noisia, Spor, Doctor P, Skrillex, Rusko, Chase and status and various heavyweights from the international dub arena, their sound is a heady journey that defies genres and synthesizes the Asian underground to the dubstep in the UK.\n\nSarvesh who formed the band, corabrated with Piyush is dub aficionado with a penchant for Indian sounds and believes in broadening his horizons as he has from age 15 when he began his musical journey. Piyush on the other hand was an equally early starter at 16, as he dabbles in not only the dub arts but electro-house and IDM and has an international presence that completes these two as they cover DJing, production and technical support for the team. Their gigs in Mumbai and Jaipur and Dehli have garnered awesome levels of recognition for them.\nProviding the live element to the band is their third member, Tarang Singhal, who began his musical tte--tte at a mere 8! and Plays the tabla, darbuka, Jembe, Bongo, Drums and other home made percussions that allow him to sample live sounds that create mayhem with the electronic deliciousness of the two.\nTheir sounds are magical and danceable at same time, a vivid journey into the unknown and the un-chartered, the sublime and the scintillating, promising to introduce a sound that is enjoyed by the masses and that is anthem-like and cerebral at the same. \n\nPast gigs :-\n\n:: 2010 ::\n\n\nMumbai - Zenzi Mills , || Jan 2010 || [Wall of the Vj\'s] \n\nChandigarh - Zinc , || Feb 2010 || \n\nMumbai - Zenzi Mils, || May 2010 || [Bass Camp Festival 2] || Live Set\n\nMumbai - Wink, Taj President, || July 2010 || LIVE Set \n\nPune - The Loop , || August 13th 2010 || \n\nMumbai - Zenzi Mills, || August 20th 2010 || Dj Set With NUPHLO [U.K]\n\nChandigarh - Zinc, || August 28th 2010 || Dj Set\n\nJaipur - Club Nirvana || September 4th 2010|| Dj set with Bandish Projekt\n\nBangalore - Bacchus || September 11th 2010 || \n\nKolkatta - Big Ben || October 22nd 2010 ||\n\nKolkatta - The Basement || October 23rd 2010 ||\n\nMumbai - MTC (Mumbai Times Cafe) || November 26th 2010 ||\n\nPune - Media Mindprints (ISB & M) || December 5th 2010 ||\n\nMumbai - Bass Camp Festival 3 || December 9th 2010 ||\n\nMumbai - MTC (Mumbai Times Cafe) || December 16th 2010 || With Nerm Chauhan {Shiva Soundsystem (U.K.) & Pravvyprav Prav (U.K.)\n\nGoa - Sunburn Festival 2010 || 27th December ||\n\n________________________________________________________________________\n\n:: 2011 ::\n\nMumbai - Submerge Sundown Session || Azok || March 6th 2011 ||\n\nPune - The High Spirits || April 8 2011 ||\n\nMumbai - Blue Frog || April 10th 2011 || With NU:Tone,Vachan Chinnappa & BBC\n\nMumbai - Bonobo || April 15th 2011 || With Pravvy Prav and Bandish Projekt\n\nNew Delhi - 24/7 Bar, The Lalit || May 13 2011 || \n\nNew Delhi - Zook || June 25th 2011 || \n\nMumbai - Zenzi Bandra (IDNB) || July 2nd 2011 || \n\nMumbai - Blue Frog || 14th August 2011 || WIth Taufiq Qureshi\'s Mumbai Stamp\n\nMumbai - Cool Chef Cafe || 9th September 2011\n\nMumbai - Bonobo || 1st October 2011 || With Snareophobe (UK) \n\nMumbai - Cool Chef Cafe || 28th October 2011 || With Ox7gen \n\nAhemdabad - Wobble - Starz Club || 12th November 2011 || With DJ URI & Bandish Projekt\n\nMumbai - Blue Frog || 30th November 2011 ||\n\nMumbai - Blue Frog || 2nd December 2011 || With DUB FX  & Flower Fairy\n\nPune - 1lounge ||  3rd Dec 2011 || With Dub FX & Flower Fairy \n\nGoa -  9bar ||  4rd December 2011 ||With Dub FX & Flower Fairy \n\nGoa - Sunburn Festival 2011 || 29th December || Arro Stage || With BASHER (RAM RECORDS, UK), Vachan Chinnappa & Nick Hutchins \n\n________________________________________________________________________\n\n2012\n\nPune - One Republic Festival - One Lounge || 25th January || With BREED / Steppa Style & DJ Mocity.\n\nAhmedabad - SVIT Coll Annual Fest. || 1st March \n\n\n','','http://www.facebook.com/MentalMartiansOfficial','','','','192711407431062','681',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','mental-martians'),(777,0,0,0,'Boombay Central','Boombay Central is the moniker of Mumbai based Dj/ producer Tarun Shahani who started producing electronic music after being inspired by meeting Delhi based duo Midival Punditz. Seeing them use early sequencers like Cakewalk to produce electronic beats and Melodies made him realize how it was actually possible to be a band by yourself and create music solely on a computer Up until then he was djing and working with MTV as a host for shows like ClubMtv etc.. He Started producing Music on early sequencers like acid and fruity loops and I realized that he lacked the principles of audio production having never worked in a studio, though he was really happy with the sounds he was creating and the arrangements, missing the polished mixing that he heard In the music of my favourite artists so he did a stint at Sae Chennai where his real obsession with audio started.. Boombay Central is a project that has seen many collaborations with other arstists like Midival punditz, Ashvin from jalebee cartel, Nirav Gandhi from Junkt etc. The sound is emotional deep progressive electronica ranging from Chilled ethnic grooves to Minimal Tech, Progressive, Psychedelic Trance and Breaks. The live set mostly consists of Tarun on laptop running sequences and djing with a visual backing by a VJ or installation artist, For samples of Boombay Central music please visit his myspace page:\n\nhttp://www.myspace.com/boombaycentral\n\nfor videos please visit:\n\nhttp://youtube.com/user/djboombaba\n\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Boombay-Central/81432506731','','','','81432506731','679',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','boombay-central'),(778,0,0,0,'Pisakas','          Pisakas meaning Demon which feasts on the left overs from corpses, regarding smelly rotten bits as delicacies. They are not averse to having a go at mourners who would be well advised to keep both nose and mouth covered and at all costs.  \n                The name itself focuses on all the unsocial elements of the society, and all that people have gone through. Here is a band that screams against injustice... Hailing from Bangalore they are a thrash metal band that plays with a blend of black and death metal with a passion for brutality in their genre. From complex guitar riffs to shrieking leads, thundering bass patterns to intense grind beats and double base drumming, from low gutturals to high pitched screeches defines  the sound of Pisakas. Influenced by the early old school pioneers of death, black and thrash like Sepultura, Megadeth, early Metallica, Slayer, early Cannibal Corpse, Deicide, Venom, Celtic Frost, Bathory etc., they play with speed and utmost aggression, keeping in mind the lyrical content to be entirely focused on the societys atrocities. They also believe in spreading their message to the people to rise against injustice and accept humanity as it is and not forced by some external deity.','+919886718704,  pisakas666@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Pisakas/153250484712343','','','','153250484712343','678',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','pisakas'),(779,0,0,0,'Eclipse','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Eclipse/106042166150526','','','','106042166150526','678',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','eclipse'),(780,0,0,0,'Beastial Murder','','vivek:0900306187/09895691857','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Beastial-Murder/153211768066998','','','','153211768066998','678',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','beastial-murder'),(781,0,0,0,'MindFlew','Mindflew is the re incarnation of The Angry Mob which was formed in 2006. Mindflew started of as a school band and the focus shifted from covering other artists to making music. As Angry Mob the band played at the Fete De La Musique 08 organized by Alliance Francais and its song was reviewed in the November 08 issue of Rolling Stones India. The band was then featured in a compilation by Furtados Music.\n\nThe band believes in making its own music and sticking to self compositions all the time.\n\nMore Details coming soon..','','http://www.facebook.com/mindflew','','','','318551841618','677',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','mindflew'),(782,0,0,0,'Deathaphor','DeathaphoR is a Metal band from Agartala, Tripura, India formed in August 2010 by Nasen and Smashhead. Later joined by Brutuz, Amos , JD and DJ. \n\n#Line Up :-\n\n*Nasen Chakma- Lead Guitar/Vocals |Au