d never heard before in the local scene, a style mixed with progressive ideas in the existing aggressive metal-corish feelThe band has jus started playing on a regular basis and is generating good reviews from across statesthey have gained recognition for their unique sound there as wellThey were also the only Indian act to be invited to open up for the international act Red Rain(new Zealand hard rock) 2 years back in Bangalore December 2005 was the year in which the band embarked on a journey towards their musical interests, playing at numerous underground venues. The band had a break in a years time, which soon led to a line up change. With a new drummer, the sound changed to a more technical and aggressive tone. Crucifix guide was initially branded as a Christian band, but they are basically, 5 guys, who love music, and enjoy expressing their past personal experiences through their music. Filled with a drive to present the best live show to its audiences, their energy gives them an experience to remember. The band is working on their debut album, which will be out this year. Some people think in the box, some think Out of it, and someDestroy it. ','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/CRUCIFIX-GUIDE/28596150702','','','','28596150702','668',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','crucifix-guide'),(789,0,0,0,'Philosophy of life','It all started in the summer of 2010. when 4 dudes Udeeksh,Vivek,Rohan,VT.initially they started jamming with no real direction but nomenclated ourselves as \"nightout\"....but then there was no real spark in the band and it hit the band real hard in a negative way when VT left the outfit..leaving it a 3 piece band...and in november 2010 we travelled to ropar for our first ever life performance..as Nightout...we became serious after the gig it acted as a boost for us...and then we got a chance from lingya\'s university..that was when we got in touch with Pramit for the spot for a bass guitarist.We came runner\'s up at lingya\'s.We headlined LRITM,palwal. After that rohan abruptly left the outfit and again leaving it a 3 piece band. We then recorded our first single \"All Alone\"....after the recording the band was renamed to \"Philosophy Of Life\"..in the summer of 2011..it went on as a 3 piece band for a long time...in the winter of 2011 kartik came into the band as another guitarist..with whom we played 5 gigs..in which we came runner\'s up again in ropar. We played as a guest band at Tryst cafe at saket..post which Udeeksh left the band for some personal reasons. the band went incognito for 2-3 months..we then endevoured into the music scene in search for the \"man with the beats\" and fortunately banged into Avneesh Asija..and simultaneously deepak and chinki joined in as the lead guitarist and keyboard player respectively and we came 3rd at echelon...after that the band thought of strengthening the line up even more to hit it big...thenceforth Deepak was transferred to an adiditional guitarist and Andy(Aniruddha) came in as the new lead guitarist since then we\'ve had steady progress..getting into the the top 5 band of Corna\'12 according to Heavy genre.com...we hope to hit it big time.','','http://www.facebook.com/philosophyoflife5','','','','171645079558243','662',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','philosophy-of-life'),(790,0,0,0,'Portal of Deception','WINNERS OF NIT WARANGAL IRA ROCK \'11\nWINNERS OF NIFT SPECTRUM BANGLORE BATTLE OF BANDS \'11\nWINNERS OF CHRIST UNIVERSITY BANGLORE BATTLE OF BANDS \'11\nWINNERS OF SIT TUMKUR HALCYON \'11\nWINNERS OF MSRIT BANGLORE UDBHAV \'11\n\nWINNERS OF M.V.I.T BANGALORE BATTLE OF BANDS \'11\nRUNNERS UP OF M.S.RAMAIAH MEDICAL COLLEGE BANGLORE BATTLE OF BANDS \'11\nWINNERS OF NATIONAL INSTITUTE OF DESIGN Dfrost BATTLE OF BANDS \'11\nWINNERS OF BANGALORE MEDICAL COLLEGE COBALT SKIES BATTLE OF BANDS \'11\nWINNERS OF RV COLLEGE OF ENGG BATTLE OF BANDS \'11\nRUNNERS UP OF AMBEDKAR MEDICAL COLLEGE BATTLE OF BANDS \'11\nWINNERS OF AATMATRISHA BATTLE OF THE BANDS, PESIT \'12 \n','portalofdeception@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Portal-of-Deception/187952324577935','','','','187952324577935','661',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','portal-of-deception'),(791,0,0,0,'Echoes Of The Throne','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Echoes-Of-The-Throne/259648854020','','','','259648854020','661',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','echoes-of-the-throne'),(792,0,0,0,'Space Zitar','Jeet plays the Mohan Veena (a Hawaiian slide guitar modified to sitar standards  a fusion instrument if ever there was one). \nA musical adventurist, hes inspired by soaring rave tunes and virtual campfires around which electronic musicians improvise on actual Ragas.','','http://www.facebook.com/spacezitar','','','','20610580121','661',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','space-zitar'),(793,0,0,0,'Fear ME deaR','Fear Me Dear is a trance-core-metal band from Kohima(Nagaland) formed in the year 2009.\n\"the first trance-core-metal band from NorthEast India\"','wearefearmedear@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/JentemK','','','','107917975941891','655',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','fear-me-dear'),(794,0,0,0,'punkh','PuNkH was formed in Germany 2004 under the name, GURU. After releasing their debut album Ghoom with Times Music, India in 2006, the band changed their name to PuNkH because lead singer and founder member Deepak Nair (Dean) decided on moving back to India.\n From 2004 to 2007 post release of Ghoom  the 4 piece high-energy set up toured through Europe and Germany and  competed for the prestigious Rockbuster Das Ding New Comer Contest in 2004 and went on to win the same.  \nIn 2007, after a mutual disagreement and the bands inability to strike any kind of a chord in the Indian Sub-Continent, Dean teamed up with Rapper Carsten Kraushaar and the duo decided to continue and work on material Dean had written over the past years.\nIn, what was.... short of a Tsunami of Combined Musical Fornication, they gave birth to the Self titled album, which was recorded in the winter of 2006 in Germany and co-produced and doctored by Audiotreatz.\nAudiotreats who had already produced  top-selling German artists like Dendemann, Nadja Benaissa (No Angels), Joy Denalane, Julian Smith and Nico Suave found it an ultimate challenge to work on a project with Hindi lyrics going in tandem with minimal electro beats and melodic raps in German and English.\nThe album was immediately picked up by EMI Virgin Music, India and released in 2007 with the debut music video Punjabi Na Aawe on Mtv and Channel V.\nThe song was also featured on an international compilation album released by EMI Music, France: Voyage au coeur de l\'inde [Songs from the heart of India] .\nDue to personal reasons Carsten could not move base to India and decided to quit the entire project.\nThe time was ripe,for Dean, to get in, singer Robin Joseph to Rap  and one of Nagalands most accomplished guitar players and buddy Yanger Sanglir to handle guitars along with DJ kunal, to tease with the mixes , turntables and grooves.\nBy now, PUNKH had toured coast to coast, across India and got themselves nine back-to-back gigs in Singapore, for the Kalaa Utsavam festival In 2009, from where, EMI Virgin featured the song Yunajaa on he compilation album India Rocks, featuring top Indian bands.\nWell, in the course of the mayhem of 2010, normal Metamorphosis, saw the departure of the DJ and inclusion of  keyboards and a second guitar player on power chords.\nIn Early 2011 the Band brainstormed on some of the famed tracks from the first album Ghoom, \nThe nu/metal sound literally blew the new members and since it was still a set of unknown and unheard songs despite a major label release in 2007 it was decided that it would be only apt to play and promote the same. \nIndias leading online independent artist portal ArtistAloud.com released the songs Karma , Insaaf and Tanha in 2011.\n','Mr.Fardean Khan','http://www.facebook.com/punkhband','','','','9141247007','653',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','punkh'),(795,0,0,0,'52 Commercial Road','Formed in late 2003 at the age of seventeen, 52 Commercial Road have been developing the post-rock sound far beyond the loud-quiet riffs we\'re used to. Emotive soundscapes built on fragile foundations become crescendous taking the listener to introspective worlds never explored.\n\nThe band have become most well known through being part of various projects in London aimed at the re-use of derelict and empty spaces from benefit nights, to art exhibitions to squat parties.\n\nTheir self released debut album has sold hundreds of copies and can be downloaded for free below. Their follow up E.P. will be released soon on south London based label \"A Future Without\"\n\nDownload the first album here:\nhttp://www.megaupload.com/?d=1VOTS2DO\n\n( to contact us about anything or if the download link above has expired email us at fiftytwocommercialroad@soon.com )\n\n\n','fiftytwocommercialroad@soon.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/52-Commercial-Road/19544293696','','','','19544293696','651',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','52-commercial-road'),(796,0,0,0,'In Dying Days','In Dying Days is an Indian Post-Hardcore/Metalcore band from Cochin, Kerala consisting of five members. The current members are Richie Titus, Ajay George Joseph, Jishnu V.N, Sandeep P.R and Sarath P.R.\n\nThe band was initially formed in 2007, when the founding band members, drummer Richie, vocalist Naveen Francis, and guitarist Jishnu created \"Split-Second Decision\". By November 2007, the band \"Split-Second\" was formed, adding Ajay on bass. Sandeep joined the band shortly after, taking up the role of bass and Ajay moving to guitar. The band continued to develop their vision of what the band would be, and moving on, the band played their first live performance in February 2008 at Kerala Rocks 08. \nWith plenty of material ready, the band started doing more local shows, following their first gig. \n\nIn July 2008, Naveen left the band for personal reasons. His replacement, Sarath P.R, Sandeep\'s younger brother, arrived during the mixing stages of this new project. Soon after, Ajay suggested renaming the band \"In Dying Days\", and in September 2009, the band played their first public performance with new vocalist Sarath at Underground 09 organised by Unwind Center, which became a huge breakthrough for the band, placing first in the entire South Zone. \n\nEver since, the band has been playing shows at various events, and is currently working towards the release of its first full-length album.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/In-Dying-Days/109155289104977','','','','109155289104977','644',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','in-dying-days'),(797,0,0,0,'Dormant Inferno','Amidst the clutter of Thrash, Death & Metalcore bands in Mumbai, two guys decided to take a different route and play Doom Metal. Influenced by varied bands Dormant Inferno aims at attaining a sound which is minimal yet captivating. Dormant Inferno hopes at exposing the Metalheads in Mumbai to Doom Metal, a beautiful yet ignored genre of Metal','Promotions Handled by Frameshift Initiatives - https://www.facebook.com/frameshiftinitiatives','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Dormant-Inferno/110769485617352','','','','110769485617352','640',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dormant-inferno'),(798,0,0,0,'BURN the Water','Formed in early 2011 as a solo Metal project by Debojyoti under the moniker of BURN the Water, it started out with creating experimental tunes influenced by musical genius Devin Townsend. Recently, released debut EP titled \'ESCHATOLOGICAL\'.','crapsound@in.com','http://www.facebook.com/waterburns','','','','205701026129427','637',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','burn-the-water'),(799,0,0,0,'Point Blanc','Point Blanc is a Hard Rock band from Pune. Formed with a new lineup in June 2011 with a almost completely new lineup , Point Blanc  found a new sound to itself with a blend of influences from all its members. \n\nThe history\n\nFormed in 2006, with almost an entirely different lineup, Point Blanc met moderate success. After a couple of successful shows, split up in their individual pursuit of interests.But as they say, the day is darkest just before the dawn, The band\'s premature split-up was the end that never was!\n \nThe new beginning\n\nCash and Bradley , the original founding members of the band stuck together with undeterred focus and determination to regroup and finally when they found Siddharth through a mutual friend and then discovered a wonderful drummer in Ajit. Thanks to Amit Godse , drummer of the band \'Silver\' , and brother of Ajit, the spot of a bassist was soon filled up by Gautam a.k.a \'Boomer\' and with him joined Arjun on the keyboards/synth.\n\nThe band clicked on \'first note\' and the first jam together was as tight as it could have been. Soon , the creative process took over, and in the first few jams , Point Blanc found a new sound to itself , and took re-birth in May 2011. \n\n\nProfile:\n\nWinners of Voice of the Voiceless Maadhyam 2011.\nWinners of \'Titans of Rock\' at IISER Karavaan 2011.\nWinners of Silhouette synesthesia 2012 at AFMC 2012.\nFinalists at W.O.R.M.E fest in Delhi\nRunners up at CASCADE 2011 at Symbiosis international School.\nQualified for Pune leg of Independence Rock XXVI\n\n\nIndividual Awards :\n Best Vocalist (twice) - Cash\n Best Bassist              - Boomer\n Best Keyboardist      - Arjun \n                                \n','Bradley Nipps - nippsbradley@gmail.com, Arjun Shrivatsan arjunshrivatsan@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/PointBlanc.in','','','','215702655130365','633',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','point-blanc'),(800,0,3,3,'Moon Arra','MoonArra means Three Streams. The lietmotif of all our lives is our quest and fascination for beautiful sounds  how sounds travelled from Northern India in the 13th century, journeyed thru Persia, Morocco even up to Andalucian Spain','','http://www.facebook.com/moonarra','http://www.moonarra.com','','http://www.reverbnation.com/moonarra','0','631',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','moon-arra'),(801,0,0,0,'Carnival Underground Music-Alley','Carnival Underground is a collaboration of the various aspects of audio and video production under one roof. Thrown in with the studio, is a jam pad and music classes. A concept to provide every musician, filmaker, photographer, model and artist out there, a space to perform, create and find like minded people to become a part of an idea, a concept, an initiative and a space where creativity brings on a high. \n\nJAM PAD: WHITE NOISE\nCarnival Underground\'s jam pad offers a range of high- end equipment. Aptly named WHITE NOISE, the jam pad has white walls and a red carpet with a reflecting glass ceiling. Dimmer lights in different shades complete the ambience. The equipment details are given below:\n\nPearl Forum 7 piece\nVT 100 VOX Tube Guitar Amp\nLine 6 Spider Guitar Amp\nWarwick Profet 3.03 Bass Amp\nAKG D5 mic\nSennheiser Evolution mic\nDB Technology PA 400 RMS Speakers\nSoundcraft Mixer EFX 8\nDBX 31 Band EQ \nBSS Audio AR 133 DI Box  ','Shatabdi Chakrabarti: c.shatabdi@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Carnival-Underground-Music-Alley/159246354098528','','','','159246354098528','631',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','carnival-underground-music-alley'),(802,0,0,0,'Pranoy BliXter x [Official]','\n\nBorn in 1991, in the City of Cochin,India. He is a prolific and aspiring Indian drummer. Since childhood music was his passion and soul.\n\n At the age of 6 he started his first lessons in 