OCs), to grow as musicians & also to get acknowledged and recognized as a band.\n\nVery soon the band found their full-time bassist in Manish, lending an ecstatic groove to their sound. Being heavily influenced by Pakistani band Call, they needed a growler to enhance the Urdu Metal compositions & thats when Karthik, a hardcore metal-head & a friend of Irfan was invited to join. His growls added a complete new flavor & dimension to the band & also allowed them to diversify their genre & to experiment.\n\nBoth Salil & Irfan had been writing & composing songs all this time & now it was time to recollect the work done. They introduced the OC\'s to other members of the band and by the end of an all-night jam, they could clearly end up with 7 tracks (5 in Urdu/hindi and 2 in English). The compositions came up way better than they\'d expected & gave the band a sound-footing to go for something bigger : An EP !!\n\nNow there grew a need for a more meaningful & relevant name for the band. And thus the name was changed to \'Firaaq\' which means a keen desire for something. The people at Firaaq justify the name as: \"we guys came together to fulfill our intense desire to create some good & mesmerizing music & also to make our listeners yearn for more. Through our music we hope to induce desires into people who are crushed & oppressed so they look ahead for a better tomorrow. In a nutshell, we & our listeners, we both are in each others Firaaq & hence there couldn\'t have been a more apt name but Firaaq \" !!!!\n\nThe Band\'s influences range from bands like Call, Akash - The Band, Greenday, Junoon, Entity Paradigm (EP), Jal, Led Zeppelin, RATM, Nirvana, Pink Floyd & Guns n Roses.\n\nThe band is currently working on their first single \'Naya Aashiyaan\' & their EP of six tracks, looking forward to release their music very soon.','thebandfiraaq@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/FiraaqTheBand','','','','167017316722608','612',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','firaaq-the-band'),(806,0,0,0,'Heavens Down','','studioesp@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/Heavensdown','','','','185164781510548','611',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','heavens-down'),(807,0,0,0,'Nepal ka Sangit chor haru.','','','http://www.facebook.com/nepali.copycats','','','','306121182732833','611',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','nepal-ka-sangit-chor-haru'),(808,0,0,0,'Third Culture Sound','Third Culture is an exclusive school for global music education and is the first of it\'s kind in India.\nThird Culture Sound is an institution that is driven by the motto \"Globalization\".At Third Culture, importance is given to technique and skill, while laying equal emphasis on overall performance.We at Third Culture believe in taking indian music to the next level in educating and creating an awareness for the potential that Indian musician\'s possess.The method of teaching is strictly one-on-one, allowing the faculty to understand the student\'s needs individually.The various level of talent and skill present in India which is the second largest population in the world, is beyond belief. We believe in striving harder in unifying musicians and people to cause of \"United India\" through music. May the force be with you! \nInitiated by Jerry John (Jere-Maya), a well established drummer and musician.\n\nCOURSES: \nBasic Drum Education.\nAdvanced Drumming.\nGuitars\nVocals \n\n\nFACULTY:\n\nJERRY JOHN (Founder).\n\n\"Be a part of the movement\"','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Third-Culture-Sound/127772650588059','','','','127772650588059','611',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','third-culture-sound'),(809,0,1,1,'DJ SOUL Remixes','A Virgoan by birth, music connoisseur by profession and a roadie for life. \nDJ SOUL is a down to earth friendly guy who is amongst  the youngest DJ\'s getting \nrenowned day by day with his intoxicating tracks.  \nThis male bastion is now a DJ turned Music Producer who specializes in bollywood \nas well as commercial, progressive & punch electro. \nHe not only creates channels for self-expression but also gives prime importance to creativity while spinning the disc. His wicked sense of music separates him from his contemporaries. He knows how to harness rhythm in order to get most out of his audience.','+919545597007','http://www.facebook.com/DJ.SOUL.Remixes','','','','251473884879952','611',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-soul-remixes'),(810,0,0,0,'Calling Superman','Yo\' know that rock music is dying... so we wanted Superman to come and save rock n\' roll... So thats how we got the name CALLING SUPERMAN!!\n\nWe are a newly formed pop/rock band with all the band members from the north-east india. Currently based in new delhi consisting of vocalist John Maram (A4apple), guitarist Abhishek Boro (Rampazze) and guitarist Roon.\n\n','','http://www.facebook.com/callingsuperman','','','','107060242682782','607',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','calling-superman'),(811,0,0,0,'Scratch Card Winners','Born on 18th April, 2009.\n\nOne of the most energetic bands in the circuit, The Cards need a beer tank to refill.\n\nSo put on headphone, crank up the volume and switch to the louder side up.\n\nCaution : Exercise caution when listening to this band. Use Ear Plugs as the music might damage your ears.\n\nAnd about our achievements, we still havent won the Grammys yet ','scratchcardwinners@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/scratchcardwinners','','','','181273528262','607',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','scratch-card-winners'),(812,0,0,0,'Trojan Horse','TROJAN HORSE started off as a 2 man project (Hasnain and Siddhartha of CARNAGE), using a few drum softwares to \'\'get the job done\'\' temporarily.\n\nThen we got hold of the drumming talent of Vishnu and Brute vocals of Siva Sbk (both being members of an already accomplished band named CRYPTED)\n\nWe\'ve been an active 4-piece band since November 2010 and have already come up with a few originals.\n\n\nWe have big plans for the future, and are confident to say that the Heavy Metal scene in Chennai/India is beginning to take Center-Stage.\n\n\\m/>_<\\m/','trojanhorseofficial@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/trojanhorseband','','','','175314279156128','607',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','trojan-horse'),(813,0,0,0,'ReCycle','Recycle came into existence in November 2006 with a common urge to bring the musical landscapes of 90\'s grunge, Alternative and funk flavor to the Imphal music scene for the very first time. Pior to starting off their Recycle journey all band members played in different local bands separately. The band won the Best Vocalist award at the Hornbill Rock Festival 2007.\n\nRecycle also took part in the mega Nokia Promotional Christmas Rock Festival 2008 held in three districts of Manipur and Shillong (Meghalaya).\n\nIn 2009, Recycle also worked in a project titled \"Rock4Life\" which is part of social awareness/anti-stigma HIV/AIDS campaign and contributed their talent by writing a song called \"Walk On\" for its compilation CD. The compilation album was written by various artists from across the 8 States in North East India to support the cause. So far so good, the journey has been culminated an experience of live gigs, rehearsals and studio recordings. Looking at the long journey ahead, the band is ever more than ready for the miles ahead.','Bode Paonam +91 9856344013','http://www.facebook.com/recycleimphal','','','','206617215426','607',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','recycle'),(814,0,0,0,'Attyachari','We\'ve come a long way from angry and self-obsessed personas to whatz now called\'ATTYACHARI\'.A crew of four and as I call them \"The FIVE Insanes\", came together because of their love for music. so, lemme juz go person by person so 