t these, our home grown star Praveen Achary has left the audiences wanting more of him. And why not?\r\n\r\nHaving grown up in Lebanon and Canada, dance music had a major influence on him. His diverse international sound is influenced from his strong musical background as well as traveling across the world. The dedication and commitment to dance music led him to be one of co-founders, along with Tanseer, of \'The SF Show\', which is Indias FIRST 2 hour international progressive podcast. The show has featured guests like Cid Inc, Darin Epsilon, Sonic Union, Deepfunk etc and recently celebrated its landmark 25th episode. As a part of The SF Shows launch tour in India, Praveen has played at a few of Indias most sought after clubs.\r\n\r\nHis DJing skills have always gained him a lot of appreciation, but the compliments dont stop here. His panache & signature style, with an emphasis on a unique combination of Deep, Tech and Progressive house, give his audiences the platform they crave. In late 2009, he signed his debut original single \'Crossover\' on \'Maktub Music\', owned by Arjun Vagale & Nicolas Silvano, a monster big-room tune with a star cast of great remixes on board that received play among A-list DJs & producers.\r\n\r\nWith new originals already signed to \'Maktub Music\' and \'Mirabilis Records\', along with remixes on \'Outside The Box Music\' & \'Spherax Records\', 2011 is proving to be Praveens favourite year so far! His productions have already received massive support from Sasha, Nick Warren, Cid Inc, Henry Saiz, Darin Epsilon and the likes. Praveens guest mixes over various radio shows have been a super hit with his audiences. He has been invited by friskyRadio to showcase an exclusive hour long guest mix on \'Frisky Loves India\' with the other Indian giant artists like Anil Chawla, Arjun Vagale, Sanjay Dutta etc. After many compliments on this guest mix, Praveen was again invited to be featured as \'Artist of The Month\' on friskyRadio. \r\n\r\nAlready on the fast track, Praveen Achary is most definitely a name to keep an eye on. He is on his way to gain repute of a pioneer in the progressive music scene in India. In a scene, where electronic dance music has been dominated by giant international names, it is stunningly refreshing to see a young Indian make his way through this with consistent quality productions & sets.','nirali@sqprojekt.com','https://www.facebook.com/praveenacharymusic','http://twitter.com/praveenachary','http://soundcloud.com/praveenachary','','0','591',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-06 03:10:13',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','praveen-achary'),(820,0,0,0,'_AdaManTiuM_','','Avadhoot Ket - +919730207560,  Kevin - +919665081041, Aditya - +918390566765','http://www.facebook.com/amtmtheband','','','','70566302462','589',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','adamantium-1'),(821,0,0,0,'8 BulletS','THIS BAND WAS FORMED BY 8 MUGICIANS IN 13TH JUNE 2009 _ In fall of 2010, I & members decided to start a Metal project of a dark and aggressive nature. In January of 2011,we recorded 2 metal songs . With a passion for the darker side of the metal realm, 8 BulletS combines elements of Black Metal / Death Metal / Melodic Death Metal into one. With the ruthless ambition to expose this metal assault to the world, a live crew will be assembled upon the completion of 8 BulletS song, 3 minute d \"BulleT FirE\" to be released on April 1st, 2011.CONCERTS .. d new Arrival song was \"Dead on Soul$\"length 6 mins released on 7th of august 2011 . \nAND ALL MEMBERS ARE UNDER 18 AGES. \nSOO KEEP ON TOUCH \\\\M//','arrivaltodeath@yahoo.in','http://www.facebook.com/pages/8-BulletS/180775691946163','','','','180775691946163','588',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','8-bullets'),(822,0,0,0,'Cheisrah','Cheisrah is an Experimental Metal Band formed in May\'2011 and based in Bangalore, India. \"Cheisrah\" is Imon Nirvan: Vocals, Amit Debnath: Guitars, Thejus Nair: Guitars, Rajdeep Chakraborty: Bass Guitars, Amarjeet Karam: Drums\n','cheisrahtheband@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/cheisrah','','','','189725371075670','587',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','cheisrah'),(823,0,0,0,'Bhaanu Mendiratta','Well, i\'m primarily a guitarist/composer. Mostly into blues/rock/alternative, my primary influences being the likes of Pat Metheny, DMB, SRV, BB King, John Mayer, Floyd... Let me know how you like what you hear on my page. Spread the word if you like it. Would definitely help in presenting my stuff to a larger audience, which is basically the purpose of this page. And it would mean a lot, to me. \nI also won the biggest nationwide wide online guitar solo competition called \"Solo Stunts\". So you better stay tuned to this space! ','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Bhaanu-Mendiratta/152067821521562','','','','152067821521562','585',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','bhaanu-mendiratta'),(824,0,1,1,'DJ Govinda','Govinda is an Italian dj and psytrance party organizer. Born in 1986 to parents who had been traveling for many years, he grew up living in Goa, India six months a year and experiencing its magic and freaky context from an early age.\n\nHis first party in 1999 brought a full understanding of the Goa reality with its emphasis on freedom, and manifested his attraction to trance music. He started collecting music and playing it, at first with a Minidisc player and later with CDJs.\n\nIn 2002, Govinda played his first dj set in the well-known Ninebar in Goa, thus marking the beginning of his dj career. He instantaneously loved the feeling of enjoyment he could provide through music and the palpable interconnection that forms on a dancefloor. After a practice season, he was soon playing in the main party spots in Goa: Discovalley, Paradiso, Primrose, Monkey Valley, Hilltop and many more.\n\nIn 2005, he was signed to Spun records (the GMS label). Two years later, he went on his first international tour where he played along artists such as GMS, Pixel, Alien Project, Spacecat, Domestic, Perplex and Psysex, in Thailand, Nepal, Goa as well as several European countries.\n\nDuring the Goa season of 2007/2008, Govinda started following a different vibe and looking for a more psychedelic sound that would best fit his personality. At the time, Phatmatix, Digital Talk and Concept were his favorite artists. At the Mountain Madness Festival in Nepal, he played a set right before Ajja and fell in love with his sound. The meeting also started a connection with Peak Records, which later led to Govinda being signed on as a label dj.\n\nWhile frequently performing at Goan hotspots such as Club Westend, Hilltop, Ninebar and Shivavalley, he created with a group of friends the NightRainbow Project, a Goa-based party organization responsible for more than ten parties in the first season of its existence. \n\nTo this day, Govinda splits his life between Europe and India and organizes a number of events in both Goa and Italy. He has played at numerous international events (Sonica, Full Moon and Antaris to name but a few) and continues to rock the dancefloors around the globe. His dj sets are widely appreciated for their colorful, positive and twisted sounds, artfully blended to form a harmonic sequence. \n\nLet the adventure begin!This are the biggest parties till 2011:\n\nGoa season 2008/2009:\n29-30.11.08		MYSTICALL Club Westend\n13-14.12.08		REBEL REUNION Club Westend (special dj set by Giuseppe vs Arjuna) \n21-22.12.08		LIQUID SOUNDS Club Westend\n27-28.12.08		TRANSMISSION Club Westend\n31.12.08-02.01.09	THE NEW YEAR PARTY 48hrs Club Westend\n12.01.09			RELOAD Club Westend (special guest Gms Pixel n Manifold)\n12.02.09			COCO HUTS beach party (sp. guest Pixel & Liquid Ross)\n22-23.02.09		SHIVA RATRI Club Westend (special guest Madmaxx, Sirius isness and Gidra)\n29.03.09			ELEMENTS Club Westend (line up by Arjuna)\n30.03.09			RELEASE CHANDRA PARTY\n\nGo