://www.facebook.com/pages/Lycanthropia/135328556483310','','','','135328556483310','556',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','lycanthropia'),(842,0,0,0,'Culminant','Culminant was formed in June 2007 when Pranay and Sudarshan  were looking for members to form a band. Their search co-incided with Bharad looking to do vocals for a band. They met up and jammed a couple of times until it was decided that it sounded good. Still lacking a drummer, and after auditioning about 3 of them, it was decided that Pranay\'s brother Deep was the best of the lot despite still being a learner.  In October 2007, a replacement was found when we welcomed Danny Johnson (ex-Catatonic Rage) into the fold. Line-up change dogged the band again when in February 2008, founder member/bassist Sudarshan left the band due to work-related reasons. In early April, locally well known guitarist/solo artist Umanath Kamath was added as the new bass player. In August 2009, the band decided to part ways with Danny Johnson, and found a replacement in Siddharth \"Mukul\" Das (ex-Cranium Shatter, Speedblade). In October 2009, Umanath decided to leave the band to pursue different styles of music, and an immediate replacement was found in Anup. 2010 saw yet another line up change with the departure of Mukul and Anup switching to lead guitar duties and bass duties filled in by Adarsh. Culminant finally do have a stable line up and are looking for more gigs and also to hit the studios soon.','mail.culminant@gmail.com | +91 - 9916256887','http://www.facebook.com/Culminant','','','','182529265100557','554',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','culminant'),(843,0,2,2,'The Riot Peddlers','G Och D. Qui tes-vous. my balle. ???? ????????? . ??? ??? ???? ??? ??????? . ?????? ??????? ?? ???????. If you cant grasp our rant try catching us live in your city.','','http://www.facebook.com/theriotpeddlers','http://www.reverbnation.com/theriotpeddlers','','','156751364352667','553',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-riot-peddlers'),(844,0,0,0,'Atiar','The band was officially formed on 18th November, 2003.  Had been performing for almost a decade, Praising and Glorifying the name of our Lord Jesus Christ in various places of the State of Meghalaya and with Him by our side we had gained much confidence, mentality and experience.  In 2009, Atiar released its self-titled album which includes 9 originals and 1 hymn recorded at Rangdap\'s T&KC Studio.\n\nThe band could not have gone through without thanking God Almighty and Jesus Christ, our Saviour for all the blessings He had showered on the  band and also all our friends,families and all the fans for their support.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Atiar/141042557260','','','','141042557260','553',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','atiar'),(845,0,0,0,'Sanjay Divecha','TO DOWNLOAD SANJAY\'S MUSIC PLEASE GO TO\nwww.musicstore.bluefrogsounds.com\nYOU CAN DOWNLOAD INDIVIDUAL TRACKS @ Rs 25\nALBUM AVAILABLE @ Rs 300 FOR PHYSICAL CDs \nRs 250 FOR DIGITAL\nFREE SHIPPING!!!! (INDIA ONLY)\n\nSanjay has crossed many borders, physical & cultural, in pursuit of his vision - a vision of world community, expressed through music.\n\nA native of Mumbai, India, Sanjay graduated from GUITAR INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY, Los Angeles in 1989, where he studied with SCOTT HENDERSON, JOE DIORIO and ROBBEN FORD.\n\nSanjay was quick to become an active member of the Los Angeles music scene, as a guitar player and composer, where he had the opportunity to play and absorb a myriad of styles ranging from Jazz, Brazilian, African, R&B and Gospel. In his 15 years stay in Los Angeles, he recorded and toured with a variety of artists including ANGELIQUE KIDJO, CARLOS SANTANA, DAVE WECKL, LOUIS JOHNSON, DUMAZZ, SAMBAGURU, MICHAEL MC DONALD, FRED RAULSTON among others, and played on some of the most prestigious stages including the PLAYBOY JAZZ FESTIVAL at the HOLLYWOOD BOWL, and the NEW ORLEANS JAZZ FESTIVAL. He also has worked on several soundtracks for movies including WOMAN ON TOP and LEELA, which he scored.\n\nReturning to India in 2003 in search of his musical & cultural roots, Sanjay has spent the last 2 years exploring the sounds and languages of his heritage, and recording his new album \"FULL CIRCLE\".\n\nPlaying with the creme de la creme of musicians from his home town Mumbai, each live concert has been an uplifting and inspiring event for all who have attended. Sanjay has also been actively working in the BOLLYWOOD film industry as a composer and session musician for film songs & soundtracks. ','Stuart Dacosta [stuart@bluefrog.co.in]','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Sanjay-Divecha/10027294762','','','','10027294762','552',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sanjay-divecha'),(846,0,0,0,'Chokfite','Erstwhile PnM Inc.;  Chokfite(pronounced as chalk-fight) is a Delhi based band and has been together for 2 years now. The band was formed in 2009 by Ankit Murarka, Sahil Gupta, Kanishk Mehta and Anshul Vashist. It featured Kanishk on vocals, and Ankit on vocals as well as guitars with Sahil, while Deepak Garg was on drums and Anshul on bass and the keyboard. \n\nWinters of 2009 brought about some changes in the lineup with Deepak leaving the band in search of musical enlightenment and the addition of Abhay sharma on Drums. Around about this period in time Kanishk took the reins of lead guitarist and hence shared the same with Ankit. Chokfite, then, proceeded to record a single with Saffire Studios (their original composition someone better than me), which is now available on its reverbnation and facebook page along with other demo records. \nOctober 2010 brought about another paradigm shift in the bands existence. Abhay Sharma left the band and Deepak rejoined, hence becoming an integral part on the lineup that stands today; Ankit on vocals and guitars, Sahil on guitars, Kanishk on vocals and guitars, Anshul on synth and bass and Deepak on drums.\nIn Febuary 2011, Chokfite played to a crowd of approximately 1,500 at PSIT, New Delhi. The band also performed at Rocknova at Hindustan Times Youth Nexus (held in DCAC, delhi university, south campus) amongst the 10 best bands of the state.\n\nChokfites music  is much debated upon due to its non-conformity to a particular genre. Chokfite is arguably the pioneer of Chalk rock. A five piece band with members from different backgrounds, the influences are many, varying from Alternative to progressive rock and even psychedelic rock. Chokfite\'s music is characterized by let go vocals and fills, punk/grunge and rock& roll influenced rhythm guitars with Blues influenced lead guitar, haunting synth effects and drum beats that make a statement, all complemented by a combination of mature, poetic & contradictory i-dont-wanna-grow-up song writing. The band also tries to bring in a flavour of Psychedelic/Experimental Rock with prolonged keyboard, guitar and drum solos which forms as essential part of their music. \nChokfite is a socially active band and through their music they express what everyone feels and learns through those feelings in every sphere of an exceedingly complicated life. Experience rises over \'on-paper\' biased perceptions. In a world of groggy imperfections, It isnt in our identity but through our actions that we are defined.  This is what Chokfite represents and tries to bring to life in the form of music. We want you to take with us a journey of new thoughts; introspection;  meditation; bring your sub-conscious to travel to the conscious, living a life that you want to, into a space of free self. \n\nPast Gigs:\n\nBlues cafe (3 times)\nThe stage Manajsa\nCafe oz (2 Times)\nTurquoise Cottage\nCafe bahi\nTryst Music Cafe\nUndrgrnd Cafe\nIIM Lucknow Manfest as Headliners\n\nMajor Achievements:\n\n1. Winners proactivate gigs and events 2011 among bands from all over the country.\n2. Winners War of bands at Reverb\'11 with best guitarist award.\n3. Played in the top 10 bands from delhi in ht city youth nexus 2011.\n4. Headliners at Hi-tech institute of technology\'10\n5. Winners at Rock war at Amity school of aerospace engg\'09\n6. Runners up at battle of bands at amity school of engineering and Tecnology\'09.\nMany more...\\m/\n\n','7838860833','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Chokfite/142919019079759','','','','142919019079759','551',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','chokfite'),(847,0,0,0,'Bramfatura','Bramfatura is a collaborative music production duo consisting of Mark Fulgado and Gaurav Godkhindi. Working alongside favored session musicians and vocalists, they make records and tour live.\n\nThis collaboration was a result of a chance meeting while in Sydney. They quickly realized a potential to combine their almost polar tastes and aesthetics in music, which led to a series of productive studio sessions.\n\nIn the aftermath of these experimentations, the duo decided to take some of this material on the road. What followed was a number of stints at underground clubs and these initial shows helped cement their distinctive sound and imagery.\n\nInterestingly, Bramfatura\'s work extends beyond their particular blend of contemporary songwriting and electronica. Their interest in various genres and formats of music has lead them down avenues of Film & TV production, Electronic Dance Music Production and performing DJ sets.\n\nBramfatura is currently recording and touring with independent singer/songwriter Cherry Fernandes','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Bramfatura/177151178999464','','','','177151178999464','550',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','bramfatura'),(848,0,0,0,'Hourglass Inversion','No were not going to tell you any clichd tale about how we all just discovered each other and what came out as Hourglass Inversion (formerly Hourglass) was really predestined. Hourglass Inversion was formed painstakingly by bringing together a range of talented musicians whose varied interests, influences and egos would never come is the way of music. Our music is here to stay - we hope eternally! \n\n\nGigs. Music. Media \n\nHourglass Inversion has given several memorable performances at various venues in Pune - Soul, (Not Just Jazz) By the Bay, Curve, SITM, DY Patil, Elysium, SIMS... to name a few. \n\nThe ripples that the band\'s distinct music created, found their way into the media circles of Pune and consequently Hourglass featured in Pune Mirror, Saakal Times, Times of India (Westside Plus supplement) and Outlook Profit. In 2009, Hourglass was invited by FM Fever 104, Mumbai to perform at its studio. Most recently, Hourglass featured in music magazine, BIG M in their cover story. \n\nHourglass was also selected for and participated in Channel V Launchpad 2009 , a revered destination for most bands in India. \n\nMost recently Hourglass was among the top 15 bands in the Indian Rock Revolution contest organized by Seamless Education Academy to win an opportunity to record a track at their studios.','hourglasstheband@gmail.com, Amit 9767723875, Yayati 9011043161, Hemant 9960755283, Chetan 9970164115','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Hourglass-Inversion/167382349953511','','','','167382349953511','547',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','hourglass-inversion'),(849,0,0,0,'Six Strings','A band trying to introduce music that blends blues basically and rock-fusion (Rok-usion)...\nSIX STRINGS are..shaggy-vocals,adil-lead guitars,mandy-bassist,varun-drums,vicky and tirkey-rhythms..Winners at battle of the bands-Acoustic [nmit]\nPlayed at Oscar \'11 Trichy [TN] ,Gopalan arch,innovation,colleges,Sat jam , crossword bookstores, etc..\n','+919945526934  mandy26934@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/sixstrings.bengaluru','','','','120361514708427','546',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','six-strings'),(850,0,0,0,'Mushroom Lake','','mushroomlaketheband@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/MushroomLake','','','','194696407225842','546',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','mushroom-lake'),(851,0,0,0,'When Everything Falls Apart (W.E.F.A)','','wefallsapart@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/When-Everything-Falls-Apart-WEFA/174674035876328','','','','174674035876328','544',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','when-everything-falls-apart-wefa'),(852,0,0,0,'bird of youth','  Beth Wawerna\'s involvement with rock music started a couple minutes after she was born, when her 14-year-old brother stubbornly insisted she be named for the 1976 KISS power ballad \"Beth.\" Her parents consented  thus unwittingly sealing their daughter\'s fate.\n    \n  Beth now fronts her own rock band, Bird of Youth, whose debut album \"Defender\" (out May 24) was produced by Will Sheff of Okkervil River and Phil Palazzolo (The New Pornographers, Ted Leo, Neko Case), with a cast of players that includes members of The Wrens, Nada Surf, The National, Okkervil River and the Mendoza Line. \n     \n  Growing up in Atlanta, GA, Beth spent her formative years sifting through her brother\'s abandoned record collection. She became taken with artists like Elvis Costello and The Replacements, whose rowdy intellect fit in nicely with the Southern indie-rock she\'d already been exposed to  bands like R.E.M., Pylon and The Rock*A*Teens. When it came time to leave the South, Beth got a job, moved to Brooklyn, got laid off, went to bars and stayed up late with her musician friends  drinking beer and singing songs. But she was also writing songs of her own  songs that felt both brainy and tough, thoughtful and tossed-off, vicious and vulnerable. For so long, Beth had been the consummate green-room insider, but dubious creative outsider  comfortable hanging backstage, but terrified of being on it. For that reason, she wrote for years before sharing so much as a note. But she kept writing, and the number of songs grew. Then finally, a few years down the road  armed with a collection of home-recorded demos  she mustered the courage to send them to friends, and they encouraged her to make an album.\n  \n  \"Defender\" recalls the classic and college rock Beth grew up with, as well as the swagger of old New York girl groups and the insight and sarcasm the early new wave songwriters. Inherent in Beths voice is a cool stoicism  a dry, knowing wink that is as affecting in Defenders moments of dark humor and ornate storytelling as it is in its flashes of unvarnished heartbreak. Beth\'s dry delivery finds a perfect match in lead guitarist Clinton Newman, whose lush, multilayered harmonies and intertwining guitar parts give this record its distinctive sound  something like Chrissie Hynde fronting Squeeze or Nico signed to Stiff Records. As intricate pop songcraft crumbles into gauzy atmospherics and literate observations devolve into boozy chaos, Bird of Youths rave ups and kiss offs turn indie-rock braininess back on itself with a casual frivolity. \n\nOver the past few years, Beth has put that wonderfully unstable marriage to the test on stage, appearing with The Wrens, The Mendoza Line, Okkervil River, Roky Erickson, A.C. Newman and others. With the band\'s permanent touring lineup rounded out by bassist Johnny North, drummer Ray Ketchem and keyboardist Eli Thomas, Bird of Youth plan to spend the summer months of 2011 bringing \"Defender\" direct to the fans.      \n\n[press] \nChris Vinyard: vinyard@bighassle.com\n    \n','chris vinyard / vinyard@bighassle.com','http://www.facebook.com/birdofyouth','','','','81141069058','542',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','bird-of-youth'),(853,0,0,0,'Devoid of Dreams','','Kaushik Jai Barua | +91-9650699951','http://www.facebook.com/DevoidOfDreams','','','','167107199981199','541',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','devoid-of-dreams'),(854,0,0,0,'Lalon Band Bangla','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Lalon-Band-Bangla/187406281300159','','','','187406281300159','540',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','lalon-band-bangla'),(855,0,2,2,'SHKABANG!','Shkabang is a bunch of musicians who have played stage many times, separately. Rock, electronic, jazz, reggae, classic, funk and bollywood..they\'re doing/done/will do all of that. They hang out..and played a gig together for kicks early last year. They sounded great and had so much fun, they decided to hook up and play some music together for real.\r\nShkabang likes big sounds and the rush that comes with the banging bass and they\'re sound can best be described as electro-pop-rock-bubble-disco-dance-bang music!Comprising of four members, the band came together for one reason only- to make some noise!\r\nA video director by day and probably the music scene\'s most banging drummer by night, Shiraz Bhatacharya gives Shkabang the raw power and energy they need on stage. He is also part of the immensely popular rock act, Pentagram, and has just finished shooting Shkabang\'s first video.\r\nNiranjan \'Pozy\' Dhar, a guitar chameleon, is known for his contribution to India\'s most adored rock band, Zero. Pozy is also part of great new acts like Tough On Tobacco and KNAP.Makarand Mane aka Papal who plays bass is also part of Pentagram.\r\nFrontwoman Anushka Manchanda is a livewire on stage. Anushka is a playback singer in Bollywood amongst many other things and quite the diva in rock music circles.\r\nSo come, Shkabang?!','admin@mixtapelive.in','www.facebook.com/shkabang ','','','','0','537',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','shkabang'),(856,0,0,0,'Sound Avtar','','','http://www.facebook.com/iamSoundAvtar','','','','155893024517289','536',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sound-avtar'),(857,0,0,0,'7Tones','------------------ \"  F O R M A T I O N   OF  T H E  B A N D  \"-------------------\n\nThe previous band of Kamal was going good but things started changing as the other members  sought different likes in music changing their inclination towards heavy metal and keeping the band only for festive purpose. Thus the vocalist was secluded and what he wanted to do was not happening but the zeal was still alive which needed to be rekindled. As days were passing, the passion for music was making him numb but luckily he met Probin one of his school mate who was then playing guitar. His inviting me to his house resulted in forming some self compositions which till now had ignited the flame within to form another band. Then came Utpal another school friend who also wanted to give his best towards the new Initiative. Indeed,both Utpal and Probin penned down a wonderful song \"Ankhon Mein Ban Gayi\" which is still afresh in our mind. Utpal\'s journey couldn\'t last long as he had other priorities in life. The hunt for a drummer was on when one fine day Probin landed with a so called Drummerist at my house introducing him as Prabh Nair another junior fellow of our school who pressed that he would certainly meet our expectation. Though an amature then, he was given a chance to join us but the problem was he didn\'t have a drum set. That too was taken care off when the newly bought Indian drumkit was stationed at the vocalist\'s house and jamming started. By chance I met Premanjan Bhattacharya another school pal who was a guitarist then,while going to office. The next thing was that I asked him to come the next sunday as some of us had already started jamming. One fine sunday after jamming, Probin told me that he met a fellow named Rajiv who is a guitarist, Theoretically Sound and we should once try his capability. Jamming together was going good but we still were missing something i.e a Bass Guitarist. During these incidences my classmate Iqbal hussain started attending the practise sessions and showed his inclination towards playing the Bass Guitar, which finally got fulfilled as we persuaded him to buy one. During that time, the band was going through financial crisis as we didnt have proper equipments for which some of the band members contributed for buying some equipments.\n\n                   Now the thought of naming the entire Initiative was of prime concern, and it came from the mind of Iqbal Hussain. Thus the band was christined with the name 7Tones. The name means the unity among all the band members as all the notes of music are incomplete without each of them. If talked in hindi it can also be called \"SAATH SUR\". As the band was newly formed, we didnt have any knowledge what genre to concentrate upon but then we thought of keeping Hindi Rock as the topic to play.\n\n    August was round the corner and our jamming sessions were in it\'s peak on the rented attic whose expences we all agreed to share. Practising on the roof was going good and our confidence level reached new heights when a promotional photo shoot was done by one of Iqbal\'s friend. Now the band consists of S.Kamal,Probin,Prabh Nair,Premanjan,Rajiv and Iqbal hussain. With this line up we video recorded two covers and one self composition but still the crave for getting shows was eating us within. Time flew by and the festive season was near and luckily we bagged a couple of shows in Durga Puja in Sep 2009.We started on a good note and plastered our confidence level by also performing in Christmas Carnival followed by performance in New Years Eve on 31st Dec 2009 in Indore. However, the new year didnt start with a happy note as differences cropped up among the band members and the productivity of the band decreased. Premanjan left the band due to his personal problems and Rajiv was asked to leave as it was a joint decision taken by all of us. So now we were 4 members left in the band and the hunt for a lead guitarist was revived again.\n\n                      Through Orkut, we came in contact with Abhishek Bhandari a college going lad who just started strumming the guitar then. He was being called by us and his potential was knocked. Though an amature, his mingling nature was liked by all of us and he started attending our jam sessions. In july 2010 we got a chance to perform in a charity show for an N.G.O where the band members regained their confidence and started everything altogether. But something else was written in the destiny of 7Tones.Probin started keeping himself more involved in his fathers business due to which his interest was becoming less towards the band. At the end Probin parted from us after giving his best in Durga Puja 2010 and finally four of us were there to take the journey of 7Tones ahead.\n\n----------  A New Era Started ---------\n\nNow it was a mammoth task ahead how we should had continued the journey as already many members chose their different ways. We strategically planned, worked upon weeks and decided what should be our next step and how often we should jam. After few months everybody started jamming at kamals house where practicing upon our Self Compositions and taking inputs from each other was our prime concern. During this time kamals neighbour invited trouble for us by calling the police. It was an harrowing experience then but we managed somehow. Our jamming still continued with full vigor and we were lucky enough to bag a show on the New Years eve of 2010 in Meerut. It was one of the highest paid shows. We never looked back after that and kept on performing in various battle of bands and even won many accolades. Its been almost 9 to 10 months of our continuous efforts for which we are getting the fruitful results. \n   \n     We are moving ahead keeping in mind the genres like Rock / Sufi / Fusion and it could very well be heard in our own Self Compositions.Soon we would be coming with our first single Pari of our yet to be released album.\n\n7TONES family :-\nPremanjan Bhattacharya, Probin, Rajiv, Vishal.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/7Tones/114741451910863','','','','114741451910863','535',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','7tones'),(858,0,0,0,'Ibn Batuta & Tatar','The concept was formed in the year 2000. iBt is the winner of Band E Mataram III. After that it released its debut album \'\'Timbacktoo\'\' from Big Music. The band mostly writes songs on dual identity and illision.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Ibn-Batuta-Tatar/68856077179','','','','68856077179','535',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ibn-batuta-tatar'),(859,0,0,0,'Ciphertext','started as a bedroom project.then heads came together :) ','','http://www.facebook.com/ciphertextmetal','','','','279708052076166','534',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ciphertext'),(860,0,0,0,'The soHam','Short Bio- Soham Bhattacharya, better known as his stage name the soham, is a young, talented singer-songwriter from Kolkata India. He belongs to a musical family. His musical journey starts from his childhood days. He started learning tabla at the age of six and he started playing on stage for his school function. The singer-songwriter got his first vocal lesson from his mother. Later on,  he learnt vocals  from Brett Mannings singing lesson DVD  and a few music schools. Soon, Soham focussed on acoustic music. Currently, Soham sings country, classic rock, Blues, acoustic rock and pop songs.\n\nSoham appeared in  Kolkatas radio station  called Power Fm (All hits no bakwaz) for an interview and in TV South Asias talk show Caf South Asia which was broadcasted in 5 Asian countries. Soham has also performed in The Park Street Carnival,  House of Kommons, Someplace else open mic, Roland On stage, Afraa lounge and at the Street music Festival. He also got featured at a music chat show called Take a break LIVE in Bengali Channel Tara Muzik . Soham has got the opportunity to perform in  international events like Ray Ban Presents Never Hide Sound Open Mic by Rolling Stone Magazine. Soham was selected for the finals of Channel V Nokia Indiafest 2012 (Acoustica Event). Channel V covered the performance and broadcasted it LIVE .','sohamb112@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/thesohamofficial','','','','175872329092232','530',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-soham'),(861,0,0,0,'Lokesh Bakshi','','lokeshbakshi@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Lokesh-Bakshi/154110511281951','','','','154110511281951','529',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','lokesh-bakshi'),(862,0,0,0,'Warhorse Chained','Warhorse Chained was formed in early 2004, by vocalist Fredrich \'Black\' Vivek and drummer Arun (currently in Kaav) with Saja and Shyam on guitars and Varun on bass. Covering bands like Obituary and Sepultura, they were the first band that marked the beginning of the metal scene in their home city Cochin, Kerala. In 2006, Shyam and Varun left the band being busy with their studies. The band came into a short hiatus, losing the two members and lack of a permenant jam room. \n\nA few months later, the silence was finally over in early 2007, when Vivek and Arun met Divin, a guitarist who was looking for fellow musicians to form a metal band. Divin joined on guitars and soon a friend of the group, Rixon joined on bass and started jamming at the \'old house\' jamroom behind Divin\'s house.\n\nRixon and Arun left after a few months, and the slots were filled soon by Dino, brother of Divin on drums and David on bass. With the new line up, the band decided on sounding more heavier and started working on original sound. A few killer gigs in different cities in Kerala gathered them an underground cult following of their music. Divin left the band in 2008 with a promise of joining back again. Guitarist Bineesh joined on guitar duties.\n\nWarhorse Chained, widely known in short as WHC, is reckoned as the pioneers of extreme metal in Kerala togather with Darkcrucifix. The band has made its mark in the local metal scene and is looking forward for more shows accross the country. They are planning to hit the stuido and release an album in 2011. ','Fredrich Black Vivek','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Warhorse-Chained/126364617429522','','','','126364617429522','528',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','warhorse-chained'),(863,0,0,0,'Jahiliyyah','\n\n\n','loki_jahiliyyah@hotmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Jahiliyyah/243330832377333','','','','243330832377333','527',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','jahiliyyah'),(864,0,0,0,'Sixes and Sevens Mizoram','','9856018788','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Sixes-and-Sevens-Mizoram/169194689783926','','','','169194689783926','527',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sixes-and-sevens-mizoram'),(865,0,0,0,'In Heavens Eyes','In Heavens Eyes is a christian metal band hailing from India that started in 2009. They comprise of Rueban Issac (Lead Vocals), Joshua Shodavaram (Lead Guitars/Backing Vocals), Rohith Girish (Rhythm Guitars), Jacob Thomas (Bass/Backing Vocals) and Hurricane (Drums).\n\nRueban bears the responsibilities of being the bands lead vocalist and lyricist. He employs a varied range of vocal styles spanning from clean to growls. He performs his responsibilities as a front man with greater ease and conviction by presenting the message of his music passionately with power and grace to his audience.\n\nJoshua contributes to the primary riffs of the music comprising of a blend of heavy shredding and clean melodic progressions. His skills as a cutting edge lead guitarist and backing vocalist are a huge asset to the bands music.\n\nRohith contributes in building a tighter rhythm section to the bands music. Rohith\'s style involves a blend of heavy and progressive riffing.\n\nJacob bears the responsibility of not only being the bass player but also the backing vocalist and part lyricist of the band. He incorporates a wide array of styles on the bass which comprises of metal infused with funk/rock.\n\nHurricane is the technical skin basher of the band and is considered to be the back bone to the bands music. His style involves hyperblasting, poly rhythms and speedy up tempo grooves.\n\nIn Heavens Eyes have a variety of musical influences that fall under the alternative and hardcore/metalcore genre. This is evident in the more aggressive, traditional metal instrumental and vocal parts of their music. The band strictly follows on lyrically sharing a positive message that upholds christian values.','','http://www.facebook.com/inheavenseyes','','','','334376411496','527',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','in-heavens-eyes'),(866,0,0,0,'Rooftop Vigilantes','We accidentally became a band, now we tour and record records. oops!','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Rooftop-Vigilantes/238132872369','','','','238132872369','526',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rooftop-vigilantes'),(867,0,0,0,'Blues Conscience','','','http://www.facebook.com/bluesconscience','','','','150016928384991','523',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','blues-conscience'),(868,0,0,0,'Cambyses','Cambyses muted into existence on 11th February 2010. Cambyses is a four piece metal band from Dimapur Nagaland. It was formed when the boys were at the age on 13th.\n\nThey say:-\n\"we are very much young and as we accumulate experiences our tastes evolve us so that we get rid of our influences and become better at crafting our music.. Cambyses is a vessel to enjoy ourselves.\" \n\nOur lyrics are born out of inspiration from coarser realities of life. we evoke our lyrics through scrutiny endeavoring not to be vicious to religious or neither are we aesthetics. \n\n\"Rest in my paradise, Breath me as your Cambyses\"\n\n\n\n\n??????????????????????????? ??????????????????????????? ??????????????????????????? ??????????????????????????? ??????????????????????????? 