07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','jim-ankan-deka'),(870,0,0,0,'The Local People','The Local People started off with only two members, Nihal & Hamza who met through a mutual friend in college. It took a few jams and a cross country road trip for them to realize that they needed to get serious with their music and put together a complete line up. After searching long and hard, the two came across Angad Malli ( Lead Guitar ) who also happened to introduce the band to their bassist, Samrat. \n\nIt took less than one and a half jams for the four to realize that they had chemistry. The idea was to bring different musicians with similar tastes yet unique abilities together and create magic within the jam room, and that\'s exactly what the local people were up to.\n\nAfter digging up some riffs and laying down a couple of demos, the band decided it was time they began recording their 1st single and so the hunt for the vocalist had begun. A few auditions later, it was decided that Nishank was the man for the band. \n\nThe Local People are a very non-mainstream blues influenced rock band with incorporations of psychedelic and funk. In todays word, home studios are easy to set up and it feels so much better when we hear our song and know that it\'s completely \"ours\". And because it\'s.. well, fun. We may not be professional sound engineers or producers but the very rawness of the music is what defines us. \n\n Nihal\'s crunchy riffs thrown into a mix with Samrats funky bass, Malli\'s explosive improvise solos, Hamza\'s raw sound and Nishank\'s \"chill\" vocals give the band a tone that isn\'t too common around the music circuit these days.\n\nThe Local People are always experimenting and adding new elements to their music whenever they jam. It\'s never going to be a \"Heard one, heard em\' all\" scenario. We look forward to bringing back the blues and entertaining the few who appreciate it.','Samrat Chakrabarti - 09958891071','http://www.facebook.com/thelocalpeople','','','','141184342600567','520',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-local-people'),(871,0,0,0,'Now We Collide','Started in the later half of 2011 , Now We Collide is a Metalcore/Electro/Experimental band , started by Aman after he got sick of changing bands and changing line ups and started making tracks by himself on his laptop , after a few of them were finished and the lyrics written , asked his friend Abhijeet to help out for the heavy duty growl/scream vocals and decided that two were enough to create the kind of music that they love .\n\n\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Now-We-Collide/102529713172645','','','','102529713172645','517',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','now-we-collide'),(872,0,0,0,'Pt Divyang Vakil\'s T?lavya','What began as an experiment has bloomed over ten years.   Created with the intention of expanding the audience for classical tabla and sharing the joys of an instrument often sidelined, Pandit Divyang Vakils contemporary classical tabla work has been embraced by audiences around the world.  \n\nFor the last decade, he has been carefully composing group tabla works that carry the nuances and richness of classical tabla, while being accessible to an untrained ear.  Each composition has its own identity; each created with consideration of the artists strengths and personality, each with a different feel, but essence being the same.   \n\nT?lavya\'s current work is Tabla Ecstasy.  Previous works include Power of Tabla, Tabla Taandav and Tabla Tarkhat.\n','','http://www.facebook.com/talavyatabla','','','','165062176868625','516',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','pt-divyang-vakils-tlavya'),(873,0,0,0,'The Doppler Effect','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Doppler-Effect/124688850937325','','','','124688850937325','515',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-doppler-effect'),(874,0,0,0,'Unconventional Science','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Unconventional-Science/122306987858819','','','','122306987858819','513',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','unconventional-science'),(875,0,0,0,'DamagEra(Damage Era)','NER 2011\nUNDERGROUND UNLEASH 2011\nHELLBOUND 2011\nDARJEELING TEA FEST 2011\nMETAL EVOLUTION 2012\nSIKKIM REDFEST 2011-2012','sidbguru@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/DamagEraDamage-Era/179396865461170','','','','179396865461170','513',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','damageradamage-era'),(876,0,1,1,'Gumnaam ( Producer/DJ )','For bookings , remixes and other inquiries contact : riddimandculture@gmail.com\n\nWith a fiercely independent ethos, Gumnaam has been putting out vinyl releases on his own Riddim & Culture Recordings record label  ensuring he stays true to his unique dub/desi sound. \n\n','Riddimandculture@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Gumnaam-ProducerDJ-/171954072819671','','','','171954072819671','510',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','gumnaam-producerdj'),(877,0,0,0,'PaperEdge','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/PaperEdge/82773091646','','','','82773091646','510',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','paperedge'),(878,0,0,0,'Darkest Red','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Darkest-Red/283289527290','','','','283289527290','509',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','darkest-red'),(879,0,0,0,'Battle Beyond the Stars','Philip Kramer (Battle Beyond the Stars) is a Cape Town based DJ and producer, known for his unique blend of Electro, French House and unusual tracks that no DJ in their right mind would play in public. He has performed alongside many well known local and international acts - including FEADZ, The Bloody Beetroots, Steve Aoki, Sweat.X, D.I.M, DJEDJOTRONIC, Le Castlevania, HAEZER, Ikki, Stereoheroes, Saint Pauli and The Cyberpunkers - and is the cofounder of the pioneering club night Get Nasty\'. ','072 600 8023','http://www.facebook.com/battlebeyondthestars','','','','37188147536','508',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','battle-beyond-the-stars'),(880,0,0,0,'Mass Damnation','Mass Damnation formed from the remains of the thrash/groove metal band Sword of the Spirit. SOS was put on hiatus for a while as Tony was finishing up with his studies and when he returned the band had changed, personal issues had formed and the members decided to go their own way. Tony along with drummer Nirodha decided to form the band \'Mass Damnnation\'.\n\nAfter hearing a vocal cover by Ryan Johnson of a Hatebreed track at a local gig, the band sought the potential and talent they saw in him. The band is not complete without Khazim\'s grooves along with his brother Zia, the latest addition to the band handling bass duties. \n\nThe band will hold on to some of their old tracks while the new songs to be released will show a lot of technical work.\n\nLyrical themes include mankind\'s demise, the issues people deal with on a daily basis, the destruction of the environment, political madness and various addictions.\n\nTo sum it all up, Mass Damnation is a cup of fucking rage against the destruction and ignorance mankind has caused upon the Earth.','','http://www.facebook.com/massdamnation','','','','126307914095385','507',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','mass-damnation'),(881,0,0,0,'Claver C Menezes','Claverography\n\n Steps onto the stage for the first time playing popular music in a years time.\n\n Forms his own rock band Rust Angels. Performs with Rust Angels at Live Wire (IIT, Mood Indigo) and enters the finals. Rust Angels attains poularity across Mumbai and neighbouring cities.\n\nIn 5 years, Claver gains recognition in the league of the best guitarists in Mumbai(no youtube or online guitar lesson available :P).\n \nPerforms a tribute to his idol Joe Satriani with an electrifying performance featuring the best Satriani solos at Razzberry Rhinocerous, Mumbai.\n\nLater forms Hangar Records to support rock music and musicians. \n\nFurther Hangar Records releases the guitar instrumental album The Unborn Recital (FOK II) by getting together the top guitarists from the country.\n\nHangar Records releases a non-instrumental rock album featuring the top rock bands of the country.\n\n Disbands Rust Angels to concentrate on Guitar solo instrumentals.\n\n2004  Sets up his own studio to compose music full time for himself and the fraternity.\n\n2005  Scores music for the movie Sacred Evil produced by Percept Picture Company\n\n2008  playing with the rockband Zedde\n\n','claverrocks@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/ClaverCMenezes','','','','187521624645507','503',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','claver-c-menezes'),(882,0,0,0,'Rat King','Formed sometime in 2008 in Velachery, Madras (India). The music of RATKING has spread across the globe (or atleast places with Internet access) like a vehement plague and etched it\'s disease-ridden claws into the minds of thousands of hapless humanoids.\n\nTwo years after their ground-breaking debut album \"The Plague of Hamelin\" and the critically acclaimed sophomore \"Larva\", the duo are busy writings material for a release scheduled for late 2011 on LARVAL TRANSMISSION.','larvaltransmission@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/raatkeeng','','','','86187274843','503',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rat-king'),(883,0,2,2,'Nirmika & The Few Good Men','When you have a song, you gotta sing it. Thats what singer-songwriter Nirmika Singh has been doing for a few years now. And now that there is an amazing bunch of real good men ganging up with her, the songs only get better. Think velvety vocals, think trippy music, think melodies that will surprisingly dance on your lips while you take a shower the morning after the gig, think lyrics that will surprise you with their simple profoundness-thats Nirmika & The Few Good Men for you.\r\n\r\nDont be surprised if the band gets you an adrenaline rush with one song and leaves you in a contemplative space with the next. But be surprised if they dont make you happy, because thats what theyre best at. With heavy strokes of pop-rock, jazz and reggae, their music might make you want to consider forgiving your crazy boss for his eccentricity or even convince you to take your lover for a walk on the beach. They like to look at the sunny side of the street, you see. The fact that lyrics are bilingual-English and Hindi-is not the only selling point of their tracks, but the zealous feel that underlies them definitely is.','91-9619819804','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Nirmika-The-Few-Good-Men/188060711258119','','','','188060711258119','502',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','nirmika-the-few-good-men'),(884,0,0,0,'Tapasya','The band was formed in October, 2009 by a bunch of college guys who wanted to play heavy stuff. The band started off covering great bands such as Metallica and Children Of Bodom and has since moved on to creating their own Music and lyrics in a particular manner that gives the band its sound and its ideology.\n\nWe as a band wish to work hard (Tapasya) to contribute, whatever little we can, to change the society to a better one. \"Hindi Metal\", opposes any kind of orthodoxy. The lyrics, though, are not always essentially Hindi; you might even see English there, which again points to the Anarchist nature.\n\nOur lyrics show an element of concern for the present Indian society, and show social evils present around us today. The band believes in secularism and equality which is reflected by our lyrics. We also write stuff that shows death and despair and how a common man\'s life goes around it.','9654461480,9999962082','http://www.facebook.com/tapasyatheband','','','','169788936419018','502',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','tapasya'),(885,0,0,0,'Conflicting resonance','this band came into being in 2006 with a simple purpose of playing music. \nbasically a school band creating many ripples by winning back to back inter-school competitions, the band finally started creating its own music. \neveryday happenings and mishaps, the cry of the oppressed, the tranquility experienced by the mind when under hallucination, the loved and the lost, the passion of the flesh and the random thoughts of the conscious mind are few of the themes which the band tries to contemplate upon. \nthe sound of the band varies from that of heavy alternate metal to a soft and mellow sound appealing to each one.each song has something new and better to offer!! \nover the years the band has been undergoing a number of line-up changes but as the great ones often said \"THE SHOW MUST GO ON\" we\'ve never let it affect us. \n ....','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Conflicting-resonance/157112494300450','','','','157112494300450','502',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','conflicting-resonance'),(886,0,0,0,'Keba Jeremiah','Be it playing live at a concert or in the controlled environs of a studio, irrespective of the style of music, Keba treats each new song, each familiar note as a brand new experience- his tribute to the art form and his secret to being a musician who is constantly evolving. A musician who strives to make mellifluous music every moment. ','','http://www.facebook.com/kebajeremiah','','','','217388314949463','502',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','keba-jeremiah'),(887,0,0,0,'Eternity','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Eternity/109839435707870','','','','109839435707870','499',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','eternity'),(888,0,0,0,'Nihilanth','The band was formed in mid 2011 when Sankalp and Vivek started jamming with an aim to compose good original music, Inspired by the likes of  \'The Faceless\' \'Obscura\' and \'Psycroptic\' etc.\nAfter a few jams the duo ended up composing their first single \'Dimensional Domination\'. The theme was chosen to bring forth an aura of mystique and add a technical preface to the track.\nA few months later the band was joined by Dheeraj on vocals and Adwait on Bass, The band will be launching an E.P very soon which is being recorded at Closed eye productions, Andheri.\n','','http://www.facebook.com/nihilanth.india','','','','242154355840218','498',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','nihilanth'),(889,0,0,0,'DEAD Mobster','Vavananda,Chingkhei, Kenyo,Romesh, Morly and Ronidy first started plotting their music careers back in the year 2008 influenced by diverse groove ,thrash and Death  Metal bands like Cannibal Corpse,Pantera, Six feet Under,Sepultura etc and also produced originals \" Give me my Strength\",\" \"Corruption\", and self intro -\" Dead Mobster\" And the Band played its first gig at their self organized event called \" Indie Rock Fest\".  By the end of 2008, Romesh and Chingkhei left the band after their second gig, By early 2009, they felt \" tight\" looking for a new guitarist which was answered by Kebi. A gig at Mega Rock Event Bishnupur,as guest band made a Positive vibes and people came to know the existence of the band and Dead Mobster was born.\n \n\nBy mid 2009, Dead Mobster featured in several contest and gigs, and Manipur Rock Idol ( District level )labelled Dead Mobster as the Best Band in Manipur, Dead Mobster started touring out of Manipur , and after the Concert Rock and Raga, Shillong  Kebi is Replaced by Bungi, And with the New Line up ,the Band Participated the next Manipur Idol 2010 and won the 2nd Best Band as well as the Best Vocalist ( District level) . And after the Monsoon 2011,Ronidy left the band and Samson chipped in. With the latest line up - \n\nVocalist - Vavananda,\nGuitarist- Samson,\nGuitarist- Kenyo, \nBass Guitar- Bungbi and \nDrum - Molly performed their gigs at Manipur Rock Fest 2011 and won the 2nd Runner up. The band is currently working on to record their originals and expected to release New tracks by Mid 2012, Dead Mobster is known for Horryfing Growling and Pig Squealing and they are into Death metal, Goregind, Thrash Metal and On the Verge of Producing new sounds, new genre which comes under Metal Genre.\n','+918826247284','http://www.facebook.com/pages/DEAD-Mobster/161384873874260','','','','161384873874260','492',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dead-mobster'),(890,0,0,0,'BROTHERS IN ARMS','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/BROTHERS-IN-ARMS/119213068117691','','','','119213068117691','491',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','brothers-in-arms'),(891,0,0,0,'The Lies Inside','','','http://www.facebook.com/theliesinside','','','','193585657370629','488',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-lies-inside'),(892,0,0,0,'Swastika - The Band','','Varun Singh','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Swastika-The-Band/169425573071911','','','','169425573071911','488',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','swastika-the-band'),(893,0,0,0,'BARZAK','Barzak was formed in the year 2003, sometime around June-July. Upon its birth, the band was named AZAZEL by the members. Although, the first few months of this band were frustrating, they continued jamming some songs by Black Sabbath and Old Sepultura. Barzak, at its preliminary stage faced lineup inefficiency. The band found a palpable lineup in the early 2004 (around January). \n\nInitially, the band tried some experimental single releases, blending 80s heavy metal and thrash/death metal elements. They recorded their 1st demo single in April 2004 titled Judhou Shanti Chaay. The second single was titled as Imaan which is when the band found a new name BARZAKH. The song Malakul-Maut, dedicated to the Angel of Death was the last single the band released in that year. At that time Barzakh was: Naushad (Saad)-Guitars, Amit-Vocals/ Guitars/ Bass, Rana-Drums. For axeman Naushad (Saad) quitting the band became necessary, and he left the country for higher studies. This was a wearisome era for the remaining members. Subsequently, Barzakh went to a long hibernation, almost to a state of non-existence. For about ten months the band had no activities. \n\nThe revivification of the band took place in the middle of the year 2005, when the vocal & guitarist Amit and the battery Rana took initiatives to hire a permanent bassman and reform the band. Thats when Rony joined. At this time (around July) they started working on some new tracks. After two and a half months of continuous rehearsals they released the debut Demo tape titled Opocheshta in September under the new and ultimate name BARZAK which was recorded at BD Sounds, Dhaka during a rehearsal session. This was a self release and was limited to only 17 copies. The demo consisted of four rehearsal and raw versions of songs. \n\nBarzak released their debut Album (full-length) titled Qabiluhu in 12th August 2006, consisting 9 tracks including the unreleased demo tape Narabali. That was recorded in 2005-2006 at Sound Machine Studio and Art of Noise Studio, Dhaka Bangladesh. This album was re-released by Sacramental Records, Brazil on 5th February 2007, limited to 100 copies which were distributed via Nihilistic Music: Distribution and Production, Brazil. \n\nUp until now all the songs are released in their native language Bengali, but, in future the band plans to release every song in English. \n\nAt present, Barzak is a trio and wills to be it as long as the Mighty Hell can bear. Barzak only focuses on preaching hatred through its own compositions as a prelude to the upcoming dissolution of the illusory earth. The dramatic intoxication of the tempter demiurge is forever bestowed upon feeble minded humans. Dancing upon the carcasses of ignorant hyles, Barzak ties itself with the ever devouring forces of death & destruction for the manifestation of impure hatred and spiritual detachments from the hyles. \nTherefore, Barzak hails the esoteric spiritualism of the reverse current and the burning path of self-becoming!! \n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/BARZAK/131693500413','','','','131693500413','487',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','barzak'),(894,0,0,0,'T For Two','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/T-For-Two/122920907763169','','','','122920907763169','486',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','t-for-two'),(895,0,0,0,'Adroit','\'\'ADROIT\'\' - Means \'\'Skilful\'\'...........\\m/...\\m/...\\m/ The Band was formed in 2000 with Dondor-Guitar,Remdor-Vocals,Wallam-Bass n Benny-Drums n the Band started playing covers like-Halloween,Mr.Big,Rainbow,Fire House,White Lion,Deep Purple,Great White,Y N T,Skid Row,Riot,Mass,Roxus,Guns N Roses...etc in n around Hynniewtrep places,on 2004 the Band two members(Benny n Remdor)split then Tony n Eamond-(Who is the vocalist of the popular gospel Band Atiar)came in where Eamond on Vocals n Tony on Drums,n these two also didnt last long,where as on 2005 two members split again n then new members were in again as Mangara on Drums n Hubert on Vocals and after a very2 hard work n practises,The Band has achieved as the Runners up in the beat contest in Sain Kardev College,then became the Winner of The Flames Of Rock Beat Contest n Continue with the Winner of \'\'The Hero Honda Campus Rock Idols\'\' in the Regional Final in shg 2006-07 n after all these success the Band Released a Debut Album \'\'The Adroit\'\' on 2007,n on 2008 Hubert split the Band,then Domanic who is the X- member of some popular Band in Shillong Like Un-fade,Innocent Eyes...etc,Joined the Band n on 2010 the Band also Achieved to be the Winner of the Shillong Lajong(SLFC) Theme Song Compitetion\\Theme Song Composition...n the Band now is still busy working in originals for the Up cumin 2nd Album......n ADROIT Would 