ey guys thank you for joining us here in our page. \nit is a huge joy to feel your involvement in numerous ways in our tiny effort to entertain. we give our special thanks to the ones who had been mega support in many ways because without your constant dose of encouragement we don\'t know how for we could have come and also to all our new visitors it would mean a lot if you could leave a comment too. we really don\'t mind if its a compliment or a curse. guess it all adds up for a good cause in the end.\nafter the band formed in 2008, there had been so many positive response and surprising help from so many unsuspecting corners. and for this we really don\'t wish to be selfish and take all the name to ourselves for whatever we are as a band now. \nwishing for more support for our tiny group here and also for all other such bands here for as we all know that the fight in this very arena isn\'t that easy.\n\n Melodrama Plays Metal but they prefer to call their symphonic Hybrid as Nu-Melodic Metal. \nYear 2008\n\nWe got together in the year 2008 with a primal need to feed their musical desires to play original and unique music. This was in itself a reaction to the already stagnant market of bands playing mostly covers. After days and nights of relentless practice this collective union of guitar-shredding, Bass-thumping and rear- kickin souls hybrided into Melodrama. The band started doing the round of colleges and small shows around the state feeding their well bred symphony of sorts to the music hungry masses who almost immediately devoured each serving with a craving for more. And almost immediately the name Melodrama became synonymous among metal fans across the state. \n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Melodrama/163859560332288','','','','163859560332288','428',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','melodrama'),(935,0,0,0,'Bleed SiX\'','','Vishakha Zimba (Pyro Engineer/Press Contact)','http://www.facebook.com/bleed6','','','','313065385390050','426',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','bleed-six'),(936,0,0,0,'Plecto Aliquem Capite','Pain knows no boundaries nor does it restrict itself, the same can be said about the music made by Sri Lanka`s Plecto Aliquem Capite. A band that evolves and experiments in order to capture the true essence of pain and suffering in thier music. ','','http://www.facebook.com/plectoaliquemcapite','','','','120685148027447','425',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','plecto-aliquem-capite'),(937,0,0,0,'Crucide','Crucide is an Alternative/Contemporary band from New Delhi, IN.\n\nThe main characteristic of their genre is the variation in tempo, rhythm and sometimes the use of musical \"journeys\" that are divided into smaller parts, each with their own dynamics, style and tempo. Also the level of originality needed to create a completely new genre can be noticed. They believe in experimenting, keeping in mind that music comes from the heart, & it should touch the heart.\n','+91-7838905621, +91-8447840493, +91-8826936670','http://www.facebook.com/Crucide','','','','212329975478567','423',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','crucide'),(938,0,0,0,'Vivek Rajagopalan','If world music today is a melting pot of cultures & genres, then Viveks music is a drop of spicy red curry in the concoction. It combines Carnatic, Hindustani, jazz, folk, electronic, and drum n bass and creates sound-scapes that are edgy as much as international. The music combines melody (a hallmark of Indian music) with grooves that youll hear in various corners of the planet. Together it makes a heady mix of energy and melody; something youll find difficult to remove from your head, and stop your feet from tapping to. To sum things up: Viveks music is an impression of todays India: traditional, funky, global, dynamic, and contagiously pulsating.\n\nExclusively Managed by Folktronic - Day 1 (Sony Music Independent)','','http://www.facebook.com/vivekrajagopalanmusic','','','','26684658792','422',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','vivek-rajagopalan'),(939,0,0,0,'The 5th Fret','Started: 2009\nSound:Alternative/Progressive Rock,Folk and Fusions.\nFor Shows:\nCall Piku: 9038628542, 9831143883\nE-mail us: mail.5thfret@gmail.com\nor Log on to: http://5thfret.weebly.com/\nListen Us: https://www.reverbnation.com/5thfret\n','Piku: 9038628542','http://www.facebook.com/5th.Fret','','','','163102837063903','422',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-5th-fret'),(940,0,0,0,'Sunday Mourning','Sunday Mourning is a garage rock band formed in the fall of winter on 28th December, 2008. .After its complete line up, the band has been performing in the local gigs snd pubs in the city.\n\nFeatures: \n\"Get Over It\" Featured in RSJ CD of the month in July 2011 issue. \n\nFeatured in Rolling Stone India - rated 3 out of 5 stars for the single\"Get Over It\" in the August 2010 issue.\n\nFeatured in RSJ magazine in August-September 2010 issue.\n\nFeatured in \"THE ECLECTIC VIBES\" in the March 2010 issue.\n\nFeautured in newspapers like \"THE SENTINEL\" and \"THE EASTERN CHRONICLE\".\n\nFeatured in BIG 92.7 FM in July 2010.\n\nsignificant shows:\n\n#Debut at Sonaram Field on Jan 9, 2009.\n\n#Played in Peace Concert, Shilpgram sharing the stage with Lucid Recess and Digital Suicide.\n\n#Played in pub rock fests held at - Silver Streak, Kingdom and Blues in Guwahati.\n\n#Played in Rocka Rolla Pub Rock Fest.\n\n#Played in Blues pub Guwahati - Rocka Rolla celebrating Mark Knophlers birthday.\n\n#9th Feb 10\' - Record Label Launch With Unicornis Movement Pro Records.\n\n#Played in Fireball 2010 at Shilpgram - opening act for Bhayanak Maut and East India company. \n\n#Played in Kingsberg Pub Rock Fest. \n\n#Played in Classic Rock Night at Guwahati Club - opening act for Girish And The Chronicles.\n\n#Played in Jumping Bean Cafe - Dimapur , Nagaland. \n\n#Played at ROCK-O-PHONIX 2011 at Alcheringa,IIT-Guwahati.\n\n#Played at THE ASSAM VALLEY SCHOOL as guest band.\n\n#Played at Maniram Dewan Trade Centre sharing the stage with Joy Baruah.\n\n#Played at Independence Rock xxvi(East Zone Finals 2011) at Someplace Else,The Park International Hotel,Kolkata.\n\nand at various places....','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Sunday-Mourning/171258502917646','','','','171258502917646','420',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sunday-mourning'),(941,0,0,0,'VICEVERSAH','VICEVERSAH was raised on Gun\'s n Roses, Nirvana, Wu-Tang Clan, Rage Against the Machine, Doc Cheatham, Biggie, and Led Zeppellin among others. His razor sharp delivery and keen ear set him apart from other rappers.\n\nBorn in NYC but raised in the suburbs, rhyming was an unlikely trail for VICE to blaze. He started performing at the age of fifteen at political open mics, spitting scathing verses that caught the attention of anyone within earshot. However, a lack of original production kept him from making headway into a real project. A 2002 EP was circulated through the Boston area and received critical acclaim, but the disc was not actually replicated officially.\n\nIn 2003, after having dropped out of NYU a year earlier, VICE linked up with producer, The Arcitype, and the two immediately began making track after track. At this point, it was clear that an album was in the works, and stirred up by the criticism of skeptics, VICE wryly named the album \"Career Suicide.\"\n\nSince then VICE has been no stranger to the stage. He has performed at some of the Northeast\'s most reputable venues, such as The Middle East Downstairs, Harper\'s Ferry, and The Bowery Poetry Club. VICE even had the opportunity to perform inside the general assembly hall at The United Nations in 2007 for their International Day Of Peace celebrations. VICE has had the opportunity, either in the studio or on stage, to work with some of Hip Hop\'s greatest legends including Kool G Rap, Edo. G, Immortal Technique, Freeway, Styles P, M.O.P. and more.\n\nWith multiple albums under his belt, tracks off his latest LP, \"James And The Giant Beats\" featuring hip hop legends Kool G Rap, Edo. G and Killa Sha burning up radio across the country and internationally, and his recent selection as one of URB Magazine\'s Next 100 Artists, VICE can only foresee himself as a powerful voice for a generation who may rather remain silent.','info@arclassicrecords.com','http://www.facebook.com/viceversahmusic','','','','73601981960','419',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','viceversah'),(942,0,0,0,'Orantem','Orantem is an epic tale of emotions. It will take you on a journey through your own mind and at the end you will be craving for more. A definitive piece in the history of Music.\n\nOrantem is a band extremely passionate about the music it creates. Orantem was originally created when the founding members, Aviral Bajpai (Vocalist,Guitarist) got along with Prachi Gupta (Vocalist) and decided they had to make a band after the success of their duet on Aviral\'s album \"A Step Into The Horizon\". They started making music for the band that suited the requirements for the genre of Gothic Metal. In 2011, Abhishek Sharma joined the band and shouldered the responsibility of being the guitarist and the trio was then ably joined by Karan on the drums and Vibhu who shouldered the bass and percussions.\n\nOn the 14th February 2011, Orantem  released the single \"I\'m With You\" by Republic Digital Distribution. It will be available on all major online music stores including iTunes, Amazon, Napster, emusic, shockhound, thumbplay etc.\n\nTheir music is a portrayal of their deep love for the music they make and has helped them gather a lot of  fans. The numbers grow exponentially everyday.\n\nThey are an ambiance that has to be heard, to be believed...','info@orantem.com','http://www.facebook.com/orantem','','','','107219296011964','418',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','orantem'),(943,0,11,11,'Grey Shack','Grey Shack comprises of a bunch of comics who enjoy inebriation. Sorry, music. The brainchild of Vikram, Rohan and Tomojit, Grey Shack was formed sometime in mid-July 2007, after which they went on to play gigs (read competitions) in and around the wonderfully wonderful city of Chennai. Underground 2007 hosted by The Unwind Centre provided Grey Shack with a launchpad to showcase their music, and the band ended up winning the competition, making their presence felt in the Chennai circuit very early on. More competitions followed, and only recently have Grey Shack started playing gigs. Their music is an eclectic mix of Rock N\' Roll, Grunge, Funk and Blues, thus, the non-conformity to stick to a particular genre. The members draw their influences from numerous acts, which only adds to versatility of Grey Shack\'s music. So sit back, pop a beer (or anything more suited to your well-being) and listen up. \r\n\r\nMembers:\r\nRohan Sen (Vox) - Rohan has been brought up on a diet of Elvis, The Beatles, The Who and other such acts from the glorious 60s and 70s. Ever seen Winnie The Pooh getting it on with a mic stand?\r\n\r\nVikram Vivekanand (Guitars) - An 80s fanatic, he draws inspiration from the testosterone-driven quirky haired guitarists from the age. His influences include John Petrucci, Frank Gambale, Steve Morse and Joe Satriani. Lately, he\'s taken a liking to Bangalore\'s TAAQ as well. Vikram also doubles up as the official band driver. It\'s his car.\r\n\r\nVinay Ramakrishnan (Drums) - Drawing influences from Mike Portnoy, Carter Beauford, Aaron Spears and even having learnt from Benny Greb for a short period, Vinay is one of the hardest rocking drummers that you can find in Madras. He can really lay down a groove! He also doesn\'t have a drum kit. Yep...he sold it, and then he started getting more gigs. \r\n\r\nMadhav Ravindranath (Bass) - Maybe the odd one out, because he likes a lot of metal. But we still love him and he can really rock! And that\'s why he\'s our bassist. This biker, engineer and record label owner was also seen dancing to desi music at a popular club in Madras.\r\n\r\nPrevious Members:\r\n\r\nTomojit Basu (Bass) - Led Zeppelin, The Who, The Beatles, Alice In Chains, Pearl Jam, Foo Fighters, Incubus, Red Hot Chili Peppers and Rage Against The Machine are all acts he thrives off. His nose is worth a million, soon to be seen in a beauty magazine near you!\r\n\r\nDeepak (Drums) - He died. Kidding. Deepak\'s invaluable contribution to Grey Shack\'s sound is recognized by all who know the band. Grey Shack misses the TASMAC man and wishes him all the best for future projects. Whoever said academics help, lied.\r\n\r\nElvin D\'Costa Jones Fernandez John Smith (Drums) - Yes, his name really is that long. A Jazz drummer, Elvin enjoys doses of Steely Dan, Dennis Chambers and so on. Incidentally, Elvin is a male feminist. We wonder why.\r\n','Rohan Sen +919940276048','http://www.facebook.com/greyshack','http://www.soundcloud.com/grey-shack-madras','http://www.soundcloud.com/grey-shack-madras','','0','415',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','grey-shack'),(944,0,63,63,'Lou Majaw and Friends','Lou Majaw (born 1947) is a Khasi guitar strumming singer who is big Fan of Bob Dylan from Shillong in the North-Eastern India\r\n\r\nBorn to a poor family, the Majaws could not afford a guitar or a radio. In a friends house he was introduced to the music of Bill Haley and Elvis Presley, and taught himself the guitar as most boys and girls did in those days.His mother sent him to a boarding school where his love for music grew. Majaw then moved on to Kolkata (Calcutta) where he sang in bars and pubs for various groups such as the Dynamite Boys, Vanguards, Supersound Factory, and Blood and Thunder. In 1966, Lou was introduced to Bob Dylans work. Inspired by his music, he later organized a Dylans birthday concert in Shillong on 24 May 1972. Since then he has organized the concert each year on 24 May to pay obeissance to Dylan, with the shows generating national and international interest.On May 24th,2011, Lou Majaw celebrated the 70th birthday of Bob Dylan with a grand concert with one band each from 8 states of North East India. The bands were- Hip Pocket (Indian band)(Kolkata), Alive (Sikkim), Dluzion (Assam), Swraijak (Tripura), Evenflow(Mizoram), Cleave(Manipur), Incipit(Nagaland), Symmetry Clan(Arunachal Pradesh) and Midnight Garden Factor(Meghalaya).','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Lou-Majaw-and-Friends/146774868696508','','','','146774868696508','415',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','lou-majaw-and-friends'),(945,0,0,0,'IF HOPE DIES.','Formed in mid 2010.... we play metal !!!  rest you guys can name!!! \'\' MOTIVE ... KEEP HOPING, KEEP IMPLEMENTING,\nKEEP COMPOSING & KEEP RAWKING \'\'\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/IF-HOPE-DIES/124328317633904','','','','124328317633904','414',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','if-hope-dies'),(946,0,0,0,'The Hoffman Code','will be published very soon!','thehoffmancode@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Hoffman-Code/277594222296901','','','','277594222296901','412',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-hoffman-code'),(947,0,11,11,'Before The Holocaust','We are a six piece band from Chennai. We have attitude problems and we kill jews. We create words that don\'t exist. We love KFC. We also play metalcore. Mostly.\r\n\r\nMembers\r\n\r\nAbhishek Thomas - Vocals\r\n(https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100001616417133)\r\n\r\nBhargav Choudhury - Guitars\r\n(https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100001753070705)\r\n\r\nJahnavi Bhat - Guitars/Backing Vocals\r\n(https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100000105091744&ref=ts)\r\n\r\nDennis Peter - Keys/Synth\r\n(https://www.facebook.com/dennispeter?ref=ts)\r\n\r\nFahim Farzad - Bass\r\n(https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=623344532)\r\n\r\nAshwin Jacob - Drums\r\n(https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=1067744111) ','8015799323,9500044798','http://www.facebook.com/bthchennai/info','','','','0','412',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','before-the-holocaust'),(948,0,0,0,'Aughad','Crusades, Jihad, holy religious wars, or just a war raged to satisfy ones whimsical selfish demands. The concept of religion misunderstood by many and kept limited to baseless rituals, and religious hierarchy dividing the society.\nAughad as a band speaks about such blasphemies of religion, we don\'t aim to bring about a social change with our musics lyrical theme. We aim at silent criticism of the institution of religion.\n\nAt the end of the day what counts is faith in yourself, \n\"When your facing a gun it doesn\'t matter by what name you call out your lord, if you don\'t have the balls, you might as well sing \'Highway to hell\'\" ','','http://www.facebook.com/pseudocorvus','','','','185689801516501','412',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','aughad'),(949,0,29,29,'Tritha','Kolkata-born Tritha Sinha juggles three musical outfits  the solo/ acoustic TRITHA, her ethnopunk band Tritha Electric, and her Hindustani trip-hop band SPACE. She shuttles between Delhi, Kolkata and Paris, experimenting with different kinds of music.','trithasinha@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/trithamusic/info','','','','0','411',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','tritha'),(950,0,0,0,'Swara Sutra','Swara Sutra is the solo project of Sriram Ved, an Indian musician/ music enthusiast/ creative writer. The band is very experimental and draws influences from various forms of music ranging from Carnatic Classical, jazz and alternative, all the way to extreme metal.\n\nSwara Sutra is known for seamlessly blending in Carnatic style music into it\'s tracks and transitions that leave the listener guessing as the song progresses.\n\nSriram loves to collaborate and the tracks often feature other artists.\n\nIt all started on a hot summer afternoon in May 2009 during an agonizing power cut by playing guitar chords on a Veena which soon turned into a 3 minute untitled song that was put up on SoundClick the following evening. It received a great response and comments asking for some more music and that was when Swara Sutra was born online. It has come a long way since then, quickly making a good connection with musicians and music lovers online.\n\nBelieving in the freedom of painting it\'s music on an empty canvas, the band has created a very unique and original sound which rapidly moved the band up in the rankings on many popular platforms like SoundClick, ReverbNation and Myspace. The band was featured in the SoundClick Top 10 Charts after the release of it\'s track - Aura Esoteric. Arabian Sunset, another popular track debuted at #7 on SoundClick World Charts and climbed upto #4.\n\nCheers to original music!','','http://www.facebook.com/swarasutra','','','','138125708449','407',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','swara-sutra'),(951,0,2,2,'Slow Down Clown','It began as a solo project, formed by singer/songwriter Vitek Tek Goyel in Upstate New York in 2001. \r\nUpon his return to Mumbai, Tek teamed up with producer/guitarist Anurag Shanker, to translate his bedroom enterprise into a full band experience together with bassist Wilson Kenneth and drummer Arfaaz Fuzz Kagalwala.\r\nAnd thus the evolution of Slow Down Clown, a four-piece Mumbai outfit whose sound oscillates between folk, alternative and punk.\r\nTheir songs are characteristic of Bombay, brimming with anecdotes, steeped in nostalgia and entirely relatable. Distinct, melodic vocals painted over a memorable musical backdrop. Frenetic and ecstatic, lovelorn yet optimistic, Slow Down Clown are an easy, addictive listen.\r\nTheir debut EP, Say Nothing was released on Meteorik Records in September 2010. The band played to packed venues at their launch parties across three cities, completely selling out their first print of 500 copies. Since then, they have toured Mumbai, Pune and Bangalore, and performed at the Bandstand Revival gigs at Hanging Gardens, the Blue Frog, and more recently at the Celebrate Bandra Festival in Mumbai.\r\nThe band are currently back in the studio recording their follow up to Say Nothing.\r\n','Vitek Goyel','http://www.facebook.com/slowdownclown','http://www.myspace.com/slowdownclown','','','127064487350373','407',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','slow-down-clown'),(952,0,0,0,'Plan Aftermath','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Plan-Aftermath/292698547429970','','','','292698547429970','407',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','plan-aftermath'),(953,0,0,0,'Ayush Shrestha','Ayush Shrestha has been regularly captivating audiences as a singer songwriter in India and Nepal for more than a year now. His music demonstrates a range of shades and temperaments.  The sound boils down to acoustic simplicity, which draws influences from an eclectic range of genres from blues, rock, pop, folk, to classic ballads.\n\nHis song writing has been evolving for over 12 years now and is often peppered with a clever play of words. The content is inspired by his own conscious and sub-conscious exposure to day to day stimuli.  He had started writing in Nepali, his mother tongue, and then moved to writing more in English after moving to Mumbai to pursue music seriously. \n\nAyush expresses all this in a passionate yet smoothly controlled vocal rendition, sometimes surprising the audience by little funny things he does with his voice.  He takes liberty of having minimalistic music to freely alter the tempo and temperament of his music during live performances. \n\nAyush had a few minutes to introduce himself as a singer songwriter to the huge new crowd at NH7, Nov 19,  which is the biggest indie music festival in India. 2 songs  and that was it!  He got an overwhelmingly positive response from the audience and the crew alike  both for the music and for his traditional Nepali dress!','','http://www.facebook.com/ayushmusic','','','','222483724488477','406',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ayush-shrestha'),(954,0,0,0,'Lyrics Indy','','','http://www.facebook.com/LyricsIndy','','','','231544686881377','406',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','lyrics-indy'),(955,0,0,0,'42 Street Station','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/42-Street-Station/251449494904182','','','','251449494904182','404',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','42-street-station'),(956,0,0,0,'Plan B (Bangalore)','Plan B was formed in 2006 by Aditya, Yasaswi, Siddhant, and Abhishek. we were all classmates together in school. We performed for numerous school and college fests for the first couple years. But the band has been playing under the name Plan B only since august 2009. During this time, Nakul was inducted into the band as the bassist. Plan B recorded our first album, To hell with Plan A on 13th august 2009 which consists of 7 original compositions and 2 music videos. Since then, the band has played for numerous shows- Purple haze pub, Bangalore central mall Saturday jam, Shoppers stop mall, college fests, Kyra and Opus restaurants, etc. and been featured in an interview on RadioIndigo 91.9 fm Bangalore. We were ranked number 11 for Rock in Bangalore according to www.reverbnation.com during august and september of 2010. \nWe also feature various artists for several songs and shows- Maduri, Kanchita, Anjan, Anubhav, Yashwant, Keerthan and Chirag are a few of them. We later recorded a new album which included 2 new original compositions. \nOur music is diverse, we play many genres such as rock, alternative, blues rock, soft rock, acoustic, and a little bit of heavy metal. Our influences include Iron Maiden, Metallica, LOG, BLS, The Doors, GnR, AC/DC, Opeth, Pink Floyd, The Beatles, Junkyard groove, The Bicycle days, Motherjane, Advaitha etc. \nPlan B will continue to do what we love to do, making music from our souls. \nAll songs written and composed by Plan B. We encourage you to share our music as long as the credit is given to the band. \nFor more information please contact: \nAditya- 9844463078 \nSiddhant- 9886812773 \nAbhishek- 9886709618 \nNakul- 9986108455\nVisit our webpages \nwww.reverbnation.com/planbbangalore similarly on myspace or connect with us on Facebook.','','http://www.facebook.com/planbbangalore','','','','144289218938726','401',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','plan-b-bangalore'),(957,0,0,0,'The BottleFlower Seeds','','bottleflowerseeds@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-BottleFlower-Seeds/140368942642318','','','','140368942642318','401',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-bottleflower-seeds'),(958,0,0,0,'Zuriel','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Zuriel/153908541329307','','','','153908541329307','400',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','zuriel'),(959,0,0,0,'Ambar Das Music','i started out in my musical journey at a very early age, and have been travellin on ever since... i come from the northeast part of india where the very air breaths music... i want to reach out to the world with my music that comes from the rich, vibrant and soulful melodies of my native place with influnces from the music i have grown up with...','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Ambar-Das-Music/229959747055338','','','','229959747055338','397',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ambar-das-music'),(960,0,0,0,'San fan page','San\nBorn on 5th of Feb\nOrigin Indian.\n\nOccupation(s) Composer, Mixing Engineer, Mastering Engineer , Record Producer, Music Director, programmer, Sound Designer , Singer , Songwriter , technical adviser.                \n\n  With his second International album, San adopts the role of transporter. He attempts to teleport the listener to a destination clear of turbulent weather. Sans brand of Peace music has been crafted by exploiting his expert technical capabilities as an accomplished sound designer. Working with the best musicians in the industry, he has been able to engender a sound that is distinct, with diminutive vocals interspersing the already strapping compositions. San has ingeniously incorporated the efforts of over 52 artists and 80 instruments to spawn a sound that people worldwide can embrace effortlessly. Each instrument resonates with distinct passion that explodes onto the horizon of his musical vision. Complex software shapes traditional Indian and Western instruments to echo the message of peace and spirituality. His music encapsulates not only myriad cultures but also the collective contemporary mindset of the 21st century. Mystic, sinister rhythms combine with meticulously designed vocals and are caressed with an electronic touch to generate the perfect disposition for self discovery. His spirituality laps the shore of our own sense of self-discovery to create a very personal bond with the listener. The dynamic rhythms vary from song to song creating an array of tempos that instigate various moods, emotions and sensibilities. Join San as he reconnects with nature en route the journey for inner peace. ','+91 9820441454 ( Mumbai )','http://www.facebook.com/sanfanpage','','','','496002705310','397',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','san-fan-page'),(961,0,0,0,'Bliss Logic','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Bliss-Logic/277503135441','','','','277503135441','395',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','bliss-logic'),(962,0,0,0,'The Open Door Project','Created in 2009 as a recording outfit, The Open Door Project is an exploration of sound. Incorporating live elements with samples and loops, the purpose remains to be as creative and open as possible in creating coherent concept driven pieces. \nAlthough drenched in self-indulgence, the intention is to let the songs write themselves. To remain a medium for the music to take shape than to dictate it. To be involved in the purity of the creative zone and let things unfold as they have to, often incorporating influences from other arts such as literature or photography. The result is soundscapes defined by moods and vice versa. The song-writing uses imagery as a strong base to create lyrical pieces in sync with the concept defining the music. \nFusing elements from psychedelia, rock, trip-hop and electronica, the band tries to create textured and layered music to build upon the lyrical imagery. There is a conscious struggle within the band to break across the comfort zones of genre specificity to create a fluid soundscape that has a voice and a story to tell. The songs find home in languid movements through corridors of the mind.\nSit back. Relax. Let us in.\n\n','','http://www.facebook.com/theopendoorproject','','','','125201564196798','394',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-open-door-project'),(963,0,0,0,'Pranav Pahwa','Pranav Pahwa is a Delhi based Jazz Fusion guitar player. He is currently studying\nwith Berklee online and is a part of the band Jester. He is also a sessions artist\nand solo artist. During his college days he was part of the Kirori Mal college\nmusic society (Musoc) and later was made president in his third year. Musoc had\na considerable impact on his playing as he had to play everything from Indian\nFusion, classical, Jazz, Funk and even some Bollywood music. During his school\ndays he played for Other Life Experiences, a prog rock band, which is now\ndisbanded. Along with playing for many bands like Five 8 and Groove Adda, he\nwas also an instructor at Music Basti. He attended the Berklee Five week summer\nperformance programme this year, where he got placed in the all star world\nmusic ensemble and played at the BPC.\nYou can check out his music at.\nJester- www.myspace.com/jesterdelhi\nhttp://www.facebook.com/pages/Jester/127030677340642\nMusoc- www.myspace.com/kmcmusoc\nOther life experiences- www.myspace.com/otherlifeexperiences\nYoutube- http://www.youtube.com/user/pranavpahwa\nhttp://www.youtube.com/user/pranav2570\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pranav.pahwa.guitar','','','','142323912504739','394',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','pranav-pahwa'),(964,0,0,0,'Swimming Elephants','Too poor to go out, too lazy to face the traffic jams, we\'re too bored with the city, and so we play.','','http://www.facebook.com/swimmingelephantsband','','','','111309775570310','390',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','swimming-elephants'),(965,0,0,0,'Cursed Arrows','Reviews of 2011\'s SKIN BEHIND THE SHROUD:\n\n\"The six song EP finds Cursed Arrows mining some familiar (but still very potent) ground: their buzzsaw guitar-and-drum attacks still fuse together perfectly with bittersweet hooks and harmonies. Thats not to say theyre treading water though  they find time to bust out the drum machine on One In The Blue and some spoken word on Close To The Exit.\n~Two Way Monologues (Canada)\n\nReviews of 2011\'s THE MADNESS OF CROWDS:\n\n\"I was reminded as the sound filled our ears like a sandstorm how much this reminded me of PJ Harvey (the band has, fittingly, covered Rid of Me), or Patti Smith, or maybe even more appropriately the Israeli co-ed duo Carusella as although the woman in front of us sang more lead (as she played drums!), the man sang as well. They harmonized well when needed as on the strangely beautiful Strip Joint Roundabout, an oasis, to stretch the metaphor, of jangly pop in the midst of the blooze-rock bluster. But here they were like angels, these Cursed Arrows, here to show us the way.\"\n~Critical Masses (US)\n\nReviews of 2009\'s TELEPATHIC HIGH FIVE:\n\n\"Over 10 songs, the husband/wife duo run through a score of early 90s reference points  a hint of Pixies, a dash of Melvins, a heavy dollop of Nirvana  but sound surprisingly fresh in the process.  Alternating between beautifully sinister power chords and nuanced rhythm patterns, the album squeezes ample variety from just two instruments. The title track, for instance, crams more riffs into four and a half minutes than can be reasonably counted.\"\n~NOW Magazine(Canada)\n\n\"A name tweak and a shot of adrenaline are welcome in the second offering from one of Canada\'s best fresh rock bands...Sludgy slabs of dissonant, augmented power chords lead a blazing charge of pummelling drum work and vocal harmonies threatening to tear with passion with each climax.\"\n~Exclaim! (Canada)\n\n\"If you dont agree, then I will fight you. Its that good. There are two of them. A lad and a lass, and they are an utterly joyous duo of fuzzy post-grunge indie-rock babbling. The drums are woolly and boomy, and the guitar is earthy. They both sing, and when they sing together, hearts will melt.\"\n~Collective Zine (UK)\n\n\"Run Forever manages to encompass the stoned-groove of Z-era My Morning Jacket with the legitimate fury of the White Stripes, while still adding a remarkably adept coat of Canadian paint on. \"\n~PopMatters (US)\n\n\"Imagine a marvelous song structure combination between Nirvana and The Melvins, the stoney trips of The Flaming Lips, the heaviness of Black Sabbath, the voice of legendary Wendy O. Williams mutated with the L7 lead singer Donita Sparks, powerful, groovy drumming & scratchy, phenomenal, well executed guitar riffs that will get stuck in your mind & you get Cursed Arrows.\"\n~Heavy Stoned and Doomed (Puerto Rico)\n\n\"Run Forever comes out swinging like an underdog heavyweight fighter, knowing there is only one chance to grab the spotlight and like Little Mac they shock us all and connect square on the jaw. \"\n~Herohill (Canada)\n\n\"If you were into Dennis Thompson of the MC5, you\'re going to fall head-over-heels in love with Jackie Stanley because she schools his ass. It\'s like that old school Detroit rock where everybody got jazz, blues, and R&B tutelage and then went and joined garage bands (thus fostering the punk and metal yet to come). This woman is drumming all the drum parts that we all wished Dave Grohl had been doing for the past decade, plain and fucking simple.\" (US)\n~Sound Design and Assembly\n\n\"(Telepathic High Five) carries forward their sound, which condenses nearly every important 90s alt-rock touchstone into sharp blasts of post-grunge fury.\"\n~The Record (Canada)\n\nReviews of 2007\'s Knives Are Falling From The Sky:\n\n\"Constant harmonies keep the songs sounding full and the raw, self-recorded production seems suitable for this adept opening volley from these indie rock revolutionaries.\" ~Exclaim! (Canada)\n\n\"Their gorgeous boy-girl harmonies and traded verses aside, its a sound that effectively marries Lightning Dust with The Melvins. But its the nuanced power chords, obscure lyrics and crashing, existential excitement of opener Here in Time, as well as the title track, that certify Arrows valiant attempt at a post-grunge masterpiece.\" ~Eye Weekly (Canada)','info@cursedarrows.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Cursed-Arrows/14740519851','','','','14740519851','390',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','cursed-arrows'),(966,0,0,0,'Reverrse Polarity','Reverrse Polarity is a five piece metal band from Mumbai, India. The band was formed in April 08 but took off mid-September 08. Since then Reverrse Polarity has paved its way in the metal scene gaining recognition and popularity that other bands can only hope to achieve in such a short span of time.\n\nIn June 2011 Reverrse Polarity tragically lost their drummer Jonathan Joshua Fernandes and now Gautam Deb has joined the band as the new drummer.\n\nThe Band derives its musical compositions from straws of different inspirations. Say hello to the madness!','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Reverrse-Polarity/232977073439797','','','','232977073439797','386',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','reverrse-polarity'),(967,0,0,0,'Ministry Of Blues','Ministry of Blues (MoB) is a Blues-Rock band. We play a genre of music that originated in the 1900s, but combine it with a distinctly 21st-century flair. Our intention is to:\n\n    * Create a musical experience that blends music with deep emotional roots with the sounds and skills that typify modern Rock\n\n    * Play this music in a manner that is enjoyable to both the discerning Blues aficionado as well as the lover of todays Rock music\n\n    * Reintroduce the listener to the sheer excitement of intense and high-energy live \nmusic\n\n\nThe MoB line-up includes Philipe (vocals & lead guitars), Vinoo (bass), Rauf (vocals & keyboard) and Deepak (drums).\n\nAlthough Philipe, Deepak and Vinoo have been playing together since 1993, MoB as a concept and a band, was formed in 2005. Sarat Sidhan was the original Bass player for MoB. He moved out of Bangalore & MoB for professional reasons a year later.\n\nThe first difficult task was coming up with a name that suitably described the blues-rock music played by the band. After experimenting with a series of names the band finally settled on Ministry of Blues coined by Deepak or DK for short, which somehow seemed to sum up the overall feel of the band.\n\nMOB performed their first gig Bangalore to all of ten people...but then The Police have actually played a gig where only three people showed up!\nThe subsequent performances showed a rapid recovery with turnouts ranging from crowded to over flowing to Are you nuts?...theres too many people in here...cant get to the wash room!\n\nThe success of MoBs performances, marked by raw energy, quickly generated great interest in the band .\nMOB\'s repertoire is a mix of classics like Stevie Ray Vaughn, Jimi Hendrix, Robben Ford, John Mayall, Joe Cocker, Deep Purple, Gary Moore and Eric Clapton among others. The band is known for their unique rock renditions of these classic tracks, making their music appealing to lovers of rock, rhythm and blues.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Ministry-Of-Blues/109651810841','','','','109651810841','387',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ministry-of-blues'),(968,0,0,0,'Reverrse Polarity','Reverrse Polarity is a five piece metal band from Mumbai, India. The band was formed in April 08 but took off mid-September 08. Since then Reverrse Polarity has paved its way in the metal scene gaining recognition and popularity that other bands can only hope to achieve in such a short span of time.\n\nIn June 2011 Reverrse Polarity tragically lost their drummer Jonathan Joshua Fernandes and now Gautam Deb has joined the band as the new drummer.\n\nThe Band derives its musical compositions from straws of different inspirations. Say hello to the madness!','Vivek Gupta - +91 9920346510','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Reverrse-Polarity/232977073439797','','','','232977073439797','386',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','reverrse-polarity-1'),(969,0,0,0,'Fidel Mehra Music','Fidel started experimenting with electronic sounds and instruments in the year 2007. Slowly he developed the liking for creating music which touches all genres and is not limited by any restricted identity.He has experimented with various musical instruments ranging from Gopichand to kalimba, koto and oboes. Not only that, the artist has a passion for rock and metal music and some of the songs draw heavily from these genres.','','http://www.facebook.com/fidelmusic','','','','361241818546','386',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','fidel-mehra-music'),(970,0,0,0,'Dead Calm Chaos','Started as a jamming band in early 2009. The band was looking to take metal music to a different direction and create a sound unique to the band, while following the Do It Yourself principle. This led to a lot of experimentation with other genres and sub-genres of metal music and infusing it with melodic death metal.\nTook a hiatus in mid 2009 and 2010, and became active again in mid 2011, with a few lineup changes. Currently, the band has Baribor on vocals, Malcolm and Kyrshan on guitars, Iaidon Jyrwa on the bass guitar and Biang aka. Malice on the drums.\nDead Calm Chaos played it\'s first ever show on the 4th of June 2011 in Elephant\'s Falls, Upper Shillong followed by the Cloud Confluence Concert, World Music Day in Shillong on the 21st of June 2011.\nThe band is currently recording newer material which will be released in the near future. All recordings are self recorded, self mixed, self mastered and self produced by the band.','Baribor K. Khongwir - +919863213714','http://www.facebook.com/DeadCalmChaosShillong','','','','209621212170','384',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dead-calm-chaos'),(971,0,0,0,'UnMute Agency','UnMute was brought into being with a very specific agenda: to generate a superior experience for the artist, both on and off stage. With a focus on DJs and live acts producing and playing cutting-edge techno and house, we aim to devise the most innovative shows possible, both in terms of music quality and the total experience. \n \nThe agency will manage and book a select cache of quality Indian artists as well as serve as a countrywide (India) agency for international artists. UnMute is led by Dev Bhatia, manager of Jalebee Cartel and media professional, and Arjun Vagale, one of India\'s biggest electronic music exports in his own right and as part of his live act, Jalebee Cartel.\n\nWe believe that our pool of artists are the future of Indias underground sounds. And ultimately, thats what UnMute is all about: bringing their potential straight to the stage. \n\n:: UnMute is an invite only agency, our domestic (India) roster for 2012 is now closed!','','http://www.facebook.com/UnmuteAgency','','','','195970147081505','384',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','unmute-agency'),(972,0,0,0,'Whitenoiz','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Whitenoiz/51590174358','','','','51590174358','384',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','whitenoiz'),(973,0,0,0,'Buffer Zone','Allan: The newest and the youngest member of the team.. fresh our of collage with fresh ideas.. plays bass and lead, sings with \"feelings\" and loves to write.. music runs in his soul the same way it runs into everyone else...\n\nDJ: A passionate loyalty applications expert who doesn\'t mind working right from 5am or even weekends... Most enthusiastic member who is always ready to go extra miles.. he gives flexibility to experiment with vocal grooves and make the vocals more fuller..\n\nDilip: Drummer the \"Great\"... The most seasoned member of the band.. fresh out of college with a fresh perspective and open mind.. Always \"cool\" & \"OK\" with everything... He has been playing in Bangalore from past few years, being associated with other bands as well and have performed at various places including Kyra & Palace grounds..\n\nGnanraj: Our Rythm Guitarist.. again a loyalty expert giving production support.. working in shifts, one can really learn \"Work-life balance\" from him.. Always ready to learn and the first one to arrive for any jamming session.. Speaks very less and yes.. he is indeed a \"tall\" figure among us..\n\nNishant: The Management grad. in Finance is looking after the marketing & PR of the Band. He brings with him not just a powerful & energetic voice but also the maneuverability with his ability to play guitar & keyboard as well.. A writer, composer and so called \"Philosopher\" who says \"Buffer Zone\" is his baby as well as his dream, and wants both of them to grow BIG... A small town guy whose dream is to bring his city on the Rock Map of India.\n\nTirthankar: The senior-most person and undoubtedly the backbone of the band.. with more than 8 yrs of playing experience, brings with him the rich musical heritage of Kolkata.. An expert in managing Networks & Servers by profession has equal dexterity on his guitar... The thinker, the analyst & the visionary.. His suggestions are very instrumental as is his understanding of music..','bufferzone@bufferzone.in','http://www.facebook.com/BufferZoneTheBand','','','','186622574695731','383',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','buffer-zone'),(974,0,0,0,'Frederik Teige','Previous releases:\n\"Autumn Totem\" ( EP, November 2010 ) \nhttp://frederikteigemusic.bandcamp.com/album/autumn-totem-ep\n\n\"Elevate\" ( single+Remix, November 2010 )\nhttp://frederikteigemusic.bandcamp.com/album/frederik-teige-elevate-single-remix\n\n\"Body God\" ( Album, January 2011 ) \nhttp://frederikteigemusic.bandcamp.com/album/body-god\n\nFor more information, contact, questions, answers or whatever.. send an email to: frederikteige@gmail.com','atmpromo@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/frederikteigeofficial','','','','116100401764350','383',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','frederik-teige'),(975,0,0,0,'The Travelling Blues',' The TravellingB was formed on nov 2007, It was the coming together of Two people for whom music was more about subtleness and sophistication....\nFrom the starting of our music listening days our major influence were the blues and country genre, BB king, JJ cale,eric clapton,Norah jones, Willie nelson, Eva cassidy are some of our inspirations their music is like a time capsule to us... Back to the days when music was more about the person playing it and his feel for music.....\n\nOne of the only Indian band who is sound with onstage looping ,\nThe rhythm, bass,the guitar riff is all done by the guitarist on the loop station,\nThe percussion is also  covered on the guitar. Even though it is a two piece band our music is never dull the looping creates a fuller effects  of the beautiful music created by the guitarist and the vocals take care of the rest.\n\nArtist bio:\n\nGuitars: Harshit Sharma.....\n\nHas been playing professionally for 10 years now\nHas performed with visiting artists from France and with renowned musicians like Bobby Cash, before starting  The Travelling Blues he was also part of different bands such as The Time Machine and Organised confusion.\n\nHis influences are:\nBB King\nJJ cale\nEric Clapton\nStevie raywaughn\nJoe Pass\nThe Who\n\nVocals: Poorva Gairola\n\nA classicaly trained vocalist who has been singing for a lil more than 15 years now ;)..Has been part of The Travelling Blues since it was formed before travelling blues was also part of the organised confusion and have performed with many other artists, have performed at many shows and festivals , Individually have also won many shows including IIT Roorkee 3 years in a row.\n\nHER influence as a vocalist:\nEva Cassidy\nMiranda Lambert\nDixie Chicks\nNorah Jones\nPricilla ahn\nAmy Winehouse\nBeatles\n\n','07579068404','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Travelling-Blues/262082820501622','','','','262082820501622','383',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-travelling-blues'),(976,0,0,0,'Battalions','Battalions is a 5 piece melodic progressive metal band from Chennai, India formed in 2006 comprising of Godwin (Vocals), Joshua (Guitars), Jacob (Bass), Julius (Keyboards) and Vishal (Drums).\n\nGodwin Duraisingh employs a varied range of vocal styles spanning from clean to deep growls. He performs his responsibilities as a frontman with greater ease and conviction by presenting the message of his music passionately with power and grace to his audience Godwin is heavily influenced by bands such as Petra, Iron Maiden, As I Lay Dying, Scar Symmetry, Dream Theater,etc.\n\nJoshua Shodavaram is one of the architect\'s of the band\'s music. He contributes to the primary riffs of the music comprising of a blend of heavy shredding and clean melodic progressions. His skills as a cutting edge lead guitarist are a huge asset to the bands music. Joshua is heavily influenced by bands such as Petra, Iron Maiden, Dream Theater, Stryper, Balance of Power, As I Lay Dying,etc.\n\nJacob Thomas is the other architect of the band\'s music. He bears the responsibilities of not only being the bass player but also the lyricist of the band. He incorporates a wide array of styles on the bass which comprises of metal infused with funk/rock. Jacob is heavily influenced by bands such as Creed, 12 Stones, Killswitch Engage, Staind, All that Remains,etc.\n\nJulius Roland contributes to the melody and harmony of the band\'s music. His playing is classically stylized involving an infusion of eclectic and ambient vibes. He is heavily influenced by Dream Theater, Yanni and Western classical/jazz music.\n\nBattalions music is based on a first person\'s perspective that revolves around a constant theme based on Christian values.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Battalions/130859627112','','','','130859627112','382',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','battalions'),(977,0,0,0,'Purvaja','','Rahul Das','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Purvaja/145492128867975','','','','145492128867975','381',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','purvaja'),(978,0,0,0,'Kali Briis','Discography:\n\n\"Magnetofon\"                              (Compilation)      2007          CD\n\n\"Taipohhography\"                        (EP)                   2008          Digital\n\n\"Breakfast EP\" (with Hommik)       (EP)                   2009           Vinyl/Free Digital\n\n\"Das Bing EP\"                              (EP)                   2010           Digital\n\n\"Kila Kola\"                                   (Compila.)          2010           CD\n\n\"Ilge Ulme EP\"                             (EP)                   2010           Free Digital\n\n\"5151\"           