/www.facebook.com/pages/Devolution/194021944002605','','','','194021944002605','374',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','devolution'),(981,0,0,0,'Drift!! The Trio','Drift is a Bebop and Contemporary Jazz trio  based out of New Delhi  with over three hundred gigs and counting. \r\nThe band plays an eclectic mix and fusion of classical Jazz  inspired by and including artists such as John Coltrane, Miles Davis, Dave Brubeck - mixed with modern sensibilities such as the likes of Joshua Redman and Chris Potter.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe band is led by Drummer  Reuben Narain  who is an alumni of the Berklee School of Music, Boston; On guitars  there is Pranai Gurung  director and founder of the Delhi based  Blue Notes Academy. Sahil Warsi on Double bass  who is one of the youngest Double Bassists in the city.\r\n\r\n\r\nEach member of the band  is independently established within the circuit  and has spent time abroad and domestically collaborating with other musicians. \r\n\r\n\r\nDrift has played extensively in and out of the city  and has been the preferred band  for events and residencies by brands and companies including (but not exclusively): Absolut; Aman Resorts; Baci  Caf and Bar; Chivas; Penguin; Seagrams/Nine Hills; Indigo; Hard Rock Caf; Lodi  The Garden Restaurant  to name just a few. The band has also toured Nepal in 2010.','','http://www.facebook.com/DriftJazzDelhi','http://www.myspace.com/driftthetrio','','','337768315747','374',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','drift-the-trio'),(982,0,0,0,'Unsure Uncertain','Unsure/Uncertain,formed in May 2007, when Mitesh Mudras (Drums) showed an oceanic level of dedication by travelling all the way from Powai to Lower Parel for a jam. The band sponsored by sheer pocket-money were impelled to cope with compromised instruments, such as a borrowed acoustic guitar, second-hand bass guitar, a puny little Stranger amp and a drum-set comprising of a Hi-hat stand, a stool for a snare, a wooden chair and loads of boxes. After playing a dozen of engineering college competitions, failing miserably in getting noticed, composing a couple of Punk songs, covering almost very little, not getting eliminated being similar to a Grammy Award, changing 5 jam-rooms with the entire drum-kit, the genre being transformed to Alternative/Progressive, and punching and kicking through a huge calamity-list, here is Unsure/Uncertain\n\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Unsure-Uncertain/179539645424326','','','','179539645424326','373',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','unsure-uncertain'),(983,0,0,0,'Until We Last','Until We Last is a post-rock band started in the summer of 2011 by Ketan Bahirat. It was originally started off as a one man bedroom project. Over a course of 2-3 months, a line-up was being formed to take the music live. In October 2011, a full line-up of the band came together to work on writing new material as well as play live. The bands sound is defined by many as something very different and that it could lead to a much bigger fan base for the genre in India. ','untilwelast@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/untilwelast','','','','193069364078221','369',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','until-we-last'),(984,0,0,0,'Plok','','','http://www.facebook.com/plokme','','','','188915941159596','369',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','plok'),(985,0,0,0,'Keep The Skies Clear','\"Keep The Skies Clear\" is an electronically influenced metalcore band formed in 2011. Starting with playing covers of bands such as Abandon All Ships, Asking Alexandria, currently working on a couple of own original compositions.\nThe genre of the band is completely different, that has elements of metalcore, screamo, techno and electronicore that promises to deliver a tight mixture of never heard before music.\n__________________________________\n\nPast Shows and Achievements :\n-> Winners at Blithchron 2012 - IIT Gandhinagar\n-> Performed at Blizzards of Rock - IIM-A\n-> Winners at Equipo 2012 - EDI (Ahmedabad)\n-> Performed at Metamorphosis 2012 - CEPT (Ahmedabad)\n-> Runners Up at Sphinx Rock Fest - BK School Of Business Management (Ahmedabad)','','http://www.facebook.com/keeptheskiesclear','','','','222267847803256','368',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','keep-the-skies-clear'),(986,2,11,11,'The Shakey Rays','The Shakey Rays are a four-piece Indie Rock band from Chennai. Songwriting duo Dhruva Gautham and Vikram Kannan, having disbanded seminal Chennai rock group, Easy Street, decided to get together with Chennais most adaptive rhythm section, Niranjan Swaminathan and Iuni Yoomi, to form The Shakey Rays- a D.I.Y Indie rock n roll unit that combines the ancient traditions of rhythm n blues, swing with the aggressive energy and attitude of Garage Rock and Punk.\r\n\r\nThe band is at its strongest when the music is interactive and impulsive. Extended, onstage jams allow the musicians to branch out musically and vary the 4-piece format. Dhruva Gautham and Vikram Kannan tend to work on different arrangements for each song and explore various musical patterns, with an emphasis on the intricacies of crafting a record. The musical style of The Shakey Rays is raw and rooted in blues and Rhythm n Blues while their approach and setting are fresh and contemporary, setting them apart in the Indian indie circle.','Nithin Subramanian: +91 9176666890','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Shakey-Rays/196463863718688','http://theshakeyrays.bandcamp.com/','http://myspace.com/theshakeyrays','http://www.reverbnation.com/theshakeyrays','0','366',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-10 16:31:10',360,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','the-shakey-rays'),(987,0,0,0,'AN*S THE MENACE (AtM)','\nATM WAS FORMED IN MARCH 2008 WHEN THE THREE EXISTING MEMBERS FOUND THE VOCALIST AT A GIG JUST A WEEK BEFORE THERE FIRST PERFORMANCE..\nSINCE THEN THE BAND HAS DONE WELL NAD NEVER MISSED ANY OPPURUNITY TO GROW MUSICALLY.\n\nTHE DRUMMER AND THE GUITARIST WERE IN A METAL BAND BEFORE,BASS GUITARIST IS A NIRVANAHOLIC AND THE VOCALIST HAS THE BEATLEMANIA GOING ON...WHEN ALL THESE GUYS COME TOGETHER U GET A DIFFERENT SOUND THAT IS \"ATM\".\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/ANS-THE-MENACE-AtM/151141335090','','','','151141335090','366',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ans-the-menace-atm'),(988,0,0,0,'TudenMusic','','9612934139','http://www.facebook.com/tudenmusic','','','','125153544213776','365',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','tudenmusic'),(989,0,0,0,'band RAB','','kunal-9336728400, rohit-9307263868, vineet-9307266566','http://www.facebook.com/pages/band-RAB/119816911392360','','','','119816911392360','364',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','band-rab'),(990,0,0,0,'ChromaDerma','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/ChromaDerma/207748505173','','','','207748505173','363',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','chromaderma'),(991,0,3,3,'Schizophonic','Schizophonic is an experimental project that brings together many different styles and genres in an electronic environment that is painstakingly created and maintained at each performance. The band comprises three musicians, all networked together and sharing material wirelessly, capturing sounds from the moment and introducing them into their own compositions in real time. \r\n\r\nThe humans in the band have had experience playing a plethora of musical styles and their material reflects the influences of all that has gone by. From deep, dark Dub delays and Hip Hop turn-tablism to jazz piano and blues guitar licks off crackling LP\'s, all human-generated sound is fed into an electronic hive-mind that behaves intuitively and dramatically; in essence, a fourth member of the band that can only be given suggestions but never entirely controlled. \r\n\r\nSchizophonic performances are unpredictable. The band works with a variety of people ranging from visual artists and designers to dancers and musicians. The experience is customized to best suit each venue/gig and no two concerts are the same.','','http://www.facebook.com/projectschizophonic','','http://soundcloud.com/projectschizophonic','','238473992849404','362',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','schizophonic'),(992,0,0,0,'Low volume','A collaboration of two young inspiring artists and old friends, who happen to find each other living in a German neighbourhood, trying to make some music late at night, at a nearly unaudible volume level. Cannot describe it better !!','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Low-volume/112103762167724','','','','112103762167724','362',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','low-volume'),(993,0,0,0,'Porco Rosso','Groupe parisien form en 2002 par Yann Giraud (chants, guitares) et Stphane Perez (basse), Porco Rosso est un cas  part dans l\'Hexagone. Il se dmarque de la  nouvelle scne franaise  par des instrumentations ambitieuses, avec des rfrences parses  l\'indie-rock amricain. Des textes simples et sensibles, peu ancrs dans le quotidien, et un sens aiguis de la mlodie le distinguent galement de la scne rock alternative franaise. Porco Rosso propose ainsi un univers singulier, naviguant entre chanson et pop. Le groupe est complt depuis peu par Jean-Baptiste Fleury (batterie) et Xavier Guant (guitares, claviers). ','porcocrou@yahoo.fr','http://www.facebook.com/porcorossos','','','','36365505753','361',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','porco-rosso'),(994,0,0,0,'Revelations','','08197219867,09686619886,09739801152','http://www.facebook.com/Revelations.in','','','','322259995958','246',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','revelations'),(995,0,0,0,'Katai Bum','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Katai-Bum/223269217685551','','','','223269217685551','359',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','katai-bum'),(996,0,0,0,'Ashes On My Grave','With no genre boundaries , the band aims to create divine music .\n\nStarted on 28/3/11 , AOMG is currently recording tracks for their first album which would probably be released in 2012 !\n\n We use products of Jackson , Ibanez , Greg Bennett , Fanndec , Hartke , Roland , Yamaha , Boss , Korg , Jim Dunlop etc . ','Anuj Singh ','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Ashes-On-My-Grave/248328645196147','','','','248328645196147','356',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ashes-on-my-grave'),(997,0,0,0,'Synaps','','synaps.india[at]gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/SynapsIndia','','','','64521609400','355',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','synaps'),(999,0,0,0,'Prateek Kuhad','With influences stemming from Elliot Smith and Nick Drake to Jimi Hendrix and Pearl Jam, this upcoming singer-songwriter is for a listener, searching for something emotive in their musical palette. Find a blend of pop rock and poetic folk in the acoustic beats of Prateek Kuhad. Born in Jaipur, India, and now based in New York City, Prateek grew up playing the guitar and training vocally in Indian classical music. After weaving through diverse musical genres, he found a sense of direction after attending a jazz workshop in Prague where he began fusing different styles to reach his own sound.\n\nHis talents extend to playing the ukulele, drums, bass and harmonica, but they dont end there. His heartfelt lyrics artfully capture lifes everyday thoughts and experiences, while his tunes and deep rhythms softly resonate within you. With his Debut EP that released in July 2011 via Pagal Haina Records and upcoming gigs in town, this NYC performer is already a bright star in the world of music.','Info@pagalhaina.com','http://www.facebook.com/prateekkuhadmusic','','','','143617089024158','352',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','prateek-kuhad'),(1000,0,1,1,'Vaeya','Vaeya is Vaibhav / VB. After being introduced to his first outdoor party outside Bombay, India in 2002 something made him want more. Then in 2003 he moved to Brisbane, Australia for university. After being a regular punter at parties for 2 years, He started to mess around in fruity loops writing music under the project name Vaeya in 2005. Over the years he has gotten more serious with his music. The diversity of people and music at parties, and the extreme vastness and untouched beauty of Australia was a massive influence on him. Progressive music being his main weapon of choice. He has very flexible progressive style ranging from a very intelligent techy style to a nice lush progresssive sound and more in between. Recently he has gotten on board with Glitchy Tonic Records (Germany) and is looking forward to promote his more darker techy sound with them, and also to promote the other brilliant artists on the label. \r\n\r\n2010 was the year in when he released a whoe lot of music on Glitchy.Tonic.Records and Fatali Music this included a full length album, an EP and a few tracks on various compilations. 2010 also saw him remix Fatali\'s Dreaming track which was then selected and released on Fatali\'s Label  Fatali Music and then was given an oppurtunity to release an original EP on Fatali Music, which reached the Beatport Psytrance top Downloaded Charts. He has also remixed artists like Tom Cosm, Plastikman (Richie Hawtin), Nine Inch Nails, Royksopp and Fiord (Antix).\r\n\r\nVaeya has played a whole bunch of parties and festivals all over east coast Australia. He plays 2 completely different Live sets, One style being Dark Intelligent Tech (more suited to the night time). The other style being a very Lush Progressive Sound which is perfect for the day time or the afternoon. Having moved back to Mumbai, India in march 2010 he joined forces with Occulta Records which is a Bangalore based progressive trance label. In mid 2011 he moved to New Delhi to work for event mangement and music label bad boy Audio Aashram - The only crew in India dedicated to showcase some of the best music from around the world to the Indian masses.\r\n\r\nHe has played alongside Ocelot, Lish, Frechbax, Perfect Stranger, Krumelur, Braindrop, Aghori Tantrik, Sensient, Tetrameth, Grouch etc etc. Things are only going to get bigger and better in 2011.','vaeyamusic@gmail.com / vaibhav.bhavsar@audioashram.in','http://www.facebook.com/vaeya','http://www.myspace.com/vaeya','http://www.soundcloud.com/vaeya','','0','352',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','vaeya'),(1001,0,0,0,'Crash & Boom','Crash & Boom is the psychedelic expression of Ash Roy and Ashvin Mani Sharma, founding members of Indian electronic giants, Jalebee Cartel who have been at the forefront of electronic music in India producing music, and performing all over the world. \n\nAsh is an accomplished percussionist and brings a live wire energy to any performance while Ashvin has been a part of the Psy Trance music scene in India since it\'s inception in the 90\'s, already having played with Psycho Micro, Damage , Kerosene Club, Astrix, Ace Ventura, Atmos and Perfect Stranger.\n\nThis project was born out of a deep love for the psychedelic trance experience. With their tribal Indian rhythms and driving baselines, Crash and Boom have their own distinct style and sound. \n\nCrash and Boom perform as a 2 person DJ set or a Live Act with laptops, synthesizers and live percussions!\n','','http://www.facebook.com/crashnboom','','','','178578718855961','350',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','crash-boom'),(1002,0,0,0,'Puzzles','','','http://www.facebook.com/PuzzlesTheBand','','','','181951861836872','347',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','puzzles'),(1003,0,0,0,'2 POINT 4 THREE','ARTIST BIO\nTHE BAND PLAYS A UNIQUE BLEND OF PROGRESSIVE INNOVATIVE METAL WITH TRACES OF THRASH AND CLASSIC GROOVE.....HIGHLY INFLUENCED IN THEIR MUSIC WITH PROGRESSIVE METAL!THE DRUMMER AND THE VOX COME FROM BLACK AND SYMPHONIC METAL BACKGROUND!SO THE BAND\'S SOUND BLENDS WITH PROGRESSIVE DEATH METAL.....AND WE LIKE TO EXPERIMENT A LOT!THE GENRE OF THE BAND VARIES WITH EACH AND EVERY NEW SONG BUT MAINLY FOCUSES ON BLACK PROGRESSIVE DEATH METAL!\n2 POINT 4 THREE RECREATED THEIR MUSIC WITH A NEW TASTE AND ERA OF PROGRESSIVE DEATH METAL.....\nTHE BAND WAS FORMED IN FEBRUARY 2011,\n\nTHE BAND HAS ALSO SHARED THE STAGE WITH INTERNATIONAL BANDS LIKE DHISTI FROM SRI LANKA,NARSAMHAR FROM POKHRA,NEPAL,ARSEMES FROM IRAN AND WITH GRINDCORE HEAVYWEIGHTS \'NAPALM DEATH\'.....\\m/','+919804766591,+919002790979,+919733062879','http://www.facebook.com/2point4threee','','','','229693263742731','345',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','2-point-4-three'),(1004,0,0,0,'Zero Transition','Zero Transition is a D.I.Y Metalcore band from the Himalayan. Formed early of 2010.\nCurrently a 2 member band. Everything from album art/design to recording & post production are all done at a home studio. \n------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nDOWNLOAD OUR FREE DEBUT EP:\nhttp://chugcore.blogspot.com/2011/02/zero-transition-zero-transition-2011.html\nOR\nhttp://duckcore.blogspot.com/2011/02/zero-transition-zero-transition-2011.html','Bishal.kirawa.rai@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Zero-Transition/113534955332312','','','','113534955332312','345',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','zero-transition'),(1005,0,0,0,'Incarnadine','http://www.reverbnation.com/incarnadineindia\nBand Mail : incarnadineindia@gmail.com','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Incarnadine/337136735850','','','','337136735850','343',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','incarnadine'),(1006,0,0,0,'Quantic and his Combo Brbaro','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Quantic-and-his-Combo-B%C3%A1rbaro/134547886609869','','','','134547886609869','341',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','quantic-and-his-combo-barbaro'),(1007,0,0,0,'Pandora\'s Box','','','http://www.facebook.com/Pandorasboxindia','','','','147235611975448','340',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','pandoras-box'),(1008,0,0,0,'Nawed Khan','Born and raised in Karachi, Pakistan currently located in New York, USA. He has performed with many artists and bands in New York, New Jersey, and Virginia at several occasions including Community Festivals and Pakistan Day Parades. With several Radio, TV, and Media Production credits his skills consists vocals, songwriting, composing, performing, recording, production, promotion and marketing.','Nawed Khan','http://www.facebook.com/NawedKhanMusic','','','','58012657300','339',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','nawed-khan'),(1009,0,0,0,'Aviral','Welcome to the official music page of Aviral Bajpai.\n\nThis page is dedicated to information about upcoming music releases and information about and from Aviral.\n\nBorn and brought up in Lucknow, Uttar Pradesh, Aviral was always in the frontlines whenever it came to music. Aviral has been a part of various musical projects and is today a member of the Gothic Metal band, \"Orantem\".\n\nThis page will keep you updated about all that will go on in his musical career.','premsbajpai@yahoo.co.in','http://www.facebook.com/bajpaiaviral','','','','133593586667872','339',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','aviral'),(1010,0,0,0,'Alter State','Alter State (Sanil Sudan) is the co-founder of \"TheMassive.in - India\'s only definitive bass heavy community\" and part of the \"PURENOiSE\" crew in Delhi. From playing a part promoting bass heavy music with his community and club nights, to push House & Techno music with the PURENOiSE crew , to working dancefloors across the city, Alter State brings his own musicality to the underground sound.\n\nAlways fresh and innovative, Alter State can be seen working dance floor grooves with his unique take on House/Techno music at once and destroying dancefloors with raw bass heavy Drum and Bass/Dubstep music at the other. Always following a journey like structure in his sets on and off the floor, tracks handpicked to match various styles and mood, Alter State can always be relied on to push the conventional sounds into new and unconventional directions. \n\nBeing part of the burgeoning dance music scene in Delhi, Alter State apart from promoting various club nights at various hotspots like 24/7 @Lalit, Ai-The Love Hotel, Double Decker Bar, Kuki , Shooters, Zoo Bar, Zook, Mojo  has been invited over to play at Festivals like BassCamp , Holi Cow, Sunrise Mist & guest spots at BASSFoundation, Delitronica playing alongside massive headline acts like Klute (U.K/Commercial Suicide) , NuTone (U.K/Hospital Records) and various other local acts notably Arjun Vagale (Maktub) ,BBC, Vachan, Phi degrees and more.\n\nCurrently, Alter State is honing his studio techniques and has started putting out soulful interpretations of music he loves, ranging from Chill Out versions of Classics to dance floor oriented Tech (House) and Drum & Bass originals. \n\nWith much focus on playing and pushing interesting music coupled with favorable reviews on his productions, Alter State is a talent to look out in 2011. \n\nLinks -\nwww.themassive.in\nwww.facebook.com/alterstate\nhttp://twitter.com/djsanils\nhttp://soundcloud.com/alterstate\nhttp://soundcloud.com/themassive\nhttp://soundcloud.com/purenoise\n\nDJ Bookings- djsanils@gmail.com\nContact Info-+91 9311888674','djsanils@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/alterstate','','','','188239301191343','336',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','alter-state'),(1011,0,0,0,'Spook','Spook is a 5 piece pop-rock alternative band\n\nSpook  now have Timmy Verghese on bass in place of Sonam Lama\nand currently Feature Rahul Hariharan on Drums with Michael Lee soon to be joining in on guitar!!!\n\nSpook was born out of a previous 1-gig fun covers outfit played by drummer Zain Calcuttawala, violin player-Clavell Santiago and guitarist/vocalist Akshay Deodhar. Wanting to complete the band and move past the whole covers rut that bands get stuck in, after much searching, almost in the same week they came across keyboard player, Anis Gandhi(of Sledgehammer fame) who bass player Sonam Lama. The 5 instantly clicked and got together for their first show at Cafe Goa for BEP\'s UTV music and movies night opening for the band Aftertaste.\nWith various influences of Funk, Metal, Progressive Metal, Western Classical, Grunge , Classic and pop-rock, Sonam and Akshay did most of the songwriting with the entire band actually coming together to complete and arrange songs.\n\nThe music that the 5 churn out is an interpretation by 4 people of a song written by the fifth.\n\nWhile they are constantly working on their increasing originals set, the band are at present in the process of recording a 5 song EP to get some of their music out and not just leave it online. With 5 shows under their belt and 2 more coming up, Spook hopefully shall have their music well known and widespread. Concentrating more on how they sound as opposed to how they look, Spook are around and here to stay!\n\nOverhauls can be powerful, and more so when they happen in your own garage. Spook is a band thats a manifestation of pure, unbridled, raw energy. A collective of five band expats barely-into-their-twenties minds; Spook sounds fresh off the laundromat  spiffy. Akshay Deodhar on vocals and rhythm guitar is the songwriting talent, crafting the incendiary musicianship of Anis Gandhi on piano, Zain Calcuttawala on percussion and drums, Clavell Santiago on violin and Sonam Lama on bass into scattered sound-packets stitched in melodies and harmonies. Grunge based, heavy, reverberating sounds echo in a spiral of constant whirlpool of musical emoting  Spook represent everything a young band should be. Passionate. Thats the least you can expect out of an outfit represented by a gawking Owl called Pedro as the mascot, considering their influences range from Pearl jam, Chris Cornell, Coldplay, RHCP, GooGoo Dolls, Alice In Chains, Foo Fighters, The Calling and Kings of Leon to name a few. Progressively new age, yet rebelliously old-skool; Spook songs bridge the gaps between instrumental solos and melodic riffs enchantingly. Diverse logic may be easy to define each band mates musical heritage Post their one gig at Caf Goa where they played a 3 song solo set, where a call for resurrection from a threatening damper called power failure only displayed their eclectic performance skills. This be true grunge and just made you raise your fingers in a m/. Spook have the potential to spook the daylights out of you. Hang around and lend an ear!','Akshay Deodhar - 9930911312','http://www.facebook.com/spooktheband','','','','124598530895910','336',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','spook'),(1012,0,0,0,'Nikhil & Ujjwal','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Nikhil-Ujjwal/406815812665232','','','','406815812665232','336',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','nikhil-ujjwal'),(1013,0,1,1,'Ditty & Mark','Alternative jazz-influenced original music by Aditi Veena & Mark Aranha. We would love it if you could share the music, tell us what you think or contact us to donate matchboxes!\r\n\r\nDescription\r\n\r\n? Ditty has curly hair, a pretty voice and collects matchboxes \r\n? Mark has a talent for tongue tricks, loves guitars, and can cook a mean steak ? Together, they make beautiful music\r\n\r\nAlternative jazz-influenced original music by Aditi Veena & Mark Aranha. Additional grooves to be supplied by the talented Pranoy Praveen and Jayant Manchanda. We would love it if you could share the music, tell us what you think or contact us to donate