e into existence in may 2011. \nBut prior to that Anand,Vicky and Aakash met at a guitar class and decided to jam and form a band in 2009.\n \nIn the early days, the trio used to jam with a drummer - Akhil(Anand\'s friend), \nBut in mid 2011,the trio met a new drummer-Evan and started playing with him !!! \nt0Rt is influenced by Alternative Music with their own personal respective influences....\n\nt0Rt performed for the 1st time in August 2011\n\n\"Independent alternative music sub is a viable commodity\" \n-Krist Novoselic(the bassist and co-founder of the band Nirvana)','','http://www.facebook.com/tort123','','','','247261668646128','327',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','tort'),(1023,0,1,1,'East Stepper','Complimented on his production skills by the likes of Robert Babbicz, DJ UMB(generationbass.com), DJ Nihal (BBC Radio 1 UK), Bobby Friction (BBC Asian Network) and many local talent also.\r\nHis blend of ethnic Indian sounds with hard and pumping sounds of the UK underground have been claimed to be amongst the only few Indian productions which are taking the Indian dubstep and drum and bass music to the global level. \r\nThanks to his widely acclaimed productions, he is now a regular feature on BBC Radio 1 and has also been featured and interviewed on BBC Asian Network representing the bass heavy music scene of the country. \r\n\r\nEast Stepper has a strict motto Create the music you perform. And he does it with solid ingenuity and technical skills and his productions dont stop at D&B and Dubstep only, Mungeritek is his progressive/techno project which has been praised by the worlds most leading EDM sound engineer Robert Babbicz himself. TheMASSIVE Soundsystem is also his brain child and today has become one of the more sought after Drum and Bass acts in the city which evolved from the online drum and bass/dubstep community (themassive.in) which he started about an year ago.\r\nSynesthesia is his ambient chill project and he also creates and performs psychedelic trance under the moniker Children of Anunnaki. \r\nAs a producer he has the musical and technical prowess to create the music he feels and hence does not restrict himself to just one sound and therefore all the different music projects he is involved with.\r\n\r\nA multi instrumentalist who plays the flute, keyboard, doumbek , djembe , drumkit and still constantly exploring new instruments in order to expand his horizons\r\nDuring live shows he doubles up as a percussionist playing and bringing his own style to instruments like the djembe, doumbek and conga infusing any dance music with percussive magic. \r\n\r\nAt the forefront of trying to push new sounds into the countries music consciousness East Stepper has founded UMI - Underground Music India (http://www.facebook.com/umiofficial)\r\nUMI is a body which strives to bring new sounds from all over the globe and give them an outlet in the capital. \r\nThe modus operandi right now for UMI is to have events and shows all across the city pushing Indian and global underground music. UMI will eventually turn into a media outlet for the same counter culture movement.\r\nEast Stepper is also the founder and brain behind the only online dubstep/Drum and bass community in the country called The Massive (facebook.com/IndiaMassive , themassive.in) which has been successful in bringing the community of D&B/Dubstep listeners together at a common space.','eaststepper@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/eaststepper','http://www.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fuser%2FD1vine&h=aAQHT-1Pz','http://www.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fsoundcloud.com%2Fd1vineillusion&h=DAQGpUXAH','','0','326',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','east-stepper'),(1024,0,0,0,'Badmarsh & Shri','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Badmarsh-Shri/127813737260128','','','','127813737260128','325',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','badmarsh-shri'),(1025,0,0,0,'I Killed Grim','','','http://www.facebook.com/ikilledgrim','','','','166445416764829','324',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','i-killed-grim'),(1026,0,0,0,'Mescaline','Cre en 2005, Mescaline a parcouru une longue route avec de nombreux vnements et premires parties. Aprs leurs 2 prcdents (Mescaline en 2005 et Mescal-core en 2008) le groupe prsente  Pathology of an ordinary man  enregistr au Ekoh Studio (Pleasure to kill, Aphrodite\'s babies, From Wisdom to hatred, fedjha, A bitch for my pigs). Aprs diverses changements de line-up, 2009 commence par larriv de son 5eme Membre  Alx   la basse qui apporte un jeu trs technique, intensifiant le rendu sonore du groupe. Mescaline  fait de nombreuses premires parties de groupes internationaux et montants tels que :\nDharma (hongrie), In Other Climes (Nice), Begarsound (Paris), Prime Sinister (Belgique), Danforth (Paris), 91 allstars (Paris), 7th Nemesis (Paris), Admiral Arms (Paris), Sentence (Paris), Tao menizoo (Paris), Memories of a dead man (Paris), Bawdy Festival (Paris) Et a galement particip  des tremplins musicaux tels que le Fallenfest, ou le festival Emergenza o ils sont arrivs jusquen finale et demi-finale franaise. Mescaline a aussi gagn plusieurs concours (radio Rock your life avec le titre Marchand de sable, promos etc) et a particip au fameux Halloween metal fest 2010 en premire partie de Prime Sinister et de Memories of a dead man.\n\nMescaline est aussi le groupe fondateur avec le groupe Wild Shades de lassociation/collectif de musique  RockEssonne. Le groupe fera le 11 fvrier 2012 la premire partie du groupe mythique du hardcore Franais : L\'ESPRIT DU CLAN AU RACK\'AM DE BRETIGNY SUR ORGE dont les places sont disponibles  la Fnac, France Billet et particepera aux MASTERCLASS organis par le Plan de Ris-Orangis avec LOFOFORA.\n\nContact :\nManager/booking : camille.grigaut@gmail.com\nGroupe : psyco_91@hotmail.fr\nAsso : rockessonne@gmail.com\n\nRejoindre le collectif :\nhttp://www.facebook.com/pages/Mescaline/116943905020782\nhttp://facebook.com/mescalineband\nhttp://myspace.com/mescalinemetalcore\n\nInterviews/Chroniques :\n- http://www.zikannuaire.com/report/dossiers/dossiers.php?val=1622_mescaline\n- http://rockyourlife-france.blogspot.com/2010/02/fiche-groupe-rockyourlife-mescaline.html\n\nLive reports :\n- www.inwe-b-zine.com/site/message.php?message=1325\n- www.zikannuaire.com/report/dossiers/dossiers.php?val...live\n- www.therockersplace.com/t5459-12-12-mescaline-perl-hwb-lachrymal-thought-bfgmelun\n- www.coreandco.fr/news/mescaline-au-fet-estival-10426.html \n\n\n','Rock\'Essonne','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Mescaline/116943905020782','','','','116943905020782','321',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','mescaline'),(1027,0,0,0,'NEPHUNK','Strung together by nephew & uncle - NEPHUNK are a band built over many years of family-dinners & basement-jams, Pink Floyd & A.R. Rahman, iced tea & \'pooki\'s squeals... Ishaan Chhabra (from the Berklee College of Music) & Chintan Kalra (from the \'parikrama\'s cool of music) produce these genre-defying soundscapes that are soulful, if sublime... melodic, often grand... and thanks to that \'generation-gap\', never ever boring.','Chintan Kalra','http://www.facebook.com/nephunk','','','','108808638056','320',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','nephunk'),(1028,0,0,0,'Cosmic Infusion','Formed in 2003, Cosmic Infusion is a Symphonic Black Metal band from Mumbai, India. Formed to create a pure blend of symphony and extreme metal. With some of the best and most experienced musicians from the underground scene of the country, they play their very own style of extreme metal.','','http://www.facebook.com/CosmicInfusion','','','','112453615540465','319',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','cosmic-infusion'),(1029,0,0,0,'The Boy Toy','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Boy-Toy/162938993797172','','','','162938993797172','318',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-boy-toy'),(1030,0,0,0,'DA Primitive Future','Da Primitive Future was formed in the year 2004 in a small town Darjeeling (India) when the situation was worst as a struggle for a pol. domain was still going on. Till then the band had been playing a very few gigs in their hometown. Adding to it the pol.scene left the town with no peace. And after leaving the band by the former guitarist Tenzin.D.Bhutia the band was left with Anup/hopeless lad (guitar/vox), Darpan/Eddy drunker (bass/vox) and Sandeep/ the garbage (drums). Since then the lads have seen moving forward with their urge for the PUNK ROCK music. The band has been influenced by the bands from the old 70s up till the 20s. Off course, the band has its own personality & sound, PUNK ROCK with a bit of SKA blend. The lads count their music to rise against the injustice and the exploitation of the generation by the authority and the nations. The day to day struggles, wrong turn of the youths and all the fuckin realities of this world, they include in their songs. \nDa Primitive Future right now is playing gigs here and there in India and focus to come out with full length tracks. Their achievements and motives does not count to win the crowns in national rock fests and success in selling albums but to stick to their basics and to follow their motto  Oppose and Depose . As the phase of music changes from one generation to the other, Da Primitive Future pays no heed to it, rather the band focus to keep the voice of the PUNK ROCK elite.\n\n               ','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/DA-Primitive-Future/118282184900663','','','','118282184900663','317',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','da-primitive-future'),(1031,0,0,0,'Seher','Seher is a Mumbai base band, started in 2009. with Tushar & Vispy. The thought process was to make Hindi music, jam, play live & have a great time.\n   \nAs we all know, Time & tide stop for no one.The band had initial teething problems with members coming in and out till we settled on this line up. Idea still remains the same. Making music with a catch to it. \n\nBut why did we choose Hindi to express ourselves? \nWe always attack that dilemma with the clich - music has no language. Extending the thought we are creating novel soundscapes that portray the spirit of our generation. In fact our music shouts for change.\n\nSeher\'s ideology is simple. As the word means morning glory, which signifies a new beginning, a fresh start; Seher focusses on releasing sounds which have unique Indian roots and western influences. The mix makes for an interesting combo of new sounds, wave of grooves & melodies that capture your mind. \n\nCome join us, as we embark on this journey, pen a fresh beginning.... Seher','','http://www.facebook.com/SeherTheBand','','','','101989876552522','317',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','seher'),(1032,0,0,0,'Innate Propensity','Innate Propensity is young as a band consists of members with years of musical experiences. We play to Thrash/Death Metal.','Soumyajit Basu.(9945473091),Prateek Chhetri.(9538077523)','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Innate-Propensity/252649981466553','','','','252649981466553','316',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','innate-propensity'),(1033,0,0,0,'Meteor Tamed','We got together in Jan 2011, after splitting from our previous bands and the first jam itself told us we got to be together. \nStarted out with covering some stuff ,but, then quickly went on to get some OCs underhand.\nRecently we have two OCs which are recording good and have material for atleast 3 OCs in hand.\nHave played at various venues across pune city namely , Big wheels motoring, arc asia, Ishanya Mall amphitheater, Cafe euthanasia, Symbiosis college of design, Phoenix mall.\n\nAchievements: \n1) Winners at Imagine Rock Fest,2012.  \n2)Runners up at blizzard rock fest, 2011,\n3) Runners up at CASCADE ,Rock Cult , 2011\n4) Finalists at Battle of the Bands- Kumar Pacific Mall 2012. \n5) Finalists at Maadhyam, Symbiosis,Viman nagar, 2011,\n','Vinay - 9766707903, Adarsh- 9552597117','http://www.facebook.com/MeteorTamed','','','','204065462958510','316',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','meteor-tamed'),(1034,0,0,0,'High Octave(India)','','highoctave2010@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/High-OctaveIndia/203098103034836','','','','203098103034836','316',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','high-octaveindia'),(1035,0,0,0,'Burning God Little','http://soundcloud.com/nabovarsel/sets/burning-god-little-notes-on/','','http://www.facebook.com/BurningGodLittle','','','','159455630755009','314',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','burning-god-little'),(1036,0,0,0,'Rangskarsha','RANGSKARSHA : a tongue twister indeed!! But the essence is soulful...meaning \"sprinkling of joyful colors\". Music comes straight from our heart...and we come from the heart of Kolkata. Born in July \'08, we set sail with popular covers, mostly progressive numbers. As years passed by, OCs came up...and now we have 18 original numbers. Heartful thanks to our existing fans, and hope you guys walk down with us on this melodious journey of Rangskarsha\'s music! \nLove you all...','Biddu(8961147994)','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Rangskarsha/235977453089285','','','','235977453089285','314',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rangskarsha'),(1037,0,0,0,'BOOST My BAND','','','http://www.facebook.com/BoostMyBand','','','','112346025539355','313',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','boost-my-band'),(1038,0,0,0,'Lemon House (Official)','Jazz Band','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Lemon-House-Official/101396036624461','','','','101396036624461','311',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','lemon-house-official'),(1039,0,1,1,'Susmit Sen','Formed in the early 90\'s Indian Ocean has been one of the spearheads of the Indian Rock Scene. \r\n\r\nTheir unique sound of Contemporary Rock mixed with classical, jazz and fusion have earned them a cult following. \r\n\r\nTheir band has managed to maintain this inimitable sound in all their albums and have attained some rave reviews from the critics.\r\n\r\nSome of the themes of their songs are sufism, enviornmentalism and mythology. \r\n\r\nDefinitely exclusive in what they do, Indian Ocean have toured all over India and played all across the globe.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Susmit-Sen/107926862573512','','','','107926862573512','310',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','susmit-sen'),(1040,0,0,0,'The Delhi Jazz Club','','Shalabh Singh','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Delhi-Jazz-Club/117182558322767','','','','117182558322767','310',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-delhi-jazz-club'),(1041,0,0,0,'Joos','A band trying to introduce music that blends Funk, Jazz, Blues, Rock n Roll and Reggae to create something fresh and groovy.\n\nPlayed at: Economic times corp rock, Kyra, 64 Bistro, Legends of Rock, Radio One 94.3FM, Big Junction Jam festival, War of Bands by Moonlight Theater, Palace Grounds etc. ','9731476543, varunsrivastava2@gmail.com, JoosBrothers@gmail.com ','http://www.facebook.com/JoosBand','','','','127907737269929','309',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','joos'),(1042,0,0,0,'Rai Ko Ris','We\'ve had at least four line up changes since we began Rai Ko Ris in 2000. Presently, the band comprises of just the two of us however, we collaborated with a friend (Bodh Ghale from Knife) the past year after our previous guitarist went abroad. \nWe did a mini tour of France in July 2001. During the tour, we not only had a good excuse to holiday with our kids but we had the opportunity to meet people who really inspired and encouraged us to continue socio-political activities here in Nepal , with punk/hardcore as a vehicle, and giving respect to D.I.Y. ethics. \nChris Luppi (Arise zine and Elephant Eye Records) in Thailand was also extremely encouraging as we fumbled through the beginnings. \nRai Ko Ris then toured Malaysia in March 2002. The incredible experience of meeting and learning from fellow Asian punks added more fuel to our fire. The collectives and individuals we met allowed us to rock ourselves to a heatstroke in the name of active punk.\n\nWe visited Sri Lanka & South India (travelled by road/train) at the end of last year. Played our acoustic set to some mafia who owned bars and kept guns in their kitchen  and who recorded us on their mobile phones! \nWe didn\'t find any d.i.y. hc/punk scenes in either Sri Lanka or South India , but there was a mass of metal/rock genres, pretty high-fi events, & not much on the socio-political front (even though we were not just looking for that). We couldn\'t afford the live gigs advertised on posters! The fun of watching Angus Young on a big screen at a metal bar in Bangalore & students headbanging along wore off as fast as our cash did. \nA lot like Nepal , the most pro-active people we met were local musicians who live in villages and came begging to the city centres, or human rights activists. But rock is for sure alive and kicking in both these countries we visited! \n\nPresent Activities: \nThe band organises benefit gigs with a purpose to hold interactions about political and social causes that are pertinent to us in Nepal . Speakers are invited to gigs, e.g. anarchist/anti-war activist Milan Rai (from ARROW, Justice Not Vengence, Voices in the Wilderness) and coming to the next gig, Amnesty International, Reason To Believe. \n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Rai-Ko-Ris/156466774414586','','','','156466774414586','307',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rai-ko-ris'),(1043,0,0,0,'Zehen','','','http://www.fa