-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','indi-graffiti'),(1091,0,0,0,'Jagged Surge','Formed in March 2010, armed with a unique stealth sound, fused by genres of Classic Hard Rock and Old School Heavy Metal, the band marches forward to break boundaries and captivate fans ... \n\nAnd the journey goes on.....','9945011969','http://www.facebook.com/JaggedSurge','','','','187147737966418','244',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','jagged-surge'),(1092,0,0,0,'VJ samraat singh','emcee / VJ / poet / stylist / spoken word artist /  fashion writer / event co-ordinator / vocalist / non-fiction director','www.facebook.com/hightv','http://www.facebook.com/vjsamraat.singh','','','','176222669091816','244',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','vj-samraat-singh'),(1093,0,0,0,'Hamza Kazi','Hamzas obsession with Drums began at the age of 4, when his parents gifted him a toy drum kit. After banging away relentlessly for years, he happened to hear Tools Lateralus album and decided that he wanted to take it seriously. Despite the lack of a drum kit, he began taking formal lessons from renowned drummer Gino Banks. Not owning a kit did not hinder his progress and infact enhanced his drum programming skills and his knowledge of drum theory as he would program beats and air drum to them. \n\nYears of air drumming finally paid off and he was rewarded with his first drum kit, coincidentally a Mapex, which he eventually came to endorse. His love for Paiste became evident then as, with his limited budget, he chose to buy a pair of Paiste 402 hi-hats instead of buying a Solar Starter Pack. He used just those hats for over 2 years then slowly expanded his kit to its current  setup containing over 20 high end Paiste cymbals.\n\nToday, he is known not only for his ability to adapt to different musical settings but also for his in depth knowledge of drum theory, its advanced applications and technical prowess for flawless execution of the same. \n\nHis major influences are Danny Carey, Gavin Harrison, Tomas Haake, Virgil Donati, Marco Minnemann, Mike Mangini, Thomas Lang, Terry Bozzio , Josh Freese and Tim Alexander. Glimpses of their various styles are visible at times in his primary playing style which can be broadly described as Progressive. He has studied odd time signatures, unconventional patterns and polyrhythms in great detail and subtly incorporates them in his playing. \n\nHis motto has always been If the drum gods can do it, then with the right mindset, hard work and practice, you can too. It is this very philosophy that has made him strive harder to achieve his goals. Those whove seen him live can vouch to how he makes even the most complex drum parts look easy.\n\nHamza designed and fabricated his own Custom Bell Stand which was inspired by Gavin Harrisons Sonor Bell Stand. The Bell Stand was also featured on a show on CNN-IBN as part of their Engineers who are Musicians Program.\n\nHamza has been the official drum instructor at one of the most prestigious universities in the world, the Indian Institute of Technology, Bombay, since 2008. He has taught over 250 students there. He has also conducted clinics in many colleges across India in places like Pune, Delhi, Chennai, Rookee, Goa,  Nagpur, New Bombay, Pilani, Lucknow and many more. Hamzas Clinics are a regular at Music Conferences like the Palm Expo.\n\nThe bands which Hamza has played for are as follows:\n\nEggless Love Cake (Alternative/Grunge)\nLethe (Thrash Metal)\nZohak (Thrash Metal)\nBitchslap (Hardcore)\nApollonian Quest (Technical Death Metal)\nWorkshop (Comedy Metal)\nReverrse Polarity (Scremo)\nCoshish (Progressive Rock)\nAbraxas (Djent)\nAxetortion (Instrumental Rock)\nKvanaa (Hindi Rock)\n\nHe has been a Live Session Drummer for the following artists/bands:\nKhiladi (Comedy Rock)\nPrayag (Hindi Rock)\nApernit Singh (Instrumental Rock)\nZodiac (Alternative)\nClaver Menezes (Instrumental Rock)\nMedusa (Electronica)\nRevival (Power Metal)\nRed Cube (Alternative)\nParesh Kamath (Funk Fusion)\nJaneen Leah (Blues)\nKavita Seth (Sufi Rock)\n','Contact No: 9820589707  Email: hamzakazi@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Hamza-Kazi/311048258913719','','','','311048258913719','244',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','hamza-kazi'),(1094,0,0,0,'Space','In the winter of 2008, one evening Tritha along with her friend, Ritika decided to make music very simply in their living room in Kolkata...\nSince then, Space has performed in many clubs and pubs in Calcutta including Someplace Else, Park and several times at The Big Ben, Kenilworth Hotel.\nIn Delhi at Cafe Morrison, Geoffrey\'s, International Diner, Turquoise Cottage, Cafe Oz and at the Wills Fashion Week 2010-11.\nThe band was also invited in Naukuchiatal for the ESCAPE festival in May 2010 and 2011.\nThey performed in July 23rd in Paris at Les Ecoliers, a musical bar in Paris promoting new and experimental world music bands.','emailsofspace@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/soundofspace','','','','207827039250069','243',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','space'),(1096,0,0,0,'7:10','710 is a rock band from bangalore consisting of amyth adhir aditya and rahul...... the band tries to balance out the melody side of things with some heaviness to it while writing music!! we believe in the 70\'s lifestyle!!! rock n roll 4 life!!!! \n','Swathi Chatrapathy ','http://www.facebook.com/the710','','','','129188653803982','235',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','710'),(1097,0,0,0,'The Syndicate GOA','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Syndicate-GOA/157069194324044','','','','157069194324044','235',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-syndicate-goa'),(1098,0,0,0,'Avyakta','Avyakta means unexpressed. Feelings and emotions that often remain unexpressed, find solace in music. The bands music is their way to belong and relate to the world. \nKick-starting in 2006 with the intent of showcasing its ideas through soulful music, the band has been playing a number of gigs until now. With initial performances in the Youth festival organised by Times of India in Mumbai to play the finals of the same competition in Delhi, the band evolved to playing solo gigs in and around Mumbai to even be the opening act for the renowned Pakistani band STRINGS. \n\nVocals - Shantanu\nLead Guitarist & Composer - Vipul\nDrums - Swarupa\n\nPlaying across genres like Fusion and Pop-rock, the band blends in hues of western and Indian music thus giving their songs a brisk and refreshing sound.\n\nAvyakta will always be determined at creating music which appeals to them and to their audience as well. The bands music aims at creating a balance among all categories of music lovers.\n','','http://www.facebook.com/avyaktamusic','','','','314099788617002','229',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','avyakta'),(1099,0,0,0,'Chimera','','','http://www.facebook.com/ChimeraIndia','','','','108291399244776','227',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','chimera'),(1100,0,0,0,'Thread Melt Down','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Thread-Melt-Down/121344664594981','','','','121344664594981','226',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','thread-melt-down'),(1101,0,0,0,'Karma Konnect','From the land that bore the ilk of great musicians like TANSEN, rises another son with the same penchant for creating celestial sounds. NICK aka Manish Arora, is one of the few new age Indian musicians to have touched the epitome of EDM and are around to share the great vibes with their audiences. Performing across the globe, enthralling audiences the world over NICK has been an attraction at the FULL MOON FESTIVAL ( Germany ) , SOLSTICE FESTIVAL ( Amsterdam ) , XIBALBA FESTIVAL ( Poland ) , ECO EXISTENCE FESTIVAL ( Portugal ) , BOOM FESTIVAL (2008)( Portugal ) and every festival of repute in India.\n\nNICK is the producer behind one of the largest EDM Company in India, SHIVLINK RECORDS, which has over a dozen released CDs and another dozen digital releases to the name. Shivlink Records has played host to the stars of EDM from the world over. ASTRIX, 1200 MICS , SPACE CAT , ESKIMO ,EXAILE,SPACE BUDHA, CPU, SPACE TRIBE, ELECTRIC UNIVERSE, POLARIS , DNA , VIBE TRIBE , IRON MADNESS , MISTED MUPPET , SAMADHI , STRANGERS , SINE WAVE , VECTRO ELECTRO , QUANTUM & KEREN PORAT,SPACE BUDDHA,ACE VENTURA,ABSOLUM,ANANDA SHAKE, to name a few have already played in the country under the Shivlink banner.\n\nHaving evolved from a DJ, NICK today is releasing his own string of compositions under the name \"Karma Konnect\" and currently working on his Debut Album. Keeping deep roots of Indian Classical Music His Style is Mix of New age digital sounds & old skool goa trance\n\n. Aptly NICK says, Music is a very strong medium to connect to people, when over 50,000 people are dancing to the same tune, looking at the same stage and smiling, seeing such a dance floor is a feeling like no other, and this is the way I can best express myself.','konnectkarma@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Karma-Konnect/267660119925749','','','','267660119925749','226',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','karma-konnect'),(1102,0,0,0,'Red Energy Scythus','Friends, fans and fellow musicians, Please like and share this page. Its for the wildcard entry into Independence Rock 26. Wildcard entry means we (ScYthuS) directly get to play at the ALL INDIA FINALS in Mumbai on the 26th of November. \nNow isn\'t that Amazing. Please like and share the page. we\'ve come to 176 in 3 days, but take us to a thousand or more. don\'t let us lose this opportunity. Keep The RED ENERGY flowing. \\m/\n\nFormed in 2010, ScYthuS is a 5 piece metal act from New Delhi. With influences ranging from a variety of genres, the band has a unique and heavy sound, With a combination 