,'361249237226384','193',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','friend-or-foe'),(1127,0,0,0,'Still status','We are a Christian Metalcore band from shillong, meghalaya, india ','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Still-status/198047116876957','','','','198047116876957','184',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','still-status'),(1128,0,0,0,'Dying Out Flame','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Dying-Out-Flame/278819438819602','','','','278819438819602','184',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dying-out-flame'),(1129,0,0,0,'Hythum Morales','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Hythum-Morales/232895260115483','','','','232895260115483','182',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','hythum-morales'),(1130,0,0,0,'Shadja','We are SHADJA, a newly formed Bangalore based folk fusion/contemporary rock Band. \n\nOur music comes from life\'s experiences. Music is our way of choice to express what we feel, to communicate, and to try and understand everything just a little better.\n\nWe like to explore varied themes through our music, which, in turn, leads us to experiment with varying musical styles and lyrics. We do have a fondness for all things Indian, and so, irrespective of what we do, our music will always retain a flavor from home. ','','http://www.facebook.com/shadjaband','','','','116414858426582','181',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','shadja'),(1131,0,0,0,'Defenders Of Underground Metal','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Defenders-Of-Underground-Metal/137083493059020','','','','137083493059020','181',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','defenders-of-underground-metal'),(1132,0,0,0,'The Redmond Barry\'s','Birthed in a suburban Montreal basement in late 2009, two-piece, post-muff phenomenon The Redmond Barrys were expulsed from its depths and onto the streets in the summer of 2010.\n\nChris Briard (drums/vocals) and Varun Chopra (guitar/vocals) first met on a school bus and then again on a night in 2005 referred to only as the prom incident, when a mutual friend charged with sexual assault asked them to bail him out of jail.\nAs an end result, the boys realized the musical potential they had if combined together. They set aside their initial distaste for one another and formed TRB.\n\nLike a slap in the face on a lazy summer day, July 22nd 2011 saw the release of their debut EP entitled 1949 MURDERS, a first example of the style they so lovingly refer to as post-muff, combining raw sounds, addictive riffs, a.d.d. drums and charged lyrics from two distinct voices. Shaking things up and constantly pushing the limits of the two-piece combo, the duo spent the time leading up to the release working the streets to eventually afford a fan base, playing intense, loud, high-energy and sweaty shows.\n\nThe EPs single Woke Up Dead garnered buzz for the upcoming album when it was featured on the Montreal Gazettes download of the day upon immediate release in November 2010. The highly anticipated explosion of 1949 MURDERS into peoples ears led to headlining a ruckus raising, first Pop Montreal showcase performance as well as their current east coast tour on which they have shows with the likes of Parlovr, Pixies go to opener Imaginary Cities as well as Uncle Bad Touch.\n\nThe Redmond Barrys debut EP 1949 MURDERS is now available both digitally and as a jumbo sized post card with a QR code to stream, a unique download code, sticker and 4 exclusive pins.','info@theredmondbarrys.com','http://www.facebook.com/theredmondbarrys','','','','225549194336','177',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-redmond-barrys'),(1133,0,0,0,'Rishi Sippy','Hailing from Bangalore,India,Rishi Sippy has been a fond enthusiast of Electronic Music for over 7 years. He has completed the  DJ and Audio Engineering course at the ILM academy, Bangalore and has mastered many digital DJ softwares.\nHe has played at the biggest night clubs/festivals in the city and has played warm-up sets for some of the biggest names in the International EDM scene; some of which include Ma Faiza,Infected Mushroom, X-noise, Kindzadza, Shpongle, Daniel Kandi and Umek.\nCurrently he is working on producing his own music along with other upcoming artists in the city and intends to release his work in the near future.\n','rys1805@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Rishi-Sippy/234995933188742','','','','234995933188742','176',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rishi-sippy'),(1134,0,0,0,'Nazhorn','Conceived in the air, landed on ground, to dig a sky beneath.\nWith growing hate for contemporary djunk and metalcore in our hearts, we decided to hit those djentlemen in the face with some real metal.','','http://www.facebook.com/nazhorn.in','','','','280838025274749','175',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','nazhorn'),(1135,0,0,0,'RANGDAP (Official)','Initially the band started after launching of the first EP \"Mamas Boy\" but with non commitment from former member, the project never took off. After failing to form a band, Rangdap Cooper Kharshiing was compelled to record the second album \"Beyond the fence\" on his own. As the saying goes, when bad things can happen so do good things. With the joining of Mark Williams on drums, David Kom on vocal, Rafael on keys/guitars and Gideon on bass, Rangdap the band is now all set and ready to roll. RANGDAP is basically an instrumental band performing mostly original compositions. The band also does cover songs and other instrumental piece for live sets.','098620 97315 | rangdap.info@gmail.com ','http://www.facebook.com/rangdap','','','','177294142331522','174',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rangdap-official'),(1136,0,0,0,'BULLET STORM','Bullet Storm is a home-studio project of Debadyuti Panja and Krishanu Ganguly.\n\nWe would like to come across as a no nonsense band, which strives to bring to you a refreshing new sound. And yes we do a lot of covers as well. That is just one of the ways we want our sound to do all the talking.\n\n1.Numb(linkin Park Cover):\nDebadyuti- Guitars, Vocals,Sequencing and mixing, Music Production.     \nKrishanu-Vocals,Guitars.\n\n\n2.Shadow of mine:\nLyrics,Composition-Debadyuti.\nDebadyuti- Guitars, Vocals,Sequencing and mixing, Music Production.     \nKrishanu-Vocals,Guitars.\n\n                                                                             ','','http://www.facebook.com/bulletstormindia','','','','188851851212265','172',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','bullet-storm'),(1137,0,0,0,'The Window Seat','Lindsay DMello is an accomplished and versatile drummer performing music almost every other day; a big fan of collective communication, writing great tunes and playing with a dedicated attitude. Credits include The Petri Dish Project, Bliss Logic, Groove Suppa, Bombay Black and the GGs.\r\n\r\nSaxophonist and keyboardist, Tala Faral is truly a gifted world player. His experience in jazz and funk idioms has shaped many a bands sound. He strives for complete expression with a focus on melody. Credits include Sarimanouk in Indonesia, Potomac Jazz Quartet in D.C, and Groove Suppa in Mumbai.\r\n\r\nBassplayer Sonu Sangameswaran has been playing electric bass for over a decade. His experience spans the sounds of progressive rock, latin, hip-hop, funk and african music integrated with an original sense of groove. Credits include Vivek Rajagopalan Quartet, Anal Funk, Smoke Signals and Parallel Reality.\r\n\r\nSuman Sridhar joins us in expanding our sound! \r\n\r\nThe repertoire includes originals created out of a few years of musical interactionit also includes dynamic takes on a few covers! 	\r\n\r\nFor bookings, please call +91-9820370611.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Window-Seat/194094350614369','','','','194094350614369','169',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 11:24:40',329,'[\"\"]','[\"For bookings, please call +91-9820370611.\"]','the-window-seat'),(1138,0,0,0,'Constellation Project','Bahamabeats introduces the world to hip-hops hottest new collective with the release of the Constellation Project mixtape. \n\nG-Five, B.Eazzy, Finnesse, Kelz, and Toogi are the 5 talented up-and-coming artists who make up the group Constellation Project. They are all gifted individuals with something unique and special to offer the world.','bahamabeats@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Constellation-Project/123431764392746','','','','123431764392746','166',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','constellation-project'),(1139,5,1,1,'Jayant | Jitter','Jayants obsession with creating music, started at an early age. While his friends studied, and his parents worried, he immersed himself in sounds, creating his own unique brand of electronica. His curiosity and eagerness has not waned ever since.\r\nHe began producing music in 2003 and has done numerous projects since working with artists such as Anoushka Shankar, Chebi Sabah, Karsh Kale, Midival Punditz, to name a few. He\'s also produced music for a few film scores. Despite having no formal training in music theory, Jayant has created exceptional work with all of these artists and continues to work with many more.\r\nBoundaries as an artist are practically limitless for him, and that ethos reflects in all his work. His influences come from a wide spectrum of artists & musicians ranging from Indian classical, electronica, rock, psy-chill, trance, techno and ambient. Jayant has developed a unique style of music by experimenting with all these genres. He works with what moves him emotionally and translates that experience into his own, eclectic electronic sound.\r\nEven though these genres give a fundamental idea of his work, you still cannot characterize what you really experience and feel at his shows. It is indescribable in words alone, you just have to come, listen and see for yourself.\r\nJiiter is a Live/Dj Minimal & Techno act by Jayant. The Sound of Jitter is very edgy, hi-tech and psychedelic in nature, almost bridging the gap between outdoor and club.','jayant@jmusic.in','https://www.facebook.com/Jitterlive','http://www.jmusic.in','','','0','166',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 13:11:38',296,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','jayant-jitter'),(1140,0,0,0,'AURA','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/AURA/147257675349605','','','','147257675349605','166',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','aura'),(1141,0,0,0,'PrayaQ','','+91-9993546363','http://www.facebook.com/prayaq','','','','116495265107877','166',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','prayaq'),(1142,0,0,0,'The Yellow Pages','The Yellow Pages was started in 2005 by Gaurav  Jagwani and Simran Talreja with the common interest of exciting audiences all around with a unique acoustic take on modern and classic rock hits. Initially, the band started off as a cover band but today takes pride in having written plenty of songs on their own. \n\nWith a range of influences from the classic bands such as The Doors & Pink Floyd to the more modern bands such as Oasis and Coldplay, The Yellow Pages gigs will mesmerize you with not only their covers but also their original psychedelic acoustic music. With a series of guests accompanying them at times, their gigs arent to be missed. ','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Yellow-Pages/106638992699005','','','','106638992699005','165',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-yellow-pages'),(1143,0,0,0,'Teddy Boy Kill','???? TEDDY BOY KILL IS TECHNOLOGIC BEAT PUNK ? NEOTERIC ELECTRO MUSIC ? THE PREMIER AUDIO BLITZKRIEG ? MUSIC TO THRILL - LIVE SKILL ? WE DONT BEAT BONGOS & TABLAS ? WE DONT MOCK ? AUDIO SHOCK ? BOT ROCK ! Rising out of the usual clutter and clam of electronic music in India, Teddy Boy Kil