163',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','undefined-human'),(1145,0,0,0,'Shanren','Formed in 2000 in the remote and mysterious Yunnan province of southwest China, the region thought to have inspired the Shangri-la of James Hiltons classic novel Lost Horizon, Shanren, literally mountain men, have become one of Chinas top indie folk bands. With members representing some of Chinas 56 ethnic groups, including the Wa and Buyi ethnic minorities from Yunnan and Guizhou, the four-piece aims to promote and preserve the colorful and diverse heritage of Yunnan and Guizhous many ethnic minority tribes through original compositions and reworkings of local folk melodies.\n\nShanren fuse indigenous music with rock, reggae, and ska, while showcasing a variety of traditional instruments such as the xiangzi and qinqin (four-stringed plucked instruments) and xianggu (a type of drum). Gaining popularity in Beijings small but vibrant alternative folk scene on the strength of their energetic live shows, the band appeared in front of 5,000 people in Cathedral Square at the Barcelona Festival Asia 2010. In 2011, Shanren performed at MIDEM in Cannes and Liverpool Sound City, UK. They are staple headliners at Chinas major music festivals and have been featured twice on Hunan Television, reaching an audience in the tens of millions. Wild, eccentric, and charismatic, Shanren are true ambassadors for Chinas ethnic diversity and emerging musical creativity.\n\n2009 saw the release of their self-titled debut, and the band is currently recording the follow-up, to be released in early 2012.\n\nHIGH RES PHOTO DOWNLOAD: http://dl.dropbox.com/u/3333970/shanren/shanren%20photos.rar\n\nPress for Shanren:\nEthinic Music Tests the Limits in China, The New York Times \nhttp://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/17/world/asia/17music.html\n\nChinese Indie-Folk Band Shanren Uses Crowdfunding to Connect with Fans for North American Tour, Crowdsourcing.org\nhttp://www.crowdsourcing.org/document/chinese-indie-folk-band-shanren-uses-crowdfunding-to-connect-with-fans-for-north-american-tour-/11090\n\nResponse to Times Piece, World Music Network\nhttp://www.worldmusic.net/news/news/2011-09-21/ethnic-music-tests-limits-in-china/\n\nFolk Explosion, Time Out Beijing (PDF)\nhttp://jenniferconrad.org/folk1.pdf\n\nInterview, Kochipan (in French)\nhttp://kochipan.over-blog.com/article-interview-shanren-73397165.html\n\nInterview, Smart Shanghai\nhttp://www.smartshanghai.com/articles/nightlife/interview-shanren\n\nInterview, Pangbianr\nhttp://pangbianr.com/shan-ren-interview/\n\nLive Review, The Beijinger\nhttp://www.thebeijinger.com/blog/2011/12/19/Weekend-Live-Music-Reviews-Hanggai-Shanren\n\n\nLinks:\nRocketHub: http://rockethub.com/projects/5431-shanren-tour-shangri-la-to-north-america\n\nSoundCloud: http://soundcloud.com/shanren\n\n','unitysam@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/shanrenband','','','','317592468268482','162',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','shanren'),(1146,0,0,0,'Requiem','','','http://www.facebook.com/Ontologus','','','','126507464093552','162',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','requiem'),(1147,0,0,0,'Grossty','swinery is lavatory','','http://www.facebook.com/Grossty','','','','123217304451132','162',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','grossty'),(1148,0,0,0,'Short Round','My music is a selection of songs played most when busking on the streets of England. A majority of my original material has also been written on, or about, the very streets on which I play. Back to the honest grass-root basics. But just because it\'s all acoustic it doesn\'t mean it\'s necessarily going to be quiet. Yay folk rock! My music sounds a bit like folksy-rocksy-bippity-boppity-curry-curry-curry.\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Short-Round/261029203907337','','','','261029203907337','162',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','short-round'),(1149,0,0,0,'Spliff','','','http://www.facebook.com/musicbyspliff','','','','311629965542109','159',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','spliff'),(1150,0,0,0,'Seed Of Changes','Seed of Changes was formed in 2009 as a four piece band and has played in couple of gigs around the city of Bangalore mostly influenced by Pink Floyd, Dire Straits, Eric Clapton and Jimi Hendrix. Seed of Changes aims at creating soulful music that can be felt rght from the heart with a blues fyl.','','http://www.facebook.com/seedofchangesband','','','','105053652876758','157',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','seed-of-changes'),(1151,0,0,0,'The Underknowns','Not much is known about The Underknowns. \n\nWell, they\'re not in it for the fame anyway. You might be forgiven for thinking they aren\'t in it for the money either (they were once billed \'the underpaids\' though that particular name didn\'t quite roll off the tongue as nicely) but they foolishly continue to hope to be adequately compensated for the efforts in the future. \n\nDubious sources have revealed that the subjects in question were tinkering with the idea of forming some sort of a partnership back in 1944 when they were brought together by Lt Aldo Raine. After defeating the fascist forces, they ran through several alternate career options before reconvening in 2011, in a last ditch effort to reverse the aging process.\nThe attempted alchemy may or may not have worked but it seemingly provoked semi-musical tendencies.  We have no further information regarding this particular mutation nor are we responsible for what is to follow.\n\nRumour has it, however, that this just might be.. Possibly the best band you\'ve never heard','Mark Aranha 9899588626','http://www.facebook.com/TheUnderknowns','','','','234728986591712','156',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-underknowns'),(1152,0,0,0,'Abhijit singh','music for me is way to express myself. pink floyd and porcupine tree are the two bands i\'m greatly inspired by. this is just a solo attempt to bring out what i play, just by my self and its not too elaborate and maybe never will be. i enjoy slower ambient music with a lot of guitar work and thats what i will try to play! :)','','http://www.facebook.com/abhijitsinghjds','','','','113703392037315','154',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','abhijit-singh'),(1153,0,2,2,'Necrocomium','Necrocomium was formed in fall 2011 by two fellow brothers and Death Fanatics to keep \'The Cult Of Death\' alive with some true, uncompromising, rancid, primitive death metal onslaught, an art form abandoned and forgotten!\n\nNecrocomium are currently working on their untitled debut materials, Ancient Demo shall be unleashed soon!','necrocomiumdeathmetal@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/necrocomium','','','','236411786386332','154',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','necrocomium'),(1154,0,0,0,'Switch Bitch','','Nikhil: (+91) 9958752275, Mail: switch3itch@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/switch3itch','','','','202607813125423','153',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','switch-bitch'),(1155,0,0,0,'Vitamin M','Anant  Drums and Percussion\n\nAnant has over 10 years of experience in music specifically in rhythm section. This includes seven years in drums and three years in Tabla.\nHe has played at various live concerts with different bands and artists with music style ranging from indian classical to soft rock, classic rock, hard rock, progressive and alternate rock.\nA hardcore mad man on the drums when let loose, Anant can take even the most complicated of rhythms and seamlessly roll it into one of his gut-wrenching drum solos.\nCurrenlty Anant plays professionally as a drummer for bands Highway61, Vitamin M, Moon Beans, Crosswired and Harmonic Recession. He was actively involved in recording songs at Sound Ideaz Studio, Pune for these bands by playing drum parts for the same. He has more than a year of teaching experience.\nMuang  Guitars\nMuang is a certified Grade 8 guitarist from Trinity College London in Classical guitar (theory & practical) under Pune Music Society. He graduated B.Mus from Spicer Memorial College.  He specializes in Hard Rock and Blues playing styles. He is also a composer. Muang has more than 15 years experience of playing guitar in classical, rock & blues. In 2006 he won best guitarist at Inter college rock band competition conducted by IIPM. He is a well known guitar teacher as well. He teaches Classical guitar and Plectrum guitar for Trinity music students in Pune.\nHe was part of the band Gamma Companion. It was the 1st bands to be featured on the Radio\nMirchi Pune?s show - Mirchi Soundcheck. He is playing with his current band (Vitamin M). His favorite musicians are: Bob James (FourPlay), Chuck Berry, B.B King, Jeff Beck, Jimmy Page, Jimi Hendrix, Eric Clapton, RitchieBlackmore, Stevie Ray Vaughan, Eric Johnson. Paul Gilbert, Malmsteen, Shawn Lane, Joe Satriani, Steve Vai, John Petrucci, Steve Morse, Greg Howe, John Myer and etc.\nHe likes Blues, Hard Rock, Jazz and Classical Music.Favorite composers: J.S.Bach, Handel, Paganini, Beethoven, Mozart, Isaac Albeniz, FernandoSor, F. Carulli, M. Carcassi, F. Tarrega, Yani, Kenny G, Michael Jackson, Joe Satriani, and Steve Vai, etc\nMangpu  Bass\nMangpu started playing guitar since he was 6 years old. He has been playing Bass guitar for 6 years.  He loves playing Country music, Blues, Rock, Rock N Roll and Metal. Before he came to Pune he played with his local band (Teu Vit Vit). Since he came to Pune he has been playing with his college bands.  Currently he is playing with Vitamin M. \nHis favorite musicians are: Billy Sheehan, John Myung, Stu Hamm, Michael Anthony, Nathan East, Gene Simmons (Kiss), and Hugh McDonald (Bon Jovi).\nFavorite bands: The Eagles, Mr. Big, Dream Theater, Fire House, Skid Row.\n\n\n\n\nRishi  Vocals and Guitars\n\nRishi started playing professionally in 1999, and formed the first Hard Rock / Metal band in Nashik called Stubborn Brains. He has been composing ever since and is also a part of RUCKUS (Mumbai based Rock Band).\n\nHe loves to compose songs that are more on the lines of  tickling your funny bone or bones and mixing Blues and Rock with Fun Lyrics and getting the crowd to sing along, one such composition is The Tortilla Song, (Official Video on Youtube).\n\nNow with Vitamin M, he plans to do the same with originals to get you of your seat and also do covers from Bands like SRV, Tenacious D, CCR, Chickenfoot, Skin, Airbourne, and more.  \n\n\n\n\n\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Vitamin-M/181626631850316','','','','181626631850316','153',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','vitamin-m'),(1156,0,0,0,'Acoustic Kult','','acoustickult@me.com','http://www.facebook.com/acoustickult','','','','143990709007564','152',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','acoustic-kult'),(1157,0,0,0,'Ekam Satyam Band','EkamSatyam is a music band from the heart of Delhi. We write and compose our own songs on social issues. The essence of EkamSatyam is  The one truth. The one truth indisputably being music. \nMusic is a reflection for us, a language for us to communicate  with people who understand us and who don\'t, an idea for everyone to be able to sense the ecstasy of life. We express with music, learn and teach with music, convey ideas and messages with music and interact with music\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Ekam-Satyam-Band/178334048875991','','','','178334048875991','152',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ekam-satyam-band'),(1158,0,3,1,'Manta Sidhu ft. MAP','Representing Alternative Pop styles in composition and disposition, Delhi-based band MAP seeks to accentuate the brilliance of open spaces in sound - all musical elements merged together in a carefree environment, while standing vulnerable in all their rawness. Subtle in expression, minimalist in essence, easy on the ear - what lies in pursuit is a treat for the all-embracing music lover.\r\n\r\nThe band is led by singer-songwriter Manta Sidhu, whose experiments as an artist delve into the luxury of being instinctive, intrusive and indulgent all at once - where music is uncomplicated and comprehensible as we all know it and love it. Accompanying her is Jishnu Banerjee on Guitar, Abhishek Mangla on Bass and, Reuben Narain on Drums. \r\n','map.mantasidhu@gmail.com ','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Manta-Sidhu-ft-MAP/254443694618226','','','','254443694618226','151',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','manta-sidhu-ft-map'),(1159,0,0,0,'ONE MAN CLAN','well when bands and stuff don work out this is the only option....its not tht i ain good enough to have a band....its jus tht my luck doesnt seem to favour when m in a band....','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/ONE-MAN-CLAN/125175247583546','','','','125175247583546','149',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','one-man-clan'),(1160,0,0,0,'D-Code','D-Code is an Experimental/Christian-Rock band from Kohima, Nagaland formed on the month of December 2011. The band holds a concept of positivity in their music to bring a change and to spread with the message enclosed in the songs. The band strongly believes that with positivity one can make music a reason to live.\nThe band consists of five members who has been partly into the metal scene in the past.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/D-Code/334222573266149','','','','334222573266149','148',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','d-code'),(1161,0,0,0,'Tank Girl','TANK GIRL is a band with 2 members of the best known DIY punk band in Nepal, RAI KO RIS. The Line up is : Sareena Rai (from Rai Ko Ris): bass guitar,vocals. Sampreety Gurung : Guitar,backing vocals. Olivier Bertin (also from Rai Ko Ris): drums. Tank girl has been doing many benefit gigs in Nepal for women\'s rights,women foundation etc.Most of their songs describe the exploitation,hatred,sexism,domestic violence,unequality etc against the women in the Nepalese community.Thus the band being an anarcha-feminist foundation.\nTank Girl / Rai ko ris has also set up an Anarchist infoshop known as \"The Infoshop\" in Kathmandu Nepal.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Tank-Girl/130901016939240','','','','130901016939240','148',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','tank-girl'),(1162,0,74,74,'The Incredible MindFunk','Fresh out of the oven, The Incredible MindFunk is a Delhi/Gurgaon based project . Though new to the circuit, the idea had been floating around for a while with Siddhant, Amar and Ranajoy jamming occasionally. And just like any clichd story, they wanted to take it a step further, thus bringing on Amira to complete the lineup. \r\n\r\n\r\nCONTACT US - \r\nPhone-9810048237\r\nEmail - sid_thrashing@hotmail.com\r\n\r\nor hit any of us up on facebook....','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Incredible-MindFunk/115372355236005','','','','115372355236005','148',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-incredible-mindfunk'),(1163,0,0,0,'Terminal Laceration','','','http://www.facebook.com/terminal.laceration','','','','191768800895768','145',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','terminal-laceration'),(1164,0,0,0,'OverCome HC','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/OverCome-HC/246616975351897','','','','246616975351897','145',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','overcome-hc'),(1165,0,0,0,'AnthraMorphia','It all began with Advik and Pritish , at their places , jammin on Hangar18 and Holy Wars just for fun... 2011 began with Asif\'s advent into the band. At that time , the trio didn\'t have a name for the band yet , as it was still incomplete. But started jamming together, nevertheless, on some Cannibal Corpse and Obscura. Then somewhere in mid \'11 , enter Abhimanue and own compositions were on progress. By the end of may , they get a chance to gig at Unseen Underground but were without a drummer.. Pulling a couple strings here and there , the band got Sidharth to fill in for drumming and the gig went on. \n\nAfter the first gig , the band went on a hibernation for a few months. With Abhimanue outta the scene cause some of urgent work that had come up ,things weren\'t looking too good. But to keep something going , the band signed in for a Black Sabbath Tribute and were with the idea of playing Sabbath songs in their own Death Metal way. They got Kaustub to fill in for drums and Michael for the lead. \n\nThe band then decided to use programmed drumming for any further gigs\nuntil they find someone who can keep up.\nAnd now they\'re upto individual training , coming up with something more promising and HEAVIER. Watch out for them this December...','Asif : +919677249516 / Pritish : +919840082096 or email us @  anthramorphia1@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/anthramorphia','','','','185080328191947','144',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','anthramorphia'),(1166,0,0,0,'Monkey Skull','Monkey skull is a 3 piece experimental band from Manipal, India that started in January 2011. The band was started with the intention of making music that people could connect to without compromising with the sound stuck in our heads. We prefer playing music we make more than covering songs and like to create our own little sonic environment that we can slip into at any point of time. \nThe music we play is sort of hard to classify into one particular genre though we tend to gravitate towards a more psychedelic and progressive sound. We like to experiment with our songwriting and our outlook towards music through extremely random jam sessions and from taking inspiration from things we see and hear around us.\nwe have performed at the following venues-\n\nRevels 2011- Manipal\n\nIncident 2011 - NIT Suratkal (Best bassist - Akshay Ramesh)\n\nVortex(manipal leg) - Manipal\n\nPub Rock Fest \'11 - Manipal\n\nMAFIA Carnival - Manipal\n\nSaarang 2011 (Powerchords finalists) - Chennai\n\nArticle 19 Unplugged - Manipal\n\nManipal Music Fest(eliminations) - Manipal\n\nPre-Revels \'12 - Manipal','Obzen the friendly penguin.','http://www.facebook.com/monkeyskullband','','','','153654534689844','143',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','monkey-skull'),(1167,0,0,0,'Skinny Alley','Skinny Alley is one of the most respected and critically acclaimed bands in contemporary Indian music. \n\nThe band has played to diverse crowds in every possible venue, from college campuses to plush clubs, coffee houses to football stadiums, and a gangsters rooftop to car parks filled with tobacco-chewing truckers. With the musicians having been on the road together since the early 1980s, this is more than a band. This is a collective. The music of Skinny Alley reflects this richness of spirit and experience. This is a new sound and it is here to stay.\n\nSkinny Alley has collaborated with Amit Chatterjee, Louiz Banks, Ranjit Barot, Carl Clements, Gino Banks, Ehsaan Noorani and Loy Mendonsa to name a few.','','http://www.facebook.com/skinnyalley','','','','115214361882327','142',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','skinny-alley'),(1168,0,0,0,'Kerioth.','Kerioth,the band only started there journey in the may of 2011 and in july,they caught eyes in the Yamaha Asian Beat band competition.Apart from good response to their music style,their guitarist Victtor Dey was awarded the Best Guitarist award and won a Yamaha Guitar.Their old drummer left the band just 3 weeks before the competition and they had to search for a good drummer in that short time.fortunately they succeeded and performed well enough to get the second place.now the band is working on their new compositions that are to be launched soon.','Ratul-9836920047. sankalan-8981511483,victtor-9831755253,subhojit-8981252596','http://www.facebook.com/Kerioth','','','','128658723886764','138',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','kerioth'),(1169,0,0,0,'Sidd & His Self-Esteem','Sidd & His Self-Esteem are 4-piece S\'pore rock n\' roll band whose live sound is like a Police record heard through the window of a shitty hotel room assaulting your ears after endless repeats of Pearl Jam bootlegs turned up over a Velvet Underground cover band.','Jonathan Kang (65) 9752 8369','http://www.facebook.com/the.self.esteem','','','','255990487916','136',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sidd-his-self-esteem'),(1170,0,0,0,'Rajarshi \'Coco\' Mukherjee','','','http://www.facebook.com/rajarshiofficial','','','','266082063421978','136',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rajarshi-coco-mukherjee'),(1171,0,0,0,'Paranoid Earthling','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Paranoid-Earthling/105175436205425','','','','105175436205425','135',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','paranoid-earthling'),(1172,0,0,0,'The Fourth Floor.','It all started when paras,jatin,tapas,abhay used to jam, covering bands like lamb of god,children of bodom,metallica,opeth,junoon, etc. but without a vocalist we were still pulling it off.we were pissed with the same old situation,and after jamming with some vocalists, finally we approached kaushik handoo a die hard junoon & Ustad Nusrat fateh ali khan fan,and a great singer, he joined us in the first week of feb..(2011)..\nThe Fourth Floor was formed with a simple plan of playing and making music,with an idea of taking this project further,the band performed for the first time on 19th feb 2011 in our college fest(Chitkara University)...','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Fourth-Floor/194552483907652','','','','194552483907652','134',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-fourth-floor'),(1173,0,2,2,'Dhwani','Dhwani the name itself signifies sound. Music is in every subtle thing of this world. Wind, water, fire are the basic elements which have made the possiblity of life on our planet and they too have their respective dhwani \r\nIn our music we combine the three basic elements the wind, water and fire.\r\nDhwani has the very essence of folk music fused with new age soft rock having base of hindustani classical music preserving the very fragrance of the land where we come from. We have various styles ranging from folk, hindustani, fusion, new age rock and soft metal. We have our new genere and we call it as club hindustani having a new style where hindustani music gets fused with the new age electronics.\r\n\r\nSo come and listen to dhwanis music and you will find all the three elements combined together','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Dhwani-THE-BAND/344593298904248','','','','0','134',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dhwani'),(1174,0,0,0,'Hatched','','','http://www.facebook.com/hatchedbangalore','','','','227957913887130','129',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','hatched'),(1175,0,0,0,'The Vicious Circle','\'The Vicious Circle\', is a honest translation of the life we live...The Maze with no exit, no reward and no place to hide. \n\nMay it be, The Vicious Circle of our system, our relationships or the events that occur in each of our lives.\n\n\'The Vicious Circle\' is a Hindi Rock Band that makes an attempt to project it\'s deep rooted hatred in negative politics, indifference and \'in-the-face\' double standards which are flatly destroying life, especially in this country. \n\nThe songs have simple and truthful lyrics about the \'Obvious\' and \'In your Face\' issues. These range from Corruption to Indifference to Child Abuse to Failed relations.\nThey are simple and straight forward, written in basic Hindi, for which one doesn\'t need to open up the dictionary nor consult an Urdu expert.\n\nOne will realize as the songs go by, that what we are singing, is exactly what YOU are thinking..\n\nThe band performs with the sole purpose of reaching out and putting forth their blunt message, rather than indulging in the pool of materialistic politics.\n\nIt is an earnest hope that in this quest for reaching out, someone, somewhere, understands the true meaning of \'The Vicious Circle\', retrospects and makes the first attempt to break out, within.','9769863331','http://www.facebook.com/theviciouscircleband','','','','179252518766014','125',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-vicious-circle'),(1176,0,0,0,'Ispat','the band was officially formed in 2009, by three friends sahitya, manish and sunny. Main focus of the band was to play metal.The band received a very good response from the local audience. initially the bands\'s music consisted of Sepultura and Lamb of god covers.the band faced many problems, some of the new members departed. The line up finally stabilized in the end of year\n 2011. ISPAT is going to release its first debut album by the end of year 2012. ','','http://www.facebook.com/ispat.official','','','','289173027819270','125',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ispat'),(1177,0,0,0,'Silence Fest II - Vader in Nepal (2011)','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Silence-Fest-II-Vader-in-Nepal-2011/255779631135278','','','','255779631135278','123',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','silence-fest-ii-vader-in-nepal-2011'),(1178,5,1,80,'Swaggamuffin','Joel \'Swaggamuffin\' Paes is originally from Goa, India, has always loved a wide range of musical styles from offbeat sounds to commercial hits as well as classics like The Rat Pack and Ella Fitzgerald. \r\nHaving been privileged enough to travel and live all over the globe from London to New York and from Sydney to Kenya; he has soaked in the sights and sounds of the world and is now ready to unleash his brand of madness upon Middle Earth with his quirky take on Drum & Bass, Dubstep, Grime, Funky House, Progressive and Psychedelic Trance.\r\n\r\nLets rewind to the 7th of January 2011, when he played his 1st club night in New Delhi to a house full ZOOK (Saket) alongside the legendary Box of Matchbox Collective & Praxis of BassFoundation. \r\n\r\nThe stage had been set for the beginning of something epic and that raw love for music and performing to packed clubs continues till date. Since then Swaggamuffin has gone on to found the highly successful TRIPPY TUESDAYs alongside DJ Chris, a mid week bass assault on the senses featuring established and budding local DJs and Percussionists. \r\n\r\n\r\nSome of the talent featured at TRIPPY TUESDAYS were  \r\n\r\n\r\nDJ Lusid (Goa/Holland)  Psy trance/progressive, Dubstep, urban hippie.\r\n\r\nAsh (Delhi)  The fastest hands on a Djembe in Delhi and member of DelhiDrumCircle.\r\n\r\nDJ Ben (Boston)  Progressive/Dub step/Dub and lots of Flying Lotus.\r\n\r\nDJ Chris (Delhi)  Dubstep/DnB/Psy Trance/Tech/Breaks/Commercial.\r\n\r\nDhruv Saffi (Delhi)  Percussionist extraordinaire, Keyboard/Djembe.\r\n\r\nMc Risk (New York)  Very gifted Rapper and Producer destined for greatness. \r\n\r\nDJ MoCity (Iraq/New Delhi)  Founder of UFO Entertainment, AfterShock Records and The Reggae Rajahs, He gets more google hits than Facebook. Real talk.\r\n\r\nRaidon (New Delhi)  Gifted young Drum&bass/Dubstep producer .\r\n\r\nMc Kaztet D (France)  International French rapper/producer and all round nice guy.\r\n\r\nDiggy Dang (London/New Delhi)  MC, Vocalist, Bass player, Member of the Ska Vengers and 1/3 of The Reggae Rajahs .\r\n\r\nQuantonic (Russia)  Psy-Trance DJ/Producer extrodinaire.\r\n\r\nDoktor Daniel (New Delhi)  Tech/house/progressive/Dubstep wiz kid.\r\n\r\nDJ Aaron James (NY/New Delhi) - Legend.\r\n\r\nUnconventional Science (L.A) - The original mad scientist.\r\n\r\nDivij K (New Delhi) - House, Tech, Electro\r\n\r\nKartek (New Delhi) - Resident Selekta at FBar Delhi.\r\n\r\nLeon Russell (Bombay/New Delhi) - 1 half of the epic Toyz In Panic duo & partner at Dazzle on Records.\r\n\r\nDJ Manu Flintrop (Goa/Germany)  Shiva Valley Pre Album Launch Party at Trippy Tuesdays\r\n\r\nUnconventional Science (LA)  Album Launch & Asia Tour Party\r\n\r\nSpiral Viral (New Delhi)  Our in house Visual pundit.\r\n\r\nUltra Violet (New Delhi)  A budding domestic DJ\r\n\r\nShahkar Siddique (New Delhi)  Our back up VJ & now the Blue Frog (New Delhi) resident VJ. \r\n\r\n---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nSwaggamuffin has also been featured as a guest artist at most of the prominent clubs in New Delhi and for some of the biggest organisers/nights around, such as \r\n\r\nAI (Love Hotel)  Blockbusters alongside DJ Danindie (Spain)\r\n\r\nAI (Love Hotel)  Blockbusters for IGlows UV party\r\n\r\n24/7 (The Lalit Hotel)  with Diggy Dang (UK/Delhi) of the Reggae Rajahs\r\n\r\nForgetful Elephant  Marquee Nights with DJ Shahab (Iran) and DJ Gagan (Delhi)\r\n\r\nBugaloo  Charity Party organized by Padja\r\n\r\nTLR Caf (Hauz Khas Villge)  with Su-Real (Canada/Delhi)\r\n\r\nBugaloo  Marquee Nights with DJ Shahab (Iran) and DJ Gagan (Delhi)\r\n\r\nThe Zoo (Garden of 5 senses)  Euro Nights\r\n\r\nS-Lounge  Marquee Nights with DJ Shahab\r\n\r\nShooters Caf  Euro Nights with DJ Chris (Delhi)\r\n\r\nPlutos Caf  Launch Party with DJ Chris (Delhi)\r\n\r\nPlutos Caf  with DJ Miki (Ethiopia)\r\n\r\nZook  Weird Wednesdays with DJ Ben (Boston)\r\n\r\nZook  Imported Go(o)ds with Box (Poland) of Matchbox Collective & Praxis (UK) of BassFoundation\r\n\r\nForgetful Elephant  Sound in Motion Launch Party with DJ Shahab (Iran) and DJ Chris (Delhi)\r\n\r\nCaf 27  Private event organized by Padja\r\n\r\nNews Caf  Flipping Fridays with DJ Ben (Boston) and Ash on Djembe\r\n\r\nCorona Monsoon Project Pool Party (Parkland Exotica, New Delhi)  alongside Doktor Daniel\r\n\r\nRamada Plaza Pool Party  with DJ MIKI (Ethiopia) and Dj Rohan (France)\r\n\r\nCaf 27  with DJ Rohan (France) & Aaron James (New York)\r\n\r\nSsky Bar & Lounge  alongside Aaron James (New York) and VJ Spiral Viral (London/New Delhi/Goa)\r\n\r\nFio, Garden of 5 senses  Magic Moments Vodka Launch Party with Dualist Inquiry (LA/New Delhi)\r\n\r\nThe ZOO, Garden of 5 senses  alongside Dualist Inquiry (LA/New Delhi) and VJ Spiral Viral (London/New Delhi/Goa)\r\n\r\nBass Camp Festival at Out Of The Box - with JazzSteppa (UK), Delhi Sultanate (India) & Bay Beat Collective (India)\r\n\r\nWills India Fashion Week, New Delhi.\r\n\r\nThe Double Bass Tour Launch Party at Zook - Diggy Dang (UK/India) & Raidon (UK/India)\r\n\r\nSound Therapy at Aqua, The Park Hotel\r\n\r\nHalloween Crawl 2011 at ZOOK- With Jatin Puri, Dualist Inquiry & Order Of The Essence (B.R.E.E.D + Nucleya)\r\n\r\nTLR Caf  The Future #4 with DJ MoCity (Iraq/New Delhi), Dualist Inquiry (LA/New Delhi) and VJ Spiral Viral (London/New Delhi/Goa)\r\n\r\nBacardi NH7 Festival 2011  2nd artist to play after the festival opened and part of the core team behind the conceptualization, management and organization of the Pepsi Dub Station Stage.\r\n\r\nPsy Fri (Soshio Lounge)  Opened for world famous trance DJ Psykovsky for the launch of his Dubstep project Lob Zany\r\n\r\nOut Of The Box (Haus Khaz Village)  Launch & New Years Eve Party 2011\r\n\r\nSpring On The Ridge Festival for Escape Delhi\r\n\r\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nMEDIA SAMPLES\r\n\r\n\r\nSoundcloud \r\n\r\nhttp://soundcloud.com/swaggamuffin\r\n\r\n\r\nMixCloud\r\n\r\nhttp://www.mixcloud.com/joel-swaggamuffin-paes/\r\n\r\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nCONTACT INFORMATION\r\n\r\n\r\nTo catch the madman at work or for bookings and inquiries, either visit him at his regular Tuesday night gig, TRIPPY TUESDAYS at ZOOK (Saket) or check