nderlying root of the bands unique sound. Bearing the responsibilities of being the bands lead guitarist and bass player, he puts in a lot of effort to smoothen out the rough edges of the bands music. Yohans style involves a blend of melodic acoustic progressions gelled with heavy riffage further fused with vibrant solos. \n\nRueban is the architect of the bands music. He bears the responsibilities of being the drummer, vocalist and lyricist for the band. His vocal styles involve a variable  and his range of warm to crunch singing and his drumming style adds to a tighter and more definitive sound to the bands music.\n\nOnslaughts sound is new age alternative music interlaced with ambient overtones. The band strictly follows on lyrically sharing a positive message that upholds Christian values.','onslaught.india@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/onslaughtindia','','','','166030856753857','110',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','onslaught'),(1184,0,0,0,'Khadki Junction Blues','Khadki Junction Blues was formed when a group of young musicians in \ncollege with varying influences decided to merge their creativity into a band. \n\nBopodi Love Affair, Khadki Junction Blues Demo Album, \nRecorded, Mixed and Produced By Karan Kulkarni and Co-Produced By \nBhrigu Sahni at Gimmix Productions, was released in December 2006. \n\nKhadki Junction Blues consists of musicians that listen to and play different \nstyles of music, bringing these individuals together to form a band has \ncreated a different sound, some call it fusion, others call it funk, some \nthink its the blues and others think its just good ol rock. But we like to \ncall it music, Khadki Junction Blues Style !!! \n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Khadki-Junction-Blues/9825588865','','','','9825588865','108',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','khadki-junction-blues'),(1185,0,0,0,'Kshya Kramasha (official)','Formerly called DnQ(Drawn and Quartered), the band was formed in December 2009 in New Delhi and have witnessed radical variances since then. The band is currently recording their debut EP in India with Ujwal Kashyap and in American with Mike Menocker (Silent Owl Studios.)....... In much short time, Kshya Kramasha has successfully augmented a respectable representation in the domestic circuit and beyond with its forcible yet subtle compositions.\n_____________________\nSome past achievements:\n\nWinners of fort rock@LBSIM\nPlayed @The Last drop cafe\nHeadlined battle of bands 2010@DIT\nHeadlined battle of bands 2010 (garden of 5 senses)\nHeadlined MIARAJ\'10 DIT dehradoon\nHeadlined Woodstock\'10 YMCA winners of RXC\'10 @ jamia hamdard\nHMR Hell Gates \'10 - Runners up, Best vocalist and best guitarist\nJamia Millia University pheonix \'10 - Winners\nPlayed @ chicane Noida @ hysteria\'10\nHeadlined Exuberence\'10 apparel house\nRunners up at DCAC Delhi University 2010\nHeadlined dream rock concert rajori garden 2010\nRagnarock DAICT gandhi nagar\nBlizzard of Rock - IIM Ahemdabad\nSecond runnerup\'s @Crosswinds\'10 IT-BHU\nAnugoong \'09 IBS noida (held @ hansdwani pragati maidan) - Winners\nConfluence \'09 Delhi university - winners\nHansraj college DU Commerce \'09 - Winners','','http://www.facebook.com/KshyaKramasha','','','','312598098788168','107',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','kshya-kramasha-official'),(1186,0,0,0,'Band Authority of Kanpur','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Band-Authority-of-Kanpur/143051692443117','','','','143051692443117','107',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','band-authority-of-kanpur'),(1187,0,0,0,'Stage Theory','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Stage-Theory/137441519656382','','','','137441519656382','103',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','stage-theory'),(1188,0,110,110,' INDIDGINUS','Indidginus, purveyor of quality riddims since 1996, specializes in dubstep, dub, dancehall and global bass music. His authentic, expressive and eminently danceable live performances draw on his diverse array of influences. Always a crowd pleaser, his incorporation of slide didgeridoo into his performances in an unusual and inspired take on the tribal instrument forms an integral part of his signature live sound.\r\n\r\nHis music is receiving critical acclaim and garnering widespread support from Bobby Friction (BBC Radio Asian Network), Nihal (BBC Radio 1), Sonny Ji (BBC Radio Asian Network), Tom Robinson (BBC Radio 6), Adrian Sherwood, DJ Fresh (5FM), Liquid Stranger, ill Gates, DimmSummer (High Chai Recordings), Greg Hunter, Red Bull Studios, Rod Azlan (Choice FM/Rinse FM) and Unity Radio amongst others.\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/indidginus.music','http://www.indidginus.com','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','indidginus'),(1189,0,91,91,'Tocadisco','Tocadisco celebrates over 15 years of international DJ stardom. After more than 150 international remixes, three artist albums and 30 successful worldwide singles, his success continues to grow with every gig, every record spun and every high profile remix.\r\n\r\nTheres no other producer in the current dance scene thats been able to produce as many wide-ranging, crossover hits as Tocadisco. Be it the much lauded remixes for Steve Aoki, Laidback Luke, Moby, Tiga, Pet Shop Boys or New Order amongst many others, or even the production, writing and execution of music for David Guetta, Kelis latest album Fleshtone, or Fischerspooners impressive back catalogue. Tocas work is far ranging, reaching and tickling the taste buds of DJs from across the musical spectrum, even gaining coveted spots on TV adverts broadcast across Europe.\r\n\r\nBack in 2008, Toca released his first solo album Solo and won an MTV Europe Music Award for Best Dance International.\r\n\r\nTocadiscos also a smitten, proud label owner of his imprint TOCA45. His core ethos is simple  to help support, promote and present the newest, freshest sounding club tracks available today. They all contain a mark of crossover potential. His unique, well-tought out and crossover style has once again come to the fray on ever-popular English house label Toolroom Knights, of which he mixed their installment of the successful Toolroom Knights compilation with British luminaire Chris Lake in 2010.\r\n\r\nThe Tocacabana Radio Show sees the big beats and heat of his renowned sound spread across weekly slots on stations around the world. Now confirmed to the schedule are more than 30 territories and stations within the big German\'s sights! It\'s represented perfectly within Toca\'s and his wife Nathizinha - who is also the head of their artist agency: MORUMBI BOOKING - new TOCACABANA event night. A fun fuelled, hot adventure that serves as a perfect remedy to those clubbers lacking summery, tech-drenched beats and bars. Celebrating their one year anniversary of TOCACABANA in 2011 the people enjoying and following the project are continually growing.\r\n\r\nIn 2011 Tocadisco\'s contract with the german label Superstar Recordings ended. He will now release the majority of his productions on his own label. Exciting times for Mr. Disco!\r\n\r\nIt wont be long until all corners of the globe are dancing to the sound of Tocacabana.','Alex Richter <info@lovetomusic.de>','http://www.facebook.com/tocadisco/info','http://www.tocadisco.com','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','tocadisco'),(1190,0,10,10,'Mux Mool','Mux Mool was born in Minnesota, but began his career in the New York City borough of Brooklyn, releasing his first tracks with Moodgadget in 2006.[1] In 2008, he released several EPs and had a track placed on the Ghostly Swim compilation assembled for Adult Swim by the label Ghostly International. His debut full-length, Skulltaste, followed in 2010.[2]','garrison@marchonemusic.com','http://www.facebook.com/muxmool/info','http://www.muxmool.com/','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','mux-mool'),(1191,0,2,2,'Sickflip','SICKFLIP is a collaborative and experimental solo project brought to life by Sarvesh Shrivastava, 20 year old music producer and DJ from Bombay (of Mental Martians fame with gigs in all the prime cities in India including Sunburn 2010 and 2011 )\r\n\r\nMusically, SICKFLIP ranges from Glitch hop, Dubstep, Drumstep, Experimental to Chill out. Making everything from Phat & Glitchy sounds to groovy smooth beats.\r\nHis styles are majorly influenced by artists like Bassnectar, Vent, Ill-Esha, Koan Sound, Skrillex, Trolley snatcha, Funtcase, Amon Tobin, Noisia and a lot more. \r\n\r\nTo make things more interesting behind the console, he plays a groovy blend of Glitch hop, Drumstep and Dubstep, along with Live Maschine samples, loops and sequences, keeping it fresh and distinct from usual DJ sets.\r\n\r\nKicks off this year with his upcoming EP on the Dutch label - Rub A Duck records (Black hole recordings) comprising of his original Experimental Dubstep track and a Remix by Relay & Front. \r\n\r\nHe intends to collaborate with other artists and work on his original Album which will be coming out later this year.','','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sickflip'),(1192,0,2,2,'Dale Anderson','Dale Anderson has brought his techno-tinged sound to more than fifty cities in twenty countries on four continents. As both a DJ and producer, Dale\'s musical diversity cuts across the deepest and darkest percussive house, to a tougher 4am club sound that borders the line between house and techno. \r\n\r\nA musician through and through, Dale is equally at home manning the controls in the studio as he is in the the dingiest of dimly lit low ceiling basement clubs or the main stage of an outdoor festival.\r\n\r\nAppearances at some of the the most widely respected clubs and parties in the world - Cocoon in Frankfurt, Ministry of Sound in London, the Miami Winter Music Conference etc. - has solidified his reputation as a consistent deliverer of quality.\r\n\r\nA British Canadian born in Vancouver, Dale got an early start at the height of the warehouse scene in the late nineties, playing rave parties in Canada and the US. As things developed, Dale migrated westward across the Atlantic to what was then the epicentre of the house scene, London England. It was here that his career began to take shape, as Dale played dates up and down the country - from Ministry of Sound in London, to Gatecrasher in Birmingham, Honey in Brighton to Digital in Bristol. As Dale\'s productions started to gain support from the international DJ community, his own DJ schedule blossomed. Dale was invited further afield to places like Eastern Europe, Central and South America, Asia, and beyond.\r\n\r\nIt was also in London where Dale met long time friend and production partner Anil Chawla. The duo\'s first ever track, \"Makes Me Feel\", was an instant hit, with Saved Records label boss Nic Fanciulli snapping it up for inclusion on his Renaissance compilation. Other labels took notice, and heavyweight Global Underground came calling, asking the boys to do a full length artist album. \"Roadhouse\" was released on Global Underground to critical acclaim from all the major dance music press, with DJ Mag calling it \"sparkling pro to-prog pop\" to IDJ who said that Dale and Anil had \"set the standard for 2009\".\r\n\r\nThe fourth track on the album \"Leftorium\" went on to be one of GU\'s biggest single releases ever, sitting in the top ten on the main Beatport chart for more than two months, and garnering a nomination for Best Deep House track in the Beatport Awards. Following on from this, Dale and Anil released the first ever GU Loopmasters Sample Pack, mixed the GU Classics compilation on GU Music, and joined the GU artist roster as resident DJs.\r\n\r\nAside from this, Dale has released more than forty original productions on labels like Nic Fanciulli\'s Saved Records, Fergie and Mr Henry Von\'s Tribal Rage, Nick Warren\'s Hope Recordings, Urban Torque and a host of others. With DJ support coming from tastemakers such as Carl Cox, Sasha, Laurent Garnier, Hernan Cattaneo and many more, Dale continues to stamp his sound on the scene. \r\n\r\nThese days Dale is based short term in Mumbai, where he is pushing the development of the house and techno scene in India, along with Anil Chawla and the boys at UnMute Agency. ','dev@unmute.in// +919999369935','http://www.facebook.com/DaleAndersonOfficial/info?ref=ts','http://www.twitter.com/daleanderson1','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dale-anderson'),(1193,0,0,0,'JAMES ZABIELA','Knowing what a great track should sound like - and the place it can be taken by warping and twisting it - is James Zabiela\'s forte. Layering different sounds with the aid of two Pioneer CDJ-2000s, a Pioneer EFX-1000, Korg Kaossilator, MIDI controller and a laptop, his hands and ears don\'t let up for a second, leaving any punters feet a-moving and mouth a-gap. Zabielas demands for such a kit wherever he spins is a reminder that he\'s one of the scant few DJs who\'s pushing things forward in 09. James\' style is trippy, bleepy and deeply - nay, downright - groovy. Oh, and watch out for a few gnarly basslines along the way, those nasty, dirty sounds are a part of JZ\'s signature now. Scratches, loops, and fluttering chord changes are all par for the course in a Zabiela set.\r\nNo wonder childhood idols Depeche Mode remain his heroes - like fellow tech-house don Mathew Bushwacka!, they all understand that the best electronic music moves both heart and feet. And if the magic\'s there, the spirit will fly as well. \"Entertainment and education are the key,\" nods James sagely. \"It\'s all about finding the balance. People have paid good money to have a party but you still need a balance.\" Which is why his effects unit is so crucial to his performance. \"Anyone can mix two records to a degree,\" he grins, while still admitting to the odd bout of nervousness during radio interviews if not behind the decks. \"But I\'m a hundred times more confident than I used to be. DJing has definitely helped my confidence as a person.\" Watching him play, its easy to forget that making things look easy takes time to perfect. Zabielas crossed a few bridges - and a few national boundaries - along the way. \"I haven\'t worked it all out yet,\" he adds. \"But I do wish I could grow an extra arm sometimes!\" \r\nJames\' career so far has been stratospheric to say the least. Swiftly snapped up by Sasha\'s Excession agency, he spent the next year taking on Eastern Europe, Australia, South America and the US of A, while still finding time to record well-received CDs for Renaissance and unleash a string of fine remixes along the way. Royksopp, Ladytron and progressive artists Spooky have all been under the Zabiela scalpel - and more are on their way. Pushing the envelope while still learning to cope with a real-life fan base and life on the other side of the record counter, its unlikely that James Zabiela will be taking a breather anytime soon. There are further late niteries like Tribal Sessions and Matter to entertain and regular slots in Romania and Budapest to attend to. On a recent trip to Argentina he played a five-hour set in front of 6,500 screaming punters at Moonpark in Buenos Aires. No wonder Sasha refers to James as the guv\'nor, This is still just the beginning.','','http://www.facebook.com/jameszabiela/info','http://www.jameszabiela.com','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','james-zabiela'),(1194,0,0,0,'DJ VAJRA','One of the most well rounded DJs in the music scene today, DJ Vajra has earned his place among the industry\'s elite. Whether he\'s dominating the biggest battles in the world, touring all over the globe, or crushing a mix set at the club, his presence is ever growing and undeniable.\r\n\r\nThe name Vajra strikes fear into the hearts of DJs in the battle realm. His skills have earned him many accolades, including becoming the 2011 DMC USA & WORLD Champion. He can also rock the party, and proved it by smashing the field during three Red Bull Thre3style victories. It\'s no wonder that legendary scratch icon DJ Q-Bert dubbed Vajra his \"favorite DJ in the world right now\".\r\n\r\nAudiences everywhere have been amazed by Vajra\'s live performances, blowing the roof off of venues from New York to LA, London to Madrid, Tokyo to Beijing, and everywhere in-between. He has shared the stage with The Roots in Amsterdam, De La Soul in Paris, and traveled across North America with A Tribe Called Quest. You can currently catch him on tour rocking one sold out show after another with Interscope / Shady Records\' superstar rapper YelaWolf.\r\n\r\nDJ Vajra whips dance floors into a frenzy, with his unique skill set of turntable tricks and original party blends. It doesn\'t matter whether it\'s Hip Hop, Dubstep, Top 40, Electro, or Funk, his versatile style can please any crowd.','','http://www.facebook.com/djvajra1/info','http://djvajra.com','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-vajra'),(1195,0,93,93,'Juliet Fox','Juliet Fox has been involved in music throughout most of her life. She is a dynamic DJ, Producer, & Radio Presenter. From the time she was taught to play the guitar & piano at a young age, only to discover later in life the musical area she would actually pursue. Her energetic attitude & versatile sets of all things house, is one not to miss.\r\n\r\nShe expresses herself through track selection and crowd interaction, and has become a favourite for Australian club nights, gigs and events over the past few years. Radio is also a massive part of Juliets career having co-hosted a radio show Freshly Squeezed which played every Friday Morning for 3 Yrs on 92.7 Fresh FM (Adelaide, Australia). Also hosting and DJing at FTV (Fashion TV) events throughout Australia, she is recognised not only for her marketing and promotional skills, but also her high quality DJ skills. She is also booked on a regular basis interstate when based in Australia, whilst also supporting some of the top DJs from around Australia and Internationally.\r\n\r\nLiving in Ibiza for the first time, for the 2010 summer, she quickly found herself playing at some of the major clubs & bars. A few of these included Bay Bar, Vodka Club, Martinas, Itaca, and also was involved with running a night at Hotel EsVive on a weekly basis.\r\n\r\nThen moving to Birmingham, UK after Ibiza, where she took to the music scene quickly gaining respect and a residency at two of the largest nights running there. IfU Want it, Bushwackers and FACE, Rainbow Warehouse. There she was also approached to launch her own Radio Show Attraction Radio on Manchester Global Radio (www.manchesterglobal.co.uk), which is aired on a bi-weekly basis, specialising in all things House.\r\n\r\nWithin one year of moving back to Australia, and over to her new home town Melbourne. Juliet has been seen to play for Gatecrasher in India, Planet Cream in Adelaide, Mbargo in Indonesia, Divine in Miami, and also a two week tour in India over NYE 2012 to play in Delhi, Bangalore, Chennai, and also GOA for the Krank Music Festival which was part of Global Under Ground, MOS & AXE. \r\n\r\n2012 looks to be a big year for Juliet with Music Production well on the way, and tracks recently being signed to Black Eye Records, EXAM, Beatdown Music, Bamboo, Purple Sun Records, and her own label Attraction Music which she launched mid 2011. Also gaining local residencies in less than 6 months at The Saint, Pretty Please, Rah Bar, Tramp, & OneSixOne, and also regular guest spots on Kiss FM (Melbourne, Australia). Juliet Fox is becoming well recognised as an International DJ and one to close watch.','','http://www.facebook.com/djjulietfox/info','http://www.julietfox.com','http://www.soundcloud.com/djjulietfox','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','juliet-fox'),(1196,0,0,0,'DJ SAN','SAN\'s productions have graced the turntables and mix CD\'s of pretty much every top DJ around the globe, either under his own name \'SAN\', or his \'Solid Sessions\' moniker. His Solid Sessions - Janeiro (Positiva UK) even made it to the top 10 in 11 countries. Now SAN is signed for the world by SONY Music (apart from ASIA, where he is signed to VIRGIN/ToCo). Summer 2011 is set for the worldwide release of SAN\'s artist album: \'Kiss of Life\'.\r\n\r\nSAN\'s productions have been featured on mix CD\'s by DJ\'s such as Armin Van Buuren, Tisto, Paul Van Dyk, Dave Seaman, Sasha, John Digweed, Deep Dish and Ferry Corsten. One of his ongoing supporters is the world\'s most popular DJ Tisto, who even asked SAN to do a remix for him! Tisto has supported all the releases that San did till this date and invited him to support him on his DJ sets in several countries.\r\n\r\nSAN has remixed Tisto, Ferry Corsten, Marco V, Dash Berlin and many more. His previous productions have been remixed by big name producers such as; Armin Van Buuren, Marco V, Dash Berlin, M.I.K.E., Kya & Albert, Rui da Silva, James Holden, Lemon 8 and Marc et Claude. The videoclip of SAN\'s single \'Nothing Remains the Same\', which included a remix from Ercola (Billboard dance #1 USA) won an award for best dance video at the Cravefest awards in Canada.\r\n\r\nIn 2010 SAN was tour-resident for Privilege (Ibiza) and also featured on their CD. He released an \'Unfold\' compilation, a SAN\'s Sessions compilation and has mixed the compilation for the worlds\' leading dance event; Sensation in Prague. This year he will release another SAN\'s Sessions CD through Virgin in Asia besides his artist album.\r\n\r\nAs a DJ SAN has residencies in Dubai (Vibe), Malta (Sunset Sundays), Germany (Ibiza Fucking Island) and Holland (Trance-Nation). He played in many other countries such as: Brasil, Argentina, Thailand, China, Japan, Colombia, Canada, UK, Holland, France, Spain, Czech Republic, Slovakia, Poland, Romania, Lithuania, Latvia, Russia, Malta, Turkey and Bulgaria. He played for organisations such as Creamfields, Sensation, Renaissance, Dancevalley, Ministry of Sound, Mysteryland and ','sophie.vandijck@sonymusic.com','http://www.facebook.com/djsanmusic/info','http://www.djsan.com','','','0','46407',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-san'),(1198,0,1,1,'Nerd Department','With several years of miscellaneous music experience behind them and partners-in-crime decided to reinvent their sound and call themselves the Nerd Department, between the two of them they have been actively pushing the House/Techno sound with their individual productions and DJ sets around the country. Both being part of the PureNoise Crew they joined forces recently to push and produce their rather selective take on grungy, gritty, in your face House & Techno music.\r\n\r\nFrom easy laid back disco grooves to hard hitting techno beats, their love for all forms House & Techno will be apparent in their productions in the Studio or there 4 deck style DJ sets. Being the analog fools they are, Nerd Department aims to geek out on their shiny toys both analog and digital to create an experience which is both intelligent and edgy.','','http://www.facebook.com/NerdDepartment/info','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','nerd-department'),(1199,0,2,2,'Under The Influence','Under The Influence is a two piece piano driven alternative band comprising of Abhijit Lahiri (vocals and lyrics) and Ashutosh Thatte (tunes and piano). Started in January 2010, the band\'s music is a melting pot of everything they love and listen to. From trip-hop, jazz and blues to funk, pop and electronica.','undertheinfluenceband.in@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/undertheinfluenceIN/info','http://www.undertheinflunceband.in','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','under-the-influence'),(1200,2,1,1,'RED Mawkin','Red is the color of warnings, emotions, roses, apples, cherries, blood and on and so on.. \r\nRED mawkin plays music rising from all of that one finds in RED. \r\nListen to the music and find out if it relates to any part of the RED in you. ','redmawkin@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/redmawkin/info','','','http://www.reverbnation.com/redmawkin','0','0',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-10 16:23:51',358,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','red-mawkin'),(1201,0,2,2,'Duncun Rufus','Stunning Debut album \'Carte Blanche\' from Mumbai outfit \'Duncun Rufus\'!\r\n\r\nDuncun Rufus makes soulful music. These are songs about hope, betrayal, desire & devotion in troubled times. Crisp contemporary pop-folk rock songs with foot tapping beats and catchy hook lines, this is music that you can truly feel when the sun rests and the night spreads itself out on the sky. This is music for journeys between where your love resides and where you are supposed to be. \r\n\r\nThe band is led by singer, songwriter Lima Yanger of Bliss Logic/Sleeping Buddha (Mumbai) and drummer Gaute Johannesen of Popface (Norway). The rest of this stellar ensemble is complimented by JD on Bass ( KK, Ashu, Bliss Logic) and Hitesh Dhutia \r\n(Junkt, Sleeping Buddha, Contraband, Rajiv Raja combine) on lead guitar and Vinay Lobo (Airport) on Guitars. \r\n\r\nThere are no carbon copies and duplicates here, the emphasis is simply about \"writing songs rather than composing technique laden musical pieces\" (Lima Y) and playing fresh music. \r\n\r\nAll hail the Republic of Duncania!\r\n\r\nSammy Saptarshi Bhattacharya.\r\n11.11','anishayanger@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/DuncunRufus/info','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','duncun-rufus'),(1202,0,0,0,'Business Class Refugess','Kartick & Gotam are a music group based in Indian and Israel, fusing local music from around the globe with electronic elements, dance and visual projections. \r\n\r\nSome press voices:\r\n\r\nBeautiful (Time Out)\r\n\r\n\"This is not only heavenly, it\'s beautiful\" (BBC)\r\n\r\nOutstanding electronic world music (Rolling Stone)\r\n\r\nA mlange of Indian and Western styles of music, left the crowd awestruck (Times of India)\r\n\r\nKartick & Gotam swept the crowd away, a scintillating performance (The Hindu)\r\n\r\nA musical journey that is utterly captivating, truly a global musical tapestry (World Music Central)\r\n\r\nGlobal in form and spirit, transcendentalindomitable energy, its core is Indian but with an unmistakable electro-funk influence, theres an earnestness and ebullience that is admirable (Economic Times) \r\n\r\n\"These Chennai-based Israeli mixmasters presented an impressive amalgam of creative digital beats infused with live Indian vocals - a kosher jugalbandi that had the dancefloor entranced\" (Seth Jordan, music journalist, on K&G Live! AWME 09, Melbourne)','+91 44 4205 2532','http://www.facebook.com/BusinessClassRefugees/info','http://www.earthsync.com/cat.asp?catalog...','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','business-class-refugess'),(1203,0,3,3,'Gowri','With music as her sole escape, Gowri turns every lover, bird and dead friend into a song (so a magazine once said). She picked up the guitar when she was 16, played guitar for a rock band that never went places, and finally took up the acoustic, and started writing songs (lyrics and guitar-riff types), as she had much to say but no one to listen.\r\n','gowriunplugged@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Gowri/130700383654225?sk=info','','http://www.soundcloud.com/kozmi-cow','','0','491',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','gowri'),(1204,0,29,29,'Kendraka','Kendraka promises an experience of the confluence of the different cultural influences(Hindustani & Carnatic classical music,hardcore rural folk of West Bengal, of that of Purulia and Bankura,the urban folk of Kolkata, Jazz , Rock, Blues, Rn B and even integrating indian classical dance form-Bharatanatyam) set to the backdrop of the modern complex urban thematic metamorphosis with emphasis on spontaneity and improvisation .Through the brave and spontaneous attempts of admixture of different cultures and lifestyles of featured musicians and the complex ever evolving \"cosmopolitan\" yet \"root consious Bengali-Indian\"conciousness of the composer and contributers ,which also includes Mainak\'s National Scholar Awardee(from the Govt. Of India), and Bharatanatyam dancer wife Arupa , Kendraka ,always, tries to capture the truth,the core spiritual-existential truth, at every given point in time of performance.Thus its ever changing ... change is the only constant force in life.','Mainak \"bumpy\" nag Chowdhury +91 9836383581','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Kendraka/179837068704416?sk=info','http://www.kendraka.com','','','0','391',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','kendraka'),(1205,0,1,1,'Ghost Crabs','WE ARE CRAZY CRABS, COMING FROM ALL AROUND THE WORLD, WE BRING LOVE AND SOUNDS TO WARM YOUR HEART...\r\n\r\nDescription\r\n\r\nPHYCHEDELIC-BEAT ...ROCK\'N\'ROLL ...INDIAN SOUNDS ...LATIN PASSION AND ITALIAN FOOD ....COMING LIVE IN DELHI VERY SOON!!!!\r\n\r\nBand Interests\r\n\r\nYOGA MEDITATION - NICE GIRLS - INDIAN SOUNDS & FOOD - BEAT MUSIC - SHORTBUS - SHARE FEELINGS WITH EVERYBODY AND BE HAPPY...\r\n\r\nArtists We Also Like\r\n\r\nBEATLES, RAVI SHANKAR, THE WHO, THE CLASH, CHINTAN KALTRA, SKA VENGERS, RAMONES, ANTOINE RENDON, THE GHOST CRABS, SUFI MUSIC, ETC...','pfattori@hotmail.it','http://www.facebook.com/ghostcrabs/info','http://www.youtube.com/theghostcrabs','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ghost-crabs'),(1206,0,2,2,'DJ Nik','','','http://www.facebook.com/djaynik','','','','103398836360938','5564',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-nik'),(1207,0,3,3,'DJ Nash','is friends call him SUPER BOY & others call him\r\nTHE BOY WONDER ...\r\n\r\nNash grew up in Banglore and was influenced by the large number of musical genres of the country. When one of his friends started working as a DJ, his interest for DJing started at the age of 17 when he started experimenting with remixing at home. Gradually, he built his own record collection. At first, he played at parties of his friends and family.\r\n\r\nIn 2007, he started working as a DJ in a club in Banglore . Nowadays, he performs all the time With Family & Friends . Nash did remixes for other bands, including David Guetta, K-Liber, The Partysquad, and Gio.\r\n\r\nIn 2008, he performed as the opening act at the dance event Sensation. Afterwards, he stated that this was a dream come true for him: he had visited the very first Sensation event in 2009 and promised himself that one day he would be standing behind the DJ table.\r\n\r\nSpinning at hundreds of events for diverse groups including\r\nnightclubs\r\ncorporate events\r\ncollege formals and alumni events\r\ncharity fundraisers\r\nfashion shows\r\nweddings and private parties','918971763765','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-nash'),(1208,0,3,3,'DJ Rohit','a','','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-rohit'),(1209,0,0,0,'DJ TT','Music and entertainment has always been a passion by birth and this lead him to begin his musical career in the year 1998. He embarked on a musical journey that has taken his music to the four corners of the globe. His cutting edge style and impeccable taste in music has made sure that TT is always classed amongst the top name DJs in India. He is still the only DJ to have won prestigious War of the DJs south zone three times. Dj TTs talent behind the decks and fearless risk taking in mixing has made sure his DJing CV contains most major clubs throughout India. He was resident DJ for clubs. TT has played most styles over the years. His shows never fail to impress, containing new and exciting material at every turn. He has played alongside many top Djs from India and throughout the world and Carved his name among the best.','9620930958','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-tt'),(1210,0,3,3,'DJ Hassan','DJ, remixer, Producer, arranger and a DJ trainer since Feb 2007\r\nBeen in the industry as a Dj and event manager for 3 yrs. done the DJ schooling from ef. Production classes from ef India music production..\r\n\r\nSpecialization:\r\n\r\nMastered his music with House, Electro bollywood, Specialized in corporate shows. Has had a gig in many major cities like Bangalore, Hyderabad, Mumbai, Delhi, Bhopal, Indore, Chennai and Mysore..\r\n\r\nA few of the Corporate Clients dealt with so far:\r\n\r\n	Accenture\r\n	Infosys\r\n	Satyam\r\n	AOL\r\n	Geometrics Software\r\n	RGBSI\r\n	Fidelity\r\n	Oracle\r\n	HP Invent\r\n	Unisys\r\n	24/7\r\n	Aviva\r\n	Convergys\r\n	IBM','09916666047','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-hassan'),(1211,0,3,1,'DJ Anoop Abosulute','DJ/MUSICIAN/ARRANGER/REMIXER/PRODUCER/PERFORMER\r\n\r\nMy DJ styles vary from Ambient to Minimal Techno Progressive Tech Tribal House to Electronica Breaks & DubStep/Drum N Bass to cutting edge Israeli & Scandinavian Psychedelic Trance\r\n\r\nI\'ve been assisted a couple of bands as a keyboardist and back up vocalist as well!\r\n\r\nCreating and performing music, both as a DJ and a Musician, for over 20 years, I\'ve been influenced by many a genre and that reflects in the sound I create and spin...\r\n\r\nMy experience, practice, and dedication has taught me the art of picking up a party at any point in the night, and giving it my ABSOLUTE! touch My versatility spans from playing long sets to doing on the fly remixes!\r\n\r\nMusic from the Indian Films, largely Hindi or better known as Bollywood Music, world over, drives the Indian Music Industry. I have been involved with quite a few projects in relation to scoring background scores for the same; producing official remixes of the soundtracks etc. My big one being the remix of the title track of the very successful magnum opus RANG DE BASANTI (2006). The original was composed by Maestro A R Rahman. The remix found itself releasing on BBC Radio One UKs star DJ, Bobby Frictions super hit compilation FRICTION 2 on Sony BMG... Enjoying generous airplay on the UK radio Besides, Desi DJs in the USA, Australia, Dubai, and UK, dished it out loud and proud in their sets at parties!\r\n\r\nI also had the privilege of remixing CHASE by SIMON HOWARDS (HOWIE B) as a part of the British Council and Channel [v] initiative, THE UNION, in 2005. Simon aka Howie B, was involved as a producer on U2s album POP. He also produces for the likes of Bjork etc.','098866 69069','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-anoop-abosulute'),(1212,0,3,3,'DJ Jasmeet','Double agent shuffling between House & Bollywood music. \nAll ACTION DJ HERO.','','http://www.facebook.com/djjasmeet','','','','205928836096634','6181',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-jasmeet'),(1213,0,1,1,'DJ Dee','','','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-dee'),(1214,0,1,1,'DJ Monty','The Music Fraternity are elated to announce that we have signed again the most sought after DJ Monty from the capital city of India. Music is the only religion DJ Monty knows. Just at the age of 16 this Dj started showing his talent, and now has emerged as one of the most poised and polished Dj enlightening the Music and the entertainment world in India . Just 26 year old and still Montys mixing experience and career has gone from strength to strength. Starting from college, private parties and now to a well renowned Disc Jockey. Currently he is a resident Dj at JYNXXX, Hotel Intercontinental Eros in New Delhi, India, his music career has always been riding up the graph.\r\n\r\nA professional DJ, Monty has plenty of experience backing him. Not only can he perform to any crowd, but is talented DJ too, can make the crowd groove by churning non-stop music. He is a killer on the prowl.\r\n\r\nHis talent is not just restricted to his city but has been rocking the nation. Monty has been mixing for Elite Clubs, Pubs and Lounge and also played for Events, Launches, Pvt. Parties and Fashion Shows for Multinational Companies, Elite Designers,, Socialites , College and School Music / Annual Festivals and many more \r\n\r\nMonty is currently planning to tour all over India IN 2011 / 2012 and then across the globe.\r\n\r\nMonty enjoys playing Commercial Top Charts, Bollywood, hip hop n house specializes in Bollywood and Electro House. He has an outstanding knack for reading a crowd and knowing exactly what to throw to capture that special something. \r\n\r\nHe is also known as one of the most talented and versatile Djs in New Delhi. Monty is highly versatile DJ with many faces, capable of spinning music of vast and can perform to his fullest abilities with commitment, professionalism and the foot tapping music. one of the most versatile Djs and knows the pulse of the crowd to rock their body and soul with his commercial style of music and sometimes takes you on a tour with the true blend of Electro house music. Has created waves with his show-stopping performances on gigs and live shows in India. Also a constant face in the Leading Newspapers, Magazines and in all the Electronic and Print Media in New Delhi n N.C.R, he can be found everywhere, where the music flows.\r\n','09818313911','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-monty'),(1215,0,5,10,'DJ Lucky Lou','DJ Lucky Lou is a turntable maestro whose base of clientele and sponsors includes such powerhouse brands as Nike, Jordan, EA Sports, Monster Cable, Ecko Unlimited, G Shock, Hennessy, IN4MATION, Reebok and MySpace. \r\n\r\nComing to you by way of Jamaica, Queens, DJ Lucky Lou operates out of Southern California, where 944 Lifestyle Magazine has recognized him as one of L.A.s hottest DJs. He is a throwback to the deeply rooted craft of Disc Jockey artistry, learned in the ways of turntable mastery, mixing and MCing by some of the most elite DJs to ever spin a record, including DJ Icy Ice, DJ Premier, DJ E-man and DJ QBert. \r\n\r\nSince beginning his DJing career in the early 1990s, DJ Lucky Lou has put his skills on display at events in Hollywood, Las Vegas, New York, Miami and the islands of Hawaii and Puerto Rico, spinning at some of the hottest celebrity events around, including the Sundance Film Festival, the Winter Olympics, the Winter Music Conference, MAGIC, E3, Power Summit, SEMA, the Grammy Awards and the National Democratic Convention. \r\n\r\nDJ Lucky Lou is a crowd pleaser with an uncanny ability to bring a party to life with his encyclopedic background of musical knowledge, ranging from disco, classic 80s, rock, soul, funk, and electro house. Despite his diverse love of music, its DJ Lucky Lous love affair with hip hop that has fueled his amazing career, landing him behind the turntable at parties for some of the music industrys heavyweights, such as Jay-Z, P. Diddy, T.I. The Black Eyed Peas, & now his current group LMFAO \r\n\r\nFor all of his success and accomplishments, DJ Lucky Lou is a true gentleman who never takes his talents for granted and is forever honing his world-class DJing skills.','','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-lucky-lou'),(1216,0,1,1,'DJ Addy','Aditya Rajput, \r\n\r\nBorn November 15, Is known For His Enthusiasm, Announcing Skills & Reception Preparation As A Disc Jockey @ Various Reputed Clubs. \r\n\r\nStarted @ A Young Age Under The Guidance Of \" DJ PRASHANT\" , He Believes In Playing In His Own Exclusive & Rigorous Style Mixing Varied Genres.\r\n\r\nConfession To Genres From House,Commercial,Electronic To Hip-Hop.\r\n\r\nHe Has Peerless Hand & Finger Dexterity @ The Music Discs & Equipment. \r\nHis Unique Talent For Music Makes For A Great Combination For Giving You & Your Guests Something No Other DJ Can Provide. He Has A Gifted Charm & The Skills To Control The Grooves Of The Crowd & Make Sure The Dance Floor Is Packed.','095 82 010701','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-addy'),(1217,0,1,1,'DJ Mukul','hi this is dj mukul from delhi i have strted my djing in 2005 and i have played in so many clubs in delhi and ncr like Hash,Velocity,masque,Quashkai,nightfever etc. I have played so many prvt events music genre house hip hop,bllywood,punjabi,retro.','','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-mukul'),(1218,0,1,1,'Hiten Panwar','Hiten Panwar - A Rhythmist par excellence. He is the grandson of renowned Kathak exponent Late Pt. Guru Sohan Lal of Jaipur Gharana ;and the legendary Classical Singer and Music Director Late Pt. Govind Prasad Jaipurwale of Kunwar Shyam Gharana, thereby making him the 5th generation musician and dancer carrying forward the family legacy. \r\n\r\n\r\nCarrying forth the family tradition, Hiten also became a Kathak disciple of Late','','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','hiten-panwar'),(1220,0,1,1,'The Metal Squid','The Metal Squid has been in existence since 2008.Though the band has performed with names like The Count, Divine Truth, it got it\'s permanent name in November 2009.The band has performed in various GIGS in and around Delhi and IITs.With the aim of getting hell out of the audience all members are young, energetic and masters in their field..\n\nWANNA KNOW US MORE? THEN SEE US PERFORM!!!','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Metal-Squid/133186910043298','','','','133186910043298','262',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-metal-squid'),(1221,0,18,18,'John OO Fleming','John 00 Fleming is an artist who has achieved international success in a career spanning over 20 years without dishonouring his musical essence or fans. With over 10 million album sales and 30 produced mix compilations, Johns a proven musical pioneer whose essence lies in what his fans call, the J00F sound. The J00F sound is as unpretentious as the artist, and is best described as deep and textured progressively edged trance, in an electronic dance music style that is an antithesis to what is normally produced within the genre.\r\n\r\nIn an industry rife in self worship and mirror gazing, John is characterised by a passion and ability to connect audiences by injecting his unique underground musical style, and not his ego, into the mainstream vein. This connection has manifested in ten mix compilations and five singles in the UK Top 40 charts on iconic labels: Virgin, EMI and Warner Music. It has also seen him headline major events worldwide, seeing in over 10,000 appearances at the likes of Gatecrasher, Godskitchen, Ministry of Sound and Global Gathering, through to Hollands Dance Valley, Serbias Exit Festival, Brazils Exxxperience, Australias Future music festivals, Belgiums Tomorrowland, and the U.S.As Electric Daisy Carnival (EDC).\r\nJohns renown lies in his desire to give back to his fans. His much lauded 2010 BBC Radio 1 Essential Mix has spawned J00F Editions, an international tour which innovatively refocuses the music onto the club and its clubbers. J00F Editions resurrects the scene of old, and reintroduces the clubbing experience to extended sets, new sounds and new artists to deliver a true musical journey devoid of fluff and predictive clich that has quickly gained international respect, residencies and support from other leading figures such as Dave Seaman, Avalon, Passion and Ministry of sound. JOOF Editions has been a huge success.\r\nJohns record label, J00F Recordings, and his monthly radio show, Global Trance Grooves, broadcast on iTunes, Ministry of Sound radio and DI. FM provides John another path to walk his own line. Here, he promotes rising stars in addition to giving over four million subscribed fans the latest in J00Fs inimitable sounds.\r\n\r\nJohn is also one of a select few endorsed by Pioneer. As the industry heavyweights inside every DJ booth, John provides subject matter expertise and consultancy in a partnership which ensures the upward evolution of the electronic music worlds tools of the trade.\r\nJohns esteem within the industry has garnered respect from electronica luminaries like Jean Michael Jarre and Simple Minds, and while humbly accepting peer endorsement he continues to let his production skills do the talking. Being humble John has never bragged the fact he writes music scores for the TV and movie world having music all over; BBC, NBC, Warner bros, Sony, ABC, Fax and more. Often being disgruntled with the commercial intrusion into the electronic John saved his writing skills for the media word, until recently where he has released an onslaught of chart topping releases, including his award winning debut album Nine lives in 2011.\r\n\r\nJohn 00 Fleming is a performer who adroitly crafts something musically organic from the inorganic, artfully opening your senses into a genre far more pervasive than you currently know. Challenge yourself, and get intelligently immersed, inside his adventurous odysseys.','','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','john-oo-fleming'),(1222,0,2,2,'DJ Pearl','From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia\r\nDJ Pearl is a popular Indian disc jockey known for her funky, tech sounds and electro beats.\r\n\r\nDJ Pearl was born in a family who resisted DJing as a profession, but later became her biggest supporters.\r\n\r\nShe is married to MTV VJ, Nikhil Chinapa also known as VJ Nikhil.\r\n\r\nDJ Pearl started her career in small clubs. She later on co-founded Submerge, with her husband Nikhil Chinappa. Submerge, a pioneering project, serves as a platform for many upcoming DJs in India.','hermit@submerge.in','http://www.facebook.com/pages/DJ-Pearl/105653546135314','djpearl.com','','','0','2119',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-pearl'),(1225,0,1,1,'Unidentified Frequency ','The name Unidentified Frequency has been chosen to define the motive involved behind the representation of sound in a way to make you reach a level of euphoria you have not yet experienced.\r\n\r\nDescription\r\n\r\n??????? ?????????? UNIDENTIFIED FREQUENCY \r\nTO THE MUSIC. \r\n\r\n\r\nPAST EVENTS\r\n\r\nSUPPORTING SETS FOR ARTISTS LIKE SKAZI, TALAMASCA, BIZZARE CONTACT, ESKIMO-SPACE TRIBE AND MANY MORE.\r\n\r\n','ufrequency666@gmail.com','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','unidentified-frequency'),(1228,0,18,18,'SANDUNES','Live music backgrounds blended with quality dark-studio-production hours, and a heavy dose of UK underground electronica,\r\nSandunes\' tunes bounce between 2 step, future garage, post dub step and experimental electronica. From an innovative live set that includes a range of performers and instruments, to an \'Old Skool is Cool\' Electro Swing and funky hip-hop DJ set, the B.P.M. swings roughly between 128 to 138 (read: dance, dance, dance)\r\nWith new tools and toys, a promising future in AV experiences, and a barrage of live and impromptu FX, Sandunes makes studio meet stage.','sandunesmusic@gmail.com','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sandunes'),(1229,0,2,2,'DJ RAYG','Reji Ravindran (a.k.a rayG) has musical experience which spans for nearly 15 years.\r\n\r\nBorn in Mumbai, Reji was bitten by the music bug during the mid-90s. After collecting a load of music cassettes, CDs and vinyl in his youth, he decided to give DJing a shot by learning from veteran DJ, Jo Azaredo. Since that year (1998), there\'s been no stopping him. Reji is one of the most prolific names in Mumbai\'s booming alternative and electronic music scene.\r\n\r\nFor the longest time in his career, Reji has been recognised as an educator within the music fraternity. After understanding India\'s unique music scene in the early 2000s, the DJ professor designed and implemented his own syllabus at some of the best DJ schools in the city; training more than 500 men and women in the art of DJing, turntablism and music production.\r\n\r\nBy putting his mouth where the money is, Reji has been a successful battle DJ by winning the DMC Champion (Pune - 2000), Times War of the DJs winner (Mumbai - 2007) and Kingfisher Ultra DJ (2010) titles through the years. Reji was the first ever turntablist in an Indian nu-age metal band called Scag and also the brains behind India\'s earliest hip hop collective called \"itch\". In December 2008, world renowned travel magazine, Time Out Mumbai, mentioned him as one of Mumbai\'s most influential DJs\" in its cover article.\r\n\r\nBy always keeping an emphasis on quality music with longer shelf life (minus short term crass commercial appeal), you can always expect Reji to dish out an unpredictable blend of indie, reggae, rock, dub, dancehall, funk, soul, breaks, disco, baltimore, house, techno, hip-hop, electro, drum and bass, jungle, swing, retro, dubstep, mash ups and much more. Phew!','reji.mumbai@gmail.com','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-rayg'),(1230,0,2,2,'Sojourne/Shibani Kashyap','Shibani Kashyap, the renowned singer, composer and a performer generates ripples with her performances as she not only creates music but also decorates its interiors with strokes of authenticity and adds life to it. She has a unique style of her own and her energy level is always unbeatable. She has given a variety of songs from Sajnaa a Bhi Jaa to a completely different song like Zinda Hoon Main and Kya Kashmakash Hai Yeh. She loves to experiment with music and believe to sing in her own way.\r\n\r\nShe started her career with AIR FM jingle and now within a few years of her journey of music she has become an international singer by doing performances in different countries and singing for Hollywood is in her schedule now.\r\n\r\nShibani Kashyap has been chosen by the famous guitar company, Gibson, to endorse Gibson guitar in India. Also, F-Bar, Ashoka has honored Shibani Kashyap on the 9th of July 2008 by making her the artist In Focus. This ceremony was inaugurated by Kapil Dev, the unforgettable cricket star, who gave a very hearty and beautiful appreciative speech for Shibani. ','info@shibanikashyap.com','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sojourneshibani-kashyap'),(1233,0,2,2,'DJ Akhtar','One of the most prominent names in club culture and the Indian dance music industry, DJ Akhtar needs no introduction. After completing his I.C.S.E. exams in 1989 he started off his dj\'ing career at a popular south Bombay club -`RG\'s- now The Intercontinental - marine drive. In 1991 he moved over to the exclusive nightclub of the Taj Mahal hotel, Mumbai - `1900\'s- now known as Insomnia. Completing his graduation in commerce from University of Bombay and obtaining diplomas in business management, airline travel n tourism(IATA) and computer systems overview(CSO)- (NCC-UK) he made sure that his passion for music and dj\'ing did not interfere with his educational background. He\'s been entertaining and enthralling audiences which include the creme de la creme of society and the likes of many socialites, film stars & international celebrities and icons with his most peculiar and inimitable style of spinning music. \r\nBesides being the resident dj at Enigma (JW Mariot) dj Akhtar free lances for private shows and parties. He\'s been hired to play at private parties hosted by or for Indian and International superstars including the likes of Mr Amitabh Bachchan, Sachin Tendulkar, Hritik Roshan, Shahrukh Khan, Shekhar Kapoor, Goldie Hawn, Steven Segal( Ford supermodels contest), Richard Gere( AIDS charity function), George Michael, Cindy Crawford(Omega launch), Bryan Adams, Lou Bega and a host of other stars. Amongst socialites, industrialist\'s and corporate clients he\'s performed for countless wedding parties and other functions hosted by personalities such as Anil and Tina Ambani, Gautam Singhania ( Annual parties and Be party at LIFW), Parthiv Kilachand, Nirmal Zaveri, Om Navani, Bharat Shah, Parmeshwar Godrej, Arvind Dubash, Ashish Raheja, Aditya Kilachand, Sanjay Narang, Rahul Narang, Ramona Narang, Sonia Garware, Aditya Birla, Yash Birla, Kumarmanglam Birla, Dr Vijay Mallya, Mr Subramanium Reddy, Kailash and Aarti Surendranath- the list could go on endlessly. \r\nDj Akhtar is very well known for his production skills and often provides music/remixes to bollywood music directors and films.\r\nHe\'s provided music for most designers in the Indian fashion industry and has worked closely with the most prominent and successful event management company\'s , choreographers and models etc. He\'s played at many after parties and for prestigious events like the Lakme India Fashion Week, Bombay Times anniversary party every year, Bacardi Blast, Smirnoff Zone, Gladrags party, Ford super models party, SIFA and IIFA awards etc.. He has played for the Mrs World Pageant party held at the Sahara Amby valley in Feb\'05. He also had the exclusive opportunity for spinning his tunes at very exclusive private parties hosted for Hollywood biggies such as Michael Douglas, Pierce Brosnan and tennis superstar Boris Becker . \r\nHe was the official Dj for all parties at the prestigious IIFA Awards held in Dubai in 2006.\r\nHe is the only dj to play along with the renowned bhangra artist dj Bally Sagoo- U.K. for his tour hosted in 12 different cities. He\'s also played by the side of many international dj\'s such as Talvin Singh, Robert Ayres - U.K., Scott Morris from Fabric - London, James Winchester-Canada, Emmanuel Muratore-Australia, Dj Spencer from the Ministry of sound -London, Dave Pearce from Ibizza? etc. \r\nHe is a very versatile dj and can easily adapt to any crowd or audience\'s taste. He is the pioneer of mainstream commercial music in India. Right from spinning live bollywood remixes, U.K. bhangra to house, retro, hip hop and r n b, dj Akhtar does it all in great style. But his main USP has always been his close interaction with the crowd and to rock private parties & wedding functions to the maximum with mainstream bollywood tunes. \r\nHis repertoire of being a rocking wedding & sangeet dj have taken him to various parts of the world including Antwerp, Brussels, Frankfurt, Bangkok, Singapore, Hong Kong, Macau, Bintaan islands- south china sea, Jakarta, Manilla, Bali, Spain -Las palomas, Teneriffe Sur, Pakistan, Amsterdam, London, Dubai, Bahrain, Tanzania - East Africa and even exotic locations like Maldives and Hoi sin islands in Thailand.','info@partymap.in ','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-akhtar'),(1234,5,1,1,'Delhi Sultanate','Born in New Delhi, India but having spent formative years in Germany and the US (Bay Area), Delhi Sultanate, has long pioneered the sounds of Dancehall / Hip Hop and performance poetry in India. In addition to his solo career, he is the MC and a founding member of BASSFoundation, New Delhi\'s first Dubstep, Drum \'n\' Bass and Reggae sound system, as well as lead singer of India\'s first Ska and Rocksteady band The Ska Vengers.\r\n?\r\n?In 2010 he started \'Word, Sound, Power\' along with producer Chris McGuinness, who is based in Brooklyn, NYC. The organization is dedicated to producing documentary films and musical collaborations featuring revolutionary singers from different parts of the Indian subcontinent. Word, Sound, Power creates bilingual tracks that embody the revolutionary and uplifting spirit of Dancehall Reggae and reflect life in India. The venture received e?xtensive coverage by AFP, BBC Asian Network and MTV. The films can be viewed on wordsoundpower.org, where all the music is available for free download!\r\n?\r\nDelhi Sultanate\'s recent solo releases NYC-2-India with Subatomic Soundsystem and Criss & Shine respectively went to #1 on Beatport Reggae Charts and Juno Hip Hop singles charts. He has collaborated with Sizzla Kalonji for an upcoming track, as well as many other notable dancehall MC\'s. He has shared the stage with Jazzsteppa, General Levy, Ant TC1, Subswara, Surya Dub and the Reggae Rajahs. Apart from his musical pursuits Delhi Sultanate trains in traditional martial arts and holds a Masters degree in South Asian Area Studies as well as an MPHIL in Indian History.\r\n?','info@delhisultanate.com','http://www.facebook.com/delhisultanate','www.delhisultanate.com','http://soundcloud.com/delhi-sultanate','','0','0',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 13:45:55',264,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','delhi-sultanate'),(1236,0,1,1,'Vipul Angirish','Vipul was set on a path familiar to many Indian students, with an intended future career working in computers.Vipul attended university to study computer science but his exposure to the diverse college community led him to house music. An intense passion for the style was born and Vipul switched his goal to becoming a house music DJ upon exiting college. Unfortunately, his traditional Indian family did not understand this new aspiration and were quite resistant. With Vipul in tow, his parents consulted an Indian astrologer for guidance. Much to the astonishment of Vipul and his family the astrologer advised Vipul to pursue his DJ passion and predicted that it would lead him to much success. Thus the family gave their blessing and Vipul\'s new career in house music was launched.','vipulang86gcet@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/vipulangirish','http://www.vipulangirish.com/','http://soundcloud.com/vipul-angirish','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-10 13:06:50',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','vipul-angirish'),(1238,2,1,1,'Asar Tauheed Sufi Rock','The idea to form ASAR Tauheed was to produce sufi rock music. ASAR Tauheed\r\nis a six member band that thrives on creating original music that is emotionally\r\nintense and technically dazzling. Its a bond of intellectual and musically sound\r\nTheir music is refreshingly original, exciting and amazingly melodious.\r\nTheir public performances and concerts are incredibly energetic, entertaining,\r\npulsating and astoundingly interactive.\r\nIn a short span of time ASAR Tauheed has developed its roots in the music world\r\nand has established its own identity as a successful rock band and this could be\r\neasily recognized by their loving and enthusiastic fan following in various parts\r\nof the country. The band has achieved success because of the taste they possess\r\nin music, which is adorned by many and praised by the masses, that is evident in\r\nevery live concert of the band where the crowd sings along their originals.\r\nBesides their original compositions their repertoire includes popular Hindi\r\nsongs from Bollywood and covers from sufi artists.','','http://www.facebook.com/AsarTauheed','http://www.asartauheed.com','','http://www.reverbnation.com/Asartauheedsufiband','0','0',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-11 11:41:16',345,'[\"\"]','[\"Yuni Shashri - 9971358886\"]','asar-tauheed-sufi-rock'),(1239,0,3,3,'PRASHANTH PALLEMONI','Turntablist Prashanth Pallemoni is one of India and Bangalore\'s best kept secrets in the Djing world. Showcasing a turntablist\'s interpretation of hip-hop, funk, nu-disco, afrobeat and broken beat, expect outbursts of twisted beat mangling, juggling and quircussionism. Prashanth is a collector and an ambassador for eclectic underground dance music and also 1/3 of Bangalore based electro-acoustic project Schizophonic.','','http://www.facebook.com/UNNAYANAA','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','prashanth-pallemoni'),(1241,5,1,2,'TOYZ IN PANIC AKA. LEON RUSSELL & DOKTOR DANIEL','Toyz In Panic , formally known as Leon Russell and Doktor Daniel is a project which brings to floor \r\na concept done by many but Delivered like none. The motive of these two people is to bring to the people \r\na very unique way of playing EDM. \r\nLeon and Daniel although have very different influences of music they share a connect that helps them not only \r\nbring out the best them but also helps them bring to the people a whole lot more than expected.\r\nLeon\'s micro understanding of EDM , Techno in particular , placement and delivery of tracks coupled with the percussive \r\nside of Daniel makes the music more thurst and gives it a new dimension. The sole motto of the two is One Sound !\r\nVisually u can see a Dj and Percussionist going at it but when you hear the music you hear One Sound and that is the essence \r\nthat this act thrives to better at each coming gig.\r\nNothing is prepared before hand , since the element of surprise is created on the spot itself.\r\n\r\nLeon and Daniel , since 2008 - the birth of their project have always stuck to the fact that music in general is a whole lot fun to play.\r\nFor them it hasent been about what one cannot do , but about what you can can do ! Be it Dj\'ing or Percussions , the thrill of creating something \r\nright at that very spot by breaking down the essentials of music and then producing a product that is meant to mesmerize people is what pushes them\r\nto probe further into making the act more fun to watch and groove to.\r\nThis act throw\'s in a style of EDM which is naughty , bouncy and groovy to the likes of Tech House , Techno and some Progressive House as well.\r\nThe momentum of the act is created by the connect it shares with the people they perform for , and post that - the grid is always a journey that is\r\nconveyed through the music.\r\nThey have hit cities like Delhi , Chandigarh , Kolkata , Bangalore , Nepal and blown the doors off the clubs they have performed at.\r\n\r\nLeon and Daniel now also have their very own Record Label , known as Dazzle On Records which has already seen mainstream Tech House/Progressive House\r\nartist Eddy Good witness the colours of India through the medium of an Indian Tour this past August - September 2010. The label is now lining up many more artist to bring to India some of the best underground in the world. The act is also Producing its EP which \r\nwill be launching worldwide by the end of this year with more music to come shortly after that in the new year. The label also has some very talented and wikid domestic artists/dj\'s signed under them to help get their material out there.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Toyz-In-Panic-aka-Leon-Russell-Doktor-Daniel','','http://www.soundcloud.com/dazzle-on-records','','0','0',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 13:48:52',321,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','toyz-in-panic-aka-leon-russell-doktor-daniel'),(1242,0,1,1,'Anil Chawla','He had the both envious and unenvious task of warming up for electronic music royalty as diverse as The Chemical Brothers, Fatboy Slim, Francois K, Josh Wink, Green Velvet, Simian Mobile Disco, Mylo, Hot Chip, MSTRKRFT, and Cassius. Dance music bastions Global Underground soon picked up on his skill across the board and after a series of singles and the stunning debut album Roadhouse (with studio partner Dale Anderson), the label has taken him around the world on tours to Argentina, Peru and Guatemala (on his headline tour of South America), to Cocoon in Frankfurt, Australia, Dubai, Miami, Egypt, Amsterdam, Philippines, Ukraine and across the UK. Thats not to mention his separate appearances at Pete Tongs Wonderland in Ibiza and in countries including Mexico, Russia, USA, Spain, India, Lithuania, Georgia, Austria, Poland, Sweden, Italy and the Channel Islands.\r\n\r\nA global fan base was soon established, and guest mixes on BBC Radio 1, Carl Coxs Global and John Digweeds Transitions radio shows followed, as well as Anil & Dale holding down their own bi-monthly GU Radio show. His DJ profile growing simultaneously and his ever increasing status as a producer, with releases on leading labels like Great Stuff, Cr2, Brique Rouge, and Nic Fanciullis Saved Records, alongside countless awards/reviews from DJMag, iDJ, Mixmag and Beatport. Looking to the future, Anil continues touring across the globe  with everything from deep melodic funk and freaky acid house still all part of his repertoire. His productions continue to gain support from the likes of Richie Hawtin, Laurent Garnier, John Digweed, Pete Tong, Hernan Cattaneo, James Zabiela and Nic Fanciulli  New releases forthcoming on Saved, Bitten, Global Underground, and Tribal Rage will ensure that his name carries on being on the house music cognoscentis lips through into the new decade.','dev@unmute.in','','https://twitter.com/#!/AnilChawla6','http://soundcloud.com/anilchawla','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','anil-chawla'),(1243,0,2,2,'Arnold From Mumbai','High energy and infectious enthusiasm are some of the adjectives that are synonymous with the name Arnold Misquitta fondly known as Arnold from Mumbai (AFM) in the Global Dance Music Scene.\r\n\r\nArnold hails from Mumbai but is at home in almost every city in the country. For that matter, his name is now a household one in the genre of electronica not only in India but across continents.\r\n\r\nFrom DJ to Producer to Musician, Arnolds pieces are an amalgamation of innovative ideas that are uniquely creative and original. His panache & signature mix style give his audiences the platform they crave. Deriving inspiration across all genres, Arnolds versatility is his forte that emerges through his adventurous musical creations.\r\n\r\nRemixing artists such as Kasey Taylor, Pena, Andrea Bertolini, Amin Golestan,Xaver,Paul Thomas, Logiztik Sounds, Curious George and the Agent, C-Jay, Cilla Black and Jalebee Cartel etc ; and releases showcased on renowned record labels like GF Recordings, Vapour Recordings, Session Deluxe, EMI UK, BDR Music UK, Echoes Records, Plusquam Records, City Lights Music, Absolutely Records, 19 Box Recordings etc., AFMs listings have been featured on various charts hosted by some of the established music stores such as Beatport, TrackitDown, Audio Jelly, ReleasePromo among others.\r\n\r\nHaving performed at venues such as Club Cubana (Goa), Elevate (Delhi), Aurus (Mumbai),Bluefrog (Mumbai), Pasha and Leather Bar (Chennai), Club Platinum (Nepal), Kosmo and Taika (Bangalore) plus festivals such as Sunburn 2011, GO:Madras (1-3), 9 feet high (Chennai), Mahashivratri (Nepal), MTC Beer (Mumbai); Along with sets featured on Digiprana Show NYC FM 90.3 among others ;His tracks are also featured in playlists by the industries Top artists ,his skills as a musician shine!\r\n\r\nTie-ups with friends across borders internationally have ensured that AFM has his net spread far and wide. Collaborating projects with pals Yves Eaux, Le Ron and Sam Farsio (Socio Robots),Shiva Moon to name a few, is only one part of AFMs journey, which he aims to expand by touring live.\r\n\r\nArnold visualized 2010 as a musically creative and promisingly original year and that is precisely what he delivered.\r\n','Dev Bhatia - 09999369935','','http://www.myspace.com/misquittaarnold','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','arnold-from-mumbai'),(1244,0,1,1,'Ash Roy','Ash Roy is one of the founding members of India\'s most prolific dance music act, Jalebee Cartel. Since its inception, Roy has been providing all vocal and percussive elements during their memorable live performances and has also steadily been creating music to add to the Cartel\'s cache of original productions. His career has long crossed the decade mark during which Roy\'s traveled across the continents touring with the band and solo, pre-Jalebee Cartel. They\'ve been basing themselves out of Europe every summer, to have equal footing in both sides of the globe. While Jalebee Cartel has shared headliner space with the likes of The Prodigy, Modeselektor and Carl Cox, he\'s also played with Sasha, Cari Lekebusch, Fergie and KaseyTaylor individually. It just keeps getting better and better for Ash Roy, and that\'s what reflects in his music.','Dev Bhatia - 09999369935','http://www.facebook.com/Ash.R0y','','http://soundcloud.com/ash-roy','','121484967947450','470',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ash-roy'),(1245,0,1,1,'Ashvin Mani Sharma / Calm Chor','calm  (km)\nadj. calmer, calmest\n1. Nearly or completely motionless\n2. Not excited \n\nchor (???)\n1. Outlaw\n2. Thief\n\nCalm Chor is here to steal your calm. \"Calm\" in this context is the safe yet, boring and predictable space that we can get stuck in. He is here to dismantle the ideas and habits that make life feel like a drag and transport us to a place where we can take a step back; and view life as the crazy, fun adventure it can be. If only we are willing...\n\nAshvin\'s intention is to make music a tool for emptying the mind with unpredictable and unusual sounds, and then fill the open space with the beauty of surrender through dance... A state of mind that takes you away from the safe space of the self to a consciousness where the tribe becomes aware of its existence.  To reaffirm that we are a bunch of freaks who listen to bizarre, crazy music that just somehow moves our soul to action...\n\nCalm chor is Indian and so is his music. It\'s dramatic and emotional like every Indian is at heart. \n\nCalm Chor is the Alter ego of Ashvin Mani Sharma who has been a part of the Indian underground music scene since 1995. He has been producing music and deejaying since 1998. He is one of the co-founders of Jalebee Cartel, a live electronic music act that has put India on the international EDM map delivering power-packed performances from Paradiso in Amsterdam to Blue Frog in Mumbai. He also makes music under the name of Crash & Boom which is a Psy-Trance Project with Ash Roy.\n\nEquipment:\n1. Apple MacBook Pro\n2. Behringher MIDI controllers\n3. Axiom MIDI keyboard controller\n4. Ableton LIVE\n5. Kaossillator\n6. Kaos Pad\n\nSTYLE OF MUSIC  Sinister Upbeat and Groovy .\nGenre - Techno/Progressive Psy/ Psy Trance  depends on the\nsituation.\nBPM  120  150. ','Dev Bhatia - 09999369935','http://www.facebook.com/CalmChor','','www.soundcloud.com/calmchor','','209659755808638','92',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','ashvin-mani-sharma-calm-chor'),(1247,0,1,1,'Tuhin Mehta / Brute Force','Tuhin Mehta belongs to the old school breed of DJs. With two decades of experience pioneering club-world in India, hes a force to be reckoned with. He is someone who has immersed himself in the art of DJing from an extremely young age, where it was not just a forged career path, rather, a way of life.\r\n\r\nA professionally qualified sound engineer from SAE in Chennai, along with being an international ambassador to the Berklee College of Music, Tuhin not only has immense experience from the various clubs that he has played in over the years, he also has a sharp understanding of the technical aspects behind sound production. His understanding of equipment is grade A and it speaks volumes that he was named a Pioneer Pro DJ for India in 2007. This combination of both prowess and technical ability only adds to his allure as a DJ who has a sharp understanding of the science of rocking a dance-floor.\r\n\r\nThere is just no way you can pigeonhole Tuhins style... his sets are an energy packed blend of diverse genres  he adds a bit of everything just as long as it gets you dancing. Filled with quirky melody and heavy drummage  Tuhin has created a genre of his own in his thumping EnergiTech and you can be rest assured that you will be losing it to his music. His extensive background in DJing also makes him a ridiculously sharp technician on the decks; he knows his equipment and his tunes inside out and youll find that his mixing ability is second to none.\r\n\r\nAs a producer, he is one half of the duo Brute Force, a collaboration that began many years ago with childhood friend, Shane Mendonsa. Together, theyve launched Brutal By Birth, the subcontinents first independent dance music label, promoting their unique brand of hard hitting, acid laden, bass heavy dance floor stompers. 2010 marked a big step on the production front for Brute Force. The duo featured on trance musics hottest star, Gareth Emerys award winning album Northern Lights with the seductive, euphoric, hands in the air tune, Arrival.\r\n\r\nTuhin continues to rock clubs all over and is without a doubt a favorite in Indias EDM circuit. He holds numerous residencies at the hottest clubs and is also a part of the core team of Submerge, Indias leading dance music community. You can catch him work his magic at Indias premier music festival Sunburn. He is a regular on the line up and his sets have each and every time rated amongst the very best.\r\n\r\n2010 was even more special for Tuhin  he along with his friends Shiv Gupta & Hema Sethuraman launched their very own music festival - Go:Madras, the very first of its kind in the city of Chennai and one that just like Sunburn has set a standard in the country for quality organization and even better music to boot.\r\n\r\nKeeping himself busy on all fronts: DJing at the biggest clubs to packed crowds, producing massive tunes that get featured on award winning albums and now organizing one of Indias top-notch music festivals in his home town  Tuhin Mehta is obviously here to stay and each year his imprint on the scene in India is becoming everlasting. It has to be said, no one really understands the intricacies and sheer power that music holds, as well as he does.','Dev Bhatia - 09999369935','http://www.facebook.com/TuhinMehtaOfficial','http://www.tuhin.com','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','tuhin-mehta-brute-force'),(1248,0,2,2,'Suneeta Rao','Suneeta Rao is India\'s leading Pop Diva - Singer, Dancer, Stage Actress. She released 5 Hindi pop albums entitled \'Suneeta Senorita\', \'Dhuan\', \'Talaash\',  \'Ab Ke Baras\' and \'Waqt\' plus a single Music video entitled \'Chhoti Chhoti Baatein\' from the album \'Reason to Smile\' involving various artists.\r\nFrom \'Senorita\' to \'Waqt\', Suneeta Rao\'s journey over the last twenty years has seen her become the\'Paree of the Masses\' - \r\none of India\'s most loved artists. \r\nSuneeta released her latest album, \'WAQT\' in 2008, which she describes  as \'Raag - based lounge and dance music\'. She shot a video on the song \'Sun Zara\', from the same album, to address the issue of Sex Selection, which was shown at the Asia Pacific  Conference in Hyderabad.\r\nSuneeta is trained  in Carnatic and Hindustani Vocal music.Trained professionally in both classical music and dance, Suneeta Rao entered the Indian music scene at an early age and catapulted to  the top with her first two albums Senorita and Dhuan, both of which crossed the  platinum mark.\r\nSuneeta Rao has been performing Live Concerts in India and abroad for the last 25 years. View Suneeta Rao - Live!\r\nSuneeta is trained in BharataNatyam, Jazz Ballet, Latin Ballroom Dance, Flamenco and the Salsa. Suneeta  performed at the 3rd Annual Salsa India Festival in 2007.\r\nSuneeta has sung playback for mainstream Bollywood films including Roop Ki Rani Choron Ka Raja, Khiladiyon Ke Khiladi, Gupt,  Ghulam-e-Mustafa, Kahin Pyar Na Ho Jaye etc., in Tamil and Telugu films for A.R Rehman, Harris Jayraj, R.P. Patnaik and Devi Prasad, and for title tracks for popular TV Serial \'Swabhimaan\' & \'Hubahu\'.\r\nAs an actress, Suneeta Rao has Guest starred in the feature film \'Laawaris\', in and as Suneeta Rao opposite Akshay Khanna. As a stage actress, Suneeta has sung, danced and acted in English Musicals \'Evita\',  \'Grease Lightning\', \'Bottoms Up\', \'They\'re Playing Our Song\', \'The Man of La Mancha\' and \'SIDD\'.\r\nSuneeta  has modelled for TV commercials. \r\nSuneeta  has sung jingles and done Voice - Overs in more than 6 languages for over a 100 products.\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Suneeta-Rao/','http://www.suneeta-rao.com','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','suneeta-rao'),(1251,2,1,1,'MenWhoPause','menwhopause is a four-member band from New Delhi, India known for being one of the first bands in India to distribute their music for free over the internet. Their first EP called \'The story begins...\' was released online as a free download in 2003.\r\nThe band has toured the USA twice with an appearance at SxSW 2007, Austin, Texas and a full-fledged tour of Texas.\r\nThe band won the 2008 Jack Daniels\' Best Band of the Year award and got an opportunity to work with REMs producer Dave Barbe.\r\nThe second album Easy was first recorded in a campsite in Uttaranchal after which it took the band four years to re-record and produce the album. Having signed up with EMI-Virgin Records India in 2009, Easy was menwhopauses major label debut with a team that included Miti Adhikari (Radiohead, Nirvana...) and Richard Dodd (Kings of Leon, Tom Petty...). \r\n\'Easy\' is available in all major stores across India as well as on amazon and iTunes. The band toured Europe in June 2012 with the support of ICCR (Indian Centre for Cultural Relations) playing sold out shows in Tallinn (Estonia), Oslo (Norway) and Paris (France).','menwhopause@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/menwhopauseonline','http://www.menwhopause.com','','','0','3026',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-10 22:23:32',138,'[\" menwhopause@gmail.com \"]','[\"GENERAL MANAGER:ritnika [ +91-9810078890 ]\"]','menwhopause'),(1252,0,1,1,'Sherry Mathews','','','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sherry-mathews'),(1253,0,1,1,'Aashish Mandhwani','Though for purposes of entirely official nature, we like to categorize Fire Exit as a band that plays Progressive Alternative Rock, we truly believe that it falls in the category of bands that are almost impossible to categorize under one single genre of music. Our music is a combination of rock, metal and electronic sounds. The band essentially blends great vocal melody along with instrument harmony, and is based on experimentation with varied time signatures, jazz-influenced bass-lines and an Indian percussion instrument. But at the same time, we like to keep our music simple. As a group of musicians brewing our styles together, we also lay equal focus on the way we sound live and on record, giving importance to not just what we play, but also how all that playing comes together and mixes when it comes out on speakers; hence immense stress is laid on the production of our tracks. Our focus as a band is to create a sound unique to the band, with varied styles of rock, metal and psychedelia coming together for great listening pleasure to both the common listener and other musicians. We lay stress on improving our songwriting and playing as we grow together as a band, looking to create mature and sensible music.','','https://www.facebook.com/aashish.mandhwani/','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 17:01:30',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','aashish-mandhwani'),(1254,0,1,1,'Ritwik De','Zokova is a post rock project and has 10 interlinked songs, which are primarily instrumental. The songs highlight and reflect on the various emotions which we face every day but neglect.\r\n\r\nWe are coming out with the album in a few months.','','https://www.facebook.com/ritwik.de.39/info','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 17:04:19',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','ritwik-de'),(1255,0,1,1,'Rohit Bhattacharya','My new little ditties exploring acid jazz, funk and downtempo. Gonna be putting up new material regularly.','','https://www.facebook.com/rohit.bhattacharya.984/','','http://soundcloud.com/rohit-bhattacharya','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rohit-bhattacharya'),(1256,0,1,1,'Suyash Gabriel','','','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','suyash-gabriel'),(1257,0,18,18,'Younger Brother','Younger Brother is an electronic duo formed in 2003 by Simon Posford and Benji Vaughan.[1] Their debut album A Flock of Bleeps was released in 2003, followed by The Last Days of Gravity in 2007 and Vaccine in 2011.\r\nAfter making a remix for a charity record, Simon Posford (Shpongle, Hallucinogen) and Benji Vaughan (Prometheus) decided to come together in the studio to create their own type of electronic music that is generally described as unclassifiable.\r\nThe album A Flock of Bleeps released on Twisted Records became a cult classic in the underground electronica scene and included such tracks as Crumblenaut and Finger. This led to massive demand to see them live and they have played shows from London to Tokyo, New York to Moscow.','rmarkus@wmeentertainment.com','http://www.facebook.com/youngerbrother','http://www.facebook.com/youngerbrother/app_178091127385','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','younger-brother'),(1258,0,18,18,'DJ Prometheus','Benjamin Vaughan, better known as Benji Vaughan, is a British psychedelic trance musician. He has released music under many names, of which most well known is his solo project, Prometheus, and his collaboration with Twisted Records label colleague, Simon Posford, under the moniker Younger Brother.[1] His music is characterized by distinct basslines, high production quality, intense thematic development and unique or alternative approaches to the psytrance genre. He frequently combines diatonic melodic content with metallic or glitchy percussive polyphonic elements to form thick contrapuntal tapestries of sound. Although much of his music sounds like it was composed using equipment at the forefront of technology, it is not uncommon for him to use equipment now considered antique, such as the 1971 Korg micro synth that he used for portions of the second Prometheus album, Corridor of Mirrors.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Prometheus/106044109436531?ref=ts&rf=108230455871478','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-prometheus'),(1259,0,29,29,'Gandu Circus','We are a Post Punk Bangla rap band.\r\n\r\nWe have played at :\r\n20 - 22 May 2011 ESCAPE FESTIVAL, NAUKUCHIATAL\r\n23rd MAY 2011 THE LIVING ROOM, DELHI\r\n5 - 10 AUGUST 2011 KATOWICE, POLAND\r\n30th AUGUST 2011 ENLIGHTEN FESTIVAL, BOMBAY\r\n21st FEBRUARY 2012 CAW - ARTS & MUSIC FESTIVAL, CALCUTTA\r\n21st JUNE, 2012 BFI, SOUTHBANK, LONDON\r\n23rd JUNE, 2012 THE YARD, HACKNEY WICK, LONDON\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe film GANDU was made by Q in 2010, one of the most radical filmmakers in recent times.\r\n\r\nA collaboration between Q and two of the most promising musicians from India, Neel & Jiver and fuses rap & roll with heavy electronic grooves and projections from the film. \r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/GanduCircus','http://www.overdosejoint.in','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','gandu-circus'),(1260,0,104,104,'Cadent Slaves','Cadent Slaves is a Metal band from Hyderabad, India. Formed in 2008.\r\n\r\nCadent Slaves had its genesis as an Rock/Metal band in 2008, founded by Rahul, Phani & Santosh switched to rather grew into Metal by the late 2008.\r\n\r\nThe band has had it\'s share of change in the line up with Vocalists changing and the band ending up dormant for almost a year till it rose up with fresh blood infused, trying to furiously make up for lost time!\r\n\r\nOwn Compositions:\r\n\r\n1. Cadence Theme\r\n2. Vengeance\r\n3. Silence of The Darkness\r\n4. Kill My Enemy\r\n5. A Blissful Spirit','Santosh - +91 9985951105','http://www.facebook.com/nsantosh1987','http://www.reverbnation.com/cadentslaves','','http://www.reverbnation.com/cadentslaves','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','cadent-slaves'),(1261,0,2,2,'Shefali Alvares','Singer/Songwriter\r\nLead Singer  Dec 1983 to present\r\nDistil Soul featuring Shefali Alvares (Vocals)\r\nJarvis Menezes (Keys / Synth)\r\nRushad Mistry (Bass)\r\nPozy Dhar (Guitar)\r\nJai row Kavi (drums)\r\n\r\nThe Jazz Project feat Adrian Dsouza , Jarvis Menezes and Sheldon Dsilva on vocals Shefali\r\n\r\nAlso doing bollywood films now','','https://www.facebook.com/shefali.alvares','','','','0','1323',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-11 12:41:39',365,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','shefali-alvares'),(1262,0,2,2,'DISTIL SOUL','Welcome to the world of a fierce, youthful talent from India. The diva extraordinaire- Shefali Alvares!!\r\n\r\nBorn to a musical high, Shefali Alvaress vocals embody melodic goodness of smoky Jazz & Blues to up-tempo Rock filling up her music arsenal. She has made her presence felt in the live music arena of this country nearly a decade now, bedazzling a wide audience with her critically acclaimed singing skills. Shefali pursued professional training from a very young age with renowned musicians, giving her an edge over and a wide range, to excel in many genres. Packed with a passionate energy to grab the post modern era of music performances with her customized style and vocal capabilities, she is truly classical and as contemporary and fresh in this new age of song uniqueness.\r\n\r\nInfluenced by some of the heavy weight music gods such as Louis Banks, Joe Alvares, Karl Peters, Michael Stanton to Tyris Washington (USA), she has performed alongside them and held her mark with strength, above all. Shefalis raw energy has been staged at an eclectic and wide variety of venues and festivals around India and internationally. Worthy of mention to some of her accomplished performances are to the Royalty of Nepal and the Presidential Entourage of President Bill Clinton, gracing the stage at a prestigious awards function for the Singapore Indian Chamber of Commerce courting Jazz luminaries from the USA and having the Prime Minister as the chief guest amongst her audience.\r\n\r\nShefalis origins are deeply rooted in various harmonics that stem from a selection as vast as its different from each other. Lush musical layerings of the kind found in Electronica, to Jazz & Blues, on to Sufi, Retro, the Opera, and Hip Hop, Psychedelic, top that all with dance music; she takes the strings off world music and infuses in with her own. Shefalis high energy stage persona is paving a powerful path as the Jazz & Blues and up tempo Rock vocalist. A rising phoenix who has many musical surprises up her sleeves\r\n\r\nOver the last 2 years, Shefali started experimenting with her Indian music roots and has Sung in a couple of Bollywood Movies.\r\nYeh Dil Hai Nakhreywalla from the Madhur Bhandarkar Film Dil toh Baccha hai ji, Always Kabhi Kabhi, Salem, Mujhse FraandShip Karoge, Desi Boys  Tu mera hero with Mika, Ek main aur ek tu\r\nAd films for Tv: Liril, Lakme, Dove, Titan fast track, Streaks Hair, Sri lanka tourism, \r\nWorking with directors like Pritam, Vishal Shekhar, Amit Trivedi, Mikey Cleary. Recently nominated for Stardust Awards and the Desi Boys hit has earned her credits in the Indian music arena.\r\n\r\nThe future is melodic with the constant refrain that Music is the speech of the angels and her star is burning brighter than ever. She stands above all with evocative weaving vocals & infectious hooks scorching the entertainment industry, bigger than ever. Shefali Alvares- the modern day musical stimulator!!\r\n','9930112805','http://www.facebook.com/Shefaliandthedistilsoul','http://www.myspace.com/shefalialvares','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','distil-soul'),(1263,0,2,2,'FUNC','Randolph Correia a.k.a. FUNC is the guitarist and producer for Pentagram + Shaa\'ir & Func, two of the most successful bands out of India. \r\nFine Art graduate 1991-1996 , Sir J.J.School of Art. \r\nJoined Pentagram 1994. Released 4 albums. Currently touring. \r\nMember of Bombay Black 1999-2002. released 2 albums. \r\nFormed FUNCinternational in 2003. Released 3 albums. \r\nFormed Shaa\'ir & Func with Monica Dogra (Shaa\'ir) in 2006.Released 3 albums.Currently touring. \r\nIs 1 of the 4 Wobble crew members, a drum\'n\'bass collective. \r\nComposes,produces,remixes for various artists, film and television.\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/funcmusic','http://func.in','',' www.reverbnation.com/funcinternational','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','func'),(1264,0,114,114,'MC KAZTET D','Mc KAZTET D, is a French Reggae/HipHop/Grime artist, part of the underground french sound system scene for about 10 years, also member of the collective R2G (Lighta D, Dude, Scars, Mista T & Kaztet D). \r\n\"Too HipHop for the Reggae,Too reggae for the rap\", Kaztet sings his views of today\'s wold, with a Background steeped in non violence protest, influenced by many travels and journey in Asia...\r\nWell Known in the sound system scene for his Fast flow and his unique style, revealed by a few youtube videos, Mc Kaztet D evolves now into a mix of HipHop , Reggae and Electronic Music (Grime, Dubstep, Drum n Bass)\r\nAfter a few songs on different mixtapes, dubplate and collaborations with several sound system and a first street album in 2009, Mc Kaztet D is now working on his First Official Project...2 B Continued...Stay connected!!!','','http://www.facebook.com/McKaztetD','http://youtube.com/kaztetdaddy','http://soundcloud.com/mc-kaztet-d/sets','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','mc-kaztet-d'),(1265,0,29,29,'Dead Veneration','Dead Veneration is a Death Metal act from suburban Kolkata. The band was formed by four friends immensely interested in creating some of the most filthy and gritty music possible in a scene dominated by commercial and pseudo-metal.\r\n\r\nLyrically the band explores dark and sinister psyche and often necrophilia and death. The band have been working on its first demo which will soon be unleashed upon the fragile mankind.','','http://www.facebook.com/deadveneration','http://www.reverbnation.com/deadveneration','','http://www.reverbnation.com/deadveneration','0','237',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dead-veneration'),(1266,0,29,29,'Mortar','We are an old school thrash metal band from Kolkata, India. We started off in the summers of 2011, and after a few line up changes we reached stable ground so that we can Thrash \'till Death! And so here we are now!','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Mortar/218460031599417','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','mortar'),(1267,0,29,29,'Armament','Armaments inception began on February 2009. Formerly called Arsanal, singer/guitarist Albert G., drummer Ramon H., and ex-bassist Auggie M. began rehearsing songs written by Albert. As time progressed, they slowly began playing shows around the city which included backyard shows and venues. After 4 months, Auggie decided to step aside and so a replacement was found. After multiple line-up changes and countless shows in the area, the line-up and sound Armament has established presently was established. The band now consist of singer/guitarist Albert G., drummer Ramon H., guitarist Frank A., and bassist Jorge G. The name was changed to Armament for simpler recognition and has therefore been established as a thrash band.\r\n\r\nThe bands sound consists of multiple genres put together. Ramon, an ex funk and experimental drummer, brings in funk and groove to the sound. Frank sets the melodic tone of his progressive/technical metal concepts derived through a wide variety of his modern influences. Albert establishes his rhythmic sound established from influences such as Led Zeppelin, Kiss, Iron Maiden, etc. He sings with the ideas set by singers like Bruce Dickinson, Joey Belladonna, Frank Sinatra, etc. Bassist Jorge hardens the sound bringing in his punk influences such as The Adicts, The Exploited, and more. The sound has evolved from simple thrash sound to a more complex, experimental sound of thrash.\r\n\r\nThe band released an LP under the name Arsenal called Prisoner in a Chamber in 2009. Consisting of 8 songs, the band managed to sell minimal number of copies. Although proving to be a failure, the band continued to write music and developed their sound more into a stronger, darker sound. 2011 saw the release of Armaments Metal Anarchy EP. Consisting of heavy riffing, fast tempo, and blistering musicianship, the EP has gotten great response and acceptance in the metal community. To date, more than 250 copies have been sold. A full length album is on the way with multiple shows planned in the near future.\r\nAlthough the band has come a long way since their foundation, the band continues to develop and create their sound. They continue to play multiple shows and spread the music to whoever dares to take a listen.\r\n\r\nMusic enthusiasts around the globe beware, they are coming your way to conquer your ears and gain your support.','','http://www.facebook.com/Armament11512','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','armament'),(1268,0,29,29,'Strangulate','We are a three piece goregrind act from Kolkata with the intentions of making music and unveiling the beastly creature within ourselves to come out and grind fuck. With the proper designation to provide the army of mass with the sickest form of music, we aim towards in achieving the truest form of admiration and recognition from the army with taste in real sick music.','strangulategrind@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/strangulategrind','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','strangulate'),(1269,0,29,29,'Purgation','A shadow shall fall over the universe, and evil will grow in its path, and death will come from the skies.\r\nDescription\r\nLyrical Themes-Morbidity,Evil perceptions,Occultism,Rage,Gruesome acts..\r\nArtists We Also Like\r\nMorbidty,Dhwesha,Dying embrace,Gorified,Orator,Nuclear winter..','Ayushman Sinha-9748785056; purgation.inc@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/PURGATION/','http://www.myspace.com/purgationinc','','http://www.reverbnation.com/purgation','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','purgation'),(1270,0,29,29,'Necrodeity','Conceptualized and envisioned as an expedition to the darkest trench of Hell with a fathomless pit, an abysmal juxtaposition of extreme malevolence and dark serenity, \'Necrodeity\' is an existence, penetrating through relentless chaos, an experience of soul mutilation and purification, a preservation of sinister psyche and a living entity of pure blackness and absolute profanation! Malignant and sacrilegious, Necrodeity rises from the tract of chasm, to uphold the Morbid Trident of Ancient Death!\r\n\r\nThe Cult was contrived by four congregants, in search of manifesting pure blackness and relentless chaos, in early 2012. The supplicants often describe the entity as \'Spirituality Seeping Through Tenebrous Abyss\'.','+91 9831 081 394','http://www.facebook.com/necrodeitydeathmetal','','','','0','85',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','necrodeity'),(1271,0,3,3,'Nekronym','Formed in October 2010 in Bangalore, India. Striving to make music by bringing back the elements of the genre that made it great. Gathering influences from bands like Suffocation, Cannibal Corpse, Malevolent Creation, Entombed, Sinister and Morbid Angel, aiming to play \"NO BULLSHIT, IN YOUR FACE\" Death Metal.','nekronym@yahoo.com','http://www.facebook.com/Nekronym','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','nekronym'),(1272,2,1,1,'FuzzCulture','Fuzzculture is a two piece Electronica outfit consisting of Arsh Sharma (Also of The Circus) and Srijan Mahajan (Also of Half Step Down,Parikrama and Cyanide).\r\n\r\n','fuzzculture@gmail.com','http://www.facebook.com/fuzzculture/','','http://soundcloud.com/fuzzculture','','0','0',0,NULL,1,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-10-09 12:55:54',279,'[\"fuzzculture@gmail.com\"]','[\"Arsh Sharma-9818804297, Srijan Mahajan-9871301102\"]','fuzzculture'),(1273,0,3,3,'WAZULU THE ILL DRAVIDIAN + HE RA','Originally from Bangalore India, Wazulu represents his Dravidian roots by fusing Indian street rhythms with beats that drop so deep he brings new meaning to the concept of owning a swing in hip hop music.\r\n\r\nTraditional melodies of exotic instruments and mystical voices, layered between the spacious sway of rhythmic pendulums rooted within flavors of the urban, Wazulu\'s music has the power to move any listener into a staccato, slow-motion bounce that can only be resurrected from the depths of the earth.\r\n\r\nHe is joined by DJ HeRa - bboy, community organiser, and founder/ director of Tiny Drops Hip-Hop Community Center. He says, \'I\'m just another dude from the block. My journey has been magical as it\'s taking place in the universe and I\'m able to feel both the physical and metaphysical - so its nice to be in a dance between both worlds, instead of being just stuck in one.','','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','wazulu-the-ill-dravidian-he-ra'),(1276,0,2,2,'LIFESAVER','A Blues Rock band that puts together the most energetic performances mixed with soul...\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/Lifesaverblues','http://www.myspace.com/lifesaverblues','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','lifesaver'),(1278,0,26,26,'Korn','Korn will never forget where they came from: a dark place where salvation arrives in the form of twisted, throbbing guitar riffs, syncopated chaotic funk beats, a schizophrenic bass thump and an unmistakable cathartic howl. Emerging from the depths of Bakersfield, California with a sound unlike any other in 1994, Korn have been able to cement themselves as one of the most important bands in rock n\' roll history.\r\n\r\nOver the course of eight full-length releases, Korn have sold in excess of 30 million albums and played countless sold-out shows worldwide. They\'ve won two Grammysone for Best Short Form Video for \"Freak on a Leash\" from 1998s Follow the Leader and one for Best Metal Performance for \"Here to Stay,\" from 2002s Untouchablesand have launched a massively successful festival of their own, The Family Values Tour. However, despite all their massive success and accolades, Korn haven\'t lost hold of the savage, raw energy that made them such a crucial band for diehard rock and metal fans. Korn are one of the preeminent voices of this generation.\r\n\r\nTheir ninth offering, Korn III Remember Who You Are, is their first effort for brand new label home, Roadrunner Records, and it bursts at the seams with that very feeling that defined the band from the get-go. Each song unleashes an uneasiness reminiscent of Korn\'s earliest and most unbridled material, but theres also a modern refinement that\'s epic in its execution. Korn definitely don\'t lose sight of their roots on Remember Who You Are, but they also venture into uncharted darkness. All that truly matters is where they\'re going. The album strikes a balance between their past and their future, as it finds the band reuniting with producer Ross Robinson, who manned the boards for their first two records, all the while joining forces with Roadrunner Records, the worlds leading rock label.\r\n\r\nWith Korn III  Remember Who You Are, it\'s their time...\r\n\r\nKorn bleed with unsettling and unpredictable aggression on Remember Who You Are\'s 10 tracks. \"Oildale (Leave Me Alone)\" buzzes with an eerie clean guitar that slowly gives way to a steamrolling bass and riff assault. \"Move On\" morphs from a myriad of creaking tones into an explosive vocal freak-out that\'s impossible not to connect with it on a visceral level. Then there\'s the neck-snapping \"Fear Is A Place to Live\" tempering deadly guitar dissonance with an unforgettable chorus. This is Korn reborn.\r\n\r\n\"This album is a reflection of us being a band since 1993,\" says vocalist Jonathan Davis. \"We worked hard on the previous records, and we experimented a lot. For Remember Who You Are, the four of us got together in a small room with the intention of writing an old school Korn record. This album is a perfect mixture of everything we\'ve done, and this version of the band is the best ever.\" It\'s as if Korn revisited their storied beginnings, but as a wiser, tighter and more precise outfit blessed with the benefit of experience.\r\n\r\nIn order to tap into the chaos that made their self-titled debut a modern classic, the band enlisted the help of the man who helmed Korn and Life is Peachyproducer Ross Robinson, whose goal was to bring Korn back to square one. He undoubtedly succeeded. Davis had an intense and invigorating recording session. \"Ross helped us remember what we used to do this for,\" the singer says. \"It was more psychological than anything. Ross was right there pushing me and he drove me insane. I sing about a lot of things that hit really close to my heart and he knew how to trigger that. I nearly fucking broke down at the end of almost every song, but I got it all out.\"\r\n\r\nFor guitarist James \"Munky\" Shaffer, the experience was no different. He elaborates, \"Teaming up with Ross has brought that raw, emotional feeling back to the music. Ross is the only person in the world that\'s ever been able to draw us to that place. He reminds us why we\'re here, why these songs are important to our fans and why what we do as a band relates. He made us remember how our music saves lives, and he came into the picture at the perfect time. We had no record label and just wanted to make a great album. Ross stepped in at the right moment to hit the reset button.\"\r\n\r\nHitting that \"reset button\" involved stripping down the process. There would be no Pro-Tools, no tracking separately and no heavy post editing. In order to conjure Remember Who You Are\'s claustrophobic yet wholly organic chaos, Korn recorded on two-inch tape and locked themselves inside a 10x10 room buried within their Los Angeles studio, nicknamed \"The Cat Box.\" Being in such close proximity to one another stirred up a torrent of explosive music. Bassist Reggie \"Fieldy\" Arvizu remembers, \"In that room, even if I turned my bass head, it would hit somebody. Getting back in there was like a family reunion. We felt like brothers again. Being older and setting egos aside, we were able to focus on making the best record we could.\"\r\n\r\nDavis dug deep for cuts like \"The Past\" and \"Never Around.\" About \"The Past,\" the singer says, \"A lot of people dwell on the past, and they feel guilt. There\'s nothing you can do about the past because it\'s gone and it\'s blown up. We\'re here now.\" On Korn III  Remember Who You Are, Davis is fully present and at his most vitriolic, violent and vibrant on the likes of \"Move On\" and \"Are You Ready to Live?\"\r\n\r\nHe goes on, \"I let everything flow, while I was coming up with lyrics. They\'re about me living my life for others when I shouldn\'t, people-pleasing all of the time, stress, guilt and all kinds of emotions we live with everyday that destroy us and tear us down. I write about all of the fake people around us and how I always try to fix other people\'s problems. I write what I feel, and it comes out naturally. I\'ve got a lot of shit built up inside me; that doesn\'t go away.\"\r\n\r\nEven though Korn went back to square one, they continue to break new ground. In a career marked by innovation, they still smash boundaries. Munky even fingerpicks certain instrumental passages, while trying out new tones on echo-y soundscapes. \"The heavier I play, the more you can hear the aggression. The lighter I pick, the lighter the mood is, he said. I used vintage guitars, echos, long delays and reverbs. When we did the first two records, we broke the music down to a completely emotional beast. Through the years, we started to experiment with vocal harmonies and more orchestrated pieces. Recording this album, we brought that knowledge into the raw emotion of what we already knew. You hear the melodies and layers, but it still comes from a very primitive Korn.\"\r\n\r\nThat primitive Korn includes drummer Ray Luzier, who became Korn\'s touring drummer in late 2007 and was made an official member in 2009. On cuts like the deadly \"Fear Is A Place To Live,\" he propels the aggression. Fieldy says, \"Ray is like the missing Korn member we never had. He just fits so well. When we found him, it just clicked because his playing sounds like Korn. He plays with me, and the way that he plays is exactly what I needed. We know what we\'re doing on stage with each other, and everybody\'s on the same page. I\'ve waited my whole career for Korn to sound like we do now.\"\r\n\r\nKorn may have changed members with Brian \"Head\" Welch and David Silveria departing in 2005 and 2006 respectively, but Jonathan, Munky, Fieldy and Ray capture the feeling that was there in the beginning.\r\n\r\nFor Davis, the album name covers it all. \"It comes down to one question: \'Who the fuck am I?\' It\'s about remembering where we came from. The title sums up everything I\'m talking about lyrically. During the first two records, we were kids, and we didn\'t have anything. We were making music, having fun and not worrying. I went back to that place where I wasn\'t worried. I wanted to be completely honest with my feelings, express myself and let them out. People get so wrapped up in social communities, the Internet and technology that they forget who they are and what life\'s really about. I fucking forgot who I was until I did this record. This album is just a bass, a guitar, drums and my vocals. I look at the records we\'ve done as slots in time, and I believe Remember Who You Are is very special.\"\r\n\r\nThe album captures the band\'s legendary performance style that\'s ignited crowds worldwide on stages ranging from OZZfest and Projekt Revolution to Woodstock and Download. It\'s the same spirit that gave pop culture hits such as \"Blind,\" \"A.D.I.D.A.S.,\" \"Got the Life,\" \"Falling Away from Me\" and \"Twisted Transistor.\" Its clear, however, that Korn III  Remember Who You Are is another thrilling chapter being etched into Korns already impressive history.\r\n\r\n\"There\'s that timeless space that we enter where nothing else matters on stage,\" says Munky. \"It\'s us, the crowd and the music. We lose track of where we are and who we are, and it\'s just a timeless shared space between us and the audience. We lose ourselves in the music. I want fans to lose themselves in the new music by forgetting about any problems or anything going on in their minds and let their hearts hear it. It\'s the same experience that I get when I\'m on stage.\"\r\n\r\nThe process brought them back to the beginning, but it also encouraged serious growth. Everyone is locked in like never before. Fieldy adds, \"We want to take you on a rollercoaster with this record. There are spacey and weird parts where the bass can breathe and there are some heavy moments. On Remember Who You Are, I\'m doing what I really wanted to do on our first record.\"\r\n\r\nIn the end, this is for the people that made Kornthe millions of kids worldwide that buy every record, wear every shirt and never miss a show. Davis concludes, \"I love doing what I do. I love helping kids. I love hearing fans say, \'You got me through this or that.\' It makes me feel like I\'ve done something positive. I want kids to feel what I\'m saying and really hear it. I\'d love for the new songs to provoke them to think about what goes on around them. We\'re very fortunate to keep doing what we\'re doing, still be relevant and create music that invokes feelings from people.\"\r\n\r\nWith music this powerful, no one will ever forget who Korn are.','amy@roadrunnerrecords.com','http://www.facebook.com/korn','korn.com','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','korn'),(1279,0,2,2,'Hipnotribe','The band was formed in January 2008 by brothers Naresh and Paresh Kamath who felt they were missing out on the live gig action post Bombay Black!\r\n\r\nThe members of Hipnotribe are all heroes on their respective instruments. Kurt Peters is the prodigal drummer son of jazz legend Karl Peters. Abhijit Nalani on keyboards is the guy behind most of the bollywood smash hits! He is also a master funker! Sankarshan Kini (Shanks) plays countless instruments (guitar, keyboards, flute, violin etc...Phew!). Sanket Naik, also the youngest in the band, is the percussion guru or \'Tablaman\' as he likes to be called. \r\n\r\nA unique ensemble which inculcates rock, funk, jazz and more!','Shazneen Acharia - # 98204 41075, shazneen@gmail.com ','https://www.facebook.com/Hipnotribe','','','','0','36',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','hipnotribe'),(1280,0,2,2,'Hipnotribe','The band was formed in January 2008 by brothers Naresh and Paresh Kamath who felt they were missing out on the live gig action post Bombay Black!\r\n\r\nThe members of Hipnotribe are all heroes on their respective instruments. Kurt Peters is the prodigal drummer son of jazz legend Karl Peters. Abhijit Nalani on keyboards is the guy behind most of the bollywood smash hits! He is also a master funker! Sankarshan Kini (Shanks) plays countless instruments (guitar, keyboards, flute, violin etc...Phew!). Sanket Naik, also the youngest in the band, is the percussion guru or \'Tablaman\' as he likes to be called. \r\n\r\nA unique ensemble which inculcates rock, funk, jazz and more!','Shazneen Acharia - # 98204 41075, shazneen@gmail.com ','https://www.facebook.com/Hipnotribe','','','','0','36',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','hipnotribe-1'),(1281,0,1,1,'Rum and Strings','','','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rum-and-strings'),(1282,0,29,29,'The Anupam Roy Band','ocals- Anupam Roy\r\n\r\nGuitar- Ronodeep Bose\r\n\r\nGuitar - Subhodip Banerjee\r\n\r\nBass- Roheet Mukherjee\r\n\r\nKeyboards- Nabarun Bose\r\n\r\nDrums- Sandipan Parial\r\n\r\nManager- Rana Singharoy\r\n\r\nContact us: 9836087757\r\n','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Anupam-Roy-Band/230728843611338?sk=info','bandedge.in','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-anupam-roy-band'),(1283,0,3,3,'FlitterMaus ','\"Flittermaus\" was formed in 2010 when Anand,Leslie,Surya and Denson came together with the intention of creating real wacky alternative music. The four of us have been jamming and playing together for a while, Ankita joined in for vocal duties. . . . . . . . . . The band members all come from various music backgrounds with Anand having experiences in playing for virtually all kinds of genres, Leslie and Surya evolved from the ashes of early thrash metal into alternative music while Ankita has her roots in western classical. . . . . . . . . The band has been working on original music as well, you could call the music \'Indie\' with layered Guitars,fillers and lots of soundscapes which make the songs very unpredictable with a pinch of progressive stuff as well. . . . . . . . . . The Agenda for now is to play as many gigs as possible and to contribute to the slowly upcoming Alternative music scene in India >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Flittermaus are: Ankita - Vocals Surya - Guitars and Backing Vocals Denson - Bass Leslie - Guitars and Backing Vocals Anand - Drums and Percussion >>>>>>>>>>>> A Few Influences to name A Perfect circle, Deftones, Stone Temple Pilots,Tool,Incubus,Guano Apes,Evanescence etc. Other influences include the works of Israel Regardie, Aleister Crowley and Arthur Waite. Sounds like? Alternative!!!','','https://www.facebook.com/flitter.maus.9','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','flittermaus'),(1284,0,68,68,'Armin Van Buuren','Armin van Buuren has been named number one in the prestigious DJ MAG Top 100 poll four times in a row, as the first DJ in the history of the DJ Magazine and an indication of his prolific output over the more than 14 years hes been djing and producing. Being the official Worlds Most Popular DJ is just one of his many achievements, but the driving force behind his success is an overriding passion for dance music.\r\n\r\nA State of Trance\r\nThe Dutchman discovered a passion for dance music by listening to mix-tapes and radio shows, and taught himself how to create his own. 20 years later, his very own radio show A State of Trance has grown out to legendary heights. Nowadays, 15 million listeners tune into his 2 hour selection of trance and progressive, every week. For 9 years in a row and more than 450 episodes already, the A State of Trance show has been and still is a weekly highlight to many dance music lovers. \r\n\r\nAwards & Accolades\r\nEven a basic list of recent successes reads like a lifetime of work. Armin van Buuren isnt just the number one on the critically acclaimed DJ Mag Top 100, but also holds the Best Global DJ and Best Trance Artist title, awarded to him at the International Dance Music Awards and Beatport Awards, respectively. Radio show A State of Trance received the IDMA for Best Mix Radio Show for 5 years in a row. Furthermore, Armin was awarded for Best Podcast, became the most popular International DJ at Australia\'s Sony inthemix DJ Poll and, in March 2010, received the Gouden Harp, the highest distinction a Dutch artist can get. \r\n\r\nAlbums\r\nArmin van Buuren has delivered four successful artist albums so far, 76, Shivers, Imagine and 2010 album \'Mirage\'. As the first dance artist in Dutch music history, his Imagine entered the Dutch Album Top 100 Chart at number one. Hit singles Going Wrong, In & Out of Love, Unforgivable and Never Say Never didnt only haunt the charts, but also became favourites of the dance crowd. The music video of In & Out of Love, featuring Dutch singer Sharon den Adel, received more than 67 million views on YouTube, holding the first position on the Dutch Top 10 of most viewed videos of all-time. Armins back catalogue, including Blue Fear, Communication, The Sound of Goodbye, Shivers, UEFA Youth Championship theme Rush Hour, Burned With Desire, Exhale, Yet Another Day en This World Is Watching Me, is full of timeless tracks that wear that classic-tag and keep returning to the clubs. But, as a true artist befits, Armin keeps creating new music and has now released his fourth artist album, \'Mirage\'. For the album, Armin collaborated with the likes of BT, Christian Burns, Ferry Corsten, Adam Young and Nadia Ali. After the first single, Full Focus, the second release of the album was a collaboration with Sophie Ellis-Bextor, Not Giving Up On Love. The music video for the track was shot on party island Ibiza and includes shots of Club Amnesia, where Armin holds his residency. \r\n\r\nPerformances & Armin Only \r\nBeing the world\'s number 1 DJ sees the Dutch DJ perform at some of the world\'s biggest and best festivals, clubs, events and shows. One of the highlights of 2010 was Armin\'s DJ set at the Museumplein in Amsterdam in July, during the honoring of the Dutch soccer team. Even though the national team lost in the FIFA Worldcup, they partied like they were the absolute winners, and so did the 200.000 strong crowd. \r\n\r\nSold-out shows for Armin Only in 2005 and 2006 created eager anticipation of the third edition, which kicked off in a sold-out Jaarbeurs in Utrecht in 2008; over 16,000 fans attended and were enthralled by the DJs nine hour set, under the name of Imagine. For his fourth artist album, Mirage, Armin will kick off another Armin Only World tour. After the first show in the sold-out Jaarbeurs in Utrecht on November 13th, Armin will continue to travel the globe with shows in 15 different countries, ranging from Australia to Ukraine, Argentina, Libanon and more. ','','https://www.facebook.com/arminvanbuuren','arminvanbuuren.com','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','armin-van-buuren'),(1285,0,1,1,'DJ AUSTIN','','','','','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-austin'),(1302,0,0,0,'Strawberry Soul','We play about 1-2 times a month so keep your eyes opened for new gigs!\r\n\r\n*********************\r\nBand members\' Bios:\r\n*********************\r\n\r\nScott Gibson: Drums, Vocals\r\n\r\nMy parents had a 45 collection including the Beatles, Beach Boys, and the Monkees and I played them until they were unplayable. Watching the Monkees and Beatles cartoons regularly as a child made me want to play music and be a rock star. I began playing saxophone in the 4th grade and I bought my first guitar in 1989 and then my first drum kit in 1990. I played in heavy metal and punk bands on some combination of guitar, bass guitar, drums, and lead vocals from 1990-1996. I got a BA in music in 1999 and since then have been playing music in churches and rock bands. I recently made an 18 track CD of my own music. There is nothing like playing live though and Get Back gives me the opportunity to get back to the music that started it all for me!\r\n\r\nBill \"Slash\", \"Dr. Thunder\" Legg: Bass, Acoustic Guitar, Vocals\r\n\r\nI remember first hearing the Beatles on the Ed Sullivan show, and the next day at school, that was all we could talk about. We played Please Please Me over and over again. My dad was a barbershop singer, and I was in the choir, so I was really taken by the Beatles great harmonies. Ive been playing both classical and rock guitar since high school, and I really love the timelessness of the Beatles songs. Theyre good songs, thats why people are still playing them now.\r\n\r\nPrashant Marathay: Electric Guitar, Vocals\r\n\r\nAs I was growing up there was never much emphasis placed on the fine arts. We sang and played instruments only because it was a class in school. I discovered the Beatles in High School, and I listened to their songs on tape every day and night for over a year. I loved the melodies, the words, the complexity, the variety, Ive been a fan ever since. We would sing Beatles songs on every road trip, much to the regret of our high school science teacher. I picked up the guitar because I wanted to play Ticket to Ride. The music kept pushing me to do more and more. The Beatles are really timeless. Its great to play great music with great people. I hope you enjoy it as much as we enjoy playing it.\r\n\r\nRob \"Robtronic\" Miller: Lead Guitar, Harmonica\r\n\r\nAwaiting Bio from Rob. Basically, Rob loves music and and plays a mean guitar.','','','http://www.StrawberrySouls.com','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','strawberry-soul'),(1303,0,2,2,'SuperVibe','SuperVibe is a Super- alternative band from Mumbai who love\r\nplaying some melodious and groovy music for their crowd.\r\nHaving played around the country at the best of venues and competitions\r\nsince 2010 in, they\'ve always tried to add colour and emotion in every\r\noriginal or cover that they play.\r\nInfluences ranging from U2, Police, Mutemath, John Mayer (and the list\r\nkeeps on increasing), SuperVibe believes in playing some positive and\r\nhonest music in its soulful form.\r\nSpreading their music and vibe whenever they go, the best way to experience\r\nand \'Feel the Vibe\' is to watch the band perform doing what they are best at.. Peace +\r\n\r\nFor Bookings Contact: Jeremiah +919819023441.\r\n','','https://www.facebook.com/supervibe','http://www.supervibe.in','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','supervibe'),(1304,0,0,0,'DJ NOEL','As the most well-known and established Hardstyle artist from the \'Lone Star State\'. He has graced the stage at almost every massive and hard dance party thrown in Texas and played all over Denmark since 2004. He has performed along side artist such as Bass Modulators, Showtek, JDX, DJ Issac, HeadHunterz, Flarup, and Used & Abused just to name a few. In 2010 he was signed to the most exclusive agency for hard dance in the USA \"Corson Agency\". There is a reason why he is Number #1 in the Hardstyle scene in Texas. His passion and dedication is enough to explain this title. As for the new decade, Noel has taken his passion to the next level and begun producing his own signature tracks. ','','https://www.facebook.com/DJNOELMUSIC/info','http://www.corsonagency.com/artist/djnoel','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-noel'),(1305,0,2,2,'Dj Aqueel','DJ Aqeel, an artist who\'s redefined the term DJ/ Producer in the last decade and is going stronger by the second and rocking the dance floors around the world.\r\n \r\nAqeel is the most sought after DJ and has played in more countries that most people can name. He is also the only Indian DJ to fill up concert size venues internationally. Besides playing for every celebrity one can imagine, he has been the only DJ to play twice at the World Economic Forum in Davos (Swiss) representing India and entertaining the likes of Bill Clinton, Kofi Annan etc.\r\n \r\nAs a Producer he has given the world some of the best remixes. His 8 albums sold over 7 million copies worldwide redefining the landscape Bollywood music forever. His seventh album is due for release in mid 2010. Besides his albums he has also introduced the first ever DJ owned record label in the country under the brand Power Play Records and has released compilations albums featuring some Indias finest talent.\r\n \r\nAlso to his credit he has introducing concept of The Super Club in India under the brand Poison that had franchises in Hyderabad & Goa as well as a high end exclusive members club under the name Bling at one of Mumbais upmarket 5 star hotels The Leela.\r\n \r\nAqeels newest Venture is Hype - Indias first luxury nightclub presenting the finest entertainment and redefining standards of lifestyle clubbing. The look and feel of this hedonistic venue is a customized luxury den with state of the art sound, lights, dcor with a world class Food & Beverage Concept and Design.\r\n \r\nExpect the unexpected from this Top Notch DJ/Producer and Business Honcho in the near future.','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Dj-Aqeel/57250454395','http://www.djaqeel.com/','','','0','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-aqueel'),(1306,0,114,114,'Chris Carrier','There are two kinds of DJs: those whose goal is to make a name for themselves and those whose goal is to make music - and let the rest follow. Parisian Chris Carrier is among the latter. For more than a dozen years he\'s been an underground icon, churning out more than one hundred records and remixes for a host of labels. Too busy working to chase a spot in the limelight, Carrier is nevertheless rightly revered as one of the most gifted, prolific producers on the dance scene. Refusing to restrict his output to one genre or one school of thought, Carrier has dabbled freely in everything from house to hip hop, drum \'n\'bass to minimal, techno to electro. Most DJ shave one label - if at all - but Chris is so restlessly creative he\'s founded a whole fistful of labels over the course of his career, including the renowned Adult Only imprint, Chronobrain, Combustible, Taka, X86 and Direct Art. He has also worked under more than a fifteen aliases. However, youthful notions of being a baker (\"I like cakes,\" he says) lost out to music when he discovered the early 90s techno rave scene and began to DJ. Driven to be the master of his musical destiny, Chris quickly learned to produce and created pioneering techno outlet Chronobrain with Guillaume La Tortue. For seven-odd years Chris devoted himself the label, and its offshoots including house-oriented Taka and drum \'n\' bass imprint X86.However, his love for rave culture led him back towards more purely creative work. From 2003 onwards Chris has founded new labels Adult Only and Catwash, as well as bringing his vision to Get Physical, Crack & Speed, Brique Rouge, Robsoul, Kill Brique and - most recently - Freak n\' Chic. This has put the underground star firmly in the forefront of the new French electronic movement, bringing his diverse style to the sexy, deep, techy house vibes that dominate the scene. Chris is more sought-after than ever for his DJ skills - he\'s penetrated thenotorious US market with gigs in Georgia, San Francisco, Denver, Las Vegas and Miami. And plays in Europe\'s clubbing capitals: London, Paris, Madrid, Amsterdam and Milan, to name a few. Look out for his gigs, and Chris\'s forthcoming remix of Matthew Dear\'s Dog Days - the first of many exciting projects for this unique artist in 2008. DISCO : 2010 Robsoul / Motel connection, P-weeks. Minority Robsoul /Album Gosse de Paris OFF / Jeudi EP 2009 Remix : Motel Connection All inn / Rills Thirty one Tweenty / Gavin Herlihy Catwash Hors Serie 01 / Pixie in the Fridge / Miss Jools Objazz 02 / Butangoy / Felipe Venegas Bass Culture 02 / Mon Amour / Alex Picone OFF 09 / Snake Seven / Luca Doobie, Andre Crom Readymade Digi 01 / Chord Wave / Vernon Polyphonics / Animal House / C-Rock Esperanza / Soul Central 1 / Kasper Nervous records / Every Now And Then / Ralph Falcon Hypercolour Digi 04 / Caballo / Mirco Violi Original : Silver Network / Chakka \"Jef K\" Si