 voice whom the audience turn to for their musical education, to his own evolution and adaptation as an artist in the scene, Ankytrixx truly represents the sound of Indian EDM.\r\n\r\nFor more than a decade, Ankit has fast forwarded himself into one of the most contemporary and exciting acts in these modern times.A disco goers delight, hes has smiling crowds blissfully lost in speedy, jump-at-you performances with melodic goodness amplified in extravagant, chunky bass lines. His energetic and emotional shows capture the audience, as his energy flows off the console infecting them with euphoric dance floor power. \r\n\r\nCurrently Ankytrixx is enjoying superstar status as the chosen beat freak to play at swanky and sold-out venues in India like The Blue Frog, Pacha, Tantra, F Bar, Aurus and many more! \r\n\r\nHe has taken his brand of foot-stomping music to international clubs in Amsterdam, Berlin, Singapore, Bangkok, and Colombo while also headlining in some of the most prestigious festivals, like A.D.E Amsterdam Dance Event 2011, Sunburn (2010, 2011), Sula Fest 2012, Universal Religion (2009,2010,2011), Global Underground India (2011) and many more. \r\n\r\n2012 promises to be a big year for the dance floor blaster, with appearances at Universal Religion in Nepal and Tree of Life in Turkey, just to start! Catch him scorching the dance floor this European summer, with appearances in Clubs in Istanbul, Asmterdam, Berlin, Brussels and more!! \r\n\r\nIn recent times Ankytrixx has shared stage space with legends of music spanning several genres of EDM. From John Digweed and Dave Seaman, to Armin Van Buren, Richie Hawtin, Axwell and Spartaque to Infected Mushroom, Ace Ventura, Liquid Soul, Zen Mechanics and many more! \r\n\r\nThe maestro spins his magic overlapping several EDM genres seamlessly, taking you on musical journeys through house, techno, progressive and psychedelic. Ankytrixx delivers consistently, both in terms of technique and tune, providing an overall performance package like very few DJs do.\r\n','','https://www.facebook.com/Ankytrixx','http://www.youtube.com/ankytrixx','http://www.soundcloud.com/ankytrixx','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','3'),(1311,0,29,29,'The Supersonics','What people have said about The Supersonics: \r\n\r\n\"Top Ten Artists to Watch For\" - Rolling Stone Magazine, India, November 2008 \r\n\r\n\"Must Have Download\" - Rolling Stone Magazine, India, October 2008; on the single \'In Memory Of\', featured on HMV Saregama\'s Kolkata Underground album. \r\n\r\n\'\'These nice guys from Kolkata\'s burgeoning music scene are making all the right noises and if this song is any indication, their album is worth watching for\'\' - Rolling Stone Magazine, India, May 2009; on \'Policemen and Nice Guys\', the first single from Maby Baking. \r\n\r\n\"Rhythm heavy melodies with mid-song tempo changes and a driving bass line all combined to create one of the most refreshing live sounds of the year so far\" - Indiecision.com, October 2008 \r\n\r\n\'\'Damn I love them.\" - Jay Singh (Pink Noise/Skinny Alley) \r\n\r\n\"Trust me, the Supersonics are as good as it gets. Their sound is no different from what\'s taking place abroad. It\'s a pleasure recording them.\" - Miti Adhikari, Producer - Maby Baking.','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-supersonics'),(1312,0,91,91,'Max Clouth Clan & Friends','Max Clouth is a musician who is deeply interested in all forms of musical expression. Born 1985, he had the chance to travel to southern Europe, US, Africa and the Middle East and experience the cultural diversity of the world in his early childhood. After graduating at Freie Waldorfschule Frankfurt, Max enrolled at Mainz University to study jazz guitar with Marc - Oliver Klenk and Norbert Scholly. \r\n\r\nParallel to his studies he performed with singers, ensembles and dancers, often playing a hard rock gig after a jazz performance. In 2008 Max changed to Dresden University where he continued his studies with Professor Ralf Beutler and Stephan Bormann and received his diploma degree in 2009. Inspired by Shakti, the influential indo jazz ensemble of John McLaughlin and Zakir Hussain, Max started learning about the Indian system of raga and tala with violinist Indradeep Ghosh. In October 2009 he enrolled at Sangit Mahabharati Music School in Mumbai (Bombay) to study Indian Classical Music with Pandit Nayan Ghosh. \r\n\r\nBesides his studies Max regularly performs in India and Europe in a solo format and with musicians like Indradeep Ghosh (violin), Hindol Deb (sitar), Nirmalya Roy, Omprakash Pandey, Niraj Kumar, Pt Shankha Chatterjee (tabla), Torsten de Winkel (guitar), Rafael Sotomayor (hang), Marc-Inti Mnnel (bass), Vaibhav Wavikar and Geronimo Dehler (perc).\r\n\r\nIn 2010, luthier Philipp Neumann and Max designed a double neck acoustic guitar equipped with 12 sympathetic strings. The Lotus Guitar, named after stylized lotus petals on the body and neck of the guitar, is a unique instrument providing an incredible variety of colours from warm nylon string sounds to oud or sarod-like microtonal shades to the silvery ring of the sympathetic strings. The Lotus Guitar has been a great success so far, being used regularly in Max\'s performances, including his India tour in January 2012.','','','	http://max-clouth.net','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','max-clouth-clan-friends'),(1313,0,0,0,'Sonic Species','Signed to Alchemy Records in 2008 as a duo, their first release - \'Lost Transmission\' - was an instant hit across the globe. \'Bend the Future\' was released in 2009 on Neurobiotic Records, and again became one of the festival anthems of the summer. Sonic Species debut EP \'Machina Terra\' was finally released in the summer of 2010 on Alchemy Records and was again proved popular through the many re-releases of the self-named title track.\r\n\r\nWith the departure of Alex Story, Sonic Species continues forward as the solo project of Joe Markendale as he carves new epic paths through modern psychedelic trance. Having performed at some of the most heavyweight international psychedelic events, Sonic Species continues to storm dancefloors with dynamic and powerful live sets. The debut album will be released in April 2012.','','http://www.facebook.com/sonicspecies','http://www.myspace.com/sonicspecies','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sonic-species'),(1314,0,1,1,'Sur','SUR consists of musicians who are a blend of experience and youth. They are comprised of the classic formation of Bass, Drums, Guitar and Vocals along with Mridangam/Tabla, percussions, keyboards and Flute. Suresh Mendoza, is on the bass. His intelligent attack and stylings are a crucial aspect of the bands sound. Glenn Fernandes, is on guitars and with his expressive licks, powerful rhythms and creative melodic ideas provides a unique sound and feel to the band. \r\n\r\nNitin Ramesh, has machine-guntiming on the drums, yet still can lace each beat with an infectious groove. The lead vocalist, Arunima Bhattacharya, has trained in Hindustani Classical Music since childhood and weaves a spell with her melodious voice. Gautam Sharma is on Mridangam/Tabla and percussion, Shashank Acharya is on Flute and Umang Doshi, is on Keyboards. \r\n\r\nThe band has a high energy sound which can be related to genres such as funk-rock, blues, alternative, and jazz, all stylized with Indian Classical ragas and Rhythms. Some of their influences include Indian Folk Music, Jamiroquai, Level 42 etc..','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','sur'),(1315,0,3,3,'DJ Karma','DJ Karma is a pioneering DJ who introduced the Delhi club scenes to Hip Hop & RnB. Thus revolutionizing the circuit with smooth beats and sexy grooves in a time when gigs were entirely oriented around Bollywood and House. \r\n\r\nGrowing up in Dubai, Karma was influenced by the multi-cultural music and was drawn to hip hop. This eventually led him to taking up spinning professionally from 2001. He started throwing jams in Delhi in 2002, attracting fame and attention in other cities as well. A skilled emcee (rapper), Karma is known to hype the crowd and evolve the craft with rhymes that transcend easily between Hindi and English. \r\n\r\nHe has been featured on Honey Singh\'s Jhaanjar Kehndi; DJ T-Nu & Amit B\'s Soniye remix; and Worren Webbe\'s Down in Love (nominated Best Pop Song and Best Collaboration for Bite My Music VIMA Awards - Indigo awards). Karma currently represents Urbanatics (DJ Grenville, DJ Cj and DJ Pema) promoting and DJing at major clubs in the city, staying fresh by dropping hits before they break, and keeping it moving with ol\' skool jams too.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/DJ-KARMA/258525084196635','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-karma'),(1316,0,0,0,'Madrobe Walfunction ','','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','madrobe-walfunction'),(1317,0,68,68,'Estiva','Steven Baan, better known as the man behind Estiva, has grown to be one of the most demanded DJs and respected producers in electronic dance music. Operating out of the city of Reeuwijk in western Holland, Stevens flair for a beautiful melodic take on progressive trance has been welcomed with open arms from many thousands in the worldwide EDM scene.\r\n\r\nThe Early Years\r\n\r\nBorn just before Christmas in 1987, Steven was the youngest sibling of three brothers whom had a very healthy childhood and stable upbringing. The passion for music was always embedded in Stevens characteristics as a child, but eventually it blossomed into a keen love for dance music one summer, in his teenage years, with a little help from In Search of Sunrise by Tiesto & A State of Trance from Armin van Buuren. Finding infectious interest in sound design and experimenting with FL Studio, it wasnt long before Steven earned a highly respected position on Enhanced Recordings in 2007 with his first released production by Estiva  Estiva pres. Sunover Stella, a track that cemented a spot on the roster of the ever growing UK label, to which he is still loyal.\r\nAs things really started to move forward for Estiva, having released frequent tracks, the up & coming producer began to gain support from the very role models that first inspired him, achieving nothing short of a dream come true when a collaboration with Marninx named Casa Grande was handpicked for Tiestos 7th Edition of In Search of Sunrise CD Series.\r\nFurther productions such as the Strawberry Fields EP and the Les Fleurs EP attracted attention from global superstars Tiesto, Armin, Ferry Corsten, & Markus Schulz, which was just a mark of Stevens hard work in the studio and the intelligence in finding the catchy melodic progressive style that so many labels wanted a piece of, including Armada, Anjunabeats, Coldharbour, & Fraction.\r\nBetween 2009 and early 2010 another Estiva EP was released on Enhanced, I Feel Fine and yet again showcased Stevens outstanding talents and again gathered big support, this time including Above & Beyond. The amazing collaboration with rising star Temple One November lovely and more Estiva hits in the form of Friends & Enemies, The Kingdom, & Adamas quickly became Estivas trademark pieces.\r\n\r\nProductions & Music\r\n\r\nIn more recent times Steven Baan has begun to unearth his own distinctive sound & style through carefully finding the perfect balance between danceable beats and melodic emotion, using desirable techniques and skills to find the edge in his productions that are nothing short of superb in todays trance & progressive industry. Prior to Estivas Festival EP in early 2011, Steven had already gained support from the greats including Armin van Buuren & Above & Beyond continuingly making trance headlines with huge productions since his start in 2007, although none of which planted enormous interest in the newly branded Estiva, on a global scale, as Festival, Lotus & Make A Wish did. From there on out, Estiva has continued along the path to higher success showcasing his musical talent in many remixes not forgetting the huge chart topper single Next Level. Arguably the biggest Estiva production to date, came in the form of Better Days featuring the outstanding Josie, a beautiful vocalist from the USA and also sister of the one and only Jaren, creditable to tracks such as Unforgettable, Beggin You & Man on The Run. With the success of this release almost immeasurable; all the while Steven gained experience in vocal production and shooting music videos during an overwhelming performance in the North of England, all combining to cement his print on the ever competitive music scene.\r\nAccelerating progress in the studio over the years has been undeniable, which was reflected by Estivas Perfect Ten digital compilation hosted by Enhanced Music. The concept featured ten of the most popular Estiva tracks voted for by thousands of fans, also including an exclusive Estiva rework of I Feel Fine, the track which received the highest percentage of votes.\r\nThe next step on the cards for the young tangible talent is his debut artist album having been working on ideas over the past year. This really will be the next level for Estiva in what seems a fast flowing journey to the top of the electronic dance podium and will mark only the beginning of a hugely triumphant music career.\r\n\r\nPerformances & Schedule\r\n\r\nEstiva joined Assured Artists in 2010 and since then, he has become one of the most sort after names on the Assured roster. Since, landing massive gigs from Cyprus to Los Angeles last year, Estiva has established himself as a highly charismatic DJ that personalizes each performance through emotional attachment to the audience. The most special part of playing music that I have written & produced, is that its personal to me, and to see people enjoying when I play it, creates an amazing connection between myself and the crowd. One highlight for Estiva was the huge performance at global electronic dance festival, Nature One, having played to an overwhelming crowd of 5,000 people.\r\nSome years back, being a part of the Luminosity line-up Before the Energy in 2009 in Utrecht, The Netherlands, was a huge leap into the premier league of DJ performances for the young Estiva. At present, having performed at Armin van Buurens groundbreaking ASOT500 celebration, also in Holland in 2011, Estiva has firmly established himself as one of the most popular DJs in the trance & progressive genre.\r\nHaving also appeared at Gatecrasher, alongside Armin in Germany and at Digital Society over in the UK, Estivas schedule has almost fully fledged of late, meaning DJ appearances in North America, Mexico, South Africa, Indonesia, and all over Europe, which judging by achievements so far, is only the beginning for the ever so talented individual.','steven@estiva-music.com','http://www.facebook.com/EstivaOfficial','http://www.estiva-music.com','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','estiva'),(1318,0,0,0,'Thompson Andrews','Thomson Andrews is an Indie Contemporary R&B Singer/Songwriter, performer and a Recording Artist. His songs are his creative innovations which portray a resemblance to the objects, people & feelings that motivate him','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/thomson-andrews','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','thompson-andrews'),(1319,0,1,1,'The Sufi Gospel Project','The Sufi Gospel Project, the brainchild of singer Sonam Kalra, blends together the many voices of language, religion and music to create one voice- the voice of faith.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Sufi-Gospel-Projectsu','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-sufi-gospel-project'),(1320,0,4,4,'Blend No. 3220  ','Blend No.3220 was formed around mid 2011 to make some noise. \r\n\r\nWhat started out as inebriated banter accompanied by unplugged instruments, was soon converted into an electric set up with a raw amplified sound reminiscent of the 60s. \r\n\r\nEssentially the band performs original music, loosely based around very early street blues Yet the catch here is that most of their music is composed, not before, but during their live performances!\r\n\r\nWith randomly changing set-lists, the band simply loves to entertain people by pumping the energy levels through the roof with provocative lyrics and wailing instrumentals backed by a super tight rhythm section. \r\n\r\nA no-nonsense performance oriented band that keeps things real dirty and real cold And most importantly always keeps one guessing What Next?\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Blend-No3220/281640755206866','','','https://www.reverbnation.com/blendno3220','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','blend-no-3220'),(1321,0,0,0,'Functuation','','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','functuation'),(1322,0,2,2,'Gary Lawyer','Gary Lawyer is an Indian singer, who started his career as a night club singer in New York. He is the first Indian to be signed for a western album outside India. Lawyer has a bass baritone, who sings in the tenor range which garnered him recognition and a stint with Bollywood.','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Gary-Lawyer/147949288636379?ref=ts','http://www.garylawyermusic.com','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','gary-lawyer'),(1323,0,0,0,'Horjwlai ','We\'re a metal band from agartala, tripura, India. Its been few years now we have been doin these gigs n have worked really hard but we need support to grow..please visit our website, www.myspace.com/horjwlai, www.reverbnation/horjwlai and listen to the songs we made..\r\n\r\nHorjwlai was formed in 2007 with Ronald (guitar), Chiranjib (bass) and Dbakar (drums) with metal music as our forte. Being young we were full of energy and ready to release the potential within us this came to pass when Tomson(vocals) and Pitra(guitar) joined the band.\r\nEarly on, we experimented with a variety of genres trying to figure out what sound would best translate what we felt inside and in 2008 we came to realise that metal and its sub genres were what we related to most.\r\n\r\nComing from Tripura, a place where there\'s no western music culture, has been very challenging though now things are beginning to change as we move towards some sort of basic development. Though a simple thing like organizing a western music concert here is still very hard to do given the state of affairs, we are determined to make a change and are doing so by creating music that incorporates the heavy sounds of metal and our own tribal tunes and melodies. Whether we get to play this music in our hometown is to be seen but that is not something holding us back!\r\n\r\nThough Tripura is not a place known for western music, being young we hope we can bring some change in the mindset of the people living here.\r\n\r\nThe three songs you hear, are the fist oc\'s that we made, hope you guys like them. The track \"jong johny jong.\" is a folk metal song sung in our native language Kokborok, that speaks of rejuvenating our culture in our own mother land, Tripura.\r\n\r\nIf you like what you hear please let us know. We are also on the lookout for promoters, financers, manager who see our potential and are willing to support us. Thanks!!!\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Horjwlai/118629541535455','http://www.myspace.com/horjwlai','','http://www.reverbnation/horjwlai','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','horjwlai'),(1324,0,0,0,'Hydrogent','','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Hydrogent/365636300119576?sk=info','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','hydrogent'),(1325,0,29,29,'Krosswindz','We KROSSWINDZ world music band from Calcutta India toured 6 cities in the US in October 2007- Los Angeles,San Fransisco,Seattle,Atlanta,Chicago andJersey City.We played 7 concerts and 1 Live Radio Broadcast 2 hour unplugged concert for Sandusky Radio Seattle-Kevin Mc Donald Presents,\r\n\r\nPrimarily a Classic Rock/folk-fusion band,focusing on world music with soulful songs,lyric oriented.Professionally performing concerts all over the world for the last seventeen years. Krosswindz is the music of Bengal and India with a blend of folk music traditions from around the world.The result- a potpouri of sounds deeply rooted in the soil that touches the heart and speaks the common language of humankind.\r\n\r\nMusic Style- World / Rock, Folk, Ambient Environmental Fusion\r\n\r\nMusical Influences John Mc Laughlin,Santana,Eric Johnson(AUSTIN TEXAS),Jimi Hendrix,Pink Floyd,The Beatles.Miles Davis,Indian Musical influences-Padmashree Protima Barua Pandey(Goalpariya-Assamese Folk Exponent and singer),Rabindranath Tagore,Kishori Amonkar,Bhupen Hazarika,Purno Das Baul,Shubha Mudgal,Abida Parveen,Runa Laila,SD Burman,Abbasuddin Ahmed,Lalon fokir, etc.\r\n\r\nSimilar Artists- Yossou n Dour,Sting,Cranberries,Joni Mitchell,Jimi Hendrix\r\n\r\nArtist History band was formed in 1990,has toured all over the sub-continent and 6 cities in USA playing at major festivals,concerts and clubs and has officially released 12 albums. Two of the most famous Bangla songs of Krosswindz are \"Prithibita Naki Choto Hote hote\" written by Gautam Chatterjee performed by Krosswindz in the album Abar Bocchor Kuri porey and \"Jhiko Jhiko\"-from the album Jhiko Jhiko Krosswindz.\r\n\r\nKrosswindz is renowned for the musical dexterity and virtuoso skill of legendary guitar player Vikramjit Banerjee(tuki)and the unique and mellifluous vocals and gayaki of Chandrani. The band is busy perfoming all over the world along with recording new material for their forthcoming album.\r\n\r\nKrosswindz is an accredited and empanneled band with the ICCR(INDIAN COUNCIL FOR CULTURAL RELATIONS NEW DELHI)and are officially enlisted as a premier band of INDIA and they call us when they need us to represent INDIA in festivals abroad.\r\n\r\nThe band has performed and collaborated with internationally reputed names like HERBIE HANCOCK (USA), SKY HIGH (SWEDEN), RAG FOUNDATION (ENGLAND WALES), TIZIAN JOST(GERMANY), PANDIT RAMESH MISHRA (INDIAN SARENGI PLAYER OF INTERNATIONAL REPUTE), SANJAY MISHRA (CLASSICAL GUITARIST USA), THE JAZZ AMBASSADORS (USA), DAVID DYKSTRA(THE BAUTISA BAND SAN-FRANSISCO).\r\n\r\nThe album TRIBUTE TO ERIC JOHNSON USA (GRAMMY winning guitarist from Austin Texas) features the dazzling guitar work by Tuki (KROSSWINDZ) on the track SPACE GUITAR. Available in USA and at Val Serrie productions site.\r\n\r\nThe album THE MUSIC OF THE GLOBE features two tracks by KROSSWINDZ namely ONE WORLD and MAHUT BONDHU which was re-released in USA by independant Washington based label JOE ANTHONY PRODUCTIONS,this album has gone on to become a hot seller from amazon , itunes and other online merchants apart from being popular at conventional music stores like TOWER.\r\n\r\nKrosswindz has been a pioneer in the band movement in West Bengal and the first bengali project/collaboration with GAUTAM CHATTERJEE(MONI MAMA)of MOHINER GHORAGULI yielded the anthemic hit Prithibita Naki Choto Hote Hote.Released in 1994 the album AABAR BOCHOR KURI POREY has become a staple amongst music lovers. The collaboration happened when Gautam suggested KROSSWINDZ record and perform one track he had written and set tune to in 1993 and eventually the studio sessions yeilded the astonishing new bengali side of KROSSWINDZ.This song has now been remade by Bollywood in the movie GANGSTER and a hindi version is doing the rounds on all music channels.\r\n\r\nKrosswindz has evolved over the early years from being a rock band to a world/fusion band and has gained repute all over the world for its pathbreaking new sound and fresh approach to music.In the early years the band created a tremendous fan following of loyal fans who followed the band and are still avid listeners/audiences, the reputation of the band as being a stupendous live act spread and gigs picked up by the mid nineties and nowadays on an average the band has ten to twelve shows a month.\r\n\r\nThe music of Krosswindz has been featured in numerous documentary films and commercials.Recently the international multi-award winning film THE WAY BACK HOME by film maker SUPRIYO SEN featured the vocals of CHANDRANI(KROSSWINDZ) in the song Ghore Pherar Gaan (written by Gautam Chatterjee from the album Khyapar Gaan) prominently as the Title track and background score for the film.\r\n\r\nThe music of Krosswindz is being aired by major FM stations around the world-BBC in UK, in CALCUTTA RADIO MIRCHI,RED FM,AAMAR FM and ALL INDIA RADIO. In AUSTRALIA pbs FM in MELBOURNE is playing the song ONE WORLD by Krosswindz on their show GLOBAL VILLAGE hosted by ROGER HOLDSWORTH.\r\n\r\nKrosswindz has been on many major national and international TV shows and reputed production houses like the BBC and MTV have covered Krosswindz on innumerable occassions.\r\n\r\nKrosswindz has acted for a feature part in the telefilm called \"Aamra Ebong\" by noted Calcutta actor/director Parambrata Chatterjee where even the soundtrack of the film has songs from the album -MISIKI MISIKI (FOLK-FUSION) Krosswindz. The song \"Morihe Shyam\" from this album is the title song of this tele-film.\r\n\r\nThe band also appears regularly on game shows and interviews on popular Indian TV channels like zee bangla(hau mau khau),Tara Muzik-Take a break and Bandemonium,Sangeet Bangla(metro music and Shudhu Gaane Shudhu Shongeete)etc.Channel S in the UK has telecast a documentary featuring KROSSWINDZ.GAAN BEDHE DOLBAJEE on CTVN PLUS channel.\r\n\r\nKROSSWINDZ has one of the highest record sales in the regional market and has had superhit albums like ONE WORLD,JHIKO JHIKO and MISIKI MISIKI selling lakhs of units.Presently Krosswindz is signed to Indian label SAGARIKA MUSIC. KROSSWINDZ has been on the charts at broadjam.com numerous times and a huge number of people have downloaded the band\'s music from free sites like mp3.com ONE WORLD has entered the Earth Top 10 at Broadjam! ONE WORLD has entered the Production - Mid Tempo Top 10 at Broadjam! ONE WORLD has entered the Pop Top 10 at Broadjam! ONE WORLD has entered the Broadjam #1 Songs Top 10 at Broadjam! ONE WORLD has entered the Production - Female Vocals Top 10 at Broadjam!\r\n\r\nKrosswindz rendition of the song TANGRA TOBU KATON JAYE from the album JHIKO JHIKO has been nominated by an AMERICAN company called JPF(CD BABY) in the BEST FOLK SONG category of their music awards http://www.jpfolks.com/MusicAwards/2006/SongNominees.html\r\n\r\nKrosswindz has one of the largest ammount of fans in the Indian music scene that spread all over the sub-continent and even to other parts of the world like in the USA,UK,MEXICO,IRELAND following the band avidly and listening with admiration.tower records,cd baby and apple i tunes also stock a healthy quota of the music of KROSSWINDZ and the number of fans is growing each day.','','https://www.facebook.com/KROSSWINDZ','http://www.krosswindz.com','http://www.soundclick.com/krosswindz','http://www.myspace.com/krosswindzbengali','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','krosswindz'),(1326,0,1,1,'MONSTERSYNC: S.O.N.R.','S.O.N.R a.k.a Rishi Handa from New Delhi is known for his intuitive ability to captivate the dance floor. His music has an organic feel to it - an influence of having lived on the magical Hawaiian Islands whilst having a love for the great outdoors. S.O.N.Rs DJ sets are atmospheric, bass responsive and intensely groovy.','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','monstersync-sonr'),(1327,0,88,88,'Apparat','If you\'ve kept a close eye on the pulse of electronic music at any point over the last five years, it\'s safe to say you\'ll have encountered Sascha Ring a.k.a Apparat, the Berlin based musician who has been a restless force in contemporary electronic music for over a decade. In that time he\'s released 4 critically acclaimed Apparat albums, alongside a techno masterpiece with long time collaborators Modeselektor as Moderat.\r\n\r\nOften described as the missing link between Steve Reich, Sigur Rs and Radiohead, Apparat will be on a tour across India later this month touching down in Kolkata, Mumbai, Chennai and New Delhi between 24 August and 31 August as part of the ongoing year of Germany in India titled \'Germany and India 2011-2012: Infinite Opportunities\'. The same initiative under which The Indo-German Urban Mela continues to travel across the country and how German electronic trio Jahcoozi came out last year.\r\n\r\nThe tour will be in support of his latest LP \'The Devil\'s Walk\', which saw him bid farewell to more dancefloor focussed productions in favour of the richly melodic tracks that make up most of the album. The album itself was conceived in Mexico with Telefon Tel Avivs Joshua Eustis, and developed in Europe with Patrick Nackt Christensen of EBM outfit Warren Suicide.','zoe.miller@mute.com','http://www.facebook.com/apparat.official','http://www.apparat.net','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','apparat'),(1328,0,0,0,'CID Inc','2011 has seen Henri Hurtig  better known as Cid Inc  step into the spotlight as a producer of electronic music of quality and imagination. His progressive techno style is championed by fellow artists and clubbers alike, while demand for his DJ skills have seen Henri play at some of the best clubs on the global dance scene. 2012 looks set to get even better with several new releases ready to go and increasing support for his label, Replug Records.\r\n\r\nBorn in Finland, raised in Sweden and now based back in Tampere in Finland, Henri began making music in the early \'90s. He first came to prominence when he teamed up with Mathias Bradler to create Mashtronic in 2004, and their productions and hectic DJ schedule soon brought them to an international audience. As well as playing all over Europe and trips to South America, Australia and New Zealand, Mashtronic signed their productions to several of the best labels including Bedrock and Global Underground.\r\n\r\nWith such strong credentials behind him, Henri\'s career as a solo artist hit the ground running. Starting with the \'Sister\' EP on Dyami in 2008, Henri has put together an impressive body of work including releases, collaborations and remixes on labels like Baroque, Inkfish, Tribal Vision, microCastle, Afterglow, AlterImage, Sudbeat, Mcgroove, Flow Vinyl, Iboga and Epsilon Trax. The word prolific hardly does it justice with over 40 Cid Inc original productions and remixes to date, and it\'s not surprising Beatport selected Henri as one of their Progressive House Artists of 2009 alongside other great names like Charlie May, Guy J and Pole Folder.\r\n\r\nIn October 2009 Henri launched Replug Records dedicated to releasing both his own and music from other artists. Cid Inc tracks include \'Defrost\', \'Cloudberries\', \'Filaments\', Caustic\' and \'Blizzard\' alongside contributions from Rich Curtis, Deepfunk and more. There\'s also been the \'Replugged Vol. 1\' compilation, and Henri has a keen eye for signing new talent. Pretty much every Cid Inc hits the upper reaches of the Beatport progressive chart, and Hernan Cattaneo, John Digweed, Nick Warren and Henry Saiz are just a few of the DJs who regularly include Henri\'s tracks in their sets.\r\n\r\nIncreased recognition of his productions over the last two years has provided Henri with a busy DJ diary and he regularly plays all over the world. Highlights from the last 12 months include Exit in Lithuania, the Volt Club in Greece, the Teleportation Festival and Fakel beach party in Russia, and Bahrein in Argentina. August 2011 saw Henri return to the famous B 018 club in Beirut where he played for over four hours, and future bookings include the Spirit of Colours festival in Mexico and the John Digweed after party in Helsinki.\r\n\r\n\"Hypnotic progressive house with a touch of techno and deeper sounds is the music I like to play,\" explains Henri. \"It\'s that hypnotic feel I look for in music. Trips to London, Germany, Spain, Russia, India, South America, Canada and the USA are already being lined up for the coming months as word spreads that Henri\'s skills behind the decks equal those in the studio. He is also part of the recently launched Global Underground World Tours roster.\r\n\r\nThere\'ll be no stopping Henri in 2012 and forthcoming releases in his packed production schedule include the \'Emotional Self\' EP with Lank on microCastle as well as remixes for Henry Saiz\'s Natura Sonoris label, Luis Junior\'s new imprint Mooseekaa, Plastik Park, Flow Vinyl and Australian label Subsonic Music. The next release on Replug, meanwhile, is Raxon\'s \'Into the Summer\' with remixes from Cid Inc and Nick Muir. All this will further enhance Henri\'s reputation as a DJ and producer destined to make his mark on electronic dance music. Cid Inc is available for DJ bookings worldwide through Sedition DJs.','','https://www.facebook.com/Cidinc','http://www.cidincmusic.com','www.soundcloud.com/cid-inc','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 17:13:28',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','cid-inc'),(1329,5,1,2,'DJ Leon Russell','Indian DJ/ Producer/Label Owner Leon Russell was born in 1984 in the city of Mumbai. Music runs in his blood, as from a very young age he was treated to the likes of classic rock legends such as Deep Purple, Iron Butterfly, Scorpions, Queen, CCR and The Steve Miller Band. The real reason for his passion for music was his father who is also a musician. He got his first dose of electronic dance music in the year 1998, when techno parties were a rage in Mumbai. He started playing music at an early age of fifteen.','','http://www.facebook.com/djleonrussell','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-17 13:56:01',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','dj-leon-russell-1'),(1330,0,0,0,'Poets of the Fall',' of the Fall (POTF) is the result of years of jamming and writing music. It all started when rock singer and Irish trad buff, Mark, and jazzy guitarist, Ollie, decided to give it a go and form their own band in 2002. A little later industrial-machine-trance-man Captain was asked to kindly come on board, and so, POTF, was born from three very different worlds merging.\r\nRemember to visit POTF\'s official website at www.poetsofthefall.com for tour dates, more music, videos, a discussion board, and other cool stuff!','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','poets-of-the-fall'),(1331,0,18,18,'DJ Nathan C','Nathan is an acclaimed Music Producer & DJ from London, UK. Over the last few years his work has been championed by many of the worlds biggest DJs including: Tiesto, Pete Tong, Gareth Emery, Funkagenda, Eric Morillo, Axwell, Mark Knight, Chuckie, Roger Sanchez, and Eddie Halliwell. His work has featured on many reputed labels such as Toolroom, Funk Farm, Cr2, Spinnin and Big & Dirty. One of his bigger successes came in 2010 with a Beatport House Top 5 position on his collaboration with Ant Brooks (titled Arigato), which was released on Starlight. Also his track with Danny Dove (titled That Trumpet Track) on Stealth Records earned a Beatport House Top 20 that same summer. Moving into 2012 Nathan will continue his ascent up the ranks of House music with big releases lined up on Armin van Buurens label Armada Music, Funkagendas Funk Farm, Mark Knights Toolroom Records, as well as In Charge, Maquina Music and Big & Dirty. With a diverse and broad musical taste Nathan is regularly commissioned for remix work and has completed official mixes for some of the biggest names in the business such as Lily Allen, Example, DJ Fresh and Dizzee Rascal right through to more underground artists such as Paul Thomas, Steve Mac and Jason Chance. On top of all this Nathan manages a relentless production schedule running his own studio and ghost producing for a large number of DJs and Producers in the House scene. As a passionate and enthusiastic DJ, Nathan knows how to rock a crowd. His gig schedule has seen him play right across the globe in countries such as China, Philippines, Russia, Ibiza and Estonia, plus a whole host of places in the UK such as Creamfields, Digital, Turnmills, Shepherds Bush Empire, Lightbox, Scala, Whitehouse, The Egg and The Cross. Testament to his years of experience behind the decks and cutting his teeth on the London circuit, 2012 has seen him join the ranks of one of the world\'s biggest dance-music brands Ministry of Sound, as an official tour resident. Stylistically Nathan plays a fine blend of quality, uplifting House music, and says If its got the right energy and makes people dance, Ill play it. It can range from dark and techy, to progressive and fu','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-nathan-c'),(1332,0,4,4,'Retro Legendary Act','RLA  Retro Legendary Act is a premier classic rock band , founded in 2005, in Pune. The line-up features Ritesh (Guitar), Vijay (Vocals), Jeson (keyboards).Vijay Murthy (Bass),and Vatayan (Drums)   RLA is prominently a covers band, catering to a vast plethora of music tastes across a broad listening audience. The band also predominantly exhibits influences by American and British rock Legends such as Bon Jovi, Brian Adams, , Deep Purple, Scorpions, Van Halen, Whitesnake, Jim Morrison, Clapton and others. Based in Pune RLA is one of the Prime Classic rock group in town and Mumbai.  RLA is known for their rocknroll sessions, soft rock and heavy metal sessions including unplugged gigs which have offered popularity also amongst college audiences. The band is also known for its well managed and well presented shows at Hard Rock Caf, Not Just Jazz by the Bay, corporate gigs and concerts otherwise,  Come 1990s saw a major positive change in the Western Music scene all over. With influx of new music channels on the TV , there was a vast variety of music easily accessible to the audience . Almost overnight, the tastes changed and listeners wanted the performances to be versatile and not typecast to any specific genre. Thus a bunch of like-minded musicians came together in early 2005 and decided to play a wide array of live music to a well-informed musical audience. The band performed with brilliant skills and was baptized as Retro Legendary Act (RLA) . RLAs sound changed dramatically as they introduced (where ever required and suited) softer & more acoustic tonality too..  Please visit & add up to RLA  Retro Legendary Act page on Face book to know more about the band , snaps and upcoming concerts. ','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/RLA-Retro-Legendary-Act/108230042571391?ref=ts','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','retro-legendary-act'),(1333,0,1,1,'Peter Cat Recording Co.','Peter Cat Recording Co. is a four-piece gypsy jazz/cabaret band formed in 2009, from San Francisco/New Delhi. Started as the solo project of Suryakant Sawhney, the new lineup of the band went on to play numerous college festivals in 2010. They also played the finals of NLS Strawberry Fields, and released their debut album Sinema in January 2011.',' Rohan Kulshreshtha +91 9811 605 746','https://www.facebook.com/petercatrc','http://www.petercatrecordingco.com','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','peter-cat-recording-co'),(1334,0,1,1,'Suryakant Sawhney','','','http://facebook.com/theprofessionalman',' http://www.petercatrecordingco.com ','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 17:14:11',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','suryakant-sawhney'),(1335,0,11,11,'SKRAT','In the later part of the day on July 15th of the year 2006 this bunch of high school graduates decided that they would form a band and make some music to aid their would be dreary engineering college lives. 6 Days later they play their first show at the Unwind center. In an environment of predominantly metal music, this original-rock act got the crowd and went on to play over a 100 gigs, and counting. This includes most of the major cities in South India, Mumbai and an independent festival in Reading, England.\r\n\r\nThe band took a shortl hiatus to explore their sound following the release of their first studio album called \'Design\'. The band reformed with a new sound and a new direction. So YOU the one reading this, Listen to their music and make your own bloody back story. Watch them live and spread the Sound.','Nithin - 9176666890','http://www.facebook.com/events/409636909099543/','https://www.facebook.com/group.php?gid=34721604219','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','skrat'),(1336,0,2,2,'Blakc','This is the story of BLAKC. BLAKC is a band from Mumbai made up of five very unique, talented individuals. They are (in no order of importance) Shawn Pereira, Shishir Thakur, Roop Thomas, Rein Dias and Anish Menon. Before we get to know them better, lets see how BLAKC was first formed. \r\n\r\nIn early 2006, Shawn was a fun-loving college-going kid. His priorities in life were to attend as little college as possible while meeting as many women as possible. He decided the way to go was to be a rockstar. Enter Anish, another fun-loving, college-going kid. He wanted to be a high flying guy in the corporate world. So much so that he actually turned up for one of BLAKCs gigs at a later time in a suit, and then left without playing. But he too wanted to be a rockstar. They made a lot more money and did a lot less to earn it. Anyway, Anish met Shawn and concluded that they might just have something in common. So they got together with Gaurav and Vishwanath (who then formed Red Cube after they left BLAKC) and Sylvester, Shawns guitarist-friend. They jammed for a week, entered into a competition under the supposedly temporary name of BLAKC and came third in a college competition and the name stuck. \r\n\r\nTowards the end of 2006, Gaurav and Nath were replaced by Roop and Shishir and BLAKC started composing its own music. In February 2007, Reinhardt replaced Sylvester and the lineup was complete. BLAKC went on to win a local college competition and thats where it all began. \r\n\r\nIn the past three years that BLAKC has been around with its present lineup, they participated in a lot of local college competitions. After making it to the finals of both IRock and Campus Rock, they graduated to opening and headlining shows in Mumbai as well as other cities. Today BLAKC has played over eighty shows across 14 cities in India. \r\n\r\nBLAKC released their debut album \'Choking On A Dream\' in December 2008. The album DID NOT sell out like crazy :) but the general consensus (fans and critics alike) is that BLAKC is definitely a band to watch out for. Lucky enough to sell around 700 cds. The band is currently writing new music for their second album and has no plans to allow life as such to disrupt the crazy life they are living. \r\n\r\nBLAKC has always been about two things, the music and the people. We believe that our music is an extension of our personalities and the only way to connect to so many music lovers. Off stage we are weird; on stage we can tear a place apart purely because of the energy we have. BLAKC since its beginning has been unable to fit into genres, we stopped trying and stuck to doing what we loved doing more than any other which is making our own music. We each have such various influences that every song has multiple personalities. We love what we do and we love that you like us enough to have read this. Peace.........and let the BLACKATTAINMENT begin.............\r\n','','http://www.facebook.com/blackattainment','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','blakc-1'),(1337,0,3,3,'Infusion Jazz','Jazz , is the genre of music that we play , and Jazz is something that cannot be strictly defined within two parallel lines .\r\n\r\nThere are so many variations of what we call Jazz , starting from the unique style of Louis Armstrong , to the plaintive notes of Miles Daviss trumpet , to the experimental Jazz rock / Funk Jazz that Weather Report played in their hey days .\r\n\r\nHowever to be fair to all jazz lovers , Infusion plays a form of modern Jazz that cannot be called Avant-garde, but is definitely not in the classification of Dixieland or Be Bop .\r\n\r\nThe style is very much like the 70s experimental music played by the Return to Forever band and improvisations on the same. Chick Correa, Jean Luc Ponty, Stanley Clarke , Lenny White , Jaco Pastorious, are musicians that have influence the band immensely .\r\n\r\nThe band also plays a lot of classic Jazz Standards that are completely improvised to render a very different sound that is both refreshing and dynamic .\r\n\r\nWith Manoj George, a guest artist who will perform with us on Electric violin, we would like to bring in a dynamism into the music that can also influence the young and get them excited enough to understand and explore the finesse and allure of what we call Jazz.','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Infusion-Jazz/','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','infusion-jazz'),(1338,0,29,29,'Fossils','','','https://www.facebook.com/FossilsIndia','http://www.rupamislam.com/','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','fossils'),(1339,0,91,91,'Neelix','ENGLISH (Deutsch siehe unten)\r\n\r\nHamburg based artist Henrik Twardzik, better known as Neelix started to produce music in the early 1998. After DJing for some years he finally decided to create his own sound.\r\n\r\nHis first track he recorded was \"Neelix - The Fourth\", released on a NOVA TEKK compilation called Maverixx in 2002 which was followed by numerous releases on different labels from all around the globe.\r\n\r\nUntill now Henrik has released 3 albums and many singles. The third album \"Same thing but different\" is already released on Millennium Records. Besides Henrik also belongs to the founders of the hamburg based label Glamour Studios.\r\n\r\nHe has already played at many big open air and indoor events in germany and in countrys like sweden - ungary - denmark - greece swiss - austria - uk - belgium - netherlands - israel and mexico. \r\n\r\nSource: http://www.myspace.com/neelixmusic\r\n','spintwist@spintwist.de','https://www.facebook.com/neelixmusic','http://www.myspace.com/neelixmusic','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 17:17:13',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','neelix'),(1340,2,71,71,'SYNCOPATION ','Originally formed in January of 2002 at Berklee College of Music in Boston, Syncopation performs catchy Swing, Latin and Pop tunes along with A Cappella Jazz and Improvisation pieces. Syncopation has performed across the US for festivals such as the Tanglewood Jazz Festival, the Tri-C Vocal Jazz Festival, the Boston Globe Jazz Festival, the Meihou Jazz Festival, and the 2004 and 2006 IAJE Conference in New York City, sharing the stage with many jazz greats. They have also been heard live on radio stations across the country. In addition, the group has been welcomed with open arms overseas, and frequently tours Japan, giving clinics and singing for sold-out audiences across the country.\r\n\r\nSyncopation\'s first album, A New Dance, was released in 2003, featuring several special guest talents, including the gifted trumpet player Tiger Okoshi and Paul Stiller of vocal group Vox One. Phil Wilson of Woody Herman big-band fame also contributed to the album\'s unique and appealing sound, as his direction of the horn section added a perfect balance to the final product. The album, featuring their unique interpretations of tunes ranging to the bebop staple \"Cherokee\" to Cyndi Lauper\'s \"Time After Time,\".\r\n\r\nSyncopation\'s success with A New Dance soon led to a record contract with Geneon Entertainment Inc. in Japan, and the group recorded their second album in Tokyo in May 2004, featuring artists such as Satoru \"Salt\" Shinoya, one of Japan\'s most well-known jazz pianists. Their second album, Of Blue, was released nationwide.','','http://www.facebook.com/syncopationsings','http://www.jazzsyncopation.com','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 15:30:35',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','syncopation'),(1341,0,0,0,'Retronome','We highly recommend the following artists: The Beatles, Ryan Adams, Queens of the Stone Age, Ben Harper, Incubus, Oasis, Jane\'s Addiction, John Frusciante, My Morning Jacket, Radiohead, Prince, The Black Keys, Velvet Revolver, Bon Iver, Regina Spektor, Rage Against the Machine, The White Stripes, Xavier Rudd, John Butler Trio, Sigor Ros, The Roots, The Rolling Stones, Bob Dylan, Lupe Fiasco, The Red Hot Chilli Peppers, Pearl Jam, Nirvana, Neil Young, Miles Davis, Charles Mingus, The Mars Volta, Gil-Scott Heron, Led Zeppelin, Pink Floyd, Kings of Leon, John Lee Hooker, Jimi Hendrix, Jeff Buckley, Interpol,','','https://www.facebook.com/Retronome','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 17:17:54',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','retronome'),(1342,0,0,0,'Fuzzy Logic','Arfaaz or \'Fuzz\' began his musical adventure at the tender age of three, when gripped by an overwhelming urge to determine the mysterious source of music emanating from his fathers wall cabinet, a tremendous fall, (cushioned only by the thick tuft of fuzz on his head) rewired his neuro-impulses causing an undying love for music and a unique approach to sound that he likes to call Fuzzy Logic.\r\n\r\nHaving previously played for rock, funk and electronic outfits such as Galeej Gurus, Zebediah Plush and Tempo Tantrick, Fuzz currently performs with his alt rock band Slow Down Clown and his collaborative electro project Fuzzy Logic.\r\n\r\nHe lives and works in Mumbai as an independent music director composing music for television commercials and short films.','','https://www.facebook.com/fuzzthebuzz/','http://www.arfaaz.com','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','fuzzy-logic'),(1343,0,2,2,'Kickstart Freedom','Heres a band comprising of 5 very talented Individuals who have been part of the Indian Rock Music Circuit for more than a Decade. Each of these individuals, while excelling in their own departmnents have always been looking for a chance to break away from the ordinary, and free themselves and the audience from normal everyday sounds. More than just a band, some call this the begining of a movement that promotes free expression of thought through music.\r\n\r\nWhat makes this band extremely versatile is that all of them have different influences and together they blend in to produce a brilliant mix of creativity, style and feel. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe bands influences include a whole lot of bands covering almost every genre, right from the Beatles to Audioslave. Their collective influences include Funk, Pop, Jazz, Heavy Metal, Grunge, Alternative and almost anything that you could think of.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAll the above Musicians have played at the Hard Rock Cafe, Jazz By the Bay, Blue Frog and many such venues in Mumbai and various other cities on different occasions with various bands like The Other People, Retropark, Excess X, Gary Lawyer, Aqua Flow, to name a few.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWHAT PLACES THIS BAND A CUT ABOVE OTHERS IS THEIR VERSATALITY AND ALSO THEIR ABILITY TO CHURN UP TRACKS DEPENDING ON THE CROWD. THEIR REPERTOIRE RANGES FROM THE BEATLES TO PEARL JAM, LED ZEPPLIN, PINK FLOYD, DEEP PURPLE, TO COLDPLAY, LINKIN PARK, AC DC AND ALMOST ANYTHING IN BETWEEN.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nOverall a very tight and entertaining act that is everready wih spontaneous compositions and crowd pleasing acts.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCajetan D\'souza (Caji) : An accomplished and very versatile musician who is equally adept at playing guitars, keyboards and also Bass. He sure is a familiar face at Hard Rock Cafe and Jazz By the Bay playing with various bands and musicians over the years. Also featured on a few music videos, this talented musician always has loads to offer. \r\n\r\n\r\nAdrian D\'mello : Adrian on Bass is the most hardworking member of the band. Always the one with the completely worked out parts. Has also done his share of Touring around the world with various musicians, is always happy to get back up on stage and Rock with the rest of us. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCassius Fernandes : Cassy on drums is definitely the driving force behind this band and his style and technique is something most aspiring drummers wish to learn. His Skill at easily changing the complete groove of a track is definitely a rare one. Also a very familiar face in Mumbais Music circuit, having played with various musicians like Gary Lawyer, Colonial Cousins, Manasi Scott and many others. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSujit Kumar : Sujit on vocals has also been in the scene for a long time and has been singing with various bands over the years. His style ranges right from the lows of Eddie vedder to the highs of Robert Plant and always gets the crowd going. His crazy stage antics and eccentricities are what people look out for whenever the band is on the go.','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Kickstart-Freedom','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','kickstart-freedom'),(1344,0,0,0,'The Thrillers','','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-thrillers'),(1345,0,2,2,'Hellwind','In the immortal words of AC/DC- \'Rock n\' roll ain\'t noise pollution, rock n\' roll ain\'t gonna die\'. United by their love for wailing guitars, pounding drums, leather and the spirit of the 80s, Hellwind is a motley crew of musicians from Mumbai who love to rock n\' roll. Hailing from various veteran bands around Mumbai (Demonic Resurrection, Workshop, Spook, Reptilian Death, Funk The System, Colossus, Apollonian Quest, Zephyr), the members of the band have trained under the tutelage of the various Gods of Rock and take immense pleasure in showcasing their wizardry before you. So expect the theatrics of KISS, the hooks of Def Leppard, the melodies of Poison, the groove of Van Halen and the banshee wails of Judas Priest. Moreover, since the band is on an eternal quest to turn everything they touch into a riffalicious masterpiece, expect their own spin on popular commercial hits as well.','demonstealerrecords@gmail.com','https://www.facebook.com/hellwindindia/','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','hellwind'),(1346,0,2,2,'Stella by Starlight','They say Bombay winters do crazy things. That may explain why Shimol Sachdev and Hayden Scott decided to start Stella By Starlight on a chilly January evening in 2011. The project began with one very simple motive: to write simple, heart-felt songs for and about the people they know, their everyday lives and loves. In late 2011, reconnecting with an old friend, Hayden got guitarist, djembe player and producer Abhinav Saxena on board. The pieces had fallen in place. With shades of folk and acoustic rock, Stella By Starlight have a stripped down, minimal approach to songwriting based on the belief that a guitar and voice can go a long way in crafting a meaningful and rich musical tapestry.','Hayden Scott (hayden.scott@gmail.com)','http://www.facebook.com/StellasStarlight/','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','stella-by-starlight'),(1347,0,29,29,'Caesars Palace','Bangalore\'s Caesars Palace have been in and out of the live scene since 2006, when they first got together as musicians from diferent bands getting together to try something fresh and original with their skills. Gigging actively in their frst 2 years of existence wherein they developed a decent amount of following for their own funk laced, blues driven originals and played some big gigs and festivals around the country(including the Delhi Eastwind Festival 2008, Independence Rock 2007 Mumbai, Bangalore Habba 2006 etc) , the band became a bit inactive post mid 2008 owing to various reasons. But the music could not keep them away for too long and the boys were back with a gig at Blue Frog in Mumbai in September 2009 with some new music and the band started gigging more\r\nregularly this time. Tis comeback of sorts has led to their frst 4 recordings in the form of \'Mindfeld\' which is an EP that showcases the diferent facets of the bands music and the unique creative process. From the rif-driven, odd timed \'Bittersweet Mind\' to the almost dance-pop \'Get Your Mojo On!\', this band has a spanking new introspective story to tell.','','http://www.facebook.com/cpindia','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','caesars-palace'),(1348,0,11,11,'Little Babooshkas Grind','Little Babooshka\'s Grind was formed in 1995 with the sole aim to promote original music and contribute to the growing independent music scene.Little Babooshka\'s Grind (LBG) are a rock band from Chennai consisting of the Janakiram brothers Arjun, Avneet & Aum, with James B Boskey on Keys, Marky Spitneck on drums & U.D Kiran behind the console. Starting of as a progressive metal band in college back in 1995, over the years the Janakiram Bros. went through numerous line up changes to discover their passion for original music in a cover dominated rock \'n\' roll scene. With it\'s quirky name and popular tunes like Money, Scarawag, Breathe, Bad Children & Super Cat from their 3 studio releases, LBG have found a place in the Indian rock \'n\' roll hall of fame as one of the top bands in the country for it\'s unique style and energetic performances all over the country. Their 3rd release \"Bad Children\" was nominated for Best Indian Rock Album of the year by RSJ Readers poll in 2007 along with artists like Pentagram, Taaq, Blackstrat Blues & Dream Out Loud. The band has also organized a series of charity show to raise funds for tsunami affected victims since 2005 and continue to donate the development funds of areas affected by natural disasters through show proceedings and merchandise sales. LBG is a form of energy that can only transform and never be destroyed. Follow them on facebook.com/LittleBabooshkasGrind or visit www.thelbg.com/music.html to listen to all their songs.','Avneet - 098840 60857','https://www.facebook.com/LittleBabooshkasGrind','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','little-babooshkas-grind'),(1349,0,3,3,'Witchgoat','We bow at the altar of Bathory, Possessed, Venom, Celtic Frost, Hellhammer and the other Elder Gods of heavy-black-thrash metal. In short...fuck off!!!!','witchgoat@gmail.com','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','witchgoat'),(1350,0,0,0,'R3HAB','Check out my other pages: http://www.soundcloud.com/r3hab http://www.twitter.com/djr3hab http://www.youtube.com/r3habtube','','https://www.facebook.com/r3habofficial','http://www.youtube.com/r3habtube','http://www.soundcloud.com/r3hab','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 17:19:15',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','r3hab'),(1351,0,72,72,'Azaan Khan','Azaan was born in Dehradun on the 11th of december, 1988. His early years were spent growing up in a family of music and musicians. His father Ustaad Shujaat Khan is today one of the most sought after musicians of our time. His grandfather Ustaad Vilayat Khan is considered to be the legend of the sitar. This makes Azaan the 8th generation of Ustaad Imdaad Khani gharana of music. \r\n\r\nAzaan studied at the Mother International School, where his inclination towards music started taking shape. He bought his beginners guitar and enrolled at the Delhi School of Music. \r\nSoon after this, at the age of 14, his interest in music turned into a passion, and he started performing at various school festivals. He started evolving in several different directions within the world of music. As he turned to a new mentor, Mr.Gussy Rikh, who was the lead guitarist of the band Euphoria, to teach him techniques of the electric guitar. Also, all throughout his formative years, the Riyaaz sessions held at home, where his father taught difficult compositions (bandishes) to his senior students, took deep roots within him, which allowed him to sing these bandishes with ease. The unique blend of having the knowledge of western classical as well as Indian classical music helped him to make his own niche in the young world of upcoming college musicians. \r\n\r\nIn the past couple of years, Azaan has found different facets to his musical creativity. He has started writing his own lyrics, he composes all his music and he sings and plays the guitar in all his compositions, the uniqueness being that he is actually comfortable doing all this in western and Indian music. At the moment, he is working on his first album, where he is bringing together this four dimensional creativity. Many aspects of Indian and folk music are predominant in his compositions, in addition to which he has enthused the western characteristics of compositions like harmonies and chords. Many elements of Sufi\'ism are also visible in his work. \r\n\r\nAlthough he has performed many times in college cultural festivals, he has even accompanied his father Ustaad Shujaat Khan in concerts. Notable amongst them are events in New York in July, where he played for the United Nations world Hindi Conference, New Delhi in august at the India Habitat Centre. In the same year, he has also toured Mauritius and South Africa. The following winter, he performed in Delhi for a gala charity event to raise funds for Smile India. Apart from this, he performed in numerous different venues in India and abroad. \r\n\r\nIn the summer 2009, Azaan joined the prestigious \"KMMC\" which is AR Rahmans music conservatory in Chennai., where he took courses in Hindustani and western vocal amongst other subjects such as music theory, music history, appreciation and sound and audio engineering. \r\n\r\nAzaan will soon be shifting to Mumbai permanently to start work with the composing duo Salim-Suleman on various different projects.\r\nArtists We Also Like\r\npink floyd, porcupine tree,dream theater, sqaurepusher, john mayer','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Azaan-Khan/152988211399869','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','azaan-khan'),(1352,0,0,0,'Bassista V ','From Mountain Madness in Nepal to the beaches of Goa, Vandana is making waves with sounds that keep you hooked and grooving. Vandana has known only one true love throughout her life, and that is music. She is a bass player and a singer, and has been a loyal fan and supporter of the Indian music circuit for over a decade now. Vandana has traveled widely and been personally involved with multiple genres of music, ranging from rock to funk, fusion, jazz and blues. However, her world turned around when she first experienced electronic music. Soon she began performing as a DJ experimenting with a unique style of dark, tribal and bass-heavy EDM (sub-genre no bar). She has since performed alongside some of the world\'s best international artists like Sultan, Ned Shepard, DJ Pearl, Atmos, Fatali, Kashyyyk, Manuel de la Mare, Nikhil Chinapa, Mad Maxx and Paul Thomas, and has frequented some of the best venues India has to offer. ','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 17:08:18',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','bassista-v'),(1353,0,1,1,'Dj Su-Real','One-half of The Living Room Cafe\'s resident audiovisual DJ/VJ dynamic duo WWYYZZZRRDDZ. Su-Real has over a decade\'s experience in the music scene of Montreal and New York, and now calls New Delhi homebase. With WWYYZZZRRDDZ he mixes disco classics, old school hip hop and \'80s/\'90s pop hits that\'ll get anyone on the dance floor.','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-su-real'),(1354,0,67,67,'MoodyBoy','Based in Mumbai, Moodyboys career spans almost two decades as a DJ and producer. In his early days, he even worked with the likes of Gaurav Raina of Midival Punditz. Back then, Tribal House reigned supreme and Moodyboy was an integral part of the scene. In recent years, we have seen a resurgence of tribal house in a more modern format via the likes of major European club stars like Riva Starr and Gregor Salto.\r\n\r\nAccordingly, Moodyboy has been busy in the studio again, releasing track after track that would fit in seamlessly at any super-club in Ibiza or Goa.','','https://www.facebook.com/djmoodyboy#','','http://soundcloud.com/moodyboy','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 17:20:32',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','moodyboy'),(1355,0,0,0,'Traffic Jam','TRAFFIC JAM is a 4 - piece band with a message. With all members from the north east of India , living under similar circumstances, and meeting up far from home in the grounds of Delhi, the band strives to pay tribute to the Rock Gods and Anthems they grew up with , in their homeground.\r\n\r\nHeavily influenced by life, love and Rock their name speaks for itself, something everyone faces in every aspect of their life. Like a calm in the storm, they handle even the hardest riffs with elan and soft notes that flow like milk and honey, eventually giving rock the respect it deserves.\r\n\r\nAs an \"all-genre\" band, the band\'s roots go down to the basic strong foundation of each of the members who are all passionate laureates of music. constantly learning and teaching, Also having had to live-off music, the band has played in numerious great places like : \"Geoffrey\'s, Lutyens, BriX, Attitude, Manajsa, DLF city club and whole lots of other greats places in NCR. This is indeed the one-step shop for your Muisc needs that where Traffic Jam happens.','','https://www.facebook.com/Jimmythang1003/info','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','traffic-jam'),(1356,0,1,1,'Paradigm Shift ','The Band Members\r\n\r\nAmit Mandal -Vocals\r\nThe voice of the band, he has immense experience of over 10 years in the Indian music scene, which he showcases with his tremendous showmanship on stage. He is also the frontman for the popular Delhi band Hypnosis. Be it with his searing vocals or his wittiness, Amit has never failed to delight crowds. \r\n\r\nWaters - Guitars\r\nOften mistaken as a blood relative of famed Floyd guitarist, Roger Waters for his remarkable skills, Fabian is at home with all sorts music. From country style slide guitar to earth shaking classic rock riffs, he is one of the most technically proficient and innovative guitarists in Delhi.\r\n\r\nAkshay Johar - Bass\r\nOne of the three founding members of the band along with Arjun and Avinish, he is the backbone of the band. Prone to manic bursts of creativity and energy, his bass lines are imbued with emotion and uniqueness fusing modern funk, rock n roll and Indian classical.\r\n\r\nBiography\r\nSometime in early 2008,\r\nParadigm Shift sprung into existence. They realized how their outlook on music had uncanny similarities though influences were vast and varied. These fundamental commonalities helped them transcend what other bands would often stumble over. Capitalizing on this chemistry they have worked fervently to identify and hone their sound.\r\nBlending the infectiousness of funk, crunchy rock n roll and staccato of progressive with hints of Indian classical in a musical kaleidoscope that deftly ventures out of the realms of each.\r\nDespite their straightforward approach to composition, Paradigm Shifts technical arsenal is singular that never alienates the listener. In fact it causes unpredictable, if not consistent bursts of head banging, violent foot tapping and vigorous cheering.\r\nWith the drummer providing a bedrock foundation, the guitarists bringing forth melodic irresistibility, the bassist, unrestrained energy and the vocalist musical rapture, Paradigm Shift hopes to keep evolving with their drive and love for sound. \r\n\r\nWith eight album capable originals which are Damn, In Too Deep, Radiance, Funk This, High, Stud Farm, Fuzzy Logic, All Wrong;\r\nThe band has won over mobs of fans and critics alike.\r\n\r\nEach time on stage, Paradigm Shift put on a vividly energized show for their music enthusiasts, combining their originals with covers of all time favorite numbers from bands like Led Zeppelin, Deep Purple, Queen, Wolfmother, Pearl Jam, Guns n Roses, Foo Fighters and The Rolling Stones among others.','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Paradigm-Shift/','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','paradigm-shift'),(1357,0,0,0,'Victor and The Crowns','Started with a bunch of friends, bound by a love for music, getting together and jamming at parties. Moved on to the band performing to raise money for charity shows like the Kripa Foundation, Mt. Carmels Church and Home for the Aged...\r\nWho knows where it will take us...\r\nDescription\r\nVICTOR AND THE CROWNS is a rock-n-roll lineup of hobby-musicians inspired by the golden era of music of the 60s to the 80s.\r\n\r\nTheir passion for music is evident in the vibrantly electrifying vocals of dynamic front-man Dr. Victor Rodrigues, heaven-on-high music arrangements and harmonies by Keith \"Maestro\" Suares, beautiful and tightly-pitched complex choral ensemble of Simone Patrick, Beryl Pinto Stephanie Petit, Raynah Braganza, Luis Chico, and L.S, flawless thumping bass lines by Ralph Pais, soul-stirring acoustic guitar chord voicing by Larry Rebello, smooth synthesizer and keyboard patterns by Dr. Nikhil Cunha, banjo-twanging and sonorous vocals of Dipak Shah, precision drumming of Benjamin Sequeira and the emotive lead-guitar bends and pulls by Douglas Misquita.\r\n\r\nComing together from a range of industries and influenced by The Rolling Stones, The Beatles, Elvis Presley, CCR and others of that genre, music is a serious pastime for this mix of doctors, businessmen, engineers, bankers, music instructors and media professionals - tempered in a cauldron of rigorous and regular practices and in-house music-critique; enough to make VICTOR AND THE CROWNS stand out as a much-awaited crowd-pulling act with their signature interpretations of a number of chart-toppers. ','','https://www.facebook.com/VictorandtheCrowns','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','victor-and-the-crowns'),(1358,0,2,2,'Helen and The Mumbai Marichis','Inspired by music from Spain, Africa, Arabia & South America, the band create soul stirring fusion jazz music assimilating lounge and Afro Cuban rhythms in their unique style.\r\n\r\nThe band not only comprise of exceptional musicians from far flung locations in Assam, INDIA to the island of Tasmania but heave an extended gypsy family of dancers and artists to make the audience experience a bona fide of the music that they play. \r\n\r\nDrawing influences from singers, soloists and bands like Cesaria Evora, Nina Simone, Miriam Makeba, Coumba Gawla, Sade, Norah Jones, Ali Farke Toure, Khaled, Buena Vista Social Club, Gipsy Kings etc to name a few, the band takes you through a musical journey from Africa going through Cuba to Southern Europe and Arabic cultures.\r\n\r\nAnd inevitably going by the name Mariachis (Mar-ree-ah-chiz) who are wandering musicians, celebrating love and life where ever they play, the band has critically earned appreciation from their audience in whichever place and venue it played.','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Helena-the-Mumbai-Mariachis/363478820329589','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','helen-and-the-mumbai-marichis'),(1359,0,0,0,'TARIK (LIVE AV)','not available on FB!','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','tarik-live-av'),(1360,0,0,0,'VARNIKA KUNDU','','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','varnika-kundu'),(1361,0,0,0,'Shashwat Pande','','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','shashwat-pande'),(1362,0,0,0,'Rhythm Method','Founded by Laiq Qureshi, who also heads Inroom Records and Urban Beat Project (an experimental label, booking agency and artists\' collective), Rhythm Method\'s sound breeds new-age collaborative ideas. Having worked with a number of artists, Rhythm Method shapes a lot of it\'s ideas around Drumstep / Breakbeat / World sounds, while heavily investing into rural folk and classical music. It\'s new album \'Cosmic Creation\' (in making) features collaborations by Classical greats like Ustad Sultan Khan and Mahesh Vinayakram, as well as world and jazz musicians like Yoann Freget (France), Kamila Nasr (Canada), Andrea Presa (Italy), Mr. Woodnote (UK) and more.\r\n','','https://www.facebook.com/rhythm.method.in','http://www.inroomrecords.com','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','rhythm-method'),(1363,0,0,0,'Zeeshan Khan','','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','zeeshan-khan'),(1364,0,93,93,'Suckafish P Jones','High Priest of Riddim and Bass\r\nBiography\r\nSuckafish P Jones is a music producer, performer and DJ. Stylistically blasting sonic terrain between soundsystem culture, hip hop and futuristic voodoou, he makes music to make you dance like youre possessed.\r\nDescription\r\nSome upcoming selected hot dates with the Voodoo Master in Spain,\r\n\r\nSeptember 11 - Suckafish P Jones @Nokodek Festival, Dinostia\r\nSeptember 29 - Banana Empire w/ MUNCHI, Razzmatazz, BCN\r\nSeptember 30 - Suckafish P Jones w / Ove Naxx (Japan), NIU, Barcelona\r\n...October 1 - Suckafish P Jones w/ Ove Naxx (Japan) and Dr Chi, Tabacalera Madrid\r\nOctober 13 - Suckafish P Jones w/ HIFANA (Japan), Razzmatazz, BCN\r\nArtists We Also Like\r\nZomby, Untold, Aoi, RZA, Dj Funk, Ennio Morricone','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Suckafish-P-Jones/','http://www.myspace.com/suckafizznit','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','suckafish-p-jones'),(1365,0,0,0,'DJ Wild City','Wild City DJ has a peculiar and varied taste in music. Straddling hip-hop, garage, grime, bass, house, techno, alternative electronica and anything in between, WCDJ always brings an informative set, favouring upfront and left of centre music over yesterday\'s tired hits. Having been a part of the underground electronic movement in London for a number of years WCDJ brings to the table a fresh and undeniably UK sound to his live shows.','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-wild-city'),(1367,0,88,88,'Booka Shade','Booka Shade is the duo of Walter Merziger and Arno Kammermeier.\r\n\r\nIn charge of their own production company and studio for the last 15 years, they have applied their wide range of talents not only to the realm of electronic music, but also a large number of other media productions. After two early 90s synth pop album releases and a number of live tours, they switched their attention to club projects for established labels such as R&S, Harthouse and Tommy Boy. It was their early incarnation of Booka Shade on the illustrious Dutch label Touch which hit the zeitgeist and triggered excitement and enthusiasm in clubs all across Europe.\r\n\r\nTogether with old friends Patrick Bodmer and Philipp Jung a.k.a M.A.N.D.Y and publisher Thomas Koch a.k.a DJ T, they launched their very own label Get Physical, in 2002. After the build up and promotion of label artists M.A.N.D.Y, DJ T, Sunsetpeople and Chelonis R. Jones, in 2004, the duo took out time to pursue their own solo careers once again.\r\n\r\nThis is a world class production and performance duo and a must attend for anyone with a taste for electronic dance music. The duo\'s two Indian shows are a part of their Asia Tour 2012 which includes dates in India, China, Singapore, Thailand and Indonesia.','','https://www.facebook.com/bookashade','www.bookashade.com','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','booka-shade'),(1368,0,1,1,'Bryan and the Bandits','Sitting in a lounge and wondering if the next few minutes are just moments of electronic sound, neck movements, jumping or hands up in the air or will there be any hips moving with grace, fingers- palms-elbows-shoulders-back-complete with spins, sharp movements, and crisp turns. With the fascinating sound of Carlinhos Brown on the percussion in the start of Magalenha, Bryan and the Bandits was birthed. At the nucleus of the Bryan and the Bandits is the passion for Latin music. Distinct, seasoned, pure blooded musicians have come together to form this spectacular ensemble to innovate and create this passionate, uplifting, soul thumping and exciting venture. The musical ambience Bryan and the Latin bandits create draws dancers and even the rhythmically challenged to the dance floor. \r\n\r\nThe versatility of the band is to Latinizes any type of music to combine traditional Latin music with any genre. The band does not always use computerized sounds or instruments as they are a live band... Their fantastic repertoire consists of bossa lounge, latin funk, brazilian lounge and latin jazz of songs written in English and Spanish and can be all that an event wants them to be. \r\n\r\nThe band is a 6 piece acoustic band with a Vocalist, a Flamenco guitarist, a percussionist, a bassist, a drummer, and a keyboardist. For a more acoustic sound the band also performs as a 3 piece with a Vocalist, a Flamenco guitarist and a percussionist. ','','https://www.facebook.com/bryanandthebandits/','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 17:21:10',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','bryan-and-the-bandits'),(1369,0,0,0,'The Politik','','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','the-politik'),(1370,2,3,3,'Beat Gurus','Started in the year 1999 at a small outhouse which was let out by one of their friends. Initially the band was called \'Green Rhythm\' & had only these two in the band, They had a burning desire of forming a larger band, whose name was chosen to be as \'BEAT GURUS\'. \r\n\r\nFrom two the band now has grown to nine members who are as enthusiastic in performing for the band if not less. We visualize our band to perform across National and International platforms whilst be able to communicate to the audience through our music.\r\n\r\n\"We Now A band of 9 with absolute love towards Djembe which is a West - African hand drum, shaped like a large goblet and meant to be played with bare hands. Djembe comes directly from the saying \"Anke dje, anke be\" which literally translates to \"everyone gather together\" and defines the drum\'s purpose In the Bamanakan language. Which is exactly what we guys are doing. We have been performing for the past ten Years and we are happy that we got our first stage in Bangalore in the year 2000. We have performed all over India mainly Mumbai, Delhi, Chennai, etc and the main person and the founding member of the band \'Ganesh Govindswamy\' has performed and conducted workshops in some parts of the world like Singapore, Europe etc. We have also performed for various corporate and other cultural events to name mainly HSBC, AXA, DELL, IBM, DELPHIA, ACCENTURE, BHOOMI JAATHRE, BANGALOORU HAABA, and some events in the section of media like ETV KANNADA, UDAYA TV, TV9, WORLD SOCIAL FORUM(Mumbai), NDTV, BBC(world travel awards) and INTERNATIONAL CULTURAL EVENING(Norway), Bangalore International WINE Festival. Etc...\"','Ganesh Gowvindaswamy - +919986300398','https://www.facebook.com/beatgurus/info','http://www.beatgurus.com','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 13:56:26',0,'[\"\"]','[\"Ganesh Gowvindaswamy - +919986300398\\r\",\"\\r\",\"Booking Agent\\t\\r\",\"\\r\",\"Prashanth - +919900510454 , \\r\",\"\\r\",\"Manjunath.B.N - +919900119030\\r\",\"\"]','beat-gurus'),(1371,0,0,0,'Dj Jc','','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-jc'),(1372,0,15,15,'Alfaaz ','It began at the age of 14, when I was just a little boy trying to be the next Romeo. A little crush then made me write my first song, from my heart. A new feeling kindled my heart, which later turned into a passion for writing. I kept writing more and more, it amazed me!\r\n\r\nAlthough I loved the fiction in the songs of great lyricist/singers but i always sang my heart instead of just following a trend of philosophical singing/writing. My songs are not fictitious, they come from my way of living, my friends, lifes incidents, basically the world around me..\r\n\r\nWhile growing up, Ive been fortunate to meet some great artists which made me realize that Dreams do come true...\r\n\r\nIt inspired me even more and my best buddies then, Harry(brother) Teji,Kulli and sukh always motivated me to take writing/singing seriously.\r\n\r\nIts funny I never even had a diary for my songs. I just had scribbled bits of pages. Its because of my songs Ive always been an eye-candy among friends, in college. \r\n\r\nBy this time I had turned my house into a \'\'ZILLA\'\' yeah ZILLA where the love and appreciation of buddies made me a star among them.\r\n\r\nDancing & choreography has also been a hobby in college which later got me to do some events with the help of my best buddy Sukhi Patran.\r\n\r\nI never thought of taking up singing as a career up until one night a very close friend called up and said \" Alfaaz, you are good at writing and singing, you should take it seriously, Make an album\'. Never thought would never hear from him again. \r\n\r\nBut I am sure, every time I sing, you can hear me dear buddy!!\r\n\r\nHis last words were the beginning of a dream and thats how I decided to do an album.\r\n\r\nThen, in 2010 I met ANUP KUMAR JI (ACME ENT.) after some efforts, he heard me and liked me and set up a meeting with Yo Yo HONEY SINGH. Meeting Honey Singh was like a dream come true. He is unbelievable, such a great artist, a gem at heart and a great support.\r\n\r\nHe changed me from a shayar to a \"lyrical Bastard\" (Laughs)!! He groomed me commercially. Its strange that not even a single song, initially selected for this album, exists in the album.\r\n\r\nYo Yo Honey Singh gave my songs a new soul.\r\n\r\nMy favorite song, Hai mera Dil , from the album Boy Next door is already a super hit among whoever has heard it.\r\n\r\nBeing busy and occupied unknowingly some relations were ignored, but Ive been fortunate enough to have great friends. \r\n\r\nI would like to thank my buddies whove always been there for me, from quick midnight beer breaks during rehearsals to answering last minutes calls. \r\n\r\nI am also thankful to Dinesh Ji and Ruby ji from Speed records, Anup kumar ji, My Mom (Mrs. Paramjit Kaur) and Dad (s. Gurjit s pannu) and my Grand Parents(Sdn.&S Sher singh) , My mentor YO YO HONEY SINGH and all my friends who always supported me and made my dream come true. I couldnt have done it without your blessings. \r\n\r\nLove you all\r\n\r\nAlfaazTHE BOY NEXT DOOR','','','http://www.alfaaz.co.uk','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 14:01:23',0,'[\"\"]','[\"+91 9814044124\\r\",\"\\r\",\"Booking Agent\\t+919814044124\"]','alfaaz'),(1374,2,11,11,'NerveReck','The difference between a good and a great band lies in its ability to maintain a perfect balance between musicality and acceptability. To showcase technical prowess whilst getting an average music buff to clap and sing along to its music truly requires a great deal of songwriting skills combined with art of knowing that sometimes. . . Less is more!\r\n\r\nWhat with, catchy guitar riffs, unexpected time signature changes, polyrhythmic yet groovy drumming, rumbling funk bass lines, ambient keys, pop influenced vocals and lyrics one can sing after the first listen, NerveRek proves time and again why its worthy of being termed as a great band!\r\n\r\nThe list of laurels is incomplete without mentioning the energetic live shows with intense headbanging, metronome precision, contrasting dynamics and a roaring crowd of course. With a lightshow and a good sound engineer, NerveRek will leave little to be desired. ','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/NerveRek/10150319896685001','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 17:42:09',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','nervereck'),(1375,0,29,29,'Gautam Ghosh Collective ','The immensely gifted, multi-tasking trio Gautam Ghosh COLLECTIVE  (\"GGC\") is a critically acclaimed \"bond\" with the philosophy of \"World Sans Differences\". Its unique style & \"real time creativity\" has carved out a new  vocabulary that is globally inclusive & plural in all aspects of culture & expression with over a 150 odd instruments from all over the planet!\r\n\r\nIts the way forward to establish the noble ideals of a \"ONE WORLD ONE PEOPLE\" vision statement. MUSIC COOKED HOT ON THE SPOT is their USP & hallmark! Welcome to \"Universal Reality-Music\"! They are a hi-energy free-form impromptu jazz based world music trio with 5 successful albums & a docu-dvd to their credit. GAUTAM GHOSH (49yrs) Founder & Creative Head Keyboards, Synths,Vocals & Abstract Voicings, Tribal Percussions & Ethnic Instruments, Instant Lyrics, Loop-Composing, \"Real-time\" Music Direction. \r\n\r\nVIKAS GAUTAM (32yrs) Principal Soloist Saxophones, Flutes, Conch & Soft Percussions. Has played in the Gulf region based out of Dubai for many years & is in great demand in the Bollywood sessions as well. SIDDHARTH DAS (30yrs) Tech Head Sarod, Drums, Synth, Percussions & Loop Programming. Son of the famous sitarist Pandit Partho Das, he is a regular with the legendary Kathak dancer Pandit Birju Maharaj & tours worldwide as an ICCR performer as well.','','','http://www.gautamghosh.com/','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 14:24:50',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','gautam-ghosh-collective'),(1376,2,2,2,'The Koniac Net','\"One Last Monsoon\" was primarily recorded in the songwriter\'s (David Abraham) bedroom - an apt environment for an album, which essentially sounds like a love letter to the Indie & Alternative genres, as well as the artists/bands that allow these genres to thrive.\r\n\r\nA few that come to mind: the Stills, Matt Pond, Swervedriver, Toadies. The debut album from The Koniac Net, in many ways, pays tribute to these artists, but at the same time breathes new life into the Indie genre. \'One Last Monsoon\' is for all intent and purposes a mixed tape for the Indie music fan; a goodie bag in which the listener is rewarded each time they choose to reach in for something familiar but new.\r\n\r\nTracks from \"One Last Monsoon\" have already gained airplay in the U.S., U.K., France, Morocco, Australia, Italy, Germany, Belgium, Poland, Austria, Canada, Hungary, and Greece (with more on the way!). After receiving numerous requests to tour internationally, in June of 2012, the Koniac Net transformed from a one-man-project to a 5-piece band:\r\n\r\nDavid Abraham - Vocals + Guitar\r\nJason D\'Souza - Guitar + Backing Vocals (+ the mixing engineer on the album) \r\nIshaan Krishna - Guitar\r\nAdil Kurwa - Bass (+ guest bass player on the song \"Divine Submersion\") \r\nKarun Kannampilly - Drums\r\n\r\nJuly 4th, 2012 (Blue Frog, Bombay) marked the first live show for the Koniac Net.\r\n\r\nWHY \"THE KONIAC NET\":\r\nI had this name for one of my mix cds I made (when cds were still used). It represents that point in your life (that can happen at any moment) where you are presented with 2 paths, and even though \"Path A\" at the time looks better than the other, for reasons unknown, you are FORCED to take the less appealing \"Path B\".\r\n\r\nLater in life you realise that \"Path B\" is FAR more fruitful & lucrative, while the more appealing choice was in fact a metaphorical net (similar to that of an Angler Fish\'s protruding fleshy light). It\'s a name that\'s been with me for over a decade. It also precipitated during a time in my life where I realised how comforting scotch, whiskey, cognac & Southern Comfort were at trying times.\r\n\r\nHence \"the koniac net\" - an optimistic representation of how life\'s surprises/plans for you have reason & purpose, and are justified at random points of time in our lives, even though we might not be aware of it.','','https://www.facebook.com/koniacnet/info','http://www.thekoniacnet.com/','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 14:31:50',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','the-koniac-net'),(1377,0,0,0,'Guy J','','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','guy-j'),(1378,0,0,0,'Disharmony III ','','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','disharmony-iii'),(1379,0,0,0,'Wanted Yesterday','','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','wanted-yesterday'),(1380,0,0,0,'Beatitude ','','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','beatitude'),(1381,0,0,0,'Dj Bala','','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-bala'),(1382,0,0,0,'Dj Brook','','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','dj-brook'),(1383,0,0,0,'Thrill Seekers','','','','','','','','0',0,NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:31','2012-09-06 07:27:31',0,'','','thrill-