INSERT INTO `core_events` VALUES (1,'REGGAE RAJAHS SIMMER DOWN SESSIONS FEAT. INDIDGINUS (SA) at TLR','Simmer Down is Delhi/NCR\'s only weekly reggae night hosted by the Reggae Rajahs. Every Thursday at TLR, Hauz Khas Village, guests can enjoy the best in roots reggae, ska, rocksteady, dub and early dancehall. From time to time the Rajahs will be screening Caribbean themed films, celebrating landmark reggae events, creating theme nights and inviting guest selectors and live musicians to come jam with them.','http://www.reggaerajahs.com/','http://www.facebook.com/reggaerajahs','http://soundcloud.com/reggaerajahs','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-10-08 05:13:31',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-06-21 05:05:00','2012-06-21 10:05:00','reggae-rajahs-simmer-down-sessions-feat-indidginus-sa-at-tlr',1,NULL),(2,'STIFF KITTENS PRESENTS: AN HOMAGE TO SERGE GAINSBOURG','Stiff Kittens Inc and blueFROG present \'An Homage To Serge Gainsbourg\' for World Music Day in collaboration with Alliance Francaise De Delhi. A project centred around the songs of iconic French composer/singer Serge Gainsbourg...\n\nFor those not in the know, Serge Gainsbourg was a French singer, songwriter, poet, composer, artist, actor and director. Gainsbourg\'s extremely varied musical style and individuality make him extremely difficult to categorise. His legacy has been firmly established, and he is often regarded as one of the world\'s most influential popular musicians.\n\nHis lyrical brilliance in French has left an extraordinary legacy. His music, always progressive, covered many styles: jazz, ballads, mambo, lounge, reggae, pop (including adult contemporary pop, kitsch pop, ye-ye pop, \'80s pop, pop-art pop, prog pop, space-age pop, psychedelic pop, and erotic pop), funk, disco, calypso, Africana, bossa nova, and rock n\' roll. He has gained a following in the English-speaking world with many non-mainstream artists finding his arrangements highly influential.\n\nProduction company \'Stiff Kittens Inc\' (Medicine Show, Ska! Ska! Ska!) have put together a revue with a strong line up of 13 musicians and dancers featuring 25 songs of the French composer. As well as Gainsbourg, songs of his that were originally performed by artists such as Brigitte Bardot, Francoise Hardy, Jane Birkin and France Gall will be interpreted by various singers. Expect to hear classic songs such as Initials BB, Intoxicated Man, La Javanaise, Histoire de Melody Nelson, Laisse tombeur les filles, 69 anee erotique, Je TAime..Mon Non Plus, Lemon Incest, Bonnie and Clyde etc.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-21 05:05:48','2012-06-21 10:05:48','stiff-kittens-presents-an-homage-to-serge-gainsbourg',1,NULL),(3,'TOCADISCO (GERMANY)','Tocadisco celebrates over 15 years of international DJ stardom. After more than 100 international remixes, two artists albums and 20 successful worldwide singles, his success continues to grow with every gig, every record spun and every high profile remix.\r\n\r\nTheres no other producer in the current dance scene thats been able to produce as many wide-ranging, crossover hits as Tocadisco. Be it the much lauded remixes for Steve Aoki, Laidback Luke, Moby, Tiga, Pet Shop Boys or New Order amongst many others, or even the production, writing and execution of music for David Guetta, Kelis latest album Fleshtone, or Fischerspooners impressive back catalogue. Tocas work is far ranging, reaching and tickling the taste buds of DJs from across the musical spectrum, even gaining coveted spots on TV adverts broadcast across Europe.\r\n\r\nTocadiscos also a smitten, proud label owner of his imprint TOCA45. His core ethos is simple  to help support, promote and present the newest, freshest sounding club tracks available today. They all contain a mark of crossover potential. His unique, well-tought out and crossover style has once again come to the fray on ever-popular English house label Toolroom Knights, of which he mixed their installment of the successful Toolroom Knights compilation with British luminaire Chris Lake in 2010.\r\n\r\nThe Tocacabana Radio Show sees the big beats and heat of his renowned sound spread across weekly slots on stations around the world. Now confirmed to the schedule are more than 30 territories and stations within the big German\'s sights!\r\n\r\nIt wont be long until all corners of the globe are dancing to the sound of Tocacabana.','','http://www.facebook.com/tocadisco','http://soundcloud.com/tocadisco','https://www.facebook.com/events/330674600345138/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-21 11:05:00','2012-06-21 10:05:48','tocadisco-germany',1,NULL),(4,'HEINEKEN GREEN ROOM: MUX MOOL','Ubiquitous within India\'s key metro cities, Heineken, the Dutch-born global beer brand bring to India for the very first time Heineken Green Room.\n\nA series of exclusive events, Heineken Green Room aims to showcase international electronic dance music artists with \"interesting music that perfectly complement the beer moment\".\n\nThe first series of Heineken Green Room will take place in Delhi, Mumbai and Bangalore on the 20th, 22nd and 24th of June respectively and will be headlined by American born DJ and producer Mux Mool.\n\nBending conventions as much as genres, Mux Mool is an artist whose following has seen an exponential growth of recent, especially online. Resolutely groovy and unfailingly charming, Mux Mools sound is a textural delight that has left audiences from Chicago to his hometown New York, begging for more.\n\nHis latest release, Planet High School (hear it here) is his second on Ghostly International and the follow up to his 2010 sonic masterpiece Skulltaste. A matured and beat laden LP, it\'s a glorious listen taking in influences from hip-hop, glitch, funk and electro of many.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-22 05:05:48','2012-06-22 10:05:48','heineken-green-room-mux-mool',1,NULL),(5,'PARIKRAMA LIVE','Parikrama formed in 1991 and have since been highly active in the Indian Rock Industry. With over 2500 concerts and more than 5 million free downloads, the band has a huge reach and fanbase across India and the world.\n\nThe band releases all its songs through their official website and social medias, free of charge. They have played the Download Festival in the UK while opening for Iron Maiden 3 times.','http://www.parikrama.com/home.html','http://www.facebook.com/parikrama?sk=wall','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-22 05:05:48','2012-06-22 10:05:48','parikrama-live',1,NULL),(6,'PETER CAT RECORDING CO.','Initially started as a solo project by front-man Suryakant Sawhney, Peter Cat Recording Co. otherwise known as pcrc is a Delhi/NCR based band that formed in 2010 and is currently made up of 4 members.\n\n\"The type of music we play is open to discussion (...) Our style ranges from gypsy jazz to ballroom waltz, midnight moonlight and car chase music (think Don). The sound is heavily inspired by 60s/70s Bollywood music, which was in turn inspired by American music of the 50s, such as big band music and soul. Lyrically, we choose to write about prostitutes, deception, android artists and about films coming to life.\"\n\nThe gypsy-like free spirits in pcrc express a laidback sound. An incredibly talented group of musicians headed by an extremely potent songwriter. A band that through this process has shown a real passion for discovering new music as well as a blatant disregard for putting themselves in any sort of box. We don\'t exactly know where this band is going to take us over the coming years. And that is exciting.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-22 05:05:48','2012-06-22 10:05:48','peter-cat-recording-co',1,NULL),(7,'WHIRLING KALAPAS','Whirling Kalapas is an acoustic-based trio created by Mahesh Tinaikar and Uday Benegal (from the pioneering rock band Indus Creed) and multi-instrumentalist Sankarshan Kini. The trios music can be described variously as neo-folk, alt-country, mellow, and often funky, acoustic rock. The bands vocally and instrumentally lush sound has been garnering much attention and praise from audiences across the country. The trio is a rich addition to Indias current wave of alternative music forms, especially for audiences looking beyond the volume-driven sounds of rock and electronic acts populating the Indie scene. This is cerebral yet accessible music for the thinking listener.\n\nWith Indus Creed, Uday and Mahesh have released 4 highly successful albums and performed across the world, including in the USSR, the Middle East and the UK. They have also won numerous awards, including an Asia-wide MTV Video Music Award for their song Pretty Child. Among a host of other achievements, Indus Creed jammed live with GunsNRoses guitar player Slash, shared the stage with Bon Jovi to more than 50,000 people in Bombay and was invited to play at Peter Gabriels prestigious WOMAD festival in the UK. They are just back from recent performance headlining Lou Majaws renowned Bob Dylan birthday celebrations in Shillong, in May, 2012.','','http://www.facebook.com/whirlingkalapas','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-22 05:05:48','2012-06-22 10:05:48','whirling-kalapas',1,NULL),(8,'SICKFLIP','Sickflip is a collaborative and experimental solo project brought to life by Sarvesh Shrivastava, a 20 year old music producer and DJ from Bombay (of Mental Martians fame).\r\n\r\nMusically, Sickflip ranges from glitch hop, through to dubstep, drumstep, experimental and chill out. His styles are majorly influenced by artists like Bassnectar, Vent, Ill-Esha, Koan Sound, Trolley Snatcha, Funtcase, Amon Tobin, Noisia and more\r\n\r\nTo make things more interesting behind the console, he plays a groovy blend of glitch hop, drumstep and dubstep along with live sampling, loops and sequences, keeping it fresh, distinct and unusual.','','','','ZOMATO',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-22 08:05:00','2012-06-22 10:05:48','sickflip',1,NULL),(9,'DJ MOCITY PRESENTS: THE FUTURE (ELECTRO HIP-HOP)','DJ MoCity was born in Baghdad and raised In Delhi/NCR. This rising star DJ/MC/promoter/street artist has long held a reputation as Delhi nightlifes busiest man-about-town.\r\n\r\nAn artist known nation-wide for his work with Reggae Rajahs, not to mention his earliest forays into event promotion with his legendary South Delhi Block parties, and numerous wildly popular properties he\'s been involved with such as Delitronica, Bass Camp and Holi Cow amongst others...\r\n\r\n\"About two years ago we stumbled upon fresh new sounds that needed to be shared with all of you. We therefore set up a monthly night called The Future, where we showcase our selection from musical visionaries such as Gramatik, Michael Menert and of course, the artist who started it all, Pretty Lights. With the right combination of lights, sound and unexplored musical territory, we hope to inspire and spark a new path to our own Future.\" - DJ Mocity','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-23 02:05:00','2012-06-23 10:05:48','dj-mocity-presents-the-future-electro-hip-hop',1,NULL),(10,'BOMBAY BASEMENT (LIVE)','Bombay Bassment is a 4 piece eclectic band from Bombay, India formed in 2010. The lineup consists of MC/rapper Bobkat, drummer Levin, bassist Ruell and Chandu on electronics. Their music is an upbeat blend of hip-hop, rap, reggae, funk and drum n bass. Each member brings forth varied influences and backgrounds making the bands sound completely unique.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-23 02:05:00','2012-06-23 10:05:48','bombay-basement-live',1,NULL),(11,'DALE ANDERSON','Dale Anderson has brought his techno-tinged sound to more than fifty cities in twenty countries on four continents. As both a DJ and producer, Dale\'s musical diversity cuts across the deepest and darkest percussive house, to a tougher 4am club sound that borders the line between house and techno.\n\nA musician through and through, Dale is equally at home manning the controls in the studio as he is in the the dingiest of dimly lit low ceiling basement clubs or the main stage of an outdoor festival.\n\nAppearances at some of the the most widely respected clubs and parties in the world - Cocoon in Frankfurt, Ministry of Sound in London, the Miami Winter Music Conference etc. - has solidified his reputation as a consistent deliverer of quality.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-23 05:05:48','2012-06-23 10:05:48','dale-anderson',1,NULL),(12,'JAMES ZABIELA','Watching James Zabiela play should remind everyone that DJing is a performance art as much as it is being the purveyor of great musical sequences. The man (is a Dalek!) is an inspiration to his peers and his apprentices. - Pete Tong, Spring 2009\n\nThe glistening sonics of electronic music enticed a grunge loving 16 year old James Zabiela to his first set of belt drive turntables some years ago. Fast forward to 2012 and James is one of the most prolific DJs and producers on the planet. Over the last 10 years he has played endless gigs the world over, some era defining like his ongoing (8 years and counting) residency at Space in Ibiza to one off shows like Exit Festival 2006 where Goldie MCd over his set.\n\nJames has released critically acclaimed compilations on various labels including Renaissance and Ministry of Sound; In 2009, James released The Masters Series, an audio diary of 3 months in the life of James. It out-sold all its predecessors, rode high in both UK and USA iTunes stores and received top reviews from across the board. His remixes (official and otherwise) hold the same esteem, commissioned remix artists include Ladytron and Spooky, not to mention killer bootlegs like his amazing meld of Radiohead and Joris Voorn.\n\nOne of the finer bookings from blueFROG in recent times.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-23 05:05:48','2012-06-23 10:05:48','james-zabiela',1,NULL),(13,'DJ VAJRA (DMC WORLD CHAMPION)DJ VAJRA (DMC WORLD CHAMPION)','One of the best all-around DJs in the scene today, DJ Vajra has earned a place among the industry\'s elite. Whether he\'s winning the biggest battles in the world or dropping a crushing mix set at the club, fans are\nquickly learning why he has become DJ QBert\'s \"Favorite DJ in the world\".\n\nA Denver, Colorado native, Vajra strikes fear into the hearts of DJs in the battle realm. An accomplished battle DJ, his persistence finally paid off by becoming the 2011 DMC US Champion (5x DMC US Finalist) and eventually becoming the 2011 DMC World DJ Champion; joining the legendary ranks of DJ Cash Money, DJ QBert, Mixmaster Mike, Roc Raida, and DJ Craze to name a few.\n\nOn top of his extraordinary technical skills, he has also proven that he can rock a party by being a 2-time finalist at the US Red Bull Thr3estyle DJ Battles. Along with his recent appearance alongside the Invisibl Skratch Piklz at Thud Rumble\'s Fader Fest, Vajra is having the best year of any DJ could have.','','http://www.facebook.com/tocadisco','http://soundcloud.com/tocadisco','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-23 05:05:48','2012-06-23 10:05:48','dj-vajra-dmc-world-championdj-vajra-dmc-world-champion',1,NULL),(14,'TOCADISCO LIVE AT KITTY SU','Tocadisco celebrates over 15 years of international DJ stardom. After more than 100 international remixes, two artists albums and 20 successful worldwide singles, his success continues to grow with every gig, every record spun and every high profile remix.\r\n\r\nTheres no other producer in the current dance scene thats been able to produce as many wide-ranging, crossover hits as Tocadisco. Be it the much lauded remixes for Steve Aoki, Laidback Luke, Moby, Tiga, Pet Shop Boys or New Order amongst many others, or even the production, writing and execution of music for David Guetta, Kelis latest album Fleshtone, or Fischerspooners impressive back catalogue. Tocas work is far ranging, reaching and tickling the taste buds of DJs from across the musical spectrum, even gaining coveted spots on TV adverts broadcast across Europe.\r\n\r\nTocadiscos also a smitten, proud label owner of his imprint TOCA45. His core ethos is simple  to help support, promote and present the newest, freshest sounding club tracks available today. They all contain a mark of crossover potential. His unique, well-tought out and crossover style has once again come to the fray on ever-popular English house label Toolroom Knights, of which he mixed their installment of the successful Toolroom Knights compilation with British luminaire Chris Lake in 2010.\r\n\r\nThe Tocacabana Radio Show sees the big beats and heat of his renowned sound spread across weekly slots on stations around the world. Now confirmed to the schedule are more than 30 territories and stations within the big German\'s sights!\r\n\r\nIt wont be long until all corners of the globe are dancing to the sound of Tocacabana.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-23 02:05:00','2012-06-23 10:05:48','tocadisco-live-at-kitty-su',1,NULL),(15,'RADIO 79 PRESENTS: BLUEORB & VAEYA','BlueOrb\'s sets present a eclectic view into the plethora of exquisite electronic music, creating a cohesive blend of spacy ambient, intricate mid-tempo beats to high energy dancefloor grooves. BlueOrb is Praketh Sunder. Conceptualised in 2004 he has been a driving force in promoting and spinning electronic chillout at various music events in India, while further expanding his style towards the dancefloor in 2007.Vaeya has played a whole bunch of parties and festivals all over east coast Australia. He plays 2 completely different live sets, One style being dark intelligent tech, the other being a very lush progressive sound which is perfect for the day time or the afternoon. Having moved back to Mumbai, India in march 2010 he joined forces with Occulta Records which is a Bangalore based progressive trance label. In mid 2011 he moved to Delhi/NCR to work for events management company Audio Aashram.\r\n\r\nHe has played alongside Ocelot, Lish, Frechbax, Perfect Stranger, Krumelur, Braindrop, Aghori Tantrik, Sensient, Tetrameth and Grouch just to name a few.\r\n\r\nBuffaPirate is his alter ego to plunder a unique take on bass heavy electronic music. His sets can best be described as an amalgamation of west coast glitch-hop, reggae/hip-hop infused dubstep, big room breaks along with funk driven fidget-bassline house. His sets always keep the dance floor on its toes with surprises lurking at every junction.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-23 02:05:00','2012-06-23 10:05:48','radio-79-presents-blueorb-vaeya',1,NULL),(16,'KOHRA','Kohra is the deep, hypnotic and often grungy mirror image of Madhav Shorey. Raw analog signals and lush soundscapes mixed with percussion sounds and sharp glitches is what can be heard through his mysterious productions. A style that is intelligent enough to mesmerize, yet simple enough to move you.\r\n\r\nConstantly paving the way for a new sub-culture of underground dance music is no task for the timid, which is why he has already become the first Indian to have hit the top 10 charts on global industry standards such as Beatport. As a producer his music has been signed to many well respected international record labels including Sounds Of Earth, Trident Music, Wide Angle Recordings and Echoes Records to name a few.','http://www.kohra.in/','https://www.facebook.com/kohra.in?sk=info','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-23 02:05:00','2012-06-23 10:05:48','kohra',1,NULL),(17,'PUMA LOVES VINYL: ANKUR & THE GHALAT FAMILY, TOUGH ON TOBACCO, DUALIST INQUIRY & MORE','Puma Loves Vinyl is project that will see the internationally recognised sports brand press an Indian indie compilation on a special 12? LP.\r\n\r\nAll tracks due to be released via the LP were made specially for Puma. The compilation includes tracks from Gaurav Raina (Midival Punditz), Karsh Kale, Ankur & The Ghalat Family, Tough On Tobacco, The Supersonics, Reggae Rajahs and Dualist Inquiry.\r\n\r\nPuma Loves Vinyl kicks off on Saturday, June 23 with a free gig at Stage 1, Mehboob Studio.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-23 02:05:00','2012-06-23 10:05:48','puma-loves-vinyl-ankur-the-ghalat-family-tough-on-tobacco-dualist-inquiry-more',1,NULL),(19,'HEINEKEN GREEN ROOM: MUX MOOL','Ubiquitous within India\'s key metro cities, Heineken, the Dutch-born global beer brand bring to India for the very first time Heineken Green Room.\r\n\r\nA series of exclusive, invite-only events (don\'t worry, we\'ll be giving tickets away), Heineken Green Room aims to showcase international electronic dance music artists with \"interesting music that perfectly complement the beer moment\".\r\n\r\nThe first series of Heineken Green Room will take place in Delhi, Mumbai and Bangalore on the 20th, 22nd and 24th of June respectively and will be headlined by American born DJ and producer Mux Mool.\r\n\r\nBending conventions as much as genres, Mux Mool is an artist whose following has seen an exponential growth of recent, especially online. Resolutely groovy and unfailingly charming, Mux Mools sound is a textural delight that has left audiences from Chicago to his hometown New York, begging for more.\r\n\r\nHis latest release, Planet High School (hear it here) is his second on Ghostly International and the follow up to his 2010 sonic masterpiece Skulltaste. A matured and beat laden LP, it\'s a glorious listen taking in influences from hip-hop, glitch, funk and electro of many.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-24 02:05:00','2012-06-24 10:05:48','heineken-green-room-mux-mool-1',1,NULL),(20,'JAMES ZABIELA, JULIET FOX, DJ IVAN, TUHIN MEHTA & MUCH MORE','Watching James Zabiela play should remind everyone that DJing is a performance art as much as it is being the purveyor of great musical sequences. The man (is a Dalek!) is an inspiration to his peers and his apprentices. - Pete Tong, Spring 2009\r\n\r\nStill only 24 and first introduced to the world of acid house through his father who worked in a local record shop at the tender age of 12, Zabiela has been a genre defying production and performance powerhouse for a number of years. Although his early days saw him stand by his signature style of breakbeat and house, more recently, he has been regarded as a tech house DJ yet still incorporating breakbeat music into his varied sets.\r\n\r\nToday, the Southampton based producer and DJ is world renowned and one of the most prolific artists on the planet. Over the last 10 years he has played countless gigs the world over, some era defining like his ongoing (8 years and counting) residency at Space in Ibiza to one off shows like Exit Festival (2006) where Goldie MCd over his set. Also known for his turntable skills, extensive use of loops and effects and the use of Pioneer CDJ-2000s and EFX1000 as well as Ableton Live with various controllers and sometimes even his iPad, Zabiela first gained fame in 2000 by winning Muzik Magazine\'s Bedroom Bedlam competition and Best Bedroom Bedlam DJ in 2001.\r\n\r\nZabiela also tested the new pioneer DJM800, the CDJ1000MK3 and the EFX 1000 at the 2006 Frankfurt Musikmesse whilst consistently helping Pioneer Electronics develop their top of the line DJ gear including the CDJ-2000 and CDJ-900 media turntables.\r\n\r\nFusing the latest breakbeat slates into dark swathes of deep tech house is the key to Zabielas sound. A heady mix of bump-laden melodies and subtle, soul-stirring chord changes...','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-24 02:05:00','2012-06-24 10:05:48','james-zabiela-juliet-fox-dj-ivan-tuhin-mehta-much-more',1,NULL),(21,'0101 ELECTRONIC: PRASHANT PALLEMONI','Sundays are all set to let in the electronic invasion. Catch the best music producers, DJs and artists playing live. Let them create a night to showcase to you some of the best electronic music around.\n\nOccupying the soundscapes in your mind, let the most intelligent forms of electronic music seep into you as you rock the night away. Come and dance to some of the most talented electronica artists from across the country and around the world.\n\n+\n\nPrashant Pallemoni is the talented producer from an off the wall project called PandA System. He also operates under the alias of UNNAYANAA and is one third of Bangalore based experimental band Schizophonic. Extremely talented and truly contemporary Prasant exemplifies the scope for electronic music in the country.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-24 05:05:48','2012-06-24 10:05:48','0101-electronic-prashant-pallemoni',1,NULL),(22,'APOCALYPSE MEOW (LIVE)','Apocalypse: n. A prophetic disclosure; a revelation.\r\n\r\nAn electronic music project still in its nascent stage, Apocalypse Meow is the brainchild of a collaboration between a video game designer and a singer/songwriter. Left to their imaginations with an adequate supply of computer RAM and a sole desire to create, electronic music has only been a tiny piece of their creative output. Pushing forward many years of stimulating psychedelia, Apocalypse Meow starts off where acts like Pink Floyd, Air, Burial, Future Sound of London, Grizzly Bear, NIN, Frank Zappa, Massive Attack, Sigur Ros and Radiohead left off.\r\n\r\nMore important to AM however, is the role of music in today\'s world. When artistry has suddenly taken a backseat to commercial success, the duo wish to reset the balance, if only just to inspire another wave of\r\nthinkers, to think only for the sake of thought. Artistic expression and entertainment aside, music is primarily a way for ideas to evolve, challenging earlier notions and ushering in a new way of perceiving the old.\r\n\r\nMusic is, indeed, an apocalypse.\r\n\r\n\"AM is an experiment. There is no sound worth hiding from, for all sounds are mere vibrations; the rustling of leaves, the roar of a tiger, the sound of rain and thunder, the crash of a meteor, the movement of ocean waves... the purr of a sleeping kitten. Here lie the seeds of endless experimentation. Conformity and genre are child\'s play, but left to the all-encompassing universe of a wave of sound, there is only possibility to be found. The only thing left to do in these uncharted lands is to follow your ear.\"','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-27 02:05:00','2012-06-27 10:05:48','apocalypse-meow-live',1,NULL),(23,'HEAVY 01: LAUNCH W/ NUCLEYA, TAPAN RAJ, DALE & GRAIN','The launch of a brand new mid-week spectacular in the heart of Hauz Khas Village, Heavy promises to fill the urge of any Delhi based electronic music lover into the darker side of sounds.\r\n\r\nPromised to only cover \"hard dubstep, breaks, drumstep and D&B\", this is \"only for the hardcore - only for the headstrong!\"\r\n\r\nLine up includes:\r\n\r\nNucleya / Tapan Raj / Dale and Introducing Grain','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-27 02:05:00','2012-06-27 10:05:48','heavy-01-launch-w-nucleya-tapan-raj-dale-grain',1,NULL),(24,'INDUS CREED \'EVOLVE\' ALBUM LAUNCH','Indus Creed are back! The trailblazers of the Indian rock movement return in a new, contemporary form. Call it IC 2.0 or Indus Creed in new form. Either way, Uday Benegal, Mahesh Tinaikar and Zubin Balaporia, the original frontman, guitar player and keyboard player of the pioneering band, are focused on the task at hand: to break new ground even as they slam it out.\r\n\r\nIt\'s been just over 10 years since Indus Creed shut shop. Many were perplexed as to why a band would suddenly call it a day at the peak of their success. After all, they were the first name on the lips of every Indian rock fan, with hits, awards and accolades stacked high and still climbing. Reasons and theories abound, but the truth is simple. The fellers were unhappy with the way the music biz in India was heading. It had become corporatized, crass and stifling. Additionally, they had reached a point individually where they wanted to explore different directions...musically and geographically.\r\n\r\nUday and guitarist Jayesh Gandhi went West, moving to New York City in 1999 with their newly formed Indo-rock and funk outfit Alms For Shanti. Nine years and many gigs later Uday returned to Bombay, where Mahesh and Zubin had remained. The axeman and keyboard wiz had both been busy too, separately making music as producers and collaborators in the studios, as well as with other bands. Uday and Mahesh first joined together with their acoustic band Whirling Kalapas, which began to make waves the moment they hit the stage. Zubin used to drop in to play the occasional gig with them. Inevitably, though, the three rockers couldn\'t resist crankin\' it out loud...and the new Indus Creed was born.\r\n\r\nFresh blood was needed to get this baby off the ground. Recruiting the rock-solid bass wunderkind Rushad Mistry was a no-brainer. A seasoned sideman and stalwart of a thousand and some gigs, Rushad has played with an impossibly diverse array of bands, artists and ensembles. Jai Row Kavi was an equally obvious selection. The 23-year-old powerhouse drummer can not only wack the bejeebers out of a drumkit, he can go from 0 to 60 at light speed while singing a Carnatic operetta in perfect falsetto. Who could ask for better bandmates?','http://www.induscreed.net/','http://www.facebook.com/IndusCreedNow','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-28 02:05:00','2012-06-28 10:05:48','indus-creed-evolve-album-launch',1,NULL),(25,'CLONEFEST SOUNDCHECK: THEM CLONES, DITTY & MARK, ADIL & VASUNDHRA, ADVAITA','Them Clones formed in 2000. \"It came about as we were looking to forge an identity as a left-of-the-middle sort of band. The name reflects the general attitude of the band which was to look at their stage personalities as clones of themselves\".\r\n\r\nInspired by the dramatic world of rock n\' roll and of course themselves, their tryst with songwriting has directed them across the course of the thoughtful to confessional, from the assertive to the provocative; but has been, consistently accompanied by a tight groove and silken melody.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-28 02:05:00','2012-06-28 10:05:48','clonefest-soundcheck-them-clones-ditty-mark-adil-vasundhra-advaita',1,NULL),(26,'CRAZY LEGS - ROCK STEADY CREW (DJ SET)','With a career that spans over 3 decades, Crazy Legs is one of the world\'s biggest names in breakdancing and is currently president (and only original member) of the internationally renowned Rock Steady Crew. Today he is also involved in community outreach, dance instruction and dance theatre productions. His pioneering status is also reflected in his appearances in fiction films and documentaries both old and new.\r\n\r\nThe legendary Rock Steady Crew (RSC) was founded in the Bronx, in the late 70s by Bboys including Jimmy Dee, Joe Joe, Jimmy Lee and Easy Mike. Only the best Bboys were in RSC and the only way to get in the crew was to battle a member. It was a competition that few won. Crazy Legs battled his way into the crew at the tender age of 12. In 1979, after his family relocated from the Bronx to Manhattan, Crazy Legs sought and eventually received permission to establish a Rock Steady Crew chapter in his new borough. RSC will be celebrating its 35th anniversary this year.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-28 02:05:00','2012-06-28 10:05:48','crazy-legs-rock-steady-crew-dj-set',1,NULL),(27,'NO JAZZ & DUALIST INQUIRY','No Jazz is a French electronic music band, often labeled as being a Nu-jazz band, with sounds borrowed from jazz and Cuba. Since November 2006, they\'ve played every Saturday inthe French TV show Salut les Terriens, presented by Thierry Ardisson.','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Nojazz/38455399437','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-29 02:05:00','2012-06-29 10:05:48','no-jazz-dualist-inquiry',1,NULL),(28,'CRAZY LEGS - ROCK STEADY CREW (DJ SET)','With a career that spans over 3 decades, Crazy Legs is one of the world\'s biggest names in breakdancing and is currently president (and only original member) of the internationally renowned Rock Steady Crew. Today he is also involved in community outreach, dance instruction and dance theatre productions. His pioneering status is also reflected in his appearances in fiction films and documentaries both old and new.\r\n\r\nThe legendary Rock Steady Crew (RSC) was founded in the Bronx, in the late 70s by Bboys including Jimmy Dee, Joe Joe, Jimmy Lee and Easy Mike. Only the best Bboys were in RSC and the only way to get in the crew was to battle a member. It was a competition that few won. Crazy Legs battled his way into the crew at the tender age of 12. In 1979, after his family relocated from the Bronx to Manhattan, Crazy Legs sought and eventually received permission to establish a Rock Steady Crew chapter in his new borough. RSC will be celebrating its 35th anniversary this year.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-29 02:05:00','2012-06-29 10:05:48','crazy-legs-rock-steady-crew-dj-set-1',1,NULL),(29,'THE GLOW SHOW W/ DJ SAN','Enter the illusionary world of SAN  The Super dj, as he transforms in his new Avatar and unleashes the LED LASER MASK 2.0. A wonderland of massive sounds, lights and live visuals. For the first time in India experience the threshold of art and technology.\r\n\r\nA Edgy team of animators, graphic designers, costume and make-up developers have designed and constructed a face hugging sound actuated luminescent mask for San comprising of over two hundred light emitting and laser diodes. This performance will feature a heavy bottom electro/dubstep/drum and bass set infected with warped sampling and experimental turntablism, creating a never experienced eye candy performance.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-02 09:05:00','2012-06-30 10:05:48','the-glow-show-w-dj-san',1,NULL),(30,'HASHBACK HASHISH & AUDIO PERVERT','Hashback Hashish is the stage name of Ashish Sachan, an incredibly creative and persistently innovative DJ/ Producer, based in Delhi, India. Beginning by experimenting with the fascinating music scene in Perth regularly, he was quickly getting recognized because of his distinct sound at Rise. Upon his arrival home, his inarguably superior taste in music mated with his creative streak - the lovechild of which is Hashback Hashish.Audio Pervert has been involved in the electronic music scene in India for the last decade.\r\n\r\nHe is a producer and composer based in Delhi/NCR with numerous collaborations with indie artists such as Da Saz, Delhi Sultanate, Tempo Tantrick, Sridhar & Thayil, Shair & Func, Advaita and Delhi Electronica Supply Unit. He is also one half of Teddy Boy Kill, an electro punk duo emerging as an distinct and hard hitting electronica act from Delhi/NCR. Creating music with synthesisers and virtual devices remains the main facet of his solo music adventures, with more than 20 singles available for downloads and streaming online.\r\n\r\nHe has been actively involved in fostering the indie electronica scene with various organisations such Goethe Institut, C.O.Pop Festival Cologne and the Global Grooves Festival in Delhi/NCR. He has also recently produced remixes for Cologne based label Serve & Destroy, for artists such as Twila Too, Bob Humid and Ernest & Drake.\r\n\r\nIn each one of HHs projects, be it the tightly-themed and executed Audio Visual Daft Punk, Deadmau5 & LCD Soundsystem Tributes or the proper techno gigs at venues like Blue Frog (DEL, MUM), Rise (Australia), TLR Caf (DEL), and Gulmarg Winter Festival and Woods Talk Festival, Delitronica, D.E.S.U. and more, his constant drive to create something unique shows clearly through.\r\n\r\nApart from performing regular DJ sets across India, he recently released his debut album The Grinning, Naked Bunch independently to rave reviews by NME India, Wild City and Indiecision (NH7) of many.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-30 02:05:00','2012-06-30 10:05:48','hashback-hashish-audio-pervert',1,NULL),(31,'INDUS CREED \'EVOLVE\' ALBUM LAUNCH','Indus Creed are back! The trailblazers of the Indian rock movement return in a new, contemporary form. Call it IC 2.0 or Indus Creed in new form. Either way, Uday Benegal, Mahesh Tinaikar and Zubin Balaporia, the original frontman, guitar player and keyboard player of the pioneering band, are focused on the task at hand: to break new ground even as they slam it out.\r\n\r\nIt\'s been just over 10 years since Indus Creed shut shop. Many were perplexed as to why a band would suddenly call it a day at the peak of their success. After all, they were the first name on the lips of every Indian rock fan, with hits, awards and accolades stacked high and still climbing. Reasons and theories abound, but the truth is simple. The fellers were unhappy with the way the music biz in India was heading. It had become corporatized, crass and stifling. Additionally, they had reached a point individually where they wanted to explore different directions...musically and geographically.\r\n\r\nUday and guitarist Jayesh Gandhi went West, moving to New York City in 1999 with their newly formed Indo-rock and funk outfit Alms For Shanti. Nine years and many gigs later Uday returned to Bombay, where Mahesh and Zubin had remained. The axeman and keyboard wiz had both been busy too, separately making music as producers and collaborators in the studios, as well as with other bands. Uday and Mahesh first joined together with their acoustic band Whirling Kalapas, which began to make waves the moment they hit the stage. Zubin used to drop in to play the occasional gig with them. Inevitably, though, the three rockers couldn\'t resist crankin\' it out loud...and the new Indus Creed was born.\r\n\r\nFresh blood was needed to get this baby off the ground. Recruiting the rock-solid bass wunderkind Rushad Mistry was a no-brainer. A seasoned sideman and stalwart of a thousand and some gigs, Rushad has played with an impossibly diverse array of bands, artists and ensembles. Jai Row Kavi was an equally obvious selection. The 23-year-old powerhouse drummer can not only wack the bejeebers out of a drumkit, he can go from 0 to 60 at light speed while singing a Carnatic operetta in perfect falsetto. Who could ask for better bandmates?','http://www.induscreed.net/','http://www.facebook.com/IndusCreedNow','','https://www.facebook.com/events/330865416992774/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-06 09:05:00','2012-07-06 10:05:48','indus-creed-evolve-album-launch-1',1,NULL),(32,'GUY J, KOHRA & BLOT (DJ SET)','Israeli producer Guy J has established himself as one of the most sophisticated and emotive producers in electronic music of the last decade, with a body of work and a sphere of influence that belies relatively short time in the spotlight. Whether it be his sensual, hypnotic take on house music, his deeply textured techno or his wondrous ambient material, his work is always touched with a magic and emotion that few rival.\r\n\r\nGuy started producing at the age of 14, amassing a wealth of equipment and experience and dedicating his life to learning the craft (my friends called my room the cave). His first release came at the age of 21, but it was his 2007s gem Save Me that proved to be his real launchpad. John Digweed snapped up the glistening, dramatic slice of deeper house music up for his legendary Bedrock Records, setting in motion a chain of events that would change his life forever. It was like a dream coming true. I never knew it would lead me to having two albums on a label that I really grew up with.\r\n\r\nNever one to be pigeonholed, his portfolio is a diverse beast, with releases finding their way onto Tigas increasingly eclectic Turbo imprint amongst others. To feature on two labels that are essentially synonymous with two very different scenes is testament to his versatility, and above all, the quality and conviction of his productions. I don\'t see myself as producer of one genre only; I believe in exploring and trying different stuff when you have all the tools you need to create he clarifies. To be signed to Turbo... its also amazing as it a big label that has its own crowd of people who listen to a certain type of music, and to be part of it is great.\r\n\r\n2012 sees Guy kick off an exciting new project with his close colleagues and friends at Bedrock: his very own imprint Lost & Found, a sub-label for John Digweeds long running mothership where hell release music by himself and his favourite producers. Then theres the small matter of a release on Cocoon, one of the most highly regarded labels in techno and beyond, and some exciting collaborations in the pipeline with some other inspiring artists. As always with this unique talent, its quality, not quantity. Each of his releases is met with a swell of anticipation, and for once in this often over-hyped world, its fully justified.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-07 02:05:00','2012-07-07 10:05:48','guy-j-kohra-blot-dj-set',1,NULL),(33,'THE FRINGE','The Fringe is a band that formed in early 2010. At the time, the bands two guitar players were composing music related to different genres whilst trying to bring out a brand new sound. The line up was completed soon after.\r\n\r\n\"We started making music in late 2010. Every member with his definition of music puts together small parts, leading to a whole new sound. We are presently experimenting and fusing different genres and aiming to give out songs with as much diversity as we can.\" - The Fringe','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1925-the-fringe',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-13 02:05:00','2012-07-13 10:05:48','the-fringe',1,NULL),(34,'ANONYMOUS: A LOVE LETTER TO MUMBAI (RAVE PARTY)','\"Dear Mumbai,\r\n\r\nYou seem to be going through some tough times. You were once so much fun, so carefree. Now a dark cloud looms over you, repressing your psyche, abusing your conscience. You begin to question who you are, your values, your moral fibre; locked up at home, you trip into a downward spiral... Break through this cloud, ride the silver lining up the spiral over to TLR Delhi/NCR.\r\n\r\nBecause honey, if he don\'t love you like you deserve, maybe you should dump his sorry behind and jump into our open arms. We promise to treat you right and never let go. Sowing the seeds of love baby. xx\"','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-14 02:05:00','2012-07-14 10:05:48','anonymous-a-love-letter-to-mumbai-rave-party',1,NULL),(35,'THE SHAKEY RAYS (CHENNAI)','The Shakey Rays are a 4-piece rhythm n blues/rock n roll band from Chennai. The band got together with an accumulation of ideas, song sketches, sounds and rhythms from previous bands, some of which have previously performed live concerts in many cities.\r\n\r\nSongwriting duo and founding members of the group, Dhruva Gautham and Vikram Kannan decided that they needed an outlet; a strong vehicle of expression for their growing musical interests. They gave their old schoolmate Niranjan Swaminathan (ex-Blacklisted) a buzz with a nice little drum kit at his doorstep and with a list of records to study. Iuni Yooni joined in on bass, completing the quartet. The band is at its strongest when the music is interactive and impulsive. Extended, onstage jams allow the musicians to branch out musically and vary the 4-piece format. Dhruva and Vikram often work on different arrangements for each song and explore various musical patterns. It is the overall sound of the record that is considered important, genre hardly being a relevant factor.','','','','http://timescity.com/delhi/events/the-shakey-rays-shashwat-pande-live/39536',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-20 02:05:00','2012-07-20 10:05:48','the-shakey-rays-chennai',1,NULL),(36,'NERD DEPARTMENT & WHITE RABBIT','Nerd Dept is the brainchild of DJ/producer Sanil Sudan and techno DJ/producer Vishnu PS. Between the two of them they have been actively pushing the house and techno sound with their individual productions and DJ sets around the country.\r\n\r\nBoth a part of the PureNoise Crew, they joined forces recently to push and produce their rather selective take on grungy, gritty, in your face house and techno music.\r\n\r\nFrom easy laid back disco grooves to hard hitting techno beats, their love for all forms these two genres will be apparent in their productions in the Studio or their 4 deck DJ sets. Being the analog fools they are, NerdDepartment aims to geek out on their shiny toys both analog and digital to create an experience which is both intelligent and edgy.\r\n\r\nNerd Dept will be accompanied on visuals by BOMB.','','','','ZOMATO',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-21 02:05:00','2012-07-21 10:05:48','nerd-department-white-rabbit',1,NULL),(41,'The Hoodwink Circle','The Hoodwink Circle is a fine ground between progressive rock and funk. We make music that goes best with good times.\r\n \r\nThe Hoodwink Circle is an eclectic mix of performers from all over Bombay. The members also play for or have played for bands like Louis Banks, Toufeeq Qureshi, Shibani Kashyap, Ash Chandler, Nandoo Bhende, Merlin Desouza, Manasi Scott, The Bombay Rock Project, Gino Banks, Para-Vayu, The Echoes, Sheldon d Silva, Asha Bhosle, Susie Q etc; and have come together to pursue their true musical roots, which are primarily based on Funk, Alternative and their derivations.\r\n \r\nThe band was initially called Wasabi, and gained local fame by competing in a few college competitions. Around October 2008, guitarist Sanju and bassist Ishaan met through the Nandoo Bhende Band; and the band hasnt looked back since.','','http://www.facebook.com/thehoodwinkcircle','','Hard Rock',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-28 02:05:00','2012-06-28 10:05:48','the-hoodwink-circle',1,NULL),(42,'Cobbled Street and October','Germinating in 2007, October is a musical hybrid of the modern genres of alternative and progressive rock layered with psychedelia, expressed through the collective musical meeting ground of its six members \r\n1.    Shantanu Shanty Sudarshan  Drums\r\n2.    Jeffrey Laloo  Bass, Backing Vocals\r\n3.    Rohan Panjiar  Guitars\r\n4.    Shashvat Pandit  Guitars\r\n5.    Amitabh Mukherjee  Vocals\r\n\r\nWe consider narrowing a band down to a genre as musical racism; therefore we strive to combine anything and everything that cools our beans. A completely secular musical orgy if you will, with its members bringing their unique musical influences to create a sound reflective of the bands gritty and stark look at its surroundings. We almost completely always believe in playing our original compositions with no regard to the number of cries of \'smoke on the water\'. The reason why we named our band \'October\' is a well kept secret within the band, and we do not wish to divulge it any time soon. Talk to our mascot (gopi) for details.','www.octobertheband.com','www.facebook.com/october.the.band','','Hard Rock',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-28 02:05:00','2012-06-28 10:05:48','cobbled-street-and-october',1,NULL),(43,'Solder','Solder is a Bangalore based band which was born with the intent of writing feel good songs, and belting them out Live and Loud.\r\n\r\nThe Indian sub-continent over the past decade has been nestling an independent music scene, and in 2009 Bangalore gave us SOLDER. Siddarth Abraham, Mark Escottee, Akhilesh Kumar, Joel Rozario and Samson Phillip got together by forces which they now like to call destiny, and started making music almost randomly, and Bangalore saw a band that played their music Live and Loud and contributing their two bits to the independent music movement on India.\r\n\r\nWith a line-up at equilibrium and a defined sound, the gigs and the competitions (runners up Strawberry Fields 2009, Bangalore Winners of Yamaha Asian Beats 2010, Bangalore Winners of Channel V Launchpad 2011) kept coming and with it Solder developed a reputation of being electric, energetic and fun on stage. The Solder show is like one big party, completely informal, with the feel good vibe, bringing the house down with funk, soul, rock and twenty-something energy. And with this passion for music and their ability to connect with their audiences, Solder started winning over fans at every gig theyve played, and made audiences feel the vibe that they call Live and Loud!! ','','','','Hard Rock',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-28 02:05:00','2012-06-28 10:05:48','solder',1,NULL),(44,'Blakc-Album Launch','Black, a grunge/alternative band from Mumbai are all set to release their sophomore album Mothered Land. Having toured extensively across the country and played hundreds of shows to a varied audience, they are undoubtedly one of the most exciting indie bands In the country today.\r\n\r\nBLAKC started of in 2005 when Shawn (vocals) and Anish (guitars) started jamming in St. Xavier?s College. 2006 saw Roop and Shishir join the band on bass and drums respectively. In 2007, the final lineup change was Reinhardt on guitars. Since then we have played over 80 shows and competitions across ten cities in India. Shows with 50 people to shows with over 3,000 people like in Indore, Kanpur, Pune, Ahmedabad, Assam and Delhi.\r\n\r\nBLAKC is only about two things, the music and the fans. Our music enables us to connect with an audience whether big or small. We have a brilliant show if we know the audience has enjoyed themselves with us. We only play our own music and have released our first album entitled Choking On A Dream?. The album has sold over 800 copies and has received some great reviews from HT caf, HT Times and Rolling Stone with more to come.\r\n\r\nBLAKC has always made an effort to keep in touch with our fans through the internet. Today BLAKC is reaching close to 9000 fans on Facebook, 27,000 hits on our online music profiles and is the #3 Alternative band in India and #1 in Mumbai on ReverbNation. The numbers and the rankings only mean that people are watching us, and that?s all we want.','','www.facebook.com/blackattainment','','Hard Rock',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-28 02:05:00','2012-06-28 10:05:48','blakc-album-launch',1,NULL),(45,'BRIAN CITRO TRIO FEATURING TARUN BALANI','The Brian Citro Trio is fusion of American jazz traditions and contemporary Indian musical styles. The trio is a welcome new addition to the contemporary Indian music scene, performing newly composed music and reinterpreting standards from jazz greats like Thelonious Monk, Sonnly Rollins and Wayne Shorter.\r\n\r\nThe group has developed a truly original sound that combines the disparate but shared musical influences of its members. Guitarist Brian Citro hails from Chicago and is steeped in the jazz and avant-garde traditions that make that city\'s music scene one of the most vibrant in the world. Brian has performed around the world and is currently based in Delhi. His refined sense of jazz improvisation and versatile harmonic vocabulary turns each performance into a unique musical experience. Bassist Abishek Mangla and drummer Nikhil Vasudeva are two of India\'s most gifted young musicians. They have established themselves as integral members of the Indian rock and creative music scenes as members of bands like Bandish, The Ska Vengers and The Commons. Together they form an agile rhythm section for the trio informed by India\'s rich rhythmic tradition as well as contemporary Western styles like funk, fusion and indie rock.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-27 02:05:00','2012-06-27 10:05:48','brian-citro-trio-featuring-tarun-balani',1,NULL),(46,'BLOT!','.L.O.T is an acronym for the Basic Love of Things.\r\n\r\nA multidisciplinary project helmed by Gaurav Malaker andAvinash Kumar and supported by a network of artists, BLOT focus on creating atypical clubland experiences. Avinash Kumar is a designer, visual artist, filmmaker and VJ, and a founding member of design and research firms Quicksand and BOX. Gaurav Malaker is a DJ, producer and a founding member of Qilla Records.\r\n\r\nThey blend sound and music, while manipulating their performance spaces to expand the frontiers of electronica performances. Visually B.L.O.T employ traditional filmmaking techniques as well as stop-motion animation and motion graphics, and the duo\' s diversity is as apparent in their music as it is in their visuals.\r\n\r\nAs India\' s original and leading audiovisual collective, B.L.O.T curated the experimental stage at Sunburn Festival in Goa (2010) and further afield, have performed at legendary venues like Tresor and Bar25 (Berlin) several times, as well as at Geneva\' s Electron Festival (2011), Berlin Music Week (2010), Champagnerama in Berlin (2010), London\' s South Bank Centre (2010) and at Nuits Sonores in Lyon (2009).','','http://www.facebook.com/blottin','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-27 02:05:00','2012-06-27 10:05:48','blot',1,NULL),(47,'THE VINYL RECORDS FEAT. AKU','The Vinyl Records (aka TVR), is a four piece girl band based in Delhi/NCR that came together in Feb 2010. The band was formed by Banu, Minam and Mithy who all hail from Arunachal Pradesh.\r\n\r\nAfter almost a years hiatus from performing the girls started jamming and coming up with ideas.The final touche of the band came when they were joined by present vocalist and keytarist Cherryian Bark from Assam early in 2011. TVR describe their sound as indie rock, post punk and the sound from new wave eras of 70s and 80s when analog and early digital sound was popular, Their influences include C.S.S, the B52s, Blondie, the Clash, the Ramones, the Strokes, Arctic Monkeys; fusing indie and post punk with a dash of glam rock kitsch with the keytar!','','http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-Vinyl-Records/162414153811500','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-27 02:05:00','2012-06-27 10:05:48','the-vinyl-records-feat-aku',1,NULL),(48,'ALTERSPACE #2: B.R.E.E.D & SUPPORT','B.R.E.E.D promotes his self-manufactured bass sounds in electronic creativity and funkiness. He uses local artifacts in his music like Indian street percussion to create a collage of funk, rhythmic texture and ethnic roots. His latest tracks breathe futuristically exotic sounds unlike any other.\r\n\r\nIn January 2010, B.R.E.E.D\'s remix of Jalebee Cartel\'s \"Mirrors\" sat in the Beatport Top 10 Dubstep charts. Shortly thereafter, B.R.E.E.D released an original EP on High Chai Recordings called Sound Killer, of which both tracks appeared in the Beatport dubstep charts yet again! This is the launch of his latest Incu-Bass EP, which you can get exclusively over at Beatport now.\r\n\r\nExpect a healthy dose of dubstep, crunk-step, dub-hop, downtempo, alternative hip-hop, beats and bass. Head here to listen to an exclusive Wild CIty mix made by B.R.E.E.D','http://breedbass.com/','http://www.facebook.com/Breeddub','http://soundcloud.com/breed','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-28 02:05:00','2012-06-28 10:05:48','alterspace-2-breed-support',1,NULL),(49,'MOONSHINE (LIVE)','Over the past couple of years, the Indian music industry has gone through a major shift giving way for bands to showcase a variety of new concepts to music lovers. For the first time in our country, Moonshine, a Delhi/NCR based band is introducing the concept of entirely original psychedelic rock.\r\n\r\nMoonshine is the brainchild of Rishi Sachdeva, who has been an integral part of the underground music scene for quite a while. Rishi is the frontman of Moonshine. Along with him, the band consists of Ananddev Banerjee on guitars, Nikhil Vasudevan on drums and Bijoy Sarkar on the bass guitar. The bands music is an entourage of sonic and surreal sounds with provoking lyrics and haunting melodies.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-29 02:05:00','2012-06-29 10:05:48','moonshine-live',1,NULL),(50,'DARREN EMERSON & KINI RAO','Darren Emerson is one of the most influential figures in dance music. His 17 year career has seen him work with everyone from Depeche Mode and The Chemical Brothers to Bjork and Jamie Cullum.\r\n\r\nHis success is evident in the numerous million+ selling hit albums and singles he has been a part of as well as his stunning DJ skills. When he turned 18, Rick Smith invited him to become the third member of techno band Underworld. 1993\'s dubnobasswithmyheadman was their commercial breakthrough onto the then burgeoning British electronica scene. While working on their second album, 1996\'s Second Toughest In The Infants, they released the single \"Born Slippy\", which was an instant hit following its inclusion on the soundtrack to the movie, Trainspotting. During his time with Underworld, the band released three albums and sold over a million albums world wide.','','http://www.facebook.com/DarrenEmersonMusic','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-29 02:05:00','2012-06-29 10:05:48','darren-emerson-kini-rao',1,NULL),(51,'KINI RAO','With rhythm in her soul, funk in her attitude and the right records on the turntable - Kini has been steadily creating waves in the EDM scene in India. Her passion for deeper harmonies were showcased on a regular basis at Zenzi Mills (Bombay). Her other notable gigs include an after hours set at Bar25 (Berlin), Villian\'s Club & Oakroom (Copenhagen) & Public Life (London).\r\n\r\nDoing complete justice to her cheeky self, Kini\'s sound can best be described as an ambivalent mlange of distorted kicks, crispy hats, funky basslines and quirky melodies. Currently producing electronic music, while also actively promoting EDM through her M.U.S.E mix series, her new project Disco Dodo intends to purse her more eclectic interests.\r\n\r\nFor music with a touch of soul subtly blended with her own intrinsic personality, Kini, is well on her way in becoming a force to be reckoned with.','','http://www.facebook.com/kinirao?sk=wall','http://soundcloud.com/kinirao','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-30 02:05:00','2012-06-30 10:05:48','kini-rao',1,NULL),(52,'R.E.D MAWKIN FEAT. AMAN MAHAJAN','Aman Mahajan, a pianist/keyboardist from India, has worked with musicians from all over the world in a plethora of musical idioms. A graduate of the Berklee College of Music (Boston), Aman is widely influenced by jazz, blues, electronic music and folk music from Africa, India, Turkey and the American continents. A few artists and groups he has worked with include Lucky Ali (Indian songwriter), Arooj Aftab (world fusion/Pakistani song), Gamelan Galak Tika (traditional Balinese), Project O.N.S (electro/jazz/funk), Joya (pop/neo-soul), and some of the foremost jazz musicians on the Indian scene.\r\n\r\nCurrently based out of Bangalore, Aman makes music and performs as a member of Schizophonic, an experimental electro-acoustic trio, and is also a member of UNK: The Radha Thomas Ensemble.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nRED Mawkin, after a decade of playing shows and 5 years of traveling between the United States and India is emerging yet again after a long break from singing and songwriting. While he very productively spent his time grooming the drummer within himself, he has stumbled his way back into the shoes of a frontman.','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-06 02:05:00','2012-07-06 10:05:48','red-mawkin-feat-aman-mahajan',1,NULL),(53,'REGGAE RAJAHS: RETURN OF THE RAJAHS at TLR','India\'s first reggae sound system. The trio composed of Diggy Dang, Mr. Herbalist and DJ MoCity (Iraq\'s first soundboy) are reggae entertainers and promoters based out of Delhi/NCR.\r\n\r\nComing together for their love of reggae music in early 2009, the Rajahs started playing a mix of roots reggae, lovers rock, ska and dancehall at venues across Delhi/NCR. By the summer of 2010, with a firm fan base established in their hometown, the Rajahs eventually broke free and invaded major cities across the world.\r\n\r\nRecently crowned India\'s first champion reggae sound (by defeating BASSFoundation in a very tightly contested Sound Clash), the Rajahs hope to keep spreading the message of love, unity and respect through the conscious sounds of original reggae music throughout India.\r\n\r\nThis is the trio\'s first weekend show at TLR for a number of months. We know this one\'s going off.','http://www.reggaerajahs.com/','http://www.facebook.com/reggaerajahs','http://soundcloud.com/reggaerajahs','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-10-08 05:13:21',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-07-07 02:05:00','2012-07-07 10:05:00','reggae-rajahs-return-of-the-rajahs-at-tlr',1,NULL),(54,'TEDDY BOY KILL','Teddy Boy Kill is a self confessed technologic \"beat punk\" consisting of Ashhar Farooqui, Samrat Bee, and recently added drummer Akshat Nauriyal. Otherwise known as Toymob, Audio Pervert and Tahska.\r\n\r\nForget everything you know about Indian electronica. \"Rising out of the usual clutter and clam of electronic music in India\", Teddy Boy Kill has forced itself to develop an edgy, moody and distinctly solid sound. An electronic-based rock/techno/electro band from Delhi/NCR, Teddy Boy Kill make a mark with their raucous live shows and high-energy music that draws comparisons to !!!, LCD Soundsystem, Justice, Walls and even Massive Attack at times. Yup, I said it.\r\n\r\nTheir music pulls towards many conflicting and opposing genres with an industrial sound that is seamlessly and disjointedly interwoven with confrontational lyrics. There is a profound quality about this partnership (especially when watching live) that gives their music a very distinctive heart and depth. Proud to be independent of any record label and giving away all their music for free via their soundcloud, Teddy Boy Kill have released one full length LP in the shape of The Exit Plan and numerous singles to date.','','http://www.facebook.com/groups/teddyboykill/','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-14 02:05:00','2012-07-14 10:05:48','teddy-boy-kill',1,NULL),(55,'Blues Blooded feat. Vinayak Pol, Denzil Mathias, Shireen Irani ','This High energy four piece blues rock outfit has been together since 2011, with their music a unique blend of styles ranging from Blues to 20th century Rock Fusion. The band\'s sound is recognisable with intensely catchy melodic heavy grooves, smooth guitars, driving rock bass and drums and the odd instrumental solos thrown in to the blues mojo mix.\r\n\r\nThe amalgamation of four passionate and driven musician is evident in their live gigs. The have an assortment of freelance vocalists, and they play anything from a fast paced dissonant rock ballad cover artist like Jeff Beck or Buddy Guy, to a light whimsical side of fusion rock with Robben Ford. They have also performed to a sell out audience in the Blues festival 2011 in Pune and Assam.','','','','BlueFrog',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-26 10:05:00','2012-06-26 10:05:48','blues-blooded-feat-vinayak-pol-denzil-mathias-shireen-irani',1,NULL),(56,'Duncun Rufus','Duncun Rufus is a band from Mumbai, comprising studio session players and members of various backing bands. The band brings together five musicians all well known in the music community. Duncun Rufus makes soulful music and the songs are about hope, betrayal, desire & devotion in troubled times. Crisp contemporary pop-folk rock songs with foot tapping beats and catchy hook lines, this is music that you can truly feel when the sun rests and the night spreads itself out on the sky. \r\n\r\nThey have released their debut 10-track album \"Carte Blanche\" in 2011. The band already has their second album \"The Folds Galore\" and is aiming for a mid-2012 release. ','','','','BlueFrog',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-27 10:05:00','2012-06-27 10:05:48','duncun-rufus',1,NULL),(57,'The Other People + DJ Ruskin','Their shows cover a variety of genres ranging from Soft Rock to Rock \'n\' Roll, throwing in some Reggae mixed with a little Contemporary and some Retro, a touch of Blues, a shout of Pop and even a bit of some thumping Disco! Known to bring an original twist into each track, the band never fails to surprise an audience and ensures that they stay hooked right through the show!','','','','BlueFrog',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-29 02:05:00','2012-06-29 10:05:48','the-other-people-dj-ruskin',1,NULL),(58,'Rolling Stone Metal Awards feat. Zygnema, Eccentric Pendulum, Abraxas, Providence, Pangea ','The Rolling Stone Metal Awards was launched in 2010 to recognise, support and promote the burgeoning metal scene and the immensely talented bands in the country. After a tremendously successful two years, the Rolling Stone Metal Awards returns in its third edition  louder, bigger and meaner.  ','','','','BlueFrog',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-01 08:05:00','2012-07-01 10:05:48','rolling-stone-metal-awards-feat-zygnema-eccentric-pendulum-abraxas-providence-pangea',1,NULL),(59,'Dance Pure w/ DJ Nasha, Pearl and Amul','','','','','Zomato',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-27 09:05:00','2012-06-27 10:05:48','dance-pure-w-dj-nasha-pearl-and-amul',1,NULL),(60,'test 5','','','','','Rolling Stone ',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-10 11:21:21',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-06-28 05:05:00','2012-06-28 10:05:00','test-5',1,NULL),(61,'Copacabana with DJ Vinoo','Join DJ Vinoo at the Copacabana for an eclectic selection of grooves from across the globe, with genres spanning African, World, Reggae, Folk, Blues and Laid Back Rock. And that\'s not all, there will be 1+1 on IMFL cocktails all night to get you into the Copacabana mood.\n\nSo, be there!','','','','Zomato',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-26 05:05:48','2012-06-26 10:05:48','copacabana-with-dj-vinoo',1,NULL),(62,'DJ Mash Live','ddictive & intoxicating is what they say when DJ Mash is on the decks. His ability to channelize his musical energy into untainted enthusiasm on the dance floor leaves the crowd always wanting more of him. His ardor for mixing and continuous trailing with sounds gives his listeners a new surprise every time he puts his headphones on. Mash\'s DJ sets are sure to set the journey mood and his style can be described as ranging from progressive to techno.\r\n\r\nHailing from India Vibe Internationally, Mash has now been playing for over a decade and also holding the title of India\'s no. 1 DJ after wining the ultimate DJ Championship by submerge & MTV for the year 2010-2011.','','','','Zomato',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-27 10:05:00','2012-06-27 10:05:48','dj-mash-live',1,NULL),(63,'For Love of Sufiyana with Guruz  Band Live','Flo Lounge presents Sufi band Guruz live on Wednesday.\r\n\r\nThe band has done around 40 shows for AIDS Awareness as two individual bands within a period of 5 days at various places all over Delhi. The band has been associated with United Breweries, Cafe Coffee Day, Barista, Efunds International, The Times of India, United Colors of Benetton for acoustic and unplugged shows. They have done more than 300 shows all over India.\r\n\r\nThe band consists of:\r\n- Ayaz Ul Haroon: Lead vocals and Guitars\r\n- Danish: Bass Guitar and backing vocals\r\n- Rajesh Thakur, Deepak Maher and Harshit Naagar: Drums, Lead Guitar, Keyboard and Indian percussions.','','','','Zomato',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-27 09:05:00','2012-06-27 10:05:48','for-love-of-sufiyana-with-guruz-band-live',1,NULL),(64,'Spin Twins Live','Hype presents India\'s first twin DJs, \'DJ Spin Twins\'. Catch the unusual duo and dance the night away. Their style of blending original house music and energetic fusions of Bollywood with commercial hip-hop are inimitable yet distinctive. Thumping that has thousands of revelers screaming for their music from India and Bangkok, Chiang Mai, Dubai, Muscat and many more. So get ready to party with the twins.','','','','Zomato',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-27 10:05:00','2012-06-27 10:05:48','spin-twins-live',1,NULL),(65,'House Funk Friday ','Though her favorite genre is Commercial House, Progressive house and minimal tech music, Kamya has got a ready hand on all kinds of music. According to her, a good DJ is one who understand the pulse of the crowd and plays the music accordingly. She adds, a good DJ is one who makes the crowd spin all through the night, yet demanding for more. Kamya\'s inspirations are DJ Nasha and DJ Tiesto. However she doesn\'t want to copy anyone, but make her own statement and mark in this profession.\n\nHer Presence at House Funk Friday along with our very own Resident Evil DJ Monty will make your Friday go Funky. So B there or b square or whatever...but you don\'t really wanna miss it..for another reason too...coz\n\n~SPIRITS WILL BE ON THE HOUSE FOR ALL THE LADY GUESTS IN THE HOUSE~','','','','',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-29 05:05:48','2012-06-29 10:05:48','house-funk-friday',1,NULL),(66,'Submerge presents Gordon Edge','ordon Edge The Trumpetman is back in India and ready to create some havoc.\r\n\r\nAbout Gordon Edge: It used to be so simple: the musicians made music, the DJ played it and the crowd danced. Then one day Gordon Edge got his trumpet out and in one shrill, soul-tingling, passion-producing blast, blew the lid off the party.\r\n\r\nA typical Gordon Edge set is a truly Balearic experience; starting solidly and establishing a base with which to build from, then shifting sublimely through the gears; teasing and releasing, ebbing and flowing - but subtly and sonically building all the time, referencing tribal, soulful house, jazz flava\'s and just the right amount of anthems.','','','','MyBangalore',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-01 02:05:00','2012-07-01 10:05:48','submerge-presents-gordon-edge',1,NULL),(67,'Bavarian Brass Band Live','This years Indo-German Urban Mela in Bangalore gives four of the bands members the stage to present their traditional German music. Johannes Grassl, Thomas Bauer and Hans-Peter Hpfl will play their instruments with exquisite ease, while marvelous Eva Petzenhauser will mesmerize the audience with her soulful voice.','','','','Ask Laila',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-27 08:05:00','2012-06-27 10:05:48','bavarian-brass-band-live',1,NULL),(68,'Ghost Crabs','WE ARE CRAZY CRABS, COMING FROM ALL AROUND THE WORLD, WE BRING LOVE AND SOUNDS TO WARM YOUR HEART','','http://www.facebook.com/ghostcrabs/info','','NH7',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-27 09:05:00','2012-06-27 10:05:48','ghost-crabs',1,NULL),(69,'Sankalp Rehab Trust Benefit Show ','','','','','http://nh7.in/indiecision/2012/06/26/dance-pure-benefit-show-announced/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-27 02:05:00','2012-06-27 10:05:48','sankalp-rehab-trust-benefit-show',1,NULL),(70,'The Brian Citro Trio','','','','','NH7',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-27 09:35:00','2012-06-27 10:05:48','the-brian-citro-trio',1,NULL),(71,'Kendraka, Chronic Xorn ','Kendraka promises an experience of the confluence of the different cultural influences(Hindustani & Carnatic classical music,hardcore rural folk of West Bengal, of that of Purulia and Bankura,the urban folk of Kolkata, Jazz , Rock, Blues, Rn B and even integrating indian classical dance form-Bharatanatyam) set to the backdrop of the modern complex urban thematic metamorphosis with emphasis on spontaneity and improvisation .Through the brave and spontaneous attempts of admixture of different cultures and lifestyles of featured musicians and the complex ever evolving \"cosmopolitan\" yet \"root consious Bengali-Indian\"c