ts reggae, dub, lovers rock, ska and dancehall. They frequently perform in Delhi/NCR and have also played in Mumbai, Pune, Bangalore, Chennai, Goa and Manali. International performances in the last 2 years include Peru, Panama and New York City. They were recently nominated for the Best International Group award at the British Reggae Industry Awards (2012) alongside illustrious Jamaican artists such as Toots & the Maytals, Mighty Diamonds and Third World.','','','','Zomato',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-28 02:05:00','2012-06-28 10:05:48','thursday-reggae-session',1,NULL),(84,'SMASH UP: RAYG','Reji Ravindran (a.k.a rayG) has musical experience which spans for nearly 15 years.\r\n\r\nBorn in Mumbai, Reji was bitten by the music bug during the mid-90s. After collecting a load of music cassettes, CDs and vinyl in his youth, he decided to give DJing a shot by learning from veteran DJ, Jo Azaredo. Since that year (1998), there\'s been no stopping him. Reji is one of the most prolific names in Mumbai\'s booming alternative and electronic music scene.\r\n\r\nFor the longest time in his career, Reji has been recognised as an educator within the music fraternity. After understanding India\'s unique music scene in the early 2000s, the DJ professor designed and implemented his own syllabus at some of the best DJ schools in the city; training more than 500 men and women in the art of DJing, turntablism and music production.\r\n\r\nBy putting his mouth where the money is, Reji has been a successful battle DJ by winning the DMC Champion (Pune - 2000), Times War of the DJs winner (Mumbai - 2007) and Kingfisher Ultra DJ (2010) titles through the years. Reji was the first ever turntablist in an Indian nu-age metal band called Scag and also the brains behind India\'s earliest hip hop collective called \"itch\". In December 2008, world renowned travel magazine, Time Out Mumbai, mentioned him as one of Mumbai\'s most influential DJs\" in its cover article.\r\n\r\nBy always keeping an emphasis on quality music with longer shelf life (minus short term crass commercial appeal), you can always expect Reji to dish out an unpredictable blend of indie, reggae, rock, dub, dancehall, funk, soul, breaks, disco, baltimore, house, techno, hip-hop, electro, drum and bass, jungle, swing, retro, dubstep, mash ups and much more. Phew!','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/822-smash-up-rayg',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-29 02:05:00','2012-06-29 10:05:48','smash-up-rayg',1,NULL),(85,'R.E.D MAWKIN FEAT. AMAN MAHAJAN','Aman Mahajan, a pianist/keyboardist from India, has worked with musicians from all over the world in a plethora of musical idioms. A graduate of the Berklee College of Music (Boston), Aman is widely influenced by jazz, blues, electronic music and folk music from Africa, India, Turkey and the American continents. A few artists and groups he has worked with include Lucky Ali (Indian songwriter), Arooj Aftab (world fusion/Pakistani song), Gamelan Galak Tika (traditional Balinese), Project O.N.S (electro/jazz/funk), Joya (pop/neo-soul), and some of the foremost jazz musicians on the Indian scene.\r\n\r\nCurrently based out of Bangalore, Aman makes music and performs as a member of Schizophonic, an experimental electro-acoustic trio, and is also a member of UNK: The Radha Thomas Ensemble.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nRED Mawkin, after a decade of playing shows and 5 years of traveling between the United States and India is emerging yet again after a long break from singing and songwriting. While he very productively spent his time grooming the drummer within himself, he has stumbled his way back into the shoes of a frontman.','','http://www.facebook.com/redmawkin?ref=ts','','NH7',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-06 09:05:00','2012-07-06 10:05:48','red-mawkin-feat-aman-mahajan-1',1,NULL),(86,'KRUNK LIVE: BAY BEAT COLLECTI