 is globally inclusive and plural in all aspects of culture and expression with over 150 odd instruments from all over the planet!\r\n\r\nIts the way forward to establish the noble ideals of  their \"ONENESS!\" vision statement. MUSIC COOKED HOT ON THE SPOT is their USP and hallmark! \r\nThey are a high-energy free-form impromptu jazz based world music trio with  6 successful albums and a docu-dvd to their credit. Audio albums \"2\" & \"3!!!\" are available on-line. They are currently compiling their music album \"SEVEN\" which will be launched on the G.O.D. 2012  annual concert.      ','','','','NH7',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-04 02:05:00','2012-07-04 10:05:48','gautam-ghosh-collective',1,NULL),(104,'The Koniac Net, The Shakey Rays','Bombay-born, The Koniac Net originally was a single-man project. The entire album (lyrics & songs) \"One Last Monsoon\" was written and recorded by David Abraham, mixed by Jason D\'Souza, with guest musicians Eden Shyodhi on \"Divine Submersion\" & \"Midnight\'s Children (h.b.m.) and Adil Kurwa playing bass on \"Divine Submersion.\" \r\n\r\nAfter not only receiving significant airplay from radio stations in Germany, Australia, U.S., U.K., Italy, Norway, Sweden, and more, but also receiving requests to come down and play live in these countries, David managed to bring together friends/musicians who he respects and believes in, and who also believe in the music he writes and loves. They plan on showcasing \"One Last Monsoon\" live and internationally, and wedging the Indie & Alternative genres even deeper into India. \r\n\r\nInfluenced by bands such as the Stills, Teenage Fanclub, Swervedriver, the French Kicks, Smashing Pumpkins, Toadies, etc., \"One Last Monsoon\" is a tribute to these bands and the Indie / Alternative genres. . ','','','','NH7',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-04 02:05:00','2012-07-04 10:05:48','the-koniac-net-the-shakey-rays',1,NULL),(105,'Shkabang at Blue Frog','Shkabang is a bunch of musicians who have played on stage many times independently of each other. Rock, electronic, jazz, reggae, classic, funk and bollywood..they\'re doing/done/will do all of that. They played a gig together for kicks early last year, sounded great and had so much fun, they decided to hook up and play some music together for real.\r\n\r\nShkabang likes big sounds and the rush that comes with the banging bass - their sound can best be described as electro-pop-rock-bubble-disco-dance-bang music!\r\n\r\nComposed of four members, the band came together for one reason only - to make some noise! A video director by day and probably the music scene\'s most banging drummer by night, Shiraz Bhatacharya gives Shkabang the raw power and energy they need on stage. He is also part of the immensely popular rock act, Pentagram, and has just finished shooting Shkabang\'s first video.','','','','NH7',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-10-06 02:50:19',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-07-05 02:05:00','2012-07-05 10:05:00','shkabang-at-blue-frog',1,NULL),(107,'Guy J','','','','','NH7',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-06 05:05:00','2012-07-06 10:05:48','guy-j',1,NULL),(108,'Mental Martians','Taking the Indian bass-scene by storm and bringing a fresh new sound, seeing never before used Indian percussion with dubstep, breaks and drum n bass to fuse together a rich, melodic and aggressive sound that rips through sound systems. \r\n\r\nIntroducing the MENTAL MARTIANS who are Piyush Bhatnagar, Sarvesh Shrivastava and Tarang Singhal; and with their brand of techno-analogue sound, you are guaranteed to be snared.\r\n\r\nInfluenced by Noisia, Spor, Doctor P, Skrillex, Rusko, Chase and status and various heavyweights from the international dub arena, their sound is a heady journey that defies genres and synthesizes the Asian underground to the dubstep in the UK.\r\n\r\nSarvesh who formed the band is a a dub aficionado, with a penchant for Indian sounds and believes in broadening his horizons as he has from age 15 when he began his musical journey. Piyush was an equally early starter at 16, dabbling in not only the dub arts but electro-house and IDM and he has an international presence that completes these two as they cover DJing, production and technical support for the team. \r\n\r\nTheir gigs in Mumbai and Jaipur and Delhi have garnered awesome levels of recognition for them. Providing the live element to the band is their third member, Tarang Singhal, who began his musical tte--tte at a mere 8 years and who plays the tabla, darbuka, Jembe, Bongo, Drums and other home made percussions that allow him to sample live sounds that create mayhem with the electronic deliciousness of the two.','','','','NH7',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-06 02:05:00','2012-07-06 10:05:48','mental-martians',1,NULL),(109,'Disharmony III at Tamu Dhi','','','','','NH7',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-07 02:05:00','2012-07-07 10:05:48','disharmony-iii-at-tamu-dhi',1,NULL),(112,'Wanted Yesterday','Wanted Yesterday is a band formed by three seasoned admen: Rajeev Raja, Prabhakar Mundkur and Subhash Kamath. The name comes from a clich describing the often-unreasonable deadlines in the ad world i.e This is wanted yesterday!! Since the band plays a lot of music from the 60s and 70s, the name also serves as a cheeky descriptor to the kind of music they revel in.\r\n\r\nWanted Yesterday plays a lot of covers: Of famous songs by J.J. Cale, The Beatles, Eric Clapton, Bob Dylan, The Allman Brothers as well as a variety of classic blues and rock numbers. But theyre not the usual tribute band. They bring a unique interpretation of these songs and play them in their own way. The use of the jazz flute, for example, changes the way these famous songs are re-interpreted, thereby creating a new sound.\r\n\r\nSoon, the band also plans to introduce their own compositions in true retro style. Wanted Yesterday believes Its time to bring back the golden era of music for a whole new audience.\"','','','','NH7',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-07 02:05:00','2012-07-07 10:05:48','wanted-yesterday',1,NULL),(113,'The Other People, DJ Leon Russell','One of blueFROG Mumbai\'s hottest properties RETRO NIGHT WITH THE OTHER PEOPLE has been rocking Delhi for a while now!. Fronted by the handsome and effervescent Zarir Warden, this is a line-up of powerhouse musicians who bring their considerable talents and an infectious energy to the stage.\r\n\r\nTheir shows cover a variety of genres ranging from Soft Rock to Rock n\' Roll, throwing in some Reggae mixed with a little Contemporary and some Retro, a touch of the Blues, a shout of Pop and even a bit of Disco; covering classic artists such as Elvis Presley, Chuck Berry, Neil Diamond, Frank Sinatra, Louis Armstrong, Pink Floyd, The Beatles, The Doors, Bon Jovi, U2, Bob Marley, Billy Joel, Billy Idol and others.','','','','NH7',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-07 02:05:00','2012-07-07 10:05:48','the-other-people-dj-leon-russell',1,NULL),(114,'Beatitude Live','','','','','NH7',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-04 02:05:00','2012-07-04 10:05:48','beatitude-live',1,NULL),(115,'Video Gaga with DJ Bala ','','','','','NH7',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-06 02:05:00','2012-07-06 10:05:48','video-gaga-with-dj-bala',1,NULL),(116,'Sufi Night ','Experience the Sufi music like never before at Kylin. The place is holding Sufi Nights for Sufi Music lovers that will have a Jam session between the Amazing DJ Brook, and Satikant one of the Most Rustic voices in NCR for Sufi. ','','','','TimesCity',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-06 02:05:00','2012-07-06 10:05:48','sufi