 10:05:00','2012-07-31 10:05:48','amaan-ayaan-ali-khan',1,NULL),(127,'Vh1 Hip Hop Hustle with DJ Lucky Lou','DJ Lucky Lou is a crowd pleaser with an uncanny ability to bring a party to life with his encyclopedic background of musical knowledge, ranging from disco, classic 80s, rock, soul, funk, and electro house. Despite his diverse love of music, its DJ Lucky Lous love affair with hip hop that has fueled his amazing career, landing him behind the turntable at parties for some of the music industrys heavyweights, such as Jay-Z, P. Diddy, T.I, The Black Eyed Peas, & now his current group LMFAO.\r\n\r\nComing to you by way of Jamaica, Queens, DJ Lucky Lou operates out of Southern California, where 944 Lifestyle Magazine has recognized him as one of L.A.s hottest DJs. He is a throwback to the deeply rooted craft of Disc Jockey artistry, learned in the ways of turntable mastery, mixing and MCing by some of the most elite DJs to ever spin a record, including DJ Icy Ice, DJ Premier, DJ E-man and DJ QBert. ','','','','Bluefrog',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-06 10:35:00','2012-07-06 10:05:48','vh1-hip-hop-hustle-with-dj-lucky-lou',1,NULL),(128,'Syncopation','Syncopation plays an eclectic mix of Modern Jazz blended with elements of bebop, swing and funk The music is centered around soulful melodies with modern funky grooves leading into a frenzied yet unique improvisation. Their repertoire consists of original music - which projects the bands attitude and approach to Jazz as the evolving art form that it is The songs are written and arranged by the band collectively. ','','','','Bluefrog',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-11 10:05:00','2012-07-11 10:05:48','syncopation',1,NULL),(129,'Kaash ','KAASH is a musical endeavor started in the year 2008. KAASH blends Indian melodies and sensibilities with a scorching Rock backbone, creating an ingenious sound, which emancipates a sea of emotions and nostalgia in the heart of its listeners.\r\n\r\nThe group released their first song Main Laut Aaunga in August 2009 which went on to become one of the most searched Hindi Rock tracks on the Internet with over 50 fan videos and more than 10,00,000 views. After that the band released 5 more tracks on the Internet which were received with even greater love and enthusiasm. Heart wrenching melodies, subtle lyrics, lavish ornamentation, and an unusual simplicity are their trademarks. \r\n\r\nKAASH is an eccentric set of five people;\r\nViren (vocals), \r\nShivam (keyboards), \r\nNishant (guitars), \r\nSonic (bass), \r\nNirvan (drums).\r\n\r\nBacked by solid education they show a marked disregard of any musical style limitations','','','','Bluefrog',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-26 10:05:00','2012-07-26 10:05:48','kaash',1,NULL),(130,'INERTIA LIVE ','','','','','Fb',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-12 09:35:00','2012-07-12 10:05:48','inertia-live',1,NULL),(131,'APHID MOON + AMD LIVE','Aphid Moon is the solo act of producer & Dj Jules Hamer. He has released two albums so far. The first called High Diver ..onfly Records in 2003; a deep night time sound with a distinctly British psy-trance flavor. His second album Global Culture was released May 2005 on Nano Records has really moved with the times and technology with fatter more fullon production and an infectious dance sound. \r\n\r\nWith the help of the insane software revolution he has steadily been developing his own unique style. Over the last decade Aphid Moon has released on countless psy-trance labels and played DJ & live sets in Japan, Israel, S.A., Brazil, Europe and the U.K parties and festivals.\r\n\r\nIn 2005 he teamed up with trance legend Dick Trevor (Green Nuns, Dickster and Jumanji); together they have formed AMD (aka. Aphid Moon & Dickster) a formidable trance duo. 2007 saw the release of there first album \"Big Fish\" on Nano Rec. which has already become a trance classic. www.amd-trance .com','','','','Fb',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-04 02:05:00','2012-07-04 10:05:48','aphid-moon-amd-live',1,NULL),(135,'Tuesday Night With DJ Ray G ','','','','','MyPurpleMartini',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-03 09:05:00','2012-07-03 10:05:48','tuesday-night-with-dj-ray-g',1,NULL),(137,'\"THE METAL SQUID\" LiVE ','\"THE METAL SQUID\" LiVE @ Club Ice Cube, CLUB ICE CUBE Presents THE METAL SQUID LIVE July 22nd, Saturday, 1 PM onw ABOUT METAL SQUID The Metal Squid has been in existence since 2008.Though the band has performed with names like The Count, Divine Truth, it got it\'s permanent name in November 2009.The band has performed in various GIGS in and around Delhi and IITs.With the aim of getting hell out of the audience all members are young, energetic and masters in their field Metal Squid is a well known hardcore metal band,famous for multiple hit concerts in India our members are Arpit (v0cals), Naman(guitar), Kiefer (drum), Nakul (Guitar), Nishanth(bass). Inviting all the Metal Lover to come and bang their head on some of the best hit of Metallica, Limp Bizkit , Korn and many More with us. with HOUSE DJs Ali, William, Raj COME ENJOY THE LIVE IN CONCERT TOGETHER WITH THE EXCLUSIVE CROWD IN TOWN LETS SPICE IT UP DELHIII N Delhi/NCR All the regular couples to get a chance to win passes of free entry throughout the year Midnight surprises to all the in house patrons.','','','','MyPurpleMartini',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-22 09:05:00','2012-07-22 10:05:48','the-metal-squid-live',1,NULL),(138,'ADAM & THE FISH EYED POETS','The brainchild of Chennai based singer-songwriter Kishore Krishna. His music, loosely categorised in the post rock genre, serves as a tribute to the great existentialist poets of the modern era.\r\n\r\nKishore has put a band together featuring some of the most talented musicians from Chennai, to fully articulate the alternating cathartic and subtly, almost incisive sense of aggression in Kishore\'s unique sound, which he claims is rooted in a volatile balance between the primal sexual energy of the Stax/ Volt era rhythm and blues, and the cynical passive aggressive precision of post-punk acts such as The Smiths, Elvis Costello, and The Cure.\r\n\r\nAdam & the Fish Eyed Poets have released two critically acclaimed, self produced albums; the brooding and intense \"Snakeism\"(2010) and the streamlined and melancholic \"Dead Loops\" (2011). ','','http://www.facebook.com/afisheyedpoet','','The Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-05 03:45:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','adam-the-fish-eyed-poets',1,NULL),(139,'MAMBO FEAT. DJ PEZ RODRIGUEZ & FLEXI K','DJs Pez Rodriguez and Flexi K will be spinning classics from the golden age of Hispanic dance music.\r\n\r\nMambo is one of the greatest Latin music rhythms ever created. Originally from Cuba, this genre was also responsible for shaping the sounds of modern Salsa music.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nA Potted History of The Mambo\r\nIn the 1930s, Cuban music was heavily influenced by Danzon. One of the popular bands at that time was the orchestra of Arcao y sus Maravillas; some of its members introduced variations to the classic beat of Danzon. They Orestes Lopez and Israel \"Cachao\" Lopez. In 1938, they produced a Danzon single entitled Mambo.\r\n\r\nThe Lopez brothers incorporated a heavier African beat into their music. This new type of Danzon, which is at the base of Mambo music, was known at that time as Danzon de Nuevo Ritmo. Sometimes, it was simply called Danzon Mambo.\r\n\r\nAfter Mambo\r\nThe 1950s and 1960s saw the golden years of Mambo. Nevertheless, these years were rapidly overcome by the development of Salsa, a new crossover experiment that borrowed elements from different Afro-Latin rhythms like Son, Charanga and of course, Mambo. The influence of Mambo in Salsa is a significant one. Besides Salsa, Mambo also played a significant role in the development of another popular Cuban invention, Cha Cha Cha. For everything it accomplished, Mambo is definitely one of the most successful creations in Latin music.','','','','The Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-05 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','mambo-feat-dj-pez-rodriguez-flexi-k',1,NULL),(140,'Franks got the funk','\"Frank is an idea. An ever evolving persona that incorporates the imagination, the hopes and dreams of five young people.\" - Chennai based alt.rock/electronica/funfunk outfit Franks Got The Funk.\r\n\r\nBorn in 2009, Franks Got The Funk is a band which treads in various genres, primarily influenced by electronic and progressive rock. The sole motivation for the band is to record and release their music is to get the music out there to the people. The surging energy and the addictive songs the band churns out are complemented by the capturing stage presence and wacky costumes, which keeps audiences enraptured and jumping.\r\n\r\nFranks Got The Funk is made up of:\r\n\r\nBjorn Surrao : Guitars / Vocals / Harmonica\r\n\r\nSajith Satya : Bass / Backing vocals\r\n\r\nRajan Chelliah : Guitars / Backing vocals\r\n\r\nVikram Ashok : Keyboards and Synth\r\n\r\nShashank Vijay : Drums','','http://www.facebook.com/fgtf.music?sk=wall','','The Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-07 08:35:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','franks-got-the-funk',1,NULL),(141,'KRUNK LIVE: DUALIST INQUIRY','We\'ve pretty simply only got good things to say about Dualist Inquiry the brainchild and solo project of Sahej Bakshi, a producer, guitarist and cerebral agent who graduated from the Thornton Music School at USC in Los Angeles, CA.\r\n\r\nSince returning to Delhi in March 2010, Sahej has been touring India extensively, in addition to being selected to perform at Berlin Music Week in Sept 2010. Additionally, he was ranked #1 nationally in the Burn Sasha Tour remix competition (2010) and was the 2nd Runner Up in the MTV Submerge Ultimate Pro DJ Championship 2010, held at Blue Frog in Mumbai. Most recently, Dualist Inquiry performed at The Great Escape Festival in Brighton UK, opening for international sensation Beardyman and hip-hop legend DJ Shadow at the world famous Brighton Dome.','','http://www.facebook.com/dualistinquiry','','https://www.facebook.com/events/409479342436183/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-07 08:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','krunk-live-dualist-inquiry',1,NULL),(142,'RLA','','','','','NH7',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-05 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','rla',1,NULL),(143,'Uncertainty Principle, Plok','','','','','',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-05 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','uncertainty-principle-plok',1,NULL),(144,'D. RAMIREZ','D. Ramirez is an English house producer and DJ.\r\n\r\nTraversing the globe with his trusty laptop in tow, the roving Ramirez has dispensed his razor sharp productions to unassuming dancefloors with the precision of first class marksman. Whether hes hidden behind devilish disguises such as The Lisa Marie Experience, Cordial, Finger Fest and Rambo, or performed as the man you know best as D Ramirez, Dean Marriot has achieved more than an entire legion of lesser DJs.\r\n\r\nAs well as being a world class remixer, producer and DJ, D. Ramirez also owns his own record label, Slave Recordings, on which he has most recently released a number of singles and EPs. He is also known for his technical musical knowledge and hosts a thriving musical forum on his website\r\n\r\nRamirez is most commonly known in the world of dance music as a champion of the upbeat \'electro house\' style, but more recent times have shown a move away from electro house in to more underground techno material.\r\n\r\n\"I don\'t feel comfortable with commerciality...When people start expecting certain things of me I tend to back away\"','','','','http://timescity.com/delhi/events/d-ramirez/41161',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-14 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','d-ramirez',1,NULL),(145,'SNAPLION ALL STAR NIGHTS: DUALIST INQUIRY & TAPAN RAJ (MIDIVAL PUNDITZ)','We\'ve pretty simply only got good things to say about Dualist Inquiry the brainchild and solo project of Sahej Bakshi, a producer, guitarist and cerebral agent who graduated from the Thornton Music School at USC in Los Angeles, CA.\r\n\r\nSince returning to Delhi in March 2010, Sahej has been touring India extensively, in addition to being selected to perform at Berlin Music Week in Sept 2010. Additionally, he was ranked #1 nationally in the Burn Sasha Tour remix competition (2010) and was the 2nd Runner Up in the MTV Submerge Ultimate Pro DJ Championship 2010, held at Blue Frog in Mumbai. Most recently, Dualist Inquiry performed at The Great Escape Festival in Brighton UK, opening for international sensation Beardyman and hip-hop legend DJ Shadow at the world famous Brighton Dome.\r\nDualist Inquiry Facebook\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nTapan Raj is one half of Indian electronica pioneers, Midival Punditz.\r\n\r\nThe Midival Punditz are arguably Indias biggest and most prolific electronica act. In 1997, after being bored with the remix and Bollywood driven music scene in India, the duo started producing original electronic music and sending out demo tracks to labels and other producers. Simultaneously, their monthly parties, Cyber Mehfil started becoming hugely popular and soon achieved cult status. Other artists and producers in the US and UK quickly recognised their efforts. Word spread about the boys, and they came to be known as The new sound of 21st Century India...','','http://www.facebook.com/dualistinquiry','','The Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','