0','1970-01-01 05:35:00','two-night-blackstratblues-summit-attempt',1,NULL),(172,'The Louiz Banks Matrixx Band','The Louiz Banks MATRIXX Trio with guest saxophonist Tala Faral is a contemporary jazz group that explores the infinite colors of jazz and other related species from mainstream to abstract but keeping the swing and thrust of jazz [which is its essence] at the core. Louiz\'s original compositions and popular jazz standards take on an exciting twist and turn and metamorphosise to create a refreshing change. Tala Faral, Sheldon D\'silva and Gino Banks display their incredible talent and virtuosity in this exciting format...enjoy the music of the MATRIXX band.','','','','blueFrog',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-19 10:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','the-louiz-banks-matrixx-band',1,NULL),(174,'Toyz In Panic','Toyz In Panic, formally known as \"Leon Russell and Doktor Daniel?, a project which brings to the floor a concept of EDM with a live element i.e. percussions. Their motive is to showcase a unique way of playing EDM. This act throw\'s in a style of EDM which is naughty, bouncy and groovy to the likes of Tech House, Techno and some Progressive House as well. \r\n\r\nThe momentum of the act is created by the connection it shares with the people they perform for, and post that, the grid is always a journey, thatis conveyed through the music. They have hit cities like Delhi, Chandigarh, Kolkata, Bengaluru, Nepal and blown the doors off the clubs they have performed at.','','','','blueFrog',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-21 10:35:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','toyz-in-panic',1,NULL),(176,'Metal Night With Demonic Ressurection & 1833 Ad','1833 AD\r\n\r\n1833 AD brings forth a fresh approach to Black Metal digressing from the traditional abrasive sound, concocting a mixture of extreme tremolo picking riffs and mellow melodic hooks and solos. The band bring together their individual playing styles to create an atmosphere of sorrow and hatred which do justice to the lyrical themes of the band. \r\n\r\nWith lyrical themes mostly centered on fiction, hatred, destruction and exploitation of the human race, 1833 AD takes a little detour from what people mostly categorize Black Metal lyrics as. Few songs do speak of supremacy of evil in this world but only to imply the ways of men and not by endorsing Satanism, Atheism or even Christianity.\r\n\r\nDemonic Resurrection\r\n\r\nRight from its inception in March 2000 Demonic Resurrection has been raising eyebrows. Starting out as bunch of 17-year-olds looking to give India a taste of extreme metal, then a nearly untouched genre, the band, spearheaded by Sahil The Demonstealer Makhija, released their first album Demonstealer within nine months of formation. \r\n\r\nIt was an amateurish first attempt but a bold step in a scene dominated by tribute and cover bands that got Demonic Resurrection noticed. As with most bands, teething problems meant that members came and went, and the first stable lineup came together only in 2001 with Demonstealer on vocals and guitars, Count Varathora on bass, Nikita Shah on vocals and keyboards and Yash Pathak on the drums. \r\n\r\nThe band re-recorded Demonstealer with the current lineup. Though a marked improvement on the original recording, the band was still experimenting with its sound and recording, something that comes across clearly on the album. It was still amateurish but it received a fair bit of acclaim and Brazilian record label Vampiria Records released a tape version of the album in the local market. (Today though, copies of this album are collectors items.)  ','','','','blueFrog',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-22 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','metal-night-with-demonic-ressurection-1833-ad',1,NULL),(177,'Jambus 2012 With Something Relevant & Caesars Palace','Something Relevant aka STR was formed in 2003 on a basketball court. After setting pan-India and international venues alight over five live-wire years through countless gigs and a reputation for explosive live acts, STR have fast established themselves as the reigning authority on Feel-Good! The 7-member ensemble have discovered sounds that are a resonating fusion of their classic blend of jazz, funk, blues, reggae, rock, pop, soul & afrohighlife, with the pulsing metrics of the megapolis Mumbai.','','','','blueFrog',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-25 10:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','jambus-2012-with-something-relevant-caesars-palace',1,NULL),(178,'Nirmika & The Few Good Men ','When you have a song, you gotta sing it. Thats what singer-songwriter Nirmika Singh has been doing for a few years now. And now that there is an amazing bunch of real good men ganging up with her, the songs only get better. Think velvety vocals, think trippy music, think melodies that will surprisingly dance on your lips while you take a shower the morning after the gig, think lyrics that will surprise you with their simple profoundness-thats Nirmika & The Few Good Men for you.\r\n\r\nDont be surprised if the band gets you an adrenaline rush with one song and leaves you in a contemplative space with the next. But be surprised if they dont make you happy, because thats what theyre best at. With heavy strokes of pop-rock, jazz and reggae, their music might make you want to consider forgiving your crazy boss for his eccentricity or even convince you to take your lover for a walk on the beach. They like to look at the sunny side of the street. ','','','','blueFrog',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-26 10:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','nirmika-the-few-good-men',1,NULL),(179,'Ska! Ska! Ska! The Ska Vengers, Bombay Bassment, Blek, Gandu Circus, Delhi Sultanate, Samara C, BBC at Blue Frog','The Ska Vengers\r\nska/sk?/noun: a modern style of Jamaican popular music, which emerged in the 1950s as a blend of African-Jamaican folk music, calypso, and American jazz and rhythm and blues, notable for its fast shuffling, scratchlike tempo and jazzlike horn riffs with a heavy accent on the  offbeat. \r\n\r\nThe Ska Vengers is a new Delhi based band that blends ska rhythms with elements of dub, punk, jazz and rap to come up with a form of music that is refreshingly different, energetic and highly danceable. Keys man, Stefan Kaye rounded up a few of his musician friends to form the band in the fall of 2009. \r\n\r\nBombay Bassment\r\nBombay Bassment was perhaps Indian indie musics most pleasant surprise of the last 12 months. A group that by their own description is closer to The Roots than to 50 Cent, and has been winning new fans with every gig they play. We wanted to make it a band because the kind of hip hop we appreciate is closer to what you could call old school, said rapper and de facto frontman Robert Bob Omulo. \r\n\r\nBBC\r\nVoted # 1 Drum N Bass / Dubstep DJ by MyFavDJ.in for 2009 - 2010, BBC (Bay Beat Collective) is Kris Correya, Sohail Arora & Raffael Kably. The Mumbai-based BBC (Bay Beat Collective) formed in response to the abundance of standard-issue electronica so commonly heard in clubs and bars across the country. A DJ collective currently consisting of Kris Correya, Sohail Arora & Raffael Kably, the BBC\'s passion lies in drum & bass, breaks, dubstep, glitch, funk and minimal sounds. \r\n\r\nBLEK\r\nBLEK (fomerly Blech) is an all original alternative trio with no idea of what their genre really is. This 3 piece act is made up of Jared Creado on the bass, Varoon Aiyer (Split) on drums, and Rishi Bradoo on guitars and vocals. \r\n\r\nTheir meeting was a result of idleness, flunky frustration, and the failure of one of them to speak un-anglicized Hindi. Each of them brings a different style and influence to their music. Rolling Stone magazine refers to them as the \"Bombay based cousins of The Supersonics\" and the best way to experience this band is to watch them perform live while they execute their trade-marked monkey dance.','','','','blueFrog',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-10-06 23:40:37',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-07-27 10:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','ska-ska-ska-the-ska-vengers-bombay-bassment-blek-gandu-circus-delhi-sultanate-samara-c-bbc-at-blue-frog',1,NULL),(180,'Retro Night: The Other People + DJ Ruskin (Mumbai) ','Their shows cover a variety of genres ranging from Soft Rock to Rock \'n\' Roll, throwing in some Reggae mixed with a little Contemporary and some Retro, a touch of Blues, a shout of Pop and even a bit of some thumping Disco! Known to bring an original twist into each track, the band never fails to surprise an audience and ensures that they stay hooked right through the show!','','','','blueFrog',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-28 10:35:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','retro-night-the-other-people-dj-ruskin-mumbai',1,NULL),(183,'The Thrillseekers (UK) ','','','','','blueFrog',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','1970-07-21 10:35:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','the-thrillseekers-uk-1',1,NULL),(184,'Audio Ashram & Third Eye Records presents Younger Brother + Prometheus','','','','','blueFrog',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-27 10:35:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','audio-ashram-third-eye-records-presents-younger-brother-prometheus',1,NULL),(185,'JOLT (LIVE) & THE INCREDIBLE MIND FUNK (LIVE)','Jolt is a four member instrumental band that continues to experiment with and create unique sounds that fuse together funk, jazz, drum & bass and electronica. These seasoned musicians who have been part of industry stalwarts such as Soulmate, HFT, Level 9, Radius to name a few have joined forces to form a band that is both highly creative and entertaining.\r\n\r\n\"A band exploring the communication between musicians, machines and party animals working on an optimum level of efficiency for deriving maximum pleasure for the longest time...\"','','','','The Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-11 12:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','jolt-live-the-incredible-mind-funk-live',1,NULL),(186,'FLUX: BAY BEAT COLLECTIVE/OX7GEN & ALGORHYTHM','\"FLUX is our attempt is to disrupt and differentiate from the prevailing music scene in India. A departure from the mainstream showcasing the best of world music featuring genres such as indie, nu-disco, chill-wave, synth pop, funk, glitch, and electro hip-hop just to name a few.\r\n\r\nWith monthly nights across Mumbai city, we aim to spread great music across various communities eventually storming our way into Delhi, Pune and Bangalore.\"\r\n\r\nNo genre egos here - Anything and everything (that sounds good) goes.','','','','The Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-13 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','flux-bay-beat-collectiveox7gen-algorhythm',1,NULL),(187,'DELHI INDIE NIGHT','\"Since the dawn of time, zombies have been threatening the human race with their stubborn insistence on dragging the rest of us down to their level. We demand the government does something about this.\r\n\r\nSo put on your blue suede shoes and get yourself along to a night described by a national newspaper as the best night out in Delhi: Cheap drinks, late nights, zombie antics, no entry charge/policy and the best indie/alternative music from the last 40 years. Free drinks all night for people who come dressed as a convincing zombie.\" - Delhi Indie Night\r\n\r\nHaving lived in India for four years, one evening Andy Dodd and Nathan Steele found themselves lamenting the dearth of playtime given to indie and alternative scenes. \"What began as an off-the-cuff joke resulted in Delhi Indie Night. At first, it was just our friends, but it didn\'t take long for word to get around.\" - Andy Dodd','','','','The Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','201