ish dance floors wherever they go.','','','http://soundcloud.com/bassjackers','The Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-21 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','bassjackers',1,NULL),(212,'NASHA LIVE','Nasha\' a Delhi based \'Sufi Rock Band\' formed in November 2009... We play soulful music in a \'Modern Contemporary Rock version\'... The kind of music we play is popular among the masses and also includes bollywood hit numbers in our own sufi style... The band includes \'Akhil Sacheva\' on the lead vocals... \'Saurabh jain\' on the \'Acoustics \'n\' vocals\'..\'rohit\' on the guitar\'s... Jivi on \'bass\' \'n\' \'Ankur\' on drums....!!\r\n\r\n\'Nasha\' has been awarded as The \'Best Band from North India\' by \'Times Music\'... Have been the winners of \'Mtv Rockothon 2010\' \'n\' have also been the participants of \'Mtv Rock On\'(top 7)... Have shared the same stage to perform with bands like Parikrama, Indian Ocean etc..\r\n\r\nThe band has just performed internationally in europe,turkey \'n\' also for a corporate show with \'Standard Chartered Bank\' in \'Dubai\'....\r\nThe title track \'Nasha\' is about to be released in an upcoming bollywood movie \'n\' our first album \'Nasha\' has been launched by \'sa re ga ma\' ...!!','','http://www.facebook.com/events/247169948719795/','','http://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=nasha%20live%2013th%20july&source=web&cd=2&cad=rja&ved=0CCYQFjAB&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.zomato.com%2Fevents%2Fncr%2Fnasha-live-100017653&ei=xm1EUJvjF4ePrgelnoCIB',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-13 10:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','nasha-live',1,NULL),(213,'Galeej Gurus','','','http://www.facebook.com/events/412261068820190/','','fb',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-13 08:35:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','galeej-gurus',1,NULL),(214,'CAESARS OF THE GREEN','CAESARS OF THE GREEN - AN INDIE ROCK BAND PERFORMING LIVE ON THE 13th JULY, 9pm ONWARDS.\r\nENJOY THE MUSIC AND 1+1 OFFER.','','http://www.facebook.com/caesarsofthegreen','http://soundcloud.com/caesarsofthegreen','Heavy Genre',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-13 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','caesars-of-the-green',1,NULL),(215,'Max Graham','Max Graham needs no introduction, from his early Trance hits Airtight and I Know Youre Gone to his 2010 Vocal smashes Sun in the Winter and Nothing Else Matters this man clearly knows how to make, and play, records that both get you dancing and touch you emotionally. \r\n\r\nAlong with the above hits in 2010 Max also released his first full length artist album Radio, collaborated with Markus Schulz and started his own acclaimed radio show entitled Cycles Radio on DI.FM. Tied in with the show was the release of his own branded double CD Cycles Two a two hour mix of Trance and Progressive mixed by the man himself.\r\n\r\nFast forward to 2011 and youll find the release of Maxs next bomb So Caught Up with Neev Kennedy. Released on his own label Re*brand Records its received multiple plays on the biggest radio shows in the world such as ASOT and TATW as well as being featured on Armin Van Buurens CD A State of Trance 2011. Along with these moving studio productions Max is more than at home In the DJ Booth. \r\n\r\nWhen Max plays he shows an enthusiasm for the crowd hes performing for with interaction and energy thats infectious. He plays a signature brand of dance music that, while containing primarily Trance and Progressive, is by no means closed to great music from all genres. His sets have rocked over 65 countries in his illustrious career and show no signs of slowing down.\r\n\r\n\r\nMax Graham is coming in the nightclub with the spirit of the youth of India while still remaining firmly grounded in its rich cultural heritage. Among many firsts of the country, it introduces the concept of \'A\' list area called \'The List\', \'The Salon\' - a mini nightclub within a nightclub and \'The Champagne Lounge\' referred to as \'The Dressing Room\'','www.maxgraham.com','http://www.facebook.com/events/319899964770248/','http://soundcloud.com/maxgraham','fb',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-13 10:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','max-graham',1,NULL),(216,'DJ Wodjer Want','For the last 16 years, Wodjer aka Stewart Dufty has thrilled dance floors in the underground techno, Progressive and house scene in the east coast of Australia, India, New Zealand and New Caledonia. He has also helped ignite and sustain the outdoor party movement in Sydney and has earned himself a reputation as the most reliable progressive Dj in the Australia and NZ scenes.\r\n\r\nHypnotically Progressive and intelligently mixing many styles taking the listener on a journey through sound to an overwhelming feeling of escapism and happiness is what describes Wodger Want. Wodjer brings together all elements of emotion through sound to move all chakras within the mind, body and soul. This is accomplished by connecting with the energy of an atmosphere, careful track selection and many years of mixing, music tuition and performing experience.\r\nWith his unique blend of progressive, house, minimal tech, tribal, dub step and breaks, Wodjers journey has led him from the lead singer of a 7 piece rock band in his teens to headlining at the biggest clubs in Asia, Australia and New Zealand as well as supporting acts such as Antix/Fiord, Sun Control Species, Sasha , John Digweed, Sensient, Hedonix, Grouch, Andromeda and Tom Cosm to just name a few .\r\n\r\nHis ability to understand his crowd and delivering what they want in his style always leaves his audience wanting for more. Generally performing on 3 decks, Wodjer delivers not only his own original tracks but also unreleased tracks from his upcoming new label Doof Wabbit Recordings and demonstrates unique mixing abilities.\r\n\r\nWodger Want can be best described as Hypnotic, Funky and a true entertainer.','','http://www.facebook.com/events/435640703125450/','http://soundcloud.com/wodjer-want','http://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=dj%20wodjer%20want%2014%20july&source=web&cd=2&cad=rja&ved=0CCYQFjAB&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.asklaila.com%2Fevent%2FDelhi-NCR%2FDJ-Wodjer-Want-Live%2F302522%2F&ei',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-14 10:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','dj-wodjer-want',1,NULL),(217,'Hundred Octane','','','','','fb',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-12 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','hundred-octane',1,NULL),(218,'Laughing Buddha','Laughing Buddha is UK Producer and DJ Jeremy van Kampen. A former guitarist, his inspiration for producing trance was kick started by the Goa parties of the early 90s. His first release was the \'Cannabanoid\' EP on Transient records under the name Cosmosis with Bill Halsey in 1995. This partnership went on to produce a top selling album \'Cosmology\' and a string of hits such as \'Morphic Resonance\' and \'Gift of the Gods\'. They also released the singles \'Infinite depths\' and \'Karma\' on T.I.P. Records as Laughing Buddha. When they went their separate ways in 1998, Jez continued the Laughing Buddha project producing more top singles such as \'If You Think You\'re Psykik\' on Transient and collaborations with Chris Decker of Medicine Drum and Purple, with whom he produced the classic track \'Remote\' on Flying Rhinos Maelstrom compilation. Jez is currently one of the UKs top producers and, after having released tracks on labels such as Dragonfly, LSD (as Drum Druids), Nano Records, Solstice and T.I.P. World, he has now joined the team at Nano Records and has just released his debut solo album, \'Sacred Technology\' on the label. An experienced Live act and DJ, Jez has toured extensively around the world including Australia,New Zealand, Japan, Israel, U.S.A., South America and Europe, and played at festivals such as Glade, Boom, Sonica, Ozora, Universo Paralello and many others.','','http://www.facebook.com/events/265514030222071/','','fb',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-13 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','laughing-buddha',1,NULL),(219,'BRIAN CITRO TRIO (LIVE JAZZ)','The Brian Citro Trio is unique fusion of American jazz traditions and contemporary Indian musical styles. The trio is a welcome new addition to the contemporary Indian music scene, performing newly composed music and reinterpreting standards from jazz greats like Thelonious Monk, Sonnly Rollins and Wayne Shorter. The group has developed a truly original sound that combines the disparate buy shared musical influences of its members. \r\n\r\nGuitarist Brian Citro hails from Chicago and is steeped in the jazz and avant-garde traditions that make that city\'s music scene one of the most vibrant in the world. Brian has performed around the world and is currently based in Delhi. His refined sense of jazz improvisation and versatile harmonic vocabulary turns each performance into a unique musical experience.\r\n\r\nBassist Abhishek Mangla has been playing all over the country as a freelance bass player. He has studied Jazz at Amsterdam Conservatory and is now writing music for various publications, teaching music and performing at various venues in the country. \r\nDrummer Nikhil Vasudevan are is one of India\'s most gifted drummer. He has established himself as an integral members of the Indian rock and creative music scenes as a member of bands like The Ska Vengers and The Commons. ','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/brian-citro-trio',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-02 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','brian-citro-trio-live-jazz',1,NULL),(220,'REGGAE RAJAHS (SOUNDSYTEM) + KAZTET DEE (MC) at TLR','','','','','',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-10-08 05:13:09',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-08-03 07:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','reggae-rajahs-soundsyt