2012-08-31 07:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','tritha-space-full-moon-trip-hop',1,NULL),(234,'PUNK & DISORDERLY: INDIGO CHILDREN, THE VINYL RECORDS & FLEXI K','Verve is a brand new watering hole and one of few mid-size music venues in New Delhi. It can be found down a side street opposite OTB and up a few stairs.\r\n\r\nStiff Kittens Inc are proud to be presenting some of the most exciting music performers and DJs in India at what will be a regular bi-weekly live night. With this inaugural show we can look forward to at least a semblance of the original spirit of punk rock with two of Delhi\'s most exuberant and wayward bands taking the stage, followed by a DJ set of 70s and 80s punk, rock and dance delights.\r\n\r\nLine up:\r\n\r\nIndigo Children: A 4-piece live group with roots in punk, garage rock and psychedelia. The line up currently consists of Sanchal Malhar, Nikhil Rufus Raj, R.N. Jaidev and Sahil Mendiratta.\r\n\r\nThe band has been part of the Indian live music circuit since 2004; among many notable achievements they\'ve won:\r\n\r\nCampus Rock Idols in 2005\r\nThe Great Indian Rock Festival in 2006\r\nChannel V Launch Pad\r\nHornbill Rock Contest in Nagaland 2011\r\n\r\nThey were one of four bands chosen by legendary producer John Leckie as part of British Council\'s Soundpad. On the back of this they embarked on a tour of the UK which included appearances at Brighton\'s \'Great Escape Festival\' and London\'s \'Barfly\'.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nThe Vinyl Records: A 4-piece all girl band based in New Delhi that came together in 2010. The band was formed by Arunachal Pradesh natives, Banu, Minam and Mithy and were later joined by lead vocalist and keytarist Cheyyrian Bark from Assam in Jan 2011. With the line up complete the band quickly went on to perform at a number of festivals, playing shows with the likes of Ska Vengers, PCRC and Parikrama. The band have also been featured on MTV F1 Rocks.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nFlexi K: The DJ moniker of cultural provocateur Stefan Kaye. With his forays into ska, jazz, punk and dance bands along with his touring cabaret \'The Medicine Show\' and various revues he has established himself as one of Delhi\'s more versatile and compelling performers. With this evening he goes back to his earlier youth and will be spinning some punky gems for your slam-dancing pleasure!\r\n\r\nFree entry / Reasonably priced drinks / Dress code: Safety pin jewellery and ripped and torn clothing.','','','','www.thewildcity.com',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-20 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','punk-disorderly-indigo-children-the-vinyl-records-flexi-k',1,NULL),(235,'MIDIVAL PUNDITZ at Ricks Bar','','','','','www.thewildcity.com',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-10-08 04:44:19',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-07-21 07:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','midival-punditz-at-ricks-bar',1,NULL),(236,'SKY RABBIT LIVE IN MUMBAI','Sky Rabbit consists of Raxit (Vocals/Samples), Rahul (Guitar/Samples), Siddharth (Bass) and Harsh (Drums). Their latest LP has been in the making for over a year with co-producer Ashish Manchanda of Flying Carpet Productions, a renowned sound mixing and recording engineer for various Bollywood and Hollywood films including The Chronicles of Narnia. This new album will symbolise the beginning of a new direction for the band, completely separate from their progressive metal days as Medusa.\r\n\r\nIn 2008, Sky Rabbit was selected as one of the four bands in India to be part of British Council Soundpad, where they got a chance to record two tracks with legendary producer John Leckie (Radiohead, Pink Floyd, The Verve) at Yash Raj Studios in Mumbai. They then went on to perform at the Great Escape Festival in Brighton continuing their UK tour to Cardiff, Oxford, Liverpool and London.\r\n\r\nThis is what John thought:\r\n\r\n\"Medusa struck me as being true and their music is contemporary and in some ways reflects what\'s happening in the UK. I chose them for their attitude as well as their honesty.... they are living for their music and are honest to what they are doing.\"','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/997-sky-rabbit-live-in-mumbai',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-19 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','sky-rabbit-live-in-mumbai',1,NULL),(237,'DJ MOCITY (EARLY SET)','DJ MoCity was born in Baghdad and raised In New Delhi. This rising star DJ/MC/promoter/street artist has long held a reputation as Delhi nightlifes busiest man-about-town.\r\n\r\nAn artist known nation-wide for his work with Reggae Rajahs, not to mention his earliest forays into event promotion with his legendary South Delhi Block parties, and numerous wildly popular properties he\'s been involved with such as Delitronica, Bass Camp and Holi Cow amongst others...\r\n\r\nThere\'s no doubt that DJ Mocity will be sharing the sounds that he regularly features in his \"Future\" nights across the city:\r\n\r\n\"About two years ago we stumbled upon fresh new sounds that needed to be shared with all of you. We therefore set up a monthly night called The Future, where we showcase our selection from musical visionaries such as Gramatik, Michael Menert and of course, the artist who started it all, Pretty Lights. With the right combination of lights, sound and unexplored musical territory, we hope to inspire and spark a new path to our own Future.\" - DJ Mocity','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1590-dj-mocity-early-set',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-20 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','dj-mocity-early-set',1,NULL),(239,'DUALIST INQUIRY & SANDUNES','We\'ve pretty simply only got good things to say about Dualist Inquiry the brainchild and solo project of Sahej Bakshi, a producer, guitarist and cerebral agent who graduated from the Thornton Music School at USC in Los Angeles, CA.\r\n\r\nSince returning to Delhi in March 2010, Sahej has been touring India extensively, in addition to being selected to perform at Berlin Music Week in Sept 2010. Additionally, he was ranked #1 nationally in the Burn Sasha Tour remix competition (2010) and was the 2nd Runner Up in the MTV Submerge Ultimate Pro DJ Championship 2010, held at Blue Frog in Mumbai. Most recently, Dualist Inquiry performed at The Great Escape Festival in Brighton UK, opening for international sensation Beardyman and hip-hop legend DJ Shadow at the world famous Brighton Dome.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nLive music backgrounds blended with quality dark-studio-production hours, and a heavy dose of UK underground electronica, Sandunes\' tunes bounce between 2 step, future garage, post dubstep and experimental electronica.\r\n\r\nFrom an innovative live set that includes a range of performers and instruments, to an \'Old Skool is Cool\' Electro Swing and funky hip-hop DJ set, the B.P.M. swings roughly between 128 to 138 (read: dance, dance, dance). With new tools and toys, a promising future in AV experiences, and a barrage of live and impromptu FX, Sandunes is bringing her studio to the stage.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1998-dualist-inquiry-sandunes',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-20 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','dualist-inquiry-sandunes',1,NULL),(240,'DJ RAYG','Reji Ravindran (a.k.a rayG) has musical experience which spans for nearly 15 years.\r\n\r\nBorn in Mumbai, Reji was bitten by the music bug during the mid-90s. After collecting a load of music cassettes, CDs and vinyl in his youth, he decided to give DJing a shot by learning from veteran DJ, Jo Azaredo. Since that year (1998), there\'s been no stopping him. Reji is one of the most prolific names in Mumbai\'s booming alternative and electronic music scene.\r\n\r\nFor the longest time in his career, Reji has been recognised as an educator within the music fraternity. After understanding India\'s unique music scene in the early 2000s, the DJ professor designed and implemented his own syllabus at some of the best DJ schools in the city; training more than 500 men and women in the art of DJing, turntablism and music production.\r\n\r\nBy putting his mouth where the money is, Reji has been a successful battle DJ by winning the DMC Champion (Pune - 2000), Times War of the DJs winner (Mumbai - 2007) and Kingfisher Ultra DJ (2010) titles through the years. Reji was the first ever turntablist in an Indian nu-age metal band called Scag and also the brains behind India\'s earliest hip hop collective called \"itch\". In December 2008, world renowned travel magazine, Time Out Mumbai, mentioned him as one of Mumbai\'s most influential DJs\" in its cover article.\r\n\r\nBy always keeping an emphasis on quality music with longer shelf life (minus short term crass commercial appeal), you can always expect Reji to dish out an unpredictable blend of indie, reggae, rock, dub, dancehall, funk, soul, breaks, disco, baltimore, house, techno, hip-hop, electro, drum and bass, jungle, swing, retro, dubstep, mash ups and much more. Phew!','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2031-dj-rayg',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-20 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','dj-rayg',1,NULL),(242,'Shibani Kashyap With Her Band Sojourne','Sojourne is a recently formed band with an eclectic mix of musicians - five musicians whose individual musical journeys have the most interesting tale to tell. And the coming together of these five has one tale to tell, through their union as Sojourne - Journey. \r\n\r\nThe band does a lot of their original songs both in English and Hindi - covers of artistes like Sting, Sade, Alanah Myles, The Corrs, Europe, Nelly Furtado etc. Its a heady mix of songs with a very unplugged sound.\r\n\r\nLead Vocalist And Rhythm Guitar Player - Shibani Kashyap\r\nShibani kashyap is a singer-composer and popular live performer, playback and pop singer. She began her career singing jingles. Her first album Ho Gayi Hai Mohabbat won her a channel V award. \r\n\r\nShe went on to compose her own music and made her debut in Bollywood as a singer, composer with the song Sajnaa aa Bhi Jaa and then followed songs like Zinda Hoon Main (from the film Zinda), kashmakash etc. Her album Nazakat was an experiment with the blues fused with urdu shayari and won her the SANGEET AWARD! For Shibani SOJOURNE is the final journey - making music she simply loves and which is also very non commercial. \r\n','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/shibani-kashyap-her-band-soujourne',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-19 09:35:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','shibani-kashyap-with-her-band-sojourne',1,NULL),(243,'Sufi Fusion Night @ Escape Terrace Bar Kitchen ','Sufi Fusion Night @ Escape Terrace Bar Kitchen, Escape Terrace Bar Kitchen presents Sufi Fusion Night with percussionist Hiten Panwar and DJ Vkey Arora. After wowing the nation with their foot tapping fusion music, they are coming to sweep you off with their live performance every Thursday. Music isn\'t always about noise. It is also about the quiet connection with the soul through soothing tunes that is Sufi music.\r\n','','','','http://www.mypurplemartini.com/search_event_detail.php?id=8186&evid=13572',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-19 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','sufi-fusion-night-escape-terrace-bar-kitchen',1,NULL),(244,'Traffic Jam Live ','Traffic Jam Live @ Striker Pub and Brewery, Striker brings to you Traffic Jam performing live and loud on every Thursday. Traffic Jam is a 4-piece band with a message. With all members from the north east of India, living under similar circumstances, and meeting up far from home in the grounds of Delhi, the band strives to pay tribute to the Rock Gods and Anthems they grew up with in their homeground. Heavily influenced by life, love and Rock their name speaks for itself, something everyone faces in every aspect of their life. Like a calm in the storm, they handle even the hardest riffs with elan and soft notes that flow like milk and honey, eventually giving rock the respect it deserves. As an \'all-genre\' band, the band\'s roots go down to the basic strong foundation of each of the members who are all passionate laureates of music. constantly learning and teaching, Also having had to live-off music, the band has played in numerious great places like Geoffrey\'s, Lutyens, Brix, Attitude, Manajsa, DLF city club and whole lots of other greats places in NCR.\r\n','','','','http://www.mypurplemartini.com/search_event_detail.php?id=8186&evid=13580',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-19 08:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','traffic-jam-live',1,NULL),(247,'Parikrama and Half Step Down','Parikrama is a legendary rock band,playing basically Classic Rock based music,fused with Indian Instruments like the Tabla and the Violin, and has been around for  21 years .\r\n\r\nThe band has done more than 2800 shows till date and still play around 160 shows a year, a record for ANY performing artiste, in any genre, in this country.\r\n\r\nParikrama has had a very successful tour of the UK earlier,where they were promoted by none other than IRON MAIDEN and their legendary manager Mr. ROD SMALLWOOD. Iron maiden saw Parikrama , at bangalore, and  you could hear what they thought of the band , in the documentary shot on Parikrama by BBC, and shown on their show \" DESI DNA\",in UK. \r\n\r\nIRON MAIDEN invited Parikrama to 07 shows in the UK, including the mighty DOWNLOAD FESTIVAL  and venues like Rio ( Leeds ) , The Underground ( Camden ) , The Peel ( kingston ) Etc.\r\n\r\nParikrama is also representing  India at the prestigious KENNEDY CENTRE,USA,On march 11th , 2011 , under the 50th year celebrations of John.F.Kennedy coming to power.\r\n\r\nParikrama is the ONLY ENGLISH ROCK BAND accredited with the ICCR and just finished a highly successful 08 city tour of Indonesia through them.\r\n\r\nHALF STEP DOWN\r\n\r\n\r\nFormed in 2005, Half Step Down began gigging in 2006 as essentially a rock \'n\' roll band, though it would be more accurate to acknowledge their sound as a versatile mish-mash incorporating elements of the blues, alt-rock, funk and reggae. \r\n\r\nConsciously refusing to let themselves be fenced in by genres, they derive their sound from influences and inspirations ranging from Led Zeppelin, RHCP and Dave Matthews to Rachmaninoff, Marley and Django Reinhardt. \r\n\r\nIn early 2007 the band made it to GIR (The Great Indian Rockshow) with their track Overture to Outerspace, which subsequently launched them on a much vaster platform. They spent most of the following year touring the country, taking time out in June to appear on Channel [V]\'s show Launch Pad. They wrapped \'07 with a highly acclaimed unplugged performance in their city, Delhi, where their cover of Redemption Song stood out as one of the critics\' finest of the evening. \r\n\r\nKnown for their antics on stage, HSD are perhaps as much the performers as they are the musicians. With a hedonistic approach to music, they maintain an air of fun that remains a key quotient despite lineup changes and other minor disruptions. ','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/louiz-banks-matrixx-trio',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-26 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','parikrama-and-half-step-down',1,NULL),(248,'Agni Presents DJ Akhtar','One of the most prominent names in club culture and the Indian dance music industry, DJ Akhtar needs no introduction. After completing his I.C.S.E. exams in 1989 he started off his dj\'ing career at a popular south Bombay club -`RG\'s- now The Intercontinental - marine drive. In 1991 he moved over to the exclusive nightclub of the Taj Mahal hotel, Mumbai - `1900\'s- now known as Insomnia. Completing his graduation in commerce from University of Bombay and obtaining diplomas in business management, airline travel n tourism(IATA) and computer systems overview(CSO)- (NCC-UK) he made sure that his passion for music and dj\'ing did not interfere with his educational background. He\'s been entertaining and enthralling audiences which include the creme de la creme of society and the likes of many socialites, film stars & international celebrities and icons with his most peculiar and inimitable style of spinning music. \r\nBesides being the resident dj at Enigma (JW Mariot) dj Akhtar free lances for private shows and parties. He\'s been hired to play at private parties hosted by or for Indian and International superstars including the likes of Mr Amitabh Bachchan, Sachin Tendulkar, Hritik Roshan, Shahrukh Khan, Shekhar Kapoor, Goldie Hawn, Steven Segal( Ford supermodels contest), Richard Gere( AIDS charity function), George Michael, Cindy Crawford(Omega launch), Bryan Adams, Lou Bega and a host of other stars. Amongst socialites, industrialist\'s and corporate clients he\'s performed for countless wedding parties and other functions hosted by personalities such as Anil and Tina Ambani, Gautam Singhania ( Annual parties and Be party at LIFW), Parthiv Kilachand, Nirmal Zaveri, Om Navani, Bharat Shah, Parmeshwar Godrej, Arvind Dubash, Ashish Raheja, Aditya Kilachand, Sanjay Narang, Rahul Narang, Ramona Narang, Sonia Garware, Aditya Birla, Yash Birla, Kumarmanglam Birla, Dr Vijay Mallya, Mr Subramanium Reddy, Kailash and Aarti Surendranath- the list could go on endlessly. \r\nDj Akhtar is very well known for his production skills and often provides music/remixes to bollywood music directors and films.\r\nHe\'s provided music for most designers in the Indian fashion industry and has worked closely with the most prominent and successful event management company\'s , choreographers and models etc. He\'s played at many after parties and for prestigious events like the Lakme India Fashion Week, Bombay Times anniversary party every year, Bacardi Blast, Smirnoff Zone, Gladrags party, Ford super models party, SIFA and IIFA awards etc.. He has played for the Mrs World Pageant party held at the Sahara Amby valley in Feb\'05. He also had the exclusive opportunity for spinning his tunes at very exclusive private parties hosted for Hollywood biggies such as Michael Douglas, Pierce Brosnan and tennis superstar Boris Becker . \r\nHe was the official Dj for all parties at the prestigious IIFA Awards held in Dubai in 2006.\r\nHe is the only dj to play along with the renowned bhangra artist dj Bally Sagoo- U.K. for his tour hosted in 12 different cities. He\'s also played by the side of many international dj\'s such as Talvin Singh, Robert Ayres - U.K., Scott Morris from Fabric - London, James Winchester-Canada, Emmanuel Muratore-Australia, Dj Spencer from the Ministry of sound -London, Dave Pearce from Ibizza? etc. \r\nHe is a very versatile dj and can easily adapt to any crowd or audience\'s taste. He is the pioneer of mainstream commercial music in India. Right from spinning live bollywood remixes, U.K. bhangra to house, retro, hip hop and r n b, dj Akhtar does it all in great style. But his main USP has always been his close interaction with the crowd and to rock private parties & wedding functions to the maximum with mainstream bollywood tunes. \r\nHis repertoire of being a rocking wedding & sangeet dj have taken him to various parts of the world including Antwerp, Brussels, Frankfurt, Bangkok, Singapore, Hong Kong, Macau, Bintaan islands- south china sea, Jakarta, Manilla, Bali, Spain -Las palomas, Teneriffe Sur, Pakistan, Amsterdam, London, Dubai, Bahrain, Tanzania - East Africa and even exotic locations like Maldives and Hoi sin islands in Thailand.','','','','http://www.mypurplemartini.com/search_event_detail.php?id=291&evid=13854',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-23 10:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','agni-presents-dj-akhtar',1,NULL),(250,'Praveen Achary','The new age Indian dance music producers and artists are creating their presence far and wide. Amongst these, our home grown star Praveen Achary has left the audiences wanting more of him. And why not?\r\n\r\nHaving grown up in Lebanon and Canada, dance music had a major influence on him. His diverse international sound is influenced from his strong musical background as well as traveling across the world. The dedication and commitment to dance music led him to be one of co-founders, along with Tanseer, of \'The SF Show\', which is Indias FIRST 2 hour international progressive podcast. The show has featured guests like Cid Inc, Darin Epsilon, Sonic Union, Deepfunk etc and recently celebrated its landmark 25th episode. As a part of The SF Shows launch tour in India, Praveen has played at a few of Indias most sought after clubs.\r\n\r\nHis DJing skills have always gained him a lot of appreciation, but the compliments dont stop here. His panache & signature style, with an emphasis on a unique combination of Deep, Tech and Progressive house, give his audiences the platform they crave. In late 2009, he signed his debut original single \'Crossover\' on \'Maktub Music\', owned by Arjun Vagale & Nicolas Silvano, a monster big-room tune with a star cast of great remixes on board that received play among A-list DJs & producers.\r\n\r\nWith new originals already signed to \'Maktub Music\' and \'Mirabilis Records\', along with remixes on \'Outside The Box Music\' & \'Spherax Records\', 2011 is proving to be Praveens favourite year so far! His productions have already received massive support from Sasha, Nick Warren, Cid Inc, Henry Saiz, Darin Epsilon and the likes. Praveens guest mixes over various radio shows have been a super hit with his audiences. He has been invited by friskyRadio to showcase an exclusive hour long guest mix on \'Frisky Loves India\' with the other Indian giant artists like Anil Chawla, Arjun Vagale, Sanjay Dutta etc. After many compliments on this guest mix, Praveen was again invited to be featured as \'Artist of The Month\' on friskyRadio. \r\n\r\nAlready on the fast track, Praveen Achary is most definitely a name to keep an eye on. He is on his way to gain repute of a pioneer in the progressive music scene in India. In a scene, where electronic dance music has been dominated by giant international names, it is stunningly refreshing to see a young Indian make his way through this with consistent quality productions & sets.','','https://www.facebook.com/events/496223593724516/','','http://gigs.gigatools.com/user/unmuteagency',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-25 07:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','praveen-achary',1,NULL),(251,'Praveen Achary + Vipul ','New age Indian dance music producers and artists are making their presence felt far and wide. Praveen Achary grew up in Lebanon and Canada, where dance music had a major influence on him.\r\n\r\nHis diverse international sound is influenced from his strong musical background as well as traveling across the world. In late 2009, he signed his debut original single \'Crossover\' on \'Maktub Music\', run by Arjun Vagale and Nicolas Silvano, a monster big-room tune with a star cast of great remixes on board.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, Vipul was heavily influenced by DJs and artists such as Darin Epsilon, Sasha, John Digweed, Robert Babicz, Chris Micall, Audiofly and Tim Davison. Vipul\'s sets are open to many different styles and genres. His upcoming projects include many new original tracks and a collaboration with renowned Argentinian producer Ricky Ryan.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2152-praveen-achary-vipul',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-11 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','praveen-achary-vipul',1,NULL),(252,'JITTER','Jayants obsession with creating music, started at an early age. While his friends studied, and his parents worried, he immersed himself in sounds, creating his own unique brand of electronica. His curiosity and eagerness has not waned ever since.\r\nHe began producing music in 2003 and has done numerous projects since working with artists such as Anoushka Shankar, Chebi Sabah, Karsh Kale, Midival Punditz, to name a few. He\'s also produced music for a few film scores. Despite having no formal training in music theory, Jayant has created exceptional work with all of these artists and continues to work with many more.\r\nBoundaries as an artist are practically limitless for him, and that ethos reflects in all his work. His influences come from a wide spectrum of artists &amp; musicians ranging from Indian classical, electronica, rock, psy-chill, trance, techno and ambient. Jayant has developed a unique style of music by experimenting with all these genres. He works with what moves him emotionally and translates that experience into his own, eclectic electronic sound.\r\nEven though these genres give a fundamental idea of his work, you still cannot characterize what you really experience and feel at his shows. It is indescribable in words alone, you just have to come, listen and see for yourself.\r\nJiiter is a Live/Dj Minimal & Techno act by Jayant. The Sound of Jitter is very edgy, hi-tech and psychedelic in nature, almost bridging the gap between outdoor and club.','','','','http://gigs.gigatools.com/city/New%20Delhi',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-25 08:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','jitter',1,NULL),(253,'Something Relevant + Caesar\'s Palace','Something Relevant is one of Mumbai\'s most colourful bands, peppered with immense and varied young talent. Boasting an impressive line up that includes trumpet, piano/keyboards, tenor saxophone, electric bass, electric guitar, congas, percussion, drums and vocals this band has already gathered momentum with a loyal fan following in Bangalore.\r\n\r\nTheir songs are distinctly original, engaging and full of youthful, irrepressible energy. STR have great stage presence and spontaneous improvisation is an integral part of their act. This \'Jam band\' is famous for jumping genres and switching musical styles during songs. This along with their on-stage theatrics, makes their live shows highly unpredictable and enjoyable.\r\n\r\nThe band\'s debut album \'Feels Good 2B Live\' was released in 2009 (Relevant Records/Silk Road)','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1259-something-relevant',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-25 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','something-relevant-caesars-palace',1,NULL),(254,'Under The Influence','Under The influence is a 2-piece piano driven alternative band from Mumbai/Delhi, comprising of Abhijit Lahiri (lyrics, vocals and guitar) and Ashutosh Thatte (compositions and piano). Our music is an amalgamation of everything we listen to and enjoy playing! Labelling the genre of their music might be difficult. A curious blend of jazz, blues, alternative, pop, indie and electronic.\r\n\r\nWhat initially started as a jam band playing covers, has slowly progressed into something more constructive and creative.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1927-under-the-influence-',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-27 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','under-the-influence',1,NULL),(255,'Emergence - Half Step Down Live','Half Step Down (New Delhi) Formed in 2005, Half Step Down began gigging in 2006 as essentially a rock \'n\' roll band, though it would be more accurate to acknowledge their sound as a versatile mish mash incorporating elements of the blues, alt-rock, funk and reggae. Consciously refusing to let themselves be fenced in by genres, they derive their sound from influences and inspirations ranging from Led Zeppelin, RHCP and Dave Matthews to Rachmaninoff, Marley and Django Reinhardt.','','','','http://www.mypurplemartini.com/search_event_detail.php?id=8186&evid=14032',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-25 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','emergence-half-step-down-live',1,NULL),(257,'PRASHANTH PALLEMONI','Turntablist Prashanth Pallemoni is one of India and Bangalore\'s best kept secrets in the Djing world. Showcasing a turntablist\'s interpretation of hip-hop, funk, nu-disco, afrobeat and broken beat, expect outbursts of twisted beat mangling, juggling and quircussionism. Prashanth is a collector and an ambassador for eclectic underground dance music and also 1/3 of Bangalore based electro-acoustic project Schizophonic.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2172-prashanth-pallemoni',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-25 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','prashanth-pallemoni',1,NULL),(258,'TOYZ IN PANIC AKA. LEON RUSSELL & DOKTOR DANIEL','Toyz In Panic, formally known as Leon Russell and Doktor Daniel is a project which brings to floor a concept repeated by many but delivered like none. Their motive is to bring a unique way of playing EDM. Although Leon and Daniel have very different influences they share a connect that helps to not only bring out the best in them but also assists in exceeding audiences expectations.\r\n\r\nLeon\'s micro understanding of EDM, techno in particular, placement and delivery of tracks coupled with the percussive side of Daniel makes the music more thurst and gives it a new dimension. The sole motto of the two is One Sound! Visually u can see a DJ and percussionist going at it but when you hear the music you hear One Sound and that is the essence that this act thrives to better at each coming gig.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2182-toyz-in-panic-aka-leon-russell-doktor-daniel',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-31 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','toyz-in-panic-aka-leon-russell-doktor-daniel',1,NULL),(259,'THE BICYCLE DAYS & PARVAAZ','The Bicycle Days\r\n\r\nExpect to be consumed by the layered and intricate sound that will scar and caress anyone paying attention. Their music shows influences of electronica, rock and even progressive and psychedlic rock. Their compositions are intelligent and contemporary, reflecting their bold musicality with a sound that is ably fronted by Karthik Basker\'s reverberating vocals, over intense psychedelic soundscapes. With their first album due later this year, witness the band live to experience what\'s in store\r\n\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nParvaaz\r\n\r\nParvaaz is a Bangalore-based rock band comprised of Khalid Ahmed(vocals, guitars), Kashif Iqbal(lead guitar, vocals, various instruments), Fidel Dsouza (bass), and Sachin Banandur (drums and percussion). The band came into the spotlight after playing at The Great Indian October Fest and then The Fireflies Festival Of Music in Febuary 2011. Parvaaz are currently working on their debut E.P which will be predominantly written in Urdu and Kashmiri.\r\n','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1695-the-bicycle-days-parvaaz',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-28 08:35:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','the-bicycle-days-parvaaz',1,NULL),(260,'IMPORTED GOODS: DJ MOCITY & DJ SU REAL','Think Global, Listen Local - Imported Goods is a trans-national movement to spread music from the farthest corners of the globe, tearing down geographic borders and encouraging communal harmony through music and culture.\r\n\r\nThe Indian ambassadors of this movement are DJ Mo City and DJ Su Real, both having played a key role in introducing new genres to the Indian dancefloor in recent years.\r\n\r\nDancehall from Jamaica, baile funk from Brasil, afro-funk from Nigeria, kuduro from Angola, 3bal from Mexico, cumbia from Columbia, moombahton from Washington D.C, Malaysian dubstep, Balkan techno, South African house and many more regional styles of dance music are all in the crates for one truly global rave. Sample the goods for yourself.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1931-imported-goods-dj-mocity-dj-su-real',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-28 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','imported-goods-dj-mocity-dj-su-real',1,NULL),(261,'SKA! SKA! SKA!: THE SKA VENGERS, GANDU CIRCUS, DELHI SULTANATE & REGGAE RAJAHS at Blue Frog','The Ska Vengers formed in New Delhi in the fall of 2009, when Delhi based musician Stefan \'Flexi\' K (organ, vocals) rounded up his mates from Emperor Minge; \'The Late\' Nikhil Vasudevan (drums), Tony \'Bass\' Guinard (bass) and Miss Samara C, joining forces with Reggae Rajahs\' Soundsystem DJ Raghav \'Diggy\' Dang (guitar) and BassFoundation founding member Delhi Sultanate (vocals) forming Indias first ska/rocksteady band. The crew strengthened its lineup by adding horn players Rie Ona, Yohei Sato and Juan Carranza the following year.\r\n\r\nWith their unique brand of ska infused dub, punk and jazz agitprop, The Ska Vengers are widely considered to be one of the most exciting and snappily attired live bands in India today.\r\n\r\nSupport from Gandu Circus (see below), Delhi Sultanate & Reggae Rajahs.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2057-ska-ska-ska-the-ska-vengers-gandu-circus-delhi-sultanate-reggae-rajahs',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-10-06 23:40:16',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-07-28 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','ska-ska-ska-the-ska-vengers-gandu-circus-delhi-sultanate-reggae-rajahs-at-blue-frog',1,NULL),(263,'MenWhoPause Acoustic','MenWhoPause is a four-member band from New Delhi, India known for being one of the first bands in India to distribute their music for free over the internet. Their first EP called \'The story begins...\' was released online as a free download in 2003.\r\nThe band has toured the USA twice with an appearance at SxSW 2007, Austin, Texas and a full-fledged tour of Texas.\r\nThe band won the 2008 Jack Daniels\' Best Band of the Year award and got an opportunity to work with REMs producer Dave Barbe.\r\nThe second album Easy was first recorded in a campsite in Uttaranchal after which it took the band four years to re-record and produce the album. Having signed up with EMI-Virgin Records India in 2009, Easy was menwhopauses major label debut with a team that included Miti Adhikari (Radiohead, Nirvana...) and Richard Dodd (Kings of Leon, Tom Petty...). \r\n\'Easy\' is available in all major stores across India as well as on amazon and iTunes. The band toured Europe in June 2012 with the support of ICCR (Indian Centre for Cultural Relations) playing sold out shows in Tallinn (Estonia), Oslo (Norway) and Paris (France).','','','','https://www.facebook.com/events/447585801939393/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-29 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','menwhopause-acoustic',1,NULL),(266,'Emergence Battle of The Bandszzz','Biggest Battle of Rock Bands in Delhi NCR, Undying Inc. from New Delhi on July 11, 2012 Whirling Kalapas from Mumbai on July 18, 2012 Half Step Down from Delhi again on July 25, 2012. The format is very engaging for the Lemp visitors because 60% of the weightage shall be given to what they like and 40% weightage shall be given to the judge\'s votes. The more interesting part is that the judging bands shall do the closing of these Wednesday night competitions by their own performance. The weekly winners shall then compete in a Grand Finale on Saturday, July 28th. The Grand Finale is special because four separate stages shall be set up at Lemp Brewpub & Kitchen - one each for the three weekly winners and a bigger one for not one but two headlining acts by very popular judging bands Grand Finale on Saturday, July 28th Soulmate from Shillong Junkyard Groove from Chennai Event Details Event: Emergence Days & Dates: Wednesdays (July 11th, 18th & 25th, 2012) Undying Inc. from New Delhi on July 11, 2012 Whirling Kalapas from Mumbai on July 18, 2012 Half Step Down from Delhi again on July 25, 2012. Grand Finale: Saturday (July 28th, 2012) Soulmate from Shillong Junkyard Groove from Chennai Time: 9:00 pm onwards Venue: LEMP Brewpub & Kitchen, 201- 204 DLF Star Mall, Sector 30, Opp. 32nd Milestone, Gurgaon 122002 Contact: 8800766144, 9899210785, 9800294020 | brewmaster@lemp.in\r\n','','','','http://www.mypurplemartini.com/search_event_detail.php?id=8186&evid=13627',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-28 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','emergence-battle-of-the-bandszzz',1,NULL),(267,'Tribute to Coldplay by Various Artists ','Tribute to Coldplay by Various Artists @ The Stage,Manajsa, Manajsa presents a tribute to Coldplay this coming Friday. A tribute performed by some of the best artists in Delhi - 1. Sherry Mathews: Vocals 2. Aashish Mandhwani: Guitars/backing vocals 3. Ritwik De: Keyboard/guitar/vocals 4. Rohit Bhattacharya: Bass 5 Suyash Gabriel: Drums On the 27th of July, 9 pm Onwards, watch as THE SCIENTISTs with GREEN EYES, FIX YOU !! For Details, Contact - +91.9999886558 +91.8826158451\r\n','','','','http://www.mypurplemartini.com/search_event_detail.php?id=8186&evid=14241',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-27 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','tribute-to-coldplay-by-various-artists',1,NULL),(268,'\'Soulmate\' opening act by \'Lagori\' ','Inspired by the roots and groove sounds of the Blues, Blues-Rock, Soul, Rock n Roll, Funk and R&B, SOULMATE was formed in Shillong, in October 2002 when Rudy Wallang and Tipriti Kharbangar decided to form a band dedicated to playing the Blues and spreading awareness about this important genre of music. Since then have played numerous gigs all over India and Abroad. In 2011 they played in the US selling out two shows at the Kennedy Center in Washington DC during the Maximum India Festival, did a successful 4 city tour of Norway, played alongside John Mayall at the Jakarta Blues Festival and most recently alongside Buddy Guy, Taj Mahal and John Lee Hooker Jr, Robert Randolph Jr at the Mahindra Blues fest 2012 and Matt Schofield, Johnny Lang and Shemika Copeland at the Mahindra Blues Fest in Mumbai 2011.\r\n\r\nIn the past Soulmate have toured the USA playing in Memphis Tn., Brown University- Rhode Island & Colorado and were twice semi finalists at the 23rd & 26th International Blues Challenge. They have performed in France (Disneyland, Paris), Germany (Baltic Blues Festival 2012), Sweden (Gothenburg and Monsteras Roots and Blues Festival 2012), Singapore (Mosaic Music Festival), Dubai (Du World Music Festival), Indonesia (Jakarta Blues Festival 2010/2011) Bhutan and Kathmandu (Jazzmandu-2004 / 2005 / 2008).\r\n\r\nSoulmate have recorded two albums thus far, Shillong and Moving On and are in the process of putting down songs for their next one.\r\n\r\nAnyone with an interest in the western music scene in India will recognize Guitar player/ Singer/Songwriter/ Rudy Wallang, who leads this tight knit musical unit. Born into music, he grew up listening to his father Toto Wallang making music and he started singing and playing the ukulele at a very tender age eventually graduating to the guitar. Today, Rudy is one of the foremost Blues guitar players/ singer / songwriters in the country with a long musical history having been part of the countrys most well known blues rock acts, Great Society & Mojo\r\n\r\nThe beautifully talented Vocalist and Rhythm guitarist of Soulmate is Tipriti Tips Kharbangar who has earned a name as one of the finest female singers to have emerged out of Shillong and India as a whole! If there is one thing Tips is happy doing it is singing and reflecting this, she vocalizes with a joy and exuberance that is unmatched and original. She has also begun to write songs for the band as well. She started out singing gospel songs at the local church choir and is now drawn to the Blues, Soul and Jazz.\r\n\r\nLAGORI\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nLagori makes Indian music with a Melodic twist and Intensity, but at the same time, filled with total fun and energetic performances. Follow the band and catch them live in your city soon! \r\n\r\n\r\nLagori is an eclectic group of musicians with varied musical influences, who have come together to dish out foot tapping, soul stirring music. \r\n\r\nAlthough Lagori draws influences from the flavour of each musician - ranging from Hindustani, Soul, Funk, Rock, Blues and Metal, the end result is a unique sound which at the same time has a tinge of familiarity to it. ','','','','http://www.hardrockindiablog.com/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-26 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','soulmate-opening-act-by-lagori',1,NULL),(269,'Indus Creed + Safar','Indus Creed are back! The trailblazers of the Indian rock movement return to form with their highly awaited new album. Self-produced by the studio (and live) veterans, and mixed by mixing genius Tim Palmer (Pearl Jam, U2, Robert Plant, Ozzy Osbourne, Porcupine Tree), Evolve will be released in the first quarter of 2012. Expect Uday Benegal, Mahesh Tinaikar, Zubin Balaporia, Rushad Mistry and Jai Row Kavi to break new frontiers with their high-on-energy/big-on-melody sound yet again.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe story of Indian rock cannot be told without a mention of the countrys most iconic rock band. Uday Benegal (vocals), Mahesh Tinaikar (guitar), Mark Selwyn (bass), Jayesh Gandhi (guitar), Zubin Balaporia (keyboards) and Mark Menezes (drums) first came together in 1985. Then called Rock Machine, the guys had no mission or plan. Just an unflagging desire to play the music they loved. In the face of all reason (there was just one government-run TV channel and radio station, neither of which thought rocknroll to be particularly \"cultural\") the band set out to do just that. It took blood, guts and a steely resolve to cut through the crap. It was just a matter of time before practically every college and concert promoter in the country wanted to book what had become Indias favourite band. The rest is history. They recorded three albums, won a bunch of awards and changed their name to Indus Creed. And in the process they inspired an entire generation to pick up an instrument and rock it out. Heres a quick roundup of some of their multifarious achievements:','','','','http://www.hardrockindiablog.com/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-26 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','indus-creed-safar',1,NULL),(270,'Thermal and a Quarter and Cadent Slaves','Thermal And A Quarter is a path-breaking band from Bangalore, India.\r\n\r\nThermal And A Quarter (TAAQ) is a path-breaking band from Bangalore, India. TAAQ describes its music as Bangalore Rock; a sound as unique and layered as the fast-growing city of its birth. Imagine a Phish-meets- Steely Dan-via-Mahavishnu-Orchestra vibe: the TAAQ sound is all that and more. Through the last 15 years, TAAQ has played all over India, completed tours in the United Kingdom, West Asia and South-East Asia, released four studio albums, supported acts like Deep Purple and Jethro Tull, and won awards for individual musicianship as well as overall contribution to Indian Rock. \r\n\r\nLive, TAAQ delivers an unforgettable, immersive musical experience. From packed clubs to arena-size venues, TAAQs stellar musicianship, hard-hitting lyrics, and fluid improvised style make every gig unique. \r\n\r\nBand Members\r\nBruce Lee Mani (guitars, vocals)\r\nRajeev Rajagopal (drums)\r\nPrakash K N (bass)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCadent Slaves is a Metal band from Hyderabad, India. Formed in 2008.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCadent Slaves had its genesis as an Rock/Metal band in 2008, founded by Rahul, Phani & Santosh switched to rather grew into Metal by the late 2008.\r\n\r\nThe band has had it\'s share of change in the line up with Vocalists changing and the band ending up dormant for almost a year till it rose up with fresh blood infused, trying to furiously make up for lost time!\r\n\r\nOwn Compositions:\r\n\r\n1. Cadence Theme\r\n2. Vengeance\r\n3. Silence of The Darkness\r\n4. Kill My Enemy\r\n5. A Blissful Spirit\r\n','','','','http://www.hardrockindiablog.com/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-26 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','thermal-and-a-quarter-and-cadent-slaves',1,NULL),(271,'Junkyard Groove and Soulmate Live','	New York Film Academy in association with Rock Street Journal Presents the Biggest Band Competition in Delhi/NCR.\r\n\r\n1st Prize - 1 Lakh\r\n2nd Prize - Holiday Package + Vouchers from OnStage\r\n3rd Prize - Gift Vouchers\r\n\r\nOn 28th July, there will be 4 Stages, One Stage for each competing band and one for Headlining Acts. On 26th July 2012, besides the competing set all 3 Finalist bands will be given a song that they have to present in their own style, Idea is to have all the bands perform one after another and have Audience Vote \r\n\r\nHeadlining Acts will be:\r\n\r\nJunkyard Groove \r\n&\r\nSoul mate','','','','http://www.facebook.com/events/294601617305825/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-07-28 08:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','junkyard-groove-and-soulmate-live',1,NULL),(273,'MIDIVAL PUNDITZ at Blue Frog','Midival Punditz is the brainchild of childhood friends, Gaurav Raina and Tapan Raj. In 1997, after being bored with the remix and Bollywood driven music scene in India, the boys started producing original electronic music and sending out demo tracks to labels and other producers. Simultaneously, their monthly parties, Cyber Mehfil started becoming hugely popular and soon achieved cult status. Other artists and producers in the US & UK quickly recognized their efforts. Word spread about the boys, and they came to be known as \'The new sound of 21st Century India\'.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1884-midival-punditz',NULL