,0,'','','','2012-08-04 07:35:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','flittermaus-live',1,NULL),(351,'Eristoff Wolf Night','','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2238-eristoff-wolf-night-dj-hamza',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-04 08:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','eristoff-wolf-night',1,NULL),(353,'DJ AUSTIN','','','','','http://www.facebook.com/someplaceelselive/events',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-04 08:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','dj-austin',1,NULL),(354,'Tribute To Slayer','','','','','http://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=10151016393093172&set=a.213875353171.131345.125868473171&type=1&permPage=1',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-10 08:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','tribute-to-slayer',1,NULL),(355,'Slow Down Clown\'s Video Premiere','It began as a solo project, formed by singer/songwriter Vitek Tek Goyel in Upstate New York in 2001. Upon his return to Mumbai, Tek teamed up with producer/guitarist Anurag Shanker, to translate his bedroom enterprise into a full band experience together with bassist Wilson Kenneth and drummer Arfaaz Fuzz Kagalwala.\r\n\r\nThus the evolution of Slow Down Clown, a four-piece Mumbai outfit whose sound oscillates between folk, alternative and punk','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/slow-down-clowns-video-premiere',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-08 07:35:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','slow-down-clowns-video-premiere',1,NULL),(356,'Opening Act: What\'s In The Name','What\'s in the Name, is a 5 piece Alternative Rock band from Mumbai. Since their inception in 2011, they\'ve created waves in the Indian Rock Scene by winning several competitions including the Goa leg of Channel V\'s Launchpad. They\'re known for their energetic, power packed stage act where they ensure the crowd claps, sings and dances along to their music. All in all they consider themselves to be value for money...Paisa Vasool.','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/opening-act-whats-name',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-08 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','opening-act-whats-in-the-name',1,NULL),(357,'Coshish','Fusing elements of Progressive Rock, with the more easily acceptable mainstream song writing styles of Hindi Rock, seems to come naturally to Mumbai based band Coshish. The band believes that their songs should have mass appeal and yet retain enough musical dexterity to appease technical musicians without compromising on simplicity.   Their songs carry very strong social messages, delivered beautifully through Hindi lyrics. The band prefers singing in their mother tongue as they consider it as a more efficient method of connecting with people from every strata of society.  With groove driven bass lines, feel based solos, catchy riffs, Indian classical inspired vocals, technical yet subtle drumming, the occasional odd time signatures and very interactive and personal live performances, these guys sure know how to get the crowd singing with them.','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/coshish',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-08 10:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','coshish',1,NULL),(358,'Sonam Kalra - The Sufi Gospel Project','If you thought devotional music was boring, it\'s time to smell the coffee! A collective that strikes the perfect balance between the traditional and the contemporary, this project has pleased many a reveller with an ear for Godly verses. Classy instrumentation and well-defined vocals melting in perfect synchrony, Ms Kalra\'s outfit is just what defines the avant-garde \'Indian indie sound\'. ','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/sonam-kalra-sufi-gospel-project-0',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-09 10:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','sonam-kalra-the-sufi-gospel-project',1,NULL),(359,'The Supersonics','What people have said about The Supersonics: \r\n\r\n\"Top Ten Artists to Watch For\" - Rolling Stone Magazine, India, November 2008 \r\n\r\n\"Must Have Download\" - Rolling Stone Magazine, India, October 2008; on the single \'In Memory Of\', featured on HMV Saregama\'s Kolkata Underground album. \r\n\r\n\'\'These nice guys from Kolkata\'s burgeoning music scene are making all the right noises and if this song is any indication, their album is worth watching for\'\' - Rolling Stone Magazine, India, May 2009; on \'Policemen and Nice Guys\', the first single from Maby Baking. \r\n\r\n\"Rhythm heavy melodies with mid-song tempo changes and a driving bass line all combined to create one of the most refreshing live sounds of the year so far\" - Indiecision.com, October 2008 \r\n\r\n\'\'Damn I love them.\" - Jay Singh (Pink Noise/Skinny Alley) \r\n\r\n\"Trust me, the Supersonics are as good as it gets. Their sound is no different from what\'s taking place abroad. It\'s a pleasure recording them.\" - Miti Adhikari, Producer - Maby Baking.','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/supersonics',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-08 10:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','the-supersonics',1,NULL),(360,'Maxime Dangles (France) + Ankytrixx','Maxime Dangles belongs to the new generation of electronic music producers. His passion has led him to produce remixes for some of the world\'s famous artists like Moby, John Digweed and Green Velvet. On stage and in the studio, Maxime is what you would call a geek. He loves old analog machines, but is also crazy about the latest technologies available to producers. He creates, invents, fiddles around and travels with many of his machines (Lemur, Monome, WiiMote...) Get Ready for some High Octane / High Energy Techno as he teams up with the finest talent from India, Ankytrixx in Mumbai and Jitter in Delhi to sweep you off the dance floor with his LIVE SET.','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/maxime-dangles-france-1',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-10 10:35:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','maxime-dangles-france-ankytrixx',1,NULL),(361,'Blek + The Supersonics','BLEK (fomerly Blech) is an all original alternative trio with no idea of what their genre really is. This 3 piece act is made up of Jared Creado on the bass, Varoon Aiyer (Split) on drums, and Rishi Bradoo on guitars and vocals. \r\n\r\nTheir meeting was a result of idleness, flunky frustration, and the failure of one of them to speak un-anglicized Hindi. Each of them brings a different style and influence to their music. Rolling Stone magazine refers to them as the \"Bombay based cousins of The Supersonics\" and the best way to experience this band is to watch them perform live while they execute their trade-marked monkey dance.\r\n\r\nThe Supersonics\r\nThe Supersonics crashed the Calcutta music scene with a high voltage performance at a crowded little bar called Someplace Else. Formed in 2006, their songwriting has already earned them a cult status. Geared with a toothpaste fresh sound and an electrifying stage presence, it would be wrong to call The Supersonics a band. They are a shiny new revolution. Their sound is not pigeonholed to any one genre. \r\n\r\nThe band has a huge, loyal and steadily increasing fan base. They write songs that are as addictive as nicotine. The band has the crowd singing along with them on practically every one of their original songs. Their debut album, Maby Baking released by HMV Saregama, was a massive success garnering rave reviews from all media. Work has started on the second album and the band is as excited as they were when they formed initially to make music.','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/blek-supersonics',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-11 10:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','blek-the-supersonics',1,NULL),(362,'Max Clouth Clan & Friends','Max Clouth is a musician who is deeply interested in all forms of musical expression. Born 1985, he had the chance to travel to southern Europe, US, Africa and the Middle East and experience the cultural diversity of the world in his early childhood. After graduating at Freie Waldorfschule Frankfurt, Max enrolled at Mainz University to study jazz guitar with Marc - Oliver Klenk and Norbert Scholly. \r\n\r\nParallel to his studies he performed with singers, ensembles and dancers, often playing a hard rock gig after a jazz performance. In 2008 Max changed to Dresden University where he continued his studies with Professor Ralf Beutler and Stephan Bormann and received his diploma degree in 2009. Inspired by Shakti, the influential indo jazz ensemble of John McLaughlin and Zakir Hussain, Max started learning about the Indian system of raga and tala with violinist Indradeep Ghosh. In October 2009 he enrolled at Sangit Mahabharati Music School in Mumbai (Bombay) to study Indian Classical Music with Pandit Nayan Ghosh. \r\n\r\nBesides his studies Max regularly performs in India and Europe in a solo format and with musicians like Indradeep Ghosh (violin), Hindol Deb (sitar), Nirmalya Roy, Omprakash Pandey, Niraj Kumar, Pt Shankha Chatterjee (tabla), Torsten de Winkel (guitar), Rafael Sotomayor (hang), Marc-Inti Mnnel (bass), Vaibhav Wavikar and Geronimo Dehler (perc).\r\n\r\nIn 2010, luthier Philipp Neumann and Max designed a double neck acoustic guitar equipped with 12 sympathetic strings. The Lotus Guitar, named after stylized lotus petals on the body and neck of the guitar, is a unique instrument providing an incredible variety of colours from warm nylon string sounds to oud or sarod-like microtonal shades to the silvery ring of the sympathetic strings. The Lotus Guitar has been a great success so far, being used regularly in Max\'s performances, including his India tour in January 201','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/max-clouth-trio',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-29 10:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','max-clouth-clan-friends',1,NULL),(363,'Ankur & The Ghalat Family','After rocking many gigs at blueFROG Bombay, Ankur Tewari and his family of musical friends are all set for their debut performance at blueFROG Delhi! Ankur composes, produces and performs Urdu and Hindi songs enriching the growing underground and alternative music scene! We can\'t wait to welcome him and his merry band to the Delhi stage for this and hopefully many more gigs!\r\n','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/ankur-ghalat-family-0',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-09 09:35:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','ankur-the-ghalat-family-1',1,NULL),(364,'MAP featuring Manta Sidhu','Representing Alternative Pop styles in composition and disposition, Delhi-based band MAP seeks to accentuate the brilliance of open spaces in sound - all musical elements merged together in a carefree environment, while standing vulnerable in all their rawness. Subtle in expression, minimalist in essence, easy on the ear - what lies in pursuit is a treat for the all-embracing music lover.\r\n\r\nThe band is led by singer-songwriter Manta Sidhu, whose experiments as an artist delve into the luxury of being instinctive, intrusive and indulgent all at once - where music is uncomplicated and comprehensible as we all know it and love it. Accompanying her is Jishnu Banerjee on Guitar, Abhishek Mangla on Bass and, Reuben Narain on Drums.','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/map-feat-manta-sidhu',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-29 10:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','map-featuring-manta-sidhu',1,NULL),(365,'RISHI INC.','The band Rishi Inc believes that \"music is the universal language of mankind\" (Henry Wadsworth Longfellow)... they got together following their belief and their passion for music, which is inspired by their own strong, rich Indian roots, with a modern approach, for everyone\'s pleasure!','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/rishi-inc',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-19 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','rishi-inc',1,NULL),(366,'Sonic Species','','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/sonic-species-uk',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-17 10:35:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','sonic-species',1,NULL),(367,'Sur','SUR consists of musicians who are a blend of experience and youth. They are comprised of the classic formation of Bass, Drums, Guitar and Vocals along with Mridangam/Tabla, percussions, keyboards and Flute. Suresh Mendoza, is on the bass. His intelligent attack and stylings are a crucial aspect of the bands sound. Glenn Fernandes, is on guitars and with his expressive licks, powerful rhythms and creative melodic ideas provides a unique sound and feel to the band. \r\n\r\nNitin Ramesh, has machine-guntiming on the drums, yet still can lace each beat with an infectious groove. The lead vocalist, Arunima Bhattacharya, has trained in Hindustani Classical Music since childhood and weaves a spell with her melodious voice. Gautam Sharma is on Mridangam/Tabla and percussion, Shashank Acharya is on Flute and Umang Doshi, is on Keyboards. \r\n\r\nThe band has a high energy sound which can be related to genres such as funk-rock, blues, alternative, and jazz, all stylized with Indian Classical ragas and Rhythms. Some of their influences include Indian Folk Music, Jamiroquai, Level 42 etc..','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/sur',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-19 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','sur',1,NULL),(368,'Tribute To The Beatles By Barefaced Liar + Special Guest','','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/tribute-beatles-barefaced-liar-special-guests',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-23 09:35:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','tribute-to-the-beatles-by-barefaced-liar-special-guest',1,NULL),(369,'DJ Karma','DJ Karma is a pioneering DJ who introduced the Delhi club scenes to Hip Hop & RnB. Thus revolutionizing the circuit with smooth beats and sexy grooves in a time when gigs were entirely oriented around Bollywood and House. \r\n\r\nGrowing up in Dubai, Karma was influenced by the multi-cultural music and was drawn to hip hop. This eventually led him to taking up spinning professionally from 2001. He started throwing jams in Delhi in 2002, attracting fame and attention in other cities as well. A skilled emcee (rapper), Karma is known to hype the crowd and evolve the craft with rhymes that transcend easily between Hindi and English. \r\n\r\nHe has been featured on Honey Singh\'s Jhaanjar Kehndi; DJ T-Nu & Amit B\'s Soniye remix; and Worren Webbe\'s Down in Love (nominated Best Pop Song and Best Collaboration for Bite My Music VIMA Awards - Indigo awards). Karma currently represents Urbanatics (DJ Grenville, DJ Cj and DJ Pema) promoting and DJing at major clubs in the city, staying fresh by dropping hits before they break, and keeping it moving with ol\' skool jams too.  ','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/dj-karma',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-10 10:35:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','dj-karma',1,NULL),(370,'Madrobe Walfunction ','','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/madrobe-walfunction',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-19 10:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','madrobe-walfunction',1,NULL),(371,'Brute Force + Lost Stories','Tuhin Mehta belongs to the old school breed of DJs. With two decades of experience pioneering club-world in India, hes a force to be reckoned with. He is someone who has immersed himself in the art of DJing from an extremely young age, where it was not just a forged career path, rather, a way of life.\r\n\r\nA professionally qualified sound engineer from SAE in Chennai, along with being an international ambassador to the Berklee College of Music, Tuhin not only has immense experience from the various clubs that he has played in over the years, he also has a sharp understanding of the technical aspects behind sound production. His understanding of equipment is grade A and it speaks volumes that he was named a Pioneer Pro DJ for India in 2007. This combination of both prowess and technical ability only adds to his allure as a DJ who has a sharp understanding of the science of rocking a dance-floor.\r\n\r\nAs a producer, he is one half of the duo Brute Force, a collaboration that began many years ago with childhood friend, Shane Mendonsa. ','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/brute-force-lost-stories',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-17 11:30:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','brute-force-lost-stories',1,NULL),(372,'Estiva','Steven Baan, better known as the man behind Estiva, has grown to be one of the most demanded DJs and respected producers in electronic dance music. Operating out of the city of Reeuwijk in western Holland, Stevens flair for a beautiful melodic take on progressive trance has been welcomed with open arms from many thousands in the worldwide EDM scene.','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/estiva-netherlands-0',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-18 10:30:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','estiva',1,NULL),(373,'Thompson Andrews','Come by, grab a drink and let your hair down as the night kicks into some funky-motown rhythms, Souled out with some brilliant music you cant deny yourself!! So do your thang on this night of African American music like never heard before, brought exclusively to you by the wonderful Thomson Andrews. \r\n','','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/thomson-andrews',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-16 10:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','thompson-andrews',1,NULL),(374,'Whirling Kalapas','Whirling Kalapas is the acoustic side proj