 a DJ and producer, Dale\'s musical diversity cuts across the deepest and darkest percussive house, to a tougher 4am club sound that borders the line between house and techno.\r\n\r\nA musician through and through, Dale is equally at home manning the controls in the studio as he is in the the dingiest of dimly lit low ceiling basement clubs or the main stage of an outdoor festival.\r\n\r\nAppearances at some of the the most widely respected clubs and parties in the world - Cocoon in Frankfurt, Ministry of Sound in London, the Miami Winter Music Conference etc. - has solidified his reputation as a consistent deliverer of quality.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1693-dale-anderson',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-10 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','dale-anderson-1',1,NULL),(392,'Soulmate','','','','','http://www.theparkhotels.com/kolkata/kolkata/offers-events.html',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-11 08:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','soulmate',1,NULL),(393,'MONSTERSYNC: S.O.N.R.','S.O.N.R a.k.a Rishi Handa from New Delhi is known for his intuitive ability to captivate the dance floor. His music has an organic feel to it - an influence of having lived on the magical Hawaiian Islands whilst having a love for the great outdoors. S.O.N.Rs DJ sets are atmospheric, bass responsive and intensely groovy. Each track represents a chapter in a story culminating into a high energy, elated flight through sound. An act that can string together a range of diverse styles of electronica with creative subtlety.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1258-monstersync-sonr',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-10 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','monstersync-sonr',1,NULL),(394,'The Supersonics','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1259-something-relevant','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1259-something-relevant',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-10 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','the-supersonics-2',1,NULL),(395,'Arjun Vagale at Blue Blazer','','','','','https://www.facebook.com/ArjunVagaleOfficial/app_153332064731618',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-10-06 03:15:36',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-08-11 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','arjun-vagale-at-blue-blazer',1,NULL),(396,'Maxime Dangles (France) + Jitter','Maxime Dangles is an experienced international artist who belongs to a new generation of electronic music producers. His first release on Kompakt was such a hit that he quickly joined the labels roster in 2006. This collaboration with the famous German label led to other high quality releases. It was not long before other prestigious labels invited him to work with them. Bedrock, Boyznoize, Skryptm and Scandium just some of the labels he went on to work for.\r\n\r\nOn stage and in the studio, Maxime is what you would call a geek. He loves old analog machines but is is also crazy about the latest technologies available to producers. He creates, invents and fiddles. His live performances are a showcase for this passion and he travels with many of his machines whilst on tour.','http://www.jmusic.in','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2263-maxime-dangles-jitter',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-11 09:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','maxime-dangles-france-jitter',1,NULL),(397,'Apparat Live','If you\'ve kept a close eye on the pulse of electronic music at any point over the last five years, it\'s safe to say you\'ll have encountered Sascha Ring a.k.a Apparat, the Berlin based musician who has been a restless force in contemporary electronic music for over a decade. In that time he\'s released 4 critically acclaimed Apparat albums, alongside a techno masterpiece with long time collaborators Modeselektor as Moderat.\r\n\r\nOften described as the missing link between Steve Reich, Sigur Rs and Radiohead, Apparat will be on a tour across India later this month touching down in Kolkata, Mumbai, Chennai and New Delhi between 24 August and 31 August as part of the ongoing year of Germany in India titled \'Germany and India 2011-2012: Infinite Opportunities\'. The same initiative under which The Indo-German Urban Mela continues to travel across the country and how German electronic trio Jahcoozi came out last year.\r\n\r\nThe tour will be in support of his latest LP \'The Devil\'s Walk\', which saw him bid farewell to more dancefloor focussed productions in favour of the richly melodic tracks that make up most of the album. The album itself was conceived in Mexico with Telefon Tel Avivs Joshua Eustis, and developed in Europe with Patrick Nackt Christensen of EBM outfit Warren Suicide.\r\n\r\nApparat officially announced the tour via a tweet that simply said: \"Yeah! We\'ll be touring India in end of August! Dates, venues tba\"\r\n\r\nThe brief trek will include appearances in New Delhi and Mumbai. You can view a full list of dates below:','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2250-apparat-live',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-26 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','apparat-live',1,NULL),(398,'Apparat Live','If you\'ve kept a close eye on the pulse of electronic music at any point over the last five years, it\'s safe to say you\'ll have encountered Sascha Ring a.k.a Apparat, the Berlin based musician who has been a restless force in contemporary electronic music for over a decade. In that time he\'s released 4 critically acclaimed Apparat albums, alongside a techno masterpiece with long time collaborators Modeselektor as Moderat.\r\n\r\nOften described as the missing link between Steve Reich, Sigur Rs and Radiohead, Apparat will be on a tour across India later this month touching down in Kolkata, Mumbai, Chennai and New Delhi between 24 August and 31 August