LL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-31 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','jayant-jitter',1,NULL),(464,'NERD DEPARTMENT & VIPUL','Nerd Dept is the brainchild of DJ/producer Sanil Sudan and techno DJ/producer Vishnu PS. Between the two of them they have been actively pushing the house and techno sound with their individual productions and DJ sets around the country.\r\n\r\nBoth a part of the PureNoise Crew, they joined forces recently to push and produce their rather selective take on grungy, gritty, in your face house and techno music.\r\n\r\nFrom easy laid back disco grooves to hard hitting techno beats, their love for all forms these two genres will be apparent in their productions in the Studio or their 4 deck DJ sets. Being the analog fools they are, NerdDepartment aims to geek out on their shiny toys both analog and digital to create an experience which is both intelligent and edgy.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, Vipul was heavily influenced by DJs and artists such as Darin Epsilon, Sasha, John Digweed, Robert Babicz, Chris Micall, Audiofly and Tim Davison. Vipul\'s sets are open to many different styles and genres. His upcoming projects include many new original tracks and a collaboration with renowned Argentinian producer Ricky Ryan.\r\n\r\nFree entry all night.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1930-nerd-department-vipul',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-31 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','nerd-department-vipul',1,NULL),(465,'Arjun Vagale  at Ricks Bar','','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-10-06 03:15:03',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-01 02:50:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','arjun-vagale-at-ricks-bar',1,NULL),(466,'B.L.O.T Album Release','','','','','',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-01 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','blot-album-release-1',1,NULL),(467,'DISCO 31: DJ MOODYBOY & SU-REAL','Disco 31 presents to you one of the truest veterans and unsung heros of the Indian electronica scene, Moodyboy.\r\n\r\nBased in Mumbai, Moodyboys career spans almost two decades as a DJ and producer. In his early days, he even worked with the likes of Gaurav Raina of Midival Punditz. Back then, Tribal House reigned supreme and Moodyboy was an integral part of the scene. In recent years, we have seen a resurgence of tribal house in a more modern format via the likes of major European club stars like Riva Starr and Gregor Salto.\r\n\r\nAccordingly, Moodyboy has been busy in the studio again, releasing track after track that would fit in seamlessly at any super-club in Ibiza or Goa. Disco 31 co-founder and host DJ Su Real will also be on board to guide the night to heady excesses.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2312-disco-31-dj-moodyboy-sureal',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-01 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','disco-31-dj-moodyboy-su-real',1,NULL),(468,'SKA SKA SKA: MICROPHON3, GANDU CIRCUS, DJ REJI at Blue Frog','This is the second of a regular series of events to be held every month at blueFROG Delhi and Mumbai all the way through till December. Ska!, Ska!, Ska! ushers in a new wave of dance and roots music featuring exciting line ups with the very best performers within their field.\r\n\r\nAugust Line Up:\r\n\r\nMicrophon3\r\n\r\nMicrophon3 is one of the front runners of the Indian/Desi hip-hop scene. Tanmay Bahulekar (front man/vocals) has been a poet for the past decade and a half. On the decks is Johnny B, who shook the Indian hip-hop scene back in the day, as the front man of \"Method\". Ex PDV/Scribe/Chaos Theory drummer, Niraj Trivedi switches the beat and the funk as he picks up the mallets again. Completing this four piece is ace bassist Romit Ranjan (Ex Them Clones).\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nGandu Circus\r\n\r\nThe movie Gandu was made by Bengali director Q in 2010. The music of the film was produced by Neel Adhikaris band Five Little Indians. The film has garnered much praise at several European and American festivals. Since there was a growing demand to hear the music from the film a fresh outfit was formed featuring Q (vocals) and Neel (guitars). Jiver Singh joined Gandu Circus in February 2012 to create additional electronic grooves, all played live, using a variety of software and hardware.\r\n\r\nAll Gandu Circus tracks have accompanying visuals produced by Q that are projected at performances.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nDJ Reji\r\n\r\nResident DJ at Mumbai\'s hippest nightspot, Bonobo, since early 2011, DJ Reji will be spinning a blend of dancehall, funk, soul, breaks, disco, baltimore, hip-hop, drum and bass/jungle, swing, retro, dubstep, mash ups and dare I say it, more! A successful battle DJ by winning the DMC Champion (Pune - 2000), Times War of the DJs (Mumbai - 2007) and Kingfisher Ultra DJ (2010) titles through the years, Reji was the first ever turntablist in an Indian nu-age metal band called Scag and also the brains behind India\'s earliest hip-hop collective called \"itch\". Reji has also been promoting fresh talent and sounds through his current role as a label DJ/promoter/talent scout for Air Snare Records.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nFlexi K (DJ Set) & Katya (Ska Dance Instructor)\r\n\r\nSka Venger, B\'stard, and main Minge man Flexi K takes you on a musical journey to a time when going to a dance didn\'t mean getting monged on controlled substances as a means to actually enjoy the music being played. Spinning 60\'s jazz, tropicalia, Ethiopian grooves and much more.\r\n\r\nEntry: Rs 600\r\nTime: Gates open at 6pm','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2375-ska-ska-ska-microphon3-gandu-circus-dj-reji',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-10-06 23:39:52',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-01 06:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','ska-ska-ska-microphon3-gandu-circus-dj-reji-at-blue-frog',1,NULL),(469,'SKY RABBIT (LIVE)','','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-04 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','sky-rabbit-live',1,NULL),(470,'Indigo Children Single Release Tour','Indigo Children are a Delhi based band duo that have been part of the Indian circuit since 2004 and are well known for their well crafted compositions. The band has generated a buzz in India\'s rock scene, no doubt catapulted by their success as the winners of the 2007 edition of Channel [V] Launchpad.\r\n\r\nThey were also one of the four bands chosen to record with world renowned producer John Leckie as a part of the British Council\'s Soundpad. As a part of the Soundpad project the band went on a two week tour of the UK, playing at festivals and venues such as The Great Escape festival in Brighton and the legendary Barfly in Camden. The band has also opened for Bryan Adams, Your Code Name is Milo, Freak Kitchen, Intronaut, Benea Reach and Backstreet Boys in India.\r\n\r\nThe band comprises Sanchal Malhar and Nikhil Rufus Raj, featuring an extended line up for the live act. The band refrains from categorizing their music to a genre but likes to write idiosyncratic vocal pop music.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/100-indigo-children',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-11 11:55:13',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-05 20:00:00','2012-09-05 23:00:00','indigo-children-single-release-tour',1,NULL),(471,'B.L.O.T Album Release','BLOT is an acronym for the Basic Love of Things. It\'s also a multidisciplinary project helmed by Gaurav Malaker and Avinash Kumar, with the sole objective of creating alternative and experimental sound and vision experiences.\r\n\r\nAvinash Kumar is a designer, visual artist, filmmaker and VJ. He\'s also a founding member of the two design and research firms Quicksand and BOX. Gaurav Malaker on the other hand is a DJ, producer and a founding member of Qilla Records. Together they blend sound and music using traditional filmmaking techniques as well as motion and stop-motion graphics to visually manipulate their performance spaces.\r\n\r\nThis is the Kolkata album launch for the duo\'s much anticipated debut album due for release later this year (preview tracks here).','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2371-blot-snafu-album-launch-3dav-set',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-05 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','blot-album-release-2',1,NULL),(472,'TARIK (LIVE AV)','Tarik was a lounge samba orchestra on their way to the Rio Sheraton that was hijacked by affinity groups and led to perform for them at their audio visual opium den. The visual material is gathered from local spaces in town (tea stalls, local bars, brothels, traditional markets, etc) that complement the musical content.\r\n\r\nOpening the evening will be Dhruv Visvanath, an acoustic percussive guitarist, playing smooth melodies on the guitar whilst simultaneously drumming on the body of the guitar. India\'s very own Andy Mckee, and he can sing too.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nImage Credit: Sakshi Kapoor (Thumbnail)','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2313-tarik-live-av-dhruv-visvanath',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-06 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','tarik-live-av',1,NULL),(473,'ARJUN VAGALE at Cloud9','To say that this gentleman alongside his bandmates has had a hand in the progression of India\'s booming electronic music scene would be an understatement. Simply, one of the most successful electronic music acts hailing from India, Jalebee Cartel has consistently challenged the notion that dance music is a Western domain by single handedly putting India on the international \'EDM\' map.\r\n\r\nUsually on electronics as a part of the band, tonight Arjun Vagale will be offering his services as a DJ, showcasing a healthy dose of the freshest house, techno, miminal and everything in between.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2282-arjun-vagale',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-10-06 03:14:49',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-08 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','arjun-vagale-at-cloud9',1,NULL),(474,'DISCO 31: VARNIKA KUNDU & DJ SU-REAL','\"On this edition of Disco 31, Varnika Kundu our featured guest hails from Chandigarh where she has been DJing furious sets of the latest dutch house, techno and electro that would blow most male DJs off their decks\" - TLR\r\n\r\nThe first mixer Kundu ever used was built for her by her father when she was just 13 years old. Although she only committed to DJing as a career last year, she has already performed in Germany and the UK. Disco 31 co-founder and host DJ Su Real will also be on board to guide the night to heady excesses.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2315-disco-31-varnika-kundu-dj-sureal',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-08 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','disco-31-varnika-kundu-dj-su-real',1,NULL),(476,'SHASHWAT PANDE & SANCHAL MALHAR (INDIGO CHILDREN)','Fans of folk rock music like Bob Dylan, Nick Drake and Robert Johnson should not miss this night! Shashwat Pande is a relatively new name in the Delhi singer-songwriter space, but hes already mesmerised T.L.R. twice in the last few months and they couldnt wait to bring him back.\r\n\r\nAfter some brief stints with a few of Delhi\'s well known rock and metal bands, Shashwat has now ventured into an acoustic blues-man format, writing and performing predominantly original material.\r\n\r\nJoining him on the support slot this evening is Sanchal Malhar, lead singer and guitarist of Indian indie-rock powerhouse Superfuzz/Indigo Children. Sanchal has graced many festival main-stages in India and abroad but is now developing his solo repertoire and by all reports this intimate performance by the critically acclaimed and charismatic rocker will only deepen his already broad appeal to the new wave of Indian rockers.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2316-shashwat-pande-sanchal-malhar-indigo-children',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-13 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','shashwat-pande-sanchal-malhar-indigo-children',1,NULL),(477,'Papon & The East India Company at Blue Frog','Angaraag Mahanta known as Papon is a singer, composer and record producer. Born to music duo and legends of Assamese music, Archana Mahanta and Khagen Mahanta, he was introduced to music early at a young age. His first language is Assamese and he also sings in Hindi and Bengali. His initial training was in Indian Classical, devotional and folk music. He learnt vocals primarily but also plays the khol, tabla, guitar, and harmonium.\r\n\r\nHis music genres are ambient electronic, acoustic folk and new age Indian Classical. He has been identified as having traces of pantatonic Mongoloid notes, local river song influences and ghazals.\r\n\r\nEntry: Rs 500','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2376-papon',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-10-08 02:19:28',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-13 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','papon-the-east-india-company-at-blue-frog-1',1,NULL),(479,'REGGAE RAJAHS at Cloud9','Reggae Rajahs are India\'s first reggae sound system. The trio composed of Diggy Dang, Mr. Herbalist and DJ MoCity (Iraq\'s first soundboy) are reggae entertainers and promoters based out of New Delhi. They operate in a traditional Jamaican sound system style with one DJ and two MC\'s.\r\n\r\nComing together for their love of reggae music in New Delhi in early 2009, the Rajahs have been introducing the Indian masses to an eclectic mix of roots reggae, dub, lovers rock, ska and dancehall. They frequently perform in New Delhi and have also played in Mumbai, Pune, Bangalore, Chennai, Goa and Manali. International performances in the last 2 years include Peru, Panama and New York City. They were recently nominated for the Best International Group award at the British Reggae Industry Awards (2012) alongside illustrious Jamaican artists such as Toots & the Maytals, Mighty Diamonds and Third World.\r\n\r\nKnown for their energetic live performances, the Rajahs hope to release their first single and music video in 2012. They are dedicated to spreading the positive, conscious message of reggae music across India. The movement is in full effect!','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1616-reggae-rajahs',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-10-08 05:12:23',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-15 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','reggae-rajahs-at-cloud9',1,NULL),(480,'The Last Puff','The Last Puff experiments and jams with a diversity of genres; psychedelic rock, goth, grunge, metal and even jazz all whilst it exhales a peculiar brand of stupefying stoner rock rarely found in India.\r\n\r\nThe group has performed live at the January 2012 Rolling Stone Jack Daniels Annual Rock Awards show and featured in the UK Guardian as well as local mainstream radio channel Hit 95FM. A band that could have come out of the heartland of USA, they could fit in seamlessly with the production output of supergroup creators such as Butch Vig and Steve Albini.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2319-the-last-puff',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-20 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','the-last-puff',1,NULL),(481,'Suckafish P. Jones','For its latest edition, Imported Go(o)ds presents Suckafish P. Jones, a producer, performer and nomadic audio assault unit from Australia. Based in Barcelona, he\'s a member of the Banana Empire family alongside Cardopusher, Nehuen and Pacheko.\r\n\r\nHis style is wild, fusing the bass heavy sensibilities of sound system culture with tropical electronics and savage beatsmithery. He fuses elements of UK bass, hip-hop, cumbia and international obscura splinter throughout his borderless, high octane sound. One thing is always sure; the results will surprise, delight and above all, vibrate.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2318-imported-goods-suckafish-p-jones',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-15 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','suckafish-p-jones',1,NULL),(482,'Vasuda Sharma & Space','Vasuda Sharma is one of Indias few one-woman electro-acoustic live acts.\r\n\r\nFamed for her use of the loop station where she fuses beat boxing, live instrumentation, Indian and Western classical influences, Sharma makes her own music live and sings compositions over it. A talent discovered from Delhi on an all-India level, last year Sharma won an online contest held by Stuttgart-based company Music2deal to represent India in the 2010 Popkomm Festival held in Berlin, Germany.\r\n\r\nIts a wonderful initiative taken up by Music2Deal to promote independent artists. They sure brought about a dramatic change in my life and I really hope they continue to promote indie music in India. This was a splendid opportunity for me, a testing ground for my music, and Im glad I could live up to all those expectations. - Vasuda Sharma\r\n\r\nA true grassroot talent.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nSpace is a journey where musicians from various parts of the world keep boarding and sharing their human experiences through musical conversations. Using unassuming objects such as a Tibetan prayer bowl, ghungroos and many other street percussive instruments, the band creates a multi-harmonic and whole sound.\r\n\r\nSpace plays a subtle mix of electro-fusion pop, singing in 7 languages: hindi, english, bengali, sanskrit, punjabi, an imaginary language, and some tribal sounds too.\r\n\r\nEntry: Rs 300','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2379-vasuda-sharma-space',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-11 13:12:20',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-20 21:30:00','2012-09-20 23:00:00','vasuda-sharma-space',1,NULL),(483,'WILD CITY DJ & DJ SU-REAL (DER ZEITGEIST)','After a brief but spirited back-to-back jam session at T.L.R. a few months back, two of Delhis most exciting underground DJs finally set a date for the official showdown. As Wild City DJ heads up Wild City, one of Indias leading music websites electronic dance music, and DJ Su Real represents Imported Go(o)ds, the Delhi-based website featuring Global Bass, both are avid collectors of dance music from around the world.\r\n\r\nThis night promises to introduce New Delhi to the Zeitgeist of dance music - the latest bangers and underground sensations from around the world, presented in a rare format for Indian dancefloors: the back-to-back session.\r\n\r\nSimilar to the soundclash format, both DJs take turns playing just 1 or 2 tracks at a time, however, in the back-to-back session the DJs mix between each other in a collaborative effort to keep the energy level rising.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2320-wild-city-dj-dj-sureal-der-zeitgeist',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-22 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','wild-city-dj-dj-su-real-der-zeitgeist',1,NULL),(484,'Booka Shade','In charge of their own production company and studio for the last 15 years, they have applied their wide range of talents not only to the realm of electronic music, but also a large number of other media productions. After two early 90s synth pop album releases and a number of live tours, they switched their attention to club projects for established labels such as R&S, Harthouse and Tommy Boy. It was their early incarnation of Booka Shade on the illustrious Dutch label Touch which hit the zeitgeist and triggered excitement and enthusiasm in clubs all across Europe.\r\n\r\nTogether with old friends Patrick Bodmer and Philipp Jung a.k.a M.A.N.D.Y and publisher Thomas Koch a.k.a DJ T, they launched their very own label Get Physical, in 2002. After the build up and promotion of label artists M.A.N.D.Y, DJ T, Sunsetpeople and Chelonis R. Jones, in 2004, the duo took out time to pursue their own solo careers once again.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2367-booka-shade',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-23 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','booka-shade',1,NULL),(485,'Booka Shade','Booka Shade is the duo of Walter Merziger and Arno Kammermeier.\r\n\r\nIn charge of their own production company and studio for the last 15 years, they have applied their wide range of talents not only to the realm of electronic music, but also a large number of other media productions. After two early 90s synth pop album releases and a number of live tours, they switched their attention to club projects for established labels such as R&S, Harthouse and Tommy Boy. It was their early incarnation of Booka Shade on the illustrious Dutch label Touch which hit the zeitgeist and triggered excitement and enthusiasm in clubs all across Europe.\r\n\r\nTogether with old friends Patrick Bodmer and Philipp Jung a.k.a M.A.N.D.Y and publisher Thomas Koch a.k.a DJ T, they launched their very own label Get Physical, in 2002. After the build up and promotion of label artists M.A.N.D.Y, DJ T, Sunsetpeople and Chelonis R. Jones, in 2004, the duo took out time to pursue their own solo careers once again.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2369-booka-shade',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-26 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','booka-shade-1',1,NULL),(486,'Papon & The East India Company at Blue Frog','As a talented offspring of illustrious parents in the arena of Assamese music, he is not the only one. Yet, Angaraag Mahanta, son of singers Khagen Mahanta and Archana Mahanta, has managed to create a separate identity with his debut album Jonaki Raati, which recently hit the stalls in Assam. Papon Papon(Angaraag Mahanta) singer. composer, programmer, producer-born in assam to set of brilliant musicians, was introduced to music and its intricacies in his early childhood. His mother ARCHANA MAHNATA and father KHAGEN MAHANTA are two very popular and respected musicians of the region. Naturally, music has been there in his veins, his pulse as well as his ears since he was born. BOrn in the environment of music and musical performances his initiantion into music happened at an age when most people learn to talk or walk. Inspired by the wide array of sound that he has been exposed to from the traditional Vaishnavite devotional songs of Assam to new-age electronica, Papons music is new and free. Free to be confined by any genre and new to be identified with anything that already exists. His initial training has been in Indian classical and traditional music (devotional and folk) from Assam a region in the north eastern corner of India, sharing its borders and culture with the very oriental - Bhutan, China, Myanmar and Bangladesh. Papons boundary-free renditions have definite traces of pentatonic Mongoloid notes, the soul searing lyrical river songs, the rhythmic spring songs, the spiritual devotional songs, restrained Indian classical and the smooth-as-mature-wine ghazals. His innovative experiments are rich with ambient electronica, acoustic folk, electro ghazals, new-age, Ind-classical sounds. papon had released his first album \'jonaaki raati\' in assamese.- the language he was born to and is working on his hindi album. Lately he is doing vocal jams with MIdiVal punditz and with Susmit Sen of INDIAN OCEAN\'. He has recently completed the back ground score for the film.... Papon has been invited to New Zealand for the Crossings festival, where some of the finest and established New Zealand jazz artists from the band Onomatopoeia will Accompaning him on his songs from his forthcoming hindi album. Also playing with him will be one of the biggest electonica musician Rhian Sheehan. \"In \'Jonaki Raati\' each one of the eight numbers is fresh both in content and rendition. Angaraag seems to be completely uninfluenced by his illustrious parents. Another significant aspect of the album Jonaaki Raati is that at no moment the singer uses tricky notes or complex musical structure,which could have overpowered the touchy lyrics. Angaraag has clearly moved deeper and touched the very essence of the lyrics.This undoubtedly is a rare piece in the contemporary Assamese modern song scenario. Angaraag indeed has a long musical sojourn to undertake. All he needs is to maintain his own concept and style of rendition.....\"..The Telegraph. Angaraag Mahanta\'s Junaki Raati Currently Anagraag has started a new band named \"East India Company\" along eight other talented musicians around various corners of India. The band is concentrating on a new blend of traditional and folk music, which is already able make a mark to the audiences across the world.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2377-papon',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-10-08 02:18:57',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-26 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','papon-the-east-india-company-at-blue-frog',1,NULL),(487,'RED Mawkin','','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1924-red-mawkin',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-27 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','red-mawkin',1,NULL),(488,'Drift The Trio','One of the busiest young jazz outfits in the country, Drift is a Bebop and contemporary Jazz trio based out of New Delhi with over three hundred gigs and counting. The band plays an eclectic mix and fusion of classical jazz inspired by and including artists such as John Coltrane, Miles Davis and Dave Brubeck, yet mixed with modern sensibilities from the likes of Joshua Redman and Chris Potter.\r\n\r\nThe band is led by Drummer Reuben Narain who is an alumni of the Berklee School of Music, Boston; On guitars there is Pranai Gurung, director and founder of the Delhi based, Blue Notes Academy. Sahil Warsi on double bass is the city\'s youngest double bassist.\r\n\r\nEach member of the band is independently established within the circuit and has spent time abroad and domestically collaborating with other musicians.\r\n','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1244-drift-the-trio',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-29 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','drift-the-trio',1,NULL),(489,'TEDDY BOY KILL & HASHBACK HASHISH (DER AUTOBAHN)','One of Germanys most esteemed cultural outputs is of course techno, whose propulsive, driving rhythms were inspired by the rhythms of driving on the Autobahn, the fastest highway in the world cutting right through the heartlands of Germany.\r\n\r\nTwo of New Delhis leading \'EDM\' acts, Teddy Boy Kill and Hasback Hashish, have both been influenced by German electronic music and helped to popularise the sound in India. Its only appropriate that they join forces to explore this territory with an explosive techno-fueled joyride for Oktoberfest!','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2321-teddy-boy-kill-hashback-hashish-der-autobahn',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-29 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','teddy-boy-kill-hashback-hashish-der-autobahn',1,NULL),(490,'Bryan and the Bandits','At the nucleus of Bryan and the Bandits is the passion for Latin music. Distinct, seasoned, pure blooded musicians have come together to form this spectacular ensemble to innovate and create this passionate, uplifting, soul thumping and exciting venture. The musical ambience Bryan and the Bandits create draws dancers and even the rhythmically challenged to the dance floor. The versatility of the band allows them to \"latinise\" any type of music by combining traditional Latin music with any genre.\r\n\r\nTheir fantastic repertoire consists of bossa lounge, Latin funk, Brazilian lounge and Latin jazz versions of songs written in English and Spanish. The group features Bryan Furtado (vocals), Le Thu (Flamenco guitar), Fakhroddin Ghaffari (percussions), Abhishek Mangla (bass), Reuben Narain (drums) and Anil Chawla (Keyboards).\r\n\r\nImage Credit: Rohit Lal Photography','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2322-bryan-the-bandits',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-10-05 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','bryan-and-the-bandits',1,NULL),(491,'The Politik','The Politik is a band consisting of five huge Coldplay fans and deliver an energetic and authentic live show. Groove to the music as they play some of the best Coldplay songs like Yellow, Trouble, Viva la Vida and many more. All the Coldplay fans, gear up as the band pays tribute to the legends, bringing them back in their full glory. Watch as The Scientists, with Green Eyes, Fix You\r\n\r\nThe band aims to bring the music and the vibe of a Coldplay show to venues across India by putting together experienced musicians from top acts in New Delhi.','','','','http://www.hardrockindiablog.com/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-08-30 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','the-politik',1,NULL),(492,'Indigo Children Single Release Tour','','','','','Wild City',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-11 12:03:08',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-27 20:00:00','2012-09-27 23:00:00','indigo-children-single-release-tour-2',1,NULL),(493,'TRIBUTE TO NIRVANA','The Nirvana tribute band will pay homage to the last great alternative rock band that changed the sound of music. The members of this band have all played in bands that have covered a Nirvana tune or two in their time. This will be the first time that the group comes together and features vocalists that have definitely been impacted by the great songbook Nirvana left behind.\r\n\r\nExpect a wall of sound and tunes that shaped generations and spawned an army of clones.\r\n\r\nLine-up\r\nDenzil M: Guitar\r\nSonu S: Bass\r\nVina