NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-09 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','house-of-floyd',1,NULL),(512,'Avril Q.','A Mangalorean first based in Mumbai and now in Bangalore. Avril Q started her singing career in Kinder Garden and has developed the raw art of singing to become one of the Indias leading vocalists. \r\nHer priceless voice has graced Princess Ann from UK and many VIP functions in India and abroad singing in 5 languages. \r\n\r\nAvril Q is one of the few to sing in English or Hindi for all  genres; Rock; Jazz; Blues; Classical; Hip Hop; Retro; Disco; Classic and the latest hits from Hollywood or Bollywood; Electro and Trance or her own originals.Performances are exhilarating whether mc or with live band, acoustic guitar, piano, live DJ or solo, adding the variety to the event that only Avril Q can provide through the different genres and languages she performs. Avril Q is a past winner of All India Bits Pilani Rock Fest, having fronted many famous bands such as Gangammas Pleasure, Pulse,  and AQ Project, performed solo, with acoustic guitar, dancers and live DJ with acoustic guitar. Avril Q has over 600 events including  opening for Inner Circle to her credit with a single and album release and is seldom far from the attention of TV, radio and print, whether in Mumbai, Bangalore and Chennai.\r\n\r\nAvril Q trained in Western and Indian Classical Music, theatre and dance, has completed work for the film, Jugaari with fantastic reviews in Bangalore and the film industry. Avril has the distinction of being the first female Indian artist to have a single video release aired on VH1 as well as other music film channels and radio.\r\nYou can hear her voice in many advertisements and now is composing and writing lyrics for her own brand of electro, trance and acoustic music. \r\nAvril Q is variety and there seems to be no limit to this petite frame with a huge voice, fantastic attitude and ever lasting energy.','','','','Hard Rock',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-09-06 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','avril-q',1,NULL),(513,'MICHAEL JACKSON TRIBUTE: THE KING OF POP CONTINUES TO THRILL','','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1974-michael-jackson-tribute-the-king-of-pop-continues-to-thrill',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-06 07:27:33','2012-09-06 07:27:33',0,'','','','2012-06-23 02:05:00','1970-01-01 05:35:00','michael-jackson-tribute-the-king-of-pop-continues-to-thrill',1,NULL),(514,'Gig Week','Running in New Delhi from September 2-8, The Gig Week is an annual music summit which aims to provide independent bands and artists a platform to showcase themselves alongside more established acts from across the country.\r\n\r\nFull line-up and venue details have now been announced for the week long festivities taking place in a different venue on each night. Excitingly, as the summit grows and evolves, its been opening doors for more unheard bands, giving them the chance to play alongside the likes of Cyanide, Dualist Inquiry and Junkyard Groove of many.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2414-the-gig-week-cyanide-mojojojo-more',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-07 10:52:19','2012-09-07 10:57:30',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','gig-week',2,NULL),(515,'Gig Week','','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2414-the-gig-week-cyanide-mojojojo-more',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-07 10:58:16','2012-09-07 10:58:16',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','gig-week-1',2,NULL),(516,'Gig Week','','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2414-the-gig-week-cyanide-mojojojo-more',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-07 11:00:08','2012-09-07 11:00:08',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','gig-week-2',2,NULL),(517,'SUN DOWNER III [ELECTRO SUFI EDITION] NASHA LIVE!','','','','','https://www.facebook.com/events/202830656514376/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-07 11:06:0