y and speed. Ambassadors for Indian percussion, Talavya has shared the stage with artists such as Mickey Hart (of Grateful Dead), Shakura S\'Aida, Sidi Toure and Cuban Fire. The group brings a dynamism to the classical art of tabla, infusing it with the power of a rock drummer while respecting its ethos and traditions. Playing in perfect synchronization, the ensemble distills the spirit and demonstrates how the drum is truly capable of anything. A rhythmic journey not to be missed.','','http://www.facebook.com/events/102817516540570/','','http://www.facebook.com/events/102817516540570/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 12:19:07','2012-09-18 12:19:07',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-21 21:15:00','2012-09-21 23:30:00','talavya-at-opus',1,NULL),(616,'Arif Lohar at Rhino','Be the first to follow Arif Lohar at Rhino!','','','','http://nh7.in/gigs/arif-lohar-at-rhino/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 12:25:58','2012-09-18 12:25:58',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-21 21:00:00','2012-09-21 23:30:00','arif-lohar-at-rhino',1,NULL),(617,'Spartaque, Ankytrixx at Blue Frog','One of the biggest names in Techno, who played the closing set on Day 2 of Sunburn 2011 on the largest stage, is smashing a club tour along side one of the biggest DJs of the Indian Subcontinent. Mega night! ','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/spartaque-ankytrixx','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/spartaque-ankytrixx',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 12:37:36','2012-09-18 12:37:36',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-21 22:30:00','2012-09-22 01:30:00','spartaque-ankytrixx-at-blue-frog',1,NULL),(618,'DJ Paroma at Jynxx','','','http://www.facebook.com/DJPAROMAOFFICIAL','','http://www.facebook.com/DJPAROMAOFFICIAL',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 12:44:44','2012-09-18 12:44:44',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-22 20:00:00','2012-09-22 23:00:00','dj-paroma-at-jynxx',1,NULL),(619,'Spartaque, Ankytrixx at Blue Frog','One of the biggest names in Techno, who played the closing set on Day 2 of Sunburn 2011 on the largest stage, is smashing a club tour along side one of the biggest DJs of the Indian Subcontinent. Mega night! ','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/spartaque-ankytrixx-0','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/spartaque-ankytrixx-0',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 12:52:00','2012-09-18 12:52:00',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-22 22:30:00','2012-09-23 01:30:00','spartaque-ankytrixx-at-blue-frog-1',1,NULL),(620,'Live from The Console - Playing for Change Day ','Last year, Live from The Console partnered with the Playing for Change Foundation to celebrate the global movement by hosting Playing for Change Day in Mumbai.\r\n\r\nThis year, we support the cause with some great live music at the Rowson\'s Reserve Smooth Spaces, Mehboob Studio.\r\n\r\nPlaying For Change (PFC) is an extraordinary effort uniting musicians and vocalists from diverse parts of the world. Those who have experienced Playing For Change are mesmerized by its ability to inspire, connect and bring peace to the world through music.\r\n\r\nMore here: http://playingforchange.com/\r\n\r\nProceeds from this event will go towards Playing for Change Foundation. \r\n\r\nTelevision Partner: 9XO \r\n\r\nLine Up:\r\n\r\n------------\r\n\r\n7:00 PM\r\nOn The Road with the Playing For Change Band (Documentary)\r\n\r\nThe global music collective Playing For Change presents their first-ever live recording; featuring performances from their highly successful 2009 world tour! Guest performers on this project include Ziggy Marley & Toots Hibbert. This documentary takes you behind the scenes as music history is created\r\n\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pJQjY2yRpPs\r\n\r\nCourtesy: Universal Music Group India\r\n\r\n------------\r\n\r\n8:30 pm : Rachel Varghese \r\n\r\nRachels music is an amalgamation of all her musical influences & life experiences. She began to write her own music about 2 years ago. \r\n\r\nHer two very good and extremely talented friends Yohan Marshall on percussion, guitar & vocals and Samir Karnik on guitar form the rest of her band and have helped her tremendously in finding her sound. Driven by raw emotion, soul and passion for music she hopes all who listen to her music can find a way to make it their own!\r\n\r\n------------\r\n\r\n9:15 pm: Vivek Rajagopalan (Carnatic, electronica, world)\r\n\r\nCombining Carnatic, Hindustani, Jazz, Folk, Electronic and Drum-n-Bass, Vivek Rajagopalans music creates rippling sound scapes that are edgy as much as international; and if world music today is a melting pot of cultures & genres, then Vivek\'s music is a drop of spicy red curry in the concoction.\r\n\r\nhttp://vivekrajagopalan.com/\r\n\r\n-----------\r\n\r\n10:15 pm: Ashu presents \'Vivienne Pocha\' (soul, funk & pop) \r\n\r\nVivienne Pocha, the indisputable Diva of the Indian music scene is all set to debut her new album, Inside My Head. The collaboration between a fantastic singer and an amazing songwriter, Ashu Phatak, the album was completed in just 3 short weeks! Written and produced by Ashu, \'Inside My Head\' takes you on a tour of Viviennes life as she transforms herself from a vocalist to an artist. The show also features a star studded line-up of musicians: Adrian D\'souza, Ashu Phatak, Kenny Rebello, Ramon Ibrahim and Vinay Lobo','','http://www.facebook.com/events/220608108067442/','','http://www.facebook.com/events/220608108067442/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 13:18:00','2012-09-18 13:18:00',0,'[\"http:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/livefromtheconsole\\r\",\"http:\\/\\/www.twitter.com\\/consoletweets\\r\",\"http:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/livefromtheconsole\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-22 18:30:00','2012-09-22 22:30:00','live-from-the-console-playing-for-change-day',1,NULL),(621,'Ganesh Talkies at Someplace Else',':::::::::::: \"ARRANGED MARRIAGE\" by GANESH TALKIES :::::::::::\r\n\r\n\r\nGanesh Talkies - feat. Suyasha (singer-songwriter, guitars), Ronodeep (guitars, backing vocals), Nabarun (keys, backing vocals), Roheet (bass, whistles) and Arka (drums, percussions) are back with yet another accoustic set to entrall