ULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 14:38:17','2012-09-18 14:38:17',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-20 20:00:00','2012-09-20 23:00:00','live-gig-one-nite-stand-performing-at-hrc-bengaluru-on-20th-sep-2012',1,NULL),(628,'Tuesday conversations featuring By2 Blues Live at CounterCulture','\"The blues is the roots, the rest is the fruits.\"  Willie Dixon\r\n\r\nBy2Blues is one of the few acoustic duos in India that sings and presents the blues in its simplest format. Its just two musicians  Ananth Menon and Vasudev Prabhu, with an abiding passion for a genre of music that is deeply and subliminally connected to almost every form of Western music that one hears today. \r\n\r\nA classic guitar-harmonica duo, Ananth and Dev have set out to pay their tribute to the blues, in many ways the haiku of the West, in their own home-grown style. Ananth lays down the gritty grooves with his guitar and tops it with a voice that is like fine whisky  smooth, mellow and welcome. Over this potent combination, the wailing harmonica dances like country rain on a tiled roof drizzling steadily and gently, and bursting into a fierce downpour at times.\r\n\r\nBy2Blues is a Bangalore-based duo influenced as much by the classic post-war era music as by other genres like R&B, Country Blues, Soul, Blues-rock, Gospel, Funk and Rock n Roll. Naturally, in their performances one hears a spirited amalgam of all these genres as they engage the audience in stories of love won or lost, struggles and triumphs, hoodoo and miracles, honesty and skullduggery, bonhomie and despair because thats what life is all about.\r\n\r\nBy2Blues works best in a setting that is personal and mature; Ananth and Dev have performed at several festivals individually and as a band, as well as at popular watering holes in Bangalore. Although a young band (comprising seasoned musicians) By2Blues is fast garnering a fan base that includes curious 17 year olds, appreciative 70 year olds, corporate execs with an evolved taste in music and just about anyone whod like to hit the pause button for a while, and sit back for some meaningful, easy-on-the-ears, uncluttered entertainment in the middle of a hectic life.','','http://www.facebook.com/events/272409929543606/','','http://www.facebook.com/events/272409929543606/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 14:47:22','2012-09-18 14:47:22',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-18 20:30:00','2012-09-18 23:00:00','tuesday-conversations-featuring-by2-blues-live-at-counterculture',1,NULL),(629,'UNK Album Launch Tour @Cafe Out of The Box Public Event ','	UNK: The Radha Thomas Ensemble\r\n\r\nTake a pinch of straight-ahead jazz, toss in a spoonful of blues and then sprinkle a generous helping of Indian music, season with hip-hop, Latin music and rhythms from Africa. Shake, dont stir. Voila, you have UNK, out of Bangalore, one of the countrys most original and dynamic bands featuring musicians from all over the globe.\r\n\r\nUNK is \r\n\r\nRadha Thomas vocals\r\nAman Mahajan keyboards\r\nMatt Littlewood saxophones\r\nRamjee Chandran guitar\r\nSuresh Bascara drums\r\nMishko Mba bass guitars\r\n\r\nCelebrating UNKs one-year anniversary is a soon-to-be released album entitled I Only Have Eyes For You.\r\n\r\nIts a great line-up and the band has a chemistry thats electric, explains Thomas.','','http://www.facebook.com/events/361141113965691/','','http://www.facebook.com/events/361141113965691/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 14:50:34','2012-09-18 14:50:34',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-19 21:00:00','2012-09-19 23:00:00','unk-album-launch-tour-cafe-out-of-the-box-public-event',1,NULL),(630,'Ditty & Mark at T.L.R. Cafe','Ditty & Mark bring their brand of Jazz, R&B and Latin to T.L.R. Cafe for the Bacardi NH7 Weekender Pre-Party.\r\n\r\nEntry: Free\r\n\r\nDitty & Mark are a guitar-vocal duo that have already been featured on the Tehelka Music Project, the Escape Festival, Clonefest, BlueFROG, and currently have their single Moonlighters playing on radio station HIT95 FM. \r\n\r\nTheirs is a sound that is seldom heard in this city. Jazz, R&B and Latin influences are combined to create an eminently listenable sound. Mark\'s understated fingerstyle guitar work plays a perfect foil to Aditi\'s soulful vocals and uncomplicated trumpet lines. \r\nListen to their music here: http://soundcloud.com/ditty-and-mark','','http://www.facebook.com/events/498615260158419/','','http://www.facebook.com/events/498615260158419/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 14:52:07','2012-09-18 14:52:07',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-19 21:00:00','2012-09-19 23:30:00','ditty-mark-at-tlr-cafe',1,NULL),(631,'Tantra & Tuborg Present.... DJ PAROMA! ','Tantra & Tuborg present... DJ Paroma from Mumbai!\r\n:: Friday SEP 21 ::\r\n\r\nfor details call Rajnish/ Neha at 40049000\r\n--\r\n\r\nDJ Paroma is a 24 year old, a complete clubbing soul, a Hip Hop hustler, a night life lover, a bling freak crazy from Mumbai. She can play almost every genre of music imaginable, but specializes in commercial house and club music.','','http://www.facebook.com/events/376960519039365/','','http://www.facebook.com/events/376960519039365/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 14:57:51','2012-09-18 14:57:51',0,'[\"\"]','[\"Rajnish\\/ Neha at 40049000\"]','','2012-09-21 20:00:00','2012-09-21 23:45:00','tantra-tuborg-present-dj-paroma',1,NULL),(632,'Tantra & Budweiser present.... DJane Kekka',':::International Celebrity Dj::: and \'Playmate\' DJ KEKKA is spinning live in Tantra Saturday SEP 22nd!! \r\n\r\nFor details call Rajnish/ Neha at 40049000\r\n~Club rules apply\r\n\r\n--\r\nBiography\r\nKekka\'s remix for Jerry Ropero & Clubworxx \"Get Down Reloaded\" ranked #1 DJTUNES & BEATPORT DANCE CHARTS in July 2011.\r\nReleased by INTERLABEL and CLUBLAND RECORDS Germany\r\n\r\nDJane Kekka with real name Francisca was exposed to music and to see and live what it means to be a DJ from an early age. Her father, a famous senior DJ of Hungarian nightlife (DJ BANDERAS) introduced her to all kinds of music and taught her how to spin vinyls when she was still a teenager and most of all to understand that being a DJ means more than just to blend two tracks together. In other words, Kekka grew up with music and developed a deep love and huge understanding about music and the essentials and techniques of professional Djing.\r\n\r\nShe would describe herself as being pierced by rhythm all over her body!\r\n\r\nStarting out as a professional model in 2005, she quickly made her way into the international model scene and was soon glancing from several covers of the most important magazines and fashion lectures. Becoming PLAYMATE of the year 2006 for the Hungarian Playboy and 2007 for the Italian issue of the infamous mag are considered as milestones of her modeling career.\r\n\r\nSoon bored by the monotony of \"just\" being a model, where she achieved a lot already, she felt like looking for another aim in entertainment and decided to follow her father\'s footsteps in becoming a DJ. 2009 and 2010 Djane Kekka was booked in almost every club in Hungary and Italy and soon invited to perform abroad.\r\n\r\nTouring the US with stops in New York, Las Vegas, Miami and Boston was a great experience in her young career and more international appearances came soon. Joining the roster of an all female agency which specializes in the exciting and ever growing Asian market-- led her to great gigs in Dubai, Indonesia, Vietnam, Jordan, Pakistan, Syria, Lebanon, just to name a few.\r\n\r\nKekka was touring official FASHION TV Asia gigs and invited to debut her show for grand openings of high profile Asian clubs. Recently Djane Kekka toured an all summer tour in Hungary and Spain again and is to guest in the South of Germany.\r\n\r\nProducing music by herself, she expresses that her definition of House and Electro music is one of the greatest things to do for her. Delivering remixes for several artists in 2011 plus the release of her own track/remixes which ranked high at all download portals just goes to show that there is much potential and you can be sure to hear much more from this promising talent.\r\n\r\nHer sets essence is a fine blend of vocal-based Electro and Tech House, sometimes twisted with a massive bassline close to Progressive.','','http://www.facebook.com/events/470296823014412/','','http://www.facebook.com/events/470296823014412/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 15:05:30','2012-09-18 15:05:30',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-18 20:00:00','2012-09-18 23:45:00','tantra-budweiser-present-djane-kekka',1,NULL),(633,'Ma Faiza at Blue Frog','Born in Africa, Ma Faiza is one of the busiest and most successful DJs in India. Pushing the psychedelic trance music scene for close to two decades now, she commands an enviable position within Indias otherwise male-dominated EDM circuit. Based out of Pune, this fierce personality is also a successful artist, producer and writer for various international and Indian publications','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/ma-faiza','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/ma-faiza',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 16:11:31','2012-09-18 16:11:32',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-27 22:30:00','2012-09-28 01:30:00','ma-faiza-at-blue-frog',1,NULL),(634,'Sanjay Divecha at Blue Frog','Sanjay Divecha explores Indo-centric folk traditions; Hindustani and Carnatic with the music of Brazil, Africa and the Americas all with acoustic sensibilities. His quartet performs music that traverses borders and genres all the while resonating close to the heartland. Sanjays experience of over 15 years; most of them being in L.A, has resulted in him studying a wide range of music while performing in his unique and distinctive style. \r\n\r\nHis album Full Circle was released to enthusiastic responses and featured thematic, multifaceted compositions. His session credits include Angelique Kidjo, Dave Weckl, Sambaguru and Dumazz among many others. More recently, Sanjay has been exploring the acoustic guitar and a breadth of orchestration involving a wide variety of engaging rhythms and melodies. This concert will feature new music created with a palette of global colours, re-orchestrated older material and the players themselves, who weave their way through a free canvas, hinting at a global community and a harmonically meaningful sound.','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/sanjay-divecha','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/sanjay-divecha',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 16:18:03','2012-09-18 16:20:50',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-03 22:00:00','2012-10-03 23:30:00','sanjay-divecha-at-blue-frog',1,NULL),(635,'Window Seat at Blue Frog','Window Seat is a band that has booked its own musical tickets; sounds influenced by afro beat, funk and jazz with an altogether melodic and improvisational outlook make this band unique. The focus is on playing for the music.','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/window-seat','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/window-seat',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 16:19:44','2012-10-09 11:15:28',328,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-09 22:00:00','2012-10-09 23:30:00','window-seat-at-blue-frog',1,NULL),(636,'Sunburn Pre Party with Pearl & Nikhil Chinapa','The Sunburn Festival finally hits Delhi! Dont miss the first Pre-Party of Sunburn in your city!','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/sunburn-pre-party-pearl-nikhil-chinapa','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/sunburn-pre-party-pearl-nikhil-chinapa',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 16:30:56','2012-09-18 16:30:56',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-21 22:30:00','2012-09-22 01:30:00','sunburn-pre-party-with-pearl-nikhil-chinapa',1,NULL),(637,'Ladies Night with DJ Leon Russell','Indian DJ/ Producer/Label Owner Leon Russell was born in 1984 in the city of Mumbai. Music runs in his blood, as from a very young age he was treated to the likes of classic rock legends such as Deep Purple, Iron Butterfly, Scorpions, Queen, CCR and The Steve Miller Band. The real reason for his passion for music was his father who is also a musician. He got his first dose of electronic dance music in the year 1998, when techno parties were a rage in Mumbai. He started playing music at an early age of fifteen.','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/ladies-night-dj-leon-russell-1','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/ladies-night-dj-leon-russell-1',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 16:32:56','2012-09-18 16:32:56',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-26 22:30:00','2012-09-27 01:30:00','ladies-night-with-dj-leon-russell-2',1,NULL),(638,'Wippenberg','Genre-warping electronic music adventurer Wippenberg (a.k.a. Olaf Dieckmann) has been supplying the worlds dancefloors with audio titans for close to 15 years. Most recently he is renowned for his neoclassical- anthems Chakalaka and \"Pong, later receiving IDMA 2010 nomination as Best Progressive House Track alongside David Guetta and Deadmau5. Wippenbergs music crosses the multiple boundaries of house, electro, trance and techno. \r\n\r\nThis unique composite electronic blend is now spun by the widest imaginable cross-section of DJs. Hes been championed by Eric Prydz, Angelo, Ingrosso & Axwell (also known as the Swedish House Mafia), and also by Tisto, Armin Van Buuren and David Guetta. This casts Wippenberg as one of, if not, the most diverse DJ/producer in todays EDM universe.','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/wippenberg-0','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/wippenberg-0',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 16:37:02','2012-09-18 16:37:02',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-29 22:30:00','2012-09-30 01:30:00','wippenberg-2',1,NULL),(639,'Ska Ska Ska!  at Blue Frog','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/ska-ska-ska','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/ska-ska-ska',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-18 16:45:29','2012-10-06 23:38:55',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-28 22:30:00','2012-09-29 01:30:00','ska-ska-ska-at-blue-frog',1,NULL),(640,'Avril Quadros-TRIBUTE TO MADONNA','Avril is a versatile singer who is comfortable with many kinds of genres.\r\n\r\nWatch her pay tribute to the DIVA OF MUSIC-MADONNA','','http://www.facebook.com/HardRockMumbai/app_191034970944620','','http://www.facebook.com/HardRockMumbai/app_191034970944