ve Seaman, Nic Fanciulli, Paolo Mojo and Cari Lekebusch while his live act, Jalebee Cartel, has shared headlining spots with the likes of The Chemical Brothers, The Prodigy and Modeselektor.\r\n\r\nABOUT JITTER\r\nIn 1998 he secured his first club residency in a premium nightclub in new delhi  his dynamic force and technical skills enabled him to give an much needed momentum to the underground clubbing scene in the capital city.Jayant is known for his timely selection coupled with elements from the wide repertoire of electronic dance, from progressive, breaks, trance, techno, minimal and Indian electronica, and creates a dreamily rhythmic liquid groove. In 2000, he joined forces with the Midival PunditZ and started playing for the famous Cyber Mehfil. This collaboration was a catalyst in his career, not only as a DJ, but as a music producer as well. With the help of the Punditz, Jayant polished his production skills to become the most sort after producer of the future. He has won numerous dj mixing competitions like DMC, Times Music war of the Djs, and holds a record no. of titles from the year 1998-2002. In later 2002, he was the first Indian Dj to perform live with a rock band, Orange Street, as a turntablist and was the electronic end of the band.\r\n\r\nABOUT KOHRA\r\nKohra is part of Indias new vanguard of intelligent dance music, for Madhav Shorey its always been about pushing boundaries in electronic music, and to stay true to myself, not to imitate or emulate. After being a co-founding member of Jalebee Cartel in 2005, he made his solo debut performance in 2007, has already played at clubs across India as well as at international festivals like Revelations (Dubai), Sonica (Italy) and Earthcore (Australia). His influence over the EDM industry in India just does not stop there, he has also founded Qila Records along with Gaurav Malaker, Now affiliated with and signed to Zenon Records (Australia) as their exclusive label Dj in India, Kohra plans to stay true to the collectives edgy, uncompromising philosophy while continuing to challenge his own musical limits and create new spaces within the revived minimal genre. As a DJ, he pushes the boundaries of intelligent dance music while filling discerning dance floors, that floor being the experimental stage at Sunburn this year!','','https://www.facebook.com/events/365526846859654/','','https://www.facebook.com/events/365526846859654/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-24 08:15:22','2012-09-27 15:00:29',0,'[\"For the latest updates, log on to:\\r\",\"www.sunburn.in\\r\",\"www.facebook.com\\/sunburnfestival\\r\",\"www.twitter.com\\/sunburnfestival\\r\",\"www.youtube.com\\/sunburnfestival\\r\",\"https:\\/\\/plus.google.com\\/107742139595064929380\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-28 08:15:00','2012-09-28 08:15:00','sunburn-noida-pre-party',1,NULL),(674,'ASH & ASHVIN @ SWIG','Ash Roy is one of the founding members of India\'s most prolific dance music act, Jalebee Cartel. Since its inception, Roy has been providing all vocal and percussive elements during their memorable live performances and has also steadily been creating music to add to the Cartel\'s cache of original productions. His career has long crossed the decade mark during which Roy\'s traveled across the continents touring with the band and solo, pre-Jalebee Cartel. They\'ve been basing themselves out of Europe every summer, to have equal footing in both sides of the globe. While Jalebee Cartel has shared headliner space with the likes of The Prodigy, Modeselektor and Carl Cox, he\'s also played with Sasha, Cari Lekebusch, Fergie and KaseyTaylor individually. It just keeps getting better and better for Ash Roy, and that\'s what reflects in his music.\r\n\r\nAshvin\'s intention is to make music a tool for emptying the mind with unpredictable and unusual sounds, and then fill the open space with the beauty of surrender through dance... A state of mind that takes you away from the safe space of the self to a consciousness where the tribe becomes aware of its existence.','','','','http://gigs.gigatools.com/user/unmuteagency',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-24 08:20:32','2012-09-24 08:20:32',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-28 20:00:00','2012-09-28 23:00:00','ash-ashvin-swig',1,NULL),(675,'Ashvin Mani Sharma @ Afraa','Ashvin\'s intention is to make music a tool for emptying the mind with unpredictable and unusual sounds, and then fill the open space with the beauty of surrender through dance... A state of mind that takes you away from the safe space of the self to a consciousness where the tribe becomes aware of its existence. To reaffirm that we are a bunch of freaks who listen to bizarre, crazy music that just somehow moves our soul to action... Calm chor is Indian and so is his music. It\'s dramatic and emotional like every Indian is at heart. Calm Chor is the Alter ego of Ashvin Mani Sharma who has been a part of the Indian underground music scene since 1995.','','','','http://gigs.gigatools.com/user/unmuteagency',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-24 08:32:40','2012-09-24 08:32:40',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-09-29 21:00:00','2012-09-29 23:30:00','ashvin-mani-sharma-afraa',1,NULL),(676,'MUZICFEST GOA 2012','FLYING IDEAS ENTERTAINMENT Presents\r\n\r\n?? MUZICFEST 2012?? \r\n\r\nWiTnEsS tHe BiGgEsT cEleBrAtIoN oF mUsIc\r\n\r\nMUZICFEST 2012, a Concept sheerly dedicated to the music lovers of goa and beyond, This Event is a Musical Festival bringing together 11 different Djs both National and International at one place. All that one can expect from it is Top of the line .One Massive Lineup, Head banging music and a Huge Setup,\r\n\r\nThis is as Big as it can be\r\n\r\n\r\nDate: 30th SEPTEMBER | 12 PM Onwards\r\n\r\nVenue: LA CALYPSO | BAGA | ENTER THROUGH THE SANDS\r\n\r\n\r\nOur STAR Djs\r\n\r\nARJUN VAGALE + ASH ROY\r\n(JALEBEE CARTEL)\r\n\r\nAdding to the Musical Mayhem are our very own Djs\r\n\r\nRINTON (DUBAI) \r\nJOEL\r\nRYAN NOGAR\r\nNAVIN\r\nJAY aka BRAINWASH\r\nPEPPY\r\nSU.EDITS\r\nURBAN TRIBE\r\nKIRAN\r\n','','https://www.f