FACEBOOK:\r\nhttp://www.facebook.com/pages/MAD-MAXX/306805104228?ref=search\r\n\r\nSOUNDCLOUD:\r\nhttp://soundcloud.com/mad-maxx\r\n\r\nI-TUNES:\r\nhttp://itunes.apple.com/us/artist/mad-maxx/id280157242?ign-mpt=uo%3D4 \r\n\r\nYOUTUBE:\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/user/MadMaxxMusic?feature=mhum\r\n\r\nTWITTER:\r\nhttp://twitter.com/#!/MadMaxxMusic\r\n\r\n\r\nANITA SHANTI, Bio-\r\nDJ Anita Shanti started performing and dancing since 1999 and in th\r\ne last few years has focused her energy into being a full time DJ. Since 2011 DJ Anita Shanti is part of Digital Om Productions. She performed in many parties in her native country Kazakhstan including open air festivals , Sicily(Italy), Nepal and even across cities in India like Goa, Delhi, Pune, Hyderabad, Guwahati, Kolkata, Bangalore, Pondicherry, Mumbai at clubs and venues like, Pebble, Bluefrog, Aurus, Urban, R&B club, 1Lounge, Aqua etc. And recently at the Universal Religion Festival -Nepal 2012. She plays house, minimal, electro, techno, prog/psyprog, full on, psy trance. Anita has an exceptional ability to mix different styles of music together and has a new trick up her sleeve every time. She has performed with artists and Djs like Zen-Mechanics, Robbie Romero, Ajja, Ital, Chicago, Ma Faiza and more.\r\n\r\nShe also performs impressive fire shows along with her Dj sets, festivals and at parties. Mixing her unique skills with dance, fire and Djing, she is a big hit at all events.\r\n\r\nHer sweet personality and charming good looks are only a teaser for her amazing stage presence and she makes crowds go wild with her electrifying energy. ','','http://www.facebook.com/events/475578272476835/','','http://www.facebook.com/events/475578272476835/',NULL,1,'2012-09-25 20:18:26','2012-10-07 16:44:07',27,'[\"\"]','[\"For Passes and info contact +91 9538 9999 40 \\/ 47\"]','','2012-10-21 15:00:00','2012-10-21 17:30:00','mad-maxx-at-pebble',1,NULL),(682,'Braindrop at Our Shack','Braindrop is a psytrance project of Sumith Suresh, from India.\r\n\r\nTraversing through many genres of music in the past decade ranging from instrumental, fusion, world music, breakbeats, acid house,techno, trance to name a few with short stints in fusion and metal bands, a craving for the most futuristic sounds evolved. The sounds are new age yet not missing the psychedelic touch. The rhythms are futuristic yet driving. The mood is mysterious yet energetic; demented but powerful. Combining varied elements of the never ending music spectrum, while turning the brooding depths of night to the remote signs of light, this sound has taken him to perform at numerous dancefloors across Dubai, India and Nepal. ','','','','http://gigs.gigatools.com/country/India',NULL,1,'2012-09-25 20:47:49','2012-10-07 16:49:53',28,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-19 08:50:00','2012-10-19 08:50:00','braindrop-at-our-shack',1,NULL),(683,'Arjun Vagale at Purple','Arjun Vagale is arguably one of the most in-demand DJs in India. As one of the countrys biggest EDM exports, he plays over 100 gigs a year, touring regularly in Europe and Asia, often spends his summers in the worlds techno Mecca, Berlin. A man with a true passion for underground music, which he relentlessly plays, produces and promotes. No wonder he was awarded 2011  2012s Best Techno DJ and DJ Of the Year and more recently topped the DJ Mag India Poll. He has played alongside such heavyweights as Fergie, Sasha, Fat Boy Slim, Dave Seaman, Nic Fanciulli, Paolo Mojo and Cari Lekebusch while his live act, Jalebee Cartel, has shared headlining spots with the likes of The Chemical Brothers, The Prodigy and Modeselektor. His knowledge and use of technology in the booth is second to none, often adding drum machines and samplers to create a uniquely raw, funk-laden techno set. It has been almost 10 years since Arjun, along with 3 friends, formed Indias biggest live act, Jalebee Cartel. With its genre-bending sets, the band has generated a huge buzz and has featured in DJ Mag, MixMag and Elles list of Rising Stars, and has even graced the cover of Rolling Stone, India.','','','','http://gigs.gigatools.com/user/ArjunVagale',NULL,1,'2012-09-25 21:13:06','2012-10-07 16:44:25',29,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-20 21:00:00','2012-10-20 23:30:00','arjun-vagale-at-purple',1,NULL),(684,'Protonica at Hilltop','PROTONICA are Piet Kaempfer and Ralf Dietze from Berlin (Germany). With Piet\'s intuition for harmonies as a skilled pianist and certified sound designer Ralf\'s feeling for propulsive grooves, Protonica deliver you their very own positive pulsing sound - a blend of psychedelic and progressive trance. The \"Refresh / Northern Storm EP\" from 2010 was certainly an important milestone and the breakthrough for the duo. In 2012 Protonica releases the second album \"Form Follows Function\" another masterpiece after their debut album \"Search\" from 2007.\r\n\r\nWith their energetic live sets Protonica have already contributed to making events a sucess all over the world, amongst others Universo Paralello (Brazil), Rainbow Serpent (Australia), Ozora Festival (Hungary), Fusion Festival (Germany), Ilo Festival (Mexico), Groove Attack (Israel) and Boom Festival (Portugal).\r\n\r\nRalf and Piet share extensive experience in DJing for more than a decade, too. Together they have also formed the progressive house/techno side project KAEMPFER & DIETZE.','','','','http://gigs.gigatools.com/user/Protonica',NULL,1,'2012-09-26 12:34:38','2012-10-07 16:44:13',32,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-21 12:35:00','2012-10-21 12:35:00','protonica-at-hilltop',1,NULL),(685,'OKTOBERFEST GOA 2012','Bullseye Entertainment created the concept of the Oktoberfest Goa to give people a real taste of the Bavarian Oktoberfest famous for its exceptional beer and food and for the extraordinary hospitality and excellent entertainment. It also provides the ideal setting for a fun gathering that offers good quality entertainment and a relaxing, joyous atmosphere.','','https://www.facebook.com/OktoberfestGoa?sk=wall','','https://www.facebook.com/OktoberfestGoa?sk=wall',NULL,1,'2012-09-26 15:00:36','2012-10-07 16:43:50',33,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-26 03:00:00','2012-10-28 03:00:00','oktoberfest-goa-2012',3,NULL),(686,'Marco Bailey at Renaissance','	\r\nMarco Bailey grew up in a small village in Belgium. Nothing much happened there really, but he did learn that one doesnt achieve much without working hard. He is a true hedonist but a workaholic as well. Marco loves to work hard and spin records as much as possible; sleeping is for later. Therefore, his colleagues know him for his no-nonsense & ass-kicking mentality. \r\n\r\nAt the age of 12, Marco wanted nothing more than to become a sportsman. Motocross and competitive cycling were his passions until injuries made it impossible to continue and Marco soon had a new obsession, music, then shortly after that DJing.\r\n\r\nHe started playing Funk, Hip Hop and Rock music, New Wave, Punk, Marco Bailey has been spinning everything and everywhere in the World ! Japan, Korea, China, Argentina , Brasil, Colombia, Mexico, whole europe etc etc ..there are not many countries of bailey was standing on the decks somewhere!','http://www.marcobailey.com/','','','http://www.marcobailey.com/',NULL,1,'2012-09-26 22:24:14','2012-10-07 16:43:29',35,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-26 10:15:00','2012-10-26 10:15:00','marco-bailey-at-renaissance',1,NULL),(687,'GO:MADras festival','The GO:MADras festival is an electronic music festival that happens every year by the beach in Chennai (India). Founded in 2009, this festival has seen three successful editions featuring top artists from across the globe, India\'s best talent, revolutionary production, mindblowing visuals with Chennai\'s scenic coastline as the backdrop. On the 27th and 28th of October 2012 the GO:Crew as they are popularly called will present the 4th Edition of this extremely popular event.','http://www.gomadras.in','http://www.facebook.com/thegomadrasfestival?sk=info','','http://www.facebook.com/thegomadrasfestival?sk=info',NULL,1,'2012-09-26 22:42:59','2012-10-07 16:43:15',36,'[\"go.madrasfestival@gmail.com\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-27 10:00:00','2012-10-28 17:00:00','gomadras-festival',3,NULL),(688,'DJ Simon Baring\'s India Tour','	\r\n2011 has been an incredible year for Simon. Its been 5 years since he first got behind a pair of decks and so much has been achieved in this short time. \r\n\r\nHe started out in December 2006 as an official DJ for Twisted Records whilst organizing massive events on behalf of the label and maintaining close ties with Nano Records and the Glade Festival who gave him his first work experiences in the industry. \r\n\r\n2011 has seen him release two tracks (Casanueva  Halloween & Simon Baring feat. AV8R - Athens to Athens) on Flow Records compilation Flutter (compiled by DJ Dovla). Another track (a collaboration with Mexican trance producer Tron) has been picked up by Echoes Records (Lish, Khainz, Magitman) for a techno progressive compilation in early 2012 and another one Simon Baring  Snowmachine is being signed to the newly reformed Digital Structures label under one of his techno heroes, Perfect Stranger, who will also be doing a remix of the track. \r\nHe has also been signed to Echoes Records for his techno progressive DJing after playing a few massive gigs in front of their artists in Brazil and Israel and being given the thumbs up by label manager and fellow DJ  Osh. \r\n\r\nBut it doesnt stop there! Simons productions are so varied in style and genre that its lead to him having a serious brainchild. The Twisted Disco. This is a product of everyone and everything that he has worked with, on and for, in the last 7 years. Its an all-encompassing super sub label that will release everything and anything that makes people move. No more genres, no more pidgeon holes, no more expectations. This is a return to music and djing in the purest form. ','','','','http://gigs.gigatools.com/country/India?page=2',NULL,1,'2012-09-27 14:39:00','2012-10-11 12:22:42',37,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-12-03 02:40:00','2012-12-03 02:40:00','dj-simon-barings-india-tour',1,NULL),(689,'Dj Giuseppe at Hilltop','Italian trance virtuosity Giuseppe Ottaviani is known as one of the most influential artists in Trance music. His distinctive sound, energetic live set and unique radio show are celebrated around the world. For over 10 years he\'s now part of Paul van Dyk\'s VANDIT Family, and after his highly successful debut album \'GO!\' in 2009, his fans are yearning for more. This summer, Giuseppe Ottaviani presents GO ON AIR, a 20 tracks strong compilation themed after his monthly radio show. A journey through the facets of electronic music with brand new trance tracks, exclusive GO edits and first class dance floor tunes. In February 2011 Giuseppe launched his global radio show GO ON AIR, a monthly format dedicated to the music he loves. The broad perspective of sounds also reflects in his new master piece compilation, featuring music by Armin van Buuren, M.I.K.E., Aly & Fila, Tom Colontonio, Paul Webster, Who.Is, Eddie Bitar and of course Giuseppe Ottaviani, himself.','','','','http://gigs.gigatools.com/country/India?page=2',NULL,1,'2012-09-27 14:40:59','2012-10-07 16:39:05',39,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-12-24 02:40:00','2012-12-24 02:40:00','dj-giuseppe-at-hilltop',1,NULL),(690,'Ash Roy at D.U.S.K','Ash Roy is one of the founding members of India\'s most prolific dance music act, Jalebee Cartel. Since its inception, Roy has been providing all vocal and percussive elements during their memorable live performances and has also steadily been creating music to add to the Cartel\'s cache of original productions. His career has long crossed the decade mark during which Roy\'s traveled across the continents touring with the band and solo, pre-Jalebee Cartel. They\'ve been basing themselves out of Europe every summer, to have equal footing in both sides of the globe. While Jalebee Cartel has shared headliner space with the likes of The Prodigy, Modeselektor and Carl Cox, he\'s also played with Sasha, Cari Lekebusch, Fergie and KaseyTaylor individually. It just keeps getting better and better for Ash Roy, and that\'s what reflects in his music.','','','','http://gigs.gigatools.com/country/India?page=2',NULL,1,'2012-09-27 14:49:23','2012-10-07 16:39:15',40,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-12-16 02:50:00','2012-12-16 02:50:00','ash-roy-at-dusk',1,NULL),(691,'Tuhin Mehta at Geoffrey\'s','INVASION! This Saturday 29th September at Geoffery\'s, Royal orchid\r\n\r\nCrazy LED Live Visuals, Banging sound, 6 artists, 3 genres of music. Here is how it looks:\r\n\r\nArtist Line up:\r\nBrute Force aka Tuhin Mehta and his (Techno Madness)\r\nDJ Marc (Techno and Proggy)\r\nDJ Arjun Nair and DJ Stallion (House)\r\nSam Abraham\r\nDJ Suvro\r\n\r\nLive Visuals by VJ Harish on the Huge LED Screen. Now, where have we planned on fitting this? I guess you\'ll have to come and find out!\r\n\r\nLoads of Surprises. Loads of New tracks. We are aiming to deliver the BEST Audio Visual experience.\r\n\r\nWhoever said you cant buy happiness has never really bought a drink and stood in the front of a banging sound system\r\n\r\n\r\nFor guestlist RSVP: \r\nChethan: 98860 98992\r\nArjun: 8123218044\r\nNishanth: 9945432326\r\n\r\n- Strictly couples & single girls only\r\n- Guest List shuts at 9:30 PM sharp\r\n- 21+ ONLY\r\n- Dress Code: Please wear clothes\r\n- Club rules apply\r\n- Right to admission reserved','','https://www.facebook.com/events/291909584255452/','','https://www.facebook.com/events/291909584255452/',NULL,NULL,'2012-09-27 15:05:19','2012-09-27 15:05:19',0,'[\"\"]','[\"For guestlist RSVP: \\r\",\"Chethan: 98860 98992\\r\",\"Arjun: 8123218044\\r\",\"Nishanth: 9945432326\"]','','2012-09-29 19:00:00','2012-09-29 23:30:00','tuhin-mehta-at-geoffreys',1,NULL),(692,'Oktoberfest at The Lalit','Experience Germanys most popular and one of the worlds most famous food and beverage festival, ri