h being quite new to the scene, his productions and remixes would make you believe hes been doing it for years. ','','http://www.facebook.com/events/467200196644945/','','http://www.facebook.com/events/467200196644945/',NULL,NULL,'2012-10-06 01:27:48','2012-10-07 16:52:58',56,'[\"http:\\/\\/www.zomato.com\\/events\\/ncr\\/steve-aoki-live-100020884\\r\",\"http:\\/\\/in.bookmyshow.com\\/events\\/Steve-Aoki-Live-at-Kitty-Su-A\\/ET00011136 \"]','[\"+91 9987603109\\/ 9987603127; 022-30673345\"]','','2012-10-07 22:00:00','2012-10-08 00:30:00','steve-aoki-at-the-lalitmumbai',1,NULL),(711,'MOVEMENT #1 (MUMBAI): SANDUNES EP LAUNCH, MONIKER, EZ RISER','Two of the most forward thinking and exciting institutions from Indias alternative electronic music scene are excited to announce the launch of Movement, a night dedicated to showcasing the most cutting edge sounds from India and across the world. An arena that will see house, techno, minimal, electronica, glitch and drum and bass take centre stage.\r\n\r\nLine up:\r\n\r\nSandunes  Temper Tonic EP Launch - Delhi debut\r\n2-step, future garage, post dubstep\r\n\r\nEZ Riser  Sohail Arora (Bay Beat Collective)  Solo Delhi debut\r\nelectronica, bass, glitch-hop\r\n\r\nMoniker  (Wild City DJ)  www.thewildcity.com\r\ngarage, alternative electronica, grime and techno\r\n\r\nWe kick off the first of a relentless series of parties in Mumbai with an EP launch for the mesmerising Sandunes. With the release packaged in robust housing sprinkled with the utmost artistic love, the EP is packed full of aural delights that send your brain flying into the heart of a black-hole. This is an incredible chance to catch one of the Mumbais most exciting performers live, for free. Live music backgrounds blended with quality dark studio-production hours alongside a heavy dose of UK underground electronica, Sandunes tunes bounce between 2-step, future garage, post dubstep and experimental electronica.\r\n\r\nIn a night seeing multiple dbuts, well also be welcoming EZ Riser to Delhi. The new solo project from Bay Beat Collective figurehead Sohail Arora, will see this DJ break new ground with a genre defying take on bass music with emphasis on glitch-hop.\r\n\r\nLast but not least Wild City head honcho, Moniker otherwise known as Wild City DJ, will provide some squeaky neck-breaking beat-haemorrhaging, hazy slo-mo lazer quest soundtracks taking you to a dimension that will cross the boundaries of forward-thinking electronic music.','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2545-movement-1-mumbai-sandunes-ep-launch-moniker-ez-riser','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2545-movement-1-mumbai-sandunes-ep-launch-moniker-ez-riser',NULL,NULL,'2012-10-06 01:37:43','2012-10-07 16:54:10',57,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-06 01:40:00','2012-10-06 01:40:00','movement-1-mumbai-sandunes-ep-launch-moniker-ez-riser',1,NULL),(712,'SOOM T & REGGAE RAJAHS at Arc Asia','Soom T is an Indian artist born and raised in Scotland creating songs within reggae, hip-hop, folk, electronic and dub genres with various experimentations centred around activist intent, spiritual enlightenment, soul evolution, unique sound wave generation and manipulation utiilising the voice, word power, rhythm and melody for inner cosmic tremor inducement.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nReggae Rajahs \r\nIndia\'s first reggae sound system. The trio composed of Diggy Dang, Mr. Herbalist and DJ MoCity (Iraq\'s first soundboy) are reggae entertainers and promoters based out of New Delhi. They operate in a traditional Jamaican sound system style with one DJ and two MC\'s.\r\n\r\nComing together for their love of reggae music in New Delhi in early 2009, the Rajahs have been introducing the Indian masses to an eclectic mix of roots reggae, dub, lovers rock, ska and dancehall. They frequently perform in New Delhi and have also played in Mumbai, Pune, Bangalore, Chennai, Goa and Manali. International performances in the last 2 years include Peru, Panama and New York City. They were recently nominated for the Best International Group award at the British Reggae Industry Awards (2012) alongside illustrious Jamaican artists such as Toots & the Maytals, Mighty Diamonds and Third World.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2594-soom-t-reggae-rajahs',NULL,NULL,'2012-10-06 01:46:58','2012-10-07 16:54:02',58,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-06 01:50:00','2012-10-06 01:50:00','soom-t-reggae-rajahs-at-arc-asia',1,NULL),(713,'THE GREAT INDIAN OCTOBERFEST: HYDERABAD','The annual great Indian Octoberfest will be held in two cities this year, featuring an eclectic bills of acts including bands such as Children Of Bodom, Gone In April, Example, Indian Ocean, Pandoras Box, The Raghu Dixit Project and Shaair+Func amongst others.\r\n\r\nIt will take place in Hyderabad from October 5-7 at N Convention, Kothaguda, Hyderabad\r\n\r\nThe full line up is below (in running order):\r\n\r\nDay 1\r\n\r\nDJ Preet\r\nOne Nite Stand\r\nPandor\'s Box\r\nShair & Funk\r\nIndian Ocean\r\nDJ Rahul\r\n\r\nDay 2\r\n\r\nOld Monk\r\nLagori\r\nAfflatus\r\nEka\r\nHari & Sukhamani\r\nDJ Chico\r\nYves V\r\n\r\nDay 3\r\n\r\nLive Banned\r\nAltered Egos\r\nAgam\r\nPopan & East India Co\r\nRaghu Dixit\r\nDJ Piyush\r\nLost Stories','http://www.kingfisherworld.com/tgiof/hyderabad/','','','http://www.kingfisherworld.com/tgiof/hyderabad/',NULL,NULL,'2012-10-06 02:02:18','2012-10-06 02:02:18',0,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-05 02:00:00','2012-10-07 02:00:00','the-great-indian-octoberfest-hyderabad',3,NULL),(714,'ROCKIT! FESTIVAL','Parikrama, Pentagram, menwhopause, Shkabang and Barefaced Liar are amoung a handful of acts that have been confirmed to play at Jaipurs Ravindra Manch Open Air Theatre on 6-7 October. Billed as 2 days, 8 bands, 14 hours of guitar drums and MAYHEM! this will be the cities first ever rock festival.\r\n\r\nOrganised by Jaipur based marketing and event management company Event Craft, the organisers are hoping to create an alternative to the established folk scene in the city by creating a platform to showcase rock music to younger audiences.\r\n\r\nThe full festival schedule can be seen below:\r\n\r\nSaturday 6 October\r\n4pm The Amity College band\r\n5pm Night Wings 3\r\n6pm Barefaced Liar\r\n7:30pm Shkabang\r\n8:30pm Parikrama\r\n\r\nSunday 7 October\r\n4pm Winter Gate\r\n5:30pm menwhopause\r\n7pm Bhayanak Maut\r\n8:30pm Pentagram','','http://www.facebook.com/rockitjaipur?sk=wall','','http://www.facebook.com/rockitjaipur?sk=wall',NULL,NULL,'2012-10-06 02:41:30','2012-10-07 16:53:54',62,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-06 02:40:00','2012-10-07 02:40:00','rockit-festival',3,NULL),(715,'SOOM T & REGGAE RAJAHS at Kamaki,Baga Beach','Soom T is an Indian artist born and raised in Scotland creating songs within reggae, hip-hop, folk, electronic and dub genres with various experimentations centred around activist intent, spiritual enlightenment, soul evolution, unique sound wave generation and manipulation utiilising the voice, word power, rhythm and melody for inner cosmic tremor inducement.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nReggae Rajahs \r\nIndia\'s first reggae sound system. The trio composed of Diggy Dang, Mr. Herbalist and DJ MoCity (Iraq\'s first soundboy) are reggae entertainers and promoters based out of New Delhi. They operate in a traditional Jamaican sound system style with one DJ and two MC\'s.\r\n\r\nComing together for their love of reggae music in New Delhi in early 2009, the Rajahs have been introducing the Indian masses to an eclectic mix of roots reggae, dub, lovers rock, ska and dancehall. They frequently perform in New Delhi and have also played in Mumbai, Pune, Bangalore, Chennai, Goa and Manali. International performances in the last 2 years include Peru, Panama and New York City. They were recently nominated for the Best International Group award at the British Reggae Industry Awards (2012) alongside illustrious Jamaican artists such as Toots & the Maytals, Mighty Diamonds and Third World.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2595-soom-t-reggae-rajahs',NULL,NULL,'2012-10-06 02:54:57','2012-10-07 16:53:13',68,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-07 02:55:00','2012-10-07 02:55:00','soom-t-reggae-rajahs-at-kamakibaga-beach',1,NULL),(716,'LE FREAK , C\'EST CHIC: M.MAT & FRIENDS','Head honcho behind the legendary Sundown Sessions at Aurus in Bombay, M.Mat (Bhavishyavani Future Soundz) is quickly gaining a reputation as on the most forward thinking DJ\'s in the country.\r\n\r\nWith influences ranging from Motown right through to Jeff Mills, Plastikman, Mancuso, Fela Kuti, Daft Punk, Villalobos, Brinkmann and more, he regularly smashes clubs across the country\'s capital of cool. Tonight him and his \"friends\" are bringing the party to New Delhi\'s Zoo bar. Oh and it\'s his birthday.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/1273-le-freak-cest-chic-mmat-friends',NULL,NULL,'2012-10-06 03:03:46','2012-10-07 16:52:50',69,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-10 03:05:00','2012-10-10 03:05:00','le-freak-cest-chic-mmat-friends',1,NULL),(717,'MID WEEK JAM # 4 FEAT. KONIAC NET & ALISHA PAIS','The Koniac Net (forged by songwriter David Abraham) spawns all the way from Bombay (India). His debut album \'One Last Monsoon\' was primarily recorded in his bedroom-an apt environment for an album which essentially sounds like a love letter to the indie/alternative genres. Influenced by bands like Swervedriver, Stills, French Kicks,Tokyo Police Club, the album is a mixed tape for the Indie music fan.\r\n\r\nTracks from \'One Last Monsoon\' have already gained airplay in the US, UK, France, Morocco, Australia, Italy, Germany, Belgium, Poland, Austria, Canada, Hungary, and Greece. After receiving numerous requests to tour internationally, in June of 2012, the Koniac Net transformed from a one-man-project to a 5-piece band.\r\nBandCamp\r\n\r\nSupport from: Alisha Pais','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2591-mid-week-jam-4-feat-koniac-net-alisha-pais',NULL,NULL,'2012-10-06 03:27:28','2012-10-07 16:52:44',70,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-10 03:30:00','2012-10-10 03:30:00','mid-week-jam-4-feat-koniac-net-alisha-pais',1,NULL),(718,'FLY!: LAURENT DE WILDE & OTISTO at Blue Frog','FLY! consists of Laurent De Wilde and Otisto. Laurent produces sounds on keyboards, strings, felt, wood, metal, anything that scratches, rubs and slaps. This provides material that Otisto then plays around with on his computer and throws back at Laurent thus building momentum and taking the music forward.\r\n\r\nThe music is very organic and their experience on stage and in the studio has resulted in a more intuitive sound embracing the piano and electronica. In the studio they have taken sound inspiration from anything ranging from herds of cows to the buzzing of flies. In fact they travelled with a colony of flies in order to see how the incessant vibrations of their wings affected their music. The homage to this is \"Water Fly No. 5\"\r\n\r\n\"FLY! invites us to listen to the earth and the air, to escape the mundane, to rise high in a rustle of wings and have an intimate conversation with the music.\"','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/fly-laurent-de-wilde-otisto-23-nico-ticot','','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/events/fly-laurent-de-wilde-otisto-23-nico-ticot',NULL,NULL,'2012-10-06 22:22:11','2012-10-07 16:51:42',71,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-10 10:20:00','2012-10-10 10:20:00','fly-laurent-de-wilde-otisto-at-blue-frog',1,NULL),(719,'FRAME/FRAME & DUB SHARMA at TLR','Frame/Frame and Dub Sharma will tonight come together at TLR Cafe for one last pre-party before the Delhi edition of Bacardi NH7 Weekender.\r\n\r\nInfo below:\r\n\r\nFrame/Frame\r\nFrame/Frame a.k.a Nikhil Kaul is a producer from New Delhi with a taste for an eclectic mix of electronica ranging from synth-driven tech to sample-laden post-dubstep and ambient electronica. It is this large palette of soundscapes and emotions that Frame/Frame attempts to showcase within his production and live shows. An exhilarating musician, Nikhil is also the producer and resident mix engineer for one of the countrys most exciting electronica acts, Switch Bitch. Whether these guys will ever come out of the studio is the million dollar question. You can hear an exclusive Wild City mix from both Switch Bitch and Frame/Frame here\r\nSoundcloud\r\n\r\nDub Sharma `\r\nDub Sharma produced Tung Tung (Feat. Nooran Sisters) and Ju Ju Leh (Feat. Tsering Stanzin) for MTV Sound Trippin. He has also done background scores for MTV Sound Trippins Leh Episode as well as for Anurag Kashyaps Gangs of Wasseypur which released in 2012. One of the country\'s most promising young producers.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2637-frameframe-dub-sharma',NULL,NULL,'2012-10-06 22:31:34','2012-10-07 16:51:34',72,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-10 10:35:00','2012-10-10 10:35:00','frameframe-dub-sharma-at-tlr',1,NULL),(720,'THE REVOLT: KINI RAO & TUHIN MEHTA at Blue Frog','\'Join The Revolt\' is a unique one off event that will feature some of the country\'s most up-and-coming musicians in support of Kranti.\r\n\r\nKranti is a small Mumbai based NGO whose name means revolution, and whose mission is to work with the daughters of sex workers; empowering them to be agents of social change.\r\n\r\nSocial justice minded corporations as well as Bollywood film stars are all joining \'The Revolt\' to end human trafficking, gender inequality, poverty and so much more by supporting Kranti\'s daughters of Mumbais red-light district.\r\n\r\nPlaying in support:\r\n\r\nKini Rao\r\nWith rhythm in her soul, funk in her attitude and the right records on the turntable - Kini has been steadily creating waves in the EDM scene in India. Her passion for deeper harmonies were showcased on a regular basis at Zenzi Mills (Bombay). Her other notable gigs include an after hours set at Bar25 (Berlin), Villian\'s Club & Oakroom (Copenhagen) & Public Life (London).\r\n\r\nDoing complete justice to her cheeky self, Kini\'s sound can best be described as an ambivalent mlange of distorted kicks, crispy hats, funky basslines and quirky melodies. Currently producing electronic music, while also actively promoting EDM through her M.U.S.E mix series, her new project Disco Dodo intends to purse her more eclectic interests.\r\n\r\nFor music with a touch of soul subtly blended with her own intrinsic personality, Kini, is well on her way in becoming a force to be reckoned with.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nDJ Tuhin Mehta \r\nBrute Force a.k.a Tuhin Mehta belongs to a old school breed of DJs. With two decades of experience pioneering club-world in India, hes a force to be reckoned with.\r\n\r\nA professionally qualified sound engineer from SAE in Chennai, along with being an international ambassador to the Berklee College of Music, Tuhin not only has immense experience from the various clubs that he has played in over the years, he also has a sharp understanding of the technical aspects behind sound production. His understanding of equipment is grade A and it speaks volumes that he was named a Pioneer Pro DJ for India in 2007. This combination of both prowess and technical ability only adds to his allure as a DJ who has a sharp understanding of the science of rocking a dance-floor.\r\n\r\nAs a producer, he is one half of the duo Brute Force, a collaboration that began many years ago with childhood friend, Shane Mendonsa.\r\n\r\nTime: 10.30pm\r\nEntry: Rs 300','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2599-the-revolt-kini-rao-tuhin-mehta',NULL,1,'2012-10-06 22:45:02','2012-10-07 16:51:28',74,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-11 22:30:00','2012-10-12 01:00:00','the-revolt-kini-rao-tuhin-mehta-at-blue-frog',1,NULL),(721,'BAY BEAT COLLECTIVE (BBC) DEBUT EP LAUNCH at TLR','The Mumbai-based BBC (Bay Beat Collective) formed in response to the abundance of standard-issue electronica so commonly heard in clubs and bars across the country. A DJ collective currently consisting of Kris Correya (ex resident DJ of Zenzi, Mumbai\'s most reputed club for experimental / underground music) and Sohail Arora (DnB promoter & founder - KRUNK, the alternative booking agency), the BBC\'s passion lies in drum & bass, breaks, dubstep, glitch, funk and minimal sounds.\r\n\r\n\'The BBC are changing trends and inspiring newer players in India with regular packed alternative beat nights all over the country. Truly one of the most inspirational emerging collectives of a much required alternative, intellectual order.\'','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2457-bay-beat-collective-bbc-debut-ep-launch',NULL,1,'2012-10-06 22:59:33','2012-10-07 16:51:11',77,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-12 11:00:00','2012-10-12 11:00:00','bay-beat-collective-bbc-debut-ep-launch-at-tlr',1,NULL),(722,'DJ URI FEAT. RHYS & DELHI SULTANATE WITH MISS SAMARA C at Ice Bar','Delhi Sultanate (BASSFoundation and Ska Vengers) tonight will most likely be playing a strictly vinyl set consisting of dubplates, 90\'s dancehall and dub. Supporting him on vocal duties will be fellow Ska Vengers front lady Miss Samara C. A duo to be truly reckoned with.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nDJ Uri\r\nWith a career spanning over 3 decades, DJ Uri has been true to the hip-hop movement. Born in East London in 1974, his journey has been in full flow since 1982. Influenced by the Street Sounds Compilations and the break dance era, Uri has had a solid upbringing being exposed to underground music from an early age.\r\n\r\nGetting his first turntables aged 13 he began to DJ for hip-hop crew The Uptown Posse. By the age of 15 Uri was performing to large crowds across the UK playing hip-hop, disco, funk and soul. The depth of his collection and knowledge he has gained over the years are a credit to hip-hop culture. He lives and breathes the real essence of the old skool DJ and his pledge to only play on vinyl decks stays loyal to the art of turntablism.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2459-dj-uri-feat-rhys-delhi-sultanate-with-miss-samara-c',NULL,1,'2012-10-06 23:28:04','2012-10-07 16:51:02',78,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-12 11:30:00','2012-10-12 11:30:00','dj-uri-feat-rhys-delhi-sultanate-with-miss-samara-c-at-ice-bar',1,NULL),(723,'MICROPHON3 at High Spirits','Microphon3 is one of the front runners of the Indian/Desi hip-hop scene. Tanmay Bahulekar (front man/vocals) has been a poet for the past decade and a half. On the decks is Johnny B, who shook the Indian hip-hop scene back in the day, as the front man of \"Method\". Ex PDV/Scribe/Chaos Theory drummer, Niraj Trivedi switches the beat and the funk as he picks up the mallets again. Completing this four piece is bassist Romit Ranjan (Ex Them Clones).\r\n\r\nRaw and aggressive hip-hop.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2565-microphon3',NULL,1,'2012-10-06 23:43:47','2012-10-07 16:50:55',81,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-12 11:45:00','2012-10-12 11:45:00','microphon3-at-high-spirits',1,NULL),(724,'DISCO 31: SU-REAL at TLR','Over 3 years, Disco 31 has crystallised its reputation as the Saturday night destination for the citys most adventurous partygoers. Disco 31 co-founder and host DJ Su-Real has exposed New Delhi to countless new nano genres from around the world meanwhile educating the rave heads on the history of dance music with themed retro nights.\r\n\r\nDisco 31 guests have included the finest underground DJs who are truly pushing the known limits of club culture in India. \"At the core of Disco 31 is the belief that a civilisation is only as vibrant as its nightlife, so come forth all ye creatures of the night in thy brightest regalia!\"','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2585-disco-31-sureal',NULL,1,'2012-10-07 01:32:58','2012-10-07 16:50:34',83,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-13 01:35:00','2012-10-13 01:35:00','disco-31-su-real-at-tlr',1,NULL),(725,'Ashvin Mani Sharma @ Quantum','Ashvin Mani Sharma has been a part of the Indian underground music scene since 1995. He has been producing music and DJ\'ing since 1998 and is one of the co-founders of Jalebee Cartel, now an international techno powerhouse.\r\n\r\nMade up of four members, Arjun Vagale (laptop, mixing, electronics), Ash Roy (vocals and percussions), Ashvin Mani Sharma (laptop and synths) and G-force Arjun (bass guitar), Jalebee has been taking India - and the world - by storm for over five years. From individual DJ sets to live gigs, producing to composing, there seems to be nothing that can get in their way.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/381-ashvin-mani-sharma',NULL,1,'2012-10-07 01:43:10','2012-10-07 16:50:13',84,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-15 01:45:00','2012-10-15 01:45:00','ashvin-mani-sharma-quantum-1',1,NULL),(726,'PRAGNYA WAKHLU & SUPPORT at TLR','Pragnya Wakhlu is a an award winning singer-songwriter and guitarist from India. Her songs are about inner reflection, thoughts, feelings and issues she feels strongly about.\r\n\r\nHer solo act is unique as she makes use of live looping and uses her guitar as a percussive instrument. Pragnya was nominated for the Bite my Music Global Music awards as the only Indian in the Best Female Vocalist Category. She also bagged 3rd place at the Indiego Music Awards (South East Asia 2011) for Best Female Vocalist and is a two time nominee for Best Female Vocalist at the Jack Daniels Rock Awards (2010/2011).\r\n\r\nTonight, she\'ll be joined by talented, young Congolese singer-songwriter Jehu Mulobo. Once the guitarist for the amazing Congolese afro-funk outfit Rio de Djika, Jehu has since ventured solo, making quite the name for him self winning over crowds at intimate gatherings across the country.','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2584-pragnya-wakhlu-support',NULL,1,'2012-10-07 01:56:04','2012-10-07 16:49:59',85,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-18 01:55:00','2012-10-18 01:55:00','pragnya-wakhlu-support-at-tlr',1,NULL),(727,'KRUNK LIVE: BAY BEAT COLLECTIVE (BBC) at Blue Frog','The Mumbai-based BBC (Bay Beat Collective) formed in response to the abundance of standard-issue electronica so commonly heard in clubs and bars across the country. A DJ collective currently consisting of Kris Correya (ex resident DJ of Zenzi, Mumbai\'s most reputed club for experimental / underground music) and Sohail Arora (DnB promoter & founder - KRUNK, the alternative booking agency), the BBC\'s passion lies in drum & bass, breaks, dubstep, glitch, funk and minimal sounds.\r\n\r\n\'The BBC are changing trends and inspiring newer players in India with regular packed alternative beat nights all over the country. Truly one of the most inspirational emerging collectives of a much required alternative, intellectual order.\'','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2460-krunk-live-bay-beat-collective-bbc',NULL,1,'2012-10-07 01:58:55','2012-10-07 16:49:45',86,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-19 10:00:00','2012-10-20 01:00:00','krunk-live-bay-beat-collective-bbc-at-blue-frog',1,NULL),(728,'CARBON BASED LIFEFORMS, VAEYA & KALYUG at Blue Frog','Carbon Based Lifeforms (CBL) are Johannes Hedberg and Daniel Segerstad (n Ringstrm), both born in 1976 and based in Gteborg, south-west Sweden. They met at the tender age of 15 and are still to this day working happily together, almost 20 years later. CBL itself was formed in 1996, as an offshoot from other projects, but soon became their focal point, culminating in their first release on mp3.com in 1998.\r\n\r\nIt is hard to categorise CBLs music but the best description might be that of a groundbreaking mixture of acid, techno and house music. Signed to celebrated Lyon-based label, Ultimae, they have released two full-length albums (Hydroponic Garden/2003, World of Sleepers/2006) to date.\r\n\r\n+\r\n\r\nKalyug\r\nKalyug is Nikhel Kumar Mahajan\'s progressive avatar. Kalyug is the fourth and final era in the spiritual evolution of man according to Hindu mythology. Kalyug has rocked dancefloors all over India and at International festivals performing along side acts such as Atmos, Vibrasphere, Skazi, Infected Mushroom and more.\r\n\r\nSupport from: Vaeya\r\n\r\nTime: 10.30pm\r\nEntry: Rs 500','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2600-carbon-based-lifeforms-vaeya-kalyug',NULL,1,'2012-10-07 03:08:08','2012-10-07 16:49:12',87,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-19 22:00:00','2012-10-20 01:00:00','carbon-based-lifeforms-vaeya-kalyug-at-blue-frog',1,NULL),(729,'DISCO 31: SU-REAL & WHITE RABBIT at TLR','Over 3 years, Disco 31 has crystallised its reputation as the Saturday night destination for the citys most adventurous partygoers. Disco 31 co-founder and host DJ Su-Real has exposed New Delhi to countless new nano-genres from around the world meanwhile educating the rave heads on the history of dance music with themed retro nights. Disco 31 guests have included the finest underground DJs who are truly pushing the known limits of club culture in India.\r\n\r\nOn this night, Su-Real will be joined by White Rabbit, the nom-de-guerre of Flipsides Robbie Bergo who has of late been dabbling in the sub-genres of dubstep and drum and bass. \"At the core of Disco 31 is the belief that a civilisation is only as vibrant as its nightlife, so come forth all ye creatures of the night in thy brightest regalia!\"','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/2586-disco-31-sureal-white-rabbit',NULL,1,'2012-10-07 03:14:52','2012-10-07 16:44:48',88,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-20 03:15:00','2012-10-20 03:15:00','disco-31-su-real-white-rabbit-at-tlr',1,NULL),(730,'RAJASTHAN ROOTS at Blue Frog','\"By dissolving all boundaries, a musician is allowed the freedom to experiment and create music.\"\r\n\r\nRajasthan Roots are a collective that promote the performing arts of Rajasthan by bringing folk to a multicultural platform and creating new folk blues/funk and electronica which appeals to various musical tastes and age groups.\r\n\r\nAll the compositions are reflective of Rajasthan folk, incorporating traditional instruments such as the Dautara, Morchang, Khurtal, Bhapang, Flute, Khamaicha, and Algoza. Rajasthan Roots provides folk musicians a platform for creativity and expression.\r\n\r\nTimes: 9pm\r\nEntry: Rs 300','','','','http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/events.xhtml/event/494-rajasthan-roots',NULL,1,'2012-10-07 03:26:30','2012-10-07 16:43:55',89,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-21 21:00:00','2012-10-21 23:30:00','rajasthan-roots-at-blue-frog',1,NULL),(731,'AREA 79 MUSIC at Blue Frog','Area 79 is back as promised this autumn, but under a slightly different guise. Team Audio Aashram will be taking over blueFROG for 12 hours of music, arts and culture. With over 30 artists performing throughout the day with music ranging from classical, jazz, reggae, roots, rock \'n\' roll, drum and bass, funk, ska, dubstep without forgetting the progressive techno and psy trance.\r\n\r\nThere will also be a good dose of dancers, performance arts, installations, fire jugglers, workshops, massages, a flea market and food stalls in this 12 hour take over.\r\n\r\nLine up so far:\r\n\r\nElectronic Stage (club)\r\nArjuna - Parvati Records - Italy\r\nGojja - Sanaton Records - Sweden\r\nCrash n Boom - India\r\n\r\nLive Stage (courtyard)\r\nSka Vengers - dub edition\r\nSyncopation - jazz\r\nSattyananda - electro classical\r\n\r\nAlternative Stage (terrace)\r\nCarbon Based Lifeforms - Ultimate Records - Sweden\r\nShantam - Audio Aashram\r\nKohra - Qilla Records\r\nDiggy Dang - reggae','','http://www.facebook.com/events/196487063817821/','','http://www.facebook.com/events/196487063817821/',NULL,1,'2012-10-07 03:44:42','2012-10-07 16:44:36',90,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-20 14:00:00','2012-10-20 23:30:00','area-79-music-at-blue-frog',3,NULL),(732,'BASS CAMP FESTIVAL: DUB PHIZIX, BASSFOUNDATION, JAZZSTEPPA & MORE at BLUE FROG','It\'s that time of year again.\r\n\r\nOctober\'s edition of BASS CAMP is a 3-city festival to be held from Oct 26-28 in Mumbai, New Delhi and Bangalore (TBC). An ongoing monthly series, it will exclusively host international headliners all representing genres such as drum and bass, dubstep and glitch.\r\n\r\nIt comes as no surprise then that their first headliner choice kick starting the series is Manchester based drum and bass producer Dub Phizix. A producer that over the last year has dominated the drum and bass scene from the very moment the world first viewed the promo video to his December 2011 release \'Marka\' (video below). Penned by Dub Phizix alongside regular collaborator Skeptical with guest vocals from Strategy, \'Marka\' adhered to no known recent stylistic formulas. Easily the drum and bass track of 2011, \'Marka\' married staccato dancehall like rhythms with slamming bass hits and Strategys unintelligible but potent rhymes.\r\n\r\nWith a back-catalogue now spanning over 10 years, Dub Phizix has released music on high profile and respected labels such as Exit, Commercial Suicide, Soul:R, Critical, Dispatch and Ingredients with Mixmag calling his music \'Essential material\'. Although he may be a fresh face to many, Dub Phizix\' DJ sets always display his depth of knowledge of what makes a great drum and bass track, mixing up often neglected classics with the freshest upfront material.\r\n\r\nOver the coming months Dub Phizix has much anticipated releases on Exit Records, Creative Source, Commercial Suicide, Innerground, Samurai Music and many more. 2011 may be the year that the world truly discovered Dub Phizix, but 2012 is set to be the year he reaches his full potential blazing a trail of innovation across the history of drum and bass music.\r\n\r\nThe full line up and dates for Octobers edition of BASS CAMP Festival can be seen below:\r\n\r\n26 October / blueFROG Mumbai\r\n\r\nDub Phizix\r\nBASSFoundation // Big Daddy Klein & Delhi Sultanate\r\nJazzsteppa (DJ)\r\nOx7gen\r\n\r\n27 October / blueFROG New Delhi\r\n\r\nDub Phizix\r\nBASSFoundation // Big Daddy Klein & Delhi Sultanate\r\nJazzsteppa (DJ)\r\nTarqeeb\r\nMr. Herbalist\r\nSwaggamuffin','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/calendar-delhi','http://www.facebook.com/events/537017326315567/','','http://www.bluefrog.co.in/calendar-delhi',NULL,1,'2012-10-07 04:07:44','2012-10-08 02:50:58',91,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-10-26 04:05:00','2012-10-27 04:05:00','bass-camp-festival-dub-phizix-bassfoundation-jazzsteppa-more-at-blue-frog',3,NULL),(733,'SEAN PAUL India Tour at HUDA GROUNDS','Sean Paul, the Jamaican star whose 2003 Dutty Rock album brought dancehall to the charts, will be playing shows in India this November. Always \"in the club\", the singer-songwriter and producers increasing demand and multi-faceted talent has made him a pioneer of commercial dancehall, reggae and R&B over the last decade.\r\n\r\nFans should expect to hear platinum smash hits such as Get Busy, Gimme The Light, I\'m Still in Love With You, Like Glue, We Be Burnin, Ever Blazin, Give It Up To Me, Baby Boy, Never Gonna Be The Same and well, you get the idea.\r\n\r\nThe Indian tour is being curated and produced exclusively by Blue Note Entertainment, a company that according to their press release specialises in big ticket film promotions, exhaustive artist management, prolific corporate events and destination weddings; foraying into the concert space for the very first time.\r\n\r\nWe are strategising on a concept based on Diwali and interestingly our stage set-up and dcor will comprise of mirrors, lights and crystals, something that hasnt yet been explored before in India. We will also be using international dancers on stage, adding a global touch and making it look like one big party as seen internationally at most concerts. We can assure you that his concerts will be mind-blowing and electric. We promise to give all his fans in India a night to remember. - Mr. Fardeen Shirazi, Creative Head, Blue Note Entertainment\r\n\r\nIts your boy Sean and you heard it straight from me - India get ready for my live show. The wait is finally over and now for the first time ever, Im excited to bring my live show to India. I cant wait for my fans to join me where Ill be performing all of your favorites and some new songs from my latest album. Watch this space for more to know where all Im performing - Sean Paul\r\n\r\nTicket Details:\r\n\r\n2 November - HUDA Grounds, Gurgaon; Tickets: Silver: Rs 1950/-, Gold: Rs 2950/-, VIP: Rs 5950/-','','http://www.facebook.com/events/427228220669063/','','http://www.facebook.com/events/427228220669063/',NULL,1,'2012-10-07 04:30:04','2012-10-07 16:43:01',93,'[\"\"]','[\"\"]','','2012-11-02 04:30:00','2012-11-02 04:30:00','sean-paul-india-tour-at-huda-grounds',5,NULL),(734,'SEAN PAUL India Tour at Andheri Sports Complex','Sean Paul, the Jamaican star whose 2003 Dutty Rock album brought dancehall to the charts, will be playing shows in India this November. Always \"in the club\", the singer-songwriter and producers increasing demand and multi-faceted talent has made him a pioneer of commercial dancehall, reggae and R&B over the last decade.\r\n\r\nFans should expect to hear platinum smash hits such as Get Busy, Gimme The Light, I\'m Still in Love With You, Like Glue, We Be Burnin, Ever Blazin, Give It Up To Me, Baby Boy, Never Gonna Be The Same and well, you get the idea.\r\n\r\nThe Indian tour is being curated and produced exclusively by Blue Note Entertainment, a company that according to their press release specialises in big ticket film promotions, exhaustive artist management, prolific corporate events and destination weddings; foraying into the concert space for the very first time.\r\n\r\nWe are strategising on a concept based on Diwali and interestingly our stage set-up and dcor will comprise of mirrors, lights and crystals, something that hasnt yet been explored before in India. We will also be using international dancers on stage, adding a global touch and making it look like one big party as se